definition: A  homoisoflavonoid that is 3,4-dihydro-2H-1-benzopyran substituted by hydroxy groups at positions 3, 4 and 7 and a (4-hydroxyphenyl)methyl group at position 3 respectively (the 3R,4R-stereoisomer). It has been isolated from Caesalpinia sappan.

name: fatsicarpain C
definition: A pentacyclic triterpenoid that is oleana-11,13(18)-diene substituted by a alpha-hydroxy group at position 3, an oxo group at position 23 and a carboxy group at position 28. Isolated from the leaves and twigs of Fatsia polycarpa, it exhibits anti-HBV activity.

name: fatsicarpain D
definition: A pentacyclic triterpenoid that is oleana-9(11),12-diene substituted by an alpha-hydroxy group at position 3 and a carboxy group at position 28. Isolated from the leaves and twigs of Fatsia polycarpa, it exhibits anti-HBV activity.

name: fatsicarpain G
definition: A terpene lactone that is 13,28-epoxyolean-11-en-28-one substituted by hydroxy groups at positions 3 and 23. Isolated from the leaves and twigs of Fatsia polycarpa, it exhibits anti-HBV activity.

name: caerulomycin F
definition: A  pyridine alkaloid that is 2,2'-bipyridine substituted at position 6 by a hydroxymethyl group and at position 4 by a methoxy group. Isolated from the marine-derived actinomycete Actinoalloteichus cyanogriseus, it exhibits antineoplastic activity.

name: caerulomycin I
definition: A pyridine alkaloid that is 2,2'-bipyridine-6-carboxamide substituted by methoxy groups at position 4 and carbamoyl nitrogen respectively. Isolated from the marine-derived actinomycete Actinoalloteichus cyanogriseus, it exhibits antineoplastic activity.

name: caerulomycin A
definition: A pyridine alkaloid that is 2,2'-bipyridine substituted by a methoxy group at position 4 and a (E)-(hydroxyimino)methyl group at position 6. Isolated from the marine-derived actinomycete Actinoalloteichus cyanogriseus, it exhibits antineoplastic activity.

name: (Z)-4-methoxy-2,2-bipyridine-6-carbaldehyde oxime
definition: A pyridine alkaloid that is 2,2'-bipyridine substituted by a methoxy group at position 4 and a (Z)-(hydroxyimino)methyl group at position 6. It has been isolated from the marine-derived actinomycete Actinoalloteichus cyanogriseus.

name: 2-(2,4-dihydroxyphenyl)-5-(E)-propenylbenzofuran
definition: A member of the class of benzofurans that is 1-benzofuran substituted by a 2,4-dihydroxyphenyl group at position 2 and a prop-1-en-1-yl group at position 5. It is a lignan derivative isolated from the roots of Krameria lappacea.

name: 2-(4-hydroxyphenyl)-5-(E)-propenylbenzofuran
definition: A member of the class of benzofurans that is 1-benzofuran substituted by a 4-hydroxyphenyl group at position 2 and a prop-1-en-1-yl group at position 5. It is a lignan derivative isolated from the roots of Krameria lappacea.

name: nigerapyrone D
definition: A member of the class of 2-pyranones that is 2H-pyran-2-one substituted by a methoxy group at position 4, a methyl group at position 3 and a 3-methyl-5-oxohexa-1,3-dien-1-yl group at position 6. It has been isolated from an endophytic fungus Aspergillus niger.

name: cinnamtannin D-1
definition: A proanthocyanidin found in Cinnamomum cassia.

name: (1R,5R,6S,7S,8S,10R,11S)-6-hydroxy-4-oxopseudoguai-2(3)-en-12,8-olide
definition: A pseudoguaianolide with anti-inflammatory activity isolated from the aerial parts of Inula hupehensis.

name: (1S,2R,5R,6S,7S,8S,10R)-6-hydroxy-2-methoxy-4-oxopseudoguai-11(13)-en-12,8-olide
definition: A pseudoguaianolide with anti-inflammatory activity isolated from the aerial parts of Inula hupehensis.

name: 6alpha-acetoxyisoinuviscolide
definition: A sesquiterpene lactone that is 3a,4,4a,5,6,7,7a,9a-octahydroazuleno[6,5-b]furan-2(3H)-one substituted by a hydroxy group at position 5, methyl groups at positions 5 and 8, a methylidene group at position 3 and an acetoxy group at position 4. It has been isolated from the aerial parts of Inula hupehensis.

name: 8-epiinuviscolide
definition: A sesquiterpene lactone that is the C-8 epimer of inuviscolide. It has been isolated from the aerial parts of Inula hupehensis.

name: 4-epiisoinuviscolide
definition: A sesquiterpene lactone that is 3a,4,4a,5,6,7,7a,9a-octahydroazuleno[6,5-b]furan-2(3H)-one substituted by a hydroxy group at position 5, methyl groups at positions 5 and 8 and a methylidene group at position 3 (the 3aR,4aR,5S,7aR,9aS stereoisomer). It has been isolated from the aerial parts of Inula hupehensis.

name: inuchinenolide B
definition: A sesquiterpene lactone that is 3a,4,4a,5,6,7,9,9a-octahydroazuleno[6,5-b]furan-2(3H)-one substituted by a hydroxy group at position 5, methyl groups at positions 5 and 8, an acetyloxy group at position 7 and a methylidene group at position 3. It has been isolated from the aerial parts of Inula hupehensis.

name: mitchellene C
definition: A sesquiterpene lactone isolated from the leaves of Eremophila mitchellii.

name: mitchellene E
definition: A sesquiterpenoid isolated from the leaves of Eremophila mitchellii.

name: casticin
definition: A tetramethoxyflavone that consists of quercetagetin in which the hydroxy groups at positions 3, 6, 7 and 4' have been replaced by methoxy groups. It has been isolated from Eremophila mitchellii.

name: 3-O-[2,3-di-O-acetyl-alpha-L-arabinopyranosyl]-hederagenin 28-O-alpha-L-rhamnopyranosyl-(1->4)-beta-D-glucopyranosyl-(1->6)-beta-D-glucopyranoside
definition: A triterpenoid saponin with hederagenin as the sapogenin. It has been isolated from the stem bark of Kalopanax pictus.

name: 3beta,6beta,23-trihydroxyolean-12-en-28-oic acid
definition: A pentacyclic triterpenoid that is oleanolic acid substituted by additional hydroxy groups at positions 6 and 23. It has been isolated from Kalopanax pictus.

name: kalopanaxsaponin C
definition: A triterpenoid saponin with hederagenin as the aglycone part. It has been isolated from the stem bark of Kalopanax pictus.

name: cauloside D
definition: A triterpenoid saponin with hederagenin as the aglycone part. It has been isolated from the stem bark of Kalopanax pictus.

name: nygerone A
definition: A member of the class of 4-pyridones that is nigerone B in which the nitrogen of the carboxamide has been acylated by a (3S)-3-carboxybutanoyl group. It has been isolated from  Aspergillus niger ATCC 1015.

name: nygerone B
definition: A member of the class of 4-pyridones that is N-phenylpyridin-4-one which is substituted by a benzyl group at position 2 and an aminocarbonyl group at position 5. It has been isolated from Aspergillus niger ATCC 1015.

name: cordysinin C
definition: A member of the class of beta-carbolines that is beta-carboline substituted by a 1-hydroxyethyl group at position 1 (the R enantiomer). It has been isolated from the mycelia of Cordyceps sinensis.

name: cordysinin D
definition: A member of the class of beta-carbolines that is beta-carboline substituted by a 1-hydroxyethyl group at position 1 (the S enantiomer). It has been isolated from the mycelia of Cordyceps sinensis.

name: diplotasin
definition: A hydroxyhomoflavonoid that is isochromeno[4,3-b]chromen-7(5H)-one substituted by a hydroxy group at position 4 and methoxy groups at positions 3, 10 and 11. It has been isolated from Mimosa diplotricha.

name: quercetin-3-O-beta-D-xylopyranoside
definition: A quercetin O-glycoside that is quercetin attached to a beta-D-xylopyranosyl residue at position 3 via a glycosidic linkage. It has been isolated from Mimosa diplotricha.

name: TAN-931
definition: A member of the class of benzoic acids that is benzoic acid substituted by a formyl group at position 3, a hydroxy group at position 5 and a 2,6-dihydroxybenzoyl group at position 4. Isolated from Penicillium purpurogenum, it exhibits antiviral activity.

name: cannabigerol
definition: A member of the class of resorcinols that is resorcinol which is substituted by a (2E)-3,7-dimethylocta-2,6-dien-1-yl group at position 2 and by a pentyl group at position 5. It is a natural product found in Cannabis sativa and Helichrysum species.

name: 19,28-didehydroxyrubiarbonol A
definition: A pentacyclic triterpenoid of the class of arborinane-type terpenoids isolated from the roots of Rubia yunnanensis.

name: rubiyunnanol C
definition: A pentacyclic triterpenoid of the class of arborinane-type terpenoids isolated from the roots of Rubia yunnanensis.

name: 2-hydroxyrubiarbonone E
definition: A pentacyclic triterpenoid of the class of arborinane-type terpenoids isolated from the roots of Rubia yunnanensis.

name: rubiarboside G 28-acetate
definition: A triterpenoid saponin with an arborinane-type terpenoid as the aglycone. It has been isolated from the roots of Rubia yunnanensis.

name: rubiarboside G 28-al
definition: A triterpenoid saponin with an arborinane-type terpenoid as the aglycone. It has been isolated from the roots of Rubia yunnanensis.

name: 1,3,6-trihydroxy-2-hydroxymethyl-9,10-anthraquinone-3-O-(6'-O-acetyl)-beta-D-glucopyranoside
definition: A dihydroxyanthraquinone that is 9,10-anthraquinone substituted by hydroxy groups at positions 4 and 7, a hydroxymethyl group at position 3 and a 6-O-acetyl-beta-D-glucopyranosyloxy residue at position 2. It has been isolated from the roots of Rubia yunnanensis.

name: rubiarbonol K
definition: A pentacyclic triterpenoid of the class of arborinane-type terpenoids isolated from the roots of Rubia yunnanensis.

name: rubiarbonol L
definition: A pentacyclic triterpenoid of the class of arborinane-type terpenoids isolated from the roots of Rubia yunnanensis.

name: 1,3,6-trihydroxy-2-methyl-9,10-anthraquinone
definition: A trihydroxyanthraquinone that is 9,10-anthraquinone substituted by hydroxy groups at positions 1, 3 and 6 and a methyl group at position 2. It has been isolated from the roots of Rubia yunnanensis.

name: rubiarbonol F
definition: A pentacyclic triterpenoid of the class of arborinane-type terpenoids isolated from the roots of Rubia yunnanensis.

name: rubiarbonone C
definition: A pentacyclic triterpenoid of the class of arborinane-type terpenoids isolated from the roots of Rubia yunnanensis.

name: spathodic acid
definition: A pentacyclic triterpenoid that is olean-12-en-28-oic acid substituted by hydroxy groups at positions 3, 19 and 24 (the 3beta,19alpha stereoisomer). It has been isolated from the roots of Rubia yunnanensis.

name: 1,6-dihydroxy-2-methyl-9,10-anthraquinone
definition: A member of the class of hydroxyanthraquinones that is anthracene-9,10-dione substituted by hydroxy groups at positions 1 and 6 and a methyl group at position 2. It has been isolated from the roots of Rubia yunnanensis.

name: 1,3,6-trihydroxy-2-methyl-9,10-anthraquinone-3-O-alpha-L-rhamnopyranosyl-(1->2)-beta-D-glucopyranoside
definition: A disaccharide derivative that is 1,3,6-trihydroxy-2-methyl-9,10-anthraquinone attached to a alpha-L-rhamnopyranosyl-(1->2)-beta-D-glucopyranosyl residue at position 3 via a glycosidic linkage. It has been isolated from the roots of Rubia yunnanensis.

name: 7-demethoxyegonol oleate
definition: A fatty acid ester that is egonol oleate in which the methoxy group at position 7 is replaced by a hydrogen. Isolated from the fruits of Styrax agrestis, it exhibits inhibitory activity against acetylcholinesterase.

name: 7-demethoxylegonol acetate
definition: An acetate ester of 7-demethoxylegonol that has been isolated from the fruits of Styrax agrestis.

name: egonolpropanoate
definition: A fatty acid ester obtained by the formal condensation of egonol with propionic acid. It has been isolated from the fruits of Styrax agrestis.

name: egonol acetate
definition: An acetate ester of egonol isolated from the fruits of Styrax agrestis.

name: 7-demethoxyegonol
definition: A member of the class of 1-benzofurans that is  egonol in which the methoxy group at position 7 is replaced by a hydrogen. It has been isolated from the fruits of Styrax agrestis.

name: lobophytumin B
definition: A diterpenoid that is cyclodeca-1,6-diene substituted by a methyl group at position 8, a methylidene group at position 4 and a 6-methyl-4-oxoheptan-2-yl group at position 1. It has been isolated from from the Hainan soft coral Lobophytum cristatum.

name: clethroidoside A
definition: A triterpenoid saponin that is primulagenin A attached to a beta-D-glucopyranosyl-(1->2)-[beta-D-glucopyranosyl-(1->4)]-alpha-L-arabinopyranosyl residue at position 3 via a glycosidic linkage. It has been isolated from the aerial parts of Lysimachia clethroides.

name: clethroidoside C
definition: A triterpenoid saponin that is (3beta)-3-hydroxy-13,28-epoxyoleanan-16-one attached to a tetrasaccharide residue at position 3 via a glycosidic linkage. Isolated from the aerial parts of Lysimachia clethroides, it exhibits antineoplastic activity.

name: clethroidoside G
definition: A triterpenoid saponin that is (3beta,16alpha)-3,16-dihydroxy-12-oxooleanan-28-al attached to a beta-D-glucopyranosyl-(1->2)-[beta-D-glucopyranosyl-(1->4)]-alpha-L-arabinopyranosyl residue at position 3 via a glycosidic linkage. It has been isolated from the aerial parts of Lysimachia clethroides.

name: clethroidoside H
definition: A triterpenoid saponin that is (2alpha,3beta,21beta)-ursa-9(11),12-diene-2,3,21,30-tetrol attached to beta-D-glucopyranosyl residues at positions 21 and 30 respectively via glycosidic linkages. It has been isolated from the aerial parts of Lysimachia clethroides.

name: ardisimamiloside E
definition: A triterpenoid saponin that is (3beta,16alpha)-13,28-epoxyoleanane-3,16,29-triol attached to a tetrasaccharide residue at position 3 via a glycosidic linkage. It has been isolated from the aerial parts of Lysimachia clethroides.

name: 7beta,15alpha-dihydroxy-22(29)-hopene
definition: A  hopanoid that is hop-22(29)-ene substituted by hydroxy groups at positions 7 and 15 respectively. It has been isolated from Hypocrella species.

name: 7beta,15alpha,22-trihydroxyhopane
definition: A  hopanoid that is hopane substituted by hydroxy groups at positions 7, 15 and 22 respectively (the 7beta,15alpha-stereoisomer). It has been isolated from Hypocrella species.

name: kaempferol-3-rutinoside
definition: A kaempferol O-glucoside that is  kaempferol attached to a rutinosyl [6-deoxy-alpha-L-mannosyl-(1->6)-beta-D-glucosyl] residue at position 3 via a glycosidic linkage. It has been isolated from the leaves of Solanum campaniforme.

name: griffithane B
definition: A dimethoxybenzene that is 2,6-dimethoxyphenol substituted by a 3-(4-hydroxy-3-methoxyphenyl)propyl group at position 3. It has been isolated from the stems of Combretum griffithii and has been shown to exhibit anticancer activity.

name: griffithane D
definition: A member of the class of 1,4-benzoquinones that is 1,4-benzoquinone which has been substituted by a methoxy group at position 5 and a 3-(4-hydroxy-3-methoxyphenyl)propyl group at position 2. It has been isolated from the stems of Combretum griffithii and has been shown to exhibit anticancer activity.

name: isowighteone
definition: A member of the class of 7-hydroxyisoflavones that is isoflavone substituted by hydroxy groups at positions 5, 7 and 4' and a prenyl group at position 3'. It has been isolated from Ficus mucuso.

name: ajugaciliatin C
definition: A diterpene lactone isolated from the whole plants of Ajuga ciliata.

name: ajugaciliatin H
definition: A diterpene lactone isolated from the whole plants of  Ajuga ciliata.

name: ajugaciliatin J
definition: A diterpene lactone isolated from the whole plant Ajuga ciliata.

name: ajugamarin H1
definition: A diterpene lactone isolated from the whole plants of Ajuga ciliata.

name: combretanone G
definition: A pentacyclic triterpenoid that is 9beta,19-cyclolanost-25-ene substituted by an oxo group at position 3, a hydroxy group at position 7 and a methoxy group at position 25. It has been isolated from the leaves of Combretum quadrangulare.

name: comazaphilone B
definition: An azaphilone that is 5,6,7,8-tetrahydro-1H-isochromene substituted by a hydroxy group at position 6, a methyl group at position 7, an oxo group at position 8, a propyl group at position 3 and a (3,4-dihydroxy-2-methoxy-6-methylbenzoyl)oxy group at position 7. It has been isolated from Penicillium commune.

name: comazaphilone D
definition: An azaphilone that is 5,6,7,8-tetrahydro-1H-isochromene substituted by a hydroxy and methyl group at position 7, an oxo group at position 8, a prop-1-en-1-yl group at position 3 and a (2,4-dihydroxy-6-methylbenzoyl)oxy group at position 6.Isolated from Penicillium commune, it exhibits antibacterial and antineoplastic activities.

name: comazaphilone F
definition: An azaphilone that is 5,6,7,8-tetrahydro-1H-isochromene substituted by a hydroxy group and a methyl group at position 7, an oxo group at position 8, a propyl group at position 3 and a (3,4-dihydroxy-2-methoxy-6-methylbenzoyl)oxy group at position 6. Isolated from Penicillium commune, it exhibits antibacterial and antineoplastic activities.

name: (S)-5,7-dihydroxy-2-(4-methoxyphenyl)-8-(3-methylbut-2-enyl)chroman-4-one
definition: A dihydroxyflavanone that is (2S)-flavanone substituted by hydroxy groups at positions 5 and 7, a methoxy group at position 4' and a prenyl group at position 8. It has been isolated from Macaranga bicolor.

name: sophoraflavanone A
definition: A trihydroxyflavanone that is (S)-naringenin substituted by a geranyl group at position 8. Isolated from Macaranga bicolor, it exhibits antibacterial and antineoplastic activities.

name: luteolin-7-O-alpha-L-rhamnoside
definition: A glycosyloxyflavone that is luteolin substituted by a alpha-L-rhamnosyl residue at position 7 via a glycosidic linkage. It has been isolated from Crotalaria lachnophora.

name: cornusalterin A
definition: A tirucallane triterpenoid that is (13alpha,14beta,17alpha,20S,23E)-lanosta-7,23-diene substituted by a beta-hydroxy group at position 3 and a methoxy group at position 25. It has been isolated from the stem and stem barks of Cornus walteri.

name: cornusalterin L
definition: A  tirucallane triterpenoid that is (13alpha,14beta,17alpha,20S,23S)-21,23-epoxylanosta-7,24-diene substituted by an oxo group at position 3. It has been isolated from the stem and stem barks of Cornus walteri.

name: smenospongines C
definition: A  sesquiterpenoid isolated from the marine sponge Dactylospongia elegans.

name: (+)-(S)-ar-turmerone
definition: A sesquiterpenoid that is 2-methylhept-2-en-4-one substituted by a 4-methylphenyl group at position 6. It has been isolated from Peltophorum dasyrachis.

name: eutypoid B
definition: A  butenolide that is furan-2(5H)-one substituted by a 4-hydroxybenzyl group at position 4 and a 4-hydroxyphenyl group at position 3. It has been isolated from Penicillium species.

name: eutypoid D
definition: A butenolide that is furan-2(5H)-one substituted by a 3,5-dihydroxyphenyl group at position 3 and a 4-hydroxybenzyl group at position 4. It has been isolated from Penicillium species.

name: aglaiabbreviatin C
definition: A tetracyclic triterpenoid isolated from the stems of Aglaia abbreviata.

name: ipomotaoside A
definition: A  resin glycoside that is the  tetrasaccharide derivative of jalapinolic acid. Isolated from Ipomoea batatas, it exhibits inhibitory activity against COX-1 and COX-2.

name: (+)-(1R)-1,12-dihydroxy-20-norabieta-5(10),8,11,13-tetraene
definition: A tricyclic diterpenoid isolated from the stem bark of Fraxinus sieboldiana.

name: 7-dehydroabietanone
definition: An  abietane diterpenoid that is abieta-8,11,13-triene substituted by an oxo group at position 7. It has been isolated from the stem bark of Fraxinus sieboldiana.

name: 7-hydroxy-5-methoxy-6,8-dimethylflavone
definition: A monohydroxyflavone that is flavone substituted by a hydroxy group at position 7, a methoxy group at position 5 and methyl groups at positions 6 and 8. Isolated from the buds of Cleistocalyx operculatus, it has been shown to exhibit inhibitory effects on the viral neuraminidases from two influenza viral strains, H1N1 and H9N2.

name: 2',4'-dihydroxy-3'-methyl-6'-methoxychalcone
definition: A member of the class of chalcones that is trans-chalcone substituted by a methyl group at position 3', hydroxy groups at positions 2' and 4' and a methoxy group at position 6'. Isolated from the buds of Cleistocalyx operculatus, it has been shown to exhibit inhibitory effects on the viral neuraminidases from two influenza viral strains, H1N1 and H9N2.

name: (2S)-7-hydroxy-5-methoxy-8-methylflavanone
definition: A  monohydroxyflavanone that is (2S)-flavanone substituted by a hydroxy group at position 7, a methoxy group at position 5 and a methyl group at position 8. It has been isolated from the buds of Cleistocalyx operculatus.

name: (2S)-5,7-dihydroxy-6,8-dimethylflavanone
definition: A dihydroxyflavanone that is (2S)-flavanone substituted by hydroxy groups at positions 5 and 7 and methyl groups at positions 6 and 8. Isolated from the buds of Cleistocalyx operculatus, it has been shown to exhibit inhibitory effects on the viral neuraminidases from two influenza viral strains, H1N1 and H9N2.

name: 1-(4-hydroxyphenyl)-7-phenyl-(6E)-hept-6-en-3-one
definition: A  diarylheptanoid that is hept-6-en-3-one substituted by a 4-hydroxyphenyl group at position 1 and a phenyl group at position 7 respectively. It has been isolated from the rhizomes of Curcuma kwangsiensis.

name: 1,7-bis(4-hydroxyphenyl)hepta-4E-6E-dien-3-one
definition: A  diarylheptanoid that is 4E-6E-dien-3-one substituted by 4-hydroxyphenyl group at positions 1 and 7. It has been isolated from the rhizomes of Curcuma kwangsiensis.

name: angucycline antibiotic
definition: Any angucycline that exhibits antibiotic activity.

name: dabigatran etexilate methanesulfonate
definition: A methanesulfonate salt obtained by reaction of dabigatran etexilate with one equivalent of dabigatran etexilate. A prodrug for dabigatran, a thrombin inhibitor and anticoagulant which is used for the prevention of stroke and systemic embolism.

name: dabigatran etexilate
definition: An aromatic amide obtained by formal condensation of the carboxy group of 2-{[(4-{N'-[(hexyloxy)carbonyl]carbamimidoyl}phenyl)amino]methyl}-1-methyl-1H-benzimidazole-5-carboxylic acid with the secondary amino group of ethyl N-pyridin-2-yl-beta-alaninate. A prodrug for dabigatran, a thrombin inhibitor and anticoagulant which is used for the prevention of stroke and systemic embolism.

name: PPAR modulator
definition: Any compound which acts on the peroxisome proliferator-activated receptor.

name: cob(II)yrinate c monoamide(5-)
definition: A precorrin carboxylic acid anion obtained by global deprotonation of the carboxy groups of cob(II)yrinic acid c monoamide.

name: CDP-4-dehydro-3,6-dideoxy-alpha-D-glucose
definition: A CDP-4-dehydro-3,6-dideoxy-D-glucose in which the anomeric centre of the pyranose fragment has alpha-configuration.

name: isopentadecanoate
definition: A methyl-branched fatty acid anion that is the conjugate base of isopentadecanoic acid, obtained by deprotonation of the carboxy group; major species at pH 7.3.

name: isopentadecanoyl-CoA(4-)
definition: A saturated fatty acyl-CoA(4-) arising from deprotonation of the phosphate and diphosphate functions of isopentadecanoyl-CoA.

name: methyl 4-hydroxypiperidine-3-carboxylate
definition: A piperidinecarboxylate ester that is the methyl ester of 4-hydroxypiperidine-3-carboxylic acid.

name: beta-D-Gal-(1->4)-beta-D-GlcNAc-(1->2)-[beta-D-Gal-(1->4)-beta-D-GlcNAc-(1->4)]-alpha-D-Man-(1->3)-[beta-D-Gal-(1->4)-beta-D-GlcNAc-(1->2)-alpha-D-Man-(1->6)]-beta-D-Man-(1->4)-beta-D-GlcNAc-(1->4)-D-GlcNAc
definition: An amino oligosaccharide that is a branched tridecasaccharide in which two beta-D-Gal-(1->4)-beta-D-GlcNAc disaccharide units are linked (1->2) and (1->4) to the terminal mannose residue of an alpha-D-Man-(1->3)-beta-D-Man-(1->4)-beta-D-GlcNAc-(1->4)-D-GlcNAc tetrasaccharide chain, to the beta-D-mannose residue of which is also linked (1->6) a beta-D-Gal-(1->4)-beta-D-GlcNAc-(1->3)-alpha-D-Man trisaccharide unit.

name: 20-methyl-21,22-didehydro-20,21-dihydrobotryococcene
definition: A triterpenoid obtained by methylation at position 20 of C30-botryococcene with concomitant double bond migration from position 20 to position 21.

name: N-hexadecenoyl-15-methylhexadecasphing-4-enine-1-phosphocholine
definition: An N-acyl-15-methylhexadecasphing-4-enine-1-phosphocholine in which the acyl group has 16 carbons and 1 double bond.

name: N-(2-hydroxyhexadecatetraenoyl)-15-methylhexadecasphing-4-enine-1-phosphocholine
definition: An N-acyl-15-methylhexadecasphing-4-enine-1-phosphocholine in which the acyl group has 16 carbons and 4 double bonds and is 2-hydroxylated.

name: N-heptadecenoyl-15-methylhexadecasphing-4-enine-1-phosphocholine
definition: An N-acyl-15-methylhexadecasphing-4-enine-1-phosphocholine in which the acyl group has 17 carbons and 1 double bond.

name: N-hexadecanoyl-4-hydroxy-15-methylhexadecasphinganine-1-phosphocholine
definition: An N-hexadecanoyl-4-hydroxy-15-methylhexadecasphinganine-1-phosphocholine in which the acyl group has 16 carbons and 0 double bonds.

name: N-octadecadienoyl-15-methylhexadecasphing-4-enine-1-phosphocholine
definition: An N-acyl-15-methylhexadecasphing-4-enine-1-phosphocholine in which the acyl group has 18 carbons and 2 double bonds.

name: N-nonadecadienoyl-15-methylhexadecasphing-4-enine-1-phosphocholine
definition: An N-acyl-15-methylhexadecasphing-4-enine-1-phosphocholine in which the acyl group has 19 carbons and 2 double bonds.

name: N-tetracosenoyl-15-methylhexadecasphing-4-enine-1-phosphocholine
definition: An N-acyl-15-methylhexadecasphing-4-enine-1-phosphocholine in which the acyl group has 24 carbons and 1 double bond.

name: N-(2-hydroxytricosanoyl)-15-methylhexadecasphing-4-enine-1-phosphocholine
definition: An N-acyl-15-methylhexadecasphing-4-enine-1-phosphocholine in which the acyl group has 23 carbons and 0 double bonds and is 2-hydroxylated.

name: N-pentacosadienoyl-15-methylhexadecasphing-4-enine-1-phosphocholine
definition: An N-acyl-15-methylhexadecasphing-4-enine-1-phosphocholine in which the acyl group has 25 carbons and 2 double bonds.

name: N-acetyltryptophan
definition: An N-acetylamino acid that is the N-acetyl derivative of tryptophan.

name: 6-formylpterin
definition: Pterin carrying a formyl group at position 6.

name: 6-[(8Z)-pentadec-8-en-1-yl]benzene-1,2,4-triol
definition: A benzenetriol that is benzene-1,2,4-triol substituted by a (8Z)-pentadec-8-en-1-yl group at position 6.

name: 6-[(8Z,11Z)-heptadeca-8,11-dien-1-yl]benzene-1,2,4-triol
definition: A benzenetriol that is benzene-1,2,4-triol substituted by a (8Z,11Z)-heptadeca-8,11-dien-1-yl moiety at position 6.

name: 3-dehydrotetradecasphinganine(1+)
definition: A cationic sphingoid that is the conjugate acid of 3-dehydrotetradecasphinganine, obtained by protonation of the primary amino function; major species at pH 7.3.

name: 2-octenoyl-L-carnitine
definition: An  octenoyl-Lcarnitine having 2-octenoyl as the acyl substituent.

name: perampanel hydrate
definition: A hydrate obtained by combining four molecules of perampanel with three molecules of water. Used as an adjunctive therapy for the treatment of partial-onset seizures in patients with epilepsy.

name: beta-D-Galp-(1->4)-beta-D-GlcpNAc-(1->2)-alpha-D-Manp-(1->3)-beta-D-Manp-(1->4)-beta-D-GlcpNAc-(1->4)-D-GlcpNAc
definition: A linear amino hexasaccharide comprised of beta-D-galactose, N-acetyl-beta-D-glucosamine, alpha-D-mannose, beta-D-mannose, N-acetyl-beta-D-glucosamine and N-acetyl-D-glucosamine residues linked sequentially (1->4), (1->2), (1->3), (1->4) and (1->4).

name: 3-hydroxybenzenesulfonic acid
definition: An arenesulfonic acid that is phenol substituted by a sulfo group at C-3.

name: hexadecasphinganine
definition: A sphingoid obtained by formal hydrogenation of the C=C bond of hexadecasphingosine.

name: beta-D-Galp-(1->4)-beta-D-GlcpNAc-(1->3)-D-GalpNAc
definition: A linear amino trisaccharide consisting of a chain of beta-D-galactose, N-acetyl-beta-D-glucosamine and N-acetyl-D-galactosamine residues linked sequentially (1->4) and (1->3).

name: N-hexadecanoyl-1-O-beta-D-glucosyl-15-methylhexadecasphing-4-enine
definition: An N-acyl-1-O-beta-D-glucosyl-15-methylhexadecasphing-4-enine in which the acyl group has 16 carbons and 0 double bonds.

name: N-2-hydroxyhexadecanoyl-1-O-beta-D-glucosyl-15-methylhexadecasphing-4-enine
definition: An N-acyl-1-O-beta-D-glucosyl-15-methylhexadecasphing-4-enine in which the acyl group has 16 carbons and 0 double bonds and is 2-hydroxylated.

name: N-icosanoyl-1-O-beta-D-glucosyl-4-hydroxy-15-methylhexadecasphinganine
definition: An N-acyl-1-O-beta-D-glucosyl-4-hydroxy-15-methylhexadecasphinganine in which the acyl group has 20 carbons and 0 double bonds.

name: N-(2-hydroxytricosatetraenoyl)-1-O-beta-D-glucosyl-15-methylhexadecasphing-4-enine
definition: An N-acyl-1-O-beta-D-glucosyl-15-methylhexadecasphing-4-enine in which the acyl group has 23 carbons and 4 double bonds and is 2-hydroxylated.

name: N-tetracosanoyl-1-O-beta-D-glucosyl-15-methylhexadecasphing-4-enine
definition: An N-acyl-1-O-beta-D-glucosyl-15-methylhexadecasphing-4-enine in which the acyl group has 24 carbons and 0 double bonds.

name: N-(2-hydroxydocosanoyl)-1-O-beta-D-glucosyl-4-hydroxy-15-methylhexadecasphinganine
definition: An N-acyl-1-O-beta-D-glucosyl-4-hydroxy-15-methylhexadecasphinganine in which the acyl group has 22 carbons and 0 double bonds and is 2-hydroxylated.

name: N-hexacosanoyl-1-O-beta-D-glucosyl-15-methylhexadecasphing-4-enine
definition: An N-acyl-1-O-beta-D-glucosyl-15-methylhexadecasphing-4-enine in which the acyl group has 26 carbons and 0 double bonds.

name: N-(2-hydroxyhexacosadienoyl)-1-O-beta-D-glucosyl-15-methylhexadecasphing-4-enine
definition: An N-acyl-1-O-beta-D-glucosyl-15-methylhexadecasphing-4-enine in which the acyl group has 26 carbons and 2 double bonds and is 2-hydroxylated.

name: pyrrole-3,4-dicarboxylic acid
definition: A pyrroledicarboxylic acid in which the two carboxy groups are located at positions 3 and 4.

name: (R)-lactoyl-CoA
definition: A lactoyl-CoA in which the lactoyl residue has (R)-configuration.

name: N-benzoylalanine
definition: An N-acylamino acid that is the N-benzoyl derivative of alanine.

name: H1-receptor agonist
definition: A histamine agonist that binds to and activates H1-receptors.

name: EC 2.1.1.4 (acetylserotonin O-methyltransferase) inhibitor
definition: An EC 2.1.1.* (methyltransferases) inhibitor that interferes with the action of N-acetylserotonin methyltransferase (EC 2.1.1.4).

name: trans-3-hydroxycotinine
definition: An N-alkylpyrrolidine that is cotinine substituted at position C-3 by a hydroxy group (the 3R,5S-diastereomer).

name: iminodiacetonitrile
definition: A secondary amino compound that is ammonia in which two of the hydrogens are substituted by cyanomethyl groups.

name: N-(cyanomethyl)glycinate
definition: An alpha-amino-acid anion that is the conjugate base of N-(cyanomethyl)glycine, obtained by deprotonation of the carboxy group.

name: beta-D-Galp-(1->4)-beta-D-GlcpNAc-(1->6)-beta-D-Galp-(1->4)-beta-D-GlcpNAc
definition: An amino tetrasaccharide comprised of a linear sequence of beta-D-galactose, N-acetyl-beta-D-glucosamine, beta-D-galactose and N-acetyl-beta-D-glucosamine residues linked (1->4), (1->6) and (1->4).

name: 3-oxocyclopentanecarboxylic acid
definition: An alicyclic ketone that is oxocyclopentanone substituted at position 3 by a carboxy group.

name: feruloylacetyl-CoA
definition: An acyl-CoA that results from the formal condensation of the thiol group of coenzyme A with the carboxy group of feruloylacetic acid.

name: sodium diphosphate
definition: An inorganic sodium salt comprised of a diphosphate(4-) anion and four sodium(1+) cations. More commonly known as tetrasodium pyrophosphate, it finds much use in the food industry as an emulsifier and in dental hygiene as a calcium-chelating salt.

name: (S,S)-asenapine(1+)
definition: An organic cation that is the conjugate acid of (S,S)-asenapine, obtained by protonation of the tertiary amino group.

name: 5-chloro-2-methyl-2,3,3a,12b-tetrahydrodibenzo[2,3:6,7]oxepino[4,5-c]pyrrole
definition: An organic heterotetracyclic compound that is 2,3,3a,12b-tetrahydrodibenzo[2,3:6,7]oxepino[4,5-c]pyrrole bearing methyl and chloro substituents at positions 2 and 5 respectively.

name: (3beta,16alpha)-13,28-epoxyoleanane-3,16,30-triol
definition: A hexacyclic triterpenoid that consists of oleanane substituted by hydroxy groups at 3beta, 16alpha and C-30 positions and an oxolane bridge across positions 13 and 28.

name: beta-D-GlcpA-(1->6)-beta-D-Galp
definition: A glycosylgalactose consisting of beta-D-galactose substituted on O-6 with a beta-D-glucopyranuronosyl (beta-D-glucopyranosyluronic acid) group.

name: mannooligosaccharide derivative
definition: An oligosaccharide derivative that is derived from a mannooligosaccharide.

name: 4-hydroxy-3-nitrophenylacetaldehyde(1-)
definition: A phenolate anion that is the conjugate base of 4-hydroxy-3-nitrophenylacetaldehyde; major species at pH 7.3

name: arabinan derivative
definition: A homopolysaccharide derivative which is formally derived from an arabinan.

name: WO2-molybdopterin cofactor(2-)
definition: An organophosphate oxoanion obtained by deprotonation of the phosphate OH groups of WO2-molybdopterin cofactor.

name: pyridobenzodiazepine
definition: Any three-ring heterocyclic compound with a skeleton consisting of a pyridine ring ortho-fused to a benzodiazepine.

name: 3'-O-(N-methylanthraniloyl)adenosine 5'-diphosphate
definition: A purine ribonucleoside 5'-diphosphate that is ADP substituted at position 3' by an N-methylanthraniloyl group.

name: norsolorinic acid
definition: A polyketide that is anthraquinone bearing four hydroxy substituents at positions 1, 3, 6 and 8 as well as a hexanoyl substituent at position 2.

name: N-(2-hydroxyoctadecanoyl)-15-methylhexadecasphing-4-enine
definition: An N-acyl-15-methylhexadecasphing-4-enine in which the acyl group has 18 carbons and 0 double bonds and is 2-hydroxylated.

name: N-docosanoyl-15-methylhexadecasphing-4-enine
definition: An N-acyl-15-methylhexadecasphing-4-enine in which the acyl group has 22 carbons and 0 double bonds.

name: beta-D-GlcpNAc-(1->6)-alpha-D-GalpNAc
definition: beta-D-GlcpNAc-(1->6)-D-GalpNAc in which the anomeric configuration of the reducing-end GalNAc residue is alpha.

name: phenazopyridine(1+)
definition: An organic cation that is the conjugate acid of phenazopyridine.

name: 3-oxoisooctadecanoyl-CoA(4-)
definition: A 3-oxo-fatty acyl-CoA(4-) arising from deprotonation of the phosphate and diphosphate functions of 3-oxoisooctadecanoyl-CoA.

name: 3-hydroxyisopentadecanoyl-CoA(4-)
definition: An 3-hydroxy fatty acyl-CoA(4-) arising from deprotonation of the phosphate and diphosphate OH groups of 3-hydroxyisopentadecanoyl-CoA; the major species at pH 7.3.

name: 3-oxoisoheptadecanoyl-CoA(4-)
definition: A 3-oxo-fatty acyl-CoA(4-) arising from deprotonation of the phosphate and diphosphate functions of 3-oxoisoheptadecanoyl-CoA.

name: alpha-D-Manp-(1->2)-alpha-D-Manp-(1->2)-alpha-D-Manp-(1->3)-[alpha-D-Manp-(1->3)-[alpha-D-Manp-(1->2)-alpha-D-Manp-(1->6)]-alpha-D-Manp-(1->6)]-alpha-D-Manp
definition: A branched mannooligosaccharide comprised of eight alpha-D-mannose residues arrangedin the configuration shown.

name: cis-trans-nepetalactol
definition: A cyclopentapyran that is 1,4a,5,6,7,7a-hexahydrocyclopenta[c]pyran substituted at position 1 by a hydroxy group and at positions 4 and 7 by methyl groups (the 4aS,7S,7aR-diastereomer)

name: cyclic di-AMP(2-)
definition: An organophosphate oxoanion obtained by deprotonation of the phosphate OH groups of cyclic di-AMP; major species at pH 7.3.

name: cyanidin 3,7-di-O-beta-D-glucoside betaine
definition: An oxonium betaine that is the conjugate base of cyanidin 3,7-di-O-beta-D-glucoside, arising from regioselective deprotonation of the 5-hydroxy group. Major structure at pH 7.3

name: 7,8-dimethylisoalloxazine-10-carbaldehyde
definition: A flavin carrying a formyl group at C-10.

name: (S)-averantin
definition: An optically active form of averantin having S-configuration.

name: dihydroagarofuran sesquiterpenoid
definition: Any sesquiterpenoid with a dihydroagarofuran skeleton.

name: alpha-D-Manp-(1->6)-beta-D-Manp
definition: alpha-D-Manp-(1->6)-D-Manp in which the anomeric configuration at the reducing end is beta.

name: (25S)-Delta(7)-dafachronic acid
definition: A Delta(7)-dafachronic acid that has S configuration at position 25 (the carbon attached to the carboxy group).

name: alpha-L-Fucp-(1->3)-[alpha-Neup5Ac-(2->3)-beta-D-Galp6S-(1->4)]-beta-D-GlcpNAc
definition: A branched amino tetrasaccharide comprised of a trisaccharide chain of N-acetyl-alpha-neuraminic acid, 6-O-sulfo-beta-D-glactose and N-acetyl-beta-D-glucosamine residues linked sequentially (2->3) and (1->4), to the GlcNAC residue of which is also linked (1->3) an alpha-L-fucose residue.

name: (8Z,11Z,14Z,17Z)-3-oxoicosatetraenoyl-CoA
definition: An unsaturated fatty acyl-CoA that results from the formal condensation of the thiol group of coenzyme A with the carboxy group of (8Z,11Z,14Z,17Z)-3-oxoicosatetraenoic acid.

name: cyclic di-AMP
definition: A cyclic purine dinucleotide that is the 3',5'-cyclic dimer of AMP.

name: (3E,5Z)-tetradecadienoate
definition: A long-chain unsaturated fatty acid anion that is the conjugate base of (3E,5Z)-tetradecadienoic acid, obtained by deprotonation of the carboxy group; major species at pH 7.3.

name: filicinic acid
definition: An enone that is cyclohexa-2,5-dien-1-one substituted by hydroxy groups at positions 3 and 5 and geminal methyl groups at position 4.

name: mycocyclosin
definition: An organic heterotetracyclic compound obtained via intramolecular oxidative aromatic coupling of cyclo(L-tyrosyl-L-tyrosyl).

name: sarmentologenin
definition: A steroid lactone that is card-20(22)-enolide substituted by hydroxy groups at positions 3, 5, 11, 14 and 19.

name: versiconol acetate(1-)
definition: An organic anion that is the conjugate base of versiconol acetate, obtained by selective deprotonation of the 2-hydroxy group.

name: N(6)-(dimethylallyl)adenosine 5'-triphosphate
definition: A purine ribonucleoside 5'-diphosphate that is ATP substituted at position N-6 by a dimethylallyl (isopentenyl) group.

name: staphyloxanthin
definition: A xanthophyll that is beta-D-glucopyranose in which the hydroxy groups at positions 1 and 6 have been acylated by an all-trans-2,6,10,15,19,23-hexamethyltetracosa-2,4,6,8,10,12,14,16,18,22-decaenoyl group and a 12-methyltetradecanoyl group, respectively. Staphyloxanthin is responsible for the characteristic yellow-golden colour which gives the bacterium Staphylococcus aureus its name.

name: alpha-D-Glc-(1->3)-L-alpha-D-Hep4P-(1->3)-L-alpha-D-Hep4P-(1->5)-[alpha-D-Kdo-(2->4)]-alpha-D-Kdo-(2->6)-beta-D-GlcN4P-(1->6)-alpha-D-Glc1P
definition: An amino octasaccharide made up from one alpha-D-glucose residue, two monophosphorylated L-alpha-D-Hep residues, two alpha-Kdo residues and two monophosphorylated alpha-D-glucosamine residues (one of which is at the reducing end).

name: phosphatidylethanolamine 30:1
definition: A 1,2-diacyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphoethanolamine zwitterion in which the acyl groups at C-1 and C-2 contain 30 carbons in total with 1 double bond.

name: phosphatidylethanolamine 30:4
definition: A 1,2-diacyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphoethanolamine zwitterion in which the acyl groups at C-1 and C-2 contain 30 carbons in total with 4 double bonds.

name: phosphatidylethanolamine 40:0 zwitterion
definition: A 1,2-diacyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphoethanolamine zwitterion in which the acyl groups at C-1 and C-2 contain 40 carbons in total with 0 double bonds.

name: phosphatidylethanolamine 40:4 zwitterion
definition: A 1,2-diacyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphoethanolamine zwitterion in which the acyl groups at C-1 and C-2 contain 40 carbons in total with 4 double bonds.

name: phosphatidylethanolamine 40:6 zwitterion
definition: A 1,2-diacyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphoethanolamine zwitterion in which the acyl groups at C-1 and C-2 contain 40 carbons in total with 6 double bonds.

name: phosphatidylethanolamine O-30:3 zwitterion
definition: An alkyl,acyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphoethanolamine zwitterion in which the alkyl or acyl groups at positions 1 and 2 contain a total of 30 carbons and 3 double bonds.

name: phosphatidylethanolamine O-32:2 zwitterion
definition: An alkyl,acyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphoethanolamine zwitterion in which the alkyl or acyl groups at positions 1 and 2 contain a total of 32 carbons and 2 double bonds.

name: phosphatidylethanolamine O-38:6 zwitterion
definition: An alkyl,acyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphoethanolamine zwitterion in which the alkyl or acyl groups at positions 1 and 2 contain a total of 38 carbons and 6 double bonds.

name: phosphatidylethanolamine O-42:2 zwitterion
definition: An alkyl,acyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphoethanolamine zwitterion in which the alkyl or acyl groups at positions 1 and 2 contain a total of 42 carbons and 2 double bonds.

name: [3)-alpha-L-Araf-(1->3)-6d-alpha-L-gulo-Hepp-(1->]n
definition: A polysaccharide composed of a backbone of alpha-L-arabinofuranosyl-(1->3)-6-deoxy-alpha-L-gulo-heptopyranosyl repeating units that are joined to each other via (1->3)-linkages.

name: 5-amino-5-deoxy-3-dehydroshikimic acid zwitterion
definition: An amino acid zwitterion obtained by transfer of a proton from the carboxy to the amino group of 5-amino-5-deoxy-3-dehydroshikimic acid; major species at pH 7.3.

name: neoflavonoid
definition: Any 1-benzopyran with an aryl substituent at position 4. The term was originally restricted to natural products, but is now also used to describe semi-synthetic and fully synthetic compounds.

name: retaspimycin(1+)
definition: An organic cation obtained by protonation of retaspimycin.

name: N-(2-hydroxytetradecanoyl)icosasphinganine
definition: A C20 dihydroceramide in which the ceramide N-acyl group is specified as 2-hydroxytetradecanoyl.

name: N-(2-hydroxytetradecanoyl)icosaphytosphingosine
definition: A C20 phytoceramide in which the ceramide N-acyl group is specified as 2-hydroxytetradecanoyl.

name: N-octacosanoylsphinganine
definition: A dihydroceramide that is the N-(octacosanoyl) derivative of sphinganine.

name: N-octacosanoylphytosphingosine
definition: A phytoceramide in which the ceramide N-acyl group is specified as octacosanoyl.

name: N-(2-hydroxytriacontanoyl)sphinganine
definition: A dihydroceramide in which the ceramide N-acyl group is specified as 2-hydroxytriacontanoyl.

name: N-tricontanoyl-4-hydroxyicosasphinganine
definition: A C20 phytoceramide in which the ceramide N-acyl group is specified as tricontanoyl.

name: phosphatidylserine 34:3(1-)
definition: A 3-sn-phosphatidyl-L-serine(1-) in which the acyl groups at C-1 and C-2 contain 34 carbons in total and 3 double bonds.

name: phosphatidylserine 40:2(1-)
definition: A 3-sn-phosphatidyl-L-serine(1-) in which the acyl groups at C-1 and C-2 contain 40 carbons in total and 2 double bonds.

name: phosphatidylserine 40:3(1-)
definition: A 3-sn-phosphatidyl-L-serine(1-) in which the acyl groups at C-1 and C-2 contain 40 carbons in total and 3 double bonds.

name: phosphatidylserine 42:1(1-)
definition: A 3-sn-phosphatidyl-L-serine(1-) in which the acyl groups at C-1 and C-2 contain 42 carbons in total and 1 double bond.

name: phosphatidylserine 44:6(1-)
definition: A 3-sn-phosphatidyl-L-serine(1-) in which the acyl groups at C-1 and C-2 contain 44 carbons in total and 6 double bonds.

name: phosphatidylserine O-32:6(1-)
definition: An alkyl,acyl-sn-glycero-3-phospho-L-serine(1-) in which the alkyl or acyl groups at positions 1 and 2 contain a total of 32 carbons and 6 double bonds.

name: phosphatidylserine O-36:6(1-)
definition: An alkyl,acyl-sn-glycero-3-phospho-L-serine(1-) in which the alkyl or acyl groups at positions 1 and 2 contain a total of 36 carbons and 6 double bonds.

name: alpha-Neup5Ac-(2->8)-alpha-Neup5Ac-(2->8)-alpha-Neup5Ac
definition: alpha-Neup5Ac-(2->8)-alpha-Neup5Ac-(2->8)-Neup5Ac in which the sialyl residue at the reducing end has alpha anomeric configuration.

name: (22S)-22-hydroxycampesterol
definition: A brassinosteroid that is campesterol bearing an additional 22S-hydroxy substituent.

name: imidazochromene
definition: An organic heterotricyclic compound that consists of a chromene ring system having an imidazole ring ortho-fused at any position.

name: 2,6-diamino-2,3,6-trideoxy-alpha-D-glucose(2+)
definition: An organic cation obtained by protonation of the amino groups of 2,6-diamino-2,3,6-trideoxy-alpha-D-glucose.

name: phosphatidylserine 44:0-OH(1-)
definition: A 3-sn-phosphatidyl-L-serine(1-) in which the acyl groups at C-1 and C-2 contain 44 carbons in total with no double bonds but 1 hydroxyl substituent.

name: lysophosphatidylethanolamine zwitterion 24:0
definition: A lysophosphatidylethanolamine zwitterion in which the remaining acyl group (position not specified) contains 24 carbons and 0 double bonds.

name: lysophosphatidylethanolamine zwitterion 26:1
definition: A lysophosphatidylethanolamine zwitterion in which the remaining acyl group (position not specified) contains 26 carbons and 1 double bond.

name: lysophosphatidylserine 20:0(1-)
definition: A lysophosphatidylserine(1-) in which the remaining acyl group (position not specified) contains 20 carbons and 0 double bonds.

name: phosphatidylcholine 44:2-OH
definition: A 1,2-diacyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphocholine in which the acyl groups at C-1 and C-2 contain 44 carbons in total with 2 double bonds and 1 hydroxy group.

name: englerin A
definition: A guaiane sesquiterpenoid that is isolated from the bark of Phyllanthus engleri, a plant native to Tanzania and Zimbabwe. It acts as a potent and specific inhibitor of renal cancer cell growth.

name: tetramethylrosamine chloride
definition: The chloride salt of tetramethylrosamine. Used as a red-orange fluorescent dye.

name: alpha-Neup5Ac-(2->8)-alpha-Neup5Ac-(2->8)-alpha-Neup5Ac-(2->3)-[beta-D-GalpNAc-(1->4)]-beta-D-Galp-(1->4)-beta-D-Glcp
definition: A branched amino hexasaccharide consisting of a chain of three alpha-sialyl residues, a beta-D-galactosyl residue and a beta-D-glucose residue linked sequentially (2->8), (2->8), (2->3) and (1->4), to the galactosyl residue of which is also linked (1->4) an N-acetyl-beta-D-galactosaminyl residue. The carbohydrate moiety of ganglioside GT2.

name: alpha-Neup5Gc-(2->3)-beta-D-Galp-(1->3)-[alpha-L-Fucp-(1->4)]-beta-D-GlcNAcp
definition: A branched amino tetrasaccharide comprising alpha-N-glycoloylneuraminyl, beta-D-galactosyl and N-acetyl-beta-D-glucosamine residues linked sequentially (2->3) and (1->3), to the galactosyl residue of which is also linked (1->4) an alpha-L-fucosyl residue.

name: sphingomyelin 32:2
definition: A sphingomyelin in which the total number of carbons in the sphingoid base and fatty acyl groups is 32 with 2 double bonds.

name: sphingomyelin 32:4
definition: A sphingomyelin in which the total number of carbons in the sphingoid base and fatty acyl groups is 32 with 4 double bonds.

name: sphingomyelin 42:2
definition: A sphingomyelin in which the total number of carbons in the sphingoid base and fatty acyl groups is 42 with 2 double bonds.

name: sphingomyelin 42:4
definition: A sphingomyelin in which the total number of carbons in the sphingoid base and fatty acyl groups is 42 with 4 double bonds.

name: (3S,4S)-3-hydroxy-4-methyloctanoic acid
definition: A hydroxy fatty acid that is caprylic (octanoic) acid substituted at positions 3 and 4 by hydroxy and methyl grous respectively.

name: imidazotetrazine
definition: Any organic heterobicyclic compound containing ortho-fused imidazole and tetrazine rings.

name: triazene derivative
definition: A nitrogen molecular entity resulting from the formal substitution of one or more of the hydrogens of triazene.

name: Man-1-6-Ins-1-P-Cer(t18:0)(1-)
definition: A mannosylinositol phosphorylceramide(1-) having an acyl group attached to the ceramide nitrogen and hydroxylation at C4 of the C18 sphingoid base; major species at pH 7.3.

name: semisynthetic derivative
definition: Any organic molecular entity derived from a natural product by partial chemical synthesis.

name: rhizoxin
definition: An macrolide antibiotic isolated from the pathogenic plant fungus Rhizopus microsporus. It also exhibits antitumour and antimitotic activity.

name: alpha-Neup5Ac-(2->3)-beta-D-Galp-(1->3)-[alpha-L-Fucp-(1->4)]-beta-D-GlcpNAc-(1->3)-beta-D-Galp-(1->3)-[alpha-L-Fucp-(1->4)]-beta-D-GlcpNAc
definition: A branched amino heptasaccharide consisting of a linear sequence of N-acetyl-alpha-neuraminyl, beta-D-galactosyl, N-acetyl-beta-D-glucosaminyl, beta-D-galactosyl and N-acetyl-beta-D-glucosamine residues linked respectively (2->3), (1->3), (1->3) and (1->4), to each N-acetyl-beta-D-glucosamine residue of which is also linked (1->4) an alpha-L-fucosyl residue.

name: 8-HDoHE
definition: A hydroxydocosahexaenoic acid that consists of 4Z,6E,10Z,13Z,16Z,19Z-docosahexaenoic acid bearing an additional 8-hydroxy substituent.

name: 9-(alpha-D-glucosyl)kinetin
definition: An N-glycosyl compound that is kinetin in which an alpha-D-glucopyranosyl residue is attached at position N-9.

name: 9-HODE
definition: A HODE that consists of (10E,12Z)-octadecadienoic acid with the hydroxy substituent located at position 9.

name: (2R)-dihomocitrate(3-)
definition: A tricarboxylic acid trianion obtained by deprotonation of the three carboxy groups of (R)-dihomocitric acid; major structure at pH 7.3.

name: 2-arachidonyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphoethanolamine
definition: A 2-acyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphoethanolamine in which the acyl group is specified as (5Z,8Z,11Z,14Z)-eicosatetraenoyl (arachidonoyl).

name: (E)-hexadec-2-enoate
definition: A straight-chain unsaturated fatty acid anion that is the conjugate base of (E)-hexadec-2-enoic acid, obtained by deprotonation of the carboxy group.

name: kanamycin C(4+)
definition: An organic cation obtained by protonation of the primary amino groups of kanamycin C.

name: 2'-oxokanamycin
definition: A kanamycin obtained by dehydrogenation at position 2' of kanamycin A.

name: beta-leucine
definition: A beta-amino acid that is pentanoic acid substituted at positions 3 and 4 by amino and methyl groups respectively.

name: kunzeaol
definition: A germacrane sesquiterpenoid derived from germacrane by dehydrogenation between the 1-10 and 4-5 positions as well as hydroxylation at position 6.

name: 11-HDoHE
definition: A hydroxydocosahexaenoic acid that consists of 4Z,7Z,9E,13Z,16Z,19Z-docosahexaenoic acid with the hydroxy group located at position 11.

name: 5-HEPE
definition: A hydroxyicosapentaenoic acid that consists of 6E,8Z,11Z,14Z,17Z-icosapentaenoic acid with the hydroxy group located at position 5.

name: 18-HEPE
definition: A hydroxyicosapentaenoic acid that consists of 5Z,8Z,11Z,14Z,16E-icosapentaenoic acid with the hydroxy group located at position 18.

name: 2-alkyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphocholine
definition: A monoalkylglycerophosphocholine that is sn-glycero-3-phosphocholine in which the alkyl group is located at position 2.

name: 1-acyl-2-[(Z)-alk-1-enyl]-sn-glycero-3-phosphocholine
definition: An alkyl,acyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphocholine having an acyl group at the 1 position and a (Z)-alk-1-enyl substituent at the 2-position.

name: exopolysaccharide
definition: A biomacromolecule composed of carbohydrate residues which is secreted by a microorganism into the surrounding environment.

name: L-alanyl-L-alanine
definition: A dipeptide consisting of two L-alanine units joined by a peptide linkage.

name: 1-methyl-2-hydroadenosine
definition: A methyladenosine that is the 1-methyl-2-hydro derivative of adenosine.

name: 1-octadecanoyl-sn-glycero-3-phospho-(1'-sn-glycerol)(1-)
definition: A 1-acyl-sn-glycero-3-phospho-(1'-sn-glycerol)(1-) in which the acyl group is specified as octadecanoyl (stearoyl); major species at pH 7.3.

name: 2-hexadecanoyl-1-octadecanoyl-sn-glycero-3-phospho-(1'-sn-glycerol)(1-)
definition: A 1,2-diacyl-sn-glycero-3-phospho-(1'-sn-glycerol)(1-) in which the 1- and 2-acyl groups are specified as octadecanoyl (stearoyl) and hexadecanoyl (palmitoyl) respectively; major species at pH 7.3.

name: 1,2-dihexadecanoyl-sn-glycero-3-phospho-D-myo-inositol(1-)
definition: A 1-hexadecanoyl-2-acyl-sn-glycero-3-phospho-1D-myo-inositol(1-) obtained by deprotonation of the phosphate OH group of 1,2-dihexadecanoyl-sn-glycero-3-phospho-D-myo-inositol.

name: 9-oxo-ODE
definition: An oxooctadecadienoic acid that consists of (10E,12Z)-octadecadienoic acid with the oxo substituent located at position 9.

name: EpETE
definition: An epoxy fatty acid obtained by formal epoxidation of one of the double bonds of any icosapentaenoic acid.

name: 1-hexadecanoyl-2-(9Z,12Z-octadecadienoyl)-sn-glycero-3-phosphate(2-)
definition: A 1,2-diacyl-sn-glycerol 3-phosphate(2-) in which the 1- and 2-acyl groups are specified as hexadecanoyl (palmitoyl) and 9Z,12Z-octadecadienoyl (linoleoyl) respectively; major species at pH 7.3.

name: dihydroxyicosatetraenoic acid
definition: A hydroxy fatty acid that is any eicosatetraenoic acid bearing two hydroxy substituents.

name: cardiolipin 52:2(2-)
definition: A cardiolipin(2-) derivative in which the four phosphatidyl acyl groups contain a total of 52 carbons and 2 double bonds.

name: cardiolipin 58:3(2-)
definition: A cardiolipin(2-) derivative in which the four phosphatidyl acyl groups contain a total of 58 carbons and 3 double bonds.

name: cardiolipin 64:4(2-)
definition: A cardiolipin(2-) derivative in which the four phosphatidyl acyl groups contain a total of 64 carbons and 4 double bonds.

name: cardiolipin 68:3(2-)
definition: A cardiolipin(2-) derivative in which the four phosphatidyl acyl groups contain a total of 68 carbons and 3 double bonds.

name: cardiolipin 68:5(2-)
definition: A cardiolipin(2-) derivative in which the four phosphatidyl acyl groups contain a total of 68 carbons and 5 double bonds.

name: cardiolipin 70:5(2-)
definition: A cardiolipin(2-) derivative in which the four phosphatidyl acyl groups contain a total of 70 carbons and 5 double bonds.

name: cardiolipin 70:6(2-)
definition: A cardiolipin(2-) derivative in which the four phosphatidyl acyl groups contain a total of 70 carbons and 6 double bonds.

name: cardiolipin 70:7(2-)
definition: A cardiolipin(2-) derivative in which the four phosphatidyl acyl groups contain a total of 70 carbons and 7 double bonds.

name: cardiolipin 72:4(2-)
definition: A cardiolipin(2-) derivative in which the four phosphatidyl acyl groups contain a total of 72 carbons and 4 double bonds.

name: cardiolipin 76:5(2-)
definition: A cardiolipin(2-) derivative in which the four phosphatidyl acyl groups contain a total of 76 carbons and 5 double bonds.

name: cardiolipin 76:9(2-)
definition: A cardiolipin(2-) derivative in which the four phosphatidyl acyl groups contain a total of 76 carbons and 9 double bonds.

name: cardiolipin 80:10(2-)
definition: A cardiolipin(2-) derivative in which the four phosphatidyl acyl groups contain a total of 80 carbons and 10 double bonds.

name: N-[(7,8-dihydropterin-6-yl)methyl]-4-(beta-D-ribofuranosyl)aniline 5'-phosphate(2-)
definition: An organophosphate oxoanion obtained by deprotonation of the phosphate OH groups of N-[(7,8-dihydropterin-6-yl)methyl]-4-(beta-D-ribofuranosyl)aniline 5'-phosphate.

name: N-decanoylsphingosine
definition: A N-acylsphingosine in which the ceramide N-acyl group is specified as decanoyl.

name: N-hexadecanoylsphingosine 1-phosphate(2-)
definition: A N-acylsphingosine 1-phosphate(2-) in which the N-acyl group is specified as hexadecanoyl (palmitoyl).

name: N-docosanoylsphingosine
definition: A N-acylsphingosine in which the ceramide N-acyl group is specified as docosanoyl.

name: N-docosanoylsphingosine-1-phosphate(2-)
definition: A ceramide 1-phosphate(2-) in which the ceramide N-acyl group is specified as docosanoyl.

name: 1-hexadecanoyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphoethanolamine zwitterion
definition: A lysophosphatidylethanolamine zwitterion 16:0 obtained by transfer of a proton from the phosphate to the amino group of 1-hexadecanoyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphoethanolamine.

name: 1,2-dihexadecanoyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphoethanolamine zwitterion
definition: A phosphatidylethanolamine 32:0 zwitterion obtained by transfer of a proton from the phosphate to the amino group of 1,2-dihexadecanoyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphoethanolamine.

name: O-isobutyrylcarnitine
definition: An O-acylcarnitine having isobutyryl as the acyl substituent.

name: Ac-His-D-Pro-NH2
definition: A dipeptide that is the N(1)-(N(alpha)-acetyl-L-histidyl) derivative of D-prolinamide.

name: 2-methylbutyrylcarnitine
definition: A C5-acylcarnitine having 2-methylbutyryl as the acyl substituent.

name: parecoxib
definition: An N-acylsulfonamide resulting from the formal condensation of valdecoxib with propionic acid. It is a prodrug for valdecoxib.

name: O-glutarylcarnitine
definition: An O-acylcarnitine having glutaryl as the acyl substituent.

name: 3-hydroxypalmitoleoylcarnitine
definition: An O-acylcarnitine having 3-hydroxypalmitoleoyl as the acyl substituent.

name: (11Z,14Z)-eicosadienoylcarnitine
definition: An O-acylcarnitine having (11Z,14Z)-eicosadienoyl as the acyl substituent.

name: 1-hexadecanoyl-2-(9Z,12Z-octadecadienoyl)-sn-glycero-3-phosphoethanolamine
definition: A 1,2-diacyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphoethanolamine in which the 1- and 2-acyl groups are specified as hexadecanoyl (palmitoyl) and 9Z,12Z-octadecadienoyl (linoleoyl) respectively.

name: 1-hexadecanoyl-2-(9Z-octadecenoyl)-sn-glycero-3-phosphoethanolamine
definition: A 1,2-diacyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphoethanolamine in which the 1- and 2-acyl groups are specified as hexadecanoyl (palmitoyl) and 9Z-octadecenoyl (oleoyl) respectively.

name: horminone
definition: An abietane diterpenoid that is abieta-8,12-diene substituted by hydroxy groups at positions 7 and 12 and oxo groups at positions 11 and 14 (the 7alpha stereoisomer) .

name: aminonicotinic acid
definition: An aromatic amino acid that is nicotinic acid in which one of the hydrogens attached to the pyridine ring is replaced by an amino group. A 'closed class'.

name: (6aR,11aR)-pterocarpan
definition: The (6aR,11aR)-enantiomer of pterocarpan.

name: EC 1.1.1.184 [carbonyl reductase (NADPH)] inhibitor
definition: An EC 1.1.1.* (oxidoreductase acting on donor CH-OH group, NAD(+) or NADP(+) acceptor) inhibitor that interferes with the action of carbonyl reductase (NADPH), EC 1.1.1.184.

name: 9-beta-D-arabinofuranosylguanine
definition: A purine nucleoside in which guanine is attached to arabinofuranose via a beta-N(9)-glycosidic bond. It inhibits DNA synthesis and causes cell death.

name: N-octadecanoylsphingosine 1-phosphate
definition: A ceramide 1-phosphate that is the N-octadecananoyl (stearoyl) derivative of sphingosine.

name: 2,6-dimethyldeca-2,4,6,8-tetraenedial
definition: An apo carotenoid compound arising from oxidative degradation of the beta,beta-carotene skeleton at the 8'- and 13-positions.

name: L-BMAA
definition: A non-proteinogenic L-alpha-amino acid that is L-alanine in which one of the methyl hydrogens is replaced by a methylamino group. A non-proteinogenic amino acid produced by cyanobacteria, it is a neurotoxin that has been postulated as a possible cause of neurodegenerative disorders of aging such as Alzheimer's disease, amyotrophic lateral sclerosis, and the amyotrophic lateral sclerosis/parkinsonism-dementia complex (ALS-PDC) syndrome of Guam.

name: acifluorfen
definition: A member of the class of benzoic acids that is 2-nitrobenzoic acid in which the hydrogen at position 5 is replaced by a 2-chloro-4-(trifluoromethyl)phenoxy group. It is a herbicide used for the post-emergence control of a variety of annual broadleaf weeds.

name: 6beta-({5-[(p-aminophenyl)imino]pentylidene}amino)penicillanic acid
definition: Penicillanic acid carrying a (p-aminophenyl)imino]pentylidene}amino substituent at the 6beta position. It has been used as a hapten in the production of a generic monoclonal antibody for determining penicillin residues in milk.

name: 1-[(9Z)-octadec-9-enoyl]-2-hexadecanoyl-sn-glycero-3-phospho-(1'-sn-glycerol)
definition: A 1,2-diacyl-sn-glycero-3-phospho-(1'-sn-glycerol) in which the 1- and 2-acyl groups are specified as (9Z)-octadec-9-enoyl (oleoyl) and hexadecanoyl (palmitoyl) respectively.

name: rhamnosyl group
definition: A glycosyl group obtained by removing the hydroxy group from the hemiacetal function of a rhamnose and, by extension, of a lower oligosaccharide having rhamnose at the reducing end.

name: 1-hexadecanoyl-2-(9Z-octadecenoyl)-sn-glycero-3-phospho-D-myo-inositol
definition: A 1-hexadecanoyl-2-acyl-sn-glycero-3-phospho-1D-myo-inositol in which the 2-acyl group is specified as 9Z-octadecenoyl (oleoyl).

name: 4-(alpha-L-rhamnosyloxy)butanoyl group
definition: The univalent carboacyl group formed by loss of -OH from the carboxy group of 4-oxobutyl alpha-L-rhamnoside [4-(alpha-L-rhamnosyloxy)butanal].

name: ethylpyrazine
definition: A member of the class of pyrazines that is pyrazine in which one of the hydrogens is replaced by an ethyl group. Found particularly in cereals and cereal products, it is present in baked or fried potato, bread, roasted peanuts, and cooked shrimp, as well as cocoa, coffee, and tea. It has a musty, nutty, buttery, peanut odor and a chocolate-peanut taste.

name: 1,2-dihexadecanoyl-sn-glycerol-3-phosphate
definition: A 1-acyl-2-hexadecanoyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphate in which the 1-acyl group is also hexadecanoyl.

name: deglymidodrine

Midrodine is used (generally as its hydrochloride salt) as a prodrug for deglymidodrine, which acts as a peripheral vasoconstrictor in the treatment of certain hypotensive states.

name: (14Z,17Z,20Z,23Z,26Z,29Z)-dotriacontahexaenoyl-CoA(4-)

name: phosphatidylinositol 32:2(1-)

name: (10Z,13Z,16Z)-3-oxodocosatrienoyl-CoA(4-)

name: N-decanoylglycine

name: (21Z,24Z,27Z,30Z,33Z)-hexatriacontapentaenoyl-CoA

name: senegasaponin b
definition: A triterpenoid saponin isolated from Polygala senega var latifolia and has been shown to exhibit hypoglycemic activity.

name: (R)-3-hydroxylauroyl-CoA

name: senegasaponin a
definition: A triterpenoid saponin isolated from Polygala senega var latifolia and has been shown to exhibit hypoglycemic activity.

name: 5-chloro-7-iodoquinolin-8-ol
definition: A monohydroxyquinoline that is quinolin-8-ol in which the hydrogens at positions 5 and 7 are replaced by chlorine and iodine, respectively. It has antibacterial and atifungal properties, and is used in creams for the treatment of skin infections. It has also been investigated as a chelator of copper and zinc ions for the possible treatment of Alzheimer's disease.

name: lysophosphatidylinositol 16:0(1-)
definition: A lysophosphatidyl-1D-myo-inositol(1-) in which the remaining acyl group (position not specified) contains 16 carbons and 0 double bonds.

name: 2'-O-methylcytidine 5'-monophosphate(1-) residue
definition: An organic anionic group obtained by deprotonation of the free phosphate OH group of 2'-O-methylcytidine 5'-monophosphate residue.

name: carbazole alkaloid
definition: Any alkaloid based on a carbazole skeleton.

name: 6-aminonicotinamide
definition: A  monocarboxylic acid amide resulting from the formal condensation of the carboxy group of 6-aminonicotinic acid with ammonia. An inhibitor of the NADP(+)-dependent enzyme, 6-phosphogluconate dehydrogenase, it interferes with glycolysis, resulting in ATP depletion and synergizes with DNA-crosslinking chemotherapy drugs, such as cisplatin, in killing cancer cells.

name: anti-obesity agent
definition: Any substance which is used to reduce or control weight.

name: Leu-Glu

name: Leu-Gly

name: Ins-1-P-Cer-C

name: methyl (R)-lactate

name: Ins-1-P-Cer B/B' 44:0(1-)
definition: An Ins-1-P-Cer B/B'(1-) in which the acyl group and the ceramide base contain a total of 44 carbons and 0 double bonds, and in which either the acyl group is hydroxylated at position 2 or the ceramide base is hydroxylated at position 4.

name: 15-demethylaclacinomycin T
definition: An anthracycline obtained by hydrolysis of the methyl ester group of aclacinomycin T.

name: 15-oxo-beta-bilirubin
definition: A biladiene that is the 15-oxo derivative of beta-bilirubin.

name: N-acetyl-L-tryptophan
definition: A  N-acetyl-L-amino acid that is the N-acetyl derivative of L-tryptophan.

name: 2-methylthio-N(6)-dimethylallyladenine 5'-monophosphate residue
definition: A nucleotide residue derived from 2-methylthio-N(6)-dimethylallyladenine 5'-monophosphate with linkages at the 3'- and 5'-positions.

name: 2-methylthio-N(6)-L-threonylcarbamoyladenine 5'-monophosphate

name: N(2),N(2),N(7)-trimethylguanosine 5'-triphosphate group

name: parabanic acid
definition: An imidazolidinone that is imidazolidine which is substituted by oxo groups at positions 2, 4 and 5.

name: 2'-O-methyladenosine 5'-monophosphate residue
definition: A nucleotide residue derived from 2'-O-methyladenosine 5'-monophosphate.

name: 1-(9Z)-octadecenoyl-2-(9Z)-hexadecenoyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphate(2-)

name: Met-beta-Ala

name: Met-Gln

name: Phe-beta-Ala

name: 3,6-diaminoacridine(1+)

name: Phe-Glu
definition: A dipeptide formed from L-phenylalanine and L-glutamic acid residues.

name: Phe-Gly-Gly
definition: A tripeptide composed of one L-phenylalanine and two glycine residues joined in sequence.

name: Phe-Met
definition: A dipeptide formed from L-phenylalanine and L-methionine residues.

name: 3,6-diamino-10-methylacridinium chloride.HCl
definition: A hydrochloride resulting from the reaction of equimolar amounts of 3,6-diamino-10-methylacridinium chloride and hydrogen chloride.

name: N(3)-methylpseudouridine 5'-monophosphate residue
definition: A nucleotide residue derived from N(3)-methylpseudouridine 5'-monophosphate.

name: N(1)-methyladenosine 5'-monophosphate residue
definition: A nucleotide residue derived from N(1)-methyladenosine 5'-monophosphate.

name: N(6),N(6)-dimethyladenosine 5'-monophosphate residue
definition: A nucleotide residue derived from N,N-dimethyladenosine 5'-monophosphate.

name: 5-methyl-imidazole-4-carboxylic acid
definition: An imidazolyl carboxylic acid that is 1H-imidazole with methyl and carboxylic acid group substituents at positions 5 and 4 respectively.

name: dTT(6-4)TT
definition: A single-stranded DNA oligonucleotide containing four consecutive thymidyl residues, T1, T2, T3 and T4, arranged in the direction from the 5'-terminus to the 3'-terminus, with a (6-4) lesion at the central T2 and T3 residues.

name: Phe-Trp
definition: A dipeptide formed from L-phenylalanine and L-tryptophan residues.

name: Pro-Asn
definition: A dipeptide formed from L-proline and L-asparagine residues.

name: aclacinomycin T(1+)
definition: A quaternary ammonium ion resulting from the protonation of the amino group of aclacinomycin T. The major species at pH 7.3.

name: alpha-methylhistamine
definition: An aralkylamino compound that is histamine bearing a methyl substituent at the alpha-position.

name: Cys-tRNA(Sec) polyanion
definition: A polyanionic polymer obtained by global deprotonation of the phosphate OH groups of Cys-tRNA(Sec).

name: 1,5-dimethyluracil
definition: A pyrimidone that is uracil with methyl group substituents at positions 1 and 5.

name: aluminium sulfate

name: Ser-Asp

name: delphinidin 3-O-beta-D-sambubioside

name: Ser-Leu
definition: A dipeptide formed from L-serine and L-leucine residues.

name: heteroaryl hydroxy compound
definition: Any organic aromatic compound having one or more hydroxy groups attached to a heteroarene ring.

name: 12-aminolauroyl tripalmitoyl cardiolipin diammonium salt

name: 1-oleoyl-2-linoleoyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphate

name: 2,3-bis-O-phytanyl-sn-glycero-3-phospho-L-serine(1-)

name: GCB

name: Trp-Trp

name: 1-dodecylguanidine
definition: A member of the class of guanidines that is guanidine in which one of the amino groups is substituted by a dodecyl group. It is used (generally as its acetate salt, known as dodine) as a agrochemical fungicide.

name: Tyr-Glu
definition: A dipeptide formed from L-tyrosine and L-glutamic acid residues.

name: 1-dodecylguanidine(1+)
definition: A guanidinium ion resulting from the protonation of the imino nitrogen of 1-dodecylguanidine. The major species at pH 7.3.

name: 1-dodecylguanidine acetate
definition: An acetate salt resulting from the reaction of equimolar amounts of 1-dodecylguanidine and acetic acid. It is used as a fungicide to control black spot and foliar diseases on apples, pears, peaches, nectarines and strawberries.

name: N(3)-methylcytidine 5'-monophosphate(1-) residue

name: 1-oleoyl-2-palmitoyl-sn-glycero-3-phospho-L-serine(1-)
definition: A phosphatidylserine 34:1 that is the conjugate base of 1-oleoyl-2-palmitoyl-sn-glycero-3-phospho-L-serine, in which the carboxy and phosphate groups are anionic and the amino group is cationic.

name: 1-acyl-2-linoleoyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphate(2-)
definition: A 1,2-diacyl-sn-glycerol 3-phosphate(2-) obtained by deprotonation of the phosphate OH groups of any 1-acyl-2-linoleoyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphate.

name: patulin
definition: A furopyran and lactone that is (2H-pyran-3(6H)-ylidene)acetic acid which is substituted by hydroxy groups at positions 2 and 4 and in which the hydroxy group at position 4 has condensed with the carboxy group to give the corresponding bicyclic lactone. A mycotoxin produced by several species of Aspergillus and Penicillium, it has antibiotic properties but has been shown to be carcinogenic and mutagenic.

name: tetracenomycin D3(1-)
definition: A hydroxy monocarboxylic acid anion that is the conjugate base of tetracenomycin F1, obtained by deprotonation of the carboxy group.

name: 1-oleoyl-2-icosanoyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphate(2-)
definition: A 1,2-diacyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphate(2-) obtained by deprotonation of the phosphate OH groups of 1-oleoyl-2-icosanoyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphate.

name: 1,5-bis(diphospho)-1D-myo-inositol 2,3,4,6-tetrakisphosphate(14-)

name: 2-(2,6-dioxopiperidin-3-yl)-1H-isoindole-1,3(2H)-dione
definition: A dicarboximide that is isoindole-1,3(2H)-dione in which the hydrogen attached to the nitrogen is substituted by a 2,6-dioxopiperidin-3-yl group.

name: d(pT)3
definition: A single-stranded DNA oligonucleotide composed of three deoxythymidylic acid residues connected by 3'->5' phosphodiester linkages and terminated by a 5'-phosphate.

name: O(4)-phospho-D-tyrosine
definition: A D-tyrosine derivative that is D-tyrosine phosphorylated at the phenolic hydroxy group.

name: 1-lauroyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphocholine
definition: A 1-O-acyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphocholine in which the acyl group is specified as lauroyl (dodecanoyl)

name: 1-oleoyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphoethanolamine zwitterion
definition: A 1-acyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphoethanolamine zwitterion obtained by transfer of a proton from the amino to the phosphate group of 1-oleoyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphoethanolamine.

name: ginsenoside
definition: Triterpenoid saponins with a dammarane-like skeleton originally isolated from ginseng (Panax) species. Use of the term has been extended to include semi-synthetic derivatives.

name: beta-D-Glcp-(1->3)-[beta-D-Glcp-(1->3)-beta-D-GalpNAc-(1->4)-alpha-D-Glcp-(1->4)]-beta-D-GalpNAc-(1->3)-alpha-D-Manp
definition: An amino hexasaccharide comprising beta-D-glucose, N-acetyl-beta-D-galactosamine, alpha-D-glucose, N-acetyl-beta-D-galactosamine and alpha-D-mannose residues in (1->3), (1->4), (1->4) and (1->3) sequence, to the N-acetyl-beta-D-galactosamine residue contiguous to the reducing-end mannose residue of which is also linked (1->3) a further beta-D-glucose residue.

name: 1,2-dioleoyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphoethanolamine zwitterion
definition: A phosphatidylethanolamine 36:2 obtained by transfer of a proton from the amino to the phosphate group of 1,2-dioleoyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphoethanolamine.

name: Tyr-Val
definition: A dipeptide formed from L-tyrosine and L-valine residues.

name: Val-Gln
definition: A dipeptide formed from L-valine and L-glutamine residues.

name: Val-Glu
definition: A dipeptide formed from L-valine and L-glutamic acid residues.

name: Val-Leu
definition: A dipeptide formed from L-valine and L-leucine residues.

name: Val-Lys
definition: A dipeptide formed from L-valine and L-lysine residues.

name: Val-Met
definition: A dipeptide formed from L-valine and L-methionine residues.

name: Ins-1-P-6-Man-1-6-Ins-1-P-Cer B/B' 46:0(2-)
definition: An Ins-1-P-6-Man-1-6-Ins-1-P-Cer B/B'(2-) in which the acyl group and the ceramide base contain a total of 46 carbons and 0 double bonds, with either the acyl group hydroxylated at position 2 or the ceramide base hydroxylated at position 4.

name: Ins-1-P-6-Man-1-6-Ins-1-P-Cer C 46:0(2-)
definition: An Ins-1-P-6-Man-1-6-Ins-1-P-Cer C(2-) in which the acyl group and the ceramide base contain a total of 46 carbons and 0 double bonds, with the acyl group hydroxylated at position 2 and the ceramide base hydroxylated at position 4.

name: phleomycin D1
definition: A glycopeptide originally isolated from the bacterium Streptomyces verticillus which contains a (4'R)-4',5'-dihydro-2,4'-bi-1,3-thiazole-2',4-diyl moiety with a a 4-guanidylbutylaminocarbonyl group attached to the 4-position of the terminal thiazole ring. Like all phleomycins, phleomycin D1 can form complexes with redox-active metals such as Co, Cu, and Fe.

name: 4-nitrophenyl phthalimidoacetate
definition: A carboxylic ester obtained by formal condensation of the carboxy group of phthalimidoacetic acid with the phenolic hydroxy group of 4-nitrophenol.

name: N(3)-methylcytidine 5'-monophosphate residue
definition: A nucleotide residue derived from N(3)-methylcytidine 5'-monophosphate.

name: tridecanoic-d25 acid
definition: A C13 straight-chain saturated fatty acid where the aliphatic hydrogens have been replaced by deuterium atoms.

name: 10-pentadecenoic acid
definition: A pentadecenoic acid having its double bond in the 10-position.

name: trans-10-pentadecenoic acid
definition: The trans-isomer of pentadec-10-enoic acid.

name: aclacinomycin Y

name: 1-oleoyl-2-nonadecanoyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphate(2-)

name: linoelaidic acid
definition: An octadecadienoic acid containing two E (trans) double bonds at positions 9 and 12.

name: (6Z)-octadecenoyl-CoA(4-)
definition: An octadecenoyl-CoA(4-) obtained by deprotonation of the phosphate and diphosphate OH groups of (6E)-octadecenoyl-CoA.

name: alpha-N-acetylneuraminyl-(2->3)-D-galactosyl group
definition: A galactosyl group derived from the disaccharide alpha-N-acetylneuraminyl-(2->3)-D-galactose. Implied reactive epitope within gangliosides LM1, GD1a and GT1b.

name: alpha-N-acetylneuraminyl-(2->8)-alpha-N-acetylneuraminyl group
definition: A sialosyl group derived from the disaccharide alpha-N-acetylneuraminyl-(2->8)-alpha-N-acetylneuraminic acid.

name: (1S,2S)-1-phenyl-2-palmitoylamino-3-morpholino-1-propanol
definition: An N-[1-hydroxy-3-(morpholin-4-yl)-1-phenylpropan-2-yl]hexadecanamide in which both stereocentres have S configuration.

name: 5'-d[GCGAGTGAT(6-4)TATGGACGG]-3'

name: 2-aminooctanoic acid

name: dT5

name: tetrazolium violet(1+)

name: 2-linoleoyl-2'-monolysocardiolipin(2-)

name: 1-acyl-2-octanoyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphoethanolamine zwitterion
definition: A 1,2-diacyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphoethanolamine zwitterion in which the 2-acyl group is specified as octanoyl while the 1-acyl group remains unspecified.

name: splitomicin
definition: A benzochromenone that is 2,3-dihydro-1H-benzo[f]chromene substituted by an oxo group at position 3. It has been found to exhibit potential inhibitory activity against Sir2 proteins.

name: tetradecyl sulfate
definition: An organosulfate oxoanion that is the conjugate base of tetradecyl sulfonic acid, obtained by deprotonation of the O-sulfo group.

name: ikarugamycin
definition: A polyketide macrolactam containing a tetramic acid (pyrrolidine-2,4-dione) ring system. It is isolated from Streptomyces as an antibiotic with  antiprotozoal and cytotoxic activities.

name: N-acetyl-D-glucosaminitol
definition: A 2-deoxyhexitol derivative that is D-glucitol in which the 2-hydroxy substituent is replaced by an acetamido group.

name: ergosterol biosynthesis inhibitor
definition: Any compound that inhibits one or more steps in the pathway leading to the synthesis of ergosterol.

name: (R)-2-(4-chloro-2-methylphenoxy)propanoate
definition: A monocarboxylic acid anion that is the conjugate base of (R)-2-(4-chloro-2-methylphenoxy)propanoic acid, obtained by deprotonation of the carboxy group.

name: (S)-dichlorprop(1-)
definition: A monocarboxylic acid anion resulting from the removal of a proton from the carboxy group of (S)-dichlorprop. The major species at pH 7.3

name: compound 48/80
definition: R1, R2 = H or CH2OH; n is normally between 1 and 10. An alternating copolymer resulting from the condensation of N,O-dimethyltyramine with formaldehyde. It is a potent histamine releasing agent, primarily from mast cells, with subsequent depletion of tissue histamine.

name: 1-palmitoyl-2-capryloyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphocholine
definition: A  phosphatidylcholine 24:0 where the acyl groups at position 1 and 2 are palmitoyl and capryloyl respectively.

name: excipient
definition: A generally pharmacologically inactive substance that is formulated with the active ingredient of a medication.

name: (8S,9S)-epoxy-(10R)-hydroxyicosa-(5Z,11Z,14Z)-trienoate
definition: An unsaturated fatty acid anion that is the conjugate base of (8S,9S)-epoxy-(10R)-hydroxyicosa-(5Z,11Z,14Z)-trienoic acid, obtained by deprotonation of the carboxy group.

name: 1-(2,4-dichlorobenzoyl)-1H-1,2,3-benzotriazole
definition: A member of the class of  benzamides that is obtained by the formal condensation of  2,4-dichlorobenzoic acid and  benzotriazole. It acts as an inhibitor for tubulin acetylation mediated by trichostatin A.

name: 1-(10Z)-heptadecenoyl-sn-glycero-3-phospho-1D-myo-inositol
definition: A 1-acyl-sn-glycero-3-phospho-1D-myo-inositol in which the 1-acyl group is specified as (10Z)-heptadecenoyl.

name: 3-[(4-bromophenyl)amino]-3-(4-methoxyphenyl)-1-phenylpropan-1-one
definition: An aromatic ketone that is propiophenone substituted at position 3 by (4-bromophenyl)amino and 4-methoxyphenyl groups respectively.

name: N-[2-(4-ethylphenyl)-1,3-benzoxazol-5-yl]-3-nitrobenzamide
definition: A member of the class of 1,3-benzoxazoles that is 1,3-benzoxazole substituted at positions 2 and 5 by 4-ethylphenyl and 3-nitrobenzamido groups respectively.

name: EC 1.11.1.* (peroxidases) inhibitor
definition: An EC 1.11.* (oxidoreductase acting on peroxide as donors) inhibitor that interferes with the action of any of the peroxidases (EC 1.11.1.*).

name: (R)-monastrol
definition: An ethyl 4-(3-hydroxyphenyl)-6-methyl-2-thioxo-1,2,3,4-tetrahydropyrimidine-5-carboxylate that has R configuration.

name: N-acetyl-beta-D-glucosaminyl-(1->4)-alpha-D-mannose
definition: An amino disaccharide comprised of N-acetyl-beta-D-glucosamine linked (1->4) to D-mannose.

name: quinpirole
definition: A pyrazoloquinoline that is  (4aR,8aR)-4,4a,5,6,7,8,8a,9-octahydro-1H-pyrazolo[3,4-g]quinoline substituted by a propyl group at position 5. It acts as a dopamine agonist.

name: tyrphostin AG 1478
definition: A member of the class of  quinazolines that is quinazoline substituted by methoxy groups at positions 6 and 7 and a (3-chlorophenyl)nitrilo group at position 4. It acts as an  epidermal growth factor receptor antagonist.

name: 2-methyl-6-phytylhydroquinone
definition: A member of the class of hydroquinones that is 2-methylbenzene-1,4-diol substituted by a phytyl group at position 6.

name: iodonitrotetrazolium
