definition: An organic cation that is the cationic component of iodonitrotetrazolium violet.

name: 5-bromo-4-chloro-3-indolyl beta-D-glucoside
definition: An indolyl carbohydrate that is the beta-D-glucoside of 3-hydroxy-1H-indole in which the indole moiety is substituted at positions 4 and 5 by chlorine and bromine, respectively. It is used to test for the presence of an enzyme, beta-glucosidase, which cleaves the glycosidic bond to give 5-bromo-4-chloro-3-hydroxy-1H-indole, which immediately dimerises to give an intensely blue product.

name: 2-palmitoylglycerol
definition: A 2-monoglyceride where the acyl group is hexadecanoyl (palmitoyl).

name: carbonyl cyanide p-trifluoromethoxyphenylhydrazone
definition: A hydrazone that is hydrazonomalononitrile in which one of the hydrazine hydrogens is substituted by a p-trifluoromethoxyphenyl group.

name: 4'-O-beta-glucosyl-7-O-(6-O-sinapoylglucosyl)tricin
definition: A glycosyloxyflavone that is tricin substituted at positions 4 and 7 by beta-glucosyl 6-O-sinapoylglucosyl residues respectively.

name: 1-octanoyl-2-oleoyl-sn-glycerol
definition: A 1,2-diacyl-sn-glycerol where octanoyl and oleoyl form the 1- and 2-acyl groups respectively.

name: 1-myristoyl-2-oleoyl-sn-glycerol
definition: A  1,2-diacyl-sn-glycerol that has myristoyl and oleoyl as 1- and 2-acyl groups respectively.

name: Ins-1-P-Cer-A 34:0(1-)
definition: An Ins-1-P-Cer A(1-) in which the acyl group and the ceramide base contain a total of 34 carbons and 0 double bonds. Major species at pH 7.3.

name: elaidylphosphocholine
definition: A phosphocholine that is the mono-1-elaidyl ester of phosphocholine

name: 5-O-sinapoylquinic acid
definition: A cinnamate ester obtained by formal condensation of the carboxy group of sinapic acid with the 5-hydroxy group of (-)-quinic acid.

name: 5-bromo-4-chloro-3-indolyl alpha-D-galactoside
definition: An indolyl carbohydrate that is the alpha-D-galactoside of indoxyl in which the indole moiety is substituted at positions 4 and 5 by chlorine and bromine, respectively.

name: 3-dehydropyranoside
definition: Any alicyclic ketone resulting from the formal oxidation of the hydroxy group at position 3 of any pyranoside to the corresponding keto group.

name: 7-O-(6-p-coumaroylglucosyl)chrysoeriol
definition: A glycosyloxyflavone that is chrysoeriol in which the hydroxyl hydrogen at position 7 is replaced by a 6-p-coumaroylglucosyl residue.

name: isoorientin 7-O-glucoside
definition: A C-glycosyl compound that is isoorientin in which the hydroxyl hydrogen at position 7 is replaced by a glucosyl residue.

name: thiosulfonate ester
definition: An organosulfur compound with the formula RSO2SR.

name: rac-1-monoacylglycerol
definition: A racemate that is composed of equal amounts of 1-acyl-sn-glycerol and 3-acyl-sn-glycerol.

name: 2-keto-3-deoxy-L-galactonate
definition: A carbohydrate acid anion that is the conjugate base of 2-keto-3-deoxy-L-galactonic acid, obtained by deprotonation of the carboxy group.

name: 1-alpha-linolenoyl-sn-glycerol
definition: A 1-acyl-sn-glycerol where alpha-linolenoyl is the 1-acyl group.

name: 3-alpha-linolenoyl-sn-glycerol
definition: A  3-acyl-sn-glycerol where alpha-linolenoyl is the 3-acyl group.

name: dT10
definition: An oligonucleotide comprised of ten thymidine residues connected via 3'->5' phosphodiester linkages.

name: EC 6.3.2.2 (glutamate--cysteine ligase) inhibitor
definition: An acid--amino-acid ligase inhibitor that inhibits the action of a glutamate--cysteine ligase (EC 6.3.2.2)

name: dT4
definition: An oligonucleotide comprised of four thymidine residues connected via 3'->5' phosphodiester linkages.

name: EC 6.5.* (phosphoric ester bond-forming ligase) inhibitor
definition: A ligase inhibitor which inhibits the action of a phosphoric ester bond-forming ligase (EC 6.5.*.*).

name: poly(5-bromo-2'-deoxyuridylic acid)
definition: A polynucleotide comprised of 5-bromo-2'-deoxyuridine units connected via 3'->5' phosphodiester linkages.

name: 1-arachidonoylglycerol
definition: A 1-monoglyceride where the acyl group is arachidonoyl.

name: N(3')-acetylgentamycin C(4+)
definition: An organic cation obtained by protonation of the four amino groups of any N(3')-acetylgentamicin C.

name: icosan-1-ol
definition: A fatty alcohol consisting of a hydroxy function at C-1 of an unbranched saturated chain of 20 carbon atoms.

name: palmityl stearate
definition: A  wax ester obtained by the formal condensation of palmityl alcohol with stearic acid.

name: holothurin A4(1-)
definition: A organosulfate oxoanion obtained by the deprotonation of the sulfo group of holothurin A4 acid.

name: 5-(2-methoxy-2-oxoethyl)uridine 5'-monophosphate residue
definition: A nucleotide residue derived from  5-(2-methoxy-2-oxoethyl)uridine 5'-monophosphate.

name: (-)-epicatechin-(4beta->8)-(-)-epigallocatechin
definition: A proanthocyanidin consisting of (-)-epicatechin and (-)-epigallocatechin units joined by a (4beta->8)-linkage.

name: (+)-catechin-(4alpha->6)-(+)-gallocatechin
definition: A proanthocyanidin consisting of (+)-catechin and (+)-gallocatechin units joined by a (4alpha->6)-linkage.

name: delphinidin 3-O-(6-O-(E)-4-coumaroyl-beta-D-glucoside)
definition: An anthocyanin cation that is delphinidin substituted at position 3 by a 6-O-(trans-4 coumaryl)-beta-D-glucosyl residue

name: delphinidin 3-O-(6-O-acetyl-beta-D-glucoside)
definition: An anthocyanin cation that is delphinidin substituted at position 3 by a 6-O-acetyl-beta-D-glucosyl residue.

name: (8R)-hydroxy-(11R,12R)-epoxyicosa-(5Z,9E,14Z)-trienoic acid
definition: An epoxy(hydroxy)icosatrienoic acid consisting of (5Z,9E,14Z)-icosa-5,9,14-trienoic acid having additional (8R)-hydroxy- and (11R,12R)-epoxy groups.

name: dC21
definition: An oligonucleotide comprised of 21 2'-deoxycytidine residues connected via 3'->5' phosphodiester linkages.

name: peonidin 3-O-(6-O-acetyl-beta-D-glucoside)
definition: An anthocyanin cation that is peonidin substituted at position 3 by a 6-O-acetyl-beta-D-glucosyl residue.

name: dU5
definition: An oligonucleotide comprised of five 2-deoxyuridine residues connected via 3'->5' phosphodiester linkages.

name: peonidin 3-O-(6-O-(E)-4-coumaroyl-beta-D-glucoside)
definition: An anthocyanin cation that is peonidin substituted at position 3 by a 6-O-(trans-4 coumaryl)-beta-D-glucosyl residue

name: dT12
definition: An oligonucleotide comprised of twelve thymidine residues connected via 3'->5' phosphodiester linkages.

name: dUMP 3'-end residue
definition: The 3'-end bound-monomer of a uridylyl-5'-monophosphoric acid that is part of a nucleic acid.

name: (R,R)-tramadol(1+)
definition: An organic cation obtained by protonation of the tertiary amino group of (R,R)-tramadol.

name: (-)-taxifolin 3-O-beta-D-xylopyranoside
definition: A flavanone glycoside that is (-)-taxifolin substituted by a beta-D-xylopyranosyl residue at position 3.

name: (+)-epitaxifolin 3-O-alpha-D-arabinopyranoside
definition: A flavanone glycoside that is (+)-epitaxifolin substituted by an alpha-D-arabinopyranosyl residue at position 3.

name: (-)-epitaxifolin
definition: A taxifolin that has (2R,3S)-configuration.

name: eukaryotic metabolite
definition: Any  metabolite produced during a metabolic reaction in eukaryotes, the taxon that include members of the fungi, plantae and animalia kingdoms.

name: isorhamnetin 4'-O-beta-D-glucopyranoside
definition: A glycosyloxyflavone that is isorhamnetin substituted at position 4' by a beta-D-glucosyl residue.

name: kaempferol 7-O-beta-D-galactopyranoside
definition: A glycosyloxyflavone that is kaempferol attached to a beta-D-galactopyranosyl moiety at position 7 via a glycosidic linkage.

name: myricetin 3-O-beta-D-glucopyranoside
definition: A myricetin O-glucoside that is myricetin with a beta-D-glucosyl residue attached at position 3.

name: myricetin 3-O-alpha-L-glucopyranoside
definition: A myricetin O-glucoside that is myricetin with a alpha-L-glucosyl residue attached at position 3.

name: 5'-CTGCAGAATTCTGGTACCA-3'
definition: A single-stranded DNA oligonucleotide comprised of five deoxyadenosine, five deoxycytidine, five thymidine and four deoxyguanidine residues connected by 3'->5' phosphodiester linkages in the sequence CTGCAGAATTCTGGTACCA.

name: (8E,10S,12Z)-10-hydroperoxyoctadeca-8,12-dienoic acid
definition: (8E,12Z)-10-hydroperoxy-8,12-octadecadienoic acid with S-configuration at C-10.

name: phytyl phosphate
definition: A polyprenol phosphate that is the monophosphate derivative of phytol.

name: 1-palmitoyl-2,3-dioleoyl-sn-glycerol
definition: The R-enantiomer of 1,2-dioleoyl-3-palmitoylglycerol.

name: 1,3-dilinolenoylglycerol
definition: A 1,3-diglyceride in which both acyl groups are specified as linolenoyl.

name: 3-methylfumaryl-CoA
definition: An omega-carboxyacyl-CoA that results from the formal condensation of the thiol group of coenzyme A with the least hindered carboxy group of mesaconic acid.

name: 1-oleoyl-3-palmitoyl-sn-glycerol
definition: A 1,3-diglyceride in which the acyl groups at positions 1 and 3 are specified as oleoyl and palmitoyl respectively (the S-stereoisomer).

name: 4-O-(beta-L-Araf)-cis-L-Hyp zwitterion
definition: An amino acid zwitterion obtained by transfer of a proton from the carboxy to the amino group of 4-O-(beta-L-Araf)-cis-L-Hyp.

name: alpha-D-rhamnoside
definition: Any rhamnoside that exists in the pyranose form and has alpha-D-configuration.

name: 5'-CTGC-3'
definition: A single-stranded DNA oligonucleotide comprised of one thymidine, one deoxyguanidine and two deoxycytidine residues connected by 3'->5' phosphodiester linkages in the sequence CTGC.

name: arsenic(1-) sulfides
definition: Any member of the class of arsenic sulfides in which the arsenic is in the (1-) oxidation state.

name: (R,R)-2-methyl-6-phytylhydroquinone
definition: The (R,R)-stereoisomer of 2-methyl-6-phytylhydroquinone.

name: 4-hydroxy-2-quinolone
definition: A heteroaryl hydroxy compound that is 2-quinolone substituted at position 4 by a hydroxy group.

name: (S)-2-hydroxyhexadecanoate
definition: The S-enantiomer of 2-hydroxypalmitate.

name: 3,4-didehydropyranoside(1-)
definition: An organic anion obtained by deprotonation of the enolic hydroxy group at position 3 of any 3,4-didehydropyranoside. It is the major species at pH 7.3. (according to MarvinSketch version 16.1.18.0).

name: (R)-2-hydroxylignocerate
definition: A hydroxy fatty acid anion that is the conjugate base of (R)-2-hydroxylignoceric acid, obtained by deprotonation of the carboxy group.

name: 5'-GTAACCGAAATCGGTTGA-3'
definition: A single-stranded DNA oligonucleotide comprised of six deoxyadenosine, three deoxycytidine, four thymidine and five deoxyguanidine residues connected by 3'->5' phosphodiester linkages in the sequence GTAACCGAAATCGGTTGA.

name: rac-1-oleoyl-3-palmitoylglycerol
definition: A racemate comprising equimolar amounts of 1-palmitoyl-3-oleoyl-sn-glycerol and 1-oleoyl-3-palmitoyl-sn-glycerol.

name: 1-(3-O-sulfo-beta-D-galactosyl)-N-[(2R)-2-hydroxybehenoyl]sphingosine(1-)
definition: A galactosylceramide sulfate(1-) in which the ceramide N-acyl group is specified as (R)-2-hydroxybehenoyl.

name: 1-(beta-D-galactosyl)-N-[(2R)-2-hydroxybehenoyl]sphingosine
definition: A D-galactosyl-N-acylsphingosine in which the ceramide N-acyl group is specified as (R)-2-hydroxybehenoyl.

name: double-stranded DNA polynucleotide
definition: A nucleobase-containing molecular entity with a polymeric structure comprised of two complementary DNA polynucleotide strands linked by hydrogen bonding.

name: single-stranded DNA polynucleotide
definition: A polynucleotide consisting of deoxyribonucleotide residues connected by phosphodiester linkages.

name: 2-capryloyl-2'-monolysocardiolipin(2-)
definition: A 2-monolysocardiolipin(2-) obtained by deprotonation of both free phosphate OH groups of 2-capryloyl-2'-monolysocardiolipin.

name: 2-arachidonoyl-2'-monolysocardiolipin(2-)
definition: A 2-monolysocardiolipin(2-) obtained by deprotonation of both free phosphate OH groups of 2-arachidonoyl-2'-monolysocardiolipin.

name: (S)-laudanine(1+)
definition: The (S)-enantiomer of laudanine(1+).

name: alpha-D-GalNAc-(1->2)-beta-D-Man-(1->4)-[beta-D-Glc-(1->2)]-alpha-D-Man-(1->5)-alpha-Kdo
definition: A branched amino pentasaccharide consisting of an N-acetyl-alpha-D-galactosaminyl-(1->2)-beta-D-mannosyl-(1->4)-alpha-D-mannosyl-(1->5)-3-deoxy-alpha-D-manno-oct-2-ulosonic acid tetrasaccharide chain, to the alpha-D-mannosyl residue of which is also linked beta(1->2) a D-glucosyl residue. Epitope of Francisella tularensis.

name: dolutegravir(1-)
definition: An organic anion that is the conjugate base of dolutegravir, obtained by deptotonation of the 7-hydroxy group.

name: vortioxetine(1+)
definition: An organic cation that is the conjugate acid of vortioxetine, obtained by protonation of the secondary amino function.

name: riociguat
definition: A carbamate ester that is the methyl ester of {4,6-diamino-2-[1-(2-fluorobenzyl)-1H-pyrazolo[3,4-b]pyridin-3-yl]pyrimidin-5-yl}methylcarbamic acid. It is used for treatment of chronic thromboembolic pulmonary hypertension and pulmonary arterial hypertension

name: poly[d(GAA)]
definition: A single-stranded DNA polynucleotide consisting of a repeating sequence of one deoxyguanosine residue and two deoxycytosine residues, with all residues connected by 3'->5' phosphodiester linkages.

name: dotriacontanoate
definition: An ultra-long-chain fatty acid anion that is the conjugate base of dotriacontanoic acid (lacceroic acid), obtained by deprotonation of the carboxy group.

name: poly(deoxyguanylic acid)
definition: A polynucleotide comprised of 2'-deoxyguanosine units connected via 3'->5' phosphodiester linkages.

name: glutamic acid-2,3,3,4,4-d5
definition: A deuterated compound that is glutamic acid in which the hydrogens at positions 2, 3, 3, 4 and 4 are replaced by deuterium.

name: 1-palmityl-2-acetyl-3-oleoyl-sn-glycerol
definition: A 1-alkyl-2-acetyl-3-acyl-sn-glycerol in which the alkyl and acyl groups are specified as palmityl and oleoyl.

name: 2-oleoyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphocholine
definition: A lysophosphatidylcholine 18:1 in which the acyl group is specified as oleoyl and is located at position 2.

name: 2-(4Z,7Z,10Z,13Z,16Z,19Z)-docosahexaenoyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphocholine
definition: A lysophosphatidylcholine 22:6 in which the acyl group is specified as (4Z,7Z,10Z,13Z,16Z,19Z)-docosahexaenoyl and is located at position 2.

name: 5'-AATTCAA-3'
definition: A single-stranded DNA oligonucleotide comprised of four deoxyadenosine, two thymidine residues and one deoxycytidine residue connected by 3'->5' phosphodiester linkages in the sequence AATTCAA.

name: cis-ferulic acid
definition: A ferulic acid consisting of cis-cinnamic acid bearing methoxy and hydroxy substituents at positions 3 and 4 respectively on the phenyl ring.

name: tryptophan N-glucoside
definition: A L-tryptophan derivative that is L-tryptophan in which the hydrogen attached to the indole nitrogen replaced by a beta-D-glucosyl residue.

name: bumadizone calcium hemihydrate
definition: A hydrate that is the hemihydrate form of bumadizone calcium. Used for treatment of rheumatoid arthritis.

name: (-)-catechin-3-O-gallate
definition: A gallate ester obtained by formal condensation of the carboxy group of gallic acid with the (3R)-hydroxy group of (-)-catechin.

name: (+)-catechin-3-O-gallate
definition: A gallate ester obtained by formal condensation of the carboxy group of gallic acid with the (3S)-hydroxy group of (+)-catechin.

name: (2R,3S)-cis-epsilon-viniferin
definition: A stilbenoid that is the (2R,3S)-cis-stereoisomer of epsilon-viniferin, obtained by cyclodimerisation of cis-resveratrol.

name: (2S,3S)-cis-delta-viniferin
definition: A stilbenoid that is the (2S,3S)-cis-stereoisomer of delta-viniferin, obtained by cyclodimerisation of cis-resveratrol.

name: flunoxaprofen
definition: A monocarboxylic acid that is propionic acid substituted at position 2 by a 2-(4-chlorophenyl)-1,3-benzoxazol-5-yl group (the S-enantiomer). Although it was shown to be effective in treatment of rheumatoid arthritis and osteoarthritis, the clinical use of flunoxaprofen was discontinued due to possible hepatotoxic side-effects.

name: cis-astringin
definition: A stilbenoid that is cis-3,5,3',4'-tetrahydroxystilbene substituted at position 3 by a beta-D-glucosyl residue.

name: ibufenac
definition: A monocarboxylic acid that is acetic acid in which one of the methyl hydrogens is replaced by a 4-isobutylphenyl group. Although it was shown to be effective in treatment of rheumatoid arthritis, the clinical use of ibufenac was discontinued due to hepatotoxic side-effects.

name: lonazolac
definition: A monocarboxylic acid that is acetic acid in which one of the methyl hydrogens is replaced by a 3-(4-chlorophenyl)-1-phenylpyrazol-4-yl group.

name: (2R)-2-hydroxy fatty acid anion
definition: A 2-hydroxy fatty acid anion obtained by deprotonation of the carboxy group of any (R)-2-hydroxy fatty acid.

name: omega-3-arachidonoyl bioconjugate
definition: A bioconjugate obtained by coupling of omega-3-arachidonic acid to another biomolecule (e.g. coenzyme A, an acyl-carrier protein, a phospholipid, an oligosaccharide, a nucleic acid etc.), which for the sake of convenience, is represented by an R group.

name: ampelopsin B
definition: A heterotetracyclic stilbenoid that is a homodimer obtained by cyclodimerisation of resveratrol.

name: sapienate
definition: A long-chain unsaturated fatty acid anion that is the conjugate base of sapienic acid, obtained by deprotonation of the carboxy group.

name: sodium sulfide nonahydrate
definition: A hydrate with formula Na2S.9H2O.

name: N-hexanoyldihydroceramide
definition: A dihydroceramide in which the ceramide N-acyl group is specified as hexanoyl.

name: 4-hydroxy-2,5-dimethylfuran-3-one
definition: A member of the class of furans that is 2,5-dimethylfuran carrying additional oxo and hydroxy groups at positions 3 and 4 respectively. It has been found particularly in strawberries and other such fruits.

name: tepoxalin
definition: A hydroxamic acid obtained by formal condensation of the carboxy group of 3-[5-(4-chlorophenyl)-1-(4-methoxyphenyl)pyrazol-3-yl]propanoic acid with the amino group of N-methylhydroxylamine. It is used in veterinary medicine for the control of pain and inflammation caused by musculoskeletal disorders such as hip dysplasia and arthritis in dogs.

name: 22-oxodocosanoate
definition: An oxo fatty acid anion that is the conjugate base of 22-ketodocosanoic acid, obtained by deprotonation of the carboxy group; major species at pH 7.3.

name: docosanedioate(2-)
definition: A dicarboxylic acid dianion obtained by deprotonation of both carboxy groups of docosanedioic acid; major species at pH 7.3.

name: omega-hydroxy fatty acid anion
definition: A hydroxy fatty acid anion obtained by deprotonation of the carboxy group of any omega-hydroxy fatty acid; major species at pH 7.3.

name: tetradecanedioic acid
definition: An alpha,omega-dicarboxylic acid that is tetradecane in which the methyl groups have been oxidised to the corresponding carboxylic acids.

name: dodecanedioyl-CoA(5-)
definition: An acyl-CoA oxoanion that is the pentaanion of dodecanedioyl-CoA, arising from deprotonation of the phosphate, diphosphate and carboxylic acid OH groups.

name: docosanedioic acid
definition: An alpha,omega-dicarboxylic acid that is docosane in which the methyl groups have been oxidised to the corresponding carboxylic acids.

name: (S)-3-hydroxyoctanedioyl-CoA(5-)
definition: An acyl-CoA oxoanion that is the pentaanion of (S)-3-hydroxyoctanedioyl-CoA, arising from deprotonation of phosphate, diphosphate and carboxylic acid functions; major species at pH 7.3.

name: 3-oxooctanedioyl-CoA(5-)
definition: An acyl-CoA oxoanion that is the pentaanion of 3-oxooctanedioyl-CoA, arising from deprotonation of phosphate, diphosphate and carboxylic acid functions; major species at pH 7.3.

name: 4-acetylaminofluorene
definition: A member of the class of acetamides that is acetamide in which one of the hydrogens attached to the nitrogen is replaced by a 9H-fluoren-4-yl group.

name: G12
definition: An oligonucleotide comprised of twelve guanosine residues connected via 3'->5' phosphodiester linkages.

name: trans-2-triacontenoyl-CoA(4-)
definition: A 2,3-trans-enoyl CoA(4-) obtained by deprotonation of the phosphate and diphosphate OH groups of trans-2-triacontenoyl-CoA; major species at pH 7.3.

name: (2E,11Z)-icosadienoyl-CoA(4-)
definition: A 2,3-trans-enoyl CoA(4-) obtained by deprotonation of the phosphate and diphosphate OH groups of (2E,11Z)-icosadienoyl-CoA; major species at pH 7.3.

name: (3R,13Z)-3-hydroxydocosenoyl-CoA(4-)
definition: A 3-hydroxy fatty acyl-CoA(4-) obtained by deprotonation of the phosphate and diphosphate OH groups of (3R,13Z)-3-hydroxydocosenoyl-CoA; major species at pH 7.3.

name: (2E,15Z)-tetracosadienoyl-CoA(4-)
definition: A 2,3-trans-enoyl CoA(4-) obtained by deprotonation of the phosphate and diphosphate OH groups of (2E,15Z)-tetracosadienoyl-CoA; major species at pH 7.3.

name: (2E,6Z,9Z,12Z,15Z,18Z)-tetracosahexaenoyl-CoA
definition: An unsaturated fatty acyl-CoA that results from the formal condensation of the thiol group of coenzyme A with the carboxy group of (2E,6Z,9Z,12Z,15Z,18Z)-tetracosahexaenoic acid.

name: (3R,17Z,20Z,23Z,26Z,29Z)-3-hydroxydotriacontapentaenoyl-CoA(4-)
definition: A 3-hydroxy fatty acyl-CoA(4-) obtained by deprotonation of the phosphate and diphosphate OH groups of (3R,17Z,20Z,23Z,26Z,29Z)-3-hydroxydotriacontapentaenoyl-CoA; major species at pH 7.3.

name: octadec-9-ynoyl-[acyl-carrier protein]
definition: An acyl-[acyl-carrier protein] in which the S-acyl group is specified as octadec-9-ynoyl.

name: 1,2-dibutyrin
definition: A dibutyrin resulting from the condensation the secondary hydroxy group and one of the primary hydroxy groups of glycerol with butyric acid.

name: (3R,7Z,10Z,13Z,16Z)-3-hydroxydocosatetraenoyl-CoA
definition: A 3-hydroxy fatty acyl-CoA that results from the formal condensation of the thiol group of coenzyme A with the carboxy group of (3R,7Z,10Z,13Z,16Z)-3-hydroxydocosatetraenoic acid.

name: dihydroisocoumarins
definition: Any member of the class of  isochromanes that is based on the skeleton of 3,4-dihydroisocoumarin and its substituted derivatives thereof.

name: (3R,17Z,20Z,23Z,26Z)-3-hydroxydotriacontatetraenoyl-CoA
definition: A 3-hydroxy fatty acyl-CoA that results from the formal condensation of the thiol group of coenzyme A with the carboxy group of (3R,17Z,20Z,23Z,26Z)-3-hydroxydotriacontatetraenoic acid.

name: polyunsaturated fatty acid anion
definition: Any unsaturated fatty acid anion containing more than one C-C unsaturated bond.  Major species at pH 7.3.

name: (2E,21Z,24Z,27Z,30Z)-hexatriacontapentaenoyl-CoA
definition: An unsaturated fatty acyl-CoA that results from the formal condensation of the thiol group of coenzyme A with the carboxy group of (2E,21Z,24Z,27Z,30Z)-hexatriacontapentaenoic acid.

name: 6-(hydroxymethyl)-8-(1-D-ribityl)lumazine
definition: The pteridine that is lumazine substituted with a hydroxymethyl group at C-6 and a 1-D-ribityl group at N-8.

name: 11,12-EET(1-)
definition: A polyunsaturated fatty acid anion that is the conjugate base of 11,12-EET, obtained by deprotonation of the carboxy group; major species at pH 7.3.

name: (2E,11Z,14Z,17Z)-icosatetraenoyl-CoA
definition: An unsaturated fatty acyl-CoA that results from the formal condensation of the thiol group of coenzyme A with the carboxy group of (2E,11Z,14Z,17Z)-icosatetraenoic acid.

name: (3R,7Z,10Z,13Z,16Z,19Z)-3-hydroxydocosapentaenoyl-CoA
definition: An unsaturated fatty acyl-CoA that results from the formal condensation of the thiol group of coenzyme A with the carboxy group of (3R,7Z,10Z,13Z,16Z,19Z)-3-hydroxydocosapentaenoic acid.

name: (2E,7Z,10Z,13Z,16Z,19Z)-docosahexaenoyl-CoA
definition: An unsaturated fatty acyl-CoA that results from the formal condensation of the thiol group of coenzyme A with the carboxy group of (2E,7Z,10Z,13Z,16Z,19Z)-docosahexaenoic acid.

name: astressin
definition: A 30-membered homodetic cyclic peptide comprising the sequence D-Phe-His-Leu-Leu-Arg-Glu-Val-Leu-Glu-Nle-Ala-Arg-Ala-Glu-Gln-Leu-Ala-Gln-Glu-Ala-His-Lys-Asn-Arg-Lys-Leu-Nle-Glu-Ile-Ile-NH2 cyclised by an amide bridge, formed by condensation of the side-chain carboxy group of the Glu residue at position 19 and the side-chain amino group of the Lys residue at position 22.

name: (2E,8Z,11Z,14Z,17Z,20Z,23Z)-hexacosaheptaenoyl-CoA
definition: An unsaturated fatty acyl-CoA that results from the formal condensation of the thiol group of coenzyme A with the carboxy group of (2E,8Z,11Z,14Z,17Z,20Z,23Z)-hexacosaheptaenoic acid.

name: (2E,12Z,15Z,18Z,21Z,24Z,27Z)-triacontaheptaenoyl-CoA
definition: An unsaturated fatty acyl-CoA that results from the formal condensation of the thiol group of coenzyme A with the carboxy group of (2E,12Z,15Z,18Z,21Z,24Z,27Z)-triacontaheptaenoic acid.

name: (3R,18Z,21Z,24Z,27Z,30Z,33Z)-3-hydroxyhexatriacontahexaenoyl-CoA
definition: An unsaturated fatty acyl-CoA that results from the formal condensation of the thiol group of coenzyme A with the carboxy group of (3R,18Z,21Z,24Z,27Z,30Z,33Z)-3-hydroxyhexatriacontahexaenoic acid.

name: 5'-TsGsTsGsGsGsTsTsAsAsGsAsCsTsTsTsTsTsAsCsC-3'
definition: A phosphorothioate oligonucleotide consisting of five deoxyguanosine, three deoxycytidine, four deoxyadenosine and nine thymidine residues connected by 3'->5' phosphorothioate linkages in the sequence T-G-T-G-G-G-T-T-A-A-G-A-C-T-T-T-T-T-A-C-C.

name: EC 5.3.* (intramolecular oxidoreductase) inhibitor
definition: An isomerase inhibitor that interferes with the action of an intramolecular oxidoreductase (EC 5.3.*.*).

name: EC 5.4.* (intramolecular transferase) inhibitor
definition: An isomerase inhibitor that interferes with the action of an intramolecular transferase (EC 5.4.*.*).

name: EC 6.1.* (C-O bond-forming ligase) inhibitor
definition: A ligase inhibitor that interferes with the action of a C-O bond-forming ligase (EC 6.1.*.*).

name: 2-hydroxybehenate
definition: A 2-hydroxy fatty acid anion that is the conjugate base of 2-hydroxybehenic acid, obtained by deprotonation of the carboxy group; major species at pH 7.3.

name: 2-hydroxyhexacosanoate
definition: A 2-hydroxy fatty acid anion that is the conjugate base of 2-hydroxyhexacosanoic acid (2-hydroxycerotic acid), obtained by deprotonation of the carboxy group; major species at pH 7.3.

name: EC 1.5.* (oxidoreductase acting on donor CH-NH group) inhibitor
definition: An oxidoreductase inhibitor which interferes with the action of an oxidoreductase acting on the CH-NH group of donors (EC 1.5.*.*).

name: EC 1.13.* [oxidoreductase acting on single donors with incorporation of molecular oxygen (oxygenases)] inhibitor
definition: An oxidoreductase inhibitor which interferes with the action of an oxidoreductase acting on single donors with incorporation of molecular oxygen (oxygenases), EC 1.13.*.*.

name: EC 1.16.* (oxidoreductase oxidising metal ions) inhibitor
definition: An oxidoreductase inhibitor which interferes with the action of an oxidoreductase oxidising metal ions (EC 1.16.*.*).

name: EC 1.20.* (oxidoreductase acting on P or As in donors) inhibitor
definition: An oxidoreductase inhibitor which interferes with the action of an oxidoreductase acting on  phosphorus or arsenic in donors (EC 1.20.*.*).

name: pikromycin(1+)
definition: An organic cation that is the conjugate acid of pikromycin, obtained by protonation of the tertiary amino group; major species at pH 7.3.

name: 5-O-mycaminosyltylonolide(1+)
definition: An organic cation that is the conjugate acid of 5-O-mycaminosyltylonolide, obtained by protonation of the tertiary amino group; major species at pH 7.3.

name: EC 2.7.7.* (nucleotidyltransferase) inhibitor
definition: An EC 2.7.* (P-containing group transferase) inhibitor that interferes with the action of any nucleotidyltransferase (EC 2.7.7.*).

name: EC 1.9.3.* (oxidoreductase acting on donor heme group, oxygen as acceptor) inhibitor
definition: An EC 1.9.* (oxidoreductase acting on donor heme group) inhibitor that interferes with the action of any such enzyme using oxygen as acceptor (EC 1.9.3.*).

name: EC 2.3.1.* (acyltransferase transferring other than amino-acyl group) inhibitor
definition: An EC 2.3.* (acyltransferase) inhibitor that inhibits the action of any acyltransferase transferring groups other than amino-acyl groups (EC 2.3.1.*).

name: EC 2.7.1.* (phosphotransferases with an alcohol group as acceptor) inhibitor
definition: An EC 2.7.* (P-containing group transferase) inhibitor that interferes with the action of any phosphotransferase with an alcohol group as acceptor (EC 2.7.1.*).

name: beta-D-Manp-(1->3)-beta-D-Manp-(1->3)-alpha-L-Rhap-(1->3)-beta-D-Glcp-yl group
definition: A linear tetrasaccharide glycosyl group consisting of two beta-D-mannose residues and an alpha-L-rhamnose residue linked to a glucosyl residue at the reducing end.

name: (3R,11Z)-3-hydroxyoctadecenoyl-CoA
definition: An unsaturated fatty acyl-CoA that results from the formal condensation of the thiol group of coenzyme A with the carboxy group of (3R,11Z)-3-hydroxyoctadecenoic acid.

name: EC 1.14.11.* (oxidoreductase acting on paired donors, 2-oxoglutarate as one donor, incorporating 1 atom each of oxygen into both donors) inhibitor
definition: An EC 1.14.* (oxidoreductase acting on paired donors, with incorporation or reduction of molecular oxygen) inhibitor that interferes with the function of any such enzyme using 2-oxoglutarate as one donor and incorporating one atom each of oxygen into both donors (EC 1.14.11.*).

name: (2E,11Z)-octadecadienoyl-CoA
definition: An octadecadienoyl-CoA that results from the formal condensation of the thiol group of coenzyme A with the carboxy group of (2E,11Z)-octadecadienoic acid.

name: (R)-nisoldipine
definition: A methyl 2-methylpropyl 2,6-dimethyl-4-(2-nitrophenyl)-1,4-dihydropyridine-3,5-dicarboxylate that has R configuration.

name: (-)-ent-copalol
definition: A labdane diterpenoid in which the labdane skeleton has double bonds at positions 8(17) and 13 (the latter with E-stereochemistry) and carries a hydroxy group at the terminal C-15 position.

name: 17(R),18(S)-EETeTr
definition: A 17(18)-EpETE in which the epoxy group has (17R,18S)-configuration.

name: 20-oxoarachidonic acid
definition: A polyunsaturated fatty acid that is arachidonic acid substituted at position 20 by an oxo group.

name: N-sulfonylurea
definition: A urea in which one of the hydrogens attached to a nitrogen of the urea group is replaced by a sulfonyl group. The N-sulfonylurea moiety is a key group in various herbicides, as well as in a number of antidiabetic drugs used in the management of type 2 diabetis mellitus.

name: metacetamol
definition: A derivative of phenol which has an acetamido substituent located meta to the phenolic -OH group. It is a non-toxic regioisomer of paracetamol with analgesic properties, but has never been marketed as a drug.

name: alpha-naphthoflavone
definition: An extended flavonoid resulting from the formal fusion of a benzene ring with the h side of flavone. A synthetic compound, it is an inhibitor of aromatase (EC 1.14.14.14).

name: 1-oleoyl-2-lauroyl-sn-glycero-3-phospho-(1'-sn-glycerol)(1-)
definition: A 1,2-diacyl-sn-glycero-3-phospho-(1'-sn-glycerol)(1-) obtained by deprotonation of the phosphate group of 1-oleoyl-2-lauroyl-sn-glycero-3-phospho-(1'-sn-glycerol); major species at pH 7.3.

name: 5-O-beta-D-mycaminosyl-20-oxotylonolide
definition: A macrolide antibiotic that is 20-oxotylactone having a 5-O-beta-D-mycaminosyl residue attached at position 6.

name: boron-10 atom
definition: A stable isotope of boron with relative atomic mass 10.0129370, 19.9 atom percent natural abundance and nuclear spin 3+.

name: EC 1.10.99.2 [ribosyldihydronicotinamide dehydrogenase (quinone)] inhibitor
definition: An EC 1.10.99.* (oxidoreductases acting on diphenols and related substances as donors, other acceptors) inhibitor that interferes with the action of ribosyldihydronicotinamide dehydrogenase (quinone), EC 1.10.99.2.

name: 7-deoxyloganetic acid
definition: An iridoid monoterpenoid that is 1,4a,5,6,7,7a-hexahydrocyclopenta[c]pyran-4-carboxylic acid substituted at positions 1 and 7 by hydroxy and methyl groups respectively; the aglycone of 7-deoxyloganic acid.

name: 3-(5-oxoisoxazolin-4-yl)-L-alanine
definition: A member of the class of isoxazoles that is L-alanine in which one of the methyl hydrogens is replaced by a 5-oxoisoxazolin-4-yl group.

name: (2S,3S)-beta-methylphenylalanine
definition: A  non-proteinogenic L-alpha-amino acid that is L-phenylalanine in which one of the benzyl hydrogens is replaced by a methyl group (the 3S-stereoisomer).

name: mucolytic
definition: A compound that alters the structure of mucus so as to decrease its viscosity and thereby facilitate its removal by ciliary action and expectoration. Compare with antitussives, which suppress the cough reflex, and expectorants, which are considered to increase the volume of secretions in the respiratory tract, so facilitating their removal by ciliary action and coughing.

name: A41030A
definition: A cyclic peptide antibiotic that is A47934 lacking the O-sulfo group; it is produced by a strain of Streptomyces toyocaensis.

name: (3S)-hydroxytetradecanedioyl-CoA(5-)
definition: An acyl-CoA oxoanion that is the pentaanion of (S)-3-hydroxytetradecanedioyl-CoA, arising from deprotonation of the phosphate, diphosphate and carboxylic acid functions; major species at pH 7.3.

name: (S)-bromisoval
definition: A 2-bromo-N-carbamoyl-3-methylbutanamide that has S configuration.

name: (S)-closantel
definition: An N-{5-chloro-4-[(4-chlorophenyl)(cyano)methyl]-2-methylphenyl}-2-hydroxy-3,5-diiodobenzamide that has S configuration.

name: (R)-eperisone
definition: A 1-(4-ethylphenyl)-2-methyl-3-(piperidin-1-yl)propan-1-one that has R configuration.

name: 1-palmitoyl-2-lauroyl-sn-glycero-3-phospho-(1'-sn-glycerol)
definition: A 1,2-diacyl-sn-glycero-3-phospho-(1'-sn-glycerol) in which the phosphatidyl acyl groups at positions 1 and 2 are specified as palmitoyl and lauroyl respectively.

name: 1,2-diarachidonoyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphate(2-)
definition: A 1-acyl-2-arachidonoyl-sn-glycerol 3-phosphate(2-) obtained by deprotonation of the phosphate OH groups of 1,2-diarachidonoyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphate; major species at pH 7.3.

name: 1,2-dilinoleoyl-sn-glycerol
definition: A 1,2-diacyl-sn-glycerol in which both acyl groups are specified as linoleoyl.

name: 1-stearoyl-2-arachidonoyl-sn-glycero-3-phospho-1D-myo-inositol 4,5-biphosphate(5-)
definition: A 1-phosphatidyl-1D-myo-inositol 4,5-bisphosphate(5-) obtained by deprotonation of the phosphate OH groups of 1-stearoyl-2-arachidonoyl-sn-glycero-3-phospho-1D-myo-inositol 4,5-bisphosphate; major species at pH 7.3.

name: dTDP-2,3,6-trideoxy-3-C-methyl-4-O-methyl-3-nitroso-beta-L-arabino-hexopyranose(2-)
definition: A nucleotide-sugar oxoanion obtained by deprotonation of the diphosphate OH groups of dTDP-2,3,6-trideoxy-3-C-methyl-4-O-methyl-3-nitroso-beta-L-arabino-hexopyranose; major species at pH 7.3.

name: ginsenoside F2
definition: A ginsenoside found in Panax species that is dammarane which is substituted by hydroxy groups at the 3beta, 12beta and 20 pro-S positions, in which the hydroxy groups at positions 3 and 20 have been converted to the corresponding beta-D-glucopyranosides, and in which a double bond has been introduced at the 24-25 position.

name: EC 2.7.1.33 (pantothenate kinase) inhibitor
definition: An EC 2.7.1.* (phosphotransferases with an alcohol group as acceptor) inhibitor that interferes with the action of pantothenate kinase (EC 2.7.1.33).

name: (10E,12Z)-octadecadienoate
definition: A polyunsaturated fatty acid anion that is the conjugate base of (10E,12Z)-octadecadienoic acid, obtained by deprotonation of the carboxy group; major species at pH 7.3.

name: (10Z,13Z,16Z,19Z,22Z,25Z)-octacosahexaenoate
definition: A polyunsaturated fatty acid anion that is the conjugate base of (10Z,13Z,16Z,19Z,22Z,25Z)-octacosahexaenoic acid, obtained by deprotonation of the carboxy group; major species at pH 7.3.

name: (17Z,20Z,23Z,26Z,29Z)-dotriacontapentaenoate
definition: A polyunsaturated fatty acid anion that is the conjugate base of (17Z,20Z,23Z,26Z,29Z)-dotriacontapentaenoic acid, obtained by deprotonation of the carboxy group; major species at pH 7.3.

name: (19Z,22Z,25Z,28Z,31Z)-tetratriacontapentaenoate
definition: A polyunsaturated fatty acid anion that is the conjugate base of (19Z,22Z,25Z,28Z,31Z)-tetratriacontapentaenoic acid, obtained by deprotonation of the carboxy group; major species at pH 7.3.

name: (9Z,12Z)-hexadecadienoate
definition: A polyunsaturated fatty acid anion that is the conjugate base of (9Z,12Z)-hexadecadienoic acid, obtained by deprotonation of the carboxy group; major species at pH 7.3.

name: (13Z,16Z,19Z,22Z)-octacosatetraenoate
definition: A polyunsaturated fatty acid anion that is the conjugate base of (13Z,16Z,19Z,22Z)-octacosatetraenoic acid, obtained by deprotonation of the carboxy group; major species at pH 7.3.

name: (23Z,26Z,29Z,32Z)-octatriacontatetraenoate
definition: An octatriacontatetraenoate that is the conjugate base of (23Z,26Z,29Z,32Z)-octatriacontatetraenoic acid, obtained by deprotonation of the carboxy group; major species at pH 7.3.

name: (10Z,13Z,16Z,19Z,22Z)-octacosapentaenoyl-CoA(4-)
definition: An acyl-CoA(4-) obtained by deprotonation of the phosphate and diphosphate OH groups of (10Z,13Z,16Z,19Z,22Z)-octacosapentaenoyl-CoA; major species at pH 7.3.

name: (25S)-3alpha,7alpha,12alpha-trihydroxy-5beta-cholestan-26-oyl-CoA(4-)
definition: An acyl-CoA(4-) oxoanion arising from deprotonation of the phosphate and diphosphate OH groups of (25S)-3alpha,7alpha,12alpha-trihydroxy-5beta-cholestan-26-oyl-CoA; major species at pH 7.3.

name: tetraoleoyl cardiolipin(2-)
definition: A cardiolipin 72:4(2-) that is the dianion formed from tetraoleoyl cardiolipin by loss of an electron from each of the phospho groups; major species at pH 7.3.

name: 5-methoxy-2-{[(4-methoxy-3,5-dimethylpyridin-2-yl)methyl]sulfinyl}-1H-benzimidazole
definition: A member of the class of benzimidazoles that is 1H-benzimidazole which is substituted by a [4-methoxy-3,5-dimethylpyridin-2-yl)methyl]sulfinyl group at position 2 and a methoxy group at position 5.

name: esomeprazole(1-)
definition: An organic anion resulting from the deprotonation of the hydrogen-bearing nitrogen of the imidazole group of esomeprazole.

name: 1-stearoyl-2-arachidonoyl-sn-glycero-3-phospho-1D-myo-inositol 4,5-biphosphate
definition: A 1-phosphatidyl-1D-myo-inositol 4,5-bisphosphate in which the phosphatidyl acyl groups at positions 1 and 2 are specified as stearoyl and arachidonoyl respectively.

name: 1-(Z)-alk-1-enyl-2-acyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphocholine
definition: A 1-O-(alk-1-enyl)-2-O-acyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphocholine in which the alkenyl group has Z geochemistry.

name: 1-(Z)-alk-1-enyl-2-acyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphoethanolamine zwitterion
definition: A 1-(alk-1-enyl)-2-acyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphoethanolamine zwitterion in which the alkenyl group has Z geochemistry.

name: 1-(Z)-alk-1-enyl-2-acyl-sn-glycerol
definition: A 1-(alk-1-enyl)-2-acyl-sn-glycerol in which the alk-1-enyl group has Z geochemistry.

name: methyl hexanoate
definition: A fatty acid methyl ester derived from hexanoic (caproic acid).

name: bicyclo[3.3.0]oct-2-ene
definition: A carbobicyclic compound consisting of two ortho-fused cyclopentane rings and containing one double bond located at position 2.

name: (8Z,11Z,14Z,17Z,20Z,23Z)-hexacosahexaenoic acid
definition: A very long-chain omega-3 fatty acid that is hexacosanoic acid having six double bonds located at positions 8, 11, 14, 17, 20, 23 (the 8Z,11Z,14Z,17Z,20Z,23Z-isomer).

name: beta-D-GlcpNAc-(1->3)-beta-D-Galp-(1->4)-beta-D-Glcp-(1->4)-[alpha-D-GlcpNAc-(1->2)-3-PEA-L-alpha-D-Hepp-(1->3)]-L-alpha-D-Hepp-(1->5)-Kdo
definition: A branched oligosaccharide phosphate comprising a D-galactose residue, two N-acetyl-D-glucosamine residues, a D-glucose residue, two L-glycero-D-manno-heptose residues (one of which is phosphoethanolamine-substituted on O-3), with linkages as shown and with a 3-deoxy-D-manno-oct-2-ulosonic acid (2-keto-3-deoxy-D-mannooctanoic acid, Kdo) residue at the reducing end. Corresponds to the lgtB mutant of the core oligosaccharide of Neisseria meningitidis.

name: 1,1-bis(phosphonic acid)
definition: Any member of the class of phosphonic acids in which a carbon atom is directly attached to two phosphonic acid groups. They are analogues of pyrophosphates (with the central oxygen atom replaced by a carbon atom) and like pyrophosphates they tend to have a strong affinity for bone, so are frequently used for their antiresorptive and hypocalcaemic properties.

name: tricaproin
definition: A triglyceride obtained by condensation of each of the three hydroxy groups of glycerol with hexanoic (caproic) acid.

name: escitalopram hydrobromide
definition: A 1-[3-(dimethylamino)propyl]-1-(4-fluorophenyl)-1,3-dihydro-2-benzofuran-5-carbonitrile hydrobromide resulting from the reaction of equimolar amounts of escitalopram and hydrogen bromide.

name: alpha-L-Rhap-(1->3)-beta-D-Glcp-(1->4)-alpha-D-Glcp
definition: A linear trisaccharide comprised of alpha-L-rhamnose, beta-D-glucose and alpha-D-glucose residues linked sequentially (1->3) and (1->4).

name: 15-methylhexadecan-1-ol
definition: A long-chain fatty alcohol that is hexadecan-1-ol bearing a methyl substituent at position 15.

name: 1-butyl-N-(2,6-dimethylphenyl)piperidine-2-carboxamide hydrochloride
definition: A hydrochloride obtained by combining 1-butyl-N-(2,6-dimethylphenyl)piperidine-2-carboxamide with one molar equivalent of hydrochloric acid.

name: dextrobupivacaine hydrochloride (anhydrous)
definition: The monohydrochloride salt of dextrobupivacaine.

name: beta-D-QuipN4Fm-(1->4)-alpha-D-GalpNAcAN-(1->4)-alpha-D-GalpNAcAN-(1->3)-beta-DQuipNAc
definition: An amino tetrasaccharide comprising a 4-deoxy-4-formamido-beta-D-quinovose residue, two 2-acetamido-2-deoxy-alpha-D-galacturonamide residues and an N-acetyl-beta-D-quinovosamine residue linked in a (1->4), (1->4), (1->3) sequence.

name: dicarboxylic acid monoamide(1-)
definition: A monocarboxylic acid anion obtained by deprotonation of the carboxy group of any dicarboxylic acid monoamide; major species at pH 7.3.

name: levobupivacaine hydrochloride hydrate
definition: The monohydrate form of levobupivacaine hydrochloride. A piperidinecarboxamide-based local anaesthetic, it has a slow onset and long duration of action.

name: dextrobupivacaine(1+)
definition: The (R)-(+)-enantiomer of bupivacaine(1+).

name: pentadecan-1-ol
definition: A long-chain fatty alcohol that is pentadecane in which one of the terminal methyl hydrogens is replaced by a hydroxy group

name: 1-octadecylglycerone 3-phosphate(2-)
definition: A 1-alkylglycerone 3-phosphate(2-) obtained by deprotonation of the phosphate OH groups of 1-octadecylglycerone 3-phosphate; major species at pH 7.3.

name: 1-oleoylglycerone 3-phosphate(2-)
definition: A 1-acylglycerone 3-phosphate(2-) obtained by deprotonation of the phosphate OH groups of 1-oleoylglycerone 3-phosphate; major species at pH 7.3.

name: 1-arachidonoylglycerone 3-phosphate(2-)
definition: A 1-acylglycerone 3-phosphate(2-) obtained by deprotonation of the phosphate OH groups of 1-arachidonoylglycerone 3-phosphate; major species at pH 7.3.

name: (16Z,19Z,22Z,25Z,28Z,31Z)-tetratriacontahexaenoic acid
definition: An omega-3 fatty acid that is tetratriacontahexaenoic acid having six double bonds located at positions 16, 19, 22, 25 ,28 and 31 (the 16Z,19Z,22Z,25Z,28Z,31Z-isomer).

name: (18Z,21Z,24Z,27Z,30Z,33Z)-hexatriacontahexaenoic acid
definition: A very long-chain omega-3 fatty acid that is hexatriacontanoic acid having six double bonds located at positions 18, 21, 24, 27, 30 and 33 (the 18Z,21Z,24Z,27Z,30Z,33Z-isomer).

name: 1,3,5-octatriene
definition: An unbranched eight-carbon alkatriene with the three double bonds located at positions 1, 3 and 5.

name: trans-2-heptadecenoyl-CoA(4-)
definition: An acyl-CoA(4-) arising from deprotonation of the phosphate and diphosphate functions of trans-2-heptadecenoyl-CoA; major species at pH 7.3.

name: 3-[1-(2,6-dichloro-3-fluorophenyl)ethoxy]-5-[1-(piperidin-4-yl)pyrazol-4-yl]pyridin-2-amine
definition: A pyrazolylpiperidine that consists of 4-(pyrazol-1-yl)piperidine carrying a 2-amino-3-[1-(2,6-dichloro-3-fluorophenyl)ethoxy]pyridin-5-yl group at the 4-position of the pyrazole ring.

name: eugeroic
definition: A phsychotropic drug that improves wakefulness and alertness, and reduces tiredness, drowsiness, and the need for sleep. Eugeroics are relatively non-addictive and are used in the treatment of narcolepsy and other sleep disorders.

name: (8Z,11Z,14Z)-icosatrien-1-ol
definition: A long-chain primary fatty alcohol that is (8Z,11Z,14Z)-icosatriene in which one of the methyl hydrogens at position 1 is replaced by a hydroxy group.

name: (R)-tosufloxacin
definition: A 7-(3-aminopyrrolidin-1-yl)-1-(2,4-difluorophenyl)-6-fluoro-4-oxo-1,4-dihydro-1,8-naphthyridine-3-carboxylic acid that is the (R)-enantiomer of tosufloxacin.

name: 2-[(diphenylmethyl)sulfinyl]acetamide
definition: A sulfoxide that is dimethylsulfoxide in which two hydrogens attached to one of the methyl groups are replaced by phenyl groups, while one hydrogen attached to the other methyl group is replaced by a carbamoyl (aminocarbonyl) group.

name: armodafinil
definition: A 2-[(diphenylmethyl)sulfinyl]acetamide that has R configuration at the sulfur atom. Like its racemate, modafinil, it is used for the treatment of sleeping disorders such as narcolepsy, obstructive sleep apnoea, and shift-work sleep disorder. Peak concentration in the blood later occurs later following administration than with modafinil, so it is thought that armodafinil may be more effective than modafinil in treating people with excessive daytime sleepiness.

name: (3S,5R)-fluvastatin(1-)
definition: A monocarboxylic acid anion resulting from the removal of a proton from the carboxy group of (3S,5R)-fluvastatin.

name: 2'-O-methyllicodione(1-)
definition: A phenolate anion that is the conjugate base of 2'-O-methyllicodione, obtained by deprotonation of the phenolic hydroxy group at position 4; major species at pH 7.3.

name: 2,3',4,6-tetrahydroxybenzophenone(1-)
definition: A phenolate anion that is the conjugate base of 2,3',4,6-tetrahydroxybenzophenone, obtained by deprotonation of the phenolic hydroxy group at position 2; major species at pH 7.3.

name: novamethymycin
definition: A twelve-membered macrolide antibiotic that is biosynthesised by Streptomyces venezuelae.

name: 1-palmityl-2-acetyl-3-linoleoyl-sn-glycerol
definition: A 1-alkyl-2-acetyl-3-acyl-sn-glycerol in which the alkyl and acyl groups are specified as palmityl and linoleoyl.

name: peloruside A
definition: A macrolide that is a novel secondary metabolite isolated from a New Zealand marine sponge, Mycale hentscheli.

name: carboxamidinium ion
definition: Any iminium ion resulting from the protonation of a carboxamidine.

name: delta-lactam
definition: A lactam in which the amide bond is contained within a six-membered ring, which includes the amide nitrogen and the carbonyl carbon.

name: p53 activator
definition: Any activator of tumour protein p53.

name: dexverapamil
definition: A 2-(3,4-dimethoxyphenyl)-5-{[2-(3,4-dimethoxyphenyl)ethyl](methyl)amino}-2-(propan-2-yl)pentanenitrile that has R configuration. It competitively inhibits the multidrug resistance efflux pump P-glycoprotein (MDR-1, EC 3.6.3.44), thereby potentially increasing the effectiveness of a wide range of antineoplastic drugs which are inactivated by MDR-1 mechanisms. Dexverapamil exhibits lower calcium antagonistic activity and toxicity than racemic verapamil.

name: dexverapamil(1+)
definition: An ammonium ion resulting from the protonation of the tertiary amino group of dexverapamil.

name: lejimalide B
definition: A macrolide that is isolated from the marine tunicate Eudistoma cf. rigida and exhibits potent in vitro cytotoxic activity.

name: KP1019
definition: A ruthenium coordination entity that is the indazolium salt of tetrachloro[bis(1H-indazole-kappaN(2))]ruthenate.

name: SCH-351591
definition: An aromatic amide resulting from the formal condensation of the carboxy group of 8-methoxy-2-(trifluoromethyl)quinoline-5-carboxylic acid with the primary amino group of 3,5-dichloropyridin-4-amine 1-oxide. It is a potent inhibitor of phosphodiesterase IV (PDE4).

name: (S)-sulconazole
definition: A 1-{2-[(4-chlorobenzyl)sulfanyl]-2-(2,4-dichlorophenyl)ethyl}-1H-imidazole that has S configuration.

name: EC 1.14.13.181 (13-deoxydaunorubicin hydroxylase) inhibitor
definition: An EC 1.14.13.* (oxidoreductase acting on paired donors, incorporating 1 atom of oxygen, with NADH or NADPH as one donor) inhibitor that interferes with the action of 13-deoxydaunorubicin hydroxylase (EC 1.14.13.181).

name: temafloxacin
definition: A racemate comprising equimolar amounts of (R)- and (S)-temafloxacin. Both enantiomers both exhibit similar pharmacological profiles. Temafloxacin was briefly used (either as the free base or as the hydrochloride salt) as an antibacterial drug but was withdrawn worldwide in 1992 following reports of serious side effects, including severe hypoglycaemia, haemolytic anaemia, liver and kidney dysfunction, anaphylaxis, and death.

name: melamine(1+)
definition: An organic cation obtained by protonation of one of the three ring nitrogens of melamine. It is the major microspecies at pH 7.3 (according to Marvin v 6.2.0.).

name: (13Z,16Z)-docosadienoate
definition: A long-chain unsaturated fatty acid anion that is the conjugate base of (13Z,16Z)-docosadienoic acid, obtained by deprotonation of the carboxy group; major species at pH 7.3.

name: 8-cyclohexyl-2,3,3a,4,5,6-hexahydropyrazino[3,2,1-jk]carbazole
definition: An organic heterotetracyclic compound that is 2,3,3a,4,5,6-hexahydropyrazino[3,2,1-jk]carbazole carrying a cyclohexyl substituent at position 8.

name: 5-fluorotryptophan
definition: A non-proteinogenic alpha-amino acid that is tryptophan in which the hydrogen at position 5 on the indole ring is replaced by a fluoro group.

name: toxaphene
definition: A highly complex mixture of several hundred polychlorinated compounds obtained by chlorination of camphene to an overall chlorine content of 67-69% by weight and having an overall empirical formula of C10H10Cl8 (including optical isomers, it could theoretically contain over 32,000 congeners). Toxaphene was used from the mid-1940s as an agricultural insecticide (mostly in the USA, particularly on corn and soybeans). Use increased with the phasing out of DDT in the 1970s (it became the most heavily manufactured pesticide in the US) but it is now banned due to concerns about toxicity and carcinogenicity. Total production since its first use is estimated at around 500,000 tons. In the environment, most of the components of toxaphene get metabolised, but from 10 to >100 resist biodegradation, depending on the medium and the specialisation of the enzyme system. Breathing, drinking or eating high levels of toxaphene can damage the lungs, kidneys, and nervous system.

name: D-glycero-D-altro-octulose-1,8-bisphosphate
definition: A ketooctose derivative that is D-glycero-D-altro-octulose carrying two phosphate substituents at positions 1 and 8.

name: precorrin-3B(6-)
definition: A precorrin carboxylic acid anion that is the hexaanionic form of precorrin-3B.

name: delphinidin 3-O-(6''-O-malonyl)-beta-D-glucoside(2-)
definition: An organic anion obtained by deprotonation of the malonyl carboxy as well as the 5- and 7-hydroxy groups of delphinidin 3-O-(6''-O-malonyl)-beta-D-glucoside. It is the major microspecies at pH 7.3 (according to Marvin v 6.2.0.).

name: N-[omega-(9R,10R)-epoxy-13-keto-(11E)-octadecenoyloxy]sphing-4-enine
definition: An N-[omega-(acylyloxy)]acylsphin-4-enine in which the omega-O-acyl group is specified as (9R,10R)-epoxy-13-keto-(11E)-octadecenoyl (R represents a very long chain acyl group).

name: (1'S,5'S)-5'-hydroxyaverantin(1-)
definition: A phenolate anion obtained by deprotonation of the 2-hydroxy group of (1'S,5'S)-5'-hydroxyaverantin. It is the major microspecies at pH 7.3 (according to Marvin v 6.2.0.).

name: (24S)-24-hydroxycholesterol 3-hexanoate
definition: A sterol ester that is the 3-hexanoyl derivative of (24S)-24-hydroxycholesterol.

name: alpha-Kdo-(2->8)-alpha-Kdo-OAll II(1),I(7)-lactone
definition: A carbohydrate lactone formed from alpha-Kdo-(2->8)-alpha-Kdo-OAll by lactone formation between the carboxy group of the non-reducing alpha-Kdo residue and O-7 of the alpha-Kdo-OAll residue.

name: tetracycline zwitterion
definition: A zwitterion obtained by transfer of a proton from the 2-hydroxy group to the 1-amino group of tetracycline. It is the major microspecies at pH 7.3 (according to Marvin v 6.2.0.).

name: anthocyanidin 3-O-sophoroside betaine
definition: An oxonium betaine obtained by deprotonation of the 5-hydroxy group of any anthocyanidin 3-O-sophoroside. It is the major microspecies at pH 7.3 (according to Marvin v 6.2.0.).

name: D-glucosyl-N-hexanoylsphingosine
definition: A D-glucosyl-N-acylsphingosine in which the ceramide N-acyl group is specified as hexanoyl.

name: alpha-Kdo1Me-(2->8)-alpha-Kdo-OAll(1-)
definition: The carbohydrate acid derivative anion formed by proton loss from the free carboxy group of alpha-Kdo1Me-(2->8)-alpha-Kdo-OAll

name: food antioxidant
definition: An antioxidant that used as a food additives to help guard against food deterioration.

name: sequestrant
definition: A food preservative that acts by chelating with metal cations (particularly those of copper, iron and nickel) that catalyse the oxidation of fats in food.

name: food humectant
definition: A humectant that is used as a food additive to prevent foodstuffs from drying out.

name: food thickening agent
definition: A food additive that is used to increase the viscosity of foodstuffs.

name: versicolorin A(1-)
definition: A phenolate anion obtained by deprotonation of the 8-hydroxy group of versicolorin A. It is the major microspecies at pH 7.3 (according to Marvin v 6.2.0.).

name: N-dodecanoylphytosphingosine
definition: A phytoceramide in which the ceramide N-acyl group is specified as dodecanoyl.

name: food colour retention agent
definition: A food additive that intensifies, retains or stabilises the colour of a food.

name: Wiskott-Aldrich syndrome protein inhibitor
definition: Any inhibitor of Wiskott-Aldrich syndrome protein.

name: 1-stearoyl-2-(alpha-linolenoyl)-sn-glycero-3-phosphocholine
definition: A 1,2-diacyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphocholine in which the two acyl substituents at positions 1 and 2 are specified as stearoyl and alpha-linolenoyl respectively.

name: 2-acetyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphocholine
definition: A 2-acyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphocholine in which the acyl group at position 2 is specified as acetyl.

name: 12(S)-HPE(5,8,10)TrE(1-)
definition: A polyunsaturated fatty acid anion that is the conjugate base of 12(S)-HPE(5,8,10)TrE, obtained by deprotonation of the carboxy group; major species at pH 7.3.

name: octadecenoate
definition: A fatty acid anion containing 18 carbons and one double bond. Formed by deprotonation of the carboxylic acid group. Major species at pH 7.3.

name: icosadienoate
definition: A polyunsaturated fatty acid anion that is the conjugate base of icosadienoic acid, obtained by deprotonation of the carboxy group; major species at pH 7.3.

name: dotriacontapentaenoate
definition: A polyunsaturated fatty acid anion that is the conjugate base of any dotriacontapentaenoic acid, obtained by deprotonation of the carboxy group; major species at pH 7.3.

name: N-hexadecanoylphosphatidylethanolamine(1-)
definition: An N-acylphosphatidylethanolamine(1-) in which the N-acyl group is specified as palmitoyl (hexadecanoyl); major species at pH 7.3.

name: trioxilin A3(1-)
definition: The trioxilin anion that is the anion formed from trioxilin A3 by deprotonation of its carboxylic acid moiety; major microspecies present at pH 7.3.

name: (Z)-(1S)-cis-tefluthrin
definition: A 2,3,5,6-tetrafluoro-4-methylbenzyl 3-[(1Z)-2-chloro-3,3,3-trifluoroprop-1-en-1-yl]-2,2-dimethylcyclopropanecarboxylate in which both of the stereocentres have S configuration.

name: fatty acid anion 12:0
definition: Any saturated fatty acid anion containing 12 carbons. Formed by deprotonation of the carboxylic acid moiety. Major species at pH 7.3.

name: fatty acid anion 15:0
definition: Any saturated fatty acid anion containing 15 carbons. Formed by deprotonation of the carboxylic acid moiety. Major species at pH 7.3.

name: fatty acid anion 30:0
definition: Any saturated fatty acid anion containing 30 carbons. Formed by deprotonation of the carboxylic acid moiety. Major species at pH 7.3.

name: 1-heptadecylglycerone 3-phosphate
definition: A 1-alkylglycerone 3-phosphate in which the alkyl group is specified as heptadecyl.

name: fatty alcohol 22:1
definition: Any fatty alcohol containing 22 carbons and 1 double bond.

name: fatty alcohol 18:2
definition: Any fatty alcohol containing 18 carbons and 2 double bonds.

name: 1-lysophosphatidate(2-)
definition: Any monoacylglycerol 3-phosphate(2-) which has a free hydroxy group at the 1-position of the glycerol moiety.

name: alkylacylglycero-3-phosphocholine
definition: A glycerophosphocholine that is glycero-3-phosphocholine carrying one alkyl and one acyl group in unspecified positions. Major species at pH 7.3.

name: 2-arachidonoyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphate(2-)
definition: A 2-acyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphate(2-) obtained by deprotonation of the phosphate OH groups of 2-arachidonoyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphate; major species at pH 7.3.

name: monoacylglycero-3-phosphoglycerol(1-)
definition: An anionic phospholipid obtained by deprotonation of the phosphate OH group of any monoacylglycero-3-phosphoglycerol. Major species at pH 7.3.

name: monoacylglycero-3-phospho-1-inositol(1-)
definition: An anionic phospholipid obtained by deprotonation of the phosphate OH group of any monoacylglycero-3-phospho-1-inositol; major species at pH 7.3.

name: N-acetyl-L-cysteinate
definition: A monocarboxylic acid anion that is the conjugate base of  N-acetyl-L-cysteine, obtained by deprotonation of the carboxy group; major species at pH 7.3.

name: 1-octadecanoyl-2-(4Z,7Z,10Z,13Z,16Z,19Z-docosahexaenoyl)-sn-glycero-3-phosphoserine(1-)
definition: A 3-sn-phosphatidyl-L-serine(1-) that is the conjugate base of 1-octadecanoyl-2-(4Z,7Z,10Z,13Z,16Z,19Z-docosahexaenoyl)-sn-glycero-3-phosphoserine; major species at pH 7.3.

name: omega-hydroxymenaquinone-4
definition: A prenylnaphthoquinone obtained by hydroxylation of one of the terminal methyl groups of menaquinone-4.

name: 8-demethyl-8-(alpha-L-rhamnosyl)tetracenomycin C
definition: A member of the class of tetracenomycins that is 8-demethyltetracenomycin C in which the hydroxyl hydrogen at position 8 is replaced by an alpha-L-rhamnosyl residue.

name: ophiobolin F
definition: A sesterterpenoid that is (7Z)-ophiobola-7,19-diene carrying a hydroxy substituent at position 3.

name: dTDP-2-deoxy-beta-L-fucose(2-)
definition: A nucleotide-sugar oxoanion obtained by deprotonation of the diphosphate OH groups of dTDP-2-deoxy-beta-L-fucose; major species at pH 7.3.

name: aclacinomycin S zwitterion
definition: A zwitterion obtained by transfer of a proton from the 5-hydroxy to the tertiary amino group of aclacinomycin S. It is the major microspecies at pH 7.3 (according to Marvin v 6.2.0.).

name: ambrein
definition: A triterpenoid alcohol that is a constituent of ambergris, an intestinal secretion of the sperm whale Physeter catodon.

name: alpha-asarone
definition: The trans-isomer of  asarone.

name: 5,10-dihydro-9-dimethylallylphenazine 1-carboxylate
definition: A monocarboxylic acid anion that is the conjugate base of 5,10-9-dimethylallyldihydrophenazine-1-carboxylic acid, obtained by deprotonation of the carboxy group; major species at pH 7.3.

name: 4,6,6-trimethylbicyclo[3.1.1]hept-3-en-2-one
definition: A carbobicyclic compound that is bicyclo[3.1.1]heptane which is substituted by an oxo group at position 2 and by methyl groups at positions 4, 6 and 6, and which contains a double bond between positions 3 and 4.

name: (S)-(-)-verbenone
definition: A 4,6,6-trimethylbicyclo[3.1.1]hept-3-en-2-one in which both chiral centres have S configuration.

name: 2-hydroxypropanoic acid
definition: A 2-hydroxy monocarboxylic acid that is propanoic acid in which one of the alpha-hydrogens is replaced by a hydroxy group.

name: ethyl 2-hydroxypropanoate
definition: The ethyl ester obtained of 2-hydroxypropanoic acid.

name: 5-hydroxyxanthotoxin(1-)
definition: A phenolate anion that is the conjugate base of 5-hydroxyxanthotoxin, obtained by deprotonation of the hydroxy group. It is the major microspecies at pH 7.3 (according to Marvin v 6.2.0.).

name: huperzine A
definition: A sesquiterpene alkaloid isolated from a club moss Huperzia serrata that has been shown to exhibit neuroprotective activity. It is also an effective inhibitor of acetylcholinesterase and has attracted interest as a therapeutic candidate for Alzheimer's disease.

name: 3,7-dimethylocta-1,6-dien-3-yl acetate
definition: A monoterpenoid that is the acetate ester of linalool. It forms a principal component of the essential oils from bergamot and lavender.

name: meta-hydroxyphenylhydracrylic acid
definition: A hydroxy monocarboxylic acid that is propionic acid substituted by a hydroxy group at position 3 and a 3-hydroxyphenyl group at position 2. It is a metabolite of flavonoids and has been identified as one of the major phenolic acids in human urine.

name: D-ribofuranose 5-phosphate(2-)
definition: An organophosphate oxoanion obtained by deprotonation of the phosphate OH groups of D-ribofuranose-5-phosphate; major species at pH 7.3.

name: (4-nitrophenyl)acetate
definition: A monocarboxylic acid anion resulting from the removal of a proton from the carboxy group of (4-nitrophenyl)acetic acid; it is the major species at pH 7.3.

name: EC 5.1.2.* (racemases acting on hydroxy acids and derivatives) inhibitor
definition: An EC 5.1.* (racemase/epimerase) inhibitor that interferes with the action of any such enzyme acting on hydroxy acids and their derivatives (EC 5.1.2.*).

name: (R)-benproperine(1+)
definition: An ammonium ion resulting from the protonation of the nitrogen of (R)-benproperine.

name: 5-(2-oxopropylideneamino)-6-D-ribitylaminouracil
definition: An aminouracil that is D-ribitol in which the hydroxy group at position 1 is substituted by the 6-amino group of 6-amino-5-(2-oxopropylideneamino)uracil. Unstable mucosal-associated invariant T (MAIT)-activating antigen, formed by non-enzymatic reaction between 5-amino-6-D-ribitylaminouracil and methylglyoxal.

name: ethyl (2S)-hydroxy(phenyl)acetate
definition: The  (2S)-enantiomer of ethyl hydroxy(phenyl)acetate.

name: tricosan-1-ol
definition: A long-chain primary fatty alcohol that is tricosane in which a hydrogen attached to one of the terminal carbons is replaced by a hydroxy group. It has been isolated from bulbs of Polianthes tuberosa, bran from the Italian bread wheat variety Pegaso and its 11 near-isogenic lines, and from the aerial parts of f Centaurea austro-anatolica.

name: 18-hydroxyoleate
definition: An omega-hydroxy fatty acid anion that is the conjugate base of 18-hydroxyoleic acid, obtained by deprotonation of the carboxy group; major species at pH 7.3.

name: 1,2-diacyl-3-(3-O-sulfo-beta-D-galactosyl)glycerol(1-)
definition: An organosulfate oxoanion obtained by deprotonation of the sulfate group of any 1,2-diacyl-3-(3-O-sulfo-beta-D-galactosyl)glycerol; major species at pH 7.3.

name: S-methyl-5-thio-D-ribofuranose
definition: A thioribose consisting of D-ribofuranose in which the hydroxy group at position 3 is replaced by a methylthio group.

name: alpha-Neu5Ac-(2->3)-beta-Gal-(1->3)-beta-GalNAc-(1->4)-[alpha-Neu5Ac-(2->8)-alpha-Neu5Ac-(2->3)]-beta-Gal-(1->4)-beta-Glc-(1<->1')-Cer(3-)
definition: An anionic ganglioside obtained by deprotonation of the neuraminosyl carboxy groups of ganglioside GT1b; major species at pH 7.3.

name: O-[S-(3R)-hydroxyhexanoylpantetheine-4'-phosphoryl]serine(1-) residue
definition: An O-(S-acylpantetheine-4'-phosphoryl)serine(1-) residue in which the S-acyl group is specified as (3R)-hydroxyhexanoyl.

name: O-[S-(2E)-hexenoylpantetheine-4'-phosphoryl]serine(1-) residue
definition: An O-(S-acylpantetheine-4'-phosphoryl)serine(1-) residue in which the S-acyl group is specified as (2E)-hexenoyl.

name: O-(S-octanoylpantetheine-4-phosphoryl)serine(1-) residue
definition: An O-(S-acylpantetheine-4'-phosphoryl)serine(1-) residue in which the S-acyl group is specified as octanoyl.

name: O-(S-3-oxotetradecanoylpantetheine-4-phosphoryl)serine(1-) residue
definition: An O-(S-acylpantetheine-4'-phosphoryl)serine(1-) residue in which the S-acyl group is specified as 3-oxotetradecanoyl.

name: O-[S-(3R)-hydroxytetradecanoylpantetheine-4-phosphoryl]serine(1-) residue
definition: An O-(S-acylpantetheine-4'-phosphoryl)serine(1-) residue in which the S-acyl group is specified as (3R)-hydroxytetradecanoyl.

name: O-[S-(2E)-hexadecenoylpantetheine-4'-phosphoryl]serine(1-) residue
definition: An O-(S-acylpantetheine-4'-phosphoryl)serine(1-) residue in which the S-acyl group is specified as (2E)-hexadecenoyl.

name: O-[S-(3R)-hydroxyoctadecanoylpantetheine-4'-phosphoryl]serine(1-) residue
definition: An O-(S-acylpantetheine-4'-phosphoryl)serine(1-) residue in which the S-acyl group is specified as (3R)-hydroxyoctadecanoyl.

name: O-[S-(2E)-octadecenoylpantetheine-4'-phosphoryl]serine(1-) residue
definition: An O-(S-acylpantetheine-4'-phosphoryl)serine(1-) residue in which the S-acyl group is specified as (2E)-octadecenoyl.

name: organic trisulfide
definition: An organosulfur compound with structure Compounds of structure R(1)SSSR(2) in which R(1) and R(2) are organic groups.

name: 3'-(L-glutamate)adenylyl(1-) group
definition: An organic anionic group obtained by deprotonation of the phosphate and carboxy functions as well as protonation of the amino function of 3'-(L-glutamyl)adenylyl group; major species at 7.3.

name: L-glutamo(2-) group
definition: An alpha-amino-acid residue anion obtained by deprotonation of the two carboxy functions of L-glutamo group. Major structure at pH 7.3.

name: 3'-(L-histidyl)adenylyl(1-) group
definition: An organic anionic group obtained by deprotonation of the phosphate function of 3'-(L-histidyl)adenylyl group; major species at 7.3.

name: 3'-(L-prolyl)adenylyl zwitterionic group
definition: A zwitterionic group obtained by transfer of a proton from the phosphate to the amino group of 3'-(L-prolyl)adenylyl group

name: beta-D-Gal-(1->3)-beta-D-GlcNAc-(1->3)-beta-D-Gal-(1->4)-beta-D-GlcNAc-(1->3)- beta-D-Gal-(1->4)-beta-D-Glc-(1<->1')-Cer
definition: A glycohexaosylceramide having beta-D-Gal-(1->3)-beta-D-GlcNAc-(1->3)-beta-D-Gal-(1->4)-beta-D-GlcNAc-(1->3)- beta-D-Gal-(1->4)-beta-D-Glc as the glycohexaosyl component.

name: 1-(1Z)-alkenyl-2-acetyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphocholine
definition: A 1-(1Z)-alkenyl-2-acyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphocholine in which the 2-acyl group is specified as acetyl.

name: alpha-Neu5Ac-(2->3)-beta-D-Gal-(1->3)-[alpha-Neu5Ac-(2->6)]-beta-D-GalNAc-(1->4)-[alpha-Neu5Ac-(2->3)]-beta-D-Gal-(1->4)-beta-D-Glc-(1<->1')-Cer(3-)
definition: An anionic ganglioside obtained by deprotonation of the neuraminosyl carboxy groups of alpha-Neu5Ac-(2->3)-beta-D-Gal-(1->3)-[alpha-Neu5Ac-(2->6)]-beta-D-GalNAc-(1->4)-[alpha-Neu5Ac-(2->3)]-beta-D-Gal-(1->4)-beta-D-Glc-(1<->1')-Cer; major species at pH 7.3.

name: aflatoxin M1 8,9-epoxide
definition: A member of the class of aflatoxins that is obtained by the formal epoxidation across the 8,9-double bond of aflatoxin M1.

name: 6-linalyl-2-O,3-dimethylflaviolin-7-olate
definition: An organic anion that is the conjugate base of 6-linalyl-2-O,3-dimethylflaviolin, obtained by deprotonation of the 7-hydroxy group. It is the major microspecies at pH 7.3 (according to Marvin v 6.2.0.).

name: dolichyl diphosphate group(2-)
definition: An organic anionic group obtained by deprotonation of the diphosphate function of dolichyl diphosphate group. It is the major structure at pH 7.3 (according to Marvin v 6.2.0.).

name: ursodeoxycholate
definition: A bile acid anion that is the conjugate base of ursodeoxycholic acid, obtained by deprotonation of the carboxy group; major species at pH 7.3.

name: alpha-L-Fuc-(1->2)-beta-D-Gal-(1->3)-beta-D-GalNAc-(1->4)-[alpha-Neu5Ac-(2->3)]-beta-D-Gal-(1->4)-beta-D-Glc-(1<->1')-Cer(1-)
definition: An anionic ganglioside that is the conjugate base of fucosyl GM1 arising from deprotonation of the neuraminosyl carboxy group; major species at pH 7.3.

name: 3-hydroxybutanoyl-CoA(4-)
definition: An acyl-CoA(4-) obtained by deprotonation of the phosphate and diphosphate OH groups of 3-hydroxybutanoyl-CoA; major species at pH 7.3.

name: C-terminal L-Cys-L-Leu-L-Val-L-Cys(1-) residue
definition: An organic anionic group obtained by deprotonation of the terminal carboxy group of C-terminal L-Cys-L-Leu-L-Val-L-Cys residue.

name: carbohydrates and carbohydrate derivatives
definition: Any organooxygen compound that is a polyhydroxy-aldehyde or -ketone, or a compound derived from one. Carbohydrates contain only carbon, hydrogen and oxygen and usually have an empirical formula Cm(H2O)n; carbohydrate derivatives may contain other elements by substitution or condensation.

name: 3-methoxy-5-methyl-1-naphthoate
definition: A naphthoate that is the conjugate base of 3-methoxy-5-methyl-1-naphthoic acid, obtained by deprotonation of the carboxy group; major species at pH 7.3.

name: fatty alcohol 15:1
definition: A fatty alcohol containing 15 carbons and 1 double bond.

name: fatty alcohol 28:1
definition: A fatty alcohol containing 28 carbons and 1 double bond.

name: fatty alcohol 20:2
definition: A fatty alcohol containing 20 carbons and 2 double bonds.

name: N-hexadecanoylphytosphingosine-1-phosphocholine
definition: A sphingomyelin 34:0 in which the N-acyl group and sphingoid base are specified as hexadecanoyl and phytosphingosine respectively.

name: N-hexadecanoylphytosphingosine-1-phosphoethanolamine zwitterion
definition: An N-acylphytosphingosine-1-phosphoethanolamine zwitterion in which the N-acyl group is specified as hexadecanoyl.

name: (9Z,12Z)-heptadecadienoyl-CoA(4-)
definition: A polyunsaturated fatty acyl-CoA(4-) arising from deprotonation of the phosphate and diphosphate functions of (9Z,12Z)-heptadecadienoyl-CoA; major species at pH 7.3.

name: 2-arachidonoyl-sn-glycero-3-phospho-L-serine
definition: A 2-acyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphoserine in which the 2-acyl group is specified as arachidonoyl.

name: S. flexneri serotype 1b O-polysaccharide (O factor 9-positive)
definition: A polysaccharide derivative comprised of a [2)-alpha-L-Rhap(III)-(1->2)-alpha-L-Rhap(II)-(1->3)-alpha-L-Rhap(I)-(1->3)-beta-D-GlcpNAc-(1->] tetrasaccharide repeat modified by the (1->4) linkage of an alpha-D-glucosyl group to the GlcNAc residue and by addition of acetyl groups to O-2 of 80% of the Rha(I) residues and to either O-3 or O-4 of many of the Rha(III) residues (70% to O-3; 15% to O-4). The structure provided is representative of that in Shigella flexneri serotype 1b and shows the most common repeating unit.

name: 2,4,5-trimethylthiazole
definition: A 1,3-thiazole that is thiazole in which all three hydrogens are replaced by methyl groups. A Maillard reaction product, it is a flavour component in many cooked foods, including cooked meats and potatoes.

name: EC 2.5.1.6 (methionine adenosyltransferase) inhibitor
definition: An EC 2.5.1.* (non-methyl-alkyl or aryl transferase) inhibitor that interferes with the action of methionine adenosyltransferase (EC 2.5.1.6).

name: LLP-3
definition: A pyridone that is pyridin-2(1H)-one which is substituted at positions 3, 4, and 6 by cyano, 3,5-bis(benzyloxy)phenyl, and 5-chloro-2-hydroxyphenyl groups, respectively. It is an inhibitor for Survivin-Ran protein complex.

name: ethylene glycol monododecyl ether
definition: A hydroxyether that is ethylene glycol substituted on one of the oxygens by a dodecyl group.

name: beta-ascarylopyranose
definition: An ascarylopyranose that has beta configuration at the anomeric centre.

name: (6S)-6-hydroxyheptanoic acid
definition: A 6-hydroxyheptanoic acid that has S configuration at the chiral centre.

name: ascr#7
definition: An (omega-1)-hydroxy fatty acid ascaroside obtained by formal condensation of the alcoholic hydroxy group of (2E,6R)-6-hydroxyhept-2-enoic acid with ascarylopyranose (the alpha anomer). A metabolite of the nematode Caenorhabditis elegans, it is weakly dauer inducing and a weak male-attractant.

name: O-[S-(methoxycarbonylacetyl)pantetheine-4'-phosphoryl]serine(1-) residue
definition: An O-(S-acylpantetheine-4'-phosphoryl)-L-serine(1-) residue in which the S-acyl group is specified as methoxycarbonylacetyl.

name: alkyl,acylglycerophosphoinositol(1-)
definition: An anionic phospholipid obtained by deprotonation of the phosphate OH group of any alkyl,acylglycerophosphoinositol. Major species at pH 7.3.

name: 1,3-indandione
definition: A member of the class of indanones that is indane in which the hydrogens at positions 2 and 4 have been replaced by oxo groups.

name: 4-chloro-7-nitrobenzofurazan
definition: A benzoxadiazole that is 2,1,3-benzoxadiazole which is substituted at position 4 by chlorine and at position 7 by a nitro group.

name: 1-(alk-1-enyl)-glycero-3-phospho-L-serine(1-)
definition: A 1-alkylglycero-3-phosphoserine(1-) in which the alkyl substituent can be any alk-1-enyl group.

name: beta-D-Manp-(1->2)-beta-D-Manp-(1->2)-alpha-D-Manp-O[CH2]2NH2
definition: A glycoside that consists of the linear trisaccharide beta-D-Manp-(1->2)-beta-D-Manp-(1->2)-alpha-D-Manp having a 2-aminoethoxy moiety at the reducing-end anomeric centre.

name: beta-D-Manp-(1->2)-beta-D-Manp-(1->2)-beta-D-Manp-O[CH2]2NH2
definition: A glycoside that consists of the linear trisaccharide beta-D-Manp-(1->2)-beta-D-Manp-(1->2)-beta-D-Manp having a 2-aminoethoxy moiety at the reducing-end anomeric centre.

name: ascr#14
definition: An (omega-1)-hydroxy fatty acid ascaroside obtained by formal condensation of the alcoholic hydroxy group of (7R)-7-hydroxyoctanoic acid with ascarylopyranose (the alpha anomer). It is a metabolite of the nematode Caenorhabditis elegans.

name: octacosahexaenoic acid
definition: A polyunsaturated fatty acid whose structure contains double bonds at any six positions of a 28-carbon straight chain.

name: 12-HPEPE
definition: A hydroperoxy fatty acid that is (5Z,8Z,10E,14Z,17Z)-icosapentaenoic acid in which the hydroperoxy group is located at the 12-position.

name: copovidone
definition: A polymer composed of copovidone macromolecules.

name: archaeal metabolite
definition: Any prokaryotic metabolite produced during a metabolic reaction in  single-celled microorganisms, archaea.

name: (2E,10R)-10-hydroxyundec-2-enoic acid
definition: An (omega-1)-hydroxy fatty acid that is trans-undec-2-enoic acid in which the 10-pro-R hydrogen is replaced by a hydroxy group.

name: (omega-1)-hydroxy fatty acid
definition: A hydroxy fatty acid that is a straight-chain fatty acid in which one of the hydrogens attached to the carbon adjacent to the terminal methyl group (i.e. at the (omega-1) position) is replaced by a hydroxy group.

name: ascr#25
definition: An (omega-1)-hydroxy fatty acid ascaroside obtained by formal condensation of the alcoholic hydroxy group of (2E,14R)-14-hydroxypentadec-2-enoic acid with ascarylopyranose (the alpha anomer). It is a metabolite of the nematode Caenorhabditis elegans.

name: ascr#29
definition: An (omega-1)-hydroxy fatty acid ascaroside obtained by formal condensation of the alcoholic hydroxy group of (2E,16R)-16-hydroxyheptadec-2-enoic acid with ascarylopyranose (the alpha anomer). It is a metabolite of the nematode Caenorhabditis elegans.

name: ascr#31
definition: An (omega-1)-hydroxy fatty acid ascaroside obtained by formal condensation of the alcoholic hydroxy group of (2E,17R)-17-hydroxyoctadec-2-enoic acid with ascarylopyranose (the alpha anomer). It is a metabolite of the nematode Caenorhabditis elegans.

name: ascr#33
definition: An (omega-1)-hydroxy fatty acid ascaroside obtained by formal condensation of the alcoholic hydroxy group of (2E,18R)-18-hydroxynonadec-2-enoic acid with ascarylopyranose (the alpha anomer). It is a metabolite of the nematode Caenorhabditis elegans.

name: (11R)-11-hydroxylauric acid
definition: An 11-hydroxylauric acid that has R configuration.

name: (2E,12R)-12-hydroxytridec-2-enoic acid
definition: An (omega-1)-hydroxy fatty acid that is (2E)-tridec-2-enoic acid in which the 12-pro-R hydrogen is replaced by a hydroxy group.

name: O-[S-(3R)-hydroxypentanoylpantetheine-4'-phosphoryl]serine(1-) residue
definition: An O-(S-acylpantetheine-4'-phosphoryl)serine(1-) residue in which the S-acyl group is specified as (3R)-hydroxypentanoyl.

name: tricosanoate
definition: A very long-chain fatty acid anion that is the conjugate base of tricosanoic acid, obtained by deprotonation of the carboxy group; major species at pH 7.3.

name: prostaglandin D1(1-)
definition: A prostaglandin carboxylic acid anion that is the conjugate base of prostaglandin D1, obtained by deprotonation of the carboxy group; major species at pH 7.3.

name: dihydromonacolin L carboxylate
definition: A hydroxy monocarboxylic acid anion that is the conjugate base of dihydromonacolin L acid, obtained by deprotonation of the carboxy group; major species at pH 7.3.

name: D-arabinose 5-phosphate
definition: An  arabinose phosphate that is D-arabinose having a phosphate substituent at position 5.

name: CHOH group
definition: The organodiyl group obtained by removal of two of the methyl protons from methanol.

name: 3-methyl-L-tyrosine
definition: A tyrosine derivative that is L-tyrosine in which the hydrogen at position 3 on the phenyl ring is replaced by a methyl group.

name: 5-hydroxy-3-methyl-L-tyrosine
definition: A tyrosine derivative that is L-tyrosine in which the hydrogens at positions 3 and 5 on the phenyl ring are replaced by a methyl and hydroxy groups respectively.

name: N(5)-hydroxy-L-ornithine
definition: A member of the class of hydroxylamines that is L-ornithine in which one of the N(5)-amino hydrogens is replaced by a hydroxy group.

name: 1-(1Z-octadecenyl)-2-(4Z,7Z,10Z,13Z,16Z,19Z-docosahexaenoyl)-sn-glycero-3-phosphoethanolamine
definition: A 1-(alk-1-enyl)-2-acyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphoethanolamine in which the alk-1-enyl and acyl groups are specified as (1Z)-octadecenyl and (4Z,7Z,10Z,13Z,16Z,19Z)-docosahexaenoyl respectively.

name: 1-(1Z-octadecenyl)-2-(4Z,7Z,10Z,13Z,16Z,19Z-docosahexaenoyl)-sn-glycero-3-phosphoserine
definition: A 1-alkyl-2-acyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphserine in which the alkyl and acyl groups are specified as (1Z)-octadecenyl and (4Z,7Z,10Z,13Z,16Z,19Z)-docosahexaenoyl respectively.

name: icas#17
definition: A 4-O-(1H-indol-3-ylcarbonyl)ascaroside derived from (2E,10R)-10-hydroxyundec-2-enoic acid. It is a metabolite of the nematode Caenorhabditis elegans.

name: icas#19
definition: A 4-O-(1H-indol-3-ylcarbonyl)ascaroside derived from (2E,11R)-11-hydroxydodec-2-enoic acid. It is a metabolite of the nematode Caenorhabditis elegans.
