name: 1-octadecanoyl-2-(4Z,7Z,10Z,13Z,16Z,19Z-docosahexaenoyl)-sn-glycero-3-phosphoethanolamine
definition: A 1,2-diacyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphoethanolamine in which the acyl substituents at positions 1 and 2 are specified as octadecanoyl and (4Z,7Z,10Z,13Z,16Z,19Z)-docosahexaenoyl respectively.

name: icos#1
definition: A 4-O-(1H-indol-3-ylcarbonyl)ascaroside derived from 7-hydroxyheptanoic acid. It is a metabolite of the nematode Caenorhabditis elegans.

name: icos#3
definition: A 4-O-(1H-indol-3-ylcarbonyl)ascaroside derived from (2E)-9-hydroxynon-2-enoic acid. It is a metabolite of the nematode Caenorhabditis elegans.

name: icos#18
definition: A 4-O-(1H-indol-3-ylcarbonyl)ascaroside derived from 11-hydroxyundecanoic acid. It is a metabolite of the nematode Caenorhabditis elegans.

name: 4-O-[(E)-2-methyl-2-butenoyl]ascaroside
definition: An ascaroside of a hydroxy fatty acid in which the hydroxy group at position 4 of the ascarylopyranose moiety has been has been converted into the corresponding (E)-2-methyl-2-butenoate ester.

name: mbas#3
definition: A 4-O-[(E)-2-methyl-2-butenoyl]ascaroside derived from (2E,8R)-8-hydroxynon-2-enoic acid. It is a metabolite of the nematode Caenorhabditis elegans.

name: oscr#18
definition: An omega-hydroxy fatty acid ascaroside obtained by formal condensation of the alcoholic hydroxy group of 11-hydroxyundecanoic acid with ascarylopyranose (the alpha anomer). It is a metabolite of the nematode Caenorhabditis elegans.

name: oscr#22
definition: An omega-hydroxy fatty acid ascaroside obtained by formal condensation of the alcoholic hydroxy group of 13-hydroxytridecanoic acid with ascarylopyranose (the alpha anomer). It is a metabolite of the nematode Caenorhabditis elegans.

name: oscr#25
definition: An omega-hydroxy fatty acid ascaroside obtained by formal condensation of the alcoholic hydroxy group of (2E)-15-hydroxypentadec-2-enoic acid with ascarylopyranose (the alpha anomer). It is a metabolite of the nematode Caenorhabditis elegans.

name: oscr#29
definition: An omega-hydroxy fatty acid ascaroside obtained by formal condensation of the alcoholic hydroxy group of (2E)-17-hydroxyheptadec-2-enoic acid with ascarylopyranose (the alpha anomer). It is a metabolite of the nematode Caenorhabditis elegans.

name: oscr#33
definition: An omega-hydroxy fatty acid ascaroside obtained by formal condensation of the alcoholic hydroxy group of (2E)-19-hydroxynonadec-2-enoic acid with ascarylopyranose (the alpha anomer). It is a metabolite of the nematode Caenorhabditis elegans.

name: (2E)-18-hydroxyoctadec-2-enoic acid
definition: An omega-hydroxy fatty acid that is trans-octadec-2-enoic acid in which one of the hydrogens of the terminal methyl group has been replaced by a hydroxy group.

name: 18-hydroxyoctadecanoic acid
definition: An omega-hydroxy-long-chain fatty acid that is octadecanoic (stearic) acid in which one of the hydrogens of the terminal methyl group has been replaced by a hydroxy group.

name: 20-hydroxyicosanoic acid
definition: An omega-hydroxy-long-chain fatty acid that is icosanoic acid (arachidonic acid) in which one of the hydrogens of the terminal methyl group has been replaced by a hydroxy group.

name: 5-acetamidopentanoate
definition: A 2-oxo monocarboxylic acid anion that is the conjugate base of 6-acetamido-2-oxopentanoic acid, obtained by deprotonation of the carboxy group; major species at pH 7.3.

name: 21-hydroxyhenicosanoic acid
definition: An omega-hydroxy-long-chain fatty acid that is henicosanoic acid in which one of the hydrogens of the terminal methyl group has been replaced by a hydroxy group.

name: ascaroside
definition: Any glycoside derived from alpha-ascarylopyranose or its derivatives.

name: alpha-N-acetylneuraminosyl-(2->8)-alpha-N-acetylneuraminosyl-(2->3)-beta-D-galactosyl-(1->4)-beta-D-glucosyl-(1<->1)-ceramide
definition: A sialodiosylceramide consisting of the tetrasaccharide alpha-N-acetylneuraminyl-(2->8)-alpha-N-acetylneuraminyl-(2->3)-beta-D-galactosyl-(1->4)-beta-D-glucose attached to the primary hydroxy function of a ceramide with undefined sphingoid base.

name: alpha-N-acetylneuraminyl-(2->8)-alpha-N-acetylneuraminyl-(2->8)-alpha-N-acetylneuraminyl-(2->3)-beta-D-galactosyl-(1->4)-beta-D-glucosyl-(1<->1)-ceramide
definition: A sialodiosylceramide consisting of the pentasaccharide alpha-N-acetylneuraminyl-(2->8)-alpha-N-acetylneuraminyl-(2->8)-alpha-N-acetylneuraminyl-(2->3)-beta-D-galactosyl-(1->4)-beta-D-glucose attached to the primary hydroxy function of of a ceramide with an undefined sphingoid base.

name: N-acetyl-beta-D-galactosaminyl-(1->4)-[alpha-N-acetylneuraminyl-(2->3)]-beta-D-galactosyl-(1->4)-beta-D-glucosyl-(1<->1)-ceramide(1-)
definition: An anionic ganglioside obtained by deprotonation of the neuraminosyl carboxy groups of N-acetyl-beta-D-galactosaminyl-(1->4)-[alpha-N-acetylneuraminyl-(2->3)]-beta-D-galactosyl-(1->4)-beta-D-glucosyl-(1<->1)-ceramide; major species at pH 7.3.

name: N-acetyl-beta-D-galactosaminyl-(1->4)-[alpha-N-acetylneuraminyl-(2->8)-alpha-N-acetylneuraminyl-(2->3)]-beta-D-galactosyl-(1->4)-beta-D-glucosyl-(1<->1)-ceramide(2-)
definition: An anionic ganglioside obtained by deprotonation of the neuraminosyl carboxy groups of N-acetyl-beta-D-galactosaminyl-(1->4)-[alpha-N-acetylneuraminyl-(2->8)-alpha-N-acetylneuraminyl-(2->3)]-beta-D-galactosyl-(1->4)-beta-D-glucosyl-(1<->1)-ceramide; major species at pH 7.3.

name: (3R,10R)-3,10-dihydroxyundecanoic acid
definition: An (omega-1)-hydroxy fatty acid that is (10R)-10-hydroxyundecanoic acid in which the 3-pro-R hydrogen is replaced by a hydroxy group.

name: 1-palmityl-2-acetyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphate
definition: A 1-alkyl-2-acyl-sn-glycerol 3-phosphate in which the alkyl and the acyl groups at positions 1 and 2 are specified as hexadecyl and acetyl respectively.

name: (3R)-3,16-dihydroxyhexadecanoic acid
definition: A 3,16-dihydroxyhexadecanoic acid in which the chiral centre has R configuration.

name: 2-hydroxy-7-methoxy-5-methyl-1-naphthoyl-CoA
definition: An acyl-CoA that results from the formal condensation of the thiol group of coenzyme A with the carboxy group of 2-hydroxy-7-methoxy-5-methyl-1-naphthoic acid.

name: glycosinolic acid
definition: An organic sulfate that is the oxime hydrogen sulfate of an S-acyl thioglycoside.

name: thia-alkylglucosinolic acid
definition: A glucosinolic acid that is an alkylglucosinolic acid in which one on the carbons in the alkyl side-chain has been replaced by a sulfur or an oxidised sulfur.

name: ibha#10
definition: A 4-O-(1H-indol-3-ylcarbonyl)ascaroside that is icas#10 in which the pro-R hydrogen beta to the carboxy group is replaced by a hydroxy group.  It is a metabolite of the nematode Caenorhabditis elegans.

name: 2-methylbutylglucosinolic acid
definition: An  alkylglucosinolic acid that consists of 1-thio-beta-D-glucopyranose attached to a 3-methyl-N-(sulfooxy)pentanimidoyl group at the anomeric sulfur.

name: isobutylglucosinolic acid
definition: An alkylglucosinolic acid that consists of 1-thio-beta-D-glucopyranose attached to a 3-methyl-N-(sulfooxy)butanimidoyl group at the anomeric sulfur.

name: ibho#22
definition: An omega-hydroxy fatty acid ascaroside that is bhos#22 in which the hydroxy group at position 4 of the ascarylopyranose moiety has been has been converted to the corresponding 1H-indole-3-carboxylate ester. It is a metabolite of the nematode Caenorhabditis elegans.

name: elesclomol-Cu(II)
definition: The copper coordination entity formed from elesclomol by coordination to copper via the thiocarbonyl and hydrazino groups.

name: monovalent inorganic anion
definition: Any inorganic anion with a valency of one.

name: 2,3-dihydro-6-hydroxy-2-(4-hydroxyphenyl)-5,7-dimethoxy-4H-1-benzopyran-4-one
definition: A dimethoxyflavanone that is flavanone substituted by methoxy groups at positions 5 and 7 and hydroxy groups at positions 6 and 4'.

name: 2,3-dihydro-2-(4-hydroxyphenyl)-5,6,7-trimethoxy-4H-1-benzopyran-4-one
definition: A methoxyflavanone that is flavanone substituted by methoxy groups at positions 5, 6 and 7 and a hydroxy group at position 4'.

name: 2,2-dimethyl-3-[4-(acetyloxy)phenyl]-4-ethyl-2H-1-benzopyran-7-ol acetate
definition: A member of the class of  chromenes that is 2H-1-benzopyran-7-ol acetate substituted by methyl groups at positions 2 and 2, an ethyl group at position 4 and a 4-(acetyloxy)phenyl group at position 3 respectively.

name: 3,6,4'-trihydroxyflavone
definition: A trihydroxyflavone that is flavone substituted by hydroxy groups at positions 3, 6 and 4'.

name: 9-hydroxy-2,6-dichlorodibenzofuran
definition: A member of the class of dibenzofurans that is dibenzo[b,d]furan substituted by a hydroxy group at position 1 and chloro groups at positions 4 and 8 respectively.

name: 3-(3,4-dichlorophenyl)-1-hydroxy-1-methylurea
definition: A member of the class of ureas that is  1-methylurea substituted by a hydroxy group at position 1 and a 3,4-dichlorophenyl group at position 3.

name: 3-(allyloxy)estra-1,3,5(10)-triene-16alpha,17beta-diol
definition: A 16alpha-hydroxy steroid that is  estriol in which the hydroxy group at position 3 is replaced by an allyloxy group.

name: aureothin
definition: A C-nitro compound that is (3Z)-3-[(2E)-2-methyl-3-(4-nitrophenyl)prop-2-en-1-ylidene]tetrahydrofuran which is substituted by a 6-methoxy-3,5-dimethyl-4-oxo-4H-pyran-2-yl group at position 5. It is isolated from the soil bacterium, Streptomyces thioluteus and exhibits antitumor, antifungal, and insecticidal activities.

name: 7-hydroxy-2',4',5'-trimethoxyisoflavone
definition: A hydroxyisoflavone that is isoflavone substituted by a hydroxy group at position 7 and methoxy groups at the 2', 4' and 5' positions.

name: desmethylxanthohumol
definition: A member of the class of chalcones that is trans-chalcone substituted by hydroxy groups at positions 4, 2', 4', and 6'  and a 3-methylbut-2-en-1-yl group at position 3'.

name: 5,6-epoxyretinoic acid
definition: A retinoid obtained by epoxidation across the 5,6-double bond of retinoic acid.

name: 19-bromoaplysiatoxin
definition: A member of the class of aplysiatoxins that has the structure of the parent aplysiatoxin, but is carrying an additional bromo substituent on the benzene ring at the position ortho to the phenolic hydroxy group. It is a cyanotoxin produced by several species of freshwater and marine cyanobacteria, as well as algae and molluscs.

name: toxoflavin
definition: A pyrimidotriazine that is 1,6-dimethyl-1,5,6,7-tetrahydropyrimido[5,4-e][1,2,4]triazine with oxo groups at positions 5 and 7.

name: guvacoline
definition: The methyl ester of guvacine.

name: puerarin xyloside
definition: A hydroxyisoflavone that is puerarin substituted by an alpha-D-xylopyranosyl residue at position 7 via a glycosidic linkage.

name: 3beta-hydroxycholest-5-en-26-oic acid
definition: A steroid acid resulting from the oxidation of one of the terminal methyl groups of cholesterol to the corresponding aldehyde.

name: sakuranin
definition: A flavanone glycoside that is  sakuranetin attached to a beta-D-glucopyranosyl residue at position 5 via a glycosidic linkage.

name: genisteine
definition: A quinolizidine alkaloid that is sparteine in which the hydrogen atom at position 6 is in the beta-configuration.

name: kurarinol
definition: A trihydroxyflavanone that is (2S)-flavanone substituted by hydroxy groups at positions 7, 2' and 4' , a methoxy group at position 5 and a (2S)-5-hydroxy-5-methyl-2-(prop-1-en-2-yl)hexyl group at position 8 respectively.

name: allodeoxycholic acid
definition: An allo-bile acid that is 5alpha-cholan-24-oic acid bearing two alpha-hydroxy substituents at position 3 and 12.

name: allocholic acid
definition: An allo-bile acid that is 5alpha-cholan-24-oic acid bearing three alpha-hydroxy substituents at position 3, 7 and 12.

name: beta-nootkatol
definition: A 4,4a-dimethyl-6-(prop-1-en-2-yl)-2,3,4,4a,5,6,7,8-octahydronaphthalen-2-ol with (2S,4R,4aS,6R) stereochemistry.

name: dTDP-4-amino-2,3,4,6-tetradeoxy-alpha-D-glucose
definition: A pyrimidine nucleotide-sugar having thymine as the nucleobase and 4-amino-2,3,4,6-tetradeoxy-alpha-D-glucose as the sugar component.

name: 3-(1-hydroxyethyl)bacteriochlorophyllide a
definition: A chlorophyllide obtained by hydrolysis of the terpenoid ester moiety of 3-(1-hydroxyethyl)bacteriochlorophyll a.

name: bacteriochlorophyllide a
definition: A chlorophyllide obtained by hydrolysis of the terpenoid ester moiety of bacteriochlorophyll a.

name: resolvin E1
definition: A resolvin that is (6Z,8E,10E,14Z,16E)-icosa-6,8,10,14,16-pentaenoic acid which is substituted at positions 5, 12 and 18 by hydroxy groups (the 5S,12R,18R stereoisomer).

name: 18(R)-HEPE
definition: An 18-HEPE that consists of (5Z,8Z,11Z,14Z,16E)-icosapentaenoic in which the 18-hydroxy group has R-configuration.

name: resolvin D1
definition: A resolvin that is docosa-4Z,9E,11E,13Z,15E,19Z-hexaenoic acid which is substituted by hydroxy groups at the 7, 8, and 17 positions (the 7S,8R,17S-stereoisomer).

name: resolvin D2
definition: A member of the class of resolvins that is (4Z,8E,10Z,12E,14E,19Z)-docosahexaenoic acid carrying three hydroxy substituents at positions 7, 16 and 17 (the 7S,16R,17S-stereoisomer).

name: 1,2-dihydropyrene-2-carboxylic acid
definition: A member of the class of pyrenes that is 1,2-dihydropyrene substituted by a carboxy group at position 2.

name: 4-methyl-5-nitrocatechol
definition: A nitrotoluene that is 2-nitrotoluene carrying two hydroxy substituents at positions 4 and 5.

name: 2-hydroxy-5-methylquinone
definition: A member of the class of monohydroxy-1,4-benzoquinones that is 2-hydroxy-1,4-benzoquinone carrying an additional methyl substituent at position 5.

name: cis,cis-2,4-dihydroxy-5-methyl-6-oxo-2,4-hexadienoic acid
definition: A 2,4-dihydroxy-5-methyl-6-oxo-2,4-hexadienoic acid in which both double bonds adopt a cis-configuration.

name: (2Z,6Z,10Z,14Z,18Z,22Z,26Z,30Z,34E)-decaprenyl diphosphate
definition: A decaprenyl diphosphate having (Z)-stereochemistry about all but one of the double bonds.

name: (2S)-methylsuccinyl-CoA
definition: An acyl-CoA resulting from the formal condensation of the thiol group of coenzyme A with the 1-carboxy group of (2S)-methylsuccinic acid.

name: sodium L-ascorbic acid 2-phosphate
definition: An organic sodium salt that is the trisodium salt of L-ascorbic acid 2-phosphate. It is a stable vitamin C derivative which is a highly effective antioxidant that has demonstrated efficacy in treating acne.

name: 5,6,6'-trihydroxy-5'-methoxy[biphenyl]-3,3'-dicarboxylic acid
definition: A dicarboxylic acid that is 5,5',6,6'-tetrahydroxy[biphenyl]-3,3'dicarboxylic acid in which one of the hydroxy groups that is meta to a carboxy group has been converted into the corresponding methyl ether.

name: asulam
definition: A carbamate ester that is methyl carbamate substituted by a (4-aminophenyl)sulfonyl group at the nitrogen atom. A dihydropteroate synthase inhibitor, it is used (normally as the corresponding sodium salt, asulam-sodium) as a herbicide, mainly for killing bracken.

name: chlorhexidine acetate
definition: The acetate salt of chlorhexidine. It is a disinfectant used for bacterial control in hospital, agricultural and domestic environments.

name: diminazene
definition: A triazene derivative that is triazene in which each of the terminal nitrogens is substituted by a 4-carbamimidoylphenyl group.

name: tolclofos-methyl
definition: An organic thiophosphate that is 2,6-dichloro-4-methylphenol in which the hydrogen of the hydroxy group group has been replaced by a dimethoxyphosphorothioyl group. Tolclofos-methyl is a phospholipid biosynthesis inhibitor and fungicide that is used for controlling soil-borne diseases caused by Typhula incarnata, Corticium rolfsii, Typhula ishikariensis, and Rhizoctonia solani.

name: benthiavalicarb-isopropyl
definition: A carbamate ester that is the isopropyl ester of benthiavalicarb. It is used as an agricultural fungicide.

name: desmedipham
definition: A carbamate ester that is phenylcarbamic acid in which the hydrogen of the hydroxy group has been replaced by a 3-[(ethoxycarbonyl)amino]phenyl group. It is an agrochemical used as a herbicide.

name: pyributicarb
definition: A monothiocarbamic ester that is carbamic acid in which the oxygen of the oxo group is replaced by sulfur, the hydrogens attached to the nitrogen are replaced by methyl and 6-methoxypyridin-2-yl groups, and the hydrogen of the hydroxy group is replaced by a p-tert-butylphenyl group. It has fungicidal and herbicidal activity and is used in paddy rice and turf production.

name: azimsulfuron
definition: An N-sulfonylurea that is urea in which a nitrogen attached to one of the nitrogens has been replaced by a 4,6-dipyrimidin-2-yl group while a hydrogen attached to the other urea nitrogen has been replaced by a [1-methyl-4-(2-methyl-2H-tetrazol-5-yl)-1H-pyrazol-5-yl]sulfonyl group. An acetolactate synthase inhibitor, it is used as a herbicide for the control of a variety of broad-leaved and sedge weeds in paddy fields and other aquatic situations.

name: amobam
definition: A dithiocarbamate salt resulting from the formal reaction of ethylenebis(dithiocarbamic acid) with 2 mol eq. of ammonia. A water-soluble crystalline solid, it is a fungicide used to protect fruit, vegetable, and field crops against a wide spectrum of fungal diseases. Mixing amobam with zinc sulfate affords the fungicide zineb.

name: propineb
definition: A polymeric complex of zinc with the propylene 1,2-bis(dithiocarbamate) anionic ligand. A fungicide, it is used to control a wide range of fungal diseases, including downy mildew, brown rot, black rot, red fire, leaf spot, and blight in crops such as grapes, tomatoes, potatoes, berries, citrus, rice and tea.

name: bispyribac-sodium
definition: The organic sodium salt of bispyribac. It is used as a broad spectrum post-emergent herbicide for the control of grasses, sedges and broadleaf weeds in rice crops.

name: cyproconazole
definition: A diastereoisomeric mixture composed of the enantiomeric pair (2R,3S)- and (2S,3R)-cyproconazole in ratio 1:1 with the enantiomeric pair (2R,3R)- and (2S,3S)-cyproconazole. A broad spectrum fungicide, it is used on cereals and other field crops used to control Septoria, rust, powdery mildew and other diseases.

name: diclomezine
definition: A pyridazinone that is pyridazin-3(2H)-one which is substituted at position 6 by a 3,5-dichloro-4-methylphenyl group. A fugicide, it is used to treat rice sheath blight caused by Rhizoctonia solani.

name: difenoconazole
definition: A member of the class of dioxolanes that is 1,3-dioxolane substituted at position 2 by 2-chloro-4-(4-chlorophenoxy)phenyl and 1,2,4-triazol-1-ylmethyl groups.  A broad spectrum fungicide with novel broad-range activity used as a spray or seed treatment. It is moderately toxic to humans, mammals, birds and most aquatic organisms.

name: etridiazole
definition: A member of the class of  thiadiazoles that is 1,2,4-thiadiazole which is substituted at positions 3 and 5 by trichloromethyl and ethoxy groups, respectively. A fungicide, it has been used particularly for the control of Phytophthora and Pythium species in soils.

name: fenbuconazole
definition: A racemate comprising equimolar amounts of (R)- and (S)-fenbuconazole. A fungicide used to control a range of diseases including powdery mildew, black rot and scab.

name: hexaconazole
definition: A racemate comprising equimolar amounts of (R)- and (S)-hexaconazole. An agricultural fungicide introduced in the 1980s, it is not approved for use within the European Union.

name: imibenconazole
definition: A member of the class of imidothioates that is the S-4-chlorobenzyl thioester of N-(2,4-dichlorophenyl)-2-(1H-1,2,4-triazol-1-yl)ethanimidothioic acid. Used to control a range of fungal diseases affecting fruit, vegetables, turf and ornamentals. It has a low mammalian toxicity and shows a moderate level of toxicity to fish, daphnia and earthworms but is relatively non-toxic to honey bees, birds and algae.

name: ipconazole
definition: A member of the class of cyclopentanols carrying 1,2,4-triazol-1-ylmethyl, 4-chlorobenzyl and isopropyl substituents at positions 1, 2 and 5 respectively. Used to control a range of seed diseases in rice, vegetables and other, mainly non-food, crops.

name: mepiquat chloride
definition: A quaternary ammonium salt consisting of equimolar amounts of mepiquat cations and chloride anions. A plant growth regulator, it is used in agriculture to reduce vegetative growth including sprout suppression in garlic, leeks and onions.

name: pefurazoate
definition: A racemate comprising equimolar amounts of (R)- and (S)-pefurazoate. Pefurazoate is a seed treatment with preventative and curative activity against ascomycetes, basidiomycetes and deuteromycetes.

name: penthiopyrad
definition: A racemate comprising equimolar amounts of (R)- and (S)-penthiopyrad. Used to control rust and Rhizoctonia diseases and also shows activity against grey mould, powdery mildew and apple scab.

name: probenazole
definition: A member of the class of 1,2-benzothiazoles that is 1,2-benzothiazole 1,1-dioxide substituted at position 3 by an allyloxy group. A fungicide used to control rice blast.

name: pyriminobac-methyl
definition: A benzoate ester resulting from the formal condensation of the carboxy group of pyriminobac with methanol.

name: tricyclazole
definition: A triazolobenzothiazole that is [1,2,4]triazolo[3,4-b][1,3]benzothiazole which is substituted at position 5 by a methyl group. A fungicide used for the control of rice blast, it is not approved for use within the European Union.

name: triflumizole
definition: A carboxamidine resulting from the formal condensation of the amino group of 4-chloro-2-(trifluoromethyl)aniline with the oxygen of the acetyl group of N-(propoxyacetyl)imidazole. A sterol demethylation inhibitor, it is used as a fungicide for the control of powdery mildew, scab and other diseases on a variety of crops.

name: uniconazole P
definition: A (1E)-1-(4-chlorophenyl)-4,4-dimethyl-2-(1H-1,2,4-triazol-1-yl)pent-1-en-3-ol that has S configuration at the chiral centre. It is the enantiomer of (R)-uniconazole; the fungicide and plant growth retardant uniconazole is the racemic mixture comprising (R)-uniconazole and uniconazole-P.

name: cymoxanil
definition: A member of the class of ureas that is urea in which the two nitrogen atoms are substituted by an ethyl group and a 2-cyano-2-(methoxyimino)acetyl group respectively. A fungicide used to control Peronosporales on a range of crops including vines, hops and potatoes.

name: dimethenamid
definition: A racemate composed of equimolar amounts of (R)- and (S)-dimethenamid. A herbicide, it is applied to the soil for the control of various broad-leaved weeds and grasses. Only the S enantiomer (generally known as dimethenamid-P) is active.

name: flutolanil
definition: A member of the class of benzamides, obtained by formal condensation of the carboxy group of 2-(trifluoromethyl)benzoic acid with the amino group of 3-(ispropyloxy)aniline.  A fungicide used to control a range of pathogens especially Rhizoctonia spp. on rice, turf and other crops.

name: furametpyr
definition: A racemate comprising equimolar amounts of (R)- and (S)-furametpyr. A fungicide used to control rice sheath blight.

name: thifluzamide
definition: An aromatic amide obtained by formal condensation of the carboxy group of 2-methyl-4-(trifluoromethyl)thiazole-5-carboxylic acid with the amino group of 2,6-dibromo-4-(trifluoromethoxy)aniline. Used to control Rhizoctonia spp. diseases on rice, potatoes, maize, grass and other crops.

name: cyflufenamid
definition: A member of the class of (trifluoromethyl)benzenes that is 2,3-difluoro-6-(trifluoromethyl)benzenecarboxamidine in which the hydrogen attached to the imino nitrogen is replaced by a cyclopropylmethoxy group while one of the hydrogens attached to the other nitrogen is replaced by a phenylacetyl group. It is used as a fungicide for the control of powdery mildew in cereal crops as well as in apple and pear orchards.

name: cyflumetofen
definition: A racemate comprising equimolar amounts of (R)- and (S)-cyflumetofen. A proacaricide (via ester hydrolysis and subsequent decarboxylation), it is used to control phytophagous mites at all development stages in a variety of fruit crops. It acts as an inhibitor of complex II of mitochondrial electron transport chain.

name: diclocymet
definition: A diastereoisomeric mixture comprising equimolar amounts of (1R,2S)- and (1R,2R)-diclocymet. A fungicide used for the control of rice blast in paddy fields. It also shows some activity against paddy field insect pests including rice water weevil and rice-stem borer. Diclocymet is moderately toxic to fish.

name: fenoxanil
definition: A four component diastereoisomeric mixture composed of the diastereomeric pair (R,R)- and (R,S)-fenoxanil in an 85:15 ratio with the diastereomeric pair (S,R)- and (S,S)-fenoxanil. A fungicide used mainly for control of rice blast.

name: flusulfamide
definition: A sulfonamide resulting from the formal condensation 4-chloro-3-(trifluoromethyl)benzenesulfonic acid with 2-chloro-4-nitroaniline. A fungicide, it is used to control Plasmodiophora brassicae in brassicas and Polymyxa betae in sugarbeet.

name: mandipropamid
definition: A racemate comprising equimolar amounts of (R)- and (S)-mandipropamid. An agricultural fungicide, it is used to control late blight and downy mildew in many salad, vegetable and fruit crops.

name: fluazifop
definition: A racemate comprising equimolar amounts of (R)-fluazipop (the active enantiomer, also known as fluazifop-P) and (S)-fluazifop (the inactive enantiomer). Both fluazifop and fluazifop-P have been used (generally as the corresponidng n-butyl esters, known as fluazifop-butyl and fluazifop-P-butyl, respectively) as herbicides for the pre-emergence control of grass weeds in a variety of crops.

name: quizalofop-ethyl
definition: A racemate coprising equimolar amounts of  quizalofop-P-ethyl and its enantiomer, (S)-quizalofop-ethyl. A proherbicide for quizalofop.

name: benzobicyclon
definition: A racemate comprising equimolar amounts of (1R,5S) and (1S,5R)-benzobicyclon. It is a pro-herbicide (by hydroyltic loss of the phenylthio group to afford the corresponding meso-triketone) used for the control of both annual and perennial weeds in rice.

name: trinexapac-ethyl
definition: An ethyl ester resulting from the formal condensation of the carboxy group of trinexapac with ethanol.

name: mepronil
definition: A member of the class of benzamides, obtained by formal condensation of the carboxy group of 2-methylbenzoic acid with the amino group of 3-(ispropyloxy)aniline. A fungicide used to control diseases caused by Basidomycetes including Rhizoctonia and Puccinia spp.

name: trifloxystrobin
definition: The methyl ester of (2E)-(methoxyimino)[2-({[(E)-{1-[3-(trifluoromethyl)phenyl]ethylidene}amino]oxy}methyl)phenyl]acetic acid. A foliar applied fungicide for cereals which is particularly active against Ascomycetes, Deuteromycetes and Oomycetes

name: thallium sulfate
definition: A metal sulfate in which the counterion is thallium  and the ratio of thallium to sulfate is 2:1. It is a rodenticide used to control rats, squirrels, mice, moles, prairie dogs, ants and cockroaches. It is no longer registered for pesticide use in the United States.

name: chloridazon
definition: A pyridazinone that is pyridazin-3(2H)-one substituted by an amino group at position 5, a chloro group at position 4 and a phenyl group at position 2.

name: ferimzone
definition: A member of the class of pyrimidines that is 2-hydrazino-4,6-dimethylpyrimidine in which the two amino hydrogens are replaced by a 1-(2-methylphenyl)ethylidene group. It is used for the control of fungal diseases in rice.

name: amisulbrom
definition: A member of the class of bromoindoles that is 3-bromo-6-fluoro-2-methylindole substituted at position 1 by a 1-(dimethylsulfamyl)-1,2,4-triazole-3-sulfonyl group. A fungicide for use on potatoes to control late blight (Phytophthora infestans) and downy mildew [Plasmopara viticola). It has a low mammalian toxicity but it is considered to be a reproduction toxicant, is moderately toxic to birds and honey bees but poses a greater risk to aquatic species and earthworms.

name: pentoxazone
definition: An oxazolidinone that is 1,3-oxazolidine-2,4-dione which is substituted on the nitrogen (position 3) by a 4-chloro-5-(cyclopentyloxy)-2-fluorophenyl group, and at position 5 by an isopropylidene group. A protoporphyrinogen oxidase inhibitor, it is used as a pre- and post-emergence herbicide to control weeds in rice.

name: imazamox
definition: A racemate composed of equimolar amounts of (S)- and (R)-imazamox. An inhibitor of acetohydroxyacid synthase, it is used (particularly as the corresponding ammonium salt, known as imazamox-ammonium) as a herbicide for the control of grass, broad-leaf weeds, and pond weed.

name: fenpropidin
definition: A racemate comprising equimolar amounts of (R)- and (S)-fenpropidin. A systemic fungicide, it is used for the control of foliar diseases in cereals and sugar beet.

name: fomesafen
definition: An N-sulfonylcarboxamide that is N-(methylsulfonyl)benzamide in which the phenyl ring is substituted by a nitro group at position 2 and a 2-chloro-4-(trifluoromethyl)phenoxy group at position 5. A protoporphyrinogen oxidase inhibitor, it was specially developed for use (generally as the corresponding sodium salt, fomesafen-sodium) for post-emergence control of broad-leaf weeds in soya.

name: octhilinone
definition: A member of the class of 1,2-thiazole that is 1,2-thiazol-3-one substituted on the nitrogen (position 2) by an octyl group. A fungicide and antibacterial agent, it is used for treatment of canker and other fungal and bacterial diseases in fruit trees. It is no longer approved for use within the European Union.

name: captafol
definition: A dicarboximide that captan in which the trichloromethyl group is replaced by a 1,1,2,2-tetrachloroethyl group. A broad-spectrum fungicide used to control diseases in fruit and potatoes, it is no longer approved for use in the European Community.

name: prosulfocarb
definition: A monothiocarbamic ester that is carbamothioic S-acid substituted by two propyl groups at the nitrogen atom and a benzyl group at the the sulfur atom.

name: dodemorph
definition: A member of the class of morpholines that is 2,6-dimethylmorpholine in which the hydrogen attached to the nitrogen is replaced by a cyclododecyl group. It is a fungicide used for the control of powdery mildew, particularly in rose culture.

name: ofurace
definition: A racemate comprising equal amounts of (R)- and (S)-ofurace.

name: penconazole
definition: A racemate comprising equal amounts of (R)- and (S)-penconazole. A fungicide used to control powdery mildew, scab and other pathogenic Ascomycetes, Basidiomycetes and Deuteromycetes.

name: fluometuron
definition: A member of the class of 3-(3,4-substituted-phenyl)-1,1-dimethylureas that is urea in which one of the nitrogens is substituted by a 3-(trifluoromethyl)phenyl group while the other is substituted by two methyl groups. It is a herbicide used for the control of broadleaf weeds and annual grasses in cotton.

name: pyriminobac
definition: A member of the class of benzoic acids that is benzoic acid substituted by a (4,6-dimethoxypyrimidin-2-yl)oxy group at position 2 and a N-methoxyethanimidoyl group at position 6. It is a herbicide.

name: quinoxyfen
definition: A member of the class of quinolines carrying two chloro substituents at positions 5 and 7 together with a 4-fluorophenoxy substituent at position 4. A fungicide used mainly to control powdery mildew in cereals.

name: tebutam
definition: A monocarboxylic acid amide that is propanamide substituted by a benzyl and an isopropyl group at the nitrogen atom and two methyl groups at position 2. It is an agrochemical used as a herbicide.

name: anilazine
definition: A member of the class of triazenes that is dichlorotriazene in which the hydrogen is replaced by an o-chloroanilino group. A fungicide formerly used to control leaf spots and downy mildew, it is no longer approved for use within the European Union.

name: prothiocarb
definition: A monothiocarbamic ester that is ethanethiol in which the hydrogen attached to the sulfur is replaced by a [3-(dimethylamino)propyl]carbamoyl group. Formerly used (generally as the hydrochloride salt) as an agricultural fungicide, it is not approved for use within the European Union.

name: binapacryl
definition: A racemate comprising equimolar amounts of (R)- and (S)-binapacryl.  An obsolete fungicide and acaricide once used to control of panonychid and tetranychid mites on certain fruits, mainly apple, and vegetables.

name: rac-1,2-dichloropropane
definition: A racemate comprising equimolar amounts of (R)- and (S)-1,2-dichloropropane. It is used as a fumigant to control nematodes in soil and insects in stored grain.

name: tricamba
definition: A methoxybenzoic acid that is 2-methoxybenzoic acid which is substituted at position 3, 5, and 6 by chlorines.

name: benzoyl chloride
definition: An acyl chloride consisting of benzene in which a hydrogen is replaced by an acyl chloride group. It is an important chemical intermediate for the manufacture of other chemicals, dyes, perfumes, herbicides and pharmaceuticals.

name: carbon black
definition: An elemental carbon in the form of virtually pure colloidal particles that are produced by incomplete combustion or thermal decomposition of gaseous or liquid hydrocarbons under controlled conditions. A black, finely divided pellet or powder, its properties of specific surface area, particle size and structure, conductivity and colour can be varied by varying the exact conditions for its production. It is used in tyres, rubber and plastic products, printing inks and coatings.

name: 4-(methylnitrosamino)-1-(3-pyridyl)-1-butanol
definition: A member of the class of nitrosamines that is butan-1-ol substituted by a pyridin-3-yl group at position 1 and by a methyl(nitroso)amino group at position 4. It is a major metabolite of nitrosamine 4-(methylnitrosamino)-1-(3-pyridyl)-1-butanone (NNK), which is a carcinogen found in tobacco and responsible for inducing lung cancer in smokers.

name: eprinomectin
definition: A mixture of semisynthetic avermectin derivatives comprising >=90% eprinomectin component B1a (R = CH3) and <=10% eprinomectin component B1b (R = H). It is used for the treatment of internal and external parasites in cattle.

name: eprinomectin component B1a
definition: An avermectin analogue that is avermectin A1a in which the methoxy group attached to the tetrahydrobenzofuranyl moiety is replaced by a hydroxy group and in which the hydroxy group at position 4 of the terminal 2,6-dideoxy-3-O-methyl-alpha-L-arabino-hyxopoyranosyl group is replaced by an acetamido group.

name: eprinomectin component B1b
definition: An avermectin analogue that is eprinomectin B1a in which the butan-2-yl substituent of the spiroketal moiety is replaced by an isopropyl group.

name: diminazene diaceturate
definition: An N-acetylglycinate salt resulting from the reaction of diminazene with 2 mol eq. of N-acetylglycine.

name: N-acetylglycinate salt
definition: Any salt prepared using N-acetylglycine as the acid component.

name: leucascandrolide A congener
definition: A synthetic macrolide that is an analogue of the marine metabolite leucascandrolide A that exhibits comparable antiproliferative properties.

name: trehalose 6,6'-dimycolate
definition: A trehalose mycolate compound consisting of two C58 mycolate groups attached to the 6- and 6'-positions of alpha,alpha'-trehalose. A mycobacterial cell wall glycolipid.

name: 15(R)-HPETE
definition: A HPETE that is (5Z,8Z,11Z,13E,15R)-icosa-5,8,11,13-tetraenoic acid with the hydroperoxy group located at position 15 (the R-enantiomer).

name: prostaglandin G2(1-)
definition: A prostaglandin carboxylic acid anion that is the conjugate base of prostaglandin G2, obtained by deprotonation of the carboxy group; major species at pH 7.3.

name: phytochrome chromophore
definition: A chromophore that is a linear tetrapyrrolic prosthetic group covalently attached to a large soluble protein phytochrome. Light absorption by the phytochrome chromophore triggers photoconversion between two spectrally distinct forms of the photoreceptor: Pr, the red light absorbing form, and Pfr, the far-red light absorbing form.

name: gepinacin
definition: A monocarboxylic acid amide obtained by formal condensation of the carboxy group of 3-isobutoxyphenoxyacetic acid with the amino group of 4-methoxyaniline.

name: BODIPY-3823
definition: A BODIPY compound that is 4,4-difluoro-4-bora-3a,4a-diaza-s-indacene substituted at position 5 by a methyl group and at position 3 by a 11-carboxyundecyl group.

name: 4-[(1S)-1-hydroxy-2-{[(2R)-4-(4-hydroxyphenyl)butan-2-yl]amino}ethyl]phenol
definition: A 4-(1-hydroxy-2-{[4-(4-hydroxyphenyl)butan-2-yl]amino}ethyl)phenol in which the carbon bearing the hydroxy group has S configuration while the remaining stereocentre has R configuration.

name: nolinospiroside F
definition: A spirostanyl glycoside that is isolated from Ophiopogon japonicus and exhibits antioxidant properties.

name: animal growth promotant
definition: Substances that are administered to farmed animals to improve productivity by promoting weight gain, increasing muscle mass, limiting fat deposition, reducing feed consumption, and reducing waste production.

name: curvularol
definition: An organic heterotricyclic compound that is isolated from the fermentation broth of Curvularia sp. RK97-F166.

name: diatomaceous earth
definition: A form of silicon dioxide composed of skeletons of prehistoric diatoms (a type of hard-shelled algae). It can absorb up to four times its weight in water, and is used as an absorbent, filtration aid, and mild abrasive.

name: DH334
definition: An organic bromide salt having 9-benzyl-2-butyl-1-(2-chlorophenyl)-9H-beta-carbolin-2-ium as the counterion

name: elemental iron
definition: An elemental molecular entity in which all of the atoms have atomic number 26.

name: iron(0)
definition: An elemental iron in which the atom has an oxidation state of zero.

name: EC 2.7.11.22 (cyclin-dependent kinase) inhibitor
definition: An EC 2.7.11.* (protein-serine/threonine kinase) inhibitor that interferes with the action of cyclin-dependent kinase (EC 2.7.11.22).

name: DH334(1+)
definition: An organic cation that is DH334 lacking the bromide couterion.

name: DH335
definition: An organic bromide salt having 9-benzyl-2-butyl-9H-beta-carbolin-2-ium as the counterion

name: DH335(1+)
definition: An organic cation that is DH335 lacking the bromide couterion.

name: AS-I-145
definition: An indolecarboxamide obtained by the formal condensation of the carboxy group of 5,6,7-trimethoxyindole-2-carboxylic acid with the 2-amino group of 1-(2-chloroethyl)-2,4-diaminonaphthalene.

name: ELQ-271
definition: A member of the class of quinolones that is 2-methylquinolin-4(1H)-one in which the hydrogen at position 3 is replaced by a 4-[4-(trifluoromethoxy)phenoxy]phenyl group. A potent inhibitor of Toxoplasma gondii growth.

name: syrbactin
definition: A class of azamacrocyclic natural products with a 2,7-dioxo-1,6-diazacyclododecane skeleton that includes the syringolin, glidobactin and cepafungin natural product families. In addition to their related molecular frameworks, members of the class share similar biosynthesis pathways and identical modes-of-action, being irreversible proteasome inhibitor that inhibit all three activities of eukaryotic proteasomes.

name: pomecin A
definition: A polyunsaturated fatty acid that is tetradec-9-ene-11,13-diynoic acid in which the terminal acetylenic hydrogen is replaced by a 2-furyl group. Shows potent and broad-spectrum activity in vitro against Candida, Aspergillus, and Trichophyton spp.,

name: 2-amino-6,7-dimethyl-4-oxo-8-(1'-D-ribityl)-4,8-dihydropteridine
definition: A member of the family of pteridines that is 2-amino-6,7-dimethyl-4-oxo-4,8-dihydropteridine in which the hydrogen at position 8 is replaced by a D-ribityl group.

name: alpha-D-Manp-(1->2)-alpha-D-Manp-(1->3)-[alpha-D-Manp-(1->3)-[alpha-D-Manp-(1->2)-alpha-D-Manp-(1->6)]-alpha-D-Manp-(1->6)]-beta-D-Manp-(1->4)-beta-D-GlcpNAc-(1->4)-D-GlcpNAc
definition: An amino nonasaccharide that is the linear pentasaccharide alpha-D-Man-(1->2)-alpha-D-Man-(1->3)-beta-D-Man-(1->4)-beta-D-GlcNAc-(1->4)-D-GlcNAc in which the mannosyl residue nearest the reducing end has the branched tetrasaccharide alpha-D-Man-(1->3)-[alpha-D-Man-(1->2)-alpha-D-Man-(1->6)]-alpha-D-Man attached at position 6.

name: alpha-D-Manp-(1->2)-[alpha-D-Manp-(1->6)]-alpha-D-Manp-(1->3)-[alpha-D-Manp-(1->3)-[alpha-D-Manp-(1->6)]-alpha-D-Manp-(1->6)]-beta-D-Manp-(1->4)-beta-D-GlcpNAc-(1->4)-D-GlcpNAc
definition: An amino nonasaccharide that consists of the disaccharide beta-D-GlcpNAc-(1->4)-D-GlcpNAc having a branched heptamannosyl moiety attached at position 4.

name: ridaforolimus
definition: A semisynthetic derivative that is sirolimus in which the hydroxy group attached to the cyclohexyl moiety has been converted to the corresponding dimethylphosphinate.

name: 3beta-hydroxy-7-oxo-5beta-cholan-24-oic acid
definition: A monohydroxy-5beta-cholanic acid that is (5beta)-cholan-24-oic acid substituted by beta-hydroxy and oxo groups at positions 3 and 7 respectively.

name: 7-oxolithocholic acid
definition: A bile acid that is lithocholic acid carrying an additional oxo substituent at position 7.

name: monounsaturated fatty acid anion
definition: Any unsaturated fatty acid anion with one double or triple bond in the fatty acid chain.

name: 3-methoxy-5-methyl-1-naphthoic acid
definition: A naphthoic acid that is 1-naphthoic acid carrying additional methoxy and methyl substituents at positions 3 and 5 respectively.

name: vitexin 2''-O-beta-L-rhamnoside
definition: A trihydroxyflavone that is vitexin having a beta-L-rhamnosyl residue attached at the 2''-position of the glucitol moiety.

name: O-[2'-(5-phosphoribosyl)-3'-dephospho-CoA]-L-serine(3-) residue
definition: An organic anionic group obtained by deprotonation of the phosphate and diphosphate OH groups of O-[2'-(5-phosphoribosyl)-3'-dephospho-CoA]-L-serine residue.

name: Mo(=O)(=S)-molybdopterin cofactor(2-)
definition: An organophosphate oxoanion obtained by deprotonation of the phosphate OH groups of Mo(=O)(=S)-molybdopterin cofactor; major species at pH 7.3.

name: 2-oxohept-4-ene-1,7-dioic acid
definition: An oxo dicarboxylic acid that is 2-oxohept-4-ene in which the two terminal methyl groups are replaced by carboxy groups.

name: 5-(2-hydroxyethyl)-1,3-thiazole
definition: A 1,3-thiazole in which the only substituent is a 2-hydroxyethyl group at position 5.

name: alpha-L-Fucp-(1->6)-D-GlcpNAc
definition: An amino disaccharide consisting of N-acetyl-D-glucosamine having an alpha-L-fucosyl residue attached at the 6-position.

name: 2,3-diacyl-1-(3-O-sulfo-beta-D-galactosyl)-sn-glycerol
definition: A 1,2-diacyl-3-(3-O-sulfo-beta-D-galactosyl)glycerol in which the configuration of the glycerol moiety is such that the acyl groups are at positions 2 and 3 using the Stereospecific Numbering convention.

name: 2,3-diacyl-1-(3-O-sulfo-beta-D-galactosyl)-sn-glycerol(1-)
definition: A 1,2-diacyl-3-(3-O-sulfo-beta-D-galactosyl)glycerol(1-) resulting from the deprotonation of the sulfate group of 2,3-diacyl-1-(3-O-sulfo-beta-D-galactosyl)-sn-glycerol. The major species at pH 7.3.

name: alpha-D-GalpA-(1->4)-alpha-D-GalpA-(1->4)-alpha-D-GalpA
definition: A trisaccharide in which three alpha-D-galactopyranuronic acid units are joined via (1->4)-linkages.

name: alpha-D-GalpA-(1->4)-alpha-D-GalpA-(1->4)-alpha-D-GalpA-(1->4)-alpha-D-GalpA
definition: A tetraisaccharide in which four alpha-D-galactopyranuronic acid units are joined via (1->4)-linkages.

name: 2-[(3S)-3-carboxylato-3-(methylammonio)propyl]-L-histidine residue
definition: A zwitterionic group obtained by transfer of a proton from the amino to the carboxy group of 2-[(3S)-3-carboxy-3-(methylamino)propyl]-L-histidine residue; major species at pH 7.3.

name: alpha-D-GlcpA4Me-(1->2)-beta-D-Xylp-(1->4)-beta-D-Xylp-(1->4)-beta-D-Xylp
definition: A tetrasaccharide derivative that consists of an 4-O-methyl-alpha-D-glucuronosyl residue attached at the 2-position of the non-reducing end of xylotriose.

name: 2-[(3S)-3-carboxylato-3-(dimethylammonio)propyl]-L-histidine residue
definition: A zwitterionic group obtained by transfer of a proton from the amino to the carboxy group of 2-[(3S)-3-carboxy-3-(dimethylamino)propyl]-L-histidine residue; major species at pH 7.3.

name: diphthine betaine residue
definition: A zwitterionic group that is the conjugate base of diphthine residue, obtained by deprotonation of the carboxy group; major species at pH 7.3.

name: N-(ADP-D-ribosyl)diphthamide(1-) residue
definition: An organic anionic group obtained by deprotonation of the diphosphate OH groups of N-(ADP-D-ribosyl)diphthamide residue.

name: suvorexant
definition: An aromatic amide obtained by formal condensation of the carboxy group of 5-methyl-2-(2H-1,2,3-triazol-2-yl)benzoic acid with the secondary amino group of 5-chloro-2-[(5R)-5-methyl-1,4-diazepan-1-yl]-1,3-benzoxazole. An orexin receptor antagonist used for the management of insomnia.

name: idelalisib
definition: A member of the class of quinazolines that is 5-fluoro-3-phenylquinazolin-4-one in which the hydrogen at position 2 is replaced by a (1S)-1-(3H-purin-6-ylamino)propyl group. used for for the treatment of refractory indolent non-Hodgkin's lymphoma and relapsed chronic lymphocytic leukemia.

name: vorapaxar
definition: A carbamate ester that is the ethyl ester of [(1R,3aR,4aR,6R,8aR,9S,9aS)-9-{(E)-2-[5-(3-fluorophenyl)pyridin-2-yl]ethynyl}-1-methyl-3-oxododecahydronaphtho[2,3-c]furan-6-yl]carbamic acid. A protease-activated receptor-1 antagonist used (as its sulfate salt) for the reduction of thrombotic cardiovascular events in patients with a history of myocardial infarction (MI) or with peripheral arterial disease. It has been shown to reduce the rate of a combined endpoint of cardiovascular death, MI, stroke and urgent coronary revascularisation.

name: N(alpha)-(L-gamma-glutamyl)-hercynyl-L-cysteine sulfoxide(1-)
definition: A peptide anion that is the conjugate base of N(alpha)-(L-gamma-glutamyl)-hercynyl-L-cysteine sulfoxide and major species at pH 7.3.

name: N(alpha)-(L-gamma-glutamyl)-hercynyl-L-selenocysteine(1-)
definition: A peptide anion that is the conjugate base of N(alpha)-(L-gamma-glutamyl)-hercynyl-L-selenocysteine and major species at pH 7.3.

name: hercynylselenocysteine zwitterion
definition: An L-alpha-amino acid zwitterion formed from hercynylselenocysteine by transfer of a proton from the carboxy to the amino group; major species at pH 7.3.

name: hercynylcysteine sulfoxide zwitterion
definition: An L-alpha-amino acid zwitterion formed from hercynylcysteine sulfoxide by transfer of a proton from the carboxy to the amino group; major species at pH 7.3.

name: ergothioneine thione form
definition: A L-histidine derivative that is N(alpha),N(alpha),N(alpha)-trimethyl-L-histidine in which the hydrogen at position 2 on the imdazole ring is replaced by a thioxo group.

name: AT7867
definition: A member of the class of piperidines carrying two aryl substituents (4-chlorophenyl and 4-(pyrazol-4-yl)phenyl) at position 4.

name: S-aryl-L-cysteine zwitterion
definition: An S-substituted L-cysteine zwitterion in which the S-substitutuent can be any aryl group.

name: S-alkyl-L-cysteine zwitterion
definition: An S-substituted L-cysteine zwitterion in which the S-substituent can be any alkyl group.

name: aryl thiol
definition: An aryl thiol is a thiol in which a sulfanyl group, SH, is attached to an aryl group.

name: SD-06
definition: A member of the class of pyrazoles that is 1H-pyrazole in which the hydrogens at positions 3, 4, and 5 are replaced by N-(hydroxyacetyl)piperidin-4-yl, pyrimidin-4-yl and p-chlorophenyl groups, respectively.

name: SB220025
definition: Am member of the class of imidazoles carrying piperidin-4-yl, 4-fluophenyl and 2-aminopyrimidin-4-yl substituents at posiitons 1, 4 and 5 respectively.

name: N-cyclopropyl-3-{[1-(2,4-difluorophenyl)-7-methyl-6-oxo-6,7-dihydropyrazolo[3,4-b]pyridin-4-yl]amino}-4-methylbenzamide
definition: A member of the class of benzamides obtained by formal condensation of the carboxy group of 3-{[1-(2,4-difluorophenyl)-7-methyl-6-oxo-6,7-dihydropyrazolo[3,4-b]pyridin-4-yl]amino}-4-methylbenzoic acid with the amino group of cyclopropylamine.

name: PH 797804
definition: A member of the class of benzamides obtained by formal condensation of the carboxy group of 3-{3-bromo-4-[(2,4-difluorobenzyl)oxy]-6-methyl-2-oxopyridin-1-yl}-4-methylbenzoic acid with the amino group of methylamine.

name: eprazinone
definition: A member of the class of piperazines in which the two amino hydrogens of piperazine are replaced by 2-benzoylpropyl and 2-ethoxy-2-phenylethyl groups.

name: tedizolid
definition: A member of the class of pyridines that is pyridine which is substituted by a 2-methyl-2H-tetrazol-5-yl group at position 2 and by a 2-fluoro-4-[(5R)-5-(hydroxymethyl)-2-oxo-1,3-oxazolidin-3-yl]phenyl group at position 5. It is used as its phosphate pro-drug used for the treatment of acute bacterial skin and skin structure infections caused by certain susceptible bacteria, including Staphylococcus aureus (including methicillin-resistant strains (MRSA) and methicillin-susceptible strains), various Streptococcus species, and Enterococcus faecalis.

name: efinaconazole
definition: A member of the class of triazoles that is butan-2-ol which is substituted at positions 1, 2, and 3 by 1,2,4-triazol-1-yl, 2,4-difluorophenyl, and 4-methylenepiperidin-1-yl groups, respectively (the 2R,3R stereoisomer). It is an antifungal drug used for the topical treatment of onychomycosis (a nail infection caused mainly by dermatophytes).

name: orciprenaline
definition: A racemate composed of equimolar amounts of (R)- and (S)-orciprenaline. Used (as its sulfate salt) to relax the airway muscles and improve breathing for patients suffering from asthma or bronchitis.

name: empagliflozin
definition: A C-glycosyl compound consisting of a beta-glucosyl residue having a (4-chloro-3-{4-[(3S)-tetrahydrofuran-3-yloxy]benzyl}phenyl group at the anomeric centre. A sodium-glucose co-transporter 2 inhibitor used as an adjunct to diet and exercise to improve glycemic control in adults with type 2 diabetes mellitus.

name: dalbavancin
definition: A semisynthetic glycopeptide used for the treatment of acute bacterial skin and skin structure infections caused or suspected to be caused by susceptible isolates of designated Gram-positive microorganisms including MRSA.

name: levodropropizine
definition: A member of the class of N-arylpiperazines that is N-phenylpiperazine in which the amino hydrogen is replaced by a 2,3-dihydroxypropyl group (the S-enantiomer). A peripherally acting antitussive drug that is used as an alternative to opioids.

name: ovothiol A zwitterion
definition: An L-alpha-amino acid zwitterion formed from ovothiol A by transfer of a proton from the carboxy to the amino group; major species at pH 7.3.

name: ovothiol B zwitterion
definition: An L-alpha-amino acid zwitterion formed from ovothiol B by transfer of a proton from the carboxy to the amino group; major species at pH 7.3.

name: ovothiol C zwitterion
definition: An L-alpha-amino acid zwitterion formed from ovothiol C by transfer of a proton from the carboxy to the amino group; major species at pH 7.3.

name: RNA fragment
definition: A nucleobase-containing molecular entity that is a fragment of a larger RNA molecule (either naturally occurring or synthetic). Phosphono groups may or may not be present at the 3'- and 5'- termini.

name: 5'-GAAACAC-3' RNA fragment
definition: An RNA fragment comprised of one guanosine, four adenosine and two cytidine residues connected by 3'->5' phosphodiester linkages in the sequence G-A-A-A-C-A-C.

name: S-(5-histidyl)cysteine sulfoxide dizwitterion
definition: An L-alpha-amino acid zwitterion formed from S-(5-histidyl)cysteine sulfoxide by transfer of protons from the two carboxy to the two amino grousp; major species at pH 7.3.

name: N(2)-acetyl-6-formylpterin
definition: Pterin acetylated on N-2 and carrying a formyl group at position 6.

name: (7Z)-hexadecenoate
definition: A hexadecenoate that is the conjugate base of (7Z)-hexadecenoic acid, obtained by deprotonation of the carboxy group; major species at pH 7.3.

name: (14Z,17Z,20Z,23Z,26Z)-dotriacontapentaenoate
definition: A dotriacontapentaenoate that is the conjugate base of (14Z,17Z,20Z,23Z,26Z)-dotriacontapentaenoic acid, obtained by deprotonation of the carboxy group; major species at pH 7.3.

name: N-acylsphinganine-1-phosphoethanolamine
definition: A ceramide phosphoethanolamine in which the sphingoid component is specified as sphinganine.

name: O-[S-(6-methoxycarbonylhexanoyl)pantetheine-4'-phosphoryl]serine(1-) residue
definition: An O-(S-acylpantetheine-4'-phosphoryl)-L-serine(1-) residue in which the S-acyl group is specified as 6-methoxycarbonylhexanoyl.

name: N-acylphytosphingosine-1-phosphoethanolamine
definition: A ceramide phosphoethanolamine in which the sphingoid component is specified as phytosphingosine.

name: N-hexadecanoylphytosphingosine-1-phosphoethanolamine
definition: An N-acylphytosphingosine-1-phosphoethanolamine in which the N-acyl group is specified as hexadecanoyl.

name: 1-(5-isoquinolinesulfonyl)-2-methylpiperazine dihydrochloride
definition: A hydrochloride salt prepared from anileridine and two molar equivalents of hydrogen chloride.

name: (5Z,11Z,14Z)-icosatrienoyl-CoA
definition: An unsaturated fatty acyl-CoA that results from the formal condensation of the thiol group of coenzyme A with the carboxy group of (5Z,11Z,14Z)-icosatrienoic acid.

name: (5Z,11Z,14Z,17Z)-icosatetraenoyl-CoA
definition: An unsaturated fatty acyl-CoA that results from the formal condensation of the thiol group of coenzyme A with the carboxy group of (5Z,11Z,14Z,17Z)-icosatetraenoic acid.

name: (8Z,11Z)-icosadienoyl-CoA
definition: An unsaturated fatty acyl-CoA that results from the formal condensation of the thiol group of coenzyme A with the carboxy group of (8Z,11Z)-icosadienoic acid.

name: 5-methylaminomethyl-2-selenouridine 5'-monophosphate zwitterion residue
definition: A zwitterionic group obtained by transfer of a proton from the amino to the phosphate group of 5-methylaminomethyl-2-selenouridine 5'-monophosphate residue.

name: aliphatic aldoxime
definition: Any aldoxime derived from an aliphatic aldehyde.

name: (9Z,12Z)-tetradecadienoyl-CoA
definition: An unsaturated fatty acyl-CoA that results from the formal condensation of the thiol group of coenzyme A with the carboxy group of (9Z,12Z)-tetradecadienoic acid.

name: (9Z,12Z)-pentadecadienoyl-CoA
definition: An unsaturated fatty acyl-CoA that results from the formal condensation of the thiol group of coenzyme A with the carboxy group of (9Z,12Z)-pentadecadienoic acid.

name: (9Z,12Z)-heptadecadienoyl-CoA
definition: An unsaturated fatty acyl-CoA that results from the formal condensation of the thiol group of coenzyme A with the carboxy group of (9Z,12Z)-heptadecadienoic acid.

name: cytidine 5'-monophosphate(1-) residue
definition: An organic anionic group that is the conjugate base of CMP residue, obtained by deprotonation of the phosphate OH group; major species at pH 7.3.

name: (6Z,9Z)-octadecadienoic acid
definition: An octadecadienoic acid in which the two double bonds have Z-geochemistry and are located at positions 6 and 9.

name: cholesteryl stearate
definition: A cholesterol ester obtained by the formal condensation of the hydroxy group in cholesterol with the carboxy group of stearic acid.

name: cholesteryl arachidonate
definition: A cholesterol ester obtained by the formal condensation of the hydroxy group in cholesterol with the carboxy group of arachidonic acid.

name: eliglustat
definition: A carboxamide obtained by formal condensation of the carboxy group of octanoic acid with the primary amino group of (1R,2R)-2-amino-1-(2,3-dihydro-1,4-benzodioxin-6-yl)-3-(pyrrolidin-1-yl)propan-1-ol. A ceramide glucosyltransferase inhibitor used (as its tartrate salt) for treatment of Gaucher's disease.

name: 1-oleoyl-sn-glycero-3-phospho-D-myo-inositol
definition: A 1-acyl-sn-glycero-3-phospho-1D-myo-inositol in which the acyl group is specified as oleoyl.

name: microcin c
definition: A member of the family of microcins comprising a heptapeptide covalently liinked to 3-aminopropyl-AMP via an acylphosphoramide linkage. A potent inhibitor of aspartyl-tRNA synthetase.

name: mertansine
definition: An organic heterotetracyclic compound and 19-membered macrocyclic lactam that is maytansine in which one of the hydrogens of the terminal N-acetyl group is replaced by a sulfanylmethyl group.

name: EC 6.1.1.12 (aspartate--tRNA ligase) inhibitor
definition: An EC 6.1.1.* (ligases forming aminoacyl tRNA and related compounds) inhibitor that specifically inhibits the action of aspartate--tRNA ligase (EC 6.1.1.12).

name: 2-hydroxy-5-methyl-1-naphthoate
definition: A member of the class of naphthoates that is 1-naphthoate substituted at positions 2 and 5 by hydroxy and methyl groups respectively; major species at pH 7.3.

name: prodigiosin
definition: A member of the class of tripyrroles that is a red-coloured pigment with antibiotic properties produced by Serratia marcescens.

name: (S)-3-acetyloctanal
definition: A ketoaldehyde that is octanal carrying an acetyl substituent at position 3 (the S-enantiomer).

name: maytansinoid
definition: Any member of the group of 19-membered lactams that is maytansine or structurally related to it. Maytansinoids have been isolated from members of the higher plant families Celastraceae, Rhamnaceae, and Euphorbiaceae, as well as some mosses and certain Actinomycetes, but the term is used to cover both naturally occurring compounds and their semisynthetic derivatives.

name: defensin
definition: A family of cysteine-rich polypeptides that function as host defence peptides and consist of 18-45 amino acids including six to eight cysteine residues.

name: 1-oleoyl-2-arachidonoyl-sn-glycero-3-phospho-1D-myo-inositol
definition: 1-acyl-2-arachidonoyl-sn-glycero-3-phospho-D-myo-inositol in which the 1-acyl group is specified as oleoyl.

name: 1-heptadecanoyl-2-arachidonoyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphate
definition: A 1-acyl-2-arachidonoyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphate(2-) in which the 1-acyl substituent is specified as heptadecanoyl

name: O-[S-2-methylbutanoylpantetheine-4'-phosphoryl]serine(1-) residue
definition: An O-(S-acylpantetheine-4'-phosphoryl)serine(1-) residue in which the S-acyl group is specified as S-2-methylbutanoyl.

name: 1,2-dioctanoyl-sn-glycerol 3-diphosphate(3-)
definition: A 1,2-diacyl-sn-glycerol 3-diphosphate(3-) arising from deprotonation of the diphosphate OH groups of 1,2-dioctanoyl-sn-glycerol 3-diphosphate.

name: 2-O-(alpha-D-glucopyranosyl)glycerol
definition: A glucosylglycerol consisting of an alpha-D-glucosyl residue attached at position 2 of glycerol via a glycosidic bond.

name: 4-(5-O-phosphonato-beta-D-ribofuranosyl)phenol(2-)
definition: An organophosphate oxoanion obtained by deprotonation of the phosphate OH groups of 4-(5-O-phospho-beta-D-ribofuranosyl)phenol; major species at pH 7.3.

name: caldopentamine(5+)
definition: An organic cation obtained by protonation of the five amino groups of caldopentamine.

name: caldopentamine(4+)
definition: An organic cation obtained by protonation of four of the five amino groups of caldopentamine.

name: N(4)-aminopropylspermidine(4+)
definition: An organic cation obtained by protonation of the four amino groups of N(4)-aminopropylspermidine.

name: N(4)-bis(aminopropyl)spermidine(5+)
definition: A quaternary ammonium ion obtained by protonation of the four primary amino groups of N(4)-bis(aminopropyl)spermidine.

name: N(4)-aminopropylspermine(5+)
definition: An organic cation obtained by protonation of the five amino groups of N(4)-aminopropylspermine.

name: (R)-3-phosphonatomevalonate(3-)
definition: An organophosphate oxoanion obtained by deprotonation of the carboxy and phosphate OH groups of (R)-3-phosphomevalonic acid; major species at pH 7.3.

name: (R)-3,5-bisphosphonatomevalonate(5-)
definition: An organophosphate oxoanion obtained by deprotonation of the carboxy and phosphate OH groups of (R)-3,5-bisphosphomevalonic acid; major species at pH 7.3.

name: 5'-deoxyinosine
definition: A 5'-deoxyribonucleoside in which hypoxanthine is attached to 5-deoxyribofuranose via a beta-N(9)-glycosidic bond.

name: coated silver nanoparticle
definition: Any silver nanoparticle that is specially coated to produce tailored nanoparticles for specific applications.

name: methyl N-(2,6-dimethylphenyl)-N-(phenylacetyl)alaninate
definition: An alanine derivative that is the N-phenylacetyl derivative of methyl N-(2,6-dimethylphenyl)alaninate

name: citrate-coated silver nanoparticle
definition: Any coated Ag nanoparticle in which the the silver nanoparticles are encapsulated by citrate.

name: benalaxyl-M
definition: A methyl N-(2,6-dimethylphenyl)-N-(phenylacetyl)alaninate that is the more active R-enantiomer of benalaxyl.

name: poly(vinylpyrrolidone)-coated Ag nanoparticle
definition: Any coated Ag nanoparticle in which the the silver nanoparticles are encapsulated by polyvinylpyrrolidone (PVP).

name: gum arabic-coated Ag NP
definition: Any coated Ag nanoparticle in which the the silver nanoparticles are encapsulated by gum arabic.

name: (S)-benalaxyl
definition: A methyl N-(2,6-dimethylphenyl)-N-(phenylacetyl)alaninate that is the less active S-enantiomer of benalaxyl.

name: PVP8-Ag NP
definition: Any coated Ag nanoparticle in which the the silver nanoparticles are encapsulated by 8 nm thick polyvinylpyrrolidone (PVP).

name: PVP38-Ag NP
definition: Any coated Ag nanoparticle in which the the silver nanoparticles are encapsulated by 38 nm thick polyvinylpyrrolidone (PVP).

name: GA5-Ag NP
definition: Any coated Ag nanoparticle in which the the silver nanoparticles are encapsulated by 5 nm thick gum arabic.

name: GA22-Ag NP
definition: Any coated Ag nanoparticle in which the the silver nanoparticles are encapsulated by 22 nm thick gum arabic.

name: methyl N-(2,6-dimethylphenyl)-N-2-furoylalaninate
definition: An alanine derivative that is the N-furoyl derivative of methyl N-(2,6-dimethylphenyl)alaninate

name: (R)-furalaxyl
definition: A methyl N-(2,6-dimethylphenyl)-N-2-furoylalaninate that has R configuration.

name: (S)-furalaxyl
definition: A methyl N-(2,6-dimethylphenyl)-N-2-furoylalaninate that has S configuration.

name: methyl N-(2,6-dimethylphenyl)-N-(methoxyacetyl)alaninate
definition: An alanine derivative that is methyl alaninate in which one of the hydrogens attached to the nitrogen is substituted by a methoxyacetyl group, while the other is substituted by a 2,6-dimethylphenyl group.

name: (S)-metalaxyl
definition: A methyl N-(2,6-dimethylphenyl)-N-(methoxyacetyl)alaninate that is the less active S-enantiomer of metalaxyl.

name: agrocinopine A
definition: A member of the class of agrocinopines that consists of sucrose and L-arabinose units joined via a  phosphodiester linkage between position 4(F) of sucrose and position 2 of arabinose.

name: agrocinopine B
definition: A member of the class of agrocinopines that consists of beta-D-fructose and L-arabinose units joined via a phosphodiester linkage between position 4 of fructose and position 2 of arabinose.

name: agrocinopine C
definition: A member of the class of agrocinopines that consists of sucrose and D-glucose units joined via a phosphodiester linkage between position 4(F) of sucrose and position 2 of glucose.

name: agrocinopine D
definition: A member of the class of agrocinopines that consists of two D-glucose units joined via a (2<->2)-phosphodiester linkage.

name: agrocin 84
definition: A nucleotide conjugate that is produced by Agrobacterium radiobacter strain K-84. A 'Trojan horse' antibiotic used to control crown gall.

name: N-palmitoylhexadecasphinganine
definition: An N-acylhexadecasphinganine in which the acyl group is specified as palmitoyl (hexadecanoyl).

name: N-stearoylhexadecasphinganine
definition: An N-acylhexadecasphinganine in which the acyl group is specified as stearoyl (octadecanoyl).

name: diltiazem(1+)
definition: An ammonium ion resulting from the protonation of the nitrogen of the dimethylaminoethyl substituent of diltiazem. The major species at pH 7.3.

name: ent-diltiazem
definition: A 5-[2-(dimethylamino)ethyl]-2-(4-methoxyphenyl)-4-oxo-2,3,4,5-tetrahydro-1,5-benzothiazepin-3-yl acetate in which both stereocentres have R configuration. It is a cGMP-activated K+ channel blocker.

name: 5-[2-(dimethylamino)ethyl]-2-(4-methoxyphenyl)-4-oxo-2,3,4,5-tetrahydro-1,5-benzothiazepin-3-yl acetate
definition: A lactam that is 2,3-dihydro-1,5-benzothiazepin-4(5H)-one in which positions 2 and 3 are substituted by 4-methoxyphenyl and acetoxy, respectively, while the hydrogen attached to the nitrogen is substituted by a 2-(dimethylamino)ethyl group.

name: 3-(methylthio)propanoyl-CoA(4-)
definition: An acyl-CoA(4-) oxoanion arising from deprotonation of the phosphate and diphosphate OH groups of 3-(methylthio)propanoyl-CoA; major species at pH 7.3.

name: ent-diltiazem(1+)
definition: An ammonium ion resulting from the protonation of the nitrogen of the dimethylaminoethyl substituent of ent-diltiazem. The major species at pH 7.3.

name: ent-diltiazem hydrochloride
definition: A hydrochloride salt resulting from the reaction of equimolar amounts of ent-diltiazem and hydrogen chloride.

name: Z-Val-Phe-H
definition: A dipeptide resulting from the formal condensation of the carboxy group of N-benzyloxycarbonyl-L-valine with the amino group of L-phenylalanine aldehyde. It is a potent cell-permeable inhibitor of calpain I and II, and is also a gamma-secretase inhibitor.

name: hexadecasphingosine-based sphingolipid
definition: A family of sphingolipids that share a common structural feature, a hexadecasphingosine base backbone.

name: hexadecasphinganine-based sphingolipid
definition: A family of sphingolipids that share a common structural feature, a hexadecasphinganine base backbone.

name: EC 3.4.22.53 (calpain-2) inhibitor
definition: A calpain inhibitor that interferes with the action of calpain-2 (EC 3.4.22.53).

name: mollisoside A
definition: A triterpene glycoside obtained from the New Zealand and South Australian sea cucumber Australostichopus mollis.

name: EC 3.4.22.54 (calpain-3) inhibitor
definition: An EC 3.4.22.* (cysteine endopeptidase) inhibitor that interferes with the action of calpain-3 (EC 3.4.22.54).

name: calpain inhibitor
definition: An EC 3.4.22.* (cysteine endopeptidase) inhibitor that interferes with the action of any calpain.

name: neothyonidioside
definition: A triterpene glycoside obtained from the New Zealand and South Australian sea cucumber Australostichopus mollis.

name: naphthodithiin
definition: An organic heterotricyclic compound whose skeleton contains a naphthalene fused with a dithiin.

name: oleanolic aldehyde
definition: A pentacyclic triterpenoid and hydroxyaldehyde that is erythrodiol in which the primary hydroxy group at position 28 has been oxidised to the corresponding aldehyde. It is found in grapes and olives.

name: oleanolate
definition: A monocarboxylic acid anion that is the conjugate base of oleanolic acid, obtained by deprotonation of the carboxy group; major species at pH 7.3.

name: queuosine 5'-phosphate zwitterion residue
definition: A zwitterionic group obtained by transfer of a proton from the phosphate to the amino group of queuosine 5'-phosphate residue.

name: (5Z,11Z,14Z)-icosatrienoic acid
definition: An icosatrienoic acid in which the three double bonds have Z configuration and are located at positions 5, 11 and 14.

name: 7-aminomethyl-7-carbaguanine 5'-phosphate zwitterion residue
definition: A zwitterionic group obtained by transfer of a proton from the phosphate to the amino group of 7-aminomethyl-7-carbaguanine 5'-phosphate residue.

name: epoxyqueuosine 5'-phosphate zwitterion residue
definition: A zwitterionic group obtained by transfer of a proton from the phosphate to the amino group of epoxyqueuosine 5'-phosphate residue.

name: (5Z,11Z,14Z,17Z)-icosatetraenoic acid
definition: An icosatetraenoic acid in which the four double bonds have Z configuration and are located at positions 5, 11, 14 and 17.

name: (9Z)-hexacosenoic acid
definition: A hexacosenoic acid in which the double bond is located at position 9 and has Z configuration.

name: 1-oleoyl-2-palmitoleoyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphoethanolamine
definition: A 1,2-diacyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphoethanolamine in which the 1- and 2-acyl groups are specified as oleoyl and palmitoleoyl respectively.

name: 1-oleoyl-2-palmitoyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphoethanolamine
definition: A 1,2-diacyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphoethanolamine in which the 1- and 2-acyl groups are specified as oleoyl and palmitoyl respectively.

name: 1-oleoyl-2-myristoyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphoethanolamine
definition: A 1,2-diacyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphoethanolamine in which the 1- and 2-acyl groups are specified as oleoyl and myristoyl respectively.

name: N-octanoyldihydrosphingosine
definition: A dihydroceramide in which the N-acyl group is specified as octanoyl.

name: N-octanoylphytosphingosine
definition: A phytoceramide in which the N-acyl group is specified as octanoyl.

name: guazatine
definition: A mixture of products resulting from the amidination of iminodi(ocatmethylene)diamine that contains iminoctadine together with a number of guanidines and polyamines.

name: UDP-2,3-bis[(3R)-3-hydroxytetradecanoyl]-alpha-D-glucosamine
definition: A UDP-amino sugar having 2,3-bis[(3R)-3-hydroxytetradecanoyl]-alpha-D-glucosamine as the amino sugar component.

name: docosatrienoic acid
definition: Any polyunsaturated fatty acid containing 22 carbons and 3 double bonds

name: N-hexacosenoylsphingosine
definition: An N-acylsphingosine in which the acyl moiety contains 26 carbons and 1 double bond.

name: 1,2-dioleoyl-sn-glycero-3-phospho-(1'-sn-glycerol-3'-phosphate)
definition: A 3-(3-sn-phosphatidyl)-sn-glycerol 1-phosphate in which both phosphatidyl acyl groups are specified as oleoyl.

name: 1,2-dioctanoyl-sn-glycero-3-phospho-(1'-myo-inositol-5'-phosphate)
definition: A 1-phosphatidyl-1D-myo-inositol 5-phosphate in which both phosphatidyl acyl groups are specified as octanoyl.

name: phthalimides
definition: A dicarboximide that is phthalimide or derivatives obtained from it by the formal replacement of one or more hydrogens.

name: inosine 5'-phosphate(1-) residue
definition: An organic anionic group obtained by deprotonation of the phosphate function of inosine 5'-phosphate residue; major species at 7.3.

name: 3,5-dichloro-N-(1-chloro-3-methyl-2-oxopentan-3-yl)-4-methylbenzamide
definition: A member of the class of benzamides obtained by formal condensation of the carboxy group of 3,5-dichloro-4-methylbenzamide with the amino group of 3-amino-1-chloro-3-methylpentan-2-one.

name: (S)-zoxamide
definition: A 3,5-dichloro-N-(1-chloro-3-methyl-2-oxopentan-3-yl)-4-methylbenzamide that is the (S)-enantiomer of zoxamide.

name: (R)-zoxamide
definition: A 3,5-dichloro-N-(1-chloro-3-methyl-2-oxopentan-3-yl)-4-methylbenzamide that is the (R)-enantiomer of zoxamide.

name: ethaboxam
definition: A racemate comprising equimolar amounts of (R)- and (S)-ethaboxam.  A fungicide used to control Oomycetes in vines and late potato blight. It is moderately toxic to birds, most aquatic species, honey bees and earthworms.

name: N-[cyano(2-thienyl)methyl]-4-ethyl-2-(ethylamino)-1,3-thiazole-5-carboxamide
definition: A member of the class of aromatic amides obtained by formal condensation of the carboxy group of 4-ethyl-2-(ethylamino)-1,3-thiazole-5-carboxylic acid with the amino group of amino(2-thienyl)acetonitrile.

name: (S)-ethaboxam
definition: An N-[cyano(2-thienyl)methyl]-4-ethyl-2-(ethylamino)-1,3-thiazole-5-carboxamide that is the (S)-enantiomer of ethaboxam.

name: (R)-ethaboxam
definition: An N-[cyano(2-thienyl)methyl]-4-ethyl-2-(ethylamino)-1,3-thiazole-5-carboxamide that is the (R)-enantiomer of ethaboxam.

name: diflumetorim
definition: A racemate comprising equimolar amounts of (R)- and (S)-diflumetorim.  Used mainly to control powdery mildew and rust on ornamental crops.

name: 5-chloro-N-{1-[4-(difluoromethoxy)phenyl]propyl}-6-methylpyrimidin-4-amine
definition: A member of the class of aminopyrimidines that is 5-chloro-6-methylpyrimidin-4-amine in which one of the amino hydrogens is replaced by a 1-[4-(difluoromethoxy)phenyl]propyl group.

name: eberconazole
definition: A racemate comprising equimolar amounts of (R)- and (S)-eberconazole. Used (as its nitrate salt) for topical treatment of superficial mycoses.

name: flutrimazole
definition: An imidazole antifungal agent that is imidazole in which the hydrogen attached to the nitrogen is replaced by a 2,4'-difluorotrityl group. A topical antifungal agent which displays potent broad-spectrum in vitro activity against dermatophytes, filamentous fungi and yeasts.

name: sertaconazole
definition: A racemate comprising equimolar amounts of (R)- and (S)-sertaconazole. A broad spectrum antifungal with added antipruritic and anti-inflammatory activity used (as its nitrate salt) for treatment of various skin infections.

name: (R)-diflumetorim
definition: A 5-chloro-N-{1-[4-(difluoromethoxy)phenyl]propyl}-6-methylpyrimidin-4-amine that is the (R)-enantiomer of diflumetorim.

name: (S)-diflumetorim
definition: A 5-chloro-N-{1-[4-(difluoromethoxy)phenyl]propyl}-6-methylpyrimidin-4-amine that has  S configuration.

name: (24S)-24-hydroxycholesterol ester
definition: A sterol ester consiting of (24S)-24-hydroxycholesterol esterified at the 3-hydroxy group.

name: (R)-econazole nitrate
definition: An organic nitrate salt prepared from equimolar amounts of (R)-econazole and nitric acid.

name: (S)-econazole nitrate

name: (2S)-1-O-(7Z,10Z)-hexadecadienoyl-2-O-(7Z,10Z)-hexadecadienoyl-3-O-beta-D-galactopyranosyl-sn-glycerol
definition: A galactoglycerolipid that consists of 1,2-diacyl-sn-glycerol having two (7Z,10Z)-hexadecadienoyl as the acyl groups and a beta-D-galactopyranosyl residue attached at position 3. It has been found in Daphnia pulex and exhibits cytotoxic activity.

name: (2S)-1-O-(7Z,10Z)-hexadecadienoyl-2-O-linoleoyl-3-O-beta-D-galactopyranosyl-sn-glycerol
definition: A galactoglycerolipid that consists of 1,2-diacyl-sn-glycerol having (7Z,10Z)-hexadecadienoyl and linoleoyl as the acyl groups and a beta-D-galactopyranosyl residue attached at position 3. It has been found in Daphnia pulex and exhibits cytotoxic activity.

name: (2S)-1-O-(9Z,12Z)-octadecadienoyl-2-O-(7Z,10Z)-hexadecadienoyl-3-O-(alpha-D-galactopyranosyl(1->6)-beta-D-galactopyranosyl)-sn-glycerol
definition: A galactoglycerolipid that consists of 1,2-diacyl-sn-glycerol having (7Z,10Z)-hexadecadienoyl and linoleoyl as the acyl groups and a 6-O-(alpha-D-galactopyranosyl)-beta-D-galactopyranosyl residue attached at position 3. It has been found in Daphnia pulex and exhibits cytotoxic activity.

name: (2S)-2,6-dimethylheptan-1-ol
definition: The (S)-enantiomer of 2,6-dimethylheptan-1-ol.

name: (2R)-2,6-dimethylheptan-1-ol
definition: The (R)-enantiomer of 2,6-dimethylheptan-1-ol.

name: (6S)-6-methyloctan-1-ol
definition: An  alkyl alcohol that is 6-methyloctane carrying a hydroxy group at position 1 (the S-stereoisomer).

name: (2S)-2,6-dimethylheptyl sulfate
definition: The (S)-enantiomer of 2,6-dimethylheptyl sulfate. It has been isolated from Daphnia pulex.

name: (2R)-2,6-dimethylheptyl sulfate
definition: The (R)-enantiomer of 2,6-dimethylheptyl sulfate. It has been isolated from Daphnia pulex.

name: (4R)-4,8-dimethylnonyl sulfate
definition: An organosulfate oxoanion that is the  conjugate base of (4R)-4,8-dimethylnonyl hydrogen sulfate. It has been isolated from Daphnia pulex and has been found to induce morphological changes in the phytoplankton, Scenedesmus gutwinskii.

name: (3S,4E)-3-methyldec-4-en-1-yl sulfate
definition: An organosulfate oxoanion that is the conjugate base of (3S,4E)-3-methyldec-4-en-1-yl hydrogen sulfate. It has been isolated from Daphnia pulex and has been found to induce morphological changes in the phytoplankton, Scenedesmus gutwinskii.

name: (3Z)-dec-3-en-1-yl sulfate
definition: An organosulfate oxoanion that is the conjugate base of (3Z)-dec-3-en-1-yl hydrogen sulfate. Isolated from Daphnia pulex, it induces morphological changes of phytoplankton Scenedesmus gutwinskii.

name: (3Z,6Z,9Z)-dodeca-3,6,9-trien-1-yl sulfate
definition: An organosulfate oxoanion that is the conjugate base of (3Z,6Z,9Z)-dodeca-3,6,9-trien-1-yl hydrogen sulfate. Isolated from Daphnia pulex, it induces morphological changes of phytoplankton Scenedesmus gutwinskii.

name: decyl sulfate
definition: An organosulfate oxoanion that is the conjugate base of decyl hydrogen sulfate. Isolated from Daphnia pulex, it induces morphological changes of phytoplankton Scenedesmus gutwinskii.

name: n-octyl sulfate
definition: An organosulfate oxoanion that is the conjugate base of octyl hydrogen sulfate. Isolated from Daphnia pulex, it induces morphological changes of phytoplankton Scenedesmus gutwinskii.

name: glucosyltestosterone
definition: A  steroid saponin that is the alpha-D-glucopyranosyl derivative of testosterone. It has been found in Daphnia magna.

name: 5alpha-androstane-3alpha-glcosyl-17beta-diol
definition: A steroid saponin that is 5alpha-androstane-3alpha,17beta-diol attached to a alpha-D-glucopyranosyl residue at position 3 via a glycosidic linkage.

name: glucosyl-6beta-hydroxytestosterone
definition: A steroid saponin that is 6beta-hydroxytestosterone attached to a alpha-D-glucopyranosyl residue at position 6 via glycosidic linkage.

name: 2alpha-hydroxytestosterone
definition: An androstanoid that is testosterone substituted by a alpha-hydroxy group at position 2. A natural product found in Daphnia magna exposed to the biocide tributyltin.

name: 16beta-hydroxytestosterone
definition: An androstanoid that is  testosterone substituted by a beta-hydroxy group at position 16. A natural product found in Daphnia magna exposed to the biocide tributyltin.

name: beta-D-talopyranose
definition: A D-talopyranose with a beta-configuration at the anomeric position.

name: (4Z,7Z,10Z,13Z)-hexadeca-4,7,10,13-tetraenoic acid
definition: A polyunsaturated fatty acid that is hexadecanoic acid with unsaturation at positions 4, 7, 10 and 13. It is found in Daphnia galeata.

name: (2Z,5Z,8Z,11Z,14Z,17Z)-icosa-2,5,8,11,14,17-hexaenoic acid
definition: A  polyunsaturated fatty acid that is icosanoic acid having unsaturation at positions 2, 5, 8, 11, 14 and 17. It has been found in  Daphnia galeata.

name: 4-O-beta-D-glucosyl-trans-4-coumaric acid
definition: A 4-O-beta-D-glucosyl-4-coumaric acid in which the double bond has trans-configuration.

name: EC 4.1.2.27 (sphinganine-1-phosphate aldolase) inhibitor
definition: An EC 4.1.2.* (aldehyde-lyase) inhibitor that interferes with the action of sphinganine-1-phosphate aldolase (EC 4.1.2.27).

name: EC 4.1.2.* (aldehyde-lyase) inhibitor
definition: An EC 4.1.* (C-C lyase) inhibitor that interferes with the action of any aldehyde-lyase (EC 4.1.2.*).

name: androsterone sulfate
