definition: A steroid sulfate that is the 3-sulfate of androsterone.

name: Daphnia galeata metabolite
definition: A Daphnia metabolite produced by the species Daphnia galeata.

name: crustacean metabolite
definition: An animal metabolite produced by arthropods such as crabs, lobsters, crayfish, shrimps and krill.

name: epiandrosterone sulfate
definition: A steroid sulfate that is the 3-sulfate of epiandrosterone.

name: 10-undecenoate
definition: An undecenoate that is the conjugate base of 10-undecenoic acid.

name: undecenoate
definition: A medium-chain fatty acid anion that is the conjugate base of undecenoic acid.

name: 4,4'-diapolycopenedioic acid
definition: An apo carotenoid triterpenoid that is 4,4'-diapolycopene in which two of the terminal methyl groups have been oxidised to carboxy groups.

name: 5-dodecenoic acid
definition: A dodecenoic acid having its double bond in the 5-position.

name: dodecenoate
definition: A medium-chain fatty acid anion that is the conjugate base of dodecenoic acid.

name: 5-dodecenoate
definition: A dodecenoate that is the conjugate base of 5-dodecenoic acid.

name: 1-stearoyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphoethanolamine
definition: A 1-acyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphoethanolamine in which the acyl group is specified as stearoyl.

name: O-(2-tetradecenoyl)carnitine
definition: An O-tetradecenoylcarnitine  having 2-tetradecenoyl as the acyl substituent.

name: 10-nonadecenoic acid
definition: A monounsaturated fatty acid that is nonadecanoic acid with a double bond at position 10.

name: (10Z)-nonadec-10-enoic acid
definition: The (Z)-stereoisomer of  10-nonadecenoic acid.

name: 10-nonadecenoate
definition: A monounsaturated fatty acid anion that is the conjugate base of 10-nonadecenoic acid.

name: 1-stearoyl-sn-glycero-3-phospho-1D-myo-inositol
definition: A 1-acyl-sn-glycero-3-phospho-1D-myo-inositol in which the 1-acyl group is specified as stearoyl.

name: 1-[(11Z,14Z)]-icosadienoyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphocholine
definition: A lysophosphatidylcholine 20:2 in which the acyl group is specified as (11Z,14Z)-icosadienoyl and is located at position 1.

name: Daphnia magna metabolite
definition: A Daphnia metabolite produced by the species Daphnia magna.

name: Daphnia metabolite
definition: A crustacean metabolite produced by the genus of small planktonic arthropods, Daphnia

name: dithiocarbamate salt
definition: Any salt derived from a member of the class of dithiocarbamic acids by the formal replacement of the hydrogen of the dithiocarboxy group by a metal.

name: dimethyldithiocarbamic acid
definition: A member of the class of dithiocarbamic acids that is dimethylcarbamic acid in which both of the oxygens are replaced by sulfur.

name: 3'-end ribonucleotide 3'-phosphate(3-) residue
definition: An organic anionic group obtained by deprotonation of the phosphate OH groups of any 3'-end ribonucleotide 3'-phosphate residue.

name: dihomolinoleic acid
definition: A octadecadienoic acid with unsaturation at positions 10 and 12 (the 10Z,12Z-stereoisomer).

name: 3'-end ribonucleotide 2',3'-cyclic phosphate(2-) residue
definition: An organic anionic group obtained by deprotonation of the phosphate OH groups of any 3'-end ribonucleotide 2',3'-cyclic phosphate residue.

name: isofetamid
definition: An aromatic amide obtained by formal condensation of the carboxy group of 3-methylthiophene-2-carboxylic acid with the amino group of 2-amino-1-(4-isopropoxy-2-methylphenyl)-2-methylpropan-1-one.

name: dihomolinoleate
definition: An octadecadienoate that is the conjugate base of dihomolinoleic acid.

name: pyroglutamylglycine
definition: A dipeptide composed of  glycine  and  5-oxo-L-proline joined by a peptide linkage.

name: tRNA 3'-terminal nucleotidyl-cytidine(2-) residue
definition: An organic anionic group obtained by deprotonation of the phosphate OH groups of any tRNA 3'-terminal nucleotidyl-cytidine residue.

name: tRNA 3'-terminal nucleotidyl-cytidyl-cytidine(3-) residue
definition: An organic anionic group obtained by deprotonation of the phosphate OH groups of any tRNA 3'-terminal nucleotidyl-cytidyl-cytidine residue; major species at pH 7.3.

name: fluopyram
definition: A member of the class of benzamides, obtained by formal condensation of the carboxy group of 2-(trifluoromethyl)benzoic acid with the amino group of 2-[3-chloro-5-(trifluoromethyl)pyridin-2-yl]ethylamine. A fungicide used for foiliar application and as a seed treatment in order to control botrystis, powdery mildew and other diseases.

name: tRNA 3'-terminal nucleotidyl-cytidyl-cytidyl-adenosine(4-) residue
definition: An organic anionic group obtained by deprotonation of the phosphate OH groups of any tRNA 3'-terminal nucleotidyl-cytidyl-cytidyl-adenosine residue; major species at pH 7.3.

name: EC 1.3.5.1 [succinate dehydrogenase (quinone)] inhibitor
definition: An EC 1.3.5.* (oxidoreductase acting on CH-CH of donor with a quinone or related compound as acceptor) inhibitor that interferes with the action of succinate dehydrogenase (quinone), EC 1.3.5.1.

name: 7-methyloctyl hydrogen sulfate
definition: An alkyl sulfate that is 7-methyloctyl ester of sulfuric acid.

name: kairomone
definition: A semiochemical used for inter-species chemical communication in a way that benefits an individual of another species that receives the chemical signal.

name: Daphnia pulex metabolite
definition: A Daphnia metabolite produced by the species Daphnia pulex.

name: (3E)-dec-3-en-1-yl hydrogen sulfate
definition: A sulfuric ester obtained by the formal condensation of (3E)-dec-3-en-1-ol with sulfuric acid.

name: (3Z)-9-methyldec-3-en-1-yl hydrogen sulfate
definition: A sulfuric ester obtained by the formal condensation of (3Z)-9-methyldec-3-en-1-ol with sulfuric acid.

name: chrysopine
definition: A spiroketal and delta-lactone resulting from the formal condensation of the carboxy group of L-glutamine with the anomeric hydroxy group of D-fructose and substitution of the 1-hydroxy group of the fructose by the alpha-amino group of the glutamine. It is found in crown gall tumours induced in chrysanthemums by Agrobacterium tumefaciens.

name: alpha-chrysopine
definition: A chrysopine formally derived from alpha-D-fructopyranose.

name: beta-chrysopine
definition: A chrysopine formally derived from beta-D-fructopyranose.

name: (3Z)-dodec-3-en-1-yl hydrogen sulfate
definition: A sulfuric ester obtained by the formal condensation of (3Z)-dodec-3-en-1-ol with sulfuric acid.

name: (3Z)-dec-3-en-1-ylsulfamic acid
definition: A member of the class of sulfamic acids that is sulfamic acid in which one of the amino hydrogens has been replaced by a (3Z)-dec-3-en-1-yl group.

name: (3Z,6Z)-dodeca-3,6-dien-1-ylsulfamic acid
definition: A member of the class of sulfamic acids that is sulfamic acid in which one of the amino hydrogens has been replaced by a (3Z,6Z)-dodeca-3,6-dien-1-yl group.

name: decylsulfamic acid
definition: A member of the class of sulfamic acids that is sulfamic acid in which one of the amino hydrogens has been replaced by a decyl group.

name: nonylsulfamic acid
definition: A member of the class of sulfamic acids that is sulfamic acid in which one of the amino hydrogens has been replaced by a nonyl group.

name: (R)-lipoate
definition: A lipoate that is the conjugate base of (R)-lipoic acid, obtained by deprotonation of the carboxy group; major species at pH 7.3.

name: octylsulfamic acid
definition: A member of the class of sulfamic acids that is sulfamic acid in which one of the amino hydrogens has been replaced by an octyl group.

name: (9-methyldecyl)sulfamic acid
definition: A member of the class of sulfamic acids that is sulfamic acid in which one of the amino hydrogens has been replaced by a (9-methyldecyl) group.

name: (R)-lipoyl-AMP(1-)
definition: A lipoyl-AMP(1-) obtained by deprotonation of the phosphate OH group of (R)-lipoyl-AMP; major species at pH 7.3.

name: benzovindiflupyr
definition: A racemate comprising equimolar amounts of (1R,4S)- and (1S,4R)-benzovindiflupyr. A fungicide that is active agaist a range of cereal diseases.

name: (R)-dihydrolipoate
definition: A dihydrolipoate that is the conjugate base of (R)-dihydrolipoic acid, obtained by deprotonation of the carboxy group; major species at pH 7.3.

name: (R)-lipoamide
definition: A lipoamide obtained by condensation of the carboxy group of (R)-lipoic acid with ammonia.

name: (8-methylnonyl)sulfamic acid
definition: A member of the class of sulfamic acids that is sulfamic acid in which one of the amino hydrogens has been replaced by a (8-methylnonyl) group.

name: (R)-S(6)-acetyldihydrolipoamide
definition: The (R)-enantiomer of S(6)-acetyldihydrolipoamide.

name: N-[9-(dichloromethylene)-1,2,3,4-tetrahydro-1,4-methanonaphthalen-5-yl]-3-(difluoromethyl)-1-methylpyrazole-4-carboxamide
definition: An aromatic amide obtained by formal condensation of the carboxy group of 3-(difluoromethyl)-1-methylpyrazole-4-carboxylic acid with the amino group of 9-(dichloromethylene)-1,2,3,4-tetrahydro-1,4-methanonaphthalen-5-amine.

name: (7-methyloctyl)sulfamic acid
definition: A member of the class of sulfamic acids that is sulfamic acid in which one of the amino hydrogens has been replaced by a (7-methyloctyl) group.

name: N(6)-[(R)-lipoyl]-L-lysine residue
definition: An N(6)-lipoyl-L-lysine residue in which the lipoyl group has R-configuration.

name: N(6)-[(R)-dihydrolipoyl]-L-lysine residue
definition: An N(6)-dihydrolipoyl-L-lysine residue in which the dihydrolipoyl group has R-configuration.

name: coprogen
definition: An iron(III) hydroxamate isolated from fungi and bacteria including Penicillium species and Neurospora crassa. It is a growth factor for coprophilous fungi.

name: (1R,4S)-benzovindiflupyr
definition: An N-[9-(dichloromethylene)-1,2,3,4-tetrahydro-1,4-methanonaphthalen-5-yl]-3-(difluoromethyl)-1-methylpyrazole-4-carboxamide that is the (1R,4S)-enantiomer of benzovindiflupyr.

name: N(6)-[(R)-S(8)-aminomethyldihydrolipoyl]-L-lysine residue
definition: An N(6)-(S(8)-aminomethyldihydrolipoyl)-L-lysine residue in which the dihydrolipoyl group has R-configuration.

name: 2,6-dimethylheptan-1-ol
definition: An alkyl alcohol that is 2,6-dimethylheptane carrying a hydroxy group at position 1.

name: (1S,4R)-benzovindiflupyr
definition: An N-[9-(dichloromethylene)-1,2,3,4-tetrahydro-1,4-methanonaphthalen-5-yl]-3-(difluoromethyl)-1-methylpyrazole-4-carboxamide that is the (1S,4R)-enantiomer of benzovindiflupyr.

name: bixafen
definition: An aromatic amide obtained by formal condensation of the carboxy group of 3-(difluoromethyl)-1-methylpyrazole-4-carboxylic acid with the amino group of 3',4'-dichloro-5-fluorobiphenyl-2-amine. A fungicide for use in cereals for key stem and leaf disease control including strobilurin-resistant septoria.

name: 2,6-dimethylheptyl sulfate
definition: An organosulfate oxoanion that is the conjugate base of 2,6-dimethylheptyl hydrogen sulfate.

name: 2,6-dimethylheptyl hydrogen sulfate
definition: An alkyl sulfate that is the sulfuric ester of  2,6-dimethylheptan-1-ol.

name: (2S)-2,6-dimethylheptyl hydrogen sulfate
definition: The (S)-enantiomer of 2,6-dimethylheptyl hydrogen sulfate.

name: (2R)-2,6-dimethylheptyl hydrogen sulfate
definition: The (R)-enantiomer of 2,6-dimethylheptyl hydrogen sulfate.

name: N(6)-[(R)-S(8)-acetyldihydrolipoyl]-L-lysine residue
definition: An N(6)-(S(8)-acetyldihydrolipoyl)-L-lysine residue in which the dihydrolipoyl group has R-configuration.

name: (4R)-4,8-dimethylnonyl hydrogen sulfate
definition: An alkyl sulfate that is the sulfuric ester of (4R)-4,8-dimethylnonan-1-ol.

name: fluxapyroxad
definition: An aromatic amide obtained by formal condensation of the carboxy group of 3-(difluoromethyl)-1-methylpyrazole-4-carboxylic acid with the amino group of 3',4',5'-trifluorobiphenyl-2-amine. Used to control a number of cereal fungal pathogens including those belonging to the Ascomycetes, Basidiomycetes and Zygomycetes families.

name: (3S,4E)-3-methyldec-4-en-1-yl hydrogen sulfate
definition: A sulfuric ester obtained by the formal condensation of (3S,4E)-3-methyldec-4-en-1-ol with sulfuric acid.

name: (3Z)-dec-3-en-1-yl hydrogen sulfate
definition: A sulfuric ester of (3Z)-dec-3-en-1-ol.

name: (3Z,6Z)-dodeca-3,6-dien-1-yl hydrogen sulfate
definition: A sulfuric ester of (3Z,6Z)-dodeca-3,6-dien-1-ol.

name: (3Z,6Z,9Z)-dodeca-3,6,9-trien-1-yl hydrogen sulfate
definition: A sulfuric ester of (3Z,6Z,9Z)-dodeca-3,6,9-trien-1-ol.

name: 5-chloro-1,3-dimethyl-N-(1,1,3-trimethyl-1,3-dihydro-2-benzofuran-4-yl)pyrazole-4-carboxamide
definition: An aromatic amide obtained by formal condensation of the carboxy group of 5-chloro-1,3-dimethylpyrazole-4-carboxylic acid with the amino group of 1,1,3-trimethyl-1,3-dihydro-2-benzofuran-4-amine.

name: (S)-furametpyr
definition: A 5-chloro-1,3-dimethyl-N-(1,1,3-trimethyl-1,3-dihydro-2-benzofuran-4-yl)pyrazole-4-carboxamide that is the (S)-enantiomer of furametpyr.

name: octyl hydrogen sulfate
definition: An alkyl sulfate that is the sulfuric ester of  octan-1-ol.

name: desferricoprogen
definition: A member of the class of 2,5-diketopiperazines that is 2,5-diketopiperazine which is substituted at positions 3 and 6 by 3-(hydroxyamino)propyl groups in which the nitrogens have been acylated by (2E)-5-hydroxy-3-methylpent-2-enoyl groups. The substituent at position 3 has been further modified by having its terminal hydroxy group esterified by condensation with the carboxy group of N(2)-acetyl-N(5)-hydroxy-L-ornithine in which the N(5) nitrogen has been acylated by a (2E)-5-hydroxy-3-methylpent-2-enoyl group.

name: isopyrazam
definition: A diastereoisomeric mixture consisting of the two possible anti-isomers as well as the two possible syn-isomers of isopyrazam. A persisent and broad spectrum fungicide used for the control of Septoria tritici, rusts and other diseases in cereals and some other crops.

name: desferricoprogen(3-)
definition: A hydroxamic acid anion resulting from the removal of a proton from each of the three hydroxamic acid groups of desferricoprogen.

name: 3-(difluoromethyl)-N-(9-isopropyl-1,2,3,4-tetrahydro-1,4-methanonaphthalen-5-yl)-1-methylpyrazole-4-carboxamide
definition: An aromatic amide obtained by formal condensation of the carboxy group of 3-(difluoromethyl)-1-methylpyrazole-4-carboxylic acid with the amino group of 9-isopropyl-1,2,3,4-tetrahydro-1,4-methanonaphthalen-5-amine.

name: syn-(1R,4S,9R)-isopyrazam
definition: A 3-(difluoromethyl)-N-(9-isopropyl-1,2,3,4-tetrahydro-1,4-methanonaphthalen-5-yl)-1-methylpyrazole-4-carboxamide that is the syn-(1R,4S,9R)-diastereomer of isopyrazam.

name: anti-(1R,4S,9S)-isopyrazam
definition: A 3-(difluoromethyl)-N-(9-isopropyl-1,2,3,4-tetrahydro-1,4-methanonaphthalen-5-yl)-1-methylpyrazole-4-carboxamide that is the anti-(1R,4S,9S)-diastereomer of isopyrazam.

name: syn-(1S,4R,9S)-isopyrazam
definition: A 3-(difluoromethyl)-N-(9-isopropyl-1,2,3,4-tetrahydro-1,4-methanonaphthalen-5-yl)-1-methylpyrazole-4-carboxamide that is the syn-(1S,4R,9S)-diastereomer of isopyrazam.

name: anti-(1S,4R,9R)-isopyrazam
definition: A 3-(difluoromethyl)-N-(9-isopropyl-1,2,3,4-tetrahydro-1,4-methanonaphthalen-5-yl)-1-methylpyrazole-4-carboxamide that is the anti-(1S,4R,9R)-diastereomer of isopyrazam.

name: penflufen
definition: A racemate comprising equimolar amounts of (R)- and (S)-penflufen. A fungicide used in furrow and seed piece treatment use on potatoes and as a seed treatment for legume vegetables, cereal grains, oil seeds and alfalfa.

name: 5-fluoro-1,3-dimethyl-N-[2-(4-methylpentan-2-yl)phenyl]pyrazole-4-carboxamide
definition: An aromatic amide obtained by formal condensation of the carboxy group of 5-fluoro-1,3-dimethylpyrazole-4-carboxylic acid with the amino group of 2-(4-methylpentan-2-yl)aniline.

name: (S)-penflufen
definition: 5-fluoro-1,3-dimethyl-N-[2-(4-methylpentan-2-yl)phenyl]pyrazole-4-carboxamide that is the (S)-enantiomer of penflufen.

name: (R)-penflufen
definition: 5-fluoro-1,3-dimethyl-N-[2-(4-methylpentan-2-yl)phenyl]pyrazole-4-carboxamide that is the (R)-enantiomer of penflufen.

name: Delta(1),Delta(7)-dafachronic acid
definition: A member of the class of dafachronic acids that is (25S)-5alpha-cholestan-26-oic acid which is substituted at position 3 by an oxo group and which contains double bonds at the 1-2 and 7-8 positions. Found in Caenorhabditis elegans.

name: 1-methyl-N-[2-(4-methylpentan-2-yl)-3-thienyl]-3-(trifluoromethyl)pyrazole-4-carboxamide
definition: An aromatic amide obtained by formal condensation of the carboxy group of 1-methyl-3-(trifluoromethyl)pyrazole-4-carboxylic acid with the amino group of 2-(4-methylpentan-2-yl)thiophen-3-amine.

name: long-chain fatty acyl-CoA(4-)
definition: A fatty acyl-CoA(4-) arising from deprotonation of the phosphate and diphosphate OH groups of any long-chain fatty acyl-CoA; major species at pH 7.3.

name: (S)-penthiopyrad
definition: A 1-methyl-N-[2-(4-methylpentan-2-yl)-3-thienyl]-3-(trifluoromethyl)pyrazole-4-carboxamide that is the (S)-enantiomer of penthiopyrad.

name: (R)-penthiopyrad
definition: A 1-methyl-N-[2-(4-methylpentan-2-yl)-3-thienyl]-3-(trifluoromethyl)pyrazole-4-carboxamide that is the (R)-enantiomer of penthiopyrad.

name: N(6)-[(R)-S(8)-isobutyryldihydrolipoyl]-L-lysine residue
definition: An alpha-amino-acid residue derived from N(6)-[(R)-S(8)-isobutyryldihydrolipoyl]-L-lysine.

name: N(6)-[(R)-S(8)-ammoniomethyldihydrolipoyl]-L-lysine(1+) residue
definition: An alpha-amino-acid residue cation obtained by protonation of the side-chain amino group of N(6)-[(R)-S(8)-aminomethyldihydrolipoyl]-L-lysine residue; major species at pH 7.3.

name: biotinyl-L-lysine residue
definition: An alpha-amino-acid residue derived from biotinyl-L-lysine.

name: carboxybiotinyl-L-lysine(1-) residue
definition: An alpha-amino-acid residue anion obtained by deprotonation of the carboxy group of carboxybiotinyl-L-lysine residue; major species at pH 7.3.

name: Daphnia tenebrosa metabolite
definition: A Daphnia metabolite produced by the species Daphnia tenebrosa.

name: 15alpha-hydroxy steroid
definition: A 15-hydroxy steroid in which the hydroxy group at position 15 has an alpha-configuration.

name: glycino(1-) group
definition: An alpha-amino-acid residue anion obtained by deprotonation of the carboxy group of glycino group; major species at pH 7.3.

name: (25S)-3alpha-hydroxy-5alpha-cholest-7-en-26-oic acid
definition: A steroid acid that is 5alpha-cholest-7-en-26-oic acid that has S configuration at position 25 and is substituted by a hydroxy group at the 3alpha position. It is an endogenous ligand for DAF-12 in Caenorhabditis elegans.

name: thioglycine(1-) residue
definition: An organic anionic group obtained by deprotonation of the thiolacid SH group of thioglycine residue.

name: glycyl-AMP(1-) residue
definition: An organic anionic group derived from glycyl-AMP(1-).

name: elisidepsin
definition: A synthetic cyclodepsipeptide derived from a marine metabolite that exhibits antineoplastic properties.

name: (5,6-dimethyl-1,10-phenanthroline)(1S,2S-diaminocyclohexane)platinum(II)(2+)
definition: A platinum coordination entity consisting of 5,6-dimethyl-1,10-phenanthroline and 1S,2S-diaminocyclohexane moieties bound via their nitrogen atoms to a central platinum atom.

name: 1,4-bis(diphospho)-1D-myo-inositol tetrakisphosphate
definition: A 1D-myo-inositol bis(diphosphate) tetrakisphosphate having the two diphospho groups located at positions 1 and 4.

name: adenosine 5'-hexadecylphosphate
definition: An adenosine 5'-phosphate that is the monohexadecyl ester of AMP.

name: EC 6.2.1.3 (long-chain-fatty-acid--CoA ligase) inhibitor
definition: An EC 6.2.1.* (acid-thiol ligase) inhibitor that interferes with the action of a long-chain-fatty-acid--CoA ligase (EC 6.2.1.3).

name: Ala-Eth
definition: A dipeptide formed from L-alanyl and L-ethionine residues.

name: copper(II) oxide nanoparticle
definition: An inorganic nanoparticle consisting of copper(II) oxide.

name: Echinacea extract
definition: A mixture resulting from extraction of any member of the genus Echinacea.

name: St. John's wort extract
definition: A mixture resulting from extraction from the leaves of St. John's wort (Hypericum perforatum).

name: propolis extract
definition: A mixture resulting from extraction from propolis.

name: molasses
definition: A mixture of sugar (fructose, glucose, sucrose) and carbohydrate components that is a by-product from sugar refinery.

name: non-polar lipid
definition: Any lipid that is non-polar.

name: venturicidin
definition: A family of macrolide antifungal compounds isolated from Streptomyces bacteria.

name: ethanol-containing medium
definition: Any mixture containing ethanol.

name: C20-C26 saturated fatty acid
definition: Any saturated fatty acid containing 20-26 carbons.

name: acrivastine
definition: A member of the class of pyridines that is (pyridin-2-yl)acrylic acid substituted at position 6 by a [(1E)-1-(4-methylphenyl)-3-(pyrrolidin-1-yl)prop-1-en-1-yl group. It is a non-sedating antihistamine used for treatment of hayfever, urticaria, and rhinitis.

name: N-acyl homoserine lactone
definition: A monocarboxylic acid amide resulting from the formal condensation of a carboxylic acid with the amino group of homoserine lactone. A class of autoinducers generally involved in bacterial quorum sensing.

name: (3R)-3-amino-3-phenylpropanoyl-CoA
definition: An acyl-CoA resulting from the formal condensation of the thiol group of coenzyme A with the carboxy group of (3R)-3-amino-3-phenylpropanoic acid.

name: (2E,4Z)-2-hydroxy-7-methyl-6-oxo-2,4-octadienoic acid
definition: An alpha,beta-unsaturated monocarboxylic acid that is (2E,4Z)-7-methyl-2,4-octadienoic acid carrying hydroxy and oxo substituents at positions 2 and 6 respectively.

name: N-tetracosenoylsphingosine-1-phosphocholine
definition: A sphingomyelin in which the total number of carbons in the fatty acyl group is 24 with 1 double bond.

name: sedaxane
definition: A diastereoisomeric mixture consisting of the two possible cis-isomers as well as the two possible trans-isomers of sedaxane. Used in seed treatment for the control of pathogens such as Ascomycetes and Oomycetes species in crops such as fruit and wheat.

name: 4-hydroxysphing-8-enine(1+)
definition: A cationic sphingoid that is the conjugate acid of 4-hydroxysphing-8-enine, obtained by protonation of the primary amino function; major species at pH 7.3.

name: cis-(1R,2R)-sedaxane
definition: An N-{2-[1,1'-bi(cyclopropyl)-2-yl]phenyl}-3-(difluoromethyl)-1-methyl-1pyrazole-4-carboxamide that is the cis-(1R,2R)-diastereomer of sedaxane.

name: cis-(1S,2S)-sedaxane
definition: An N-{2-[1,1'-bi(cyclopropyl)-2-yl]phenyl}-3-(difluoromethyl)-1-methyl-1pyrazole-4-carboxamide that is the cis-(1S,2S)-diastereomer of sedaxane.

name: trans-(1S,2R)-sedaxane
definition: An N-{2-[1,1'-bi(cyclopropyl)-2-yl]phenyl}-3-(difluoromethyl)-1-methyl-1pyrazole-4-carboxamide that is the trans-(1S,2R)-diastereomer of sedaxane.

name: trans-(1R,2S)-sedaxane
definition: An N-{2-[1,1'-bi(cyclopropyl)-2-yl]phenyl}-3-(difluoromethyl)-1-methyl-1pyrazole-4-carboxamide that is the trans-(1R,2S)-diastereomer of sedaxane.

name: beta-D-glucosyl-(1<->1')-N-acyltetradecasphingosine
definition: A cerebroside consisting of a  beta-D-glucosyl residue attached to the primary hydroxyl group of N-acyltetradecasphingosine.

name: beta-D-glucosyl-(1<->1')-N-acyl-(4E,6E)-tetradecasphingadienine
definition: A glucosylceramide consisting of a beta-D-glucosyl residue attached to the primary hydroxyl group of N-acyl-(4E,6E)-tetradecasphingadienine.

name: beta-D-glucosyl-(1<->1')-N-acylpentadecasphingosine
definition: A glucosylceramide consisting of a beta-D-glucosyl residue attached to the primary hydroxyl group of N-acylpentadecasphingosine.

name: beta-D-glucosyl-(1<->1')-N-acyl-(4E,6E)-pentadecasphingadienine
definition: A glucosylceramide consisting of a beta-D-glucosyl residue attached to the primary hydroxyl group of N-acyl-(4E,6E)-pentadecasphingadienine.

name: beta-D-glucosyl-(1<->1')-N-acyl-(4E,6E)-hexadecasphingadienine
definition: A glucosylceramide consisting of a beta-D-glucosyl residue attached to the primary hydroxyl group of N-acyl-(4E,6E)-hexadecasphingadienine.

name: coumoxystrobin
definition: A member of the class of coumarins that is the methyl ester of (2E)-2-(2-{[(3-butyl-4-methyl-2-oxochromen-7-yl)oxy]methyl}phenyl)-3-methoxyprop-2-enoic acid. A fungicide active against various fungal infections including downy mildew, blight, powdery mildew and rice blast.

name: beta-D-glucosyl-(1<->1')-N-acylhexadecasphingosine
definition: A glucosylceramide consisting of a beta-D-glucosyl residue attached to the primary hydroxyl group of N-acylhexadecasphingosine.

name: enoxastrobin
definition: An enoate ester that is the methyl ester of (2E)-2-{2-[({(E)-[(3E)-4-(4-chlorophenyl)but-3-en-2-ylidene]amino}oxy)methyl]phenyl}-3-methoxyprop-2-enoic acid. A fungicide used for control of leaf blotch, leaf rust and powdery mildew on wheat and other fungal diseases on cucumbers, tomatoes and grapes.

name: phosphatidylinositol monophosphate(3-)
definition: An anionic phospholipid obtained by deprotonation of the phospho groups of any phosphatidylinositol trisphosphate; major species at pH 7.3.

name: phosphatidylinositol bisphosphate(5-)
definition: An anionic phospholipid obtained by deprotonation of the phospho groups of any phosphatidylinositol bisphosphate; major species at pH 7.3.

name: phosphatidylinositol trisphosphate(7-)
definition: An anionic phospholipid obtained by deprotonation of the phospho groups of any phosphatidylinositol trisphosphate; major species at pH 7.3.

name: flufenoxystrobin
definition: An enoate ester that is the methyl ester of (2E)-2-(2-{[2-chloro-4-(trifluoromethyl)phenoxy]methyl}phenyl)-3-methoxyprop-2-enoic acid. A fungicide active against various fungal infections including downy mildew, blight, powdery mildew and rice blast.

name: glycerophosphoglycerophosphate anion
definition: An anionic phospholipid obtained by deprotonation of the phospho groups of any glycerophosphoglycerophosphate; major species at pH 7.3.

name: picoxystrobin
definition: An enoate ester that is the methyl ester of (2E)-3-methoxy-2-[2-({[6-(trifluoromethyl)pyridin-2-yl]oxy}methyl)phenyl]prop-2-enoic acid.  A cereal fungicide used to control a wide range of diseases including brown rust, tan spot, powdery mildew and net blotch.

name: desferrialbomycins
definition: A class of pentapeptides comprising three N(5)-acetyl-N(5)-hydroxy-L-ornithyl residues, an L-seryl residue, and an unusual D-amino acid [containing a variably-substituted pyrimidine (R = NCONH2, NH, or O) linked through a ring nitrogen to a thiafuranose moiety] coupled in sequence. The iron(III) complexes of desferrialbomycins, albomycins, have been isolated from various Streptomyces species; they are antibiotics that inhibit bacterial growth.

name: desferrialbomycin delta1
definition: A member of the class of desferrialbomycins in which the pyrimidone moiety is substituted by an oxo group at position 4.  The iron(III) complex of desferrialbomycin delta1 is the antibiotic albomycin delta1.

name: desferrialbomycin delta2
definition: A member of the class of desferrialbomycins that is desferrialbomycin epsilon in which the hydrogen attached to the nitrogen at position 4 of the pyrimidone moiety is replaced by a carbamoyl group.  The iron(III) complex of desferrialbomycin delta1 is the antibiotic albomycin delta2.

name: desferrialbomycin epsilon
definition: A member of the class of desferrialbomycins that is desferrialbomycin delta1 in which the oxo group at position 4 of the pyrimidone moiety is replaced by an imino group. The iron(III) complex of desferrialbomycin epsilon is the antibiotic albomycin epsilon.

name: pyraoxystrobin
definition: An enoate ester that is the methyl ester of (2E)-2-[2-({[3-(4-chlorophenyl)-1-methyl-1H-pyrazol-5-yl]oxy}methyl)phenyl]-3-methoxyprop-2-enoic acid. A broad spectrum fungicide used to control a variety of diseases on rice, vegetables and teas.

name: 1-stearoylglycerone 3-phosphate(2-)
definition: A 1-acylglycerone 3-phosphate(2-) obtained by deprotonation of the phospho groups of 1-stearoylglycerone 3-phosphate; major species at pH 7.3.

name: desferrialbomycin delta1(3-)
definition: A hydroxamic acid anion resulting from the removal of a proton from each of the hydroxamic acid groups of desferrialbomycin delta1.

name: mandestrobin
definition: A racemate composed of equimolar amounts of (R)- and (S)-mandestrobin. A strobilurin fungicide for use on cereal crops.

name: albomycin delta1
definition: An iron(III) hydroxamate in which desferrialbomycin delta1(3-) is complexed to iron(III).

name: albomycin
definition: A mixture of iron(III) hydroxamate antibiotics produced by various Streptomyces species (e.g. Streptomyces subtropicus) and consisting of iron(III) complexed to pentapeptide trihydroxamate siderophores.

name: 2-{2-[(2,5-dimethylphenoxy)methyl]phenyl}-2-methoxy-N-methylacetamide
definition: A monocarboxylic acid amide obtained by formal condensation of the carboxy group of {2-[(2,5-dimethylphenoxy)methyl]phenyl}(methoxy)acetic acid with the amino group of methylamine.

name: (R)-mandestrobin
definition: A 2-{2-[(2,5-dimethylphenoxy)methyl]phenyl}-2-methoxy-N-methylacetamide that is the (R)-enantiomer of mandestrobin.

name: (S)-mandestrobin
definition: A 2-{2-[(2,5-dimethylphenoxy)methyl]phenyl}-2-methoxy-N-methylacetamide that is the (S)-enantiomer of mandestrobin.

name: tirucallane triterpenoid
definition: Any tetracyclic triterpenoid based on a tirucallane skeleton.

name: pyrametostrobin
definition: A carbamate ester that is the methyl ester of  (2-{[(1,4-dimethyl-3-phenyl-1H-pyrazol-5-yl)oxy]methyl}phenyl)methoxycarbamic acid. A fungicide that is active against powdery mildew and other diseases.

name: triclopyricarb
definition: A carbamate ester that is the methyl ester of methoxy(2-{[(3,5,6-trichloropyridin-2-yl)oxy]methyl}phenyl)carbamic acid. A methoxycarbanilate fungicide used on rice and other crops.

name: desferrialbomycin delta2(3-)
definition: A hydroxamic acid anion resulting from the removal of a proton from each of the hydroxamic acid groups of desferrialbomycin delta2.

name: albomycin delta2
definition: An iron(III) hydroxamate in which desferrialbomycin delta2(3-) is complexed to iron(III).

name: desferrialbomycin epsilon(3-)
definition: A hydroxamic acid anion resulting from the removal of a proton from each of the hydroxamic acid groups of desferrialbomycin epsilon.

name: albomycin epsilon
definition: An iron(III) hydroxamate in which desferrialbomycin epsilon(3-) is complexed to iron(III).

name: dimoxystrobin
definition: A monocarboxylic acid amide obtained by formal condensation of the carboxy group of (2E)-{2-[(2,5-dimethylphenoxy)methyl]phenyl}(methoxyimino)acetic acid with the amino group of methylamine. A fungicide used for disease control in cereals, vegetables and turf.

name: lactate ester
definition: Any carboxylic ester resulting from the formal condensation of the carboxy group of lactic acid with the hydroxy group of an alcohol or phenol.

name: fenaminstrobin
definition: A monocarboxylic acid amide obtained by formal condensation of the carboxy group of (2E)-{2-[({(E)-[(3E)-4-(2,6-dichlorophenyl)but-3-en-2-ylidene]amino}oxy)methyl]phenyl}(methoxyimino)acetic acid with the amino group of methylamine. A broad-spectrum fungicide.

name: methyl 2-hydroxypropionate
definition: A lactate ester resulting from the formal condensation of the carboxy group of 2-hydroxypropanoic acid with methanol.

name: methyl (S)-lactate
definition: A methyl 2-hydroxypropionate that has S configuration.

name: L-erythro-N-acylsphingosine
definition: A sphingolipid comprising an unspecified fatty acyl group attached to the nitrogen of L-erythro-sphingosine.

name: N(omega)-phospho-L-arginine(1-) residue
definition: An alpha-amino-acid residue anion derived from N(omega)-phospho-L-arginine(1-).

name: sugar-phosphodiester opine
definition: Any opine whose structure is based on a sugar phosphodiester.

name: L-alpha-amino acid residue
definition: An alpha-amino-acid residue derived from an L-alpha-amino acid.

name: amino acid opine
definition: Any opine whose structure is based on the condensation of an amino acid with a carbohydrate or a keto-acid.

name: xanthone glycoside
definition: Any member of the class of  xanthones having one or more glycosyl residues attached at unspecified positions.

name: Mo(=O)(=S)-molybdopterin cofactor
definition: A Mo-molybdopterin cofactor that is MoO2-molybdopterin cofactor in which one of the oxygen atoms attached to molybdenum is replaced by a sulfur atom.

name: beta-D-galactosyl-(1<->1')-sphinganine(1+)
definition: A primary ammonium ion resulting from the protonation of the amino group of beta-D-galactosyl-(1<->1')-sphinganine; major species at pH 7.3.

name: beta-D-galactosyl-(1<->1')-sphinganine
definition: A glycosylsphingoid in which a beta-D-galactosyl residue is attached to the primary hydroxyl group of sphinganine.

name: 2-acylglycerophospho-(2'-acylglycerol)(1-)
definition: An acylglycerophosphoacylglycerol(1-) obtained by deprotonation of the phospho group of any 2-acylglycerophospho-(2'-acylglycerol); major species at pH 7.3.

name: acylglycerophosphoacylglycerol(1-)
definition: An anionic phospholipid obtained by deprotonation of the phospho group of any acylglycerophosphoacylglycerol; major species at pH 7.3.

name: (Hex)6,7(HexNAc)2
definition: Any eight- or nine membered amino oligosaccharide consisting of two acetamidohexose units and either six or seven hexose units.

name: 1,2-dibutyryl-sn-glycero-3-phospho-(1'D-myo-inositol-5'-phosphate)
definition: A 1-phosphatidyl-1D-myo-inositol 5-phosphate in which both phosphatidyl acyl groups are specified as butanoyl.

name: 1,2-dibutyryl-sn-glycero-3-phospho-(1'D-myo-inositol)
definition: A 1-phosphatidyl-1D-myo-inositol in which the two phosphatidyl acyl groups are specified as butanoyl.

name: 1D-myo-inositol 3,4-biphosphate(4-)
definition: An inositol phosphate oxoanion obtained by deprotonation of the phospho groups of 1D-myo-inositol 3,4-biphosphate; major species at pH 7.3.

name: 1D-myo-inositol 1,3-biphosphate(4-)
definition: An inositol phosphate oxoanion obtained by deprotonation of the phospho groups of 1D-myo-inositol 1,3-biphosphate; major species at pH 7.3.

name: 1-stearoyl-2-arachidonoyl-sn-glycero-3-phospho-(1D-myo-inositol 3,4,5-triphosphate)(7-)
definition: A 1-phosphatidyl-1D-myo-inositol 3,4,5-trisphosphate(7-) in which the phosphatidyl acyl groups at positions 1 and 2 are specified as stearoyl and arachidonoyl respectively.

name: N-(2-hydroxyhexanoyl)sphingosine
definition: A 2-N-(2-hydroxyacyl)sphingosine in which the ceramide N-acyl group is specified as 2-hydroxyhexanoyl.

name: N-(2-hydroxyacyl)-beta-D-galactosylsphingosine
definition: A D-galactosyl-N-acylsphingosine in which a beta-D-galactosyl residue is attached to the primary hydroxy group of any N-(2-hydroxyacyl)sphingosine.

name: N-(2-hydroxyhexanoyl)-beta-D-galactosylsphingosine
definition: A N-(2-hydroxyacyl)-beta-D-galactosylsphingosine in which the ceramide N-acyl group is specified as 2-hydroxyhexanoyl.

name: N-(2-hydroxyacyl)sphinganine
definition: A dihydroceramide in which the N-acyl moiety bears a hydroxy group alpha- to the carboxamide group.

name: N-(2-hydroxyhexanoyl)sphinganine
definition: An N-(2-hydroxyacyl)sphinganine in which the ceramide N-acyl group is specified as 2-hydroxyhexanoyl.

name: N-(2-hydroxyacyl)-beta-D-galactosylsphinganine
definition: A galactosylceramide in which a beta-D-galactosyl residue is attached to the primary hydroxy group of 2-N-(2-hydroxyacyl)sphinganine.

name: 5-methyl-5-(4-phenoxyphenyl)-3-(phenylamino)-1,3-oxazolidine-2,4-dione
definition: A member of the class of oxazolidinones that is 1,3-oxazolidine-2,4-dione in which the hydrogen attached to the nitrogen is substituted by a phenylamino group and the hydrogens at position 5 are substituted by methyl and 4-phenoxyphenyl groups.

name: N-hexanoyl-beta-D-galactosylsphinganine
definition: A galactosylceramide that is beta-D-galactosylsphinganine in which the ceramide N-acyl group is specified as hexanoyl.

name: (R)-famoxadone
definition: A 5-methyl-5-(4-phenoxyphenyl)-3-(phenylamino)-1,3-oxazolidine-2,4-dione that is the (inactive) (R)-enantiomer of famoxadone.

name: fluoxastrobin
definition: An oxime O-ether that is the O-methyl oxime of (2-{[6-(2-chlorophenoxy)-5-fluoropyrimidin-4-yl]oxy}phenyl)(5,6-dihydro-1,4,2-dioxazin-3-yl)methanone. A fungicide used for disease control of potatoes and a wide range of vegetables.

name: [3)-beta-D-Glcp6,NAc2-(1->] residue
definition: A monosaccharide residue obtained formally by removal of the anomeric hydroxy group and the hydrogen attached to the 3-oxygen of Nacetyl-D-glucopyranose in which the 6-hydroxy group is acetylated. The 6-O-acetylated GlcpNAc epitope in various Shigella flexneri O-antigens.

name: dioxazine
definition: Any six-membered organic heteromonocyclic compound that contains one nitrogen and two oxygen atoms.

name: N-(2-hydroxyhexanoyl)-beta-D-galactosylsphinganine
definition: A N-(2-hydroxyacyl)-beta-D-galactosylsphinganine in which the ceramide N-acyl group is specified as 2-hydroxyhexanoyl.

name: fenamidone
definition: A member of the class of imidazolones that is 3,5-dihydroimidazol-4-one substituted at position 2 by a methylthiogroup, at position 3 by an anilino group and at position 5 by phenyl and methyl groups (the S-enantiomer). A fungicide effective against Oomycete diseases such as downy mildew and certain leaf spot diseases.

name: 14-methylhexadecasphingosine(1+)
definition: A cationic sphingoid obtained by the protonation of the amino group of 14-methylhexadecasphingosine; major species at pH 7.3.

name: pyribencarb
definition: A carbamate ester that is the methyl ester of (2-chloro-5-{(1E)-N-[(6-methylpyridin-2-yl)methoxy]ethanimidoyl}benzyl)carbamic acid. A fungicide having excellent activity against a wide range of plant pathogenic fungi, especially gray mould diseases caused by Botrytis cinerea.

name: alkyl,acyl-3-(beta-D-galactosyl)-sn-glycerol
definition: A galactoglycerolipid in which positions 1 and 2 are substituted by unspecified acyl and alkyl groups, the positions of which are also unspecified.

name: (-)-trans-pinocarveol
definition: The (1S,3R,5S)-stereoisomer of pinocarveol.

name: beta-D-glucosylceramide
definition: Any glucosylceramide in which the glucosyl component has beta-D-configuration.

name: papuamide B
definition: A cyclodepsipeptide that is isolated from Papua New Guinea collections of the marine sponges Theonella mirabilis and Theonella swinhoei. It exhbits anti-HIV-1 activity and cytotoxicity against some human cancer cell lines.

name: tebufloquin
definition: A member of the class of quinolines that is quinoline which is substituted at positions 2 and 3 by methyl groups and at positions 4, 6, and 8 by acetoxy, tert-butyl, and fluorine, respectively. A fungicide developed mainly for the control of rice blast (Magnaporthe grisea), it has also been found to be effective against fungal diseases in soya beans and tomatoes.

name: filipin III
definition: A macrolide that is the major component of a mixture of four isomeric polyene macrolides isolated from Streptomyces filipinensis.

name: oxathiapiprolin
definition: A racemate comprising equimolar amounts of (R)- and (S)-oxathiapiprolin.

name: (R)-oxathiapiprolin
definition: A 1-(4-{4-[5-(2,6-difluorophenyl)-4,5-dihydro-1,2-oxazol-3-yl]-1,3-thiazol-2-yl}piperidin-1-yl)-2-[5-methyl-3-(trifluoromethyl)-1H-pyrazol-1-yl]ethanone that has R configuration at position 5 of the 4,5-dihydro-1,2-oxazole ring.

name: (S)-oxathiapiprolin
definition: A 1-(4-{4-[5-(2,6-difluorophenyl)-4,5-dihydro-1,2-oxazol-3-yl]-1,3-thiazol-2-yl}piperidin-1-yl)-2-[5-methyl-3-(trifluoromethyl)-1H-pyrazol-1-yl]ethanone that has S configuration at position 5 of the 4,5-dihydro-1,2-oxazole ring.

name: 1-(4-{4-[5-(2,6-difluorophenyl)-4,5-dihydro-1,2-oxazol-3-yl]-1,3-thiazol-2-yl}piperidin-1-yl)-2-[5-methyl-3-(trifluoromethyl)-1H-pyrazol-1-yl]ethanone
definition: An N-acylpiperidine that is N-acetyl 4-(1,3-thiazol-2-yl)piperidine in which the thiazole ring is substituted at position 4 by a 5-(2,6-difluorophenyl)-4,5-dihydro-1,2-oxazol-3-yl group and in which one of the hydrogens of the acetyl group is replaced by a 5-methyl-3-(trifluoromethyl)-1H-pyrazol-1-yl group.

name: 1-O-(alpha-D-galactosyl)-N-[(15Z)-tetracos-15-enoyl]phytosphingosine
definition: A glycophytoceramide that consists of phytosphingosine having an alpha-D-galactosyl attached at the O-1 position via a glycosidic linkage and a (Z)-tetracos-15-enoyl group attached to the nitrogen.

name: N-acylsphingoid
definition: A ceramide consisting of an undefined sphingoid base linked to an undefined fatty acid via an amide bond.

name: juvenile hormone III carboxylate
definition: A polyunsaturated fatty acid anion obtained by deprotonation of the carboxy group of juvenile hormone III acid; major species at pH 7.3.

name: hypothemycin
definition: A macrolide that is isolated from the cultured broth of Hypomyces subiculosus and shows antifungal activity and inhibits the growth of some human cancer cells.

name: (2E,6E)-farnesoate
definition: A polyunsaturated fatty acid anion obtained by deprotonation of the carboxy group of (2E,6E)-farnesoic acid; major species at pH 7.3.

name: flutianil
definition: A member of the class of thiazolidines that is N-(o-methoxyphenyl)thiazolidine which is substituted at position 2 by a methylene group, the hydrogens of which are replaced by cyano and [2-fluoro-5-(trifluoromethyl)phenyl]sulfanediyl groups; the double bond conjugated to the cyano group has Z configuration. A fungicide intended for use on horticultural crops including strawberries and grapevines.

name: didecanoylphosphatidate(2-)
definition: A phosphatidate(2-) obtained by deprotonation of both phosphate OH groups of didecanoylphosphatidic acid; major species at pH 7.3.

name: 3-iodoprop-2-yn-1-yl butylcarbamate
definition: A carbamate ester that is carbamic acid in which the nitrogen has been substituted by a butyl group and in which the hydrogen of the carboxy group is replaced by a 1-iodoprop-2-yn-3-yl group. A fungicide, it is used as a preservative and sapstain control chemical in wood products and as a preservative in adhesives, paints, latex paper coating, plastic, water-based inks, metal working fluids, textiles, and numerous consumer products.

name: flavone C-glycoside
definition: Any C-glycosyl compound arising formally from the elimination of water from a glycosidic hydroxy group and an H atom bound to a flavone skeleton, thus creating a C-C bond.

name: ferriheme a3
definition: A ferriheme consisting of a tetraporphyrin derivative coordinated to a central iron.

name: ferriheme a3(1-)
definition: A dicarboxylic acid anion obtained by deprotonation of the carboxy groups of ferriheme a3. Major structure at pH 7.3.

name: piperalin
definition: A racemate comprising equimolar amounts of (R)- and (S)-piperalin. A fungicide introduced in the 1960s for the control of powdery mildew on ornamental plants, shrubs, vines and trees grown in commercial greenhouses, it is no longer approved for use within the European Union.

name: 3-(2-methylpiperidin-1-yl)propyl 3,4-dichlorobenzoate
definition: A member of the class of piperidines that is 2-methylpiperidine in which the hydrogen attached to the nitrogen is replaced by a 3-[(3,4-dichlorobenzoyl)oxy]propyl group.

name: (R)-piperalin
definition: A 3-(2-methylpiperidin-1-yl)propyl 3,4-dichlorobenzoate that has R configuration.

name: (S)-piperalin
definition: A 3-(2-methylpiperidin-1-yl)propyl 3,4-dichlorobenzoate that has S configuration.

name: 3,4-dichlorobenzoate
definition: A chlorobenzoate obtained by deprotonation of the carboxy group of 3,4-dichlorobenzoic acid. The major species at pH 7.3.

name: 1-stearoyl-2-arachidonoylphosphatidate(2-)
definition: A phosphatidate(2-) obtained by deprotonation of both phosphate OH groups of 1-stearoyl-2-arachidonoylphosphatidic acid; major species at pH 7.3.

name: N(alpha)-(L-gamma-glutamyl)-hercynyl-L-cysteine sulfoxide
definition: A non-proteinogenic dipeptide formed from L-gamma-glutamic acid and hercynyl-L-cysteine sulfoxide residues. It is an intermediate in the synthesis of ergothioneine, a compound found in certain fungi and mycobacteria.

name: 1-[3-(4-tert-butylphenyl)-2-methylpropyl]piperidine
definition: A member of the class of piperidines that is N-isobutylpiperidine in which a hydrogen of one of the methyl groups is replaced by a p-tert-butylphenyl group.

name: N(alpha)-(L-gamma-glutamyl)-hercynyl-L-selenocysteine
definition: A non-proteinogenic dipeptide formed from L-gamma-glutamic acid and hercynyl-L-selenocysteine residues.

name: (R)-fenpropidin
definition: A 1-[3-(4-tert-butylphenyl)-2-methylpropyl]piperidine that has R configuration.

name: (S)-fenpropidin
definition: A 1-[3-(4-tert-butylphenyl)-2-methylpropyl]piperidine that has S configuration.

name: aldimorph
definition: A mixture of containing 65-75% 4-alkyl-2,6-dimethylmorpholines and 35-25% 4-alkyl-2,5-dimethylmorpholines, where more than 85% of the total has dodecyl as the alkyl group, and where 'alkyl' may also be octyl, decyl, tetradecyl or hexadecyl, and where the cis:trans ratio is 1:1. Formerly used as a fungicide for the control of powdery mildew in cereal crops, it is no longer approved for use within the European Union.

name: orexin receptor antagonist
definition: An antagonist that binds to and deactivates orexin receptors.

name: cis-4-dodecyl-2,6-dimethylmorpholine
definition: A 4-dodecyl-2,6-dimethylmorpholine in which the methyl substituents are in a cis relationship to each other.

name: 4-dodecyl-2,5-dimethylmorpholine
definition: A member of the class of morpholines that is 2,5-dimethylmorpholine in which the hydrogen attached to the nitrogen is replaced by a dodecyl group.

name: (2S,6S)-4-dodecyl-2,6-dimethylmorpholine
definition: A 4-dodecyl-2,6-dimethylmorpholine in which both stereocentres have S configuration.

name: (2R,6R)-4-dodecyl-2,6-dimethylmorpholine
definition: A 4-dodecyl-2,6-dimethylmorpholine in which both stereocentres have R configuration.

name: rac-trans-4-dodecyl-2,6-dimethylmorpholine
definition: A racemate comprising equimolar amounts of (2R,6R)- and (2S,6S)-4-dodecyl-2,6-dimethylmorpholine.

name: (2R,5R)-4-dodecyl-2,5-dimethylmorpholine
definition: A 4-dodecyl-2,5-dimethylmorpholine in which both of the stereocentres have R configuration.

name: oritavancin bisphosphate
definition: A phosphate salt obtained by combining oritavancin with two molar equivalents of phosphoric acid. Used for the treatment of acute bacterial skin and skin structure infections caused or suspected to be caused by susceptible isolates of designated Gram-positive microorganisms.

name: (2R,5S)-4-dodecyl-2,5-dimethylmorpholine
definition: A 4-dodecyl-2,5-dimethylmorpholine in which the stereocentre adjacent to the oxygen has R configuration, whilst that adjacent to the nitrogen has S configuration.

name: (2S,5R)-4-dodecyl-2,5-dimethylmorpholine
definition: A 4-dodecyl-2,5-dimethylmorpholine in which the stereocentre adjacent to the oxygen has S configuration, whilst that adjacent to the nitrogen has R configuration.

name: dioleoylphosphatidate(2-)
definition: A phosphatidate(2-) obtained by deprotonation of both phosphate OH groups of dioleoylphosphatidic acid; major species at pH 7.3.

name: olodaterol hydrochloride
definition: A hydrochloride obtained by combining olodaterol with one equivalent of hydrochloric acid. Used for long-term treatment of airflow obstruction in patients with chronic obstructive pulmonary disease including chronic bronchitis and/or emphysema.

name: rac-cis-4-dodecyl-2,5-dimethylmorpholine
definition: A racemate comprising an equimolar mixture of the two stereoisomers of 4-dodecyl-2,5-dimethylmorpholine in which the methyl substituents are in a cis relationship to each other.

name: rac-trans-4-dodecyl-2,5-dimethylmorpholine
definition: A racemate comprising an equimolar mixture of the two stereoisomers of 4-dodecyl-2,5-dimethylmorpholine in which the methyl substituents are in a trans relationship to each other.

name: olodaterol(1+)
definition: An organic cation obtained by protonation of the secondary hydroxy group of olodaterol

name: protease-activated receptor-1 antagonist
definition: An antagonist at the protease-activated receptor-1.

name: vorapaxar sulfate
definition: An organic sulfate salt obtained by combining vorapaxar with one molar equivalent of sulfuric acid. A protease-activated receptor-1 antagonist used for the reduction of thrombotic cardiovascular events in patients with a history of myocardial infarction (MI) or with peripheral arterial disease. It has been shown to reduce the rate of a combined endpoint of cardiovascular death, MI, stroke and urgent coronary revascularisation.

name: vorapaxar(1+)
definition: A pyridinium ion obtained by protonation of the pyridine nitrogen in vorapaxar.

name: EC 1.14.13.72 (methylsterol monooxygenase) inhibitor
definition: An EC 1.14.13.* (oxidoreductase acting on paired donors, incorporating 1 atom of oxygen, with NADH or NADPH as one donor) inhibitor that interferes with the action of methylsterol monooxygenase (EC 1.14.13.72).

name: sterol biosynthesis inhibitor
definition: Any compound that inhibits the biosynthesis of any sterol.

name: ovothiol A
definition: A L-histidine derivative that is L-histidine substituted at positions N3 and C5 on the imidazole ring by methyl and mercapto groups respectively.

name: EC 1.3.1.70 (Delta(14)-sterol reductase) inhibitor
definition: An EC 1.3.1.* (oxidoreductase acting on donor CH-CH group, NAD(+) or NADP(+) as acceptor) inhibitor that interferes with the action of Delta(14)-sterol reductase (EC 1.3.1.70).

name: 1,2 ditetradecanoylglycerol
definition: A 1,2-diglyceride  in which the acyl groups at positions 1 and 2 are specifed as tetradecanoyl.

name: 1,2-dimyrsitoylphosphatidate(2-)
definition: A phosphatidate(2-) obtained by deprotonation of both phosphate OH groups of 1,2-dimyristoylphosphatidic acid; major species at pH 7.3.

name: eprazinone(2+)
definition: An organic cation obtained by protonation of the two tertiary amino groups of eprazinone.

name: pent-2-enoyl-CoA(4-)
definition: A 2,3-dehydroacyl-CoA(4-) arising from deprotonation of phosphate and diphosphate functions of pent-2-enoyl-CoA; major species at pH 7.3.

name: beta-carboline alkaloid
definition: Any indole alkaloid based on a beta-carboline (9H-pyrido[3,4-b]indole) skeleton.

name: tedizolid phosphate
definition: A  phosphate monoester resulting from the formal condensation of equimolar amounts of phosphoric acid with the hydroxy group of tedizolid . It is a prodrug of tedizolid, used for the treatment of acute bacterial skin infections caused by certain susceptible bacteria, including Staphylococcus aureus (including methicillin-resistant strains (MRSA) and methicillin-susceptible strains), various Streptococcus species, and Enterococcus faecalis.

name: fenpyrazamine
definition: A pyrazolone that is pyazol-3-one  which is substituted at positions 2, 4, and 5 by isopropyl, o-methylphenyl, and amino groups, respectively, and in which the hydrogen attached to the nitrogen at position 1 is replaced by an S-allyl carbothioate moiety. A fungicide, it is used for the control of Botrytis in the greenhouse cultivation of tomatoes, peppers, and cucumbers.

name: pyrazolone
definition: A member of the class of pyrazoles in which one of the carbons of the pyrazole ring is substituted by an oxo group.

name: 5-[1-hydroxy-2-(isopropanylamino)ethyl]benzene-1,3-diol
definition: A member of the class of resorcinols bearing an additional 1-hydroxy-2-(isopropanylamino)ethyl substituent at position 5 of resorcinol itself.

name: (R)-orciprenaline
definition: A 5-[1-hydroxy-2-(isopropanylamino)ethyl]benzene-1,3-diol that is the (R)-enantiomer of orciprenaline.

name: (S)-orciprenaline
definition: A 5-[1-hydroxy-2-(isopropanylamino)ethyl]benzene-1,3-diol that is the (S)-enantiomer of orciprenaline.

name: (R)-orciprenaline sulfate
definition: An alkylammonium sulfate obtained by combining (R)-orciprenaline and sulfuric acid in a 2:1 ratio.

name: 12-HPE(8,10,14)TrE(1-)
definition: A polyunsaturated fatty acid anion that is the conjugate base of 12-HPE(8,10,14)TrE, obtained by deprotonation of the carboxy group; major species at pH 7.3.

name: triazoxide
definition: A member of the class of benzotriazines that is 1,2,4-benzotriazine 1-oxide which is substituted by chlorine at position 7 and by a 1H-imidazol-1-yl group at position 3. A fungicide, it is used as a seed treatment for control of seed-borne Pyrenophora graminea and Pyrenophora teres in barley.

name: 14-HPDHE(1-)
definition: A polyunsaturated fatty acid anion that is the conjugate base of 14-HPDHE, obtained by deprotonation of the carboxy group; major species at pH 7.3.

name: (S)-orciprenaline sulfate
definition: An alkylammonium sulfate obtained by combining (S)-orciprenaline and sulfuric acid in a 2:1 ratio.

name: (S)-orciprenaline(1+)
definition: An organic cation obtained by protonation of the secondary amino function of (S)-orciprenaline.

name: 10-HPO(6,8,12)TrE(1-)
definition: A polyunsaturated fatty acid anion that is the conjugate base of 10-HPO(6,8,12)TrE, obtained by deprotonation of the carboxy group; major species at pH 7.3.

name: 12(R)-HETE(1-)
definition: A polyunsaturated fatty acid anion that is the conjugate base of 12(R)-HETE, obtained by deprotonation of the carboxy group; major species at pH 7.3.

name: 8-HPETE methyl ester
definition: A fatty acid methyl ester resulting from the formal condensation of the carboxy group of 12-HPETE with methanol.

name: metrafenone
definition: A member of the class of benzophenones that is benzophenone in which one of the phenyl groups is substituted by methoxy groups at positions 2, 3, and 4 and by a methyl group at position 6, while the other is substituted at positions 2, 3, and 6 by methyl, bromine, and methoxy groups, respectively. A fungicide with protectant and curative properties, it is used for the control of powdery mildew in cereals and grape vines.

name: pyriofenone
definition: An aromatic ketone that is metrafenone in which the 3-bromo-6-methoxy-2-methylphenyl group is replaced by a 5-chloro-2-methoxy-4-methylpyridin-3-yl group. It is a fungicide developed for the control of powdery mildew in cereals and grape vines.

name: organosulfonic ester
definition: An ester resulting from the formal condensation of the hydroxy group of an alcohol, phenol, heteroarenol, or enol with an organosulfonic acid.

name: chlorophyllide a(2-)
definition: A cyclic tetrapyrrole anion arising from deprotonation of the carboxy group and the C-21 posiiton of chlorophyllide a. It is the major microspecies at pH 7.3 (according to Marvin v 6.2.0.).

name: divinyl chlorophyllide a(2-)
definition: A cyclic tetrapyrrole anion that is the conjugate base of divinyl chlorophyllide a, arising from deprotonation of the carboxy group and formation of a carbide ion. It is the major microspecies at pH 7.3 (according to Marvin v 6.2.0.).

name: protochlorophyllide(2-)
definition: A cyclic tetrapyrrole anion that is the conjugate base of protochlorophyllide, arising from deprotonation of the carboxy group and formation of a carbide ion. It is the major microspecies at pH 7.3 (according to Marvin v 6.2.0.).

name: benzenesulfonate ester
definition: An arenesulphonate ester resulting from the formal condensation of the hydroxy group of an alcohol, enol, phenol or heteroarenol with benzenesulfonic acid.

name: eliglustat tartrate
definition: A tartrate that is the hemitartrate salt of eliglustat. A ceramide glucosyltransferase inhibitor used (as its tartrate salt) for treatment of Gaucher's disease.

name: benzamidoxime
definition: A member of the class of amidoximes obtained by formal condensation of the carbonyl group of benzamide with hydroxylamine.

name: eliglustat(1+)
definition: An organic cation obtained by protonation of the tertiary amino function of eliglustat.

name: chlorophyllide b(2-)
definition: A cyclic tetrapyrrole anion that is derived from chlorophyllide b via deprotonation of the carboxy group and formation of a carbide ion. It is the major microspecies at pH 7.3 (according to Marvin v 6.2.0.).

name: 7(1)-hydroxychlorophyllide a(2-)
definition: A cyclic tetrapyrrole anion that is derived from 7(1)-hydroxychlorophyllide a via deprotonation of the carboxy group and formation of a carbide ion. It is the major microspecies at pH 7.3 (according to Marvin v 6.2.0.).

name: N-stearoylsphingosine-1-phosphocholine
definition: A sphingomyelin d18:1 in which the ceramide N-acyl group is specified as stearoyl (octadecanoyl).

name: N-icosanoylsphingosine-1-phosphocholine
definition: A sphingomyelin d18:1 in which the ceramide N-acyl group is specified as icosanoyl.

name: N-hexacosenoylsphingosine-1-phosphocholine
definition: A sphingomyelin in which the total number of carbons in the fatty acyl group is 26 with 1 double bond.

name: N-(2-hydroxyhexacosanoyl)sphingosine
definition: A 2-(2-hydroxyacyl)sphingosine in which the ceramide N-acyl group is specified as 2-hydroxyhexacosanoyl.

name: N-octacosanoylsphingosine
definition: An N-acylsphingosine in which the ceramide N-acyl group is specified as octacosanoyl.

name: 2,6-dimethyl-4-tridecylmorpholine
definition: A member of the class of morpholines that is 2,6-dimethylmorpholine in which the hydrogen attached to the nitrogen is replaced by a tridecyl group. The configuration at positions 2 and 6 is unknown or unspecified.

name: 2-sec-butyl-4,6-dinitrophenyl 3-methylbut-2-enoate
definition: An enoate ester obtained by formal condensation of the carboxy group of 3,3-dimethylacrylic acid with the phenolic hydroxy group of dinoseb.

name: (R)-binapacryl
definition: A 2-sec-butyl-4,6-dinitrophenyl 3-methylbut-2-enoate that is the (R)-enantiomer of binapacryl.

name: 2,6-dimethyl-4-undecylmorpholine
definition: A member of the class of morpholines that is 2,6-dimethylmorpholine in which the hydrogen attached to the nitrogen is replaced by an undecyl group. The configuration at positions 2 and 6 is unknown or unspecified.

name: 2,6-dimethyl-4-tetradecylmorpholine
definition: A member of the class of morpholines that is 2,6-dimethylmorpholine in which the hydrogen attached to the nitrogen is replaced by a tetradecyl group. The configuration at positions 2 and 6 is unknown or unspecified.

name: (S)-binapacryl
definition: A 2-sec-butyl-4,6-dinitrophenyl 3-methylbut-2-enoate that is the (S)-enantiomer of binapacryl.

name: meptyldinocap
definition: A racemate comprising equimolar amounts of (R)- and (S)-meptyldinocap.  A fungicide that is active against powdery mildew mainly on grapes, cucurbits and strawberries. Whilst it is not highly to toxic to birds is is toxic to many aquatic species including fish and algae.

name: 3-vinylbacteriochlorophyllide a(2-)
definition: A cyclic tetrapyrrole anion that is obtained from 3-vinylbacteriochlorophyllide a via deprotonation of the carboxy group and formation of a carbide ion. It is the major microspecies at pH 7.3 (according to Marvin v 6.2.0.).

name: all-cis-polyprenyl diphosphate(3-)
definition: An organohosphate oxoanion resulting from the removal of all three protons from the diphosphate group of all-cis-polyprenyl diphosphate(3-). Major structure at pH 7.3.

name: 2,4-dinitro-6-(octan-2-yl)phenyl (E)-but-2-enoate
definition: An enoate ester obtained by formal condensation of the carboxy group of 3-methylacrylic acid with the phenolic hydroxy group of 2,4-dinitro-6-(octan-2-yl)phenol.

name: (R)-meptyldinocap
definition: A 2,4-dinitro-6-(octan-2-yl)phenyl (E)-but-2-enoate that is the (R)-enantiomer of meptyldinocap.

name: 7(1)-hydroxychlorophyll a(1-)
definition: The cyclic tetrapyrrole anion that is the major form of 7(1)-hydroxychlorophyll a at pH 7.3 (according to Marvin v. 6.2.0).

name: (S)-meptyldinocap
definition: A 2,4-dinitro-6-(octan-2-yl)phenyl (E)-but-2-enoate that is the (S)-enantiomer of meptyldinocap.

name: dinocap
definition: A multi-component mixture comprising 2,6-dinitro-4-octanylphenyl and 2,4-dinitro-6-octanylphenyl esters of (2E)-but-2-enoic acid in which 'octanyl' is a mixture of octan-2-yl, octan-3-yl and octan-4-yl groups. The mixture is used as a protectant fungicide for powdery mildew control. The most active component is 2-(1-methylheptyl)-4,6-dinitrophenyl (2E)-2-butenoate, which has the ISO common name meptyldinocap.

name: dinocap-4
definition: A mixture of 2,6-dinitro-4-octylphenyl crotonates in which 'octyl' is a mixture of 1-methylheptyl, 1-ethylhexyl and 1-propylpentyl groups. A component of dinocap, which is used as a protectant fungicide for powdery mildew control.

name: dinocap-6
definition: A mixture of 2,4-dinitro-6-octylphenyl crotonates in which 'octyl' is a mixture of 1-methylheptyl, 1-ethylhexyl and 1-propylpentyl groups. A component of dinocap, which is used as a protectant fungicide for powdery mildew control. The most active component is where R = 1-methylheptyl, which has the ISO common name meptyldinocap.

name: D-galactaro-1,5-lactone(1-)
definition: A carbohydrate acid anion that is the conjugate base of D-galactaro-1,5-lactone, obtained by deprotonation of the carboxy group; major species at pH 7.3.

name: D-glucaro-1,5-lactone(1-)
definition: A carbohydrate acid anion that is the conjugate base of D-glucaro-1,5-lactone, obtained by deprotonation of the carboxy group; major species at pH 7.3.

name: 2,5-diformylfuran
definition: A member of the class of furans carrying two formyl substituents at positions 2 and 5.

name: 2-(dihydroxymethyl)-5-formylfuran
definition: A member of the class of furans carrying dihydroxymethyl and formyl substituents at positions 2 and 5 respectively.

name: 5-formyl-2-furoate
definition: A furancarboxylate that is the conjugate base of 5-formyl-2-furoic acid, obtained by deprotonation of the carboxy group; major species at pH 7.3.

name: 5-(dihydroxymethyl)-2-furoate
definition: A furancarboxylate that is the conjugate base of 5-(dihydroxymethyl)-2-furoic acid, obtained by deprotonation of the carboxy group; major species at pH 7.3.

name: furan-2,5-dicarboxylate
definition: A dicarboxylic acid dianion obtained by deprotonation of both carboxy groups of furan-2,5-dicarboxylic acid; major species at pH 7.3.

name: pentachlorobenzenes
definition: Any member of the class of chlorobenzenes in which a benzene ring is substituted by five chloro groups.

name: 4,4-dimethyl-8,14-cholestadien-3beta-ol derivative
definition: Any tetracyclic triterpenoid that is derived from 4,4-dimethyl-8,14-cholestadien-3beta-ol.

name: rhodanine 3-acetic acid derivative
definition: Any thiazolidinone that is derived from rhodanine 3-acetic acid.

name: silthiofam
definition: A monocarboxylic acid amide obtained by formal condensation of the carboxy group from 4,5-dimethyl-2-(trimethylsilyl)thiophene-3-carboxlic acid with the amino group of allylamine. A fungicide seed dressing for cereals used mainly to control 'take-all'.

name: 5-amino-1-[2,6-dichloro-4-(trifluoromethyl)phenyl]-4-[(trifluoromethyl)sulfinyl]-1H-pyrazole-3-carbonitrile
definition: A member of the class of pyrazoles that is 1H-pyrazole that is substituted at positions 1, 3, 4, and 5 by 2,6-dichloro-4-(trifluoromethyl)phenyl, cyano, (trifluoromethyl)sulfinyl, and amino groups, respectively.

name: (R)-fipronil
definition: A 5-amino-1-[2,6-dichloro-4-(trifluoromethyl)phenyl]-4-[(trifluoromethyl)sulfinyl]-1H-pyrazole-3-carbonitrile that has R configuration at the sulfoxide.

name: (S)-fipronil
definition: A 5-amino-1-[2,6-dichloro-4-(trifluoromethyl)phenyl]-4-[(trifluoromethyl)sulfinyl]-1H-pyrazole-3-carbonitrile that has S configuration at the sulfoxide.

name: L-citrulline residue
definition: An L-alpha-amino acid residue derived from L-citrulline.

name: ametoctradin
definition: A member of the class of triazolopyrimidines that is [1,2,4]triazolo[1,5-a]pyrimidin-7-amine carrying additional ethyl and octyl substituents at positions 5 and 6 respectively. A fungicide for the control of late blight and downey mildew on potatoes and other crops including vines.

name: marine xenobiotic metabolite
definition: Any metabolite produced by metabolism of a xenobiotic compound in marine macro- and microorganisms.

name: RNA polyanion
definition: An ionic polymer obtained by global deprotonation of the phosphate OH groups of any RNA. Major structure at pH 7.3

name: anionic tRNA polymer
definition: A polyanionic macromolecule obtained by deprotonation of the phosphate OH groups of tRNA polymer. Major structure at pH 7.3

name: nucleoside 3',5'-bisphosphate(4-)
definition: An organophosphate oxoanion obtained by deprotonation of the phosphate OH groups of any nucleoside 3',5'-bisphosphate; major species at pH 7.3.

name: monochlorobenzenes
definition: Any member of the class of chlorobenzenes containing a mono- or poly-substituted benzene ring in which only one substituent is chlorine.

name: G-573
definition: A monocarboxylic acid amide obtained by formal condensation of the carboxy group of 7-fluoro-3-[(2-fluoro-4-iodophenyl)amino]furo[3,2-c]pyridine-2-carboxylic acid with the amino group of (2S)-1-(aminooxy)propan-2-ol.

name: GDC-0879
definition: A member of the class of pyrazoles that is 1-(2-hydroxyethyl)pyrazole carrying additional 4-pyridyl and 1-(hydroxyimino)indan-5-yl substituents at positions 3 and 4 respectively.

name: MS-417
definition: A member of the class of thienotriazolodiazepines that is the methyl ester of [(6S)-4-(4-chlorophenyl)-2,3,9-trimethyl-6H-thieno[3,2-f][1,2,4]triazolo[4,3-a][1,4]diazepin-6-yl]acetic acid. A bromodomain and extra-terminal domain (BET)-specific inhibitor that belongs to a group of thienodiazepine-based compounds

name: 4-(phosphooxymethyl)-2-furancarboxaldehyde(2-)
definition: An organophosphate oxoanion obtained by deprotonation of the phosphate OH groups of 5-(phosphooxymethyl)-2-furancarboxaldehyde; major species at pH 7.3.

name: sn-glycerophosphodiester(1-)
definition: A glycerol 1-phosphodiester(1-) obtained by deprotonation of the phosphate OH group of any sn-glycerophosphodiester; major species at pH 7.3.

name: alpha-amino acid ester(1+)
definition: A primary ammonium ion obtained by protonation of the amino group of any alpha-amino acid ester; major species at pH 7.3.

name: beta-D-glucosiduronate
definition: A carbohydrate acid derivative anion obtained by deprotonation of the carboxy group of any beta-D-glucosiduronic acid; major species at pH 7.3.

name: N(5)-acyl-L-ornithine ester(1+)
definition: A primary ammonium ion obtained by protonation of the amino group of any N(5)-acyl-L-ornithine ester; major species at pH 7.3.

name: ovothiol C
definition: A L-histidine derivative that is N,N-dimethyl-L-histidine substituted at positions N3 and C5 on the imidazole ring by methyl and mercapto groups respectively.

name: 1,2-dioctanoyl-sn-glycero-3-phospho-(1D-myo-inositol-3,4,5-trisphosphate)(7-)
definition: A 1-phosphatidyl-1D-myo-inositol 3,4,5-trisphosphate(7-) in which the phosphatidyl acyl groups at positions 1 and 2 are both specified as octanoyl.

name: 1,2-dioctanoyl-sn-glycero-3-phospho-(1D-myo-inositol-3,4-bisphosphate)(5-)
definition: A 1-phosphatidyl-1D-myo-inositol 3,4-bisphosphate(5-) in which the phosphatidyl acyl groups at positions 1 and 2 are both specified as octanoyl.

name: S-(5-histidyl)cysteine sulfoxide
definition: A L-cysteine derivative that is L-cysteine sulfoxide in which the hydrogen attached to sulfur is replaced by a 5-L-histidyl group.

name: 1,2-dioctanoyl-sn-glycero-3-phospho-(1D-myo-inositol-4,5-bisphosphate)(5-)
definition: A 1-phosphatidyl-1D-myo-inositol 4,5-bisphosphate(5-) in which the phosphatidyl acyl groups at positions 1 and 2 are both specified as octanoyl.

name: 1,2-dihexadecanoyl-sn-glycero-3-phospho-(1D-myo-inositol-3,4,5-trisphosphate)(7-)
definition: A 1-phosphatidyl-1D-myo-inositol 3,4,5-trisphosphate(7-) in which the phosphatidyl acyl groups at positions 1 and 2 are both specified as hexadecanoyl (palmitoyl).

name: O-phospho-L-serine(2-) residue
definition: An alpha-amino-acid residue anion obtained by deprotonation of the phosphate OH groups of O-phospho-L-serine residue; major speices at pH 7.3.

name: 1,2-dihexadecanoyl-sn-glycero-3-phospho-(1D-myo-inositol-4,5-bisphosphate)(5-)
definition: A 1-phosphatidyl-1D-myo-inositol 4,5-bisphosphate(5-) in which the phosphatidyl acyl groups at positions 1 and 2 are both specified as hexadecanoyl (palmitoyl).

name: (14Z,17Z,20Z,23Z,26Z)-dotriacontapentaenoic acid
definition: A very long-chain omega-6 fatty acid that is dotriacontapentaenoic acid having five double bonds located at positions 14, 17, 20, 23 and 26 (the 14Z,17Z,20Z,23Z,26Z-isomer).

name: gamma-glutamyltyramine zwitterion
definition: An L-alpha-amino acid zwitterion obtained by transfer of a proton from the carboxy to the amino group of gamma-glutamyltyramine

name: (E)-dimethomorph
definition: An enamide resulting from the formal condensation of (2E)-3-(4-chlorophenyl)-3-(3,4-dimethoxyphenyl)acrylic acid with the amino group of morpholine. The agricultural fungicide dimethomorph is a mixture of (E)- and (Z)-dimethomorph; only the Z isomer has fungicidal activity.

name: (Z)-dimethomorph
definition: An enamide resulting from the formal condensation of (2Z)-3-(4-chlorophenyl)-3-(3,4-dimethoxyphenyl)acrylic acid with the amino group of morpholine. The agricultural fungicide dimethomorph is a mixture of (E)- and (Z)-dimethomorph; only the Z isomer has fungicidal activity.

name: (Z)-flumorph
definition: An enamide resulting from the formal condensation of (2Z)-3-(4-fluorophenyl)-3-(3,4-dimethoxyphenyl)acrylic acid with the amino group of morpholine.

name: (E)-flumorph
definition: An enamide resulting from the formal condensation of (2E)-3-(4-fluorophenyl)-3-(3,4-dimethoxyphenyl)acrylic acid with the amino group of morpholine.

name: [5-(ammoniomethyl)-3-furyl]methyl phosphate(1-)
definition: An organophosphate oxoanion obtained by deprotonation of the phosphate OH groups and protonation of the amino group of [5-(aminomethyl)-3-furyl]methyl phosphate; major species at pH 7.3.

name: CD532
definition: A member of the class of phenylureas that is urea with 4-[[4-[(5-cyclopentylpyrazol-3-yl)amino]pyrimidin-2-yl]amino]phenyl and 3-[3-(trifluoromethyl)phenyl substituents at positions N1 and N3.

name: 3,6-anhydro-alpha-L-galactopyranose
definition: An anhydrohexose obtained by formation of a ring across the 3 and 6 positions of alpha-L-galactopyranose.

name: 2-hydroxy-5-methyl-1-naphthoic acid
definition: A member of the class of naphthoic acids that is 1-naphthoic acid substituted at positions 2 and 5 by hydroxy and methyl groups respectively.

name: 3,6-anhydro-L-galactonate
definition: A carbohydrate acid anion that is the conjugate base of 3,6-anhydro-L-galactonic acid, obtained by deprotonation of the carboxy group; major species at pH 7.3.

name: 1,2-dihexadecanoyl-sn-glycero-3-phospho-(1D-myo-inositol-4-phosphate)(3-)
definition: A 1-phosphatidyl-1D-myo-inositol 4-phosphate(3-) in which the phosphatidyl acyl groups at positions 1 and 2 are both specified as hexadecanoyl (palmitoyl).

name: O-(S-3-oxododecanoylpantetheine-4'-phosphoryl)-L-serine residue
definition: An O-(S-3-oxoacylpantetheine-4'-phosphoryl)serine(1-) residue in which the S-acyl group is specified as 3-oxododecanoyl.

name: iminoarginine(1+)
definition: A guanidinium ion obtained by protonation of iminoarginine; major species at pH 7.3.

name: 4-(5-O-phospho-beta-D-ribofuranosyl)phenol
definition: A ribose monophosphate that is D-ribofuranose 5-phosphate in which the anomeric OH group is replaced by a 4-hydroxy phenyl group (the beta-D-anomer).

name: 2-isopropyl-6-methyl-4-pyrimidinone
definition: A  pyrimidone that is pyrimidin-4(1H)-one substituted by a methyl group at position 6 and an isopropyl group at position 2. It is a metabolite of diazinon.

name: N,N-didesmethylvenlafaxine
definition: A  monomethoxybenzene that is the N,N-didesmethyl derivative of venlafaxine.

name: metamitron-desamino
definition: A member of the class of 1,2,4-triazines that is  metamitron in which the amino group has been replaced by a hydrogen atom. It is a metabolite of  metamitron.

name: metribuzin-diketo
definition: A member of the class of  1,2,4-triazines that is 1,2,4-triazine-3,5(2H,4H)-dione substituted by an amino group at position 4 and a tert-butyl group at position 6. It is a metabolite of metribuzin.

name: alachlor ESA
definition: An organosulfonic acid that is 2-oxoethanesulfonic acid substituted by (2,6-diethylphenyl)(methoxymethyl)amino group at position 2. It is a metabolite of alachlor.

name: alachlor OXA
definition: An oxo monocarboxylic acid that is oxoacetic acid substituted by a (2,6-diethylphenyl)(methoxymethyl)amino group at position 2. It is a metabolite of the herbicide alachlor.

name: acetochlor OXA
definition: A monocarboxylic acid that is oxoacetic acid substituted by a (ethoxymethyl)(2-ethyl-6-methylphenyl)amino group at position 2. It is a metabolite of acetochlor.

name: acetochlor ESA
definition: An organosulfonic acid that is 2-oxoethanesulfonic acid substituted by an (ethoxymethyl)(2-ethyl-6-methylphenyl)amino group at position 2.

name: trinexapac
definition: A monocarboxylic acid that is 3,5-dioxocyclohexanecarboxylic acid substituted by a cyclopropyl(hydroxy)methylidene group at position 4. It is a metabolite of the plant growth regulator trinexapac-ethyl.

name: 5-methyl-1H-benzotriazole
definition: A member of the class of  benzotriazoles that is 1H-benzotriazole substituted by a methyl group at position 5.

name: N(4)-acetylsulfadimethoxine
definition: A sulfonamide that is benzenesulfonamide substituted by an acetylamino group at position 4 and a 4,6-dimethoxy-pyrimidin-2-yl group at the nitrogen atom. It is a metabolite of the sulfonamide antibiotic sulfadimethoxine.

name: N(4)-acetylsulfamethazine
definition: A sulfonamide that is benzenesulfonamide substituted by an acetylamino group at position 4 and a 4,6-dimethyl-pyrimidin-2-yl group at the nitrogen atom. It is a metabolite of the antibiotic sulfamethazine.

name: N(4)-acetylsulfadiazine
definition: A  sulfonamide that is benzenesulfonamide substituted by an acetylamino group at position 4 and a pyrimidin-2-yl group at the nitrogen atom. It is a metabolite of the drug sulfadiazine.

name: N(4)-acetylsulfathiazole
definition: A sulfonamide that is benzenesulfonamide substituted by an acetylamino group at position 4 and a 1,3-thiazol-2-yl group at the nitrogen atom. It is a metabolite of sulfathiazole.

name: dimethenamid OXA
definition: A monocarboxylic acid that is oxoacetic acid substituted by a (2,4-dimethylthiophen-3-yl)(1-methoxypropan-2-yl)amino group at position 2. It is a metabolite of the herbicide dimethenamid.

name: dimethenamide ESA
definition: An organosulfonic acid that is 2-oxoethanesulfonic acid substituted by a (2,4-dimethylthiophen-3-yl)(1-methoxypropan-2-yl)amino group at position 2.

name: metolachlor OXA
definition: A racemate containing equimolar amounts of (R)- and (S)-metolachlor OXA.

name: atrazine-desethyl-2-hydroxy
definition: A diamino-1,3,5-triazine that is N-(propan-2-yl)-1,3,5-triazine-2,4-diamine substituted by a hydroxy group at position 2. It is a metabolite of the herbicide atrazine.

name: diuron-desdimethyl
definition: A member of the class of ureas that is urea substituted by a 3,4-dichlorophenyl group at position 1. It is a metabolite of the herbicide diuron.

name: sulcotrione
definition: An  aromatic ketone that is cyclohexane-1,3-dione substituted by a 2-chloro-4-(methylsulfonyl)benzoyl group at position 2.

name: diuron-desmethyl
definition: A member of the class of phenylureas that is urea in which a hydrogens attached to one nitrogen is substituted by a methyl group, and one of the hydrogens attached to the other nitrogen is substituted by a 3,4-dichlorophenyl group. It is a metabolite of diuron.

name: N,N-dimethyl-N'-phenylsulfamide
definition: A member of the class of sulfamides that is N-phenylsulfuric diamide substituted by two methyl groups at the amino nitrogen atom. It is a metabolite of the agrochemical dichlofluanid.

name: isoproturon-monodemethyl
definition: A member of the class of phenylureas that is 1-methylurea substituted by a p-cumenyl group at position 3. It is a metabolite of the herbicide isoproturon.

name: fenofibric acid
definition: A monocarboxylic acid that is 2-methylpropanoic acid substituted by a 4-(4-chlorobenzoyl)phenoxy group at position 2. It is a metabolite of the drug fenofibrate.

name: N,N-dimethyl-N'-p-tolylsulfamide
definition: A member of the class of  sulfamides that is N,N-dimethylsulfuric diamide substituted by a 4-methylphenyl group at the amino nitrogen atom. It is a metabolite of the agrochemical tolylfluanid.

name: terbutylazine-2-hydroxy
definition: A diamino-1,3,5-triazine that is 1,3,5-triazin-2-ol substituted by a tert-butylamino group at position 4 and an ethylamino group at position 6. It is a metabolite of the herbicide terbutylazine,

name: metolachlor ESA
definition: A racemate consisting of equimolar amounts of (R)- and (S)-metolachlor ESA.

name: flufenacet ESA
definition: An  organosulfonic acid that is 2-oxoethanesulfonic acid substituted by a (4-fluorophenyl)(propan-2-yl)amino group at position 2. It is metabolite of the herbicide flufenacet.

name: flufenacet OXA
definition: A monocarboxylic acid that is oxoacetic acid substituted by a (4-fluorophenyl)(propan-2-yl)amino group at position 2. It is a metabolite of the herbicide flufenacet.

name: propachlor ESA
definition: An organosulfonic acid that is 2-oxoethanesulfonic acid substituted by a phenyl(propan-2-yl)amino group at position 2. It is a metabolite of the herbicide propachlor.

name: simazine-2-hydroxy
definition: A diamino-1,3,5-triazine that is N,N'-diethyl-1,3,5-triazine-2,4-diamine substituted by a hydroxy group at position 2. It is a metabolite of the herbicide simazine.

name: terbutylazine-desethyl-2-hydroxy
definition: A diamino-1,3,5-triazine that is 1,3,5-triazin-2-ol substituted by an amino group at position 4 and a tert-butylamino group at position 6. It is metabolite of the herbicide terbutylazine.

name: atenolol acid
definition: A monocarboxylic acid that is phenylacetic acid substituted by a 2-hydroxy-3-(propan-2-ylamino)propoxy group at position 4. It is a metabolite of the drug atenolol.

name: chloridazone-desphenyl
definition: A heteroaryl hydroxy compound that is pyridazin-3-ol substituted by an amino group at position 5 and a chloro group at position 4. It is a metabolite of the herbicide chloridazone.

name: chloridazone-methyl-desphenyl
definition: A pyridazinone that is pyridazin-3(2H)-one substituted by an amino group at position 5, a chloro group at position 4 and a methyl group at position 2. It is a metabolite of the herbicide chloridazone.jfuyklriltoil

name: ritalinic acid
definition: A monocarboxylic acid that is phenylacetic acid substituted by a piperidin-2-yl group at position 2. It is a metabolite of the drug methylphenidate.

name: metazachlor ESA
definition: An organosulfonic acid that is 2-oxoethanesulfonic acid substituted by a (2,6-dimethylphenyl)(1H-pyrazol-1-ylmethyl)amino group at position 2. It is metabolite of the herbicide metazachlor.

name: metazachlor OXA
