definition: A monocarboxylic acid that is oxoacetic acid substituted by a (2,6-dimethylphenyl)(1H-pyrazol-1-ylmethyl)amino group at position 2. It is metabolite of the herbicide metazachlor.

name: dimethachlor ESA
definition: An  organosulfonic acid that is 2-oxoethanesulfonic acid substituted by a (2,6-dimethylphenyl)(2-methoxyethyl)amino group at position 2. It is a metabolite of the herbicide dimethachlor.

name: dimethachlor OXA
definition: A monocarboxylic acid that is oxoacetic acid substituted by a (2,6-dimethylphenyl)(2-methoxyethyl)amino group at position 2.

name: 2',2'-difluoro-2'-deoxyuridine
definition: A pyrimidine 2'-deoxyribonucleoside that is uridine in which the hydroxy group at position 2' has been replaced by two fluoro substituents. It is a metabolite of the drug gemcitabine.

name: fipronil-sulfone
definition: A member of the class of pyrazoles that is 1H-pyrazole that is substituted at positions 1, 3, 4, and 5 by 2,6-dichloro-4-(trifluoromethyl)phenyl, cyano, (trifluoromethyl)sulfonyl, and amino groups, respectively. It is a metabolite of the agrochemical fipronil.

name: fipronil-sulfide
definition: A member of the class of pyrazoles that is 1H-pyrazole that is substituted at positions 1, 3, 4, and 5 by 2,6-dichloro-4-(trifluoromethyl)phenyl, cyano, (trifluoromethyl)sulfanyl, and amino groups, respectively. It is a metabolite of the agrochemical fipronil.

name: fipronil-desulfinyl
definition: A member of the class of pyrazoles that is 1H-pyrazole that is substituted at positions 1, 3, 4, and 5 by 2,6-dichloro-4-(trifluoromethyl)phenyl, cyano, trifluoromethyl, and amino groups, respectively.

name: 3,5,6-trichloropyridine-2-one
definition: A pyridone that is pyridin-2(1H)-one substituted by chloro groups at positions 3, 5 and 6. It is a metabolite of the agrochemical chlorpyrifos.

name: perfluoropentanoic acid
definition: A monocarboxylic acid that is perfluorinated pentanoic acid.

name: perfluorohexanoic acid
definition: A monocarboxylic acid that is perfluorinated hexanoic acid.

name: perfluoroundecanoic acid
definition: A fluoroalkanoic acid that is perfluorinated undecanoic acid.

name: 6:2 fluorotelomer unsaturated carboxylic acid
definition: A fluorotelomer that is oct-2-enoic acid substituted by fluoro groups at positions 3, 4, 4, 5, 5,6, 6, 7, 7, 8, 8 and 8 respectively.

name: 8:2 fluorotelomer unsaturated carboxylic acid
definition: A fluorotelomer that is dec-2-enoic acid substituted by fluoro groups at positions 3, 4, 4, 5, 5, 6, 6, 7, 7, 8, 8, 9, 9, 10, 10 and 10 respectively.

name: azoxystrobin acid
definition: An aryloxypyrimidine having a 4,6-diphenoxypyrimidine skeleton in which one of the phenyl rings is cyano-substituted at C-2 and the other carries a 1-carboxy-2-methoxyethenyl substituent, also at C-2. It is a metabolite of the fungicidal agrochemical azoxystrobin.

name: ranitidine-S-oxide
definition: A sulfoxide derivative of the drug ranitidine.

name: ranitidine N-oxide
definition: A N-oxide derivative of ranitidine.

name: climbazole
definition: A racemate composed of equimolar amounts of (R)- and (S)-climbazole. It is a topically applied antifungal agent used to treat human fungal skin infections.

name: tritosulfuron
definition: A sulfonamide  that is benzenesulfonamide substituted by a trifluoromethyl group at position 2 and a [4-methoxy-6-(trifluoromethyl)-1,3,5-triazin-2-yl]carbamoyl group at the nitrogen atom.

name: acesulfame
definition: A sulfamate ester that is 1,2,3-oxathiazin-4(3H)-one 2,2-dioxide substituted by a methyl group at position 6.

name: foramsulfuron
definition: A member of the class of  benzamides that is N,N-dimethylbenzamide substituted by a formylamino group at position 4 and a [(4,6-dimethoxypyrimidin-2-yl)carbamoyl]sulfamoyl group at position 2.

name: neotame
definition: A dipeptide composed of N-(3,3-dimethylbutyl)-L-aspartic acid and methyl L-phenylalanate units joined by a peptide linkage.

name: clopidogrel carboxylic acid
definition: A thienopyridine that is 6,7-dihydrothieno[3,2-c]pyridin-5(4H)-ylacetic acid substituted by a 2-chlorophenyl group at position 2. It is a metabolite of the drug  clopidogrel.

name: perfluorooctane sulfonamidoacetic acid
definition: A monocarboxylic acid that is (sulfoamino)acetic acid substituted by a heptadecafluorooctyl group at the sulfur atom.

name: N-methylperfluorooctane sulfonamidoacetic acid
definition: A sulfonamide that is the N-methyl derivative of perfluorooctane sulfonamidoacetic acid.

name: N-ethylperfluorooctane sulfonamidoacetic acid
definition: A sulfonamide that is the N-ethyl derivative of perfluorooctane sulfonamidoacetic acid.

name: perfluorooctyl phosphate
definition: A monoalkyl phosphate that is 3,3,4,4,5,5,6,6,7,7,8,8,8-tridecafluorooctan-1-ol in which the hydroxyl hydrogen is substituted by a phosphate group.

name: metolachlor morpholinone
definition: A member of the class of  morpholines that is morpholin-3-one substituted by a 2-ethyl-6-methylphenyl group at position 4 and a methyl group at position 5. It is a metabolite of metolachlor.

name: ethofumesate-2-keto
definition: A methanesulfonate ester that is methanesulfonic acid in which the hydrogen of the hydroxy group has been replaced by a 3,3-dimethyl-2-oxo-2,3-dihydro-1-benzofuran-5-yl group. It is a metabolite of the herbicide ethofumesate.

name: 2-methyl-4-amino-6-methoxy-s-triazine
definition: A monoamino-1,3,5-triazine that is 1,3,5-triazin-2-amine substituted by a methoxy group at position 4 and a methyl group at position 6. It is a metabolite of the herbicide thifensulfuron-methyl.

name: 2-aminosulfonyl-benzoic acid methyl ester
definition: A benzoate ester that is methyl benzoate substituted by a sulfamoyl group at position 2. It is a metabolite of the herbicide metsulfuron-methyl.

name: 4-acetamidoantipyrine
definition: A member of the class of  pyrazoles that is antipyrine substituted by an acetylamino group at position 4. It is a drug metabolite of metamizole.

name: isoproturon-didemethyl
definition: A member of the class of phenylureas that is urea substituted by a p-cumenyl group at position 1. It is a metabolite of the herbicide isoproturon.

name: N'-(2,4-dimethylphenyl)-N-methylformamidine
definition: A member of the class of  formamidines that is N-methylimidoformamide in which the hydrogen attached to the nitrogen atom has been replaced by a  2,4-dimethylphenyl group. It is a metabolite of the insecticide amitraz.

name: iooxitalamic acid
definition: An  organoiodine compound that is 2,4,6-triiodobenzoic acid substituted by an acetylamino group at position 3 and a (2-hydroxyethyl)carbamoyl group at position 5. It is used as a contrast medium.

name: 4,5-dichloro-2-n-octyl-3(2H)-isothiazolone
definition: A 1,2-thiazole that is 1,2-thiazol-3(2H)-one substituted by chloro groups at positions 4 and 5 and an octyl group at position 2. It is used as a fungicide.

name: galaxolidone
definition: An  organic heterotricyclic compound that is 4,6,7,8-tetrahydrocyclopenta[g]isochromen-1(3H)-one substituted by methyl groups at positions 4, 6, 6, 7, 8 and 8 respectively. It is a metabolite of the synthetic musk galaxolide.

name: propachlor OXA
definition: A monocarboxylic acid that is oxoacetic acid substituted by a phenyl(propan-2-yl)amino group at position 2. It is a metabolite of the herbicide propachlor.

name: sebuthylazine
definition: A racemate composed of equimolar amounts of (R)- and (S)-sebuthylazine. It is an agrochemical used as a herbicide.

name: terbutylazine-desethyl
definition: A diamino-1,3,5-triazine that is 1,3,5-triazine-2,4-diamine substituted by a tert-butyl group at the amino nitrogen and a chloro group at position 6. It is metabolite of the herbicide terbutylazine.

name: pethoxamide
definition: A monocarboxylic acid amide that is acetamide substituted by a chloro group at position 2 and a  2-ethoxyethyl and a 2-methyl-1-phenylprop-1-en-1-yl at the nitrogen atom. It is an agrochemical used as a herbicide.

name: pinoxaden
definition: A pyrazolooxadiazepine that is 7-oxo-1,2,4,5-tetrahydro-7H-pyrazolo[1,2-d][1,4,5]oxadiazepin which is substituted at positions 8 and 9 by 2,6-diethyl-4-methylphenyl and pivaloyloxy groups, respectively. A pro-herbicide (by hydrolysis of the pivalate ester to give the corresponding enol), it is used for control of grass weeds in cereal crops.

name: N-desmethylvenlafaxine
definition: A monomethoxybenzene that is the N-desmethyl derivative of venlafaxine.

name: 4-formylaminoantipyrine
definition: A  pyrazolone that is 1,2-dihydro-3H-pyrazol-3-one substituted by a formaylamino group at position 4, methyl groups at positions 1 and 5 and a phenyl group at position 2. It is a metabolite of aminophenazone.

name: O-desmethylvenlafaxine
definition: A tertiary amino compound that is N,N-dimethylethanamine substituted at position 1 by a 1-hydroxycyclohexyl and 4-hydroxyphenyl group. It is a metabolite of the drug venlafaxine.

name: D617
definition: A nitrile that is pentanenitrile substituted by a 3,4-dimethoxyphenyl group at position 2, a methylamino group at position 4 and an isopropyl group at position 2. It is a metabolite of the drug verapamil.

name: N,O-didesmethylvenlafaxine
definition: A secondary amino compound that is N-methylethanamine substituted by a 1-hydroxycyclohexyl and a 4-hydroxyphenyl group at position 1. It is a metabolite of the drug venlafaxine.

name: atenolol-desisopropyl
definition: A member of the class of ethanolamines that is 2-aminoethanol substituted by a [4-(2-amino-2-oxoethyl)phenoxy]methyl group at position 1. It is a metabolite of the drug atenolol.

name: moclobemide
definition: A member of the class of  benzamides that is benzamide substituted by a chloro group at position 4 and a 2-(morpholin-4-yl)ethyl group at the nitrogen atom. It acts as a reversible monoamine oxidase inhibitor and is used in the treatment of depression.

name: 10,11-trans-dihydroxy-10,11-dihydrocarbamazepine
definition: A  dibenzoazepine that is 10,11-dihydro-5H-dibenzo[b,f]azepine-5-carboxamide substituted by hydroxy groups at positions 10 and 11. It is a metabolite of the drug carbamazepine.

name: diazoxon
definition: An  organic phosphate that is diethyl hydrogen phosphate in which the hydrogen of the hydroxy group has been replaced by a 6-methyl-2-(propan-2-yl)pyrimidin-4-yl group. It is a metabolite of the pesticide diazinon.

name: dioxoaminopyrine
definition: A monocarboxylic acid amide that is N,N-dimethyl-2-oxoacetamide substituted by a 2-acetyl-2-methyl-1-phenylhydrazinyl group at position 2. It is a metabolite of the drug aminopyrine.

name: neohesperidin dihydrochalcone
definition: A member of the  dihydrochalcones that is 3,2',4',6'-tetrahydroxy-4-methoxydihydrochalcone attached to a neohesperidosyl residue at position 4' via glycosidic linkage. It is found in sweet orange.

name: 1-(3-(trifluoromethyl)phenyl)piperazine
definition: A N-arylpiperazine that is piperazine substituted by a 3-(trifluoromethyl)phenyl group at position 1. A serotonergic agonist used as a recreational drug.

name: 2',3'-di-O-acetyl-5'-deoxy-5-fluorocytidine
definition: A member of the class of cytidines that is a metabolite of the drug capecitabine.

name: bisperfluorooctyl phosphate
definition: A dialkyl phosphate in which the alkyl group specified is perfluorooctyl.

name: bisperfluorodecyl phosphate
definition: A dialkyl phosphate in which the alkyl group specified is perfluorodecyl.

name: perfluorodecyl phosphate
definition: A monoalkyl phosphate in which the alkyl group specified is perfluorodecyl.

name: methiocarb-sulfoxide
definition: A carbamate ester obtained by the formal condensation of the phenolic group of 3,5-dimethyl-4-(methylsulfinyl)phenol with the carboxy group of methylcarbamic acid. It is a metabolite of the pesticide methiocarb.

name: imidacloprid-urea
definition: A imidazolidinone that is imidazolidin-2-one substituted by a (6-chloropyridin-3-yl)methyl group at position 1. It is a metabolite of the insecticide imidacloprid.

name: agmatidine 5'-phosphate(1+) residue
definition: An organic cationic group obtained by protonation of agmatidine 5'-phosphate residue; major species at pH 7.3.

name: caldopentamine
definition: A polyazaalkane that is the 1,5,9,13,17-pentaaza derivative of heptodecane.

name: N(4)-aminopropylspermidine
definition: A polyazaalkane that is spermidine in which the amino hydrogen at postion 4 is replaced by a 3-aminopropyl group

name: beta-D-GlcpNAc-(1->2)-alpha-D-Manp-(1->6)-[alpha-D-Manp-(1->3)]-[beta-D-Xylp-(1->2)]-beta-D-Manp-(1->4)-beta-D-GlcpNAc-(1->4)-[alpha-L-Fucp-(1->3)]-D-GlcpNAc
definition: A branched amino octasaccharide consisting of a D-GlcNAc residue at the reducing end with a beta-D-GlcNAc-(1->2)-alpha-D-Man-(1->6)-[alpha-D-Man-(1->3)]-[beta-D-Xyl-(1->2)]-beta-D-Man-(1->4)-beta-D-GlcNAc moiety attached via a beta-(1->4)-linkage and an L-Fuc residue attached via an alpha-(1->3)-linkage.

name: cholesteryl 6-O-myristoyl-alpha-D-glucoside
definition: A cholesteryl glycoside in which cholesterol is linked glycosidically via its 3-hydroxy group to  6-O-myristoyl-alpha-D-glucose. Produced naturally by Helicobacter pylori, a bacteria that colonizes the stomach and which is associated with protection against asthma, it is also chemically synthesized as PI57.

name: 1,2-ditetradecanoyl-sn-glycerol-3-phosphate(2-)
definition: A 1-acyl-2-tetradecanoyl-sn-glycerol 3-phosphate(2-) obtained by deprotonation of both phosphate OH groups of 1,2-ditetradecanoyl-sn-glycerol-3-phosphate(; major species at pH 7.3.

name: N(4)-bis(aminopropyl)spermidine(1+)
definition: A quaternary ammonium ion that is spermidine carrying two 3-aminopropyl substituents at the N-4 position.

name: N(4)-aminopropylspermine
definition: A polyazaalkane that is spermine in which the amino hydrogen at postion 4 is replaced by a 3-aminopropyl group

name: proquinazid
definition: A member of the class of quinazolines that is quinazolin-4-one substituted at positions 2, 3 and 6 by propoxy, propyl and iodo groups respectively. A fungicide with the potential to control powdery mildew in a range of crops including cereals and grapes.

name: N-terminal L-leucyl-L-alpha-amino acid(1+) residue
definition: An alpha-amino-acid cation residue derived from N-terminal L-leucyl-L-alpha-amino acid residue; major species at pH 7.3.

name: ethyl 3-(3,5-dichlorophenyl)-5-methyl-2,4-dioxo-1,3-oxazolidine-5-carboxylate
definition: The ethyl ester of 3-(3,5-dichlorophenyl)-5-methyl-2,4-dioxo-1,3-oxazolidine-5-carboxylic acid.

name: (R)-chlozolinate
definition: An ethyl 3-(3,5-dichlorophenyl)-5-methyl-2,4-dioxo-1,3-oxazolidine-5-carboxylate that is the (R)-enantiomer of chlozolinate.

name: (S)-chlozolinate
definition: An ethyl 3-(3,5-dichlorophenyl)-5-methyl-2,4-dioxo-1,3-oxazolidine-5-carboxylate that is the (S)-enantiomer of chlozolinate.

name: alpha-glucuronosylceramide
definition: A glycosylceramide in which alpha-D-glucuronic acid is linked glycosidically to a 3-hydroxy-2-{[(2R)-2-hydroxynonadecanoyl]amino}icosyl moiety. Present in the cell walls of Sphingomonas bacteria.

name: N-terminal L-arginyl-L-alpha-amino acid(2+) residue
definition: An alpha-amino-acid cation residue derived from N-terminal L-arginyl-L-alpha-amino acid residue; major species at pH 7.3.

name: long-chain alkane
definition: Any alkane having a chain length of at least 13 carbon atoms.

name: (R)-3-phosphomevalonic acid
definition: A carboxyalkyl phosphate that is mevalonic acid phosphorylated at position 3.

name: (trifluoromethyl)benzenes
definition: An organofluorine compound that is (trifluoromethyl)benzene and derivatives arising from substitution of one or more of the phenyl hydrogens.

name: sphinga-4E,14Z-dienine(1+)
definition: A cationic sphingoid obtained by the protonation of the amino group of sphinga-4E,14Z-dienine; major species at pH 7.3.

name: (R)-3,5-bisphosphomevalonic acid
definition: A carboxyalkyl phosphate that is mevalonic acid phosphorylated at positions 3 and 5.

name: monofluorobenzenes
definition: Any member of the class of fluorobenzenes containing a mono- or poly-substituted benzene ring carrying a single fluorine substitutent.

name: trifluorobenzene
definition: Any member of the class of fluorobenzenes carrying three fluorine substituents at unspecified positions.

name: 2-carboxytetracosanoyl-CoA(5-)
definition: The pentaanion of 2-carboxytetracosanoyl-CoA arising from deprotonation of phosphate, diphosphate and carboxylic acid functions; major species at pH 7.3.

name: 2-carboxyhexacosanoyl-CoA(5-)
definition: The pentaanion of 2-carboxyhexacosanoyl-CoA arising from deprotonation of phosphate, diphosphate and carboxylic acid functions; major species at pH 7.3.

name: 3-(methylthio)propanoyl-CoA
definition: An acyl-CoA that results from the formal condensation of the thiol group of coenzyme A with the carboxy group of 3-(methylthio)propionic acid.

name: trilinoleoyl 2-monolysocardiolipin(2-)
definition: A 2-monolysocardiolipin(2-) obtained by deprotonation of the phosphate OH groups of trilinoleoyl 2-monolysocardiolipin; major species at pH 7.3.

name: tetralinoleoyl cardiolipin(2-)
definition: A cardiolipin 72:8(2-) obtained by deprotonation of the phosphate OH groups of tetralinoleoyl cardiolipin; major species at pH 7.3.

name: 1,1',2-trilinoleoyl-2'-oleoyl cardiolipin(2-)
definition: A cardiolipin 72:7(2-) obtained by deprotonation of the phosphate OH groups of 1,1',2-trilinoleoyl-2'-oleoyl cardiolipin; major species at pH 7.3.

name: 1,1',2-trilinoleoyl-2'-palmitoyl cardiolipin(2-)
definition: A cardiolipin 70:6(2-) obtained by deprotonation of the phosphate OH groups of 1,1',2-trilinoleoyl-2'-palmitoyl cardiolipin; major species at pH 7.3.

name: 1-(2,4-dichloro-10,11-dihydrodibenzo[a,d][7]annulen-5-yl)imidazole
definition: A member of the class of dibenzannulenes that is 10,11-dihydrodibenzo[a,d][7]annulene carrying two chloro substituents at positions 2 and 4 as well as an imidazol-1-yl substituent at position 5.

name: N(tele)-phospho-L-histidine residue
definition: An alpha-amino-acid residue derived from substitution of a phospho group on the tele N atom of an L-histidine residue.

name: N(tele)-phosphonato-L-histidine residue
definition: An anionic amino-acid residue formed by loss of both protons from the phospho group of N(tele)-phospho-L-histidine residue, the principal form present at pH 7.3.

name: (R)-eberconazole
definition: 1-(2,4-dichloro-10,11-dihydrodibenzo[a,d][7]annulen-5-yl)imidazole that is the (R)-enantiomer of eberconazole.

name: (S)-eberconazole
definition: 1-(2,4-dichloro-10,11-dihydrodibenzo[a,d][7]annulen-5-yl)imidazole that is the (S)-enantiomer of eberconazole.

name: eberconazole nitrate
definition: A racemate comprising equimolar amounts of (R)- and (S)-eberconazole nitrate. Used for topical treatment of superficial mycoses.

name: L-(R)-iprovalicarb
definition: The stereoisomer of isopropyl (3-methyl-1-{[1-(4-methylphenyl)ethyl]amino}-1-oxobutan-2-yl)carbamate resulting from the formal condensation of L-valine N(alpha)-isopropyl carbamate with (1R)-1-(p-tolyl)ethylamine.

name: L-(S)-iprovalicarb
definition: The stereoisomer of isopropyl (3-methyl-1-{[1-(4-methylphenyl)ethyl]amino}-1-oxobutan-2-yl)carbamate resulting from the formal condensation of L-valine N(alpha)-isopropyl carbamate with (1S)-1-(p-tolyl)ethylamine.

name: (R)-eberconazole nitrate
definition: An organic nitrate salt obtained by reaction of equimolar amounts of (R)-eberconazole and nitric acid.

name: isopropyl (3-methyl-1-{[1-(4-methylphenyl)ethyl]amino}-1-oxobutan-2-yl)carbamate
definition: A carbamate ester that is valinamide in which one of the hydrogens attached to the amide nitrogen is replaced by a 1-(p-tolyl)ethyl group and the alpha-amino group has been converted to the corresponding isopropyl carbamate.

name: (S)-eberconazole nitrate
definition: An organic nitrate salt obtained by reaction of equimolar amounts of (S)-eberconazole and nitric acid.

name: (S)-eberconazole(1+)
definition: An organic cation obtained by protonation of the imidazole group of (S)-eberconazole.

name: (R)-eberconazole(1+)
definition: An organic cation obtained by protonation of the imidazole group of (R)-eberconazole.

name: 2-(4-{[5-(trifluoromethyl)pyridin-2-yl]oxy}phenoxy)propanoic acid
definition: A monocarboxylic acid that is propanoic acid substituted by a 4-{[5-(trifluoromethyl)pyridin-2-yl]oxy}phenoxy group at position 2.

name: fluazifop-P
definition: A 2-(4-{[5-(trifluoromethyl)pyridin-2-yl]oxy}phenoxy)propanoic acid that has R configuration. It is the active enantiomer of the herbicide fluazifop and is the major metabolite of fluazifop-P-butyl.

name: (S)-fluazifop
definition: The (S)-enantiomer of 2-(4-{[5-(trifluoromethyl)pyridin-2-yl]oxy}phenoxy)propanoic acid. It is the inactive enantiomer of the racemic herbicide fluazifop.

name: benthiavalicarb
definition: A carboxamide resulting from the formal condensation of the carboxy group of L-valine with (1R)-1-(6-fluoro-1,3-benzothiazol-2-yl)ethylamine and replacement of one of the hydrogens attached to the alpha-amino group by a carboxy group. It is the active form of the fungicide benthiavalicarb isopropyl (in which the carbamic acid group has been converted to the corresponding isopropyl ester).

name: 1-[2-(2,4-dichlorophenyl)-2-{[4-(phenylsulfanyl)benzyl]oxy}ethyl]imidazole
definition: A member of the class of imidazoles that carries a 2-(2,4-dichlorophenyl)-2-{[4-(phenylsulfanyl)benzyl]oxy}ethyl group at position 1.

name: (S)-fenticonazole
definition: A 1-[2-(2,4-dichlorophenyl)-2-{[4-(phenylsulfanyl)benzyl]oxy}ethyl]imidazole that is the (S)-enantiomer of fenticonazole.

name: (R)-fenticonazole
definition: A 1-[2-(2,4-dichlorophenyl)-2-{[4-(phenylsulfanyl)benzyl]oxy}ethyl]imidazole that is the (R)-enantiomer of fenticonazole.

name: 3,5-diethoxycarbonyl-1,4-dihydrocollidine
definition: A dihydropyridine that is 2,4,6-trimethyl-1,4-dihydropyridine substituted by ethoxycarbonyl groups at positions 3 and 5.

name: fenticonazole nitrate
definition: A racemate comprising equimolar amounts of (R)- and (S)-fenticonazole nitrate. Used for the treatment of vaginal candidiasis.

name: (S)-fenticonazole nitrate
definition: An organic nitrate salt obtained by reaction of equimolar amounts of (S)-fenticonazole and nitric acid.

name: (R)-fenticonazole nitrate
definition: An organic nitrate salt obtained by reaction of equimolar amounts of (R)-fenticonazole and nitric acid.

name: steatosis inducing agent
definition: Any agent capable of inducing steatosis, a pathological condition characterised by accumulation or abnormal retention of fats within a cell.

name: valifenalate
definition: A diastereoisomeric mixture of L-(R)- and L-(S)-valifenalate. An anti-peronosporic fungicide, it is used to control mildew in many crops including grapes, potatoes and tomatoes.

name: (R)-fenticonazole(1+)
definition: An organic cation obtained by protonation of the imidazole group of (R)-fenticonazole.

name: hepatic steatosis inducing agent
definition: Any  hepatotoxic agent capable of inducing liver  steatosis or fatty liver disease.

name: (S)-fenticonazole(1+)
definition: An organic cation obtained by protonation of the imidazole group of (S)-fenticonazole.

name: L-(R)-valifenalate
definition: A methyl 3-(4-chlorophenyl)-3-{[N-(isopropoxycarbonyl)valyl]amino}propanoate resulting from the formal condensation of the carboxylic acid group of N-(isopropoxycarbonyl)-L-valine with the amino group of methyl (3R)-3-amino-3-(4-chlorophenyl)propanoate.

name: L-(S)-valifenalate
definition: A methyl 3-(4-chlorophenyl)-3-{[N-(isopropoxycarbonyl)valyl]amino}propanoate resulting from the formal condensation of the carboxylic acid group of N-(isopropoxycarbonyl)-L-valine with the amino group of methyl (3S)-3-amino-3-(4-chlorophenyl)propanoate.

name: 2-(4-chlorophenyl)-N-{2-[3-methoxy-4-(prop-2-yn-1-yloxy)phenyl]ethyl}-2-(prop-2-yn-1-yloxy)acetamide
definition: A monocarboxylic acid amide resulting from the condensation of the carboxy group of p-chloromandelic acid propargyl ether with the amino group of 2-[3-methoxy-4-(prop-2-yn-1-yloxy)phenyl]ethylamine.

name: (R)-mandipropamid
definition: A 2-(4-chlorophenyl)-N-{2-[3-methoxy-4-(prop-2-yn-1-yloxy)phenyl]ethyl}-2-(prop-2-yn-1-yloxy)acetamide that has R configuration.

name: (S)-mandipropamid
definition: A 2-(4-chlorophenyl)-N-{2-[3-methoxy-4-(prop-2-yn-1-yloxy)phenyl]ethyl}-2-(prop-2-yn-1-yloxy)acetamide that has S configuration.

name: O-adenyl-L-tyrosine(1-) residue
definition: An alpha-amino-acid residue anion obtained by removal of a proton form the phosphate group of O-adenyl-L-tyrosine residue; major species at pH 7.3.

name: O-adenyl-L-tyrosine residue
definition: An alpha-amino-acid residue derived from O-adenyl-L-tyrosine.

name: tetradecanoyl-AMP(1-)
definition: A fatty acyl-AMP(1-) obtained by deprotonation of the phosphate OH group of tetradecanoyl-AMP; major species at pH 7.3.

name: hexadecanoyl-AMP(1-)
definition: A fatty acyl-AMP(1-) obtained by deprotonation of the phosphate OH group of hexadecanoyl-AMP; major species at pH 7.3.

name: N-acylammonia
definition: A carboxamide obtained by the formal condensation of the carboxy group of any carboxylic acid with ammonia.

name: tea tree oil
definition: An essential oil consisting of approximately one hundred hydrocarbon and terpenoid components obtained by steam distillation from the leaves and terminal branchlets of the tea tree, Melaleuca alternifolia; the yield of oil is typically 1-2% of wet plant material weight. The main components are 4-terpineol (40%), gamma-terpinene (23%), alpha-terpinene (10%), 1,8-cineole (5%), terpinolene (3%), and p-cymene (3%).

name: essential oil
definition: A mixture that is a concentrated hydrophobic liquid containing volatile aroma compounds obtained from plants, commonly by distillation (particularly steam distillation), but also by solvent extraction, or by crushing of seeds or fruits in a press.

name: octyl gallate
definition: A gallate ester obtained by condensation of the carboxy group of gallic acid with the hydroxy group of octanol.

name: 2-(butan-2-yl)-4,6-dinitrophenol
definition: A dinitrophenol that is 2,4-dinitrophenol substituted by a butan-2-yl group at position 2.

name: (R)-dinoseb
definition: The (R)-enantiomer of 2-(butan-2-yl)-4,6-dinitrophenol.

name: alkylguanidinium biocide
definition: Any guanidinium salt that has antimicrobial properties.

name: guanidinium salt
definition: An organic salt in which the cation has the structure (RN)2C=N(+)R2.

name: (S)-dinoseb
definition: The (S)-enantiomer of 2-(butan-2-yl)-4,6-dinitrophenol.

name: 1-[4-(4-chlorophenyl)thiazol-2-yl]-2-(pentan-3-ylidene)hydrazine
definition: A member of the class of 1,3-thiazoles that is 2-[2-(pentan-3-ylidene)hydrazino]-1,3-thiazole carrying an additional 4-chlorophenyl substituent at position 4.

name: 2-chloro-N-(2,4-dimethylthiophen-3-yl)-N-(1-methoxypropan-2-yl)acetamide
definition: An  organochlorine compound that is 2-chloroacetamide substituted by a 2,4-dimethylthiophen-3-yl and a 1-methoxypropan-2-yl group at the nitrogen atom.

name: (R)-dimethenamid
definition: A 2-chloro-N-(2,4-dimethylthiophen-3-yl)-N-[(2R)-1-methoxypropan-2-yl]acetamide that has R configuration. It is the inactive enantiomer; its (active) enantiomer is the herbicide known as dimethenamid-P; the racemate is the herbicide dimethenamid.

name: dimethenamid-P
definition: The (S)-enantiomer of 2-chloro-N-(2,4-dimethylthiophen-3-yl)-N-[(2S)-1-methoxypropan-2-yl]acetamide. It is the active enantiomer of dimethenamid, a herbicide applied to the soil to control various broad-leaved weeds and grasses.

name: juvenile hormone III bisepoxide
definition: A juvenile hormone that is methyl farnesoate in which the 6,7 and 10,11-double bonds have been epoxidised.

name: juvenile hormone III skipped bisepoxide
definition: A juvenile hormone that is methyl farnesoate in which the 2,3 and 10,11-double bonds have been epoxidised. Found in the stink bug, Plautia stali.

name: 1-[4-(4-chlorophenyl)thiazol-2-yl]-2-(propan-2-ylidene)hydrazine
definition: A member of the class of 1,3-thiazoles that is 2-[2-(propan-2-ylidene)hydrazino]-1,3-thiazole carrying an additional 4-chlorophenyl substituent at position 4.

name: 2-chloro-N-(2-ethyl-6-methylphenyl)-N-(1-methoxypropan-2-yl)acetamide
definition: An  organochlorine compound that is 2-chloroacetamide substituted by a (2-ethyl-6-methylphenyl)-N-(1-methoxypropan-2-yl) group at the nitrogen atom.

name: (R)-metolachlor
definition: The (R)-enantiomer of 2-chloro-N-(2-ethyl-6-methylphenyl)-N-(1-methoxypropan-2-yl)acetamide.

name: (S)-metolachlor
definition: The (S)-enantiomer of 2-chloro-N-(2-ethyl-6-methylphenyl)-N-(1-methoxypropan-2-yl)acetamide.

name: 1-(butan-2-ylidene)-2-[4-(4-chlorophenyl)thiazol-2-yl]hydrazine
definition: A member of the class of 1,3-thiazoles that is 2-[2-(butan-2-ylidene)hydrazino]-1,3-thiazole carrying an additional 4-chlorophenyl substituent at position 4.

name: 3,4,5-trimethoxybenzyl isothiocyanate
definition: A member of the class of isothiocyanates in which the substituent attached to nitrogen is specified as 3,4,5-trimethoxybenzyl.

name: 1-(3-O-sulfo-beta-D-galactosyl)-N-tetracosenoylsphingosine(1-)
definition: A galactosylceramide sulfate(1-) in which the ceramide N-acyl group contains 24 carbons and 1 double bond.

name: [(2-ethyl-6-methylphenyl)(1-methoxypropan-2-yl)amino](oxo)acetic acid
definition: A monocarboxylic acid that is oxoacetic acid substituted by a (2-ethyl-6-methylphenyl)(1-methoxypropan-2-yl)amino group at position 2.

name: (R)-metolachlor OXA
definition: The (R)-enantiomer of  [(2-ethyl-6-methylphenyl)(1-methoxypropan-2-yl)amino](oxo)acetic acid.

name: 1-(3-O-sulfo-beta-D-galactosyl)-N-hydroxytetracosenoylsphingosine(1-)
definition: A galactosylceramide sulfate(1-) in which the ceramide N-acyl group contains 24 carbons, 1 double bond and a hydroxyl group.

name: (S)-metolachlor OXA
definition: The (S)-enantiomer of  [(2-ethyl-6-methylphenyl)(1-methoxypropan-2-yl)amino](oxo)acetic acid.

name: luminespib
definition: A monocarboxylic acid amide obtained by formal condensation of the carboxy group of 5-(2,4-dihydroxy-5-isopropylphenyl)-4-[4-(morpholin-4-ylmethyl)phenyl]-1,2-oxazole-3-carboxylic acid with the amino group of ethylamine.

name: isotianil
definition: A monocarboxylic acid amide resulting from the formal condensation of the carboxy group of 3,4-dichloro-1,2-thiazole-5-carboxylic acid with o-cyanoaniline. It is a fungicide used for the control of rice blast.

name: 5-bromo-3-(butan-2-yl)-6-methylpyrimidine-2,4(1H,3H)-dione
definition: A pyrimidone that is pyrimidine-2,4(1H,3H)-dione substituted by a bromo group at position 5, a butan-2-yl group at position 3 and a methyl group at position 6.

name: (R)-bromacil
definition: The (R)-enantiomer of 5-bromo-3-(butan-2-yl)-6-methylpyrimidine-2,4(1H,3H)-dione.

name: (S)-bromacil
definition: The (S)-enantiomer of 5-bromo-3-(butan-2-yl)-6-methylpyrimidine-2,4(1H,3H)-dione.

name: lysidine monophosphate
definition: A pyrimidine ribonucleoside 5'-monophosphate that is CMP in which the 2-keto group on the cytosine ring is replaced by an epsilon-L-lysyl residue.

name: lysidine monophosphate(1-)
definition: An organophosphate oxoanion that is CMP(2-) in which the 2-keto group on the cytosine ring is substituted by an epsilon-L-lysyl residue. Major structure at pH 7.3 (according to Marvin v. 6.2.0).

name: pyrimorph
definition: An enamide resulting from the formal condensation of 3-(p-tert-butylphenyl)-3-(6-chloropyridin-2-yl)acrylic acid with the amino group of morpholine. A fungicide developed in China, it shows high antifungal activity against diseases caused by Phytophthora infestans, Phytophthora capsici, Rhizoctonia solani, Peronophythora litchi, and Pseudoperonospora cubensis.

name: lysine monophosphate residue
definition: A nucleotide residue derived from lysine monophosphate.

name: lysidine monophosphate zwitterion residue
definition: A zwitterionic group that is the major structure at pH 7.3 of lysidine monophosphate residue (according to Marvin v. 6.2.0).

name: (R)-isoconazole
definition: A 1-{2-[(2,6-dichlorobenzyl)oxy]-2-(2,4-dichlorophenyl)ethyl}imidazole that is the (R)-enantiomer of isoconazole.

name: 1-{2-[(2,6-dichlorobenzyl)oxy]-2-(2,4-dichlorophenyl)ethyl}imidazole
definition: A member of the class of imidazoles that carries a 2-[(2,6-dichlorobenzyl)oxy]-2-(2,4-dichlorophenyl)ethyl group at position 1.

name: (S)-isoconazole
definition: A 1-{2-[(2,6-dichlorobenzyl)oxy]-2-(2,4-dichlorophenyl)ethyl}imidazole that is the (S)-enantiomer of isoconazole.

name: (R)-isoconazole nitrate
definition: An organic nitrate salt obtained by reaction of equimolar amounts of (R)-isoconazole and nitric acid.

name: 9-PAHSA(1-)
definition: A long-chain fatty acid anion that is the conjugate base of 9-PAHSA, obtained by deprotonation of the carboxy group; major species at pH 7.3.

name: (S)-isoconazole nitrate
definition: An organic nitrate salt obtained by reaction of equimolar amounts of (S)-isoconazole and nitric acid.

name: 5-PAHSA(1-)
definition: A long-chain fatty acid anion that is the conjugate base of 5-PAHSA, obtained by deprotonation of the carboxy group; major species at pH 7.3.

name: (S)-isoconazole(1+)
definition: An organic cation obtained by protonation of the imidazole group of (S)-isoconazole.

name: (R)-isoconazole(1+)
definition: An organic cation obtained by protonation of the imidazole group of (R)-isoconazole.

name: 10-PAHSA(1-)
definition: A long-chain fatty acid anion that is the conjugate base of 10-PAHSA, obtained by deprotonation of the carboxy group; major species at pH 7.3.

name: 11-PAHSA(1-)
definition: A long-chain fatty acid anion that is the conjugate base of 11-PAHSA, obtained by deprotonation of the carboxy group; major species at pH 7.3.

name: 12-PAHSA(1-)
definition: A long-chain fatty acid anion that is the conjugate base of 12-PAHSA, obtained by deprotonation of the carboxy group; major species at pH 7.3.

name: 13-PAHSA(1-)
definition: A long-chain fatty acid anion that is the conjugate base of 13-PAHSA, obtained by deprotonation of the carboxy group; major species at pH 7.3.

name: 2-[(2-ethyl-6-methylphenyl)(1-methoxypropan-2-yl)amino]-2-oxoethanesulfonic acid
definition: An organosulfonic acid that is 2-oxoethanesulfonic acid substituted by a (2-ethyl-6-methylphenyl)(1-methoxypropan-2-yl)amino group at postion 2.

name: (R)-metolachlor ESA
definition: The (R)-enantiomer of  2-[(2-ethyl-6-methylphenyl)(1-methoxypropan-2-yl)amino]-2-oxoethanesulfonic acid.

name: (S)-metolachlor ESA
definition: The (S)-enantiomer of  2-[(2-ethyl-6-methylphenyl)(1-methoxypropan-2-yl)amino]-2-oxoethanesulfonic acid.

name: 1-{2-[(7-chloro-1-benzothiophen-3-yl)methoxy]-2-(2,4-dichlorophenyl)ethyl}imidazole
definition: A member of the class of imidazoles that carries a 2-[(7-chloro-1-benzothiophen-3-yl)methoxy]-2-(2,4-dichlorophenyl)ethyl group at position 1.

name: N-terminal N-acetyl-L-alanine residue
definition: An N-terminal alpha-amino-acid residue derived from N-terminal N-acetyl-L-alanine.

name: (S)-sertaconazole
definition: A 1-{2-[(7-chloro-1-benzothiophen-3-yl)methoxy]-2-(2,4-dichlorophenyl)ethyl}imidazole that is the (S)-enantiomer of sertaconazole.

name: arasertaconazole
definition: A 1-{2-[(7-chloro-1-benzothiophen-3-yl)methoxy]-2-(2,4-dichlorophenyl)ethyl}imidazole that is the active R-enantiomer of sertaconazole and is used (as its nitrate salt) for treatment of vulvovaginal candidiasis. The racemate itself is also used as a broad-spectrum antifungal drug.

name: (2-chlorophenyl)(4-chlorophenyl)pyrimidin-5-ylmethanol
definition: A member of the class of pyrimidines that is pyrimidin-5-ylmethanol in which one of the hydrogens attached to the carbon bearing the hydroxy group is replaced by a 2-chlorophenyl group while the other is replaced by a 4-chlorophenyl group.

name: sertaconazole nitrate
definition: A racemate comprising equimolar amounts of (R)- and (S)-sertaconazole nitrate. A broad spectrum antifungal with added antipruritic and anti-inflammatory activity used for treatment of various skin infections.

name: (R)-fenarimol
definition: A (2-chlorophenyl)(4-chlorophenyl)pyrimidin-5-ylmethanol that has R configuration.

name: (S)-fenarimol
definition: A (2-chlorophenyl)(4-chlorophenyl)pyrimidin-5-ylmethanol that has S configuration.

name: N-terminal N-acetyl-L-serine residue
definition: An N-terminal alpha-amino-acid residue derived from N-terminal N-acetyl-L-serine.

name: (S)-sertaconazole nitrate
definition: An organic nitrate salt obtained by reaction of equimolar amounts of (S)-sertaconazole and nitric acid.

name: arasertaconazole nitrate
definition: An organic nitrate salt obtained by reaction of equimolar amounts of arasertaconazole and nitric acid. The active R-enantiomer of sertaconazole nitrate that is used for treatment of vulvovaginal candidiasis. The racemate itself is also used as a broad-spectrum antifungal drug.

name: (R)-nuarimol
definition: A (2-chlorophenyl)(4-fluorophenyl)pyrimidin-5-ylmethanol that has R configuration.

name: (S)-nuarimol
definition: A (2-chlorophenyl)(4-fluorophenyl)pyrimidin-5-ylmethanol that has S configuration.

name: CIGB-300
definition: A synthetic 25-membered heterodetic cyclic peptide consisting of a 14-membered linear component attached to an 11-membered cyclic portion. A CK2 inhibitor with potential antineoplastic activity.

name: N(5)-alkyl-L-glutamine residue
definition: An alpha-amino-acid residue derived from any N(5)-alkyl-L-glutamine.

name: (S)-sertaconazole(1+)
definition: An organic cation obtained by protonation of the imidazole group of (S)-sertaconazole

name: 7-PAHSA(1-)
definition: A long-chain fatty acid anion that is the conjugate base of 7-PAHSA, obtained by deprotonation of the carboxy group; major species at pH 7.3.

name: 8-PAHSA(1-)
definition: A long-chain fatty acid anion that is the conjugate base of 8-PAHSA, obtained by deprotonation of the carboxy group; major species at pH 7.3.

name: monothioglycerolipid
definition: Any member of the group of lipids containing a common monothioglycerol backbone to which at least one fatty acyl group is esterified.

name: 1-O-[alpha-D-galactosyl-(1->2)-alpha-D-galactosyl]-N-hexacosanoylphytosphingosine
definition: A glycophytoceramide having an alpha-D-Gal-(1->2)alpha-DGal glycosyl group at the O-1 position and a hexacosanoyl group attached to the nitrogen.

name: tetradecasphingosine
definition: A sphingoid that is the C14-analogue of sphingosine.

name: 1-(2-fluorophenyl)-1-(4-fluorophenyl)-2-(1H-1,2,4-triazol-1-yl)ethanol
definition: A tertiary alcohol that is ethanol in which one of the hydrogens at position 1 is replaced by an p-fluorophenyl group, the other hydrogen at position 1 is replaced by a p-fluorophenyl group, and one of the hydrogens at position 2 is replaced by a 1H-1,2,4-triazol-1-yl group.

name: (R)-flutriafol
definition: A 1-(2-fluorophenyl)-1-(4-fluorophenyl)-2-(1H-1,2,4-triazol-1-yl)ethanol that has R configuration.

name: (S)-flutriafol
definition: A 1-(2-fluorophenyl)-1-(4-fluorophenyl)-2-(1H-1,2,4-triazol-1-yl)ethanol that has R configuration.

name: tetradecaphytosphingosine
definition: A sphingoid that is the C14-analogue of phytosphingosine.

name: 2-(2,4-dichlorophenyl)-1-(1H-1,2,4-triazol-1-yl)hexan-2-ol
definition: A member of the class of triazoles that is 1-hexyl-1H-1,2,4-triazole in which the hydrogens at position 2 of the hexyl chain are replaced by hydroxy and 2,4-dichlorophenyl groups.

name: (R)-hexaconazole
definition: A 2-(2,4-dichlorophenyl)-1-(1H-1,2,4-triazol-1-yl)hexan-2-ol that has R configuration.

name: (S)-hexaconazole
definition: A 2-(2,4-dichlorophenyl)-1-(1H-1,2,4-triazol-1-yl)hexan-2-ol that has S configuration.

name: 1,2,2'-trilinoleoyl-1'-monolysocardiolipin(2-)
definition: A 1-monolysocardiolipin(2-) obtained by deprotonation of the phosphate OH groups of 1,2,2'-trilinoleoyl-1'-monolysocardiolipin; major species at pH 7.3.

name: 1,1'-dilinoleoyl-2-oleoyl monolysocardiolipin(2-)
definition: A 2-monolysocardiolipin(2-) obtained by deprotonation of the phosphate OH groups of 1,1'-dilinoleoyl-2-oleoyl monolysocardiolipin; major species at pH 7.3.

name: 2-aminophenylglyoxylic acid
definition: A 2-oxo monocarboxylic acid that is glyoxylic acid in which the aldehydic hydrogen is replaced by a 2-aminophenyl group.

name: 1,2-dipalmitoleoyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphocholine
definition: A phosphatidylcholine 32:2 in which both phosphatidyl acyl groups are specified as palmitoleoyl.

name: 1,2-distearoyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphocholine
definition: A phosphatidylcholine 36:0 in which both phosphatidyl acyl groups are specified as stearoyl (octadecanoyl).

name: 1-(4-chlorophenoxy)-1-(1H-imidazol-1-yl)-3,3-dimethylbutan-2-one
definition: A ketone that is butan-2-one substituted by a 4-chlorophenoxy and a 1H-imidazol-1-yl group at position 1 and 2 methyl groups at position 3.

name: (R)-climbazole
definition: The (R)-enantiomer of 1-(4-chlorophenoxy)-1-(1H-imidazol-1-yl)-3,3-dimethylbutan-2-one.

name: long-chain 3-substituted propanoyl-CoA(4-)
definition: A  3-substituted propionyl-CoA(4-) obtained by deprotonation of the phosphate and diphosphate OH groups of any long-chain 3-substituted propionyl-CoA; major species at pH 7.3.

name: (S)-climbazole
definition: The (S)-enantiomer of 1-(4-chlorophenoxy)-1-(1H-imidazol-1-yl)-3,3-dimethylbutan-2-one.

name: medium-chain 3-substituted propanoyl-CoA(4-)
definition: A 3-substituted propionyl-CoA(4-) obtained by deprotonation of the phosphate and diphosphate OH groups of any medium-chain 3-substituted propionyl-CoA; major species at pH 7.3.

name: very long-chain 3-substituted propanoyl-CoA(4-)
definition: A 3-substituted propionyl-CoA(4-) obtained by deprotonation of the phosphate and diphosphate OH groups of any very long-chain 3-substituted propionyl-CoA; major species at pH 7.3.

name: primary alkymercury(1+)
definition: Any alkylmercury compound in which a primary alkyl group is attached to a positively charged mercury atom.

name: medium-chain 2,3-trans-enoyl CoA(4-)
definition: A 2,3-trans-enoyl CoA(4-) obtained by deprotonation of the phosphate and diphosphate OH groups of any medium-chain 2,3-trans-enoyl CoA (medium-chain = chain length between C6 and C12); major species at pH 7.3.

name: long-chain 2,3-trans-enoyl CoA(4-)
definition: A 2,3-trans-enoyl CoA(4-) obtained by deprotonation of the phosphate and diphosphate OH groups of any long-chain 2,3-trans-enoyl CoA (long-chain = chain length between C13 and C22); major species at pH 7.3.

name: very long-chain 2,3-trans-enoyl CoA(4-)
definition: A 2,3-trans-enoyl CoA(4-) obtained by deprotonation of the phosphate and diphosphate OH groups of any very long-chain 2,3-trans-enoyl CoA (very long-chain = chain length greater than C22); major species at pH 7.3.

name: 2-(4-chlorophenyl)-2-(1H-1,2,4-triazol-1-ylmethyl)hexanenitrile
definition: A nitrile that is hexanenitrile substituted at the 2-position by p-chlorophenyl and (1,2,4-triazol-1-yl)methyl groups.

name: (R)-myclobutanil
definition: A 2-(4-chlorophenyl)-2-(1H-1,2,4-triazol-1-ylmethyl)hexanenitrile that has R configuration.

name: (S)-myclobutanil
definition: A 2-(4-chlorophenyl)-2-(1H-1,2,4-triazol-1-ylmethyl)hexanenitrile that has S configuration.

name: 3-(3,5-dichlorophenyl)-5-ethenyl-5-methyl-2,4-oxazolidinedione
definition: A member of the class of oxazolidinones that is 5-ethenyl-5-methyl-2,4-oxazolidinedione in which the imide hydrogen is replaced by a 3,5-dichlorophenyl group.

name: (R)-vinclozolin
definition: A 3-(3,5-dichlorophenyl)-5-ethenyl-5-methyl-2,4-oxazolidinedione that is the (R)-enantiomer of vinclozolin.

name: sterol demethylation inhibitor
definition: A sterol biosynthesis inhibitor that acts by inhibiting the C14 demethylation step within fungal steroid biosynthesis.

name: (S)-vinclozolin
definition: A 3-(3,5-dichlorophenyl)-5-ethenyl-5-methyl-2,4-oxazolidinedione that is the (S)-enantiomer of vinclozolin.

name: 3-[(3aS,4S,5R,7aS)-5-hydroxy-7a-methyl-1,5-dioxo-octahydroinden-4-yl]propanoate
definition: An oxo monocarboxylic acid anion that is the conjugate base of 5-hydroxy-3-[(3aS,4S,5R,7aS)-7a-methyl-1,5-dioxo-octahydro-1H-inden-4-yl]propanoate, obtained by deprotonation of the carboxy group; major species at pH 7.3.

name: beta-D-GlcpNAc-(1->2)-alpha-D-Manp-(1->3)-[alpha-L-Fucp-(1->4)-[beta-D-Galp-(1->3)]-beta-D-GlcpNAc-(1->2)-alpha-D-Manp-(1->6)]-[beta-D-Xylp-(1->2)]-beta-D-Manp-(1->4)-beta-D-GlcpNAc-(1->4)-[alpha-L-Fucp-(1->3)]-D-GlcpNAc
definition: A highly branched amino oligosaccharide consisting of a D-GlcNAc residue at the reducing end with a beta-D-GlcNAc-(1->2)-alpha-D-Man-(1->3)-[alpha-L-Fuc-(1->4)-[beta-D-Gal-(1->3)]-beta-D-NAc-(1->2)-alpha-D-Man-(1->6)]-[beta-D-Xyl-(1->2)]-beta-D-Man-(1->4)-beta-D-GlcNAc nonasaccharide moiety attached via a beta-(1->4)-linkage and an L-Fuc residue attached via an alpha-(1->3)-linkage.

name: 3-[(3aS,4S,5R,7aS)-5-hydroxy-7a-methyl-1-oxo-octahydroinden-4-yl]propanoyl-CoA(4-)
definition: An acyl-CoA oxoanion resulting from the removal of all four protons from the phosphate groups of 3-[(3aS,4S,5R,7aS)-5-hydroxy-7a-methyl-1-oxo-octahydroinden-4-yl]propanoyl-CoA; major species at pH 7.3.

name: ferroheme c di-L-cysteine(2-) residue
definition: An organic anionic group that is ferroheme c(2-)  bound to cytochrome c by two L-cysteine residues; major species at pH 7.3.

name: alpha-L-Fucp-(1->3)-[alpha-L-Fucp-(1->4)-[beta-D-Galp-(1->3)]-beta-D-GlcpNAc-(1->2)-alpha-D-Manp-(1->3)-[alpha-L-Fucp-(1->4)-[beta-D-Galp-(1->3)]-beta-D-GlcpNAc-(1->2)-alpha-D-Manp-(1->6)]-[beta-D-Xylp-(1->2)]-beta-D-Manp-(1->4)-beta-D-GlcpNAc-(1->4)]-D-GlcpNAc
definition: A highly branched amino oligosaccharide consisting of a D-GlcNAc residue at the reducing end with a alpha-L-Fuc-(1->4)-[beta-D-Gal-(1->3)]-beta-D-GlcNAc-(1->2)-alpha-D-Man-(1->3)-[alpha-L-Fuc-(1->4)-[beta-D-Gal-(1->3)]-beta-D-GlcNAc-(1->2)-alpha-D-Man-(1->6)]-[beta-D-Xyl-(1->2)]-beta-D-Man-(1->4)-beta-D-GlcNAc undecasaccharide moiety attached via a beta-(1->4)-linkage and an L-Fuc residue attached via an alpha-(1->3)-linkage.

name: phospholipid biosynthesis inhibitor
definition: Any compound that inhibits the biosynthesis of any phospholipid.

name: 2-(4-isopropyl-4-methyl-5-oxo-4,5-dihydro-1H-imidazol-2-yl)-5-(methoxymethyl)nicotinic acid
definition: A pyridinemonocarboxylic acid that is nicotinic acid which is substituted substituted at position 5 by a methoxymethyl group and at position 2 by a 4,5-dihydro-1H-imidazol-2-yl group, that in turn is substituted by isopropyl, methyl, and oxo groups at positions 4, 4, and 5, respectively.

name: (S)-imazamox
definition: The (S)-enantiomer of 2-(4-isopropyl-4-methyl-5-oxo-4,5-dihydro-1H-imidazol-2-yl)-5-(methoxymethyl)nicotinic acid.

name: (R)-imazamox
definition: The (R)-enantiomer of 5-(methoxymethyl)-2-[4-methyl-5-oxo-4-(propan-2-yl)-4,5-dihydro-1H-imidazol-2-yl]pyridine-3-carboxylic acid.

name: validamycins
definition: Any of the inositol-derived beta-D-glucoside antibiotics produced by Streptomyces hygroscopicus.

name: 3-ketocholest-4-en-26-al
definition: A 26-oxo steroid resulting from the oxidation of 3-oxocholest-4-en-26-ol to the corresponding aldehyde.

name: (10Z,13Z,16Z)-docosatrienoic acid
definition: A long-chain omega-6 fatty acid that is docosanoic acid having three double bonds located at positions 10, 13 and 16 (the (10Z,13Z,16Z-geoisomer).

name: 2-(4-chlorophenyl)-3-cyclopropyl-1-(1H-1,2,4-triazol-1-yl)butan-2-ol
definition: A tertiary alcohol that is butan-2-ol substituted by a 4-chlorophenyl group at position 2, a cyclopropyl group at position 3 and a 1H-1,2,4-triazol-1-yl group at position 1.

name: (2S,3S)-cyproconazole
definition: The (2S,3S)-stereoisomer of 2-(4-chlorophenyl)-3-cyclopropyl-1-(1H-1,2,4-triazol-1-yl)butan-2-ol.

name: N-acylhexadecasphinganine-1-phosphoethanolamine
definition: A ceramide phosphoethanolamine in which the sphingoid component is specified as hexadecasphinganine.

name: (2S,3R)-cyproconazole
definition: The (2S,3R)-stereoisomer of 2-(4-chlorophenyl)-3-cyclopropyl-1-(1H-1,2,4-triazol-1-yl)butan-2-ol.

name: (2R,3R)-cyproconazole
definition: The (2R,3R)-stereoisomer of 2-(4-chlorophenyl)-3-cyclopropyl-1-(1H-1,2,4-triazol-1-yl)butan-2-ol.

name: N-acylicosasphinganine-1-phosphoethanolamine
definition: A ceramide phosphoethanolamine in which the sphingoid component is specified as icosasphinganine.

name: N-acylicosaphytosphingosine-1-phosphoethanolamine
definition: A ceramide phosphoethanolamine in which the sphingoid component is specified as icosaphytosphingosine.

name: EC 2.4.1.231 [alpha,alpha-trehalose phosphorylase (configuration-retaining)] inhibitor
definition: An EC 2.4.1.* (hexosyltransferase) inhibitor that interferes with the action of alpha,alpha-trehalose phosphorylase (configuration-retaining) (EC 2.4.1.231).

name: 1-{[3-(2-chlorophenyl)-2-(4-fluorophenyl)oxiran-2-yl]methyl}-1H-1,2,4-triazole
definition: An  epoxide that is oxirane substituted by a 2-chlorophenyl, 4-fluorophenyl and a 1H-1,2,4-triazol-1-ylmethyl groups.

name: (2S,3R)-epoxiconazole
definition: The (2S,3R)-stereoisomer of 1-{[3-(2-chlorophenyl)-2-(4-fluorophenyl)oxiran-2-yl]methyl}-1H-1,2,4-triazole.

name: EC 2.4.1.64 (alpha,alpha-trehalose phosphorylase) inhibitor
definition: An EC 2.4.1.* (hexosyltransferase) inhibitor that interferes with the action of alpha,alpha-trehalose phosphorylase (EC 2.4.1.64).

name: (2R,3S)-epoxiconazole
definition: The (2R,3S)-stereoisomer of 1-{[3-(2-chlorophenyl)-2-(4-fluorophenyl)oxiran-2-yl]methyl}-1H-1,2,4-triazole.

name: EC 3.2.1.28 (alpha,alpha-trehalase) inhibitor
definition: An EC 2.4.1.* (hexosyltransferase) inhibitor that interferes with the action of alpha,alpha-trehalase (EC 2.4.1.28).

name: N-acyltetradecasphinganine-1-phosphoethanolamine
definition: A ceramide phosphoethanolamine in which the sphingoid component is specified as tetradecasphinganine.

name: N-acyltetradecasphingosine-1-phosphoethanolamine
definition: A ceramide phosphoethanolamine in which the sphingoid component is specified as tetradecasphingosine.

name: N-acyl-15-methylhexadecasphinganine-1-phosphoethanolamine
definition: A ceramide phosphoethanolamine in which the sphingoid component is specified as 15-methylhexadecasphinganine.

name: olaparib
definition: A member of the class of N-acylpiperazines obtained by formal condensation of the carboxy group of 2-fluoro-5-[(4-oxo-3,4-dihydrophthalazin-1-yl)methyl]benzoic acid with the free amino group of N-(cyclpropylcarbonyl)piperazine; used to treat advanced ovarian cancer.

name: 2''-O-acetyl-ADP-D-ribose(2-)
definition: A nucleotide-sugar oxoanion arising from deprotonation of the diphosphate OH groups of 2''-O-acetyl-ADP-D-ribose; major species at pH 7.3.

name: 2-ethoxy-3,3-dimethyl-2,3-dihydro-1-benzofuran-5-yl methanesulfonate
definition: A methanesulfonate ester that is methanesulfonic acid in which the hydrogen of the hydroxy group has been replaced by a 2-ethoxy-3,3-dimethyl-2,3-dihydro-1-benzofuran-5-yl group.

name: (S)-ethofumesate
definition: The (S)-enantiomer of  2-ethoxy-3,3-dimethyl-2,3-dihydro-1-benzofuran-5-yl methanesulfonate.

name: (R)-ethofumesate
definition: The (R)-enantiomer of  2-ethoxy-3,3-dimethyl-2,3-dihydro-1-benzofuran-5-yl methanesulfonate.

name: N,N-diethyl-2-(naphthalen-1-yloxy)propanamide
definition: A monocarboxylic acid amide that is propanamide substituted by two ethyl groups at the nitrogen atom and a naphthalen-1-yloxy group at position 2.

name: (R)-napropamide
definition: The (R)-enantiomer of N,N-diethyl-2-(naphthalen-1-yloxy)propanamide.

name: (S)-napropamide
definition: The (S)-enantiomer of N,N-diethyl-2-(naphthalen-1-yloxy)propanamide.

name: 1,2-dioctadecanoyl-sn-glycerol-3-phosphate
definition: A 1-acyl-2-octadecanoyl-sn-glycerol-3-phosphate in which the 1-acyl group is also octadecanoyl.

name: 1,2-dioleoyl-sn-glycerol-3-phosphate
definition: A 1-acyl-2-oleoyl-sn-glycerol-3-phosphate(2-) in which the 1-acyl group is also oleoyl.

name: 3-oxo-23,24-bisnorchol-4-en-22-oic acid
definition: A steroid acid that is 23,24-bisnor-chol-4-en-22-oic acid bearing an additional oxo substituent at position 3.

name: 3-oxo-23,24-bisnorchol-4-en-22-oate
definition: A steroid acid anion that is the conjugate base of 3-oxo-23,24-bisnor-chol-4-en-22-oic acid, obtained by deprotonation of the carboxy group; major species at pH 7.3.

name: 1,2-di[(4Z,7Z,10Z,13Z,16Z,19Z)-docosahexaenoyl]-sn-glycero-3-phosphate
definition: A 1,2-diacyl-sn-glycerol 3-phosphate in which both phosphatidyl acyl groups are specified as (4Z,7Z,10Z,13Z,16Z,19Z)-docosahexaenoyl.

name: 1-(4-chlorophenyl)-4,4-dimethyl-3-(1H-1,2,4-triazol-1-ylmethyl)pentan-3-ol
definition: A tertiary alcohol that is pentan-3-ol substituted by a 4-chlorophenyl, methyl, methyl, and a 1H-1,2,4-triazol-1-ylmethyl at positions 1, 4, 4 and 3 respectively.

name: (S)-tebuconazole
definition: The (S)-enantiomer of 1-(4-chlorophenyl)-4,4-dimethyl-3-(1H-1,2,4-triazol-1-ylmethyl)pentan-3-ol.

name: (R)-tebuconazole
definition: The (R)-enantiomer of 1-(4-chlorophenyl)-4,4-dimethyl-3-(1H-1,2,4-triazol-1-ylmethyl)pentan-3-ol.

name: (5Z,9E,12S,14Z)-8,11,12,20-tetrahydroxyicosa-5,9,14-trienoic acid
definition: An icosanoid that is (5Z,9E,14Z)-icosa-5,9,14-trienoic acid carrying four hydroxy substituents at positions 8, 11, 12 and 20. An intermediary metabolite from the 12(R)-lipoxygenase pathway.

name: (25S)-3beta-hydroxy-5-cholesten-26-oyl-CoA(4-)
definition: An acyl-CoA oxoanion resulting from the removal of all four protons from the phosphate groups of (25S)-3beta-hydroxy-5-cholesten-26-oyl-CoA; major species at pH 7.3.

name: galaxolide
definition: An organic heterotricyclic compound that is 1,3,4,6,7,8-hexahydrocyclopenta[g]isochromene substituted by methyl groups at positions 4, 6, 6, 7, 8 and 8 respectively. It is a synthetic musk used as a fragrance in cosmetics.

name: 1-palmitoyl-2-[(4Z,7Z,10Z,13Z,16Z,19Z)-docosahexaenoyl]-sn-glycero-3-phosphate
definition: A 1,2-diacyl-sn-glycerol 3-phosphate in which the 1- and 2-acyl substituent are specified as palmitoyl and (4Z,7Z,10Z,13Z,16Z,19Z)-docosahexaenoyl respectively.

name: N-(butan-2-yl)-N'-ethyl-6-methoxy-1,3,5-triazine-2,4-diamine
definition: A diamino-1,3,5-triazine that is N-(butan-2-yl)-N'-ethyl-1,3,5-triazine-2,4-diamine substituted by a methoxy group at position 6.

name: (R)-secbumeton
definition: The (R)-enantiomer of N-(butan-2-yl)-N'-ethyl-6-methoxy-1,3,5-triazine-2,4-diamine.

name: (S)-secbumeton
definition: The (S)-enantiomer of N-(butan-2-yl)-N'-ethyl-6-methoxy-1,3,5-triazine-2,4-diamine.

name: N-(butan-2-yl)-6-chloro-N'-ethyl-1,3,5-triazine-2,4-diamine
definition: A diamino-1,3,5-triazine that is N-(butan-2-yl)-N'-ethyl-1,3,5-triazine-2,4-diamine substituted by a chloro group at position 6.

name: (R)-sebuthylazine
definition: The (R)-enantiomer of N-(butan-2-yl)-6-chloro-N'-ethyl-1,3,5-triazine-2,4-diamine.

name: (S)-sebuthylazine
definition: The (S)-enantiomer of N-(butan-2-yl)-6-chloro-N'-ethyl-1,3,5-triazine-2,4-diamine.

name: 3-oxo-23,24-bisnorchola-1,4-dien-22-oyl-CoA(4-)
definition: An acyl-CoA oxoanion resulting from the removal of all four protons from the phosphate and diphosphate groups of 3-oxo-23,24-bisnorchola-1,4-dien-22-oyl-CoA; major species at pH 7.3.

name: 3-hydroxy-9-oxo-9,10-seco-23,24-bisnorchola-1,3,5(10)-trien-22-oyl-CoA(4-)
definition: An acyl-CoA(4-) resulting from the removal of all four protons from the phosphate and diphosphate groups of 3-hydroxy-9-oxo-9,10-seco-23,24-bisnorchola-1,3,5(10)-trien-22-oyl-CoA; major species at pH 7.3.

name: 3-oxodotriacontanoyl-CoA(4-)
definition: A 3-oxo-fatty acyl-CoA(4-) arising from deprotonation of the phosphate and diphosphate OH groups of 3-oxodotriacontanoyl-CoA (3-oxolacceroyl-CoA); major species at pH 7.3.

name: 3-hydroxy-9-oxo-9,10-seco-23,24-bisnorchola-1,3,5(10)-trien-22-oic acid
definition: An oxo seco-steroid that is 9-oxo-9,10-seco-23,24-bisnorchola-1,3,5(10)-trien-22-oic acid bearing an additional phenolic hydroxy substituent at position 3.

name: 3-hydroxy-9-oxo-9,10-seco-23,24-bisnorchola-1,3,5(10)-trien-22-oate
definition: A steroid acid anion that is the conjugate base of 3-hydroxy-9-oxo-9,10-seco-23,24-bisnorchola-1,3,5(10)-trien-22-oic acid, obtained by deprotonation of the carboxy group; major species at pH 7.3.

name: N-hexanoylsphingosine 1-phosphate
definition: A ceramide 1-phosphate in which the ceramide N-acyl group is specified as hexanoyl.

name: nonstructural protein 5A inhibitor
definition: Any inhibitor of nonstructural protein 5A.

name: daclatasvir hydrochloride
definition: A hydrochloride obtained by combining daclatasvir with two molar equivalents of hydrochloric acid. It is a potent inhibitor of nonstructural protein 5A and is used for treatment of hepatitis C.

name: daclatasvir(2+)
definition: An organic cation obtained by protonation of the imidazole groups of daclatasvir.

name: methoxysuccinyl-Ala-Ala-Pro-Ala chloromethyl ketone
definition: A tripeptide derived from methoxysuccinyl-Ala-Ala-Pro-Ala by conversion of the terminal carboxy group to the corresponding chloromethyl ketone.

name: methoxysuccinyl-Ala-Ala-Pro-Val chloromethyl ketone
definition: A tripeptide derived from methoxysuccinyl-Ala-Ala-Pro-Val by conversion of the terminal carboxy group to the corresponding chloromethyl ketone.

name: 3-{2-[4-(6-fluoro-1,2-benzoxazol-3-yl)piperidin-1-yl]ethyl}-9-hydroxy-2-methyl-6,7,8,9-tetrahydropyrido[1,2-a]pyrimidin-4-one
definition: A member of the class of pyridopyrimidines that is 9-hydroxy-2-methyl-6,7,8,9-tetrahydropyrido[1,2-a]pyrimidin-4-one carrying an additional 2-[4-(6-fluoro-1,2-benzoxazol-3-yl)piperidin-1-yl]ethyl group at position 2.

name: (S)-paliperidone
definition: A 3-{2-[4-(6-fluoro-1,2-benzoxazol-3-yl)piperidin-1-yl]ethyl}-9-hydroxy-2-methyl-6,7,8,9-tetrahydropyrido[1,2-a]pyrimidin-4-one that is the (S)-enantiomer of paliperidone.

name: (R)-paliperidone
definition: A 3-{2-[4-(6-fluoro-1,2-benzoxazol-3-yl)piperidin-1-yl]ethyl}-9-hydroxy-2-methyl-6,7,8,9-tetrahydropyrido[1,2-a]pyrimidin-4-one that is the (R)-enantiomer of paliperidone.

name: paliperidone palmitate
definition: A racemate comprising equimolar amounts of (R)- and (S)-paliperidone palmitate. A long-acting injectable formulation of paliperidone (the major active metabolite of risperidone) that is used for treatment of schizophrenia.

name: 3-{2-[4-(6-fluoro-1,2-benzoxazol-3-yl)piperidin-1-yl]ethyl}-2-methyl-4-oxo-6,7,8,9-tetrahydropyrido[1,2-a]pyrimidin-9-yl hexadecanoate
definition: A fatty acid ester obtained by the formal condensation of the carboxy group of hexadecanoic acid with the hydroxy group of 3-{2-[4-(6-fluoro-1,2-benzoxazol-3-yl)piperidin-1-yl]ethyl}-9-hydroxy-2-methyl-6,7,8,9-tetrahydropyrido[1,2-a]pyrimidin-4-one.

name: (S)-paliperidone palmitate
definition: A 3-{2-[4-(6-fluoro-1,2-benzoxazol-3-yl)piperidin-1-yl]ethyl}-2-methyl-4-oxo-6,7,8,9-tetrahydropyrido[1,2-a]pyrimidin-9-yl hexadecanoate that is the (S)-enantiomer of paliperidone palmitate.

name: (R)-paliperidone palmitate
definition: A 3-{2-[4-(6-fluoro-1,2-benzoxazol-3-yl)piperidin-1-yl]ethyl}-2-methyl-4-oxo-6,7,8,9-tetrahydropyrido[1,2-a]pyrimidin-9-yl hexadecanoate that is the (R)-enantiomer of paliperidone palmitate.

name: proteinogenic amino acid derivative
definition: Any derivative of a proteinogenic amino acid resulting from reaction at an amino group, carboxy group, or a side-chain functional group, or from the replacement of any hydrogen by a heteroatom.

name: non-proteinogenic amino acid derivative
definition: Any derivative of a non-proteinogenic amino acid resulting from reaction at an amino group or carboxy group, or from the replacement of any hydrogen by a heteroatom.

name: proteinogenic amino acid
definition: Any of the 23 alpha-amino acids that are precursors to proteins, and are incorporated into proteins during translation. The group includes the 20 amino acids encoded by the nuclear genes of eukaryotes together with selenocysteine, pyrrolysine, and N-formylmethionine. Apart from glycine, which is non-chiral, all have L configuration.

name: fluorotelomer
definition: Any organofluorine compound that is a oligomer or telomer synthesised by telomerization (a chain transfer reaction to produce an oligomer of a limited size). They are generally used in fire-fighting foams, leather protectants, food packaging and stain resistants.

name: (10S,11S)-dihydroxy-10,11-dihydrocarbamazepine
definition: The (10S,11S)-enantiomer of 10,11-trans-dihydroxy-10,11-dihydrocarbamazepine.

name: (10R,11R)-dihydroxy-10,11-dihydrocarbamazepine
definition: The (10R,11R)-enantiomer of 10,11-trans-dihydroxy-10,11-dihydrocarbamazepine.

name: rac-10,11-trans-dihydroxy-10,11-dihydrocarbamazepine
definition: A  racemate composed of equimolar amounts of (10S,11S)- and (10R,11R)-dihydroxy-10,11-dihydrocarbamazepine.

name: morphinane-like compound
definition: Any organonitrogen heterocyclic compound based on a morphinan skeleton. These are synthetic or semi-synthetic compounds that resemble the  morphinane (opioid) alkaloids in their pharmacological effects.

name: (25S)-3-oxocholest-4-en-26-oyl-CoA(4-)
definition: An acyl-CoA(4-) resulting from the removal of all four protons from the phosphate and diphosphate groups of (25S)-3-oxocholest-4-en-26-oyl-CoA; major species at pH 7.3.

name: non-proteinogenic amino acid
definition: Any amino-acid that is not naturally encoded in the genetic code of any organism.

name: pyrisoxazole
definition: A diastereoisomeric mixture of (3R,5S)- and (3R,5R)-pyrisoxazole. A novel isomeric fungicide primarily used for control of control tomato botrytis and also for fungal diseases of wheat and other crops.

name: L-cysteine derivative
definition: A proteinogenic amino acid derivative resulting from the formal reaction of L-cysteine at the amino group, carboxy group, or thiol group, or from the replacement of any hydrogen of L-cysteine by a heteroatom.

name: 3-[5-(4-chlorophenyl)-2,3-dimethyl-1,2-oxazolidin-3-yl]pyridine
definition: A member of the class of oxazolidines that is 2,3-dimethyl-1,2-oxazolidine carrying additional 3-pyridyl and  4-chlorophenyl substituents at positions 3 and 5 respectively.

name: (3R,5R)-pyrisoxazole
definition: A 3-[5-(4-chlorophenyl)-2,3-dimethyl-1,2-oxazolidin-3-yl]pyridine that is the (3R,5R)-diastereomer of pyrisoxazole

name: (3R,5S)-pyrisoxazole
definition: A 3-[5-(4-chlorophenyl)-2,3-dimethyl-1,2-oxazolidin-3-yl]pyridine that is the (3R,5S)-diastereomer of pyrisoxazole.

name: DNA polyanion
definition: An ionic polymer obtained by global deprotonation of the phosphate OH groups of any DNA. Major structure at pH 7.3

name: 1-[2-(allyloxy)-2-(2,4-dichlorophenyl)ethyl]imidazole
definition: A member of the class of imidazoles in which the hydrogen at position 1 is replaced by a 2-(allyloxy)-2-(2,4-dichlorophenyl)ethyl group.

name: (S)-enilconazole
definition: A 1-[2-(allyloxy)-2-(2,4-dichlorophenyl)ethyl]imidazole that is the (S)-enantiomer of enilconazole

name: (R)-enilconazole
definition: A 1-[2-(allyloxy)-2-(2,4-dichlorophenyl)ethyl]imidazole that is the (R)-enantiomer of enilconazole.

name: oxpoconazole
definition: A racemate comprising equimolar amounts of (R)- and (S)-oxpoconazole. Used (as its fumarate salt) to control a variety of fungal diseases including Botrytis, Sclerotinia and Monilinia spp.

name: peptidylproline (omega=0) residue
definition: The organodiyl group derived from peptidylproline (omega=0).

name: peptidylproline (omega=180) residue
definition: The organodiyl group derived from peptidylproline (omega=180)

name: D-cysteine derivative
definition: A non-proteinogenic amino acid derivative resulting from the formal reaction of D-cysteine at the amino group, carboxy group, or thiol group, or from the replacement of any hydrogen of D-cysteine by a heteroatom.

name: UDP-beta-L-rhamnose(2-)
definition: A UDP-L-rhamnose(2-) in which the rhamnose portion has beta-configuration at its anomeric centre; the major form of UDP-beta-L-rhamnose at pH 7.3.

name: {2-[3-(4-chlorophenyl)propyl]-2,4,4-trimethyl-1,3-oxazolidin-3-yl}(imidazol-1-yl)methanone
definition: A member of the class of oxazolidines that is 2-[3-(4-chlorophenyl)propyl]-2,4,4-trimethyl-1,3-oxazolidine in which the amino hydrogen is replaced by an (imidazol-1-yl)carbonyl group.

name: (S)-oxpoconazole
definition: A {2-[3-(4-chlorophenyl)propyl]-2,4,4-trimethyl-1,3-oxazolidin-3-yl}(imidazol-1-yl)methanone that is the (S)-enantiomer of oxpoconazole.

name: (S)-oxpoconazole fumarate
definition: A fumarate salt prepared from (S)-oxpoconazole by reaction of one molecule of fumaric acid for every two molecules of (S)-oxpoconazole.

name: (S)-oxpoconazole(1+)
definition: An organic cation obtained by protonation of the imidazole group of (S)-oxpoconazole.

name: pent-4-en-1-yl 2-[(2-furylmethyl)(imidazol-1-ylcarbonyl)amino]butanoate
definition: A carboxylic ester obtained by formal condensation of the carboxy group of 2-[(2-furylmethyl)(imidazol-1-ylcarbonyl)amino]butanoic acid with the hydroxy group of pent-4-en-1-ol.

name: N-tetracosadienoylsphingosine
definition: An acylsphingosine in which the acyl moiety contains 24 carbons and 2 double bonds.

name: dalcochinin-8'-O-beta-D-glucoside
definition: An organic heteropentacyclic compound that is the 8'-O-beta-D-glucoside of dalcochinin.

name: N-docosenoylsphingosine-1-phosphocholine
definition: A sphingomyelin in which the total number of carbons in the fatty acyl group is 22 with 1 double bond.

name: 1-(biphenyl-4-yloxy)-3,3-dimethyl-1-(1,2,4-triazol-1-yl)butan-2-ol
definition: A member of the class of triazoles that is 3,3-dimethyl-1-(1,2,4-triazol-1-yl)butane-1,2-diol substituted at position O-1 by a biphenyl-4-yl group.

name: N-tetracosadienoylsphingosine-1-phosphocholine
definition: A sphingomyelin in which the total number of carbons in the fatty acyl group is 24 with 2 double bonds.

name: N-pentacosenoylsphingosine-1-phosphocholine
definition: A sphingomyelin d18:1 in which the total number of carbons in the fatty acyl group is 25 with 1 double bond.

name: (1R,2R)-bitertanol
definition: A 1-(biphenyl-4-yloxy)-3,3-dimethyl-1-(1,2,4-triazol-1-yl)butan-2-ol that is the (1R,2R)-diastereomer of bitertanol.

name: (1S,2S)-bitertanol
definition: A 1-(biphenyl-4-yloxy)-3,3-dimethyl-1-(1,2,4-triazol-1-yl)butan-2-ol that is the (1S,2S)-diastereomer of bitertanol.

name: dalpatein(1-)
definition: A flavonoid oxoanion that is the conjugate base of dalpatein, obtained by deprotonation of the 7-hydroxy group. It is the major microspecies at pH 7.3 (according to Marvin v 6.2.0.).

name: (1S,2R)-bitertanol
definition: A 1-(biphenyl-4-yloxy)-3,3-dimethyl-1-(1,2,4-triazol-1-yl)butan-2-ol that is the (1S,2R)-diastereomer of bitertanol.

name: dalnigrein(1-)
definition: A flavonoid oxoanion that is the conjugate base of dalnigrein, obtained by deprotonation of the 7-hydroxy group. It is the major microspecies at pH 7.3 (according to Marvin v 6.2.0.).

name: (25S)-26-hydroxycholest-4-en-3-one
definition: A 26-hydroxycholest-4-en-3-one in which the 25-position has S-configuration.

name: (25R)-26-hydroxycholest-4-en-3-one
definition: A 26-hydroxycholest-4-en-3-one in which the 25-position has R-configuration.

name: (25R)-3-ketocholest-4-en-26-al
definition: A 3-ketocholest-4-en-26-al in which the 25-position has R-configuration.

name: (25S)-3-ketocholest-4-en-26-al
definition: A 3-ketocholest-4-en-26-al in which the 25-position has S-configuration.

name: (R)-lipoyl-AMP
definition: A lipoyl-AMP in which the lipoyl moiety has (R)-configuration.

name: androst-5-ene-3,17-dione
definition: An androstanoid that is androst-5-ene bearing two oxo substituents at positions 3 and 17.

name: N-acyl-D-galactosylsphingosine
definition: A sphingosine-based sphingolipid that is any N-acylsphingosine substituted at the O-1 position by a D-galactosyl residue.

name: N-stearoyl-D-galactosylsphingosine
definition: An N-acyl-D-galactosylsphingosine in which the ceramide N-acyl group is specified as stearoyl (octadecanoyl).

name: N-behenoyl-D-galactosylsphingosine
definition: An N-acyl-D-galactosylsphingosine in which the ceramide N-acyl group is specified as behenoyl (docosanoyl).

name: N-(2-hydroxytricosanoyl)-D-galactosylsphingosine
definition: An N-acyl-D-galactosylsphingosine in which the ceramide N-acyl group is specified as 2-hydroxytricosanoyl.

name: N-lignoceroyl-D-galactosylsphingosine
definition: An N-acyl-D-galactosylsphingosine in which the ceramide N-acyl group is specified as lignoceroyl (tetracosanoyl).

name: N-(2-hydroxylignoceroyl)-D-galactosylsphingosine
definition: An N-acyl-D-galactosylsphingosine in which the ceramide N-acyl group is specified as 2-hydroxylignoceroyl.

name: N-stearoyl-(3-O-sulfo-D-galactosyl)sphingosine(1-)
definition: An N-acyl-(3-O-sulfo-D-galactosyl)sphingosine(1-) obtained by deprotonation of the sulfo group of N-stearoyl-(3-O-sulfo-D-galactosyl)sphingosine; major species at pH 7.3.

name: N-acyl-(3-O-sulfo-D-galactosyl)sphingosine(1-)
definition: A sulfohexosyl ceramide(1-) obtained by deprotonation of the sulfo group of any N-acyl-(3-O-sulfo-D-galactosyl)sphingosine; major species at pH 7.3.

name: cationic sphingoid
definition: An organic cation obtained by protonation of the amino function of any sphingoid

name: N-lignoceroyl-(3-O-sulfo-D-galactosyl)sphingosine(1-)
definition: An N-acyl-(3-O-sulfo-D-galactosyl)sphingosine(1-) obtained by deprotonation of the sulfo group of N-lignoceroyl-(3-O-sulfo-D-galactosyl)sphingosine; major species at pH 7.3.

name: N-tricosenoyl-D-galactosylsphingosine
definition: An N-acyl-D-galactosylsphingosine in which the ceramide N-acyl group is composed of 23 carbons and 1 double bond.

name: N-tetracosenoyl-D-galactosylsphingosine
definition: An N-acyl-D-galactosylsphingosine in which the ceramide N-acyl group is composed of 24 carbons and 1 double bond.

name: N-tricosanoylsphing-4-enine-1-phosphocholine
definition: A sphingomyelin 41:1 in which the N-acyl group and sphingoid base are specified as tricosanoyl and sphingosine respectively.

name: N-(2-hydroxytetracosenoyl)-D-galactosylsphingosine
definition: An N-acyl-D-galactosylsphingosine in which the ceramide N-acyl group is composed of 24 carbons, 1 double bond and a hydroxy group at C2.

name: torvanol A(1-)
definition: An  organosulfonate oxoanion that is the conjugate base of torvanol A hydrogen sulfate.

name: torvanol A hydrogen sulfate
definition: A methoxyisoflavan that is isoflavan substituted by a hydroxy group at position 2', methoxy groups at positions 6 and 3', a 2-carboxyethenyl group at position 5' and a sulfoxy group at position 4.

name: N-tetracosadienoyl-D-galactosylsphingosine
definition: An N-acyl-D-galactosylsphingosine in which the ceramide N-acyl group is composed of 24 carbons and 2 double bonds.

name: N-(2-hydroxytetracosadienoyl)-D-galactosylsphingosine
definition: An N-acyl-D-galactosylsphingosine in which the ceramide N-acyl group is composed of 24 carbons, 2 double bonds and a hydroxyl at C2.

name: N-hexacosenoyl-D-galactosylsphingosine
definition: An N-acyl-D-galactosylsphingosine in which the ceramide N-acyl group is  composed of 26 carbons and 1 double bond.

name: N-(2-hydroxyhexacosenoyl)-D-galactosylsphingosine
definition: An N-acyl-D-galactosylsphingosine in which the ceramide N-acyl group is composed of 26 carbons, 1 double bond and a hydroxy group at C2.

name: N-(2-hydroxypentacosanoyl)-D-galactosylsphingosine
definition: An N-acyl-D-galactosylsphingosine in which the ceramide N-acyl group is composed of 25 carbons  and a hydroxy group at C2.

name: N-(2-hydroxypentacosenoyl)-D-galactosylsphingosine
definition: An N-acyl-D-galactosylsphingosine in which the ceramide N-acyl group is composed of 25 carbons, 1 double bond and a hydroxy group at C2.

name: N-icosanoyl-(3-O-sulfo-D-galactosyl)sphingosine(1-)
definition: An N-acyl-(3-O-sulfo-D-galactosyl)sphingosine(1-) obtained by deprotonation of the sulfo group of N-icosanoyl-(3-O-sulfo-D-galactosyl)sphingosine; major species at pH 7.3.

name: N-icosenoyl-(3-O-sulfo-D-galactosyl)sphingosine(1-)
definition: An N-acyl-(3-O-sulfo-D-galactosyl)sphingosine(1-) in which the ceramide N-acyl group is composed of 20 carbons and 1 double bond.

name: N-(2-hydroxyicosenoyl)-(3-O-sulfo-D-galactosyl)sphingosine(1-)
definition: An N-acyl-(3-O-sulfo-D-galactosyl)sphingosine(1-) in which the ceramide N-acyl group is composed of 20 carbons, 1 double bond and a hydroxy group at C2.

name: sphingomyelin 41:1
definition: A sphingomyelin in which the total number of carbons in the sphingoid base and fatty acyl groups is 41 with 1 double bond.

name: [4)-beta-D-ManpNAcA-(1->4)-alpha-L-Fucp3,NAc2-(1->3)-beta-D-FucpNAc-(1->]n
definition: A polysaccharide derivative comprising a trisaccharide repeating unit consisting of N-acetyl-beta-D-mannosaminouronic acid, 3,N-diacetyl-alpha-L-fucosamine and N-acetyl-beta-D-fucosamine residues linked sequentially (1->4) and (1->3), with the trisaccharide repeats themselves being linked (1->4); corresponds to the serotype 5 (CP5) capsular polysaccharide of Staphylococcus aureus.

name: [3)-beta-D-Manp4,NAc2A-(1->3)-alpha-L-FucpNAc-(1->3)-alpha-D-FucpNAc-(1->]n
definition: A polysaccharide derivative comprising a trisaccharide repeating unit consisting of 4,N-diacetyl-beta-D-mannosaminouronic acid, N-acetyl-alpha-L-fucosamine and N-acetyl-beta-D-fucosamine residues linked sequentially (1->3), with the trisaccharide repeats themselves also being linked (1->3); corresponds to the serotype 8 (CP8) capsular polysaccharide of Staphylococcus aureus.

name: alpha-L-FucpNAc-(1->3)-D-FucpNAc
definition: An amino disaccharide consisting of an N-acetyl-alpha-L-fucosaminyl residue linked (1->3) to an N-acetyl-alpha-D-fucosamine residue.

name: UDP-N-acetyl-alpha-D-muramoyl-L-alaninate(3-)
definition: A UDP-N-acetylmuramoyl-L-alaninate(3-) in which the D-muramoyl fragment has alpha-configuration at its anomeric centre; major species at pH 7.3.

name: N-docosanoyl-(3-O-sulfo-D-galactosyl)sphingosine(1-)
definition: An N-acyl-(3-O-sulfo-D-galactosyl)sphingosine(1-) obtained by deprotonation of the sulfo group of N-docosanoyl-(3-O-sulfo-D-galactosyl)sphingosine; major species at pH 7.3.

name: UDP-N-acetyl-alpha-D-muramoyl-L-alanyl-D-glutamate(4-)
definition: A UDP-N-acetylmuramoyl-L-alanyl-D-glutamate(4-) in which the muramoyl fragment has alpha-configuration at its anomeric centre; major species at pH 7.3.

name: N-(2-hydroxytetracosanoyl)-(3-O-sulfo-D-galactosyl)sphingosine(1-)
definition: An N-acyl-(3-O-sulfo-D-galactosyl)sphingosine(1-) obtained by deprotonation of the sulfo group of N-(2-hydroxytetracosanoyl)-(3-O-sulfo-D-galactosyl)sphingosine; major species at pH 7.3.

name: UDP-N-acetyl-alpha-D-muramoyl-L-alanyl-D-gamma-glutamyl-L-lysinate(3-)
definition: Trianion of UDP-N-acetyl-alpha-D-muramoyl-L-alanyl-D-gamma-glutamyl-L-lysine; major species at pH 7.3.

name: N-docosenoyl-(3-O-sulfo-D-galactosyl)sphingosine(1-)
definition: An N-acyl-(3-O-sulfo-D-galactosyl)sphingosine(1-) in which the ceramide N-acyl group is composed of 22 carbons and 1 double bond.

name: UDP-N-acetyl-alpha-D-muramoyl-L-alanyl-D-gamma-glutamyl-meso-2,6-diaminoheptanedioate(4-)
definition: A UDP-N-acetylmuramoyl-L-alanyl-D-gamma-glutamyl-meso-2,6-diaminoheptanedioate(4-) in which the muramoyl moiety has alpha-configuratijon at its anomeric centre; major species at pH 7.3

name: (S)-diniconazole
definition: A (1E)-1-(2,4-dichlorophenyl)-4,4-dimethyl-2-(1,2,4-triazol-1-yl)pent-1-en-3-ol that is the (S)-enantiomer of diniconazole.

name: N-(2-hydroxydocosenoyl)-(3-O-sulfo-D-galactosyl)sphingosine(1-)
definition: An N-acyl-(3-O-sulfo-D-galactosyl)sphingosine(1-) in which the ceramide N-acyl group is composed of 22 carbons, 1 double bond and a hydroxy group at C2.

name: N-tetracosenoyl-(3-O-sulfo-D-galactosyl)sphingosine(1-)
definition: An N-acyl-(3-O-sulfo-D-galactosyl)sphingosine(1-) in which the ceramide N-acyl group is composed of 24 carbons and 1 double bond.

name: (1E)-1-(2,4-dichlorophenyl)-4,4-dimethyl-2-(1,2,4-triazol-1-yl)pent-1-en-3-ol
definition: A member of the class of triazoles that is 4,4-dimethyl-2-(1,2,4-triazol-1-yl)pent-1-en-3-ol substituted at position 1 by a 2,4-dichlorophenyl group.

name: N-(2-hydroxytetracosenoyl)-(3-O-sulfo-D-galactosyl)sphingosine(1-)
definition: An N-acyl-(3-O-sulfo-D-galactosyl)sphingosine(1-) in which the ceramide N-acyl group is composed of 24 carbons, 1 double bond and a hydroxy group at C2.

name: diniconazole-M
definition: A (1E)-1-(2,4-dichlorophenyl)-4,4-dimethyl-2-(1,2,4-triazol-1-yl)pent-1-en-3-ol that is the active R-enantiomer of diniconazole. A fungicide used to control a range of diseases including mildew, bunts and smuts.

name: N(6)-(UDP-N-acetyl-alpha-D-muramoyl-L-alanyl-D-gamma-glutamyl)-D-lysine(3-)
definition: Trianion of N(6)-(UDP-N-acetylmuramoyl-L-alanyl-D-gamma-glutamyl)-D-lysine; major species at pH 7.3.

name: N-tetracosadienoyl-(3-O-sulfo-D-galactosyl)sphingosine(1-)
definition: An N-acyl-(3-O-sulfo-D-galactosyl)sphingosine(1-) in which the ceramide N-acyl group is composed of 24 carbons and 2 double bonds.

name: omega-hydroxy-15-methylpalmitate
definition: A hydroxy fatty acid anion that is the conjugate base of omega-hydroxy-15-methyl-palmitic acid, obtained by deprotonation of the carboxy group; major species at pH 7.3.

name: N-(2-hydroxytetracosadienoyl)-(3-O-sulfo-D-galactosyl)sphingosine(1-)
definition: An N-acyl-(3-O-sulfo-D-galactosyl)sphingosine(1-) in which the ceramide N-acyl group is composed of 24 carbons, 2 double bonds and a hydroxy group at C2.

name: omega-hydroxyphytanate
definition: An omega-hydroxy fatty acid anion that is the conjugate base of omega-hydroxyphytanic acid, obtained by deprotonation of the carboxy group; major species at pH 7.3.

name: N-(2-hydroxypentacosanoyl)-(3-O-sulfo-D-galactosyl)sphingosine(1-)
definition: An N-acyl-(3-O-sulfo-D-galactosyl)sphingosine(1-) in which the ceramide N-acyl group is composed of 25 carbons with a hydroxy group at C2.

name: N-(2-hydroxypentacosenoyl)-(3-O-sulfo-D-galactosyl)sphingosine(1-)
definition: An N-acyl-(3-O-sulfo-D-galactosyl)sphingosine(1-) in which the ceramide N-acyl group is composed of 25 carbons, 1 double bond and a hydroxy group at C2.

name: N-(2-hydroxypentacosadienoyl)-(3-O-sulfo-D-galactosyl)sphingosine(1-)
definition: An N-acyl-(3-O-sulfo-D-galactosyl)sphingosine(1-) in which the ceramide N-acyl group is composed of 25 carbons, 2 double bonds and a hydroxy group at C2.

name: 4-(4-chlorophenyl)-2-phenyl-2-(1,2,4-triazol-1-ylmethyl)butanenitrile
definition: A member of the class of triazoles that is 1-chloro-4-(3-phenylpropyl)benzene substituted at position 3 of the propyl moiety by cyano and 1,2,4-triazol-1-ylmethyl groups.

name: (S)-fenbuconazole
definition: 4-(4-chlorophenyl)-2-phenyl-2-(1,2,4-triazol-1-ylmethyl)butanenitrile that is the (S)-enantiomer of fenbuconazole.

name: (R)-fenbuconazole
definition: 4-(4-chlorophenyl)-2-phenyl-2-(1,2,4-triazol-1-ylmethyl)butanenitrile that is the (R)-enantiomer of fenbuconazole.

name: fluquinconazole
definition: A member of the class of quinazolines that is 6-fluoroquinazolin-4-one carrying additional 1,2,4-triazol-1-yl and 2,4-dichlorophenyl substituents at positions 2 and 3 respectively. A fungicide used to control Ascomycetes, Deuteromycetes and Basidiomycetes spp. on cereals, beets and fruit.

name: strobilurin B
definition: An enoate ester that is the methyl ester of (2E,3Z,5E)-6-(4-chloro-3-methoxyphenyl)-2-(methoxymethylene)-3-methylhexa-3,5-dienoic acid.

name: non-proteinogenic alpha-amino acid
