definition: Any  alpha-amino acid which is not a member of the group of 23 proteinogenic amino acids.

name: [4)-alpha-D-GlcpNAc-1-P-(O->]n
definition: A polysaccharide phosphate composed of a backbone of alpha-D-glucose residues connected by phosphodiester linkages between positions 1 and 4 of adjacent residues; structure of the Neisseria meningitidis X capsular polysaccharide.

name: sodium 3-aminopropyl 2-acetamido-2-deoxy-alpha-D-glucose-1-phosphate
definition: The organic sodium salt of 3-aminopropyl 2-acetamido-2-deoxy-alpha-D-glucose-1-phosphate

name: tubulozole
definition: A racemate comprising equimolar amounts of (2R,4R)- and (2S,4S)-tubulozole. A synthetic anticancer drug that interferes with the structure and function of microtubules in both interphase and mitotic cells.

name: 3-aminopropyl N-acetyl-alpha-D-glucosamine-1-phosphate(1-)
definition: The organophosphate oxoanion formed by proton loss from the phospho group of 3-aminopropyl N-acetyl-alpha-D-glucosamine-1-phosphate.

name: 3-aminopropyl N-acetyl-alpha-D-glucosamine-1-phosphate
definition: An amino sugar phosphate that is alpha-D-glucosamine linked glycosidically to a (3-aminopropoxy)(hydroxy)phosphoryl group.

name: ethyl [4-({[2-(2,4-dichlorophenyl)-2-(imidazol-1-ylmethyl)-1,3-dioxolan-4-yl]methyl}sulfanyl)phenyl]carbamate
definition: A carbamate ester that is the ethyl ester of [4-({[2-(2,4-dichlorophenyl)-2-(imidazol-1-ylmethyl)-1,3-dioxolan-4-yl]methyl}sulfanyl)phenyl]carbamic acid.

name: (R,R)-tubulozole
definition: An ethyl [4-({[2-(2,4-dichlorophenyl)-2-(imidazol-1-ylmethyl)-1,3-dioxolan-4-yl]methyl}sulfanyl)phenyl]carbamate in which both stereocentres have R-configuration.

name: (S,S)-tubulozole
definition: An ethyl [4-({[2-(2,4-dichlorophenyl)-2-(imidazol-1-ylmethyl)-1,3-dioxolan-4-yl]methyl}sulfanyl)phenyl]carbamate in which both stereocentres have S-configuration.

name: zaragozic acid C
definition: A polyketide isolated from fungi that is a potent inhibitor of fungal and mammalian squalene synthase.

name: 15-hydroxypalmitic acid
definition: A hydroxy fatty acid that is palmitic (hexadecanoic) acid carrying a single hydroxy substituent at position 15.

name: 15-hydroxypalmitate
definition: A hydroxy fatty acid anion that is the conjugate base of 15-hydroxypalmitic acid, obtained by deprotonation of the carboxy group; major species at pH 7.3.

name: 14-hydroxypalmitic acid
definition: A hydroxy fatty acid that is palmitic (hexadecanoic) acid carrying a single hydroxy substituent at position 14.

name: 14-hydroxypalmitate
definition: A hydroxy fatty acid anion that is the conjugate base of 14-hydroxypalmitic acid, obtained by deprotonation of the carboxy group; major species at pH 7.3.

name: 1-acyl-2-stearoyl-sn-glycero-3-phospho-(1D-myo-inositol)(2-)
definition: A 1-phosphatidyl-1D-myo-inositol(1-) which has a steroyl group as the acyl group at position 2.

name: N-acetyl-D-muramoyl-L-alaninate
definition: The carbohydrate acid derivative anion formed by loss of a proton from the carboxy group of N-acetyl-D-muramoyl-L-alanine; principal microspecies at pH 7.3.

name: N(6)-(UDP-N-acetyl-alpha-D-muramoyl-L-alanyl-D-gamma-glutamyl)-D-lysine
definition: A UDP-glycopeptide in which the glycopeptide component consists of N(6)-(N-acetyl-alpha-D-muramoyl-L-alanyl-D-gamma-glutamyl)-D-lysine, joined to UDP via a glycosyl diphosphate bond.

name: L-alanine derivative
definition: A proteinogenic amino acid derivative resulting from reaction of L-alanine at the amino group or the carboxy group, or from the replacement of any hydrogen of L-alanine by a heteroatom.

name: D-alanine derivative
definition: A non-proteinogenic amino acid derivative resulting from reaction of D-alanine at the amino group or the carboxy group, or from the replacement of any hydrogen of D-alanine by a heteroatom.

name: diazaborine
definition: A organonitrogen heterocyclic compound consisting of 2,3,1-benzodiazaborinine substituted at positions 1 and 2 by hydroxy and 4-toluenesufonyl groups respectively.

name: N-acyl-L-alanine
definition: An N-acyl-L-alpha-amino acid that is L-alanine in which a hydrogen attached to the nitrogen is replaced by an acyl group.

name: diazaborine derivative
definition: Any organonitrogen heterocyclic compound that is derived from diazaborine.

name: dihydrocanadensolide
definition: A member of the class of furofurans that is tetrahydrofuro[3,4-b]furan-2,4-dione substituted at positions 3 and 6 by methyl and butyl groups respectively (the 3R,3aR,6S,6aS-stereoisomer).

name: N-succinimidyl N-methylcarbamate
definition: A member of the class of pyrrolidinones that is N-hydroxysuccinimide in which the hydroxyl hydrogen is replaced by a methylcarbamoyl group.

name: SDZ 90-215
definition: A cyclodepsipeptide constructed from Pip, MeVal, Val, MeAsp, MeIle, MeIle, Gly, MeVal, Tyr(Me) and D-Lac residues.

name: (2E,6E,10E)-omega-hydroxyfarnesol
definition: A  farnesane sesquiterpenoid obtained by hydroxylation of one of the terminal methyl groups of farnesol.

name: (2E,6E,10E)-geranylgeranate
definition: A polyunsaturated fatty acid anion resulting from the removal of a proton from the carboxy group of (2E,6E,10E)-geranylgeranic acid; major species at pH 7.3.

name: omega-hydroxygeranylgeraniol
definition: A diterpenoid obtained by hydroxylation of one of the terminal methyl groups of geranylgeraniol.

name: (2E,6E,10E,14E)-omega-hydroxygeranylgeranate
definition: A polyunsaturated fatty acid anion resulting from the removal of a proton from the carboxy group of (2E,6E,10E,14E)-omega-hydroxygeranylgeranic acid; major species at pH 7.3.

name: 2-saturated fatty acid anion
definition: A fatty acid anion obtained by deprotonation of the carboxy group of any 2-saturated fatty acid.

name: cladoniamide
definition: A family of tryptophan-derived alkaloids produced in culture by Streptomyces uncialis, a lichen-associated actinomycete strain.

name: (2E,6E,10E)-omega-hydroxyfarnesyl diphosphate(3-)
definition: An organophosphate oxoanion obtained by deprotonation of the diphosphate OH groups of (2E,6E,10E)-omega-hydroxyfarnesyl diphosphate; major species at pH 7.3.

name: hygrolidin
definition: A macrolide consisting resulting from the formal lactonisation of the carboxy group of (2E,4E,6R,7S,8S,10E,12E,14S,15R,16S,17R,18S)-18-[(2R,4R,5S,6R)-4-{[(2E)-3-carboxyprop-2-enoyl]oxy}-2-hydroxy-5,6-dimethyltetrahydro-2H-pyran-2-yl]-7,15,17-trihydroxy-14-methoxy-2,4,6,8,10,16-hexamethylnonadeca-2,4,10,12-tetraenoic acid with the hydroxy group at position 15. It is active against SV40 tumour cells, and inhibits the growth of solid tumour-derived cell lines such as DLD-1 human colon cancer cells with increased cells in G1 and S phases.

name: N(omega)-alpha-(ADP-D-ribosyl)-L-arginine(1-) residue
definition: An organic anionic group derived from N(omega)-(ADP-D-ribosyl)-L-arginine(1-); major species at pH 7.3

name: zaragozic acid A derivative
definition: Any polyketide derived from zaragozic acid A.

name: NVP-BHS345
definition: A member of the class of imidazoquinolines that is 3-methyl-2-oxo-2,3-dihydro-1H-imidazo[4,5-c]quinoline substituted at position 1 by a 4-(1-cyanoisopropyl)phenyl group and at position 8 by a pyrimidin-5-yl group.

name: 2-acetamido-2-deoxy-3-O-(4-deoxy-alpha-L-threo-hex-4-enopyranosyluronate)-4-O-sulfonato-D-galactopyranose(2-)
definition: A carbohydrate acid derivative anion resulting from the removal of a proton from the carboxy and sulfate groups of 2-acetamido-2-deoxy-3-O-(4-deoxy-alpha-L-threo-hex-4-enopyranosyluronic acid)-4-O-sulfo-D-galactopyranose arising from deprotonation of carboxylic acid and sulfate functions.

name: 7-hydroxyflavanone 7-O-[beta-L-rhamnosyl-(1->2)-beta-D-glucoside]
definition: A glycosyloxyflavone that is 7-hydroxyflavanone having a beta-(1->2)-L-rhamnosyl)-beta-D-glucosyl moiety attached to the 7-hydroxy group.

name: L-arginine derivative
definition: A proteinogenic amino acid derivative resulting from reaction of L-arginine at the amino group, the carboxy group, or the guanidyl group, or from the replacement of any hydrogen of L-arginine by a heteroatom.

name: D-arginine derivative
definition: A non-proteinogenic amino acid derivative resulting from reaction of D-arginine at the amino group, the carboxy group, or the guanidyl group, or from the replacement of any hydrogen of D-arginine by a heteroatom.

name: bufadienolides
definition: Any steroid lactone that is a C23 steroid with a six-membered lactone ring at C-17 and its substituted derivatives. They form the aglycone constituents of cardiac glycosides.

name: 3-methyl fatty acyl-CoA(4-)
definition: A  methyl-branched fatty acyl-CoA that results from the formal condensation of the thiol group of coenzyme A with the carboxy group of any 3-methyl fatty acid.

name: 3-methylpalmitoyl-CoA(4-)
definition: A 3-methyl fatty acyl-CoA(4-) arising from deprotonation of the phosphate and diphosphate OH groups of 3-methylpalmitoyl-CoA; major species at pH 7.3.

name: cardiac glycoside
definition: Steroid lactones containing sugar residues that act on the contractile force of the cardiac muscles.

name: bufadienolide glycoside
definition: Any member of the class of  bufadienolides with glycosyl residues attached to position 3.

name: 3-methyl fatty acid anion
definition: A methyl-branched fatty acid anion obtained by deprotonation of the carboxy group of any 3-methyl fatty acid; major species at pH 7.3.

name: N-Boc-D-4-HO-3,5-Cl2-PhGly-D-4-HO-3,5-I2-PhGly-OMe
definition: A dipeptide comprising of phenylglycine derived residues linked by peptide bonds.

name: D-asparagine derivative
definition: A non-proteinogenic amino acid derivative resulting from reaction of D-asparagine at the amino group, the carboxy group, or the carboxamide, or from the replacement of any hydrogen of D-asparagine by a heteroatom.

name: 2-methyl fatty acid anion
definition: A methyl-branched fatty acid anion obtained by deprotonation of the carboxy group of any 2-methyl fatty acid; major species at pH 7.3.

name: (5beta)-bufadienolide
definition: The (5beta)-stereoiosmer of bufadienolide.

name: L-aspartic acid derivative
definition: A proteinogenic amino acid derivative resulting from reaction of L-aspartic acid at the amino group or either of the carboxy groups, or from the replacement of any hydrogen of L-aspartic acid by a heteroatom.

name: 1-stearoyl-2-arachidonoyl-sn-glycero-3-phospho-(1D-myo-inositol 3,4,5-triphosphate)
definition: A 1-phosphatidyl-1D-myo-inositol 3,4,5-trisphosphate in which the phosphatidyl acyl groups at positions 1 and 2 are specified as stearoyl and arachidonoyl respectively.

name: 3-hydroxyaspartic acid
definition: A hydroxy-amino acid that is aspartic acid in which one of the methylene hydrogens has been replaced by a hydroxy group.

name: L-glutamic acid derivative
definition: A proteinogenic amino acid derivative resulting from reaction of L-glutamic acid at the amino group or either of the carboxy groups, or from the replacement of any hydrogen of L-glutamic acid by a heteroatom.

name: D-glutamic acid derivative
definition: A non-proteinogenic amino acid derivative resulting from the formal reaction of D-glutamic acid at the amino group or either carboxy group, or from the replacement of any hydrogen of D-glutamic acid by a heteroatom.

name: N(2)-acylglutamine
definition: A glutamine derivative that is glutamine in which one of the hydrogens attached to the alpha-amino group is replaced by an acyl group.

name: ethylenebis(dithiocarbamic acid)
definition: A dithiocarbamic acid resulting from the formal addition of a molecule of carbon disulfide to each amino group of ethylenediamine.

name: D-glutamine derivative
definition: A non-proteinogenic amino acid derivative resulting from the formal reaction of D-glutamine at the amino group, carboxy group, or carboxamide, or from the replacement of any hydrogen of D-glutamine by a heteroatom.

name: 14-methylhexadecasphingosine
definition: A sphingoid that is hexadecasphingosine substituted at position 14 by a methyl group.

name: O-[S-(9Z)-hexadecenoylpantetheine-4'-phosphoryl]serine(1-) residue
definition: An O-(S-acylpantetheine-4'-phosphoryl)serine(1-) residue in which the S-acyl group is specified as (9Z)-hexadecenoyl.

name: E. coli strain 0111 B4 lipopolysaccharide
definition: A lipopolysaccharide that is produced by E. coli strain 0111 B4.

name: imidothioate
definition: A compound with the general formula R'-N=C(SR)R'' where R is organyl and R' and R'' can be organyl or H.

name: beta-D-glucosylsphingosine(1+)
definition: A D-glucosylsphingosine(1+) obtained by protonation of the amino group of any beta-D-glucosylsphingosine; major species at pH 7.3.

name: 1-[2-(2,4-dichlorophenyl)pentyl]1,2,4-triazole
definition: A member of the classof triazoles that is 1,2,4-triazole substituted at position 1 by a 2-(2,4-dichlorophenyl)pentyl group.

name: (R)-penconazole
definition: A 1-[2-(2,4-dichlorophenyl)pentyl]1,2,4-triazole that is the (R)-enantiomer of penconazole.

name: (S)-penconazole
definition: A 1-[2-(2,4-dichlorophenyl)pentyl]1,2,4-triazole that is the (S)-enantiomer of penconazole.

name: 2-(4-fluorophenyl)-1-(1,2,4-triazol-1-yl)-3-(trimethylsilyl)propan-2-ol
definition: A member of the class of triazoles that is 2-(4-fluorophenyl)-1-(1,2,4-triazol-1-yl)-3-(trimethylsilyl)propane carrying an additional hydroxy substituent at position 2.

name: (R)-simeconazole
definition: A 2-(4-fluorophenyl)-1-(1,2,4-triazol-1-yl)-3-(trimethylsilyl)propan-2-ol that is the (R)-enantiomer of simeconazole.

name: (S)-simeconazole
definition: A 2-(4-fluorophenyl)-1-(1,2,4-triazol-1-yl)-3-(trimethylsilyl)propan-2-ol that is the (S)-enantiomer of simeconazole.

name: 1-[2-(2,4-dichlorophenyl)-3-(1,1,2,2-tetrafluoroethoxy)propyl]1,2,4-triazole
definition: A member of the class of triazoles that is 1,2,4-triazole substituted at position 1 by a 2-(2,4-dichlorophenyl)-3-(1,1,2,2-tetrafluoroethoxy)propyl group.

name: (R)-tetraconazole
definition: A 1-[2-(2,4-dichlorophenyl)-3-(1,1,2,2-tetrafluoroethoxy)propyl]1,2,4-triazole that is the (R)-enantiomer of tetraconazole.

name: (S)-tetraconazole
definition: A 1-[2-(2,4-dichlorophenyl)-3-(1,1,2,2-tetrafluoroethoxy)propyl]1,2,4-triazole that is the (S)-enantiomer of tetraconazole.

name: 1-(4-chlorophenoxy)-3,3-dimethyl-1-(1,2,4-triazol-1-yl)butan-2-one
definition: A member of the class of triazoles that is 1-hydroxy-3,3-dimethyl-1-(1,2,4-triazol-1-yl)butan-2-one in which the hydroxyl hydrogen is replaced by a 4-chlorophenyl group.

name: (R)-triadimefon
definition: A 1-(4-chlorophenoxy)-3,3-dimethyl-1-(1,2,4-triazol-1-yl)butan-2-one that is the (R)-enantiomer of triadimefon.

name: (S)-triadimefon
definition: A 1-(4-chlorophenoxy)-3,3-dimethyl-1-(1,2,4-triazol-1-yl)butan-2-one that is the (S)-enantiomer of triadimefon.

name: (5E)-5-(4-chlorobenzylidene)-2,2-dimethyl-1-(1,2,4-triazol-1-ylmethyl)cyclopentanol
definition: A member of the class of cyclopentanols carrying 1,2,4-triazol-1-ylmethyl and 4-chlorobenzylidene and geminal dimethyl substituents at positions 1, 2 and 5 respectively.

name: (R)-triticonazole
definition: A (5E)-5-(4-chlorobenzylidene)-2,2-dimethyl-1-(1,2,4-triazol-1-ylmethyl)cyclopentanol that is the (R)-enantiomer of triticonazole.

name: (S)-triticonazole
definition: A (5E)-5-(4-chlorobenzylidene)-2,2-dimethyl-1-(1,2,4-triazol-1-ylmethyl)cyclopentanol that is the (S)-enantiomer of triticonazole.

name: 2-[2-(1-chlorocyclopropyl)-3-(2-chlorophenyl)-2-hydroxypropyl]-1,2-dihydro-1,2,4-triazole-3-thione
definition: A member of the class of triazoles that is 1,2,4-triazole-3-thione substituted at position 2 by a 2-(1-chlorocyclopropyl)-3-(2-chlorophenyl)-2-hydroxypropyl group.

name: (S)-prothioconazole
definition: A 2-[2-(1-chlorocyclopropyl)-3-(2-chlorophenyl)-2-hydroxypropyl]-1,2-dihydro-1,2,4-triazole-3-thione that is the (S)-enantiomer of prothioconazole.

name: (R)-prothioconazole
definition: A 2-[2-(1-chlorocyclopropyl)-3-(2-chlorophenyl)-2-hydroxypropyl]-1,2-dihydro-1,2,4-triazole-3-thione that is the (R)-enantiomer of prothioconazole.

name: EC 4.2.1.94 (scytalone dehydratase) inhibitor
definition: An EC 4.2.1.* (hydro-lyases) inhibitor that interferes with the action of scytalone dehydratase (EC 4.2.1.94).

name: 2-cyano-N-[1-(2,4-dichlorophenyl)ethyl]-3,3-dimethylbutanamide
definition: A monocarboxylic acid amide obtained by formal condensation of the carboxy group of 2-cyano-3,3-dimethylbutanoic acid with the amino group of 1-(2,4-dichlorophenyl)ethylamine.

name: (1R,2S)-diclocymet
definition: The stereoisomer of 2-cyano-N-[1-(2,4-dichlorophenyl)ethyl]-3,3-dimethylbutanamide obtained by formal condensation of the carboxy group of (S)-2-cyano-3,3-dimethylbutanoic acid with the amino group of (R)-1-(2,4-dichlorophenyl)ethylamine.

name: N-(2-cyano-3-methylbutan-2-yl)-2-(2,4-dichlorophenoxy)propanamide
definition: A monocarboxylic acid amide obtained by formal condensation of the carboxy group of 2-(2,4-dichlorophenoxy)propanoic acid with the amino group of 2-amino-2,3-dimethylbutanenitrile.

name: (R,R)-fenoxanil
definition: The stereoisomer of N-(2-cyano-3-methylbutan-2-yl)-2-(2,4-dichlorophenoxy)propanamide obtained by formal condensation of the carboxy group of (R)-2-(2,4-dichlorophenoxy)propanoic acid with the amino group of (R)-2-amino-2,3-dimethylbutanenitrile.

name: (R,S)-fenoxanil
definition: The stereoisomer of N-(2-cyano-3-methylbutan-2-yl)-2-(2,4-dichlorophenoxy)propanamide obtained by formal condensation of the carboxy group of (R)-2-(2,4-dichlorophenoxy)propanoic acid with the amino group of (S)-2-amino-2,3-dimethylbutanenitrile.

name: (S,S)-fenoxanil
definition: The stereoisomer of N-(2-cyano-3-methylbutan-2-yl)-2-(2,4-dichlorophenoxy)propanamide obtained by formal condensation of the carboxy group of (S)-2-(2,4-dichlorophenoxy)propanoic acid with the amino group of (S)-2-amino-2,3-dimethylbutanenitrile.

name: (S,R)-fenoxanil
definition: The stereoisomer of N-(2-cyano-3-methylbutan-2-yl)-2-(2,4-dichlorophenoxy)propanamide obtained by formal condensation of the carboxy group of (S)-2-(2,4-dichlorophenoxy)propanoic acid with the amino group of (R)-2-amino-2,3-dimethylbutanenitrile.

name: 9(10)-EpOME(1-)
definition: A monounsaturated fatty acid anion that is the conjugate base of 9(10)-EpOME, obtained by deprotonation of the carboxy group; major species at pH 7.3.

name: 14,15-EET(1-)
definition: An icosanoid anion that is the conjugate base of 14,15-EET, obtained by deprotonation of the carboxy group; major species at pH 7.3.

name: 8,9-EET(1-)
definition: An icosanoid anion that is the conjugate base of 8,9-EET, obtained by deprotonation of the carboxy group; major species at pH 7.3.

name: vernolate
definition: A monounsaturated fatty acid anion that is the conjugate base of vernolic acid, obtained by deprotonation of the carboxy group; major species at pH 7.3.

name: 9,10-DiHOME(1-)
definition: A monounsaturated fatty acid anion that is the conjugate base of 9,10-DiHOME, obtained by deprotonation of the carboxy group; major species at pH 7.3.

name: 12,13-DiHOME(1-)
definition: A monounsaturated fatty acid anion that is the conjugate base of 12,13-DiHOME, obtained by deprotonation of the carboxy group; major species at pH 7.3.

name: (5Z,8Z,11Z)-14,15-dihydroxyicosatrienoate
definition: A polyunsaturated fatty acid anion that is the conjugate base of (5Z,8Z,11Z)-14,15-dihydroxyicosatrienoic acid, obtained by deprotonation of the carboxy group; major species at pH 7.3.

name: (5Z,8Z,14Z)-11,12-dihydroxyicosatrienoate
definition: A polyunsaturated fatty acid anion that is the conjugate base of (5Z,8Z,14Z)-11,12-dihydroxyicosatrienoic acid, obtained by deprotonation of the carboxy group; major species at pH 7.3.

name: (5Z,11Z,14Z)-8,9-dihydroxyicosatrienoate
definition: A polyunsaturated fatty acid anion that is the conjugate base of (5Z,11Z,14Z)-8,9-dihydroxyicosatrienoic acid, obtained by deprotonation of the carboxy group; major species at pH 7.3.

name: fosetyl-Al
definition: An aluminium salt composed of ethyl phosphonate anions and aluminium cations in a 3:1 ratio. A fungicide for various horticultural crops used to control a range of diseases including Phytophthora, Pythium and Plasmopara.

name: pyridoxatin
definition: A member of the class of dihydroxypyridines that is 1,4-dihydroxypyridin-2-one carrying an additional 6-ethenyl-2,4-dimethylcyclohexyl substituent at position 3. Pyridoxatin is a MMP-2 (Gelatinase A) inhibitor with antibiotic and anticancer properties. Also indicated to be a lipid peroxidation and DNA synthesis inhibitor as well as a free radical scavenger.

name: EC 3.4.24.24 (gelatinase A) inhibitor
definition: An EC 3.4.24.* (metalloendopeptidase) inhibitor that interferes with the action of gelatinase A (EC 3.4.24.24).

name: ravidomycin
definition: A C-glycosylated naphthoisochromene derivative obtained from Streptomyces ravidus; exhibits antibiotic and anticancer properties.

name: dihydroresveratrol-3-O-sulfate
definition: An organic sulfate that consists of dihydroresveratrol substituted by a sulfate group at position 3. It is a metabolite of dihydroresveratrol.

name: dihydroresveratrol-3-O-beta-D-glucuronide
definition: A  monosaccharide derivative that is the 7-O-glucuronide of dihydroresveratrol .

name: resveratrol-3-O-sulfate
definition: An organic sulfate that is the 3-O-sulfate derivative of trans-resveratrol.

name: 2-O-palmitoyl-alpha,alpha-trehalose
definition: A monoacyl alpha,alpha-trehalose in which the acyl group is specified as palmitoyl (hexadecanoyl) and is located at position 2.

name: 2,3-dipalmitoyl-alpha,alpha-trehalose
definition: A polyacyl alpha,alpha-trehalose carrying two palmitoyl (hexadecanoyl) substituents that are located at positions 2 and 3.

name: gallium(3+)
definition: A monoatomic trication derived from gallium.

name: dihydroresveratrol sulfate
definition: Any organic sulfate that is the monosulfate derivative of dihydroresveratrol.

name: pyoverdine
definition: A family of over forty siderophoric non-ribosomal peptides containing a dihydroxyquinoline moiety produced by several Pseudomonas species.

name: dihydroresveratrol glucuronide
definition: Any stilbenol that is the beta-D-glucosiduronic acid derivative of dihydroresveratrol.

name: resveratrol sulfate
definition: Any stilbenol that is the monosulfate derivative of resveratrol.

name: dihydroresveratrol glucuronide sulfate
definition: Any  stilbenol that consists of  dihydroresveratrol attached to a sulfate and a beta-D-glucosiduronic acid residue at unspecified positions.

name: trabectedin
definition: A tetrahydroisoquinoline alkaloid obtained from a Caribbean tunicate Ecteinascidia turbinata. Used for the treatment of soft tissue sarcoma and relapsed ovarian cancer.

name: resveratrol disulfate
definition: Any  stilbenol that is the disulfate derivative of resveratrol.

name: resveratrol glucuronide sulfate
definition: Any stilbenol that consists of resveratrol attached to a sulfate and a beta-D-glucosiduronic acid residue at unspecified positions.

name: resveratrol glucuronide sulfate 1
definition: An isomer of the class of  resveratrol glucuronide sulfate.

name: resveratrol glucuronide sulfate 2
definition: An isomer of the class of  resveratrol glucuronide sulfate.

name: pentose phosphate
definition: Any phospho sugar that is the phosphate derivative of pentose.

name: N-acetylisoleucine
definition: An  isoleucine derivative that is the N-acetyl derivative of isoleucine.

name: trapoxin A
definition: A homodetic cyclic tetrapeptide constructed from L-phenylalanyl (x2), D-pipecolinyl and L-2-amino-8-oxo-9,10-epoxydecanoyl residues.

name: ophthalmic acid
definition: A L-glutamine derivative that is L-glutamine substituted by a 1-[(carboxymethyl)amino]-1-oxobutan-2-yl at the terminal amino nitrogen atom.

name: octyl palmitate
definition: A palmitate ester resulting from the formal condensation of the carboxy group of palmitic acid with the hydroxy group of octan-1-ol.

name: tridecanoyl-CoA(4-)
definition: A long-chain fatty acyl-CoA(4-) arising from deprotonation of phosphate and diphosphate functions of tridecanoyl-CoA; major species at pH 7.3.

name: nonyl palmitate
definition: A palmitate ester resulting from the formal condensation of the carboxy group of palmitic acid with the hydroxy group of nonan-1-ol.

name: decyl palmitate
definition: A palmitate ester resulting from the formal condensation of the carboxy group of palmitic acid with the hydroxy group of decan-1-ol.

name: myristyl palmitate
definition: A palmitate ester resulting from the formal condensation of the carboxy group of palmitic acid with the hydroxy group of tetradecan-1-ol.

name: arachidyl palmitate
definition: A palmitate ester resulting from the formal condensation of the carboxy group of palmitic acid with the hydroxy group of icosan-1-ol.

name: stearyl palmitate
definition: A palmitate ester resulting from the formal condensation of the carboxy group of palmitic acid with the hydroxy group of stearyl alcohol.

name: tetradecanal
definition: A long-chain fatty aldehyde that is tetradecane in which two hydrogens attached to a terminal carbon are replaced by an oxo group. It is found in coriander.

name: sodium arsenate
definition: An inorganic sodium salt composed from sodium cations and arsenate anions in a 3:1 ratio.

name: C22-C26 saturated fatty acid
definition: Any saturated fatty acid containing 22-26 carbons.

name: hexadecyl elaidate
definition: A wax ester resulting from the formal condensation of the carboxy group of elaidic acid with the hydroxy group of hexadecan-1-ol.

name: aminocandin
definition: A member of the family of echinocandins that shows broad-spectrum in vitro activity against Aspergillus and Candida spp.

name: [4)-beta-D-ManpNAcA-(1->4)-alpha-L-FucpNAc-(1->3)-beta-D-FucpNAc-(1->]n
definition: A polysaccharide derivative comprising a trisaccharide repeating unit consisting of N-acetyl-beta-D-mannosaminouronic acid, N-acetyl-alpha-L-fucosamine and N-acetyl-beta-D-fucosamine residues linked sequentially (1->4) and (1->3), with the trisaccharide repeats themselves being linked (1->4); corresponds to the de-O-acetylated serotype 5 (CP5) capsular polysaccharide of Staphylococcus aureus.

name: [3)-beta-D-ManpNAcA-(1->3)-alpha-L-FucpNAc-(1->3)-alpha-D-FucpNAc-(1->]n
definition: A polysaccharide derivative comprising a trisaccharide repeating unit consisting of N-acetyl-beta-D-mannosaminouronic acid, N-acetyl-alpha-L-fucosamine and N-acetyl-beta-D-fucosamine residues linked sequentially (1->3), with the trisaccharide repeats themselves also being linked (1->3); corresponds to the de-O-acetylated serotype 8 (CP8) capsular polysaccharide of Staphylococcus aureus.

name: L-histidine derivative
definition: A proteinogenic amino acid derivative resulting from the formal reaction of L-histidine at the amino group, carboxy group, or the imidazolyl moiety, or from the replacement of any hydrogen of L-histidine by a heteroatom.

name: D-histidine derivative
definition: A non-proteinogenic amino acid derivative resulting from the formal reaction of D-histidine at the amino group, carboxy group, or the imidazolyl moiety, or from the replacement of any hydrogen of D-histidine by a heteroatom.

name: beta-D-Galp-(1->4)-beta-D-GlcpNAc-(1->3)-beta-D-Galp-(1->4)-beta-D-Glcp-(1->4)-[alpha-D-GlcpNAc-(1->2)-3-PEA-L-alpha-D-Hepp-(1->3)]-L-alpha-D-Hepp-(1->5)-alpha-Kdo-(2->6)-(de-O-acylated lipid A)
definition: A lipid A derivative that consists of a branched octasaccharide phosphate made up from two D-galactose residues, two N-acetyl-D-glucosamine residues, a D-glucose residue, two L-glycero-D-manno-heptose residues (one of which is phosphoethanolamine-substituted on O-3), with linkages as shown and with a 3-deoxy-D-manno-oct-2-ulosonic acid (2-keto-3-deoxy-D-mannooctanoic acid, Kdo) residue at the reducing end connected via an alpha(2->6) linkage to a de-O-acylated lipid A.  Corresponds to the de-O-acylated lipid A conjugate of the core oligosaccharide of Neisseria meningitidis.

name: palmityl heptadecanoate
definition: A wax ester resulting from the formal condensation of the carboxy group of heptadecanoic acid with the hydroxy group of palmityl alcohol.

name: palmityl laurate
definition: A wax ester resulting from the formal condensation of lauric acid with palmityl alcohol.

name: beta-D-Glcp-(1->4)-[alpha-D-GlcpNAc-(1->2)-3-PEA-L-alpha-D-Hepp-(1->3)]-L-alpha-D-Hepp-(1->5)-alpha-Kdo-(2->6)-(de-O-acylated lipid A)
definition: A lipid A derivative that consists of a branched pentasaccharide phosphate made up from a D-glucose residue, an N-acetyl-D-glucosamine residue, two L-glycero-D-manno-heptose residues (one of which is phosphoethanolamine-substituted on O-3), with linkages as shown and with a 3-deoxy-D-manno-oct-2-ulosonic acid (2-keto-3-deoxy-D-mannooctanoic acid, Kdo) residue at the reducing end connected via an alpha(2->6) linkage to a de-O-acylated lipid A. Corresponds to the de-O-acylated lipid A conjugate of the galE mutant of the core oligosaccharide of Neisseria meningitidis.

name: alpha-D-GlcpNAc-(1->2)-3-PEA-L-alpha-D-Hepp-(1->3)-L-alpha-D-Hepp-(1->5)-alpha-Kdo-(2->6)-(de-O-acylated lipid A)
definition: A lipid A derivative that consists of a linear tetrasaccharide phosphate comprising an N-acetyl-alpha-D-glucosamine residue,an L-glycero-alpha-D-manno-heptose residue phosphoethanolamine-substituted on O-3, another L-glycero-alpha-D-manno-heptose residue and a 3-deoxy-D-manno-oct-2-ulosonic acid (2-keto-3-deoxy-D-mannooctanoic acid, Kdo) in a (1->2), (1->3), (1->5) sequence, with the Kdo residue at the reducing end connected via an alpha(2->6) linkage to a de-O-acylated lipid A. Corresponds to the de-O-acylated lipid A conjugate of the icsB mutant of the core oligosaccharide of Neisseria meningitidis.

name: 3-PEA-L-alpha-D-Hepp-(1->3)-L-alpha-D-Hepp-(1->5)-alpha-Kdo-(2->6)-(de-O-acylated lipid A)
definition: A lipid A derivative that consists of a linear trisaccharide phosphate comprising an L-glycero-alpha-D-manno-heptose residue phosphoethanolamine-substituted on O-3, another L-glycero-alpha-D-manno-heptose residue and a 3-deoxy-D-manno-oct-2-ulosonic acid (2-keto-3-deoxy-D-mannooctanoic acid, Kdo) in a (1->3), (1->5) sequence, with the Kdo residue at the reducing end connected via an alpha(2->6) linkage to a de-O-acylated lipid A. Corresponds to the de-O-acylated lipid A conjugate of the icsA mutant of the core oligosaccharide of Neisseria meningitidis.

name: 2-(acetylamino)-4-methylphenyl acetate
definition: An  acetate ester that is phenyl acetate substituted by an acetylamino group at position 2 and a methyl group at position 4.

name: 6-(2-hydroxyethoxy)-6-oxohexanoic acid
definition: A dicarboxylic acid monoester obtained by the formal condensation of one of the hydroxy groups of ethylene glycol with one of the carboxy groups of  adipic acid.

name: human urinary metabolite
definition: Any metabolite (endogenous or exogenous) found in human urine samples.

name: 6-(carboxymethoxy)hexanoic acid
definition: A dicarboxylic acid that is hexanoic acid substituted by a carboxymethoxy group at position 6.

name: 2,5-dihydroxycinnamic acid methyl ester
definition: A cinnamate ester that is the methyl ester of 2,5-dihydroxycinnamic acid.

name: hydroxyretinoic glucuronide
definition: Any retinoid obtained by the glycosylation of hydroxyretinoic acid with glucuronic acid.

name: 1-O-all-trans-4-hydroxyretinoyl-beta-glucuronic acid
definition: A hydroxyretinoic glucuronide obtained by the glycosylation of the carboxy group of all-trans-4-hydroxyretinoic acid with beta-glucuronic acid.

name: 4-(beta-D-glucopyranuronosyloxy)retinoic acid
definition: A hydroxyretinoic glucuronide that is all-trans-4-hydroxyretinoic acid attached to a beta-D-glucuronic acid residue via a glycosidic linkage.

name: 3-(benzyloxy)-3-oxopropanoic acid
definition: A dicarboxylic acid monoester obtained by the formal condensation of one of the carboxy groups of malonic acid with benzyl alcohol.

name: testosterone sulfate
definition: A steroid sulfate that is testosterone substituted by a sulfoxy group at position 17.

name: 2-carboxypalmitoyl-CoA(5-)
definition: A 2-carboxyacyl CoA(5-) arising from deprotonation of phosphate, diphosphate and carboxylic acid functions of 2-carboxypalmitoyl-CoA; major species at pH 7.3.

name: 2-carboxymyristoyl-CoA(5-)
definition: A 2-carboxyacyl CoA(5-) arising from deprotonation of phosphate, diphosphate and carboxylic acid functions of 2-carboxymyristoyl-CoA; major species at pH 7.3.

name: O-linoleyl-L-carnitine
definition: An O-octadecadienoyl-L-carnitine where the acyl group specified is linoleyl.

name: 2-carboxylauroyl-CoA(5-)
definition: A 2-carboxyacyl CoA(5-) arising from deprotonation of phosphate, diphosphate and carboxylic acid functions of 2-carboxylauroyl-CoA; major species at pH 7.3.

name: 3-hydroxyoctanoylcarnitine
definition: An O-acylcarnitine having 3-hydroxyoctanoyl as the acyl substituent.

name: 2-methoxy-N-[3-oxo-3-(pyrrolidin-1-yl)propyl]acetamide
definition: A monocarboxylic acid amide that is acetamide substituted by a methoxy group at position 2 and a 3-oxo-3-(pyrrolidin-1-yl)propyl group at the nitrogen atom.

name: Phe-Tyr-Asp
definition: A tripeptide composed of L-phenylalanine, L-tyrosine and L-aspartic acid joined by peptide linkages.

name: O-(S-2-carboxyacylpantetheine-4'-phosphoryl)-L-serine(2-) residue
definition: An O-(S-pantetheine-4'-phosphoryl)-L-serine(2-) residue in which the S-acyl group is a  2-carboxyacyl.

name: O-(S-2-carboxyhexadecanoylpantetheine-4'-phosphoryl)-L-serine(2-) residue
definition: An O-(S-2-carboxyacylpantetheine-4'-phosphoryl)-L-serine(2-) residue in which the S-acyl group is specified as 2-carboxyhexadecanoyl.

name: ketoretinoic acid glucuronide
definition: Any retinoid obtained by the glycosylation of ketoretinoic acid with glucuronic acid.

name: O-(S-2-carboxytetradecanoylpantetheine-4'-phosphoryl)-L-serine(2-) residue
definition: An O-(S-2-carboxyacylpantetheine-4'-phosphoryl)-L-serine(2-) residue in which the S-acyl group is specified as 2-carboxytetradecanoyl.

name: 1-O-(4-oxoretinoyl)-beta-D-glucuronic acid
definition: A ketoretinoic glucuronide obtained by the glycosylation of the carboxy group of all-trans-4-oxoretinoic acid with beta-glucuronic acid.

name: O-(S-2-carboxydodecanoylpantetheine-4'-phosphoryl)-L-serine(2-) residue
definition: An O-(S-2-carboxyacylpantetheine-4'-phosphoryl)-L-serine(2-) residue in which the S-acyl group is specified as 2-carboxydodecanoyl.

name: O-heptenoylcarnitine
definition: An O-acylcarnitine that is the O-heptenoyl derivative of carnitine.

name: 4-(2-carboxyethyl)-7a-methyl-1-oxo-octahydro-1H-indene-5-carboxylic acid glucuronide
definition: A glucosiduronic acid derivative of 4-(2-carboxyethyl)-7a-methyl-1-oxo-octahydro-1H-indene-5-carboxylic acid.

name: L-isoleucine derivative
definition: A proteinogenic amino acid derivative resulting from reaction of L-isoleucine at the amino group or the carboxy group, or from the replacement of any hydrogen of L-isoleucine by a heteroatom.

name: triprolidine(1+)
definition: An ammonium ion resulting from the protonation of the pyrrolidine nitrogen of tripoloidine. It is the major species at pH 7.3.

name: ganglioside GM3
definition: A sialodiaosylceramide that is an alpha-N-acetylneuraminosyl-(2->3)-beta-D-galactosyl-(1->4)-beta-D-glucosyl-N-acylsphingosine in which the acyl group on nitrogen is (15Z)-tetracos-15-enoyl.

name: triprolidine hydrochloride (anh.)
definition: A hydrochloride resulting from the formal reaction of equimolar amounts of triprolidine and hydrogen chloride. Its monohydrate is used for the symptomatic relief of uticaria, rhinitis, and various pruritic skin disorders.

name: L-methionine derivative
definition: A proteinogenic amino acid derivative resulting from reaction of L-methionine  at the amino group or the carboxy group, or from the replacement of any hydrogen of L-methionine by a heteroatom.

name: D-methionine derivative
definition: A non-proteinogenic amino acid derivative resulting from reaction of D-methionine  at the amino group or the carboxy group, or from the replacement of any hydrogen of D-methionine  by a heteroatom.

name: advanced glycation end-product
definition: Carbohydrate derivatives resulting from the non-enzymatic glycosylation of proteins. They result in cells becoming stiffer and more prone to damage and premature aging.

name: D-tyrosine derivative
definition: A non-proteinogenic amino acid derivative resulting from reaction of D-tyrosine at the amino group or the carboxy group, or from the replacement of any hydrogen of D-tyrosine by a heteroatom.

name: globoside Gb4
definition: A glycotetraosylceramide in which a linear beta-D-GalNAc-(1->3)-alpha-D-Gal-(1->-4)-beta-D-Gal-(1->4)-beta-D-Glc tetrasaccharide unit is linked glycosidically to a (3R,4E)-3-hydroxy-2-(pentacosanoylamino)octadec-4-en-1-yl ceramide group.

name: 2-carboxyacyl-CoA
definition: An acyl-CoA that results from the formal condensation of the thiol group of coenzyme A with the carboxy group of any 1,1-dicarboxylic acid.

name: D-valine derivative
definition: A non-proteinogenic amino acid derivative resulting from reaction of D-valine at the amino group or the carboxy group, or from the replacement of any hydrogen of D-valine by a heteroatom.

name: O-(S-2-alkyl-3-oxoacylpantetheine-4'-phosphoryl)-L-serine residue
definition: An O-(pantetheine-4'-phosphoryl)-L-serine residue derivative in which the S-2-alkyl-3-oxoacyl group is the product of a Claisen-type condensation of an acyl and a 2-carboxyacyl chain.

name: O-(S-2-tetradecyl-3-oxooctadecanoylpantetheine-4'-phosphoryl)-L-serine(1-) residue
definition: An O-(S-2-alkyl-3-oxoacyl-pantetheine-4'-phosphoryl)-L-serine(1-) residue in which the S-2-alkyl-3-oxoacyl-group is specified as 2-tetradecyl-3-oxooctadecanoyl.

name: L-serine derivative
definition: A proteinogenic amino acid derivative resulting from reaction of L-serine at the amino group or the carboxy group, or from the replacement of any hydrogen of L-serine by a heteroatom.

name: O-(S-2-tetradecyl-3-oxohexadecanoylpantetheine-4'-phosphoryl)-L-serine(1-) residue
definition: An O-(S-2-alkyl-3-oxoacyl-pantetheine-4'-phosphoryl)-L-serine(1-) residue in which the S-2-alkyl-3-oxoacyl-group is specified as 2-tetradecyl-3-oxohexadecanoyl.

name: O-(S-2-tetradecyl-3-oxotetradecanoylpantetheine-4'-phosphoryl)-L-serine(1-) residue
definition: An O-(S-2-alkyl-3-oxoacyl-pantetheine-4'-phosphoryl)-L-serine(1-) residue in which the S-2-alkyl-3-oxoacyl-group is specified as 2-tetradecyl-3-oxotetradecanoyl.

name: myo-inositol phosphate(2-)
definition: An inositol phosphate oxoanion resulting from the removal of both of the protons from the phosphate group of a myo-inositol monophosphate.

name: myo-inositol monophosphate derivative
definition: Any myo-inositol monophosphate which has been derivatised.

name: 1D-myo-inositol 2-phosphate(2-)
definition: A myo-inositol phosphate(2-) obtained by deprotonation of the phosphate OH groups of 1D-myo-inositol 2-phosphate; major species at pH 7.3.

name: D-phenylalanine derivative
definition: A non-proteinogenic amino acid derivative resulting from reaction of D-phenylalanine at the amino group or the carboxy group, or from the replacement of any hydrogen of D-phenylalanine by a heteroatom.

name: 3beta-hydroxycholest-5-en-26-oate
definition: A steroid acid anion that is the conjugate base of 3beta-hydroxycholest-5-en-26-oic acid, obtained by deprotonation of the carboxy group; major species at pH 7.3.

name: alpha-D-ribose 5-triphosphate(4-)
definition: An organophosphate oxoanion resulting from the deprotonation of all four phosphate OH groups from alpha-D-ribose 1-triphosphate; it is the major species at pH 7.3.

name: 4-hydroxy-6-undecylpyran-2-one
definition: A 2-pyranone in which the hydrogens at positions 4 and 6 of 2H-pyran-2-one are replaced by hydroxy and undecyl groups respectively.

name: 4-hydroxy-6-(2-oxotridecyl)pyran-2-one
definition: A 2-pyranone in which the hydrogens at positions 4 and 6 of 2H-pyran-2-one are replaced by hydroxy and 2-oxotridecyl groups respectively.

name: 1-octadecanoyl-2-(6Z,9Z,12Z,15Z,18Z-docosapentaenoyl)-sn-glycero-3- phosphocholine
definition: A phosphatidylcholine 40:5 in which the acyl groups at C-1 and C-2 are octadecanoyl and (6Z,9Z,12Z,15Z,18Z)-docosapentaenoyl respectively.

name: 1-octadecanoyl-2-(3Z,6Z,9Z,12Z,15Z,18Z-docosahexaenoyl)-sn-glycero-3-phosphoserine
definition: A 3-sn-phosphatidyl-L-serine in which the phosphatidyl acyl groups at positions 1 and 2 are specified as octadecanoyl and (3Z,6Z,9Z,12Z,15Z,18Z)-docosahexaenoyl respectively.

name: 1-stearoyl-2-arachidonoyl-sn-glycero-3-phospho-1D-myo-inositol
definition: A 1-octadecanoyl-2-acyl-sn-glycero-3-phospho-1D-myo-inositol in which the 2-acyl group is specified as (5Z,8Z,11Z,14Z)-icosa-5,8,11,14-tetraenoyl (arachidonoyl).

name: sennosides
definition: A class of beta-D-glucosides of reductively-coupled dimers of hydroxyanthraquinones found particularly in senna (Cassia augustifolia) and rhubarb (Rheum rhabarbarum).

name: lauryl palmitoleate
definition: A wax ester obtained by the formal condensation of palmitoleic acid and lauryl (dodecyl) alcohol.

name: methyl palmitoleate
definition: A fatty acid methyl ester obtained from the formal condensation of methanol and palmitoleic acid.

name: alpha-D-Manp-(1->2)-alpha-D-Manp-(1->2)-alpha-D-Manp-(1->3)-[alpha-D-Manp-(1->6)]-alpha-D-Manp-(1->5)-alpha-Kdo
definition: A branched hexasaccharide comprised of five alpha-D-mannose residues linked as shown and also to a 3-deoxy-alpha-D-manno-oct-2-ulosonic acid (3-deoxy-D-manno-oct-2-ulosonic acid; Kdo) residue at the reducing end, corresponding to the core oligosaccharide of the phytopathogenic bacterium Rhizobacterium radiobacter strain Rv3.

name: 1-O-(alpha-D-galactopyranosyl)-N-tetradecanoylphytosphingosine
definition: A glycophytoceramide having an alpha-D-galactopyranosyl residue at the O-1 position and a tetradecanoyl group attached to the nitrogen.

name: 1-O-(alpha-D-galactopyranosyl)-N-dodecanoylphytosphingosine
definition: A glycophytoceramide having an alpha-D-galactopyranosyl residue at the O-1 position and a dodecanoyl group attached to the nitrogen.

name: 1-O-(alpha-D-galactosyl)-N-decanoylphytosphingosine
definition: A glycophytoceramide having an alpha-D-galactopyranosyl residue at the O-1 position and a decanoyl group attached to the nitrogen.

name: alpha-Gal glycan
definition: An amino glycan in which an alpha-Gal-(1->3)-beta-Gal-(1->4)-GlcNAc trisaccharide unit is linked glycosidically to a polysaccharide moiety.

name: (2E,6E)-farnesoic acid
definition: A farnesoic acid in which the double bonds at positions 2 and 6 both have E-configuration.

name: anthocyanidin 3-O-(6-O-malonyl-beta-D-glucoside) betaine
definition: An oxonium betaine obtained by deprotonation of the carboxy group of any anthocyanidin 3-O-(6-O-malonyl-beta-D-glucoside). It is the major microspecies at pH 7.3.

name: didecanoylphosphatidic acid
definition: A phosphatidic acid in which both of the phosphatidyl acyl groups are specified as decanoyl.

name: 1-stearoyl-2-arachidonoylphosphatidic acid
definition: A phosphatidic acid in which the acyl groups at positions 1 and 2 are specifed as stearoyl and arachidonoyl respectively.

name: 2-methoxy-6-all-trans-polyprenylhydroquinone
definition: A polyprenylhydroquinone in which the polyprenyl substituent is at C-2 with an additional methoxy group present at C-6.

name: 2-methoxy-3-methyl-6-all-trans-polyprenylhydroquinone
definition: A polyprenylhydroquinone in which the polyprenyl substituent is at C-2 together with additional methyl and methoxy groups present at C3 and C-6 respectively.

name: 4-hydroxy-6-pentadecylpyran-2-one
definition: A 2-pyranone in which the hydrogens at positions 4 and 6 of 2H-pyran-2-one are replaced by hydroxy and pentadecyl groups respectively.

name: 4-hydroxy-6-heptadecylpyran-2-one
definition: A 2-pyranone in which the hydrogens at positions 4 and 6 of 2H-pyran-2-one are replaced by hydroxy and heptadecyl groups respectively.

name: 4-hydroxy-6-nonadecylpyran-2-one
definition: A 2-pyranone in which the hydrogens at positions 4 and 6 of 2H-pyran-2-one are replaced by hydroxy and nonadecyl groups respectively.

name: 4-hydroxy-6-(2-oxoheptadecyl)pyran-2-one
definition: A 2-pyranone in which the hydrogens at positions 4 and 6 of 2H-pyran-2-one are replaced by hydroxy and 2-oxoheptadecyl groups respectively.

name: 4-hydroxy-6-(2-oxononadecyl)pyran-2-one
definition: A 2-pyranone in which the hydrogens at positions 4 and 6 of 2H-pyran-2-one are replaced by hydroxy and 2-oxononadecyl groups respectively.

name: 4-hydroxy-6-(2-oxohenicosyl)pyran-2-one
definition: A 2-pyranone in which the hydrogens at positions 4 and 6 of 2H-pyran-2-one are replaced by hydroxy and 2-oxohenicosyl groups respectively.

name: 12-HPE(8,10,14)TrE
definition: A hydroperoxy fatty acid that is (8Z,10E,14Z)-icosatrienoic acid in which the hydroperoxy group is located at position 12.

name: 2-methylhexadecanoate
definition: A 2-methyl fatty acid anion that is the conjugate base of 2-methylhexadecanoic acid, obtained by deprotonation of the carboxy group; major species at pH 7.3.

name: 12-methyloctadecanoate
definition: A methyl-branched fatty acid anion that is the conjugate base of 12-methyloctadecanoic acid, obtained by deprotonation of the carboxy group; major species at pH 7.3.

name: 14-HPDHE
definition: A hydroperoxy fatty acid that is (4Z,7Z,10Z,12E,16Z,19Z)-docosahexaenoic acid in which the hydroperoxy group is located at position 14.

name: 10-HPO(6,8,12)TrE
definition: A hydroperoxy fatty acid that is (6Z,8E,12Z)-octadecatrienoic acid in which the hydroperoxy group is located at position 10.

name: 12-methyloctadecanoyl-CoA(4-)
definition: A long-chain fatty acyl-CoA(4-) oxanion arising from deprotonation of the phosphate and diphosphate OH groups of 12-methyloctadecanoyl-CoA; major species at pH 7.3

name: 2-methylhexadecanoyl-CoA(4-)
definition: A long-chain fatty acyl-CoA(4-) oxanion arising from deprotonation of the phosphate and diphosphate OH groups of 2-methylhexadecanoyl-CoA; major species at pH 7.3

name: 3-methylundecanoyl-CoA(4-)
definition: A 3-methyl fatty acyl-CoA(4-) oxanion arising from deprotonation of the phosphate and diphosphate OH groups of 3-methylundecanoyl-CoA; major species at pH 7.3

name: 3-methylundecanoate
definition: A 3-methyl fatty acid anion that is the conjugate base of 3-methylundecanoic acid, obtained by deprotonation of the carboxy group; major species at pH 7.3.

name: D-proline derivative
definition: A non-proteinogenic amino acid derivative resulting from reaction of D-proline at the amino group or the carboxy group, or from the replacement of any hydrogen of D-proline by a heteroatom.

name: L-proline derivative
definition: A proteinogenic amino acid derivative resulting from reaction of L-proline at the amino group or the carboxy group, or from the replacement of any hydrogen of L-proline  by a heteroatom.

name: 2-epi-5-epi-valiolone
definition: A member of the class of cyclitols that is valiolone in which the stererocentres at positions 2 and 5 have been inverted.

name: D-threonine derivative
definition: A non-proteinogenic amino acid derivative resulting from reaction of D-threonine  at the amino group or the carboxy group, or from the replacement of any hydrogen of D-threonine  by a heteroatom.

name: L-threonine derivative
definition: A proteinogenic amino acid derivative resulting from reaction of L-threonine  at the amino group or the carboxy group, or from the replacement of any hydrogen of L-threonine  by a heteroatom.

name: D-galactaro-1,5-lactone
definition: An aldarolactone formed via intramolecular cyclocondensation of galactaric acid.

name: D-glucaro-1,5-lactone
definition: A glucarolactone formed via intramolecular cyclocondensation of the 5-hydroxy and 1-carboxy groups of D-glucaric acid.

name: teixobactin
definition: A cyclodepsipeptide that is isolated from the previously unculturable bacterial species Eleftheria terrae and is active against gram-positive bacteria.

name: isomyristate
definition: A methyl-branched fatty acid anion that is the conjugate base of 12-methyltridecanoic acid, obtained by deprotonation of the carboxy group; major species at pH 7.3.

name: hydroxytryptophan
definition: A hydroxy-amino acid that is tryptophan substituted by at least one hydroxy group at unspecified position.

name: isomyristoyl-CoA(4-)
definition: A long-chain fatty acyl-CoA(4-) oxanion arising from deprotonation of the phosphate and diphosphate OH groups of 12-methyltridecanoyl-CoA; major species at pH 7.3

name: 3-hydroxy fatty acid anion
definition: A hydroxy fatty acid anion obtained by deprotonation of the carboxy group of any 3-hydroxy fatty acid.

name: 3-hydroxytetradecanoate
definition: A 3-hydroxy fatty acid anion that is the conjugate base of 3-hydroxytetradecanoic acid, obtained by deprotonation of the carboxy group; major species at pH 7.3.

name: 3-hydroxytetradecanoyl-CoA(4-)
definition: A 3-hydroxy fatty acyl-CoA(4-) oxanion arising from deprotonation of the phosphate and diphosphate OH groups of 3-hydroxytetradecanoyl-CoA; major species at pH 7.3.

name: 12-hydroxyoctadecanoyl-CoA(4-)
definition: A long-chain fatty acyl-CoA(4-) arising from deprotonation of the phosphate and diphosphate OH groups of 12-hydroxyoctadecanoyl-CoA; major species at pH 7.3.

name: 15-hydroxypentadecanoate
definition: An omega-hydroxy-lon-chain fatty acid anion that is the conjugate base of 15-hydroxypentadecanoic acid, obtained by deprotonation of the carboxy group; major species at pH 7.3.

name: omega-hydroxy fatty acyl-CoA(4-)
definition: A fatty acyl-CoA(4-) arising from deprotonation of the phosphate and diphosphate OH groups of any omega-hydroxy fatty acyl-CoA; major species at pH 7.3.

name: 15-hydroxypentadecanoyl-CoA(4-)
definition: An omega-hydroxy fatty acyl-CoA(4-) arising from deprotonation of the phosphate and diphosphate OH groups of 15-hydroxypentadecanoyl-CoA; major species at pH 7.3.

name: 5-formyl-2-furoic acid
definition: A member of the class of furoic acids that is 2-furoic acid substituted at position 5 by a formyl group.

name: selenocysteine derivative
definition: An amino acid derivative resulting from reaction of selenocysteine at the amino group or the carboxy group, or from the replacement of any hydrogen of selenocysteine by a heteroatom. The definition normally excludes peptides containing selenocysteine residues.

name: L-selenocysteine derivative
definition: A proteinogenic amino acid derivative resulting from reaction of L-selenocysteine at the amino group or the carboxy group, or from the replacement of any hydrogen of L-selenocysteine by a heteroatom.

name: D-selenocysteine derivative
definition: A non-proteinogenic amino acid derivative resulting from reaction of D-selenocysteine at the amino group or the carboxy group, or from the replacement of any hydrogen of D-selenocysteine by a heteroatom.

name: 5-(dihydroxymethyl)-2-furoic acid
definition: A member of the class of furoic acids that is 2-furoic acid substituted at position 5 by a dihydroxymethyl group.

name: furan-2,5-dicarboxylic acid
definition: A member of the class of furans carrying two carboxy substituents at positions 2 and 5.

name: 4-(phosphooxymethyl)-2-furancarboxaldehyde
definition: A member of the class of furans that is 2-furfural substituted at position 4 by a phosphooxymethyl group.

name: 9-decenoyl-CoA(4-)
definition: An unsaturated fatty acyl-CoA(4-) arising from deprotonation of the phosphate and diphosphate OH groups of 9-decenoyl-CoA; major species at pH 7.3.

name: gamma-glutamyltyramine
definition: An L-glutamine derivative obtained by formal condensation of the side-chain carboxy group of glutamic acid with the amino group of tyramine.

name: (2R,3S)-2-methyl-3-propyloxirane
definition: An  epoxide that is oxirane substituted by a methyl and a propyl group at positions 2 and 3 respectively. Metabolite observed in cancer metabolism.

name: [5-(aminomethyl)-3-furyl]methyl phosphate
definition: A member of the class of furans that is 2-furylmethylamine substituted at position 4 by a phosphooxymethyl group.

name: (4E)-7-methyldec-4-ene
definition: An alkene that is (4E)-dec-4-ene with a methyl group at position 7. Metabolite observed in cancer metabolism.

name: 11-nitro-1-undecene
definition: A nitroalkene that is 1-undecene substituted by a nitro group at position 11.  Metabolite observed in cancer metabolism.

name: 1-docosene
definition: An alkene that is docosane with an unsaturation at position 1. Metabolite observed in cancer metabolism.

name: 1-ethyl-2-propylcyclohexane
definition: A cycloalkane that is cyclohexane substituted by an ethyl and a propyl group at positions 1 and 2 respectively. Metabolite observed in cancer metabolism.

name: 1-iodo-2-methylundecane
definition: An   iodoalkane that is undecane substituted by an iodo group at position 1 and a methyl group at position 2. Metabolite observed in cancer metabolism.

name: 4,6,8-trimethyl-1-nonene
definition: An alkene that is 1-nonene substituted by methyl groups at positions 4, 6 and 8 respectively. Metabolite observed in cancer metabolism.

name: 2-(4-methoxyphenyl)propan-2-ol
definition: A tertiary alcohol that is propan-2-ol substituted by a 4-methoxyphenyl group at position 2. Metabolite observed in cancer metabolism.

name: (3E)-2,3,4-trimethylhex-3-enal
definition: A  hexenal that is (3E)-hex-3-enal substituted by methyl groups at positions 2, 3 and 6. Metabolite observed in cancer metabolism.

name: 2,3,5,8-tetramethyldecane
definition: An alkane that is decane substituted by methyl groups at positions 2, 3, 5 and 8. Metabolite observed in cancer metabolism.

name: 2,4,4-trimethylpentane-1,3-diyl bis(2-methylpropanoate)
definition: A  diester obtained by the formal condensation of 2,4,4-trimethylpentane-1,3-diol with two molecules of 2-methylpropanoic acid. Metabolite observed in cancer metabolism.

name: 2,6,10,14-tetramethylheptadecane
definition: A long-chain alkane that is heptadecane substituted by methyl groups at positions 2, 6, 10 and 14. Metabolite observed in cancer metabolism.

name: 2,6,10,15-tetramethylheptadecane
definition: A long-chain alkane that is heptadecane substituted by methyl groups at positions 2, 6, 10 and 15. Metabolite observed in cancer metabolism.

name: (3E)-2,6-dimethyloct-3-ene
definition: An  alkene that is (3E)-oct-3-ene substituted by methyl groups at positions 2 and 6. Metabolite observed in cancer metabolism.

name: thienotriazolodiazepine
definition: Any organic heterotricyclic compound constructed from fused thiophene, triazole and diazepeine rings.

name: triethylene glycol monomethyl ether
definition: A hydroxypolyether that is the monomethyl ether derivative of triethylene glycol. Metabolite observed in cancer metabolism.

name: 2-butyl-1-octanol
definition: A primary alcohol that is 1-octanol substituted by a butyl group at position 2. Metabolite observed in cancer metabolism.

name: 2-methylbutan-2-amine
definition: A primary aliphatic amine that is butan-2-amine substituted by a methyl group at position 2. Metabolite observed in cancer metabolism.

name: 3,5-dimethyloctane
definition: An alkane that is  octane substituted by methyl groups at positions 3 and 5. Metabolite observed in cancer metabolism.

name: 1,2-dioctanoyl-sn-glycero-3-phospho-(1D-myo-inositol-3,4,5-trisphosphate)
definition: A 1-phosphatidyl-1D-myo-inositol 3,4,5-trisphosphate in which the phosphatidyl acyl groups at positions 1 and 2 are both specified as octanoyl.

name: 3,7,11-trimethyldodecan-1-ol
definition: A fatty alcohol that is 1-dodecanol substituted by methyl groups at positions 3, 7 and 11. Metabolite observed in cancer metabolism.

name: 1,2-dioctanoyl-sn-glycero-3-phospho-(1D-myo-inositol-3,4-bisphosphate)
definition: A 1-phosphatidyl-1D-myo-inositol 3,4-bisphosphate in which the phosphatidyl acyl groups at positions 1 and 2 are both specified as octanoyl.

name: 1,2-dioctanoyl-sn-glycero-3-phospho-(1D-myo-inositol-4,5-bisphosphate)
definition: A 1-phosphatidyl-1D-myo-inositol 4,5-bisphosphate in which the phosphatidyl acyl groups at positions 1 and 2 are both specified as octanoyl.

name: 3,7-dimethyl-3-octanol
definition: A fatty alcohol that is 3-octanol substituted by methyl groups at positions 3 and 7. Metabolite observed in cancer metabolism.

name: 3,8-dimethylundecane
definition: An alkane that is undecane substituted by methyl groups at positions 3 and 8. Metabolite observed in cancer metabolism.

name: 1,2-dihexadecanoyl-sn-glycero-3-phospho-(1D-myo-inositol-3,4,5-trisphosphate)
definition: A 1-phosphatidyl-1D-myo-inositol 3,4,5-trisphosphate in which the phosphatidyl acyl groups at positions 1 and 2 are both specified as hexadecanoyl (palmitoyl).

name: 2,4-dimethylpentan-3-amine
definition: A primary aliphatic amine that is pentan-3-amine substituted by methyl groups at positions 2 and 4. Metabolite observed in cancer metabolism.

name: 4-hydroxy-6-heptylpyran-2-one
definition: A 2-pyranone in which the hydrogens at positions 4 and 6 of 2H-pyran-2-one are replaced by hydroxy and heptyl groups respectively.

name: 1,2-dihexadecanoyl-sn-glycero-3-phospho-(1D-myo-inositol-3,4-bisphosphate)
definition: A 1-phosphatidyl-1D-myo-inositol 3,4-bisphosphate in which the phosphatidyl acyl groups at positions 1 and 2 are both specified as hexadecanoyl (palmitoyl).

name: pentan-3-amine
definition: A primary aliphatic amine that is pentane substituted by an amino group at position 3. Metabolite observed in cancer metabolism.

name: 4,6-dimethyldodecane
definition: An alkane that is  dodecane substituted by methyl groups at positions 4 and 6. Metabolite observed in cancer metabolism.

name: 4-methylundecane
definition: An alkane that is undecane substituted by a methyl group at position 4. Metabolite observed in cancer metabolism.

name: 1,2-dihexadecanoyl-sn-glycero-3-phospho-(1D-myo-inositol-4,5-bisphosphate)
definition: A 1-phosphatidyl-1D-myo-inositol 4,5-bisphosphate in which the phosphatidyl acyl groups at positions 1 and 2 are both specified as hexadecanoyl (palmitoyl).

name: 5-methyldec-1-ene
definition: An alkene that is dec-1-ene substituted by a methyl group at position 5. Metabolite observed in cancer metabolism.

name: 4-hydroxy-5-methyl-6-pentadecylpyran-2-one
definition: A 2-pyranone in which the hydrogens at positions 4, 5 and 6 of 2H-pyran-2-one are replaced by hydroxy, methyl and pentadecyl groups respectively.

name: N,N-dimethylacetamide
definition: A member of the class of  acetamides that is  acetamide in which the hydrogens attached to the N atom have been replaced by two methyl groups respectively. Metabolite observed in cancer metabolism.

name: 4-hydroxy-5-methyl-6-heptadecylpyran-2-one
definition: A 2-pyranone in which the hydrogens at positions 4, 5 and 6 of 2H-pyran-2-one are replaced by hydroxy, methyl and heptadecyl groups respectively.

name: methyl phenylglyoxalate
definition: The methyl ester of  phenylglyoxylic acid with methanol. Metabolite observed in cancer metabolism.

name: 3,6-anhydro-L-galactonic acid
definition: An anhydrohexose obtained by formation of a ring across the 3 and 6 positions of L-galactonic acid

name: D-prolinol
definition: The D-enantiomer of prolinol. Metabolite observed in cancer metabolism.

name: ethyl phenylglyoxylate
definition: The ethyl ester of phenylglyoxylic acid. Metabolite observed in cancer metabolism.

name: isobutyric acid anhydride
definition: An acyclic carboxylic anhydride of  isobutyric acid. Metabolite observed in cancer metabolism.

name: isopropyl palmitate
definition: A fatty acid ester obtained by the formal condensation of carboxy group of palmitic acid with  propan-2-ol. Metabolite observed in cancer metabolism.

name: 1,2-dihexadecanoyl-sn-glycero-3-phospho-(1D-myo-inositol-4-phosphate)
definition: A 1-phosphatidyl-1D-myo-inositol 4-phosphate in which the phosphatidyl acyl groups at positions 1 and 2 are both specified as hexadecanoyl (palmitoyl).

name: EC 3.5.1.19 (nicotinamidase) inhibitor
definition: An EC 3.5.1.* (non-peptide linear amide C-N hydrolase) inhibitor that interferes with the action of nicotinamidase (EC 3.5.1.19).

name: N(1)-isopropyl-2-methylpropan-1,2-diamine
definition: A primary aliphatic amine that is propan-1,2-diamine substituted by an isopropyl group at N(1) and a methyl group at position 2. Metabolite observed in cancer metabolism.

name: 1,2-ditetradecanoyl-sn-glycerol-3-phosphate
definition: A 1-acyl-2-tetradecanoyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphate in which the 1-acyl group is specified as tetradecanoyl (myristoyl).

name: N-methylbutan-2-amine
definition: A secondary aliphatic amine that is sec-butylamine substituted by a methyl group at the N atom. Metabolite observed in cancer metabolism.

name: nonanal
definition: A saturated fatty aldehyde formally arising from reduction of the carboxy group of nonanoic acid. Metabolite observed in cancer metabolism.

name: (2S)-2-methylheptadecanoate
definition: A 2-methyl fatty acid anion that is the conjugate base of (2S)-2-methyl-heptadecanoic acid, obtained by deprotonation of the carboxy group; major species at pH 7.3.

name: N-propylbenzamide
definition: A member of the class the class of benzamides that is benzamide substituted by a propyl group at the N atom. Metabolite observed in cancer metabolism.

name: allyl octadecyl oxalate
definition: A  diester obtained by the formal condensation of both the carboxy group of oxalic acid with the hydroxy groups of allyl alcohol and  stearyl alcohol respectively. Metabolite observed in cancer metabolism.

name: dodecamethylpentasiloxane
definition: An  organosiloxane that is pentasiloxane in which all the hydrogens have been replaced by methyl groups. Metabolite observed in cancer metabolism.

name: (2,3-diphenylcyclopropyl)methyl phenyl sulfoxide
definition: A sulfoxide in which the S atom is substituted by a phenyl and (2,3-diphenylcyclopropyl)methyl group. Metabolite observed in cancer metabolism.

name: (E)-dodec-2-enoate
definition: An unsaturated fatty acid anion that is the conjugate base of trans-2-dodecenoic acid obtained by deprotonation of the carboxy group; major species at pH 7.3.

name: trichloro(docosyl)silane
definition: An  organosilicon compound that is docosylsilane in which the hydrogens attached to the Si atom have been replaced by chloro groups. Metabolite observed in cancer metabolism.

name: methyl phenyl(piperidin-2-yl)acetate
definition: A amino acid ester that is methyl phenylacetate in which one of the hydrogens alpha to the carbonyl group is replaced by a piperidin-2-yl group.

name: 2-methyltridecane
definition: A long-chain alkane that is tridecane substituted by a methyl group at position 2. Metabolite observed in cancer metabolism.

name: 1,1,3,3-tetramethylurea
definition: A member of the class of ureas that is urea substituted by methyl groups at positions 1, 1, 3 and 3 respectively. Metabolite observed in cancer metabolism.

name: vinyl benzoate
definition: An  enoate ester obtained by the formal condensation of the carboxy group of benzoic acid with ethenol. Metabolite observed in cancer metabolism.

name: 2,7,10-trimethyldodecane
definition: An alkane that is dodecane substituted by methyl groups at positions 2, 7 and 10.

name: 2-isopropyl-5-methyl-1-heptanol
definition: A primary alcohol that is 1-heptanol substituted by an isopropyl group at position 2 and a methyl group at position 5.

name: 2-methyl-1,3-thiazolidine-2-carboxamide
definition: A  thiazolidinecarboxamide that is 1,3-thiazolidine-2-carboxamide substituted by a methyl group at position 2.

name: bis(2-methylundecan-2-yl) disulfide
definition: An organic disulfide that results from the formal oxidative dimerisation of 2-methylundecane-2-thiol.

name: tetradecan-2-ol
definition: A fatty alcohol that is tetradecane substituted by a hydroxy group at position 2.

name: 3-methoxy-3-methylhexane
definition: An ether consists of a hexane chain substituted by a methoxy and a methyl group at position 3.

name: 2-isopropylaminoethylamine
definition: A primary aliphatic amine that is ethane-1,2-diamine substituted by an isopropyl group at the N atom.

name: tetratetracontane
definition: A long-chain alkane consisting of an unbranched chain of 44 carbon atoms.

name: 2-(4-methyl-1-piperazinyl)ethanamine
definition: A N-alkylpiperazine that is piperazine substituted by a methyl and a 2-aminoethyl group at the N atoms respectively.

name: organic sulfur anion
definition: An organic anion in which the charge resides on a sulfur atom.

name: dithiocarbamate anions
definition: Any organic sulfur anion resulting from the removal of a proton from any N-substituted dithiocarbamic acid.

name: dimethyldithiocarbamate
definition: A member of the class of dithiocarbamate anions resulting from the removal of the proton from the dithiocarbamic acid moiety of dimethyldithiocarbamic acid. The major species at pH 7.3.

name: propylene 1,2-bis(dithiocarbamic acid)
definition: A member of the class or dithiocarbamic acids resulting from the formal addition of a molecule of carbon disulfide to each of the nitrogens of propylenediamine.

name: propylene 1,2-bis(dithiocarbamate)
definition: A member of the class of dithiocarbamate anions resulting from the deprotonation of both of the dithiocarbamic acid moieties of propylene 1,2-bis(dithiocarbamic acid). The major species at pH 7.3.

name: 2-S-cysteinyl-DOPA
definition: An L-tyrosine derivative that is L-DOPA in which the hydrogen at position 2 on the phenyl ring is replaced by a cysteinyl group. Found in the urine of patients with melanoma.

name: EC 3.4.21.64 (peptidase K) inhibitor
definition: An EC 3.4.21.* (serine endopeptidase) inhibitor that interferes with the action of peptidase K (EC 3.4.21.64).

name: 2,5-S,S'-dicysteinyldopa
definition: An L-tyrosine derivative that is L-DOPA in which the hydrogens at positions 2 and 5 on the phenyl ring are replaced by cysteinyl groups. Found in the urine of patients with melanoma.

name: 1-myristoyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphoethanolamine zwitterion
definition: A 1-acyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphoethanolamine zwitterion obtained by transfer of a proton from the amino to the phosphate group of 1-myristoyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphoethanolamine; major species at pH 7.3.

name: 1-myristoyl-2-oleoyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphoethanolamine zwitterion
definition: A phosphatidylethanolamine 32:1 zwitterion obtained by transfer of a proton from the amino to the phosphate group of 1-myristoyl-2-oleoyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphoethanolamine; major species at pH 7.3.

name: 7-(2-amino-2-carboxyethyl)-5-hydroxy-2H-1,4-benzothiazine-3-carboxylic acid
definition: A member of the class of benzothiazines that is 2H-1,4-benzothiazine-3-carboxylic acid bearing additional hydroxy and 2-amino-2-carboxyethyl substituents at positions 5 and 7 respectively.

name: trilinoleoyl 2-monolysocardiolipin
definition: A 2-monolysocardiolipin in which all three phosphatidyl acyl groups are specified as linoleoyl.

name: 2-carboxytetracosanoyl-CoA
definition: A 2-carboxyacyl-CoA that results from the formal condensation of the thiol group of coenzyme A with one of the the carboxy groups of 2-carboxytetracosanoic acid.

name: cholesteryl myristate
definition: A cholesterol ester obtained by the formal condensation of the hydroxy group of cholesterol with the carboxy group of myristic acid.

name: 2-carboxyhexacosanoyl-CoA
definition: A 2-carboxyacyl-CoA that results from the formal condensation of the thiol group of coenzyme A with one of the the carboxy groups of 2-carboxyhexacosanoic acid.

name: (13Z,16Z,19Z,22Z)-2-hydroxyoctacosatetraenoate
definition: A hydroxy fatty acid anion that is the conjugate base of (13Z,16Z,19Z,22Z)-2-hydroxyoctacosatetraenoic acid, obtained by deprotonation of the carboxy group; major species at pH 7.3.

name: (12Z,15Z,18Z,21Z,24Z)-2-hydroxytriacontapentaenoate
definition: A hydroxy fatty acid anion that is the conjugate base of (12Z,15Z,18Z,21Z,24Z)-2-hydroxytriacontapentaenoic acid, obtained by deprotonation of the carboxy group; major species at pH 7.3.

name: (14Z,17Z,20Z,23Z,26Z)-2-hydroxydotriacontapentaenoate
definition: A hydroxy fatty acid anion that is the conjugate base of (14Z,17Z,20Z,23Z,26Z)-2-hydroxydotriacontapentaenoic acid, obtained by deprotonation of the carboxy group; major species at pH 7.3.

name: rac-1-monooctanoylglycerol
definition: A rac-1-monoacylglycerol comprising equal amounts of 1-octanoyl-sn-glycerol and 3-octanoyl-sn-glycerol.

name: anticapsin zwitterion
definition: An L-alpha-amino acid zwitterion obtained by transfer of a proton from the carboxy to the amino group of anticapsin; major species at pH 7.3.

name: bacilysin zwitterion
definition: A peptide zwitterion obtained by transfer of a proton from the carboxy to the amino group of bacilysin; major species at pH 7.3.

name: dodecanoyl-AMP
definition: A fatty acyl-AMP that results from the formal condensation of the phosphoryl group of AMP with the carboxyl group of dodecanoic (lauric) acid.

name: 2-hydroxyoctacosanoate
definition: A 2-hydroxy fatty acid anion that is the conjugate base of 2-hydroxyoctacosanoic acid, obtained by deprotonation of the carboxy group; major species at pH 7.3.

name: oligomycin mixture
definition: Any mixture comprising two or more oligomycins.

name: L-arginyl-L-alpha-amino acid(1+)
definition: A dipeptide cation that is the conjugate base of any L-arginyl-L-alpha-amino acid; major species at pH 7.3.

name: 2-hydroxytricosanoate
definition: A 2-hydroxy fatty acid anion that is the conjugate base of 2-hydroxytricosanoic acid, obtained by deprotonation of the carboxy group; major species at pH 7.3.

name: 1-acyl-2-stearoyl-sn-glycero-3-phospho-(1D-myo-inositol)
definition: A 1-phosphatidyl-1D-myo-inositol which has a steroyl group as the acyl group at position 2.

name: cholesteryl pentadecanoate
definition: A cholesterol ester obtained by the formal condensation of  cholesterol with  pentadecanoic acid.

name: dapdiamide A zwitterion
definition: A peptide zwitterion obtained by transfer of a proton from the carboxy to the amino terminus of dapdiamide A; major species at pH 7.3.

name: dapdiamide B zwitterion
definition: A peptide zwitterion obtained by transfer of a proton from the carboxy to the amino terminus of dapdiamide B; major species at pH 7.3.

name: dapdiamide C zwitterion
definition: A peptide zwitterion obtained by transfer of a proton from the carboxy to the amino terminus of dapdiamide C; major species at pH 7.3.

name: cholesteryl palmitoleate
definition: A cholesterol ester obtained by the formal condensation of  cholesterol with palmitoleic acid.

name: 2-hydroxynervonate(1-)
definition: A 2-hydroxy fatty acid anion that is the conjugate base of 2-hydroxynervonic acid, obtained by deprotonation of the carboxy group; major species at pH 7.3.

name: 2-hydroxy fatty acid anion 24:1
definition: A 2-hydroxy fatty acid anion with a chain that is composed of 24 carbons and 1 double bond (position  unspecified).

name: cholesteryl heptadecanoate
definition: A cholesterol ester obtained by the formal condensation of  cholesterol with margaric acid.

name: torin 1
definition: A member of the class of pyridoquinolines that is 9-(quinolin-3-yl)benzo[h][1,6]naphthyridin-2-one bearing an additional 4-(4-propionylpiperazin-1-yl)-3-(trifluoromethyl)phenyl substituent at position 1. It is a potent inhibitor of mTOR and exhibits anti-cancer properties.

name: cholesteryl (9Z)-heptadecenoate
definition: A cholesterol ester obtained by the formal condensation of  cholesterol with cis-9-heptadecenoic acid.

name: N(3)-fumaroyl-(S)-2,3-diaminopropanoate
definition: An alpha-amino-acid anion that is the conjugate base of N(3)-fumaroyl-(S)-2,3-diaminopropanoic acid; major species at pH 7.3.

name: N(3)-fumaramoyl-(S)-2,3-diaminopropanoic acid zwitterion
definition: An L-alpha-amino acid zwitterion that results from the transfer of a proton from the carboxylic acid group to the alpha-amino group of N(3)-fumaramoyl-(S)-2,3-diaminopropanoic acid; major species at pH 7.3.

name: synthalin
definition: A hydrochloride resulting from the reaction of decamethylenediguanidine with 2 mol eq. of hydrogen chloride.

name: 2-hydroxymyristate
definition: A 2-hydroxy fatty acid anion that is the conjugate base of 2-hydroxymyristic acid, obtained by deprotonation of the carboxy group; major species at pH 7.3.

name: 2-hydroxyoctadecenoate
definition: A 2-hydroxy fatty acid anion with a chain that is composed of 18 carbons and 1 double bond (position unspecified).

name: synthalin A
definition: A member of the class of guanidines that is decane having guanidino groups at the 1- and 10-positions.

name: hydrazinocurcumin
definition: A pyrazole obtained by cyclocodensation of the two carbonyl groups of curcumin with hydrazine.

name: nogalaviketone(1-)
definition: A phenolate anion obtained by deprotonation of the 5-OH group of nogalaviketone. It is the major microspecies at pH 7.3 (according to Marvin v 6.2.0.).

name: 6-(2-amino-2-carboxyethyl)-4-hydroxybenzothiazole
definition: A member of the class of benzothiazoles bearing hydroxy and 2-amino-2-carboxyethyl substituents at positions 4 and 6 respectively.

name: 7-(2-amino-2-carboxyethyl)-5-hydroxy-3,4-dihydro-2H-1,4-benzothiazin-3-one
definition: A member of the class of benzothiazines that is 3,4-dihydro-2H-1,4-benzothiazin-3-one bearing additional hydroxy and 2-amino-2-carboxyethyl substituents at positions 5 and 7 respectively.

name: methyl nogalonate(1-)
definition: A phenolate anion resulting from the removal of a proton from the phenolic hydroxy group at position 5 of methyl nogalonate. The major species at pH 7.3.

name: cholesteryl all-cis-icosa-8,11,14-trienoate
definition: A cholesterol ester obtained by the formal condensation of  cholesterol with all-cis-icosa-8,11,14-trienoic acid.

name: 2-palmitoyl-3-stearoyl-2'-sulfo-alpha,alpha-trehalose(1-)
definition: An organosulfate oxoanion that is the conjugate base of 2-palmitoyl-3-stearoyl-2'-sulfo-alpha,alpha-trehalose arising from deprotonation of the sulfate OH group; major species at pH 7.3.

name: 2-palmitoyl-3,6,6'-tristearoyl-2'-sulfo-alpha,alpha-trehalose(1-)
definition: An organosulfate oxoanion that is the conjugate base of 2-palmitoyl-3,6,6'-tristearoyl-2'-sulfo-alpha,alpha-trehalose arising from deprotonation of the sulfate OH group; major species at pH 7.3.

name: 2-hydroxyicosenoate
definition: A 2-hydroxy fatty acid anion with a chain that is composed of 20 carbons and 1 double bond (position unspecified).

name: 2-hydroxydocosenoate
definition: A 2-hydroxy fatty acid anion with a chain that is composed of 22 carbons and 1 double bond (position unspecified).

name: cholesteryl behenate
definition: A cholesterol ester obtained by the formal condensation of  cholesterol with  behenic acid.

name: 2',3'-dipalmitoyl-2-sulfo-alpha,alpha-trehalose(1-)
definition: An organosulfate oxoanion that is the conjugate base of 2',3'-dipalmitoyl-2-sulfo-alpha,alpha-trehalose arising from deprotonation of the sulfate OH group; major species at pH 7.3.

name: (4R)-3,4-dihydro-4-hydroxyphenylpyruvate
definition: A 3,4-dihydro-4-hydroxyphenylpyruvate having R-configuration.

name: 3-[(1E,4R)-4-hydroxycyclohex-2-en-1-ylidene]pyruvate
definition: 3-(4-hydroxycyclohex-2-en-1-ylidene)pyruvate obtained by deprotonation of the carboxy group of 3-[(1E,4R)-4-hydroxycyclohex-2-en-1-ylidene]pyruvic acid; major species at pH 7.3.

name: (3E)-3-[(1R,5R,6S)-5-hydroxy-7-oxabicyclo[4.1.0]heptan-2-ylidene]pyruvate
definition: A 2-oxo monocarboxylic acid anion that is the conjugate base of (3E)-3-[(1R,5R,6S)-5-hydroxy-7-oxabicyclo[4.1.0]heptan-2-ylidene]pyruvic acid, obtained by deprotonation of the carboxy group.

name: 3-[(1R,2S,5R,6S)-5-hydroxy-7-oxabicyclo[4.1.0]heptan-2-yl]pyruvate
definition: A 2-oxo monocarboxylic acid anion that is the conjugate base of 3-[(1R,2S,5R,6S)-5-hydroxy-7-oxabicyclo[4.1.0]heptan-2-yl]pyruvic acid, obtained by deprotonation of the carboxy group; major species at pH 7.3.

name: L-dihydroanticapsin zwitterion
definition: An L-alpha-amino acid zwitterion obtained by transfer of a proton from the carboxy to the amino group of L-dihydroanticapsin; major species at pH 7.3.

name: 3-hydroxy-2,4-dioxopentyl phosphate(2-)
definition: An organophosphate oxoanion obtained by deprotonation of the phosphate OH groups of 3-hydroxy-2,4-pentanedione 5-phosphate; major species at pH 7.3.

name: cetoniacytone A
definition: A member of the class of cyclohexenones that is (1R,5S,6R)-4-amino-5-hydroxy-1-(hydroxymethyl)-7-oxabicyclo[4.1.0]hept-3-en-2-one in which one of the amino hydrogens is replaced by an acetyl group.

name: 2-epi-5-epi-valiolone 7-phosphate(2-)
definition: An organophosphate oxoanion obtained by deprotonation of the phosphate OH groups of 2-epi-5-epi-valiolone 7-phosphate; major species at pH 7.3.

name: acarbose(1+)
definition: An organic cation obtained by protonation of the secondary amino group of acarbose; major species at pH 7.3.

name: cladoniamide derivative
definition: Any organic heteropolycyclic compound that is derived from a cladoniamide.

name: cladoniamide A
definition: An organic heterohexacyclic compound that is cladoniamide B in which the chlorine attached to the methoxy-bearing indole moiety is replaced by a hydrogen. It has been isolated from the culture broth of Streptomyces uncialis.

name: cladoniamide B
definition: 8a,13-dihydrobenzo[2,3]pyrrolo[3',4':5,6]indolizino[8,7-b]indole-6,8(5aH,7H)-dione which is substituted by chlorines at positions 2 and 10, hydroxy groups at positions 5a and 8a, a methoxy group at position 14, and a methyl group at position 7 (the 5aR,8aS diastereoisomer). It has been isolated from the culture broth of Streptomyces uncialis.

name: cladoniamide C
definition: An organic heterohexacyclic compound that is cladoniamide B in which both of the chlorines are replaced by hydrogen. It has been isolated from the culture broth of Streptomyces uncialis.

name: cladoniamide D
definition: An organic heteropentacyclic compound that is cladoniamide E in which the chlorine attached to the methoxy-bearing indole moiety is replaced by a hydrogen. It has been isolated from the culture broth of Streptomyces uncialis.

name: cladoniamide E
definition: An organic heteropentacyclic compound that is 7,12-dihydro-6H-pyrido[1,2-a:3,4-b']diindole substituted by chloro groups at positions 2 and 9, a hydroxy group and an N-methyl carbamyl group at position 6, a methoxy group at position 13, and an oxo group at position 7 (the 6R stereoisomer). It is isolated from the culture broth of Streptomyces uncialis.

name: cladoniamide F
definition: An organic heteropentacyclic compound that is cladoniamide G in which the chlorine attached to the methoxy-bearing indole moiety is replaced by a hydrogen. It has been isolated from the culture broth of Streptomyces uncialis.

name: N-tricosanoylsphingosine
definition: A N-acylsphingosine in which the ceramide N-acyl group is specified as tricosanoyl.

name: chitotriose
definition: An amino trisaccharide comprising of three 2-amino-2-deoxy-D-glucopyranose units joined by beta-(1->4) linkages.

name: 3-ammonio-L-alanine(1+)
definition: An alpha-amino-acid cation that is the conjugate acid of 3-amino-L-alanine.

name: N-(17Z-hexacosenoyl)sphingosine
definition: A N-acylsphingosine in which the ceramide N-acyl group is specified as (17Z)-hexacosenoyl.

name: pentacosanoate
