definition: A straight-chain saturated fatty acid anion that is the conjugate base of pentacosanoic acid, obtained by deprotonation of the carboxy group; major species at pH 7.3.

name: pentacosenoate
definition: A monounsaturated fatty acid anion with a chain that is composed of 25 carbons and 1 double bond (position unspecified).

name: 2-hydroxypentacosenoate
definition: A 2-hydroxy fatty acid anion with a chain that is composed of 25 carbons and 1 double bond (position unspecified).

name: chondramide B
definition: A chondramide that is chondramide A in which the hydrogen at position 2 of the indole moiety has been replaced by a chlorine. It is produced by strains of the myxobacterium, Chondromyces crocatus.

name: chondramide D
definition: A chondramide that is chondramide C in which the hydrogen at position 2 of the indole moiety is replaced by a chlorine.  It is produced by strains of the myxobacterium, Chondromyces crocatus.

name: chondramide
definition: Any of the 18-membered ring cyclodepsipeptides produced by strains of the myxobacterium, Chondromyces crocatus.

name: 1-myristoyl-2-palmitoyl-sn-glycerol
definition: A 1,2-diacyl-sn-glycerol that has myristoyl and palmitoyl as 1- and 2-acyl groups respectively.

name: 1-myristoyl-2-palmitoleoyl-sn-glycerol
definition: A 1,2-diacyl-sn-glycerol with myristoyl and palmitoleoyl as 1- and 2-acyl groups respectively.

name: (1s,4s)-prephenic acid
definition: A prephenic acid having (1s,4s)-cis-configuration.

name: 2-hydroxyhexacosenoate
definition: A 2-hydroxy fatty acid anion with a chain that is composed of 26 carbons and 1 double bond (position unspecified).

name: 2-hydroxyhexacosadienoate
definition: A 2-hydroxy fatty acid anion with a chain that is composed of 26 carbons and 2 double bond (positions unspecified).

name: hexacosadienoate
definition: A very long-chain fatty acid anion with a chain that is composed of 26 carbons and 2 double bond (positions unspecified).

name: tetracosadienoate
definition: A polyunsaturated fatty acid anion composed of 24 carbons with 2 double bonds in unknown positions.

name: 1-myristoyl-2-linoleoyl-sn-glycerol
definition: A 1,2-diacyl-sn-glycerol that has myristoyl and linoleoyl as 1- and 2-acyl groups respectively.

name: 2-hydroxytetracosadienoate
definition: A 2-hydroxy fatty acid anion with a chain that is composed of 24 carbons and 2 double bond (positions unspecified).

name: 1-palmitoyl-2-palmitoleoyl-sn-glycerol
definition: A 1,2-diacyl-sn-glycerol that has palmitoyl and palmitoleoyl as 1- and 2-acyl groups respectively.

name: amylodextrin
definition: A linear dextrin or short chained amylose (DP 20-30) that can be produced by enzymatic hydrolysis of the alpha-1,6 glycosidic bonds or debranching amylopectin.

name: chondramide derivative
definition: Any cyclodepsipeptide that is a derivative of a chondramide.

name: 1,1',2-trilinoleoyl-2'-oleoyl cardiolipin
definition: A cardiolipin in which the phosphatidyl acyl groups at positions 1, 1' and 2 are specified as linoleoyl, while that at position 2' is specified as oleoyl.

name: 1,1',2-trilinoleoyl-2'-palmitoyl cardiolipin
definition: A cardiolipin in which the phosphatidyl acyl groups at positions 1, 1' and 2 are specified as linoleoyl, while that at position 2' is specified as palmitoyl.

name: 1-palmitoyl-2-(11Z,14Z-eicosadienoyl)-sn-glycerol
definition: A 1,2-diacyl-sn-glycerol in which the 1- and 2-acyl groups are specified as palmitoyl and (11Z,14Z)-eicosadienoyl respectively.

name: 1-palmitoyl-2-(8Z,11Z,14Z-eicosatrienoyl)-sn-glycerol
definition: A 1,2-diacyl-sn-glycerol in which the 1- and 2-acyl groups are specified as palmitoyl and (8Z,11Z,14Z-eicosatrienoyl respectively.

name: phytoceramides
definition: A phytoceramide is a ceramide where the sphingoid base is hydroxylated at position 4. These backbone bases can be 14 to 20 carbons long, either straight chain or branched. The N-linked fatty acids are typically saturated or monounsaturated with chain lengths from 14 to 26 carbon atoms; the presence of a hydroxyl group on carbon 2 is fairly common. In the illustrated generalised structure, R1 = OH, OX (where X = acyl, glycosyl, phosphate, phosphonate, etc.), or H.

name: ceramide 1-phosphate(2-)
definition: An organophosphate oxoanion obtained by deprotonation of the phosphate OH groups of any ceramide 1-phosphate.

name: 1-palmitoyl-2-(7Z,10Z,13Z,16Z-docosatetraenoyl)-sn-glycerol
definition: A 1,2-diacyl-sn-glycerol in which the 1- and 2-acyl groups are specified as palmitoyl and (7Z,10Z,13Z,16Z)-docosatetraenoyl  respectively.

name: sphingoid base(1+)
definition: A cationic sphingoid obtained by protonation of the amino group of any 2-amino-1,3-dihydroxysphingoid base.

name: 3-dehydrosphingoid base(1+)
definition: A cationic sphingoid obtained by protonation of the amino group of any 3-dehydrosphingoid base. Major species at pH 7.3.

name: tetradecanoyl-AMP
definition: A fatty acyl-AMP that results from the formal condensation of the phosphoryl group of AMP with the carboxyl group of tetradecanoic (myristic) acid.

name: cleistanthin derivative
definition: Any glycoside that is a derivative of a cleistanthin.

name: hexadecanoyl-AMP
definition: A fatty acyl-AMP that results from the formal condensation of the phosphoryl group of AMP with the carboxyl group of hexadecanoic (palmitic) acid.

name: acetyltaurine
definition: An amino sulfonic acid that is taurine substituted by an acetyl group at the N atom.

name: cleistanthin E
definition: A member of the class of cleistanthins that is cleistanthin C in which the hydroxy group at position 4 of the 2,3-di-O-methyl-beta-D-xylopyranosyl moiety has been converted to the corresponding 2,3,5-tri-O-methyl-D-xylofuranoside.

name: 1,2-di-palmitoleoyl-2-sn-glycerol
definition: A 1,2-diacyl-sn-glycerol in which the 1- and 2-acyl groups are specified as palmitoleoyl.

name: 1-palmitoleoyl-2-stearoyl-sn-glycerol
definition: A 1,2-diacyl-sn-glycerol in which the 1- and 2-acyl groups are specified as palmitoleoyl and stearoyl respectively.

name: 1-palmitoleoyl-2-linoleoyl-sn-glycerol
definition: A 1,2-diacyl-sn-glycerol in which the 1- and 2-acyl groups are specified as palmitoleoyl and linoleoyl respectively.

name: 3-demethylubiquinol
definition: A polyprenylhydroquinone having the structure of a ubiquinol with hydroxy replacing methoxy at C-5.

name: 3-demethylubiquinol-9
definition: A 3-demethylubiquinol in which the polyprenyl chain contains 9 prenyl units.

name: ubiquinol-9
definition: A ubiquinol in which the polyprenyl substituent is nonaprenyl.

name: 9-PAHSA
definition: A FAHFA (fatty acid ester of a hydroxy fatty acid) obtained by formal condensation of the carboxy group of palmitic acid with the hydroxy group of 9-hydroxyoctadecanoic acid (9-hydroxystearic acid).

name: FAHFA
definition: A fatty acid ester obtained by formal condensation of the carboxy group of any fatty acid with the hydroxy group of any hydroxy fatty acid.

name: 1-heptadecanoyl-2-lauroyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphate(2-)
definition: A 1,2-diacyl-sn-glycerol 3-phosphate(2-) in which the phosphatidyl acyl groups at postions 1 and 2 are specified as heptadecanoyl and lauroyl respectively.

name: 1-heptadecanoyl-2-myristoyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphate(2-)
definition: A 1,2-diacyl-sn-glycerol 3-phosphate(2-) in which the phosphatidyl acyl groups at postions 1 and 2 are specified as heptadecanoyl and myristoyl respectively.

name: 1-heptadecanoyl-2-stearoyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphate(2-)
definition: A 1,2-diacyl-sn-glycerol 3-phosphate(2-) in which the phosphatidyl acyl groups at postions 1 and 2 are specified as heptadecanoyl and stearoyl respectively.

name: 1-heptadecanoyl-2-palmitoyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphate(2-)
definition: A 1,2-diacyl-sn-glycerol 3-phosphate(2-) in which the phosphatidyl acyl groups at postions 1 and 2 are specified as heptadecanoyl and palmitoyl respectively.

name: 3-demethylubiquinol-7
definition: A 3-demethylubiquinol in which the polyprenyl chain contains 7 prenyl units.

name: ubiquinol-7
definition: A ubiquinol in which the polyprenyl substituent is heptaprenyl.

name: 1-stearoyl-2-(8Z,11Z,14Z-icosa-8,11,14-trienoyl)-sn-glycerol
definition: A 1,2-diacyl-sn-glycerol in which the acyl groups at positions 1 and 2 are specified as stearoyl and 8Z,11Z,14Z-icosa-8,11,14-trienoyl respectively.

name: 5'-GACCCCUG-3' RNA fragment
definition: An RNA fragment comprised of two guanosine, one adenosine, one uridine and four cytidine residues connected by 3'->5' phosphodiester linkages in the sequence G-A-C-C-C-C-U-G.

name: 1-stearoyl-2-(7Z,10Z,13Z,16Z-docosatetraenoyl)-sn-glycerol
definition: A 1,2-diacyl-sn-glycerol in which the acyl groups at positions 1 and 2 are specified as stearoyl and 7Z,10Z,13Z,16Z-docosatetraenoyl respectively.

name: 1-oleoyl-2-gondoyl-sn-glycerol
definition: A 1,2-diacyl-sn-glycerol in which the acyl groups at positions 1 and 2 are specified as oleoyl and gondoyl respectively.

name: 1-oleoyl-2-(8Z,11Z,14Z-eicosatrienoyl)-sn-glycerol
definition: A 1,2-diacyl-sn-glycerol in which the acyl groups at positions 1 and 2 are specified as oleoyl and 8Z,11Z,14Z-eicosatrienoyl respectively.

name: 1-oleoyl-2-(7Z,10Z,13Z,16Z-docosatetraenoyl)-sn-glycerol
definition: A 1,2-diacyl-sn-glycerol in which the acyl groups at positions 1 and 2 are specified as oleoyl and 7Z,10Z,13Z,16Z-docosatetraenoyl respectively.

name: 1-oleoyl-2-(4Z,7Z,10Z,13Z,16Z,19Z-docosahexaenoyl)-sn-glycerol
definition: A 1,2-diacyl-sn-glycerol in which the acyl groups at positions 1 and 2 are specified as oleoyl and 4Z,7Z,10Z,13Z,16Z,19Z-docosahexaenoyl respectively.

name: 1,2-di-(7Z,10Z,13Z,16Z-docosatetraenoyl)-sn-glycerol
definition: A 1,2-diacyl-sn-glycerol in which the acyl groups at positions 1 and 2 are specified as 7Z,10Z,13Z,16Z-docosatetraenoyl.

name: 3-methoxy-4-hydroxy-5-all-trans-polyprenylbenzoic acid
definition: A monohydroxybenzoic acid that is 4-hydroxybenzoic acid substituted with a methoxy group at C-3 and a polyprenyl chain of unspecified length at C-5.

name: 3-methoxy-4-hydroxy-5-all-trans-polyprenylbenzoate
definition: The hydroxybenzoate anion formed by loss of a proton from the carboxy group of 3-methoxy-4-hydroxy-5-all-trans-polyprenylbenzoic acid. The major species present at pH 7.3.

name: thromboxane B3
definition: A member of the class of thromboxanes B that is (5Z,13E,17Z)-thromboxa-5,13,17-trien-1-oic acid substituted by hydroxy groups at positions 9, 11 and 15.

name: N-acylheptadecasphingosine
definition: Any ceramide where the sphingoid component is specified as heptadecasphingosine.

name: 3,4-dihydroxy-5-all-trans-heptaprenylbenzoic acid
definition: A dihydroxybenzoic acid where the hydroxy groups are at the 4- and 5-positions together with a heptaprenyl group at the 3-position.

name: (5Z,8Z,10E,14Z)-12-hydroxyicosatetraenoic acid
definition: The (5Z,8Z,10E,14Z)-stereoisomer of 12-HETE.

name: 1-(1-methylpyrrolidin-2-yl)acetone
definition: A methyl ketone that is acetone in which one of the hydrogens is replaced by a 1-methylpyrrolidin-2-yl group.

name: rac-hygrine
definition: A racemate comprising equimolar amounts of hygrine and (--hygrine.

name: 3,4-dihydroxy-5-all-trans-heptaprenylbenzoate
definition: A 3,4-dihydroxy-5-polyprenylbenzoate in which the polyprenyl chain contains 7 prenyl units; major species at pH 7.3.

name: 3,4-dihydroxy-5-all-trans-octaprenylbenzoic acid
definition: A dihydroxybenzoic acid where the hydroxy groups are at the 4- and 5-positions together with a octaprenyl group at the 3-position.

name: 3,4-dihydroxy-5-all-trans-octaprenylbenzoate
definition: A 3,4-dihydroxy-5-polyprenylbenzoate in which the polyprenyl chain contains 8 prenyl units; major species at pH 7.3.

name: 3-methoxy-4-hydroxy-5-all-trans-heptaprenylbenzoic acid
definition: A 3-methoxy-4-hydroxy-5-all-trans-polyprenylbenzoic acid in which the polyprenyl component is specified as heptaprenyl.

name: 3-methoxy-4-hydroxy-5-all-trans-heptaprenylbenzoate
definition: A 3-methoxy-4-hydroxy-5-all-trans-polyprenylbenzoate in which the polyprenyl component is specified as heptaprenyl.

name: 3-methoxy-4-hydroxy-5-all-trans-octaprenylbenzoic acid
definition: A 3-methoxy-4-hydroxy-5-all-trans-polyprenylbenzoic acid in which the polyprenyl component is specified as octaprenyl.

name: 3-methoxy-4-hydroxy-5-all-trans-octaprenylbenzoate
definition: A 3-methoxy-4-hydroxy-5-all-trans-polyprenylbenzoate in which the polyprenyl component is specified as octaprenyl.

name: 5-PAHSA
definition: A FAHFA obtained by formal condensation of the carboxy group of palmitic acid with the hydroxy group of 5-hydroxystearic acid.

name: 1-oleoyl-2,3-di-linoleoyl-sn-glycerol
definition: A  triacyl-sn-glycerol in which the acyl groups at positions 1, 2 and 3 are specified as oleoyl, linoleoyl and linoleoyl respectively.

name: 3-oxo-N-[(3S)-2-oxotetrahydrofuran-3-yl]tetradecanamide
definition: A monocarboxylic acid amide that is tetradecanamide substituted by an oxo group at position 3 and a (3S)-2-oxotetrahydrofuran-3-yl group at the N atom.

name: 10-PAHSA
definition: A FAHFA obtained by formal condensation of the carboxy group of palmitic acid with the hydroxy group of 10-hydroxystearic acid.

name: 1-heptadecanoyl-2-arachidonoyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphoserine(1-)
definition: A 3-sn-phosphatidyl-L-serine(1-) that is the conjugate base of 1-heptadecanoyl-2-arachidonoyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphoserine; major species at pH 7.3.

name: 1-heptadecanoyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphoserine(1-)
definition: A 1-acyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphoserine(1-) that is the conjugate base of 1-heptadecanoyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphoserine; major species at pH 7.3.

name: 11-PAHSA
definition: A FAHFA obtained by formal condensation of the carboxy group of palmitic acid with the hydroxy group of 11-hydroxystearic acid.

name: 1-stearoyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphoserine(1-)
definition: A 1-acyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphoserine(1-) that is the conjugate base of 1-stearoyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphoserine; major species at pH 7.3.

name: 12-PAHSA
definition: A FAHFA obtained by formal condensation of the carboxy group of palmitic acid with the hydroxy group of 12-hydroxystearic acid.

name: 13-PAHSA
definition: A FAHFA obtained by formal condensation of the carboxy group of palmitic acid with the hydroxy group of 13-hydroxystearic acid.

name: 1-heptadecanoyl-2-arachidonoyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphocholine
definition: A phosphatidylcholine 37:4 in which the acyl substituents at positions 1 and 2 are specified as heptadecanoyl and arachidonoyl respectively.

name: 1-palmitoyl-2-oleoyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphoglycerol(1-)
definition: A phosphatidylglycerol(1-) that is the conjugate base of 1-palmitoyl-2-oleoyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphoglycerol obtained by deprotonation of the phosphate OH group; major species at pH 7.3.

name: 1-alkyl-2-methyl-sn-glycerol
definition: An alkylglycerol that is any 1-alkyl-sn-glycerol bearing an additional methyl substituent at position 2.

name: 1-alkyl-2-methyl-3-acyl-sn-glycerol
definition: A glycerol ether that is any 1-alkyl-3-acyl-sn-glycerol bearing an additional methyl substituent at position 2.

name: 1-palmitoyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphoglycerol(1-)
definition: A 1-acylglycero-3-phospho-1'-glycerol(1-) in which the 1-acyl substituent is specified as hexadecanoyl; major species at pH 7.3.

name: N-(17Z-hexacosenoyl)-sphingosine-1-phosphocholine
definition: A N-hexacosenoylsphingosine-1-phosphocholine consisting of sphingosine as the sphingoid base acylated at the N atom by a (17Z)-hexacosenoyl group.

name: 5'-CGAAAGUCCGAUCGGCGUAAUGUCA-3' RNA fragment
definition: An RNA fragment comprised of six cytidine, seven guanosine, seven adenosine and five uridine residues connected by 3'->5' phosphodiester linkages in the sequence C-G-A-A-A-G-U-C-C-G-A-U-C-G-G-C-G-U-A-A-U-G-U-C-A.

name: N,O-diacylethanolamine
definition: Any carboxamide obtained by acylation of both the amino and hydroxy functions of ethanolamine.

name: 5'-GUUUGGCGACGUCCCACAUGAGCC-3' RNA fragment
definition: An RNA fragment comprised of seven guanosine, five uridine, eight cytidine and four adenosine residues connected by 3'->5' phosphodiester linkages in the sequence G-U-U-U-G-G-C-G-A-C-G-U-C-C-C-A-C-A-U-G-A-G-C-C.

name: 1-O-acyl-N-acetylsphingosine
definition: Any 1-O-acyl-N-acylsphingosine in which the N-acyl group is specified as acetyl.

name: N-nonadecanoylsphingosine-1-phosphocholine
definition: A sphingomyelin d18:1 in whihc the acyl group specified is nonadecanoyl.

name: 8-PAHSA
definition: A FAHFA obtained by formal condensation of the carboxy group of palmitic acid with the hydroxy group of 8-hydroxystearic acid.

name: N-oleoylsphingosine-1-phosphocholine
definition: A N-octadecenolsphingosine-1-phosphocholine in which the acyl group specified is 9Z-octadecenoyl.

name: N-heptadecanoylsphingosine-1-phosphocholine
definition: A sphingomyelin d18:1 in which the acyl group specified is heptadecanoyl.

name: 1-heptadecanoyl-2-arachidonoyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphoethanolamine zwitterion
definition: A 1,2-diacyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphoethanolamine zwitterion in which the acyl groups at positions 1 and 2 are specified as heptadecanoyl and arachidonoyl respectively.

name: 1-heptadecanoyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphoethanolamine zwitterion
definition: A 1-acyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphoethanolamine zwitterion obtained by transfer of a proton from the amino to the phosphate group of 1-heptadecanoyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphoethanolamine; major species at pH 7.3.

name: poly(I:C)
definition: A mismatched double-stranded RNA with one strand being a polymer of inosinic acid, the other a polymer of cytidylic acid.

name: 4-hydroxy-3-all-trans-hexaprenylbenzoate
definition: A 4-hydroxy-3-polyprenylbenzoate in which the polyprenyl chain contains 6 prenyl units; major species at pH 7.3.

name: (omega-1)-ethyl fatty acid anion
definition: A fatty acid anion where the last 2 carbons (omega and omega-1) form an ethyl end. Formula:C3H5O2R

name: 4-hydroxy-3-all-trans-heptaprenylbenzoic acid
definition: A monohydroxybenzoic acid that is 4-hydroxybenzoic acid substituted at position 3 by a heptaprenyl group.

name: N-tetracosanoylsphinganine-1-phosphocholine
definition: A N-acylsphinganine-1-phosphocholine in which the acyl group specified is tetracosanoyl.

name: 4-hydroxy-3-all-trans-heptaprenylbenzoate
definition: A 4-hydroxy-3-polyprenylbenzoate in which the polyprenyl chain contains 7 prenyl units; major species at pH 7.3.

name: (omega-1)-hydroxy fatty acid anion
definition: A hydroxy fatty acid anion obtained by deprotonation of the carboxy group of any (omega-1)-hydroxy fatty acid; major species at pH 7.3.

name: varenicline
definition: An organic heterotetracyclic compound that acts as a partial agonist for nicotinic cholinergic receptors and is used (in the form of its tartate salt) as an aid to giving up smoking.

name: 4-hydroxy-3-all-trans-nonaprenylbenzoic acid
definition: A monohydroxybenzoic acid that is 4-hydroxybenzoic acid substituted at position 3 by a nonaprenyl group.

name: 4-hydroxy-3-all-trans-nonaprenylbenzoate
definition: A 4-hydroxy-3-polyprenylbenzoate in which the polyprenyl chain contains 9 prenyl units; major species at pH 7.3.

name: hexadecasphing-4-enine-1-phosphate
definition: A sphingoid 1-phosphate that is hexadecasphing-4-enine substituted by a phospho group at position 1.

name: varenicline tartrate
definition: A tartrate salt obtained by reaction of varenicline with one equivalent of (R,R)-tartaric acid. A partial agonist for nicotinic cholinergic receptors, it is used as an aid to giving up smoking.

name: varenicline(1+)
definition: An organic cation obtained by protonation of the secondary amino group of varenicline.

name: 2-all-trans-heptaprenylphenol
definition: A member of the class of 2-polyprenylphenol in which the polyprenyl component is specified as heptaprenyl.

name: 2-all-trans-decaprenylphenol
definition: A member of the class of 2-polyprenylphenol in which the polyprenyl component is specified as decaprenyl.

name: 1-stearoyl-2-(8Z,11Z,14Z-icosatrienoyl)-sn-glycero-3-phosphoserine
definition: A 3-sn-phosphatidyl L-serine in which the phosphatidyl acyl groups at positions 1 and 2 are stearoyl and (8Z,11Z,14Z)-eicosatrienoyl group respectively.

name: 1-stearoyl-2-linoleoyl-sn-glycero-3-phospho-L-serine
definition: A 3-sn-phosphatidyl L-serine in which the phosphatidyl acyl groups at positions 1 and 2 are stearoyl and (9Z,12Z)-octadecadienoyl respectively.

name: sn-glycero-3-phosphoglycerol(1-)

name: 3-(all-trans-heptaprenyl)benzene-1,2-diol
definition: A 3-(all-trans-polyprenyl)benzene-1,2-diol in which the substituent at position 3 is an all-trans-heptaprenyl moiety.

name: 3-(all-trans-nonaprenyl)benzene-1,2-diol
definition: A 3-(all-trans-polyprenyl)benzene-1,2-diol in which the substituent at position 3 is an all-trans-nonaprenyl moiety.

name: 1,2-distearoyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphoserine
definition: A 3-sn-phosphatidyl L-serine in which the phosphatidyl acyl group at both positions 1 and 2 is stearoyl.

name: 1-palmitoyl-2-stearoyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphoserine
definition: A 3-sn-phosphatidyl L-serine in which the phosphatidyl acyl groups at positions 1 and 2 are palmitoyl and stearoyl respectively.

name: 2-methoxy-6-(all-trans-heptaprenyl)phenol

name: 2-methoxy-6-(all-trans-nonaprenyl)phenol
definition: A 2-methoxy-6-(all-trans-polyprenyl)phenol in which the polyprenyl component is specified as all-trans-nonaprenyl.

name: 1,2-dihexadecanoyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphoserine

name: 1,2-di-(9E-octadecenoyl)-sn-glycero-3-phospho-(1'-sn-glycerol)

name: 1-palmitoyl-2-arachidonoyl-sn-glycero-3-phospho-(1'-sn-glycerol)
definition: A 1,2-diacyl-sn-glycero-3-phospho-(1'-sn-glycerol) in which  acyl groups at positions 1 and 2 are specified as palmitoyl and arachidonoyl respectively.

name: 1-(1Z-hexadecenyl)-2-arachidonoyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphoethanolamine
definition: A 1-(alk-1-enyl)-2-acyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphoethanolamine in which the alkenyl and acyl groups are specified as (1Z)-hexadecenyl and arachidonoyl respectively.

name: 2-methoxy-6-all-trans-heptaprenylhydroquinonel
definition: A 2-methoxy-6-all-trans-polyprenylhydroquinone in which the polyprenyl component is specified as all-trans-heptaprenyl.

name: 2-methoxy-6-all-trans-nonaprenylhydroquinone
definition: A 2-methoxy-6-all-trans-polyprenylhydroquinone in which the polyprenyl component is specified as all-trans-nonaprenyl.

name: 6-methoxy-3-methyl-2-all-trans-heptaprenylhydroquinone
definition: A 6-methoxy-3-methyl-2-all-trans-polyprenylhydroquinone in which the polyprenyl component is specified as all-trans-heptaprenyl.

name: 2-methoxy-3-methyl-6-all-trans-nonaprenylhydroquinone
definition: A 6-methoxy-3-methyl-2-all-trans-polyprenylhydroquinone in which the polyprenyl component is specified as all-trans-nonaprenyl.

name: 1-(1Z-hexadecenyl)-2-linoleoyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphoethanolamine
definition: A 1-(alk-1-enyl)-2-acyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphoethanolamine in which the alkenyl and acyl groups are specified as (1Z)-hexadecenyl and linoleoyl respectively.

name: 1-(1Z-hexadecenyl)-2-oleoyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphoethanolamine
definition: 1-(alk-1-enyl)-2-acyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphoethanolamine in which the alkyl and the acyl groups at positions 1 and 2 are specified as (1Z)-hexadecenyl and oleoyl respectively.

name: 1-eicosyl-2-linolenyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphoethanolamine
definition: A 1-alkyl-2-acyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphoethanolamine in which the alkyl and the acyl groups at positions 1 and 2 are specified as eicosyl and linolenyl respectively.

name: dTDP-4-dehydro-2,6-dideoxy-alpha-D-glucose(2-)

name: 2-demethylmenaquinol-6

name: dTDP-3,4-didehydro-2,6-dideoxy-alpha-D-glucose(2-)
definition: A nucleotide-sugar oxoanion obtained by deprotonation of the diphosphate OH groups of dTDP-3,4-didehydro-2,6-dideoxy-alpha-D-glucose; major species at pH 7.3.

name: menaquinol-9

name: 2-demethylmenaquinol-9

name: 1-oleoyl-2-linoleyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphoethanolamine
definition: A 1,2-diacyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphoethanolamine in which the acyl groups at positions 1 and 2 are specified as stearoyl and linoleoyl respectively.

name: menaquinol-10

name: 2-demethylmenaquinol-10
definition: A 2-demethylmenaquinol whose structure comprises a benzohydroquinone nucleus and a side chain of ten isoprenoid units.

name: menaquinol-11
definition: A menaquinol whose structure comprises a 2-methylbenzohydroquinone nucleus and a side chain of eleven isoprenoid units.

name: 2-demethylmenaquinol-11
definition: A 2-demethylmenaquinol whose structure comprises a benzohydroquinone nucleus and a side chain of eleven isoprenoid units.

name: 1-palmitoyl-2-(7Z,10Z,13Z,16Z-docosatetraenoyl)-sn-glycero-3-phosphoethanolamine

name: 2-demethylmenaquinol-12

name: menaquinol-13

name: 2-demethylmenaquinol-13

name: 3,5-dihydroxyphenylacetyl-CoA(4-)

name: 1-(1Z-octadecenyl)-2-(9Z,12Z-octadecadienoyl)-sn-glycero-3-phosphocholine

name: 4-O-(2-acetamido-2-deoxy-alpha-D-glucosylphospho)-2-acetamido-2-deoxy-alpha-D-glucosyl 3-aminopropyl phosphate(2-)

name: 2,4-dinitroanisole

name: 2,4-dinitrophenol(1-)

name: 1-octadecanoyl-2-(7Z,10Z,13Z,16Z-docosatetraenoyl)-sn-glycero-3-phosphocholine
definition: A phosphatidylcholine 40:4 in which the two acyl substituents at positions 1 and 2 are specified as stearoyl and (7Z,10Z,13Z,16Z)-docosatetraenoyl respectively.

name: 1-heptadecanoyl-2-(9Z,12Z-octadecadienoyl)-sn-glycero-3-phosphocholine
definition: A 1,2-diacyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphocholine in which the two acyl substituents at positions 1 and 2 are specified as heptadecanoyl and (9Z,12Z)-octadecadienoyl respectively

name: 1-palmitoleoyl-2-linoleoyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphocholine
definition: A phosphatidylcholine 34:3 in which the acyl groups specified at positions 1 and 2 are palmitoleoyl and linoleoyl respectively.

name: 4-O-[4-O-(2-acetamido-2-deoxy-alpha-D-glucosylphospho)-2-acetamido-2-deoxy-alpha-D-glucosylphospho]-2-acetamido-2-deoxy-alpha-D-glucosyl 3-aminopropyl phosphate(3-)
definition: The organophosphate oxoanion formed by proton loss from each of the phospho groups of 4-O-[4-O-(2-acetamido-2-deoxy-alpha-D-glucosylphospho)-2-acetamido-2-deoxy-alpha-D-glucosylphospho]-2-acetamido-2-deoxy-alpha-D-glucosyl 3-aminopropyl phosphate.

name: trihydrogen 4-O-[4-O-(2-acetamido-2-deoxy-alpha-D-glucosylphospho)-2-acetamido-2-deoxy-alpha-D-glucosylphospho]-2-acetamido-2-deoxy-alpha-D-glucosyl 3-aminopropyl phosphate
definition: An amino sugar phosphate that is 4-O-[4-O-(N-acetyl-alpha-D-glucosaminylphospho)-N-acetyl-alpha-D-glucosaminylphospho]-N-acetyl-alpha-D-glucosamine linked glycosidically to a (3-aminopropoxy)(hydroxy)phosphoryl group.

name: 1-palmitoleoyl-2-stearoyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphocholine
definition: A 1,2-diacyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphocholine in which the acyl groups specified at positions 1 and 2 are palmitoleoyl and stearoyl respectively.

name: rifamycin SV(1-)
definition: A phenolate anion obtained by deprotonation of the 5-hydroxy group of rifamycin SV. It is the major microspecies at pH 7.3 (according to Marvin v 6.2.0.).

name: 27-O-demethylrifamycin SV(1-)
definition: A phenolate anion obtained by deprotonation of the 5-hydroxy group of 27-O-demethylrifamycin SV. It is the major microspecies at pH 7.3 (according to Marvin v 6.2.0.).

name: 1-palmitoyl-2-(11Z,14Z-eicosadienoyl)-sn-glycero-3-phosphocholine
definition: A 1,2-diacyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphocholine in which the acyl groups specified at positions 1 and 2 are palmitoyl and (11Z,14Z)-eicosadienoyl respectively.

name: 1-palmitoyl-2-(11Z-eicosenoyl)-sn-glycero-3-phosphocholine
definition: A 1,2-diacyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphocholine in which the acyl groups specified at positions 1 and 2 are palmitoyl and (11Z)-eicosenoyl respectively.

name: (25S)-3beta-hydroxy-5-cholesten-26-oyl-CoA
definition: A cholestenoyl-CoA that results from the formal condensation of the thiol group of coenzyme A with the carboxy group of (25S)-3beta-hydroxy-5-cholesten-26-oic acid.

name: 1-palmitoyl-2-(9Z-heptadecenoyl)-sn-glycero-3-phosphocholine
definition: A  phosphatidylcholine 33:1 in which the acyl groups specified at positions 1 and 2 are palmitoyl and (9Z)-heptadecenoyl respectively.

name: 1-myristoyl-2-palmitoleoyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphocholine
definition: A phosphatidylcholine 30:1 in which the acyl groups at positions 1 and 2 are myristoyl and palmitoleoyl respectively.

name: 3-[(3aS,4S,5R,7aS)-5-hydroxy-7a-methyl-1-oxo-octahydroinden-4-yl]propanoic acid
definition: A dioxo monocarboxylic acid that consists of hydrindane bearing oxo and hydroxy substituents at positions 1 and 5 respectively as well as a 2-carboxyethyl substituent at position 4 (the 3aS,4S,5R,7aS diastereomer).

name: dinitroanisoles
definition: Any member of the class of nitroanisoles in which the anisole ring is substituted by two nitro groups.

name: 1,2,2'-trilinoleoyl-,1'-monolysocardiolipin
definition: A 1-monolysocardiolipin in which the remaining phosphatidyl acyl groups at positions 1, 2 and 2' are specified as linoleoyl.

name: schizokinen
definition: A hydroxamic acid resulting from the formal condensation of the primary amino group of N-(3-aminopropyl)-N-hydroxyacetamide (2 mol eq.) with the carboxy groups at positions 1 and 3 of citric acid. It is a siderophore produced by Bacillus megaterium and Anabaena species.

name: 1,1'-dilinoleoyl-2-oleoyl monolysocardiolipin
definition: A 2-monolysocardiolipinin which the remaining phosphatidyl acyl groups at positions 1 and 1' are specified as linoleoyl while that at position 2' is  specified as oleoyl.

name: 3-oxodotriacontanoyl-CoA
definition: A 3-oxo-fatty acyl-CoA obtained from the formal condensation of the thiol group of coenzyme A with the carboxy group of 3-oxodotriacontanoic acid (3-oxolacceroic acid).

name: vibrioferrin
definition: A tricarboxylic acid that is citric acid in which the pro-R carboxy group has been esterified with the primary hydroxy group of 2-hydroxy-1-{(2S)-1-[(2-hydroxyethyl)amino]-1-oxopropan-2-yl}-5-oxoproline. It is a siderophore isolated from bacteria closely associated or symbiotic with toxic, bloom-forming dinoflagellates.

name: furoquinoline
definition: An organic heterotricyclic compound consisting of a furan ring ortho-fused to a quinoline.

name: 2,3-saturated fatty aldehyde
definition: Any fatty aldehyde that is saturated at positions 2 and 3.

name: trans-2,3-unsaturated fatty aldehyde
definition: A fatty aldehyde with a trans-double bond at carbon 2.

name: mitomycin A(1-)
definition: An organic anion obtained by removal of the acidic proton from position 8 of mitomycin A. It is the major microspecies at pH 7.3 (according to Marvin v 6.2.0.).

name: mitomycin B(1-)
definition: An organic anion obtained by removal of the acidic proton from position 8 of mitomycin B. It is the major microspecies at pH 7.3 (according to Marvin v 6.2.0.).

name: 7-demethylmitomycin B(1-)
definition: An organic anion obtained by removal of the acidic proton from position 8 of 7-demethylmitomycin B.

name: 7-demethylmitomycin A(1-)
definition: An organic anion obtained by removal of the acidic proton from position 8 of 7-demethylmitomycin A.

name: 5'-GAUAUACACGCAUAUCAGCGUUCGCGU-3' RNA fragment
definition: An RNA fragment comprised of six guanosine, seven adenosine, seven uridine and seven cytidine residues connected by 3'->5' phosphodiester linkages in the sequence G-A-U-A-U-A-C-A-C-G-C-A-U-A-U-C-A-G-C-G-U-U-C-G-C-G-U.

name: 5'-AGGCAAUAAAACACGACCWUAAUG-3' RNA fragment
definition: An RNA fragment comprised of four guanosine, eleven adenosine, two uridine and five cytidine residues connected by 3'->5' phosphodiester linkages in the sequence A-G-G-C-A-A-U-A-A-A-A-C-A-C-G-A-C-C-W-U-A-A-U-G.

name: 5'-CUGCGAUUUUAAAGACCUAGAGUAC-3' RNA fragment
definition: An RNA fragment comprised of five guanosine, eight adenosine, seven uridine and five cytidine residues connected by 3'->5' phosphodiester linkages in the sequence C-U-G-C-G-A-U-U-U-U-A-A-A-G-A-C-C-U-A-G-A-G-U-A-C.

name: U1 small nuclear RNA
definition: The small nuclear RNA (snRNA) that is a component of U1 snRNP (small nuclear ribonucleoprotein), an RNA-protein complex that combines with other snRNPs, unmodified pre-mRNA, and various other proteins to assemble a spliceosome, a large RNA-protein molecular complex upon which splicing of pre-mRNA occurs.

name: 1-NO-cAMP
definition: A 3',5'-cyclic purine nucleotide obtained by oxygenation of the nitrogen at position 1 on the purine fragment of 3',5'-cyclic AMP.

name: 2-(dimethylamino)-cAMP
definition: A 3',5'-cyclic purine nucleotide that is 3',5'-cyclic AMP in which the hydrogen at position 2 on the purine fragment is replaced by a dimethylamino group.

name: all-trans-dodecaprenyl diphosphate
definition: An all-trans-polyprenyl diphosphate composed from twelve isoprenyl units.

name: all-trans-tridecaprenyl diphosphate
definition: An all-trans-polyprenyl diphosphate composed from thirteen isoprenyl units.

name: 3-[(3aS,4S,5R,7aS)-5-hydroxy-7a-methyl-1-oxo-octahydroinden-4-yl]propanoyl-CoA
definition: An acyl-CoA resulting from the formal condensation of the thiol group of coenzyme A with the carboxy group of 3-[(3aS,4S,5R,7aS)-5-hydroxy-7a-methyl-1-oxo-octahydroinden-4-yl]propanoic acid.

name: all-trans-dodecaprenyl diphosphate(3-)
definition: An all-trans-polyprenyl diphosphate(3-) arising from deprotonation of the diphosphate OH groups of all-trans-dodecaprenyl diphosphate; major species at pH 7.3.

name: all-trans-tridecaprenyl diphosphate(3-)
definition: An all-trans-polyprenyl diphosphate(3-) arising from deprotonation of the diphosphate OH groups of all-trans-tridecaprenyl diphosphate; major species at pH 7.3.

name: N(6)-butyryl-cAMP
definition: A 3',5'-cyclic purine nucleotide that is 3',5'-cyclic AMP in which the exocyclic amino group on the purine fragment is carrying a butyryl substituent.

name: N(6)-(6-aminohexyl)-cAMP
definition: A 3',5'-cyclic purine nucleotide that is 3',5'-cyclic AMP in which the exocyclic amino group on the purine fragment is carrying a 6-aminohexyl substituent.

name: 7-deaza-cAMP
definition: A nucleoside 3',5'-cyclic phosphate that is cAMP in which the nitrogen atom at position 7 on the purine fragment is replaced by a methine (C-H) group.

name: 8-aza-cAMP
definition: A nucleoside 3',5'-cyclic phosphate that is cAMP in which the methine (C-H) group at position 8 on the purine fragment is replaced by nitrogen.

name: 8-(4-chlorophenylthio)-cAMP
definition: A 3',5'-cyclic purine nucleotide that is 3',5'-cyclic AMP in which the hydrogen at position 2 on the purine fragment is replaced by a 4-chlorophenylthio group.

name: 8-(6-aminohexylthio)-cAMP
definition: A 3',5'-cyclic purine nucleotide that is 3',5'-cyclic AMP in which the hydrogen at position 2 on the purine fragment is replaced by a 6-aminohexylthio group.

name: (Sp)-cAMPS
definition: A nucleoside 3',5'-cyclic phosphorothioate having adenine as the nucleobase (the Sp-stereoisomer).

name: 3-oxo-23,24-bisnorchol-4-en-22-oyl-CoA
definition: A steroidal acyl-CoA that results from the formal condensation of the thiol group of coenzyme A with the carboxy group of 3-oxo-23,24-bisnorchol-4-en-22-oic acid.

name: 3-oxo-23,24-bisnorchola-1,4-dien-22-oyl-CoA
definition: A steroidal acyl-CoA that results from the formal condensation of the thiol group of coenzyme A with the carboxy group of 3-oxo-23,24-bisnorchola-1,4-dien-22-oic acid.

name: 3-hydroxy-9-oxo-9,10-seco-23,24-bisnorchola-1,3,5(10)-trien-22-oyl-CoA
definition: A steroidal acyl-CoA that results from the formal condensation of the thiol group of coenzyme A with the carboxy group of 3-hydroxy-9-oxo-9,10-seco-23,24-bisnorchola-1,3,5(10)-trien-22-oic acid.

name: (Sp)-8-bromo-cAMPS
definition: A nucleoside 3',5'-cyclic phosphorothioate having 8-bromoadenine as the nucleobase (the Sp-stereoisomer).

name: (Sp)-8-bromo-7-deaza-cAMPS
definition: A nucleoside 3',5'-cyclic phosphorothioate having 8-bromo-7-deazaadenine as the nucleobase (the Sp-stereoisomer).

name: (Sp)-7-bromo-7-deaza-cAMPS
definition: A nucleoside 3',5'-cyclic phosphorothioate having 7-bromo-7-deazaadenine as the nucleobase (the Sp-stereoisomer).

name: (Rp)-cAMPS
definition: A nucleoside 3',5'-cyclic phosphorothioate having adenine as the nucleobase (the Rp-stereoisomer).

name: (Rp)-8-bromo-7-deaza-cAMPS
definition: A nucleoside 3',5'-cyclic phosphorothioate having 8-bromo-7-deazaadenine as the nucleobase (the Rp-stereoisomer).

name: (Rp)-7-deaza-cAMPS
definition: A nucleoside 3',5'-cyclic phosphorothioate having 7-deazaadenine as the nucleobase (the Rp-stereoisomer).

name: (Rp)-7-bromo-7-deaza-cAMPS
definition: A nucleoside 3',5'-cyclic phosphorothioate having 7-bromo-7-deazaadenine as the nucleobase (the Rp-stereoisomer).

name: cPuMP
definition: A nucleoside 3',5'-cyclic phosphate that is 3',5'-cyclic AMP in which the exocyclic amino group on the purine fragment is replaced by hydrogen

name: 6-(dimethylamino)-cPuMP
definition: A 3',5'-cyclic purine nucleotide that is 3',5'-cyclic AMP in which the exocylic amino hydrogens on the purine fragment are replaced by methyl groups.

name: 2-amino-cPuMP
definition: A 3',5'-cyclic purine nucleotide having 2-aminopurine as the nucleobase.

name: vibrioferrin(3-)
definition: A tricarboxylic acid trianion resulting from the deprotonation of all three carboxy groups of vibrioferrin. The major species at pH 7.3.

name: N(1)-methyl-cGMP
definition: A 3',5'-cyclic purine nucleotide having 1-methylguanine as the nucleobase.

name: iron(III) vibrioferrin
definition: An iron coordination entity comprising equimolar amounts of iron(3+) and vibrioferrin(3-).

name: O-tetradecanoyl-L-carnitine
definition: An O-acyl-L-carnitine in which the acyl group is specified as myristoyl (tetradecanoyl).

name: N(2),N(2)-dimethyl-cGMP
definition: A 3',5'-cyclic purine nucleotide having N(2),N(2)-dimethylguanosine as the nucleobase.

name: N(2),3-etheno-cGMP
definition: A nucleoside 3',5'-cyclic monophosphate analogue having imidazo[2,1-b]purin-4-one as the modified nucleobase.

name: 7-deaza-cGMP
definition: A nucleoside 3',5'-cyclic phosphate that is cGMP in which the nitrogen atom at position 7 on the purine fragment is replaced by a methine (C-H) group

name: 8-(4-chlorophenylthio)-cGMP
definition: A 3',5'-cyclic purine nucleotide that is 3',5'-cyclic GMP in which the hydrogen at position 2 on the purine fragment is replaced by a 4-chlorophenylthio group.

name: 8-(6-aminohexylthio)-cGMP
definition: A 3',5'-cyclic purine nucleotide that is 3',5'-cyclic GMP in which the hydrogen at position 2 on the purine fragment is replaced by a 6-aminohexylthio group.

name: (Sp)-cGMPS
definition: A nucleoside 3',5'-cyclic phosphorothioate having guanine as the nucleobase (the Sp-stereoisomer).

name: (Sp)-8-Br-cGMPS
definition: A nucleoside 3',5'-cyclic phosphorothioate having 8-bromoguanine as the nucleobase (the Sp-stereoisomer).

name: (Rp)-cGMPS
definition: A nucleoside 3',5'-cyclic phosphorothioate having guanine as the nucleobase (the Rp-stereoisomer).

name: O-octadecanoyl-L-carnitine
definition: An O-acyl-L-carnitine in which the acyl group is specified as stearoyl (octadecanoyl).

name: (R)-icosanoylcarnitine
definition: An O-acyl-L-carnitine in which the acyl group is specified as icosanoyl.

name: O-[(9Z)-tetradecenoyl]-L-carnitine
definition: An O-tetradecenoyl-L-carnitine in which the acyl group is specified as myristoleoyl.

name: O-[(5Z)-tetradecenoyl]-L-carnitine
definition: An O-tetradecenoyl-L-carnitine  in which the acyl group is specified as (5Z)-tetradecenoyl.

name: (5Z)-tetradecenoyl-CoA(4-)
definition: An acyl-CoA(4-) obtained by deprotonation of the phosphate and diphosphate OH groups of (5Z)-tetradecenoyl-CoA; major species at pH 7.3.

name: (R)-oleoylcarnitine
definition: An O-acyl-L-carnitine in which the acyl group is specified as oleoyl.

name: alpha-D-Rhap4NFo-(1->2)-alpha-D-Rhap4NFo-(1->3)-alpha-D-Rhap4NFo-(1->2)-alpha-D-Rhap4NFo-(1->2)-alpha-D-Rhap4NFo-(1->2)-alpha-D-Rhap4NFoO[CH2]5C(O)NH2CH2CH2NH2-3,4-dioxocyclobutyl
definition: An organyl group consisting of a hexasaccharide chain of N-formyl-alpha-D-perosamine residues linked (1->2) or (1->3), linked glycosidically to a 2-[2-(hexanamido)ethylamino]-3,4-dioxocyclobutyl group used as a tether for conjugation to proteins.

name: beta-GalNAc-(1->4)-[alpha-Neu5Ac-(2->8)-alpha-Neu5Ac-(2->8)-alpha-Neu5Ac-(2->3)]-beta-Gal-(1->4)-beta-Glc-(1->1')-Cer(d18:1/16:0)
definition: A sialotriaosylceramide consisting of the hexasaccharide beta-GalNAc-(1->4)-[alpha-Neu5Ac-(2->8)-alpha-Neu5Ac-(2->8)-alpha-Neu5Ac-(2->3)]-beta-Gal-(1->4)-beta-Glc attached to the primary hydroxy function of ceramide(d18:1/16:0).

name: (R)-4,8-dimethylnonanoylcarnitine
definition: An O-acyl-L-carnitine in which the acyl group is specified as 4,8-dimethylnonanoyl.

name: (R)-3-oxopalmitoylcarnitine
definition: An O-acyl-L-carnitine in which the acyl group is specified as 3-oxopalmitoyl.

name: alpha-Neu5Ac-(2->3)-beta-D-Gal-(1->3)-beta-D-GalNAc-(1->4)-[alpha-Neu5Ac-(2->3)]-beta-D-Gal-(1->4)-beta-D-Glc-(1<->1')-Cer(d18:1/20:0)
definition: A sialopentaosylceramide consisting of alpha-Neu5Ac-(2->3)-beta-D-Gal-(1->3)-beta-D-GalNAc-(1->4)-[alpha-Neu5Ac-(2->3)]-beta-D-Gal-(1->4)-beta-D-Glucosyl unit attached to the Cer(d18:1/20:0).

name: triacylglycerol 54:3
definition: A triglyceride in which the three acyl groups contain a total of 54 carbons and 3 double bonds.

name: triacylglycerol 52:4
definition: A triglyceride in which the three acyl groups contain a total of 52 carbons and 4 double bonds.

name: triacylglycerol 52:3
definition: A triglyceride in which the three acyl groups contain a total of 52 carbons and 3 double bonds.

name: triacylglycerol 50:2
definition: A triglyceride in which the three acyl groups contain a total of 50 carbons and 2 double bonds.

name: alpha-D-Rhap4NFo-(1->3)-alpha-D-Rhap4NFoO[CH2]5C(O)NH2CH2CH2NH2-3,4-dioxocyclobutylaminomethyl group
definition: An organyl group consisting of a disaccharide of N-formyl-alpha-D-perosamine residues linked (1->3), linked glycosidically to a 2-[2-(hexanamido)ethylamino]-3,4-dioxocyclobutylaminomethyl group used as a tether for conjugation to proteins.

name: triacylglycerol 50:1
definition: A triglyceride in which the three acyl groups contain a total of 50 carbons and 1 double bond.

name: (25S)-3-oxocholest-4-en-26-oyl-CoA
definition: A cholestenoyl-CoA that results from the formal condensation of the thiol group of coenzyme A with the carboxy group of (25S)-3-oxocholest-4-en-26-oic acid.

name: alpha-Neu5Ac-(2->3)-beta-D-Gal-(1->3)-beta-D-GalNAc-(1->4)-[alpha-Neu5Ac-(2->3)]-beta-D-Gal-(1->4)-beta-D-Glc-(1<->1')-Cer(d18:1/24:0)
definition: A sialopentaosylceramide consisting of a alpha-Neu5Ac-(2->3)-beta-D-Gal-(1->3)-beta-D-GalNAc-(1->4)-[alpha-Neu5Ac-(2->3)]-beta-D-Gal-(1->4)-beta-D-Glucosyl unit attached to a Cer(d18:1/24:0).

name: alpha-Neu5Ac-(2->3)-beta-D-Gal-(1->3)-beta-D-GalNAc-(1->4)-[alpha-Neu5Ac-(2->3)]-beta-D-Gal-(1->4)-beta-D-Glc-(1<->1')-Cer(d18:1/24:1(15Z))
definition: A sialopentaosylceramide consisting of a alpha-Neu5Ac-(2->3)-beta-D-Gal-(1->3)-beta-D-GalNAc-(1->4)-[alpha-Neu5Ac-(2->3)]-beta-D-Gal-(1->4)-beta-D-Glucosyl unit attached to a Cer(d18:1/24:1(15Z)).

name: beta-D-Gal-(1->3)-beta-D-GalNAc-(1->4)-[alpha-Neu5Ac-(2->3)]-beta-D-Gal-(1->4)-beta-D-Glc-(1<->1')-Cer(d18:1/16:0)
definition: A sialotetraosylceramide having beta-D-Gal-(1->3)-beta-D-GalNAc-(1->4)-[alpha-Neu5Ac-(2->3)]-beta-D-Gal-(1->4)-beta-D-Glc as the sialotetraosyl component.

name: beta-D-Gal-(1->3)-beta-D-GalNAc-(1->4)-[alpha-Neu5Ac-(2->3)]-beta-D-Gal-(1->4)-beta-D-Glc-(1<->1')-Cer(d18:1/24:0)
definition: A sialotetraosylceramide having beta-D-Gal-(1->3)-beta-D-GalNAc-(1->4)-[alpha-Neu5Ac-(2->3)]-beta-D-Gal-(1->4)-beta-D-Glc as the sialotetraosyl component.

name: phosphatidylethanol(1-)
definition: An anionic phospholipid obtained by deprotonation of the phosphate OH group of any phosphatidylethanol; major species at pH 7.3.

name: beta-D-Gal-(1->3)-beta-D-GalNAc-(1->4)-[alpha-Neu5Ac-(2->3)]-beta-D-Gal-(1->4)-beta-D-Glc-(1<->1')-Cer(d18:1/24:1(15Z))
definition: A sialotetraosylceramide having beta-D-Gal-(1->3)-beta-D-GalNAc-(1->4)-[alpha-Neu5Ac-(2->3)]-beta-D-Gal-(1->4)-beta-D-Glc as the sialotetraosyl component.

name: alpha-Neu5Ac-(2->3)-beta-D-Gal-(1->4)-beta-D-Glc-(1<->1')-Cer(d18:1/16:0)
definition: A sialotriaosylceramide consisting of  beta-D-GalNAc-(1->4)-[alpha-Neu5Ac-(2->3)]-beta-D-Gal-(1->4)-beta-D-Glc attached to the primary hydroxy function of ceramide(d18:1/16:0).

name: alpha-Neu5Ac-(2->3)-beta-D-Gal-(1->4)-beta-D-Glc-(1<->1')-Cer(d18:1/18:0)
definition: A sialotriaosylceramide consisting of beta-D-GalNAc-(1->4)-[alpha-Neu5Ac-(2->3)]-beta-D-Gal-(1->4)-beta-D-Glc attached to the primary hydroxy function of ceramide(d18:1/18:0).

name: alpha-Neu5Ac-(2->3)-beta-D-Gal-(1->4)-beta-D-Glc-(1<->1')-Cer(d18:1/20:0)
definition: A sialotriaosylceramide consisting of beta-D-GalNAc-(1->4)-[alpha-Neu5Ac-(2->3)]-beta-D-Gal-(1->4)-beta-D-Glc attached to the primary hydroxy function of ceramide(d18:1/20:0).

name: MANT-GDP
definition: A mixture composed from 2' and 3'-O-(N-methylanthraniloyl) derivatives of GDP in unspecified amounts.

name: alpha-D-Rhap4NFo-(1->2)-alpha-D-Rhap4NFo-(1->3)-alpha-D-Rhap4NFoO[CH2]5C(O)NH2CH2CH2NH2-3,4-dioxocyclobutylaminomethyl group
definition: An organyl group consisting of a trisaccharide of N-formyl-alpha-D-perosamine residues linked sequentially (1->2) and (1->3), and linked at the reducing end glycosidically to a 2-[2-(hexanamido)ethylamino]-3,4-dioxocyclobutylaminomethyl group used as a tether for conjugation to proteins.

name: alpha-Neu5Ac-(2->3)-beta-D-Gal-(1->4)-beta-D-Glc-(1<->1')-Cer(d18:1/22:0)
definition: A sialotriaosylceramide consisting of beta-D-GalNAc-(1->4)-[alpha-Neu5Ac-(2->3)]-beta-D-Gal-(1->4)-beta-D-Glc attached to the primary hydroxy function of ceramide(d18:1/22:0).

name: alpha-D-Rhap4NFo-(1->3)-alpha-D-Rhap4NFo-(1->2)-alpha-D-Rhap4NFoO[CH2]5C(O)NH2CH2CH2NH2-3,4-dioxocyclobutylaminomethyl group
definition: An organyl group consisting of a trisaccharide of N-formyl-alpha-D-perosamine residues linked sequentially (1->3) and (1->2), and linked at the reducing end glycosidically to a 2-[2-(hexanamido)ethylamino]-3,4-dioxocyclobutylaminomethyl group used as a tether for conjugation to proteins.

name: alpha-Neu5Ac-(2->3)-beta-D-Gal-(1->4)-beta-D-Glc-(1<->1')-Cer(d18:1/24:0)
definition: A sialotriaosylceramide consisting of beta-D-GalNAc-(1->4)-[alpha-Neu5Ac-(2->3)]-beta-D-Gal-(1->4)-beta-D-Glc attached to the primary hydroxy function of ceramide(d18:1/24:0).

name: alpha-Neu5Ac-(2->3)-beta-D-Gal-(1->3)-beta-D-GalNAc-(1->4)-[alpha-Neu5Ac-(2->8)-alpha-Neu5Ac-(2->8)-alpha-Neu5Ac-(2->3)]-beta-D-Gal-(1->4)-beta-D-Glc-(1<->1')-Cer(d18:1/18:0)

name: EC 2.7.1.151 (inositol-polyphosphate multikinase) inhibitor
definition: Any EC 2.7.1.* (phosphotransferases with an alcohol group as acceptor) inhibitor that interferes with the action of inositol-polyphosphate multikinase (EC 2.7.1.151).

name: EC 2.7.4.* (phosphotransferases with a phosphate group as acceptor) inhibitor
definition: Any EC 2.7.* (P-containing group transferase) inhibitor that interferes with the action of any phosphotransferase with a phosphate group as acceptor (EC 2.7.4.*).

name: EC 2.7.4.6 (nucleoside-diphosphate kinase) inhibitor
definition: Any EC 2.7.4.* (phosphotransferases with a phosphate group as acceptor) inhibitor that interferes with the action of nucleoside-diphosphate kinase (EC 2.7.4.6).

name: UDP-N-acetyl-alpha-D-muramoyl-L-alanyl-D-gamma-glutamyl-meso-2,6-diaminoheptanedioic acid
definition: A UDP-N-acetylmuramoyl-L-alanyl-D-gamma-glutamyl-meso-2,6-diaminoheptanedioate in which the muramoyl moiety has alpha-configuration at its anomeric centre.

name: beta-D-galactosyl-(1->4)-beta-D-glucosyl-(1<->1)-N-[(17Z)-hexacosenoyl]sphingosine
definition: A beta-D-galactosyl-(1->4)-beta-D-glucosyl-(1<->1')-N-acylsphingosine in which the acyl group specified is (17Z)-hexacosenoyl.

name: 1-tetradecanoyl-2-[(9Z)-octadecenoyl]-sn-glycero-3-phosphocholine

name: 1-[(2Z)-hexadecenoyl]-2-[(9Z)-octadecenoyl]-sn-glycero-3-phosphocholine
definition: A phosphatidylcholine 34:2 in which the 1- and 2-acyl groups are specified as (2Z)-hexadecenoyl and (9Z)-octadecenoyl respectively.

name: 1-[(9Z)-hexadecenoyl]-2-[(11Z)-octadecenoyl]-sn-glycero-3-phosphocholine
definition: A phosphatidylcholine 34:2 in which the 1- and 2-acyl groups are specified as (9Z)-hexadecenoyl and (11Z)-octadecenoyl respectively.

name: 1-[(9Z)-hexadecenoyl]-2-[(9Z)-octadecenoyl]-sn-glycero-3-phosphocholine
definition: A phosphatidylcholine 34:2 in which the 1- and 2-acyl groups are specified as (9Z)-hexadecenoyl (palmitoleoyl) and (9Z)-octadecenoyl (oleoyl) respectively.

name: 1-[(11Z)-octadecenoyl]-2-[(4Z,7Z,10Z,13Z,16Z,19Z)]-docosahexaenoyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphocholine

name: 4-oxo-L-proline zwitterion
definition: An amino acid zwitterion resulting from a transfer of a proton from the carboxy to the amino group of 4-oxo-L-proline; major species at pH 7.3.

name: 1-[(9Z)-octadecenoyl]-2-[(4Z,7Z,10Z,13Z,16Z,19Z)-docosahexaenoyl]-sn-glycero-3-phosphocholine
definition: A phosphatidylcholine 40:7 in which the acyl groups at positions 1 and 2 are specified as (9Z)-octadecenoyl and (4Z,7Z,10Z,13Z,16Z,19Z)-docosahexaenoyl respectively.

name: 1,2-di-octadecadienoyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphocholine
definition: A phosphatidylcholine 36:4 in which the acyl groups at positions 1 and 2 are octadecadienoyl with double bonds at unspecified positions.

name: 1-[(9Z)-hexadecenoyl]-2-[(5Z,8Z,11Z,14Z)-eicosatetraenoyl]-sn-glycero-3-phosphocholine
definition: A phosphatidylcholine 36:5 in which the acyl groups specified at positions 1 and 2 are (9Z)-hexadecenoyl and (5Z,8Z,11Z,14Z)-eicosatetraenoyl respectively.

name: 1-octadecanoyl-2-octadecenoyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphocholine
definition: A phosphatidylcholine 36:1 in which the acyl groups aspecified at positions 1 and 2 are octadecanoyl and octadecenoyl (double bond at unspecified position) respectively.

name: 1-octadecanoyl-2-[(10Z,12Z)-octadecadienoyl]-sn-glycero-3-phosphocholine
definition: A phosphatidylcholine 36:2 in which the acyl groups specified at positions 1 and 2 are octadecanoyl and (10Z,12Z)-octadecadienoyl respectively

name: 1-octadecanoyl-2-[(2E,4E)-octadecadienoyl]-sn-glycero-3-phosphocholine
definition: A phosphatidylcholine 36:2 in which the acyl groups specified at positions 1 and 2 are octadecanoyl and (2E,4E)-octadecadienoyl respectively.

name: 1-octadecanoyl-2-[(6Z,9Z)-octadecadienoyl]-sn-glycero-3-phosphocholine
definition: A phosphatidylcholine 36:2 in which the acyl groups specified at positions 1 and 2 are octadecanoyl and (6Z,9Z)-octadecadienoyl respectively.

name: 1-octadecanoyl-2-[(8Z,10Z,12Z,14Z)-eicosatetraenoyl]-sn-glycero-3-phosphocholine
definition: A phosphatidylcholine 38:4 in which the acyl groups at positions 1 and 2 are octadecanoyl and (8Z,10Z,12Z,14Z)-eicosatetraenoyl respectively.

name: aromatic L-alpha-amino acid zwitterion
definition: An L-alpha-amino acid zwitterion resulting from a transfer of a proton from the carboxy to the amino group of any aromatic L-alpha-amino acid; major species at pH 7.3.

name: 1-[(9Z)-octadecenyl]-2-hexadecanoyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphocholine
definition: A phosphatidylcholine O-34:1 in which the alkenyl group at position 1 is (9Z)-octadecenyl and the acyl group at position 2 is hexadecanoyl.

name: 1-(1Z-octadecenyl)-2-hexadecanoyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphocholine
definition: A 1-O-(alk-1-enyl)-2-O-acyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphocholine in which the alkenyl group at position 1 is (1Z)-octadecenyl and the acyl group at position 2 is hexadecanoyl respectively.

name: 1-[(9Z)-octadecenyl]-2-[(5Z,8Z,11Z,14Z)-eicosatetraenoyl]-sn-glycero-3-phosphocholine
definition: A phosphatidylcholine O-38:5 in which the alkenyl group at position 1 is (9Z)-octadecenyl and the acyl group at position 2 is (5Z,8Z,11Z,14Z)-eicosatetraenoyl respectively.

name: 1-[(1Z)-octadecenyl]-2-[(5Z,8Z,11Z,14Z)-icosatetraenoyl]-sn-glycero-3-phosphocholine
definition: A  phosphatidylcholine (P-38:4) in which the alkenyl group at position 1 is (1Z)-octadecenyl and the acyl group at position 2 is (5Z,8Z,11Z,14Z)-icosatetraenoyl.

name: 1-octadecanoyl-2-[(9Z,11Z,13Z,15Z,17Z,19E)-docosahexaenoyl]-sn-glycero-3-phosphocholine
definition: A phosphatidylcholine 40:6 in which the acyl groups specified at positions 1 and 2 are octadecanoyl and (9Z,11Z,13Z,15Z,17Z,19E)-docosahexaenoyl respectively.

name: Boc-Gln-Ala-Arg-7-amino-4-methylcoumarin
definition: A tripeptide consisting of Gln-Ala-Arg carrying a Boc group at the N-terminal and a 7-amino-4-methylcoumarin group at the C-terminal.

name: 1-hexadecanoyl-2-(11Z-octadecenoyl)-sn-glycero-3-phosphoethanolamine
definition: A 1,2-diacyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphoethanolamine in which the 1- and 2-acyl groups are specified as hexadecanoyl (palmitoyl) and 11Z-octadecenoyl respectively.

name: O-hexanoyl-L-carnitine
definition: An O-hexanoylcarnitine that has L configuration.

name: 1-hexadecanoyl-2-(7Z-octadecenoyl)-sn-glycero-3-phosphoethanolamine
definition: A 1,2-diacyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphoethanolamine in which the 1- and 2-acyl groups are specified as hexadecanoyl (palmitoyl) and 7Z-octadecenoyl respectively.

name: 1,2-di-octadecenoyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphocholine
definition: A phosphatidylcholine 36:2 in which the acyl group both at positions 1 and 2 is octadecenoyl with double bond at unspecified position.

name: 1-octadecanoyl-2-(5E,8E,11E,14E-eicosatetraenoyl)-sn-glycero-3-phosphoethanolamine
definition: A 1,2-diacyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphoethanolamine in which the acyl substituents at positions 1 and 2 are specified as octadecanoyl (stearoyl) and (5E,8E,11E,14E)-eicosatetraenoyl respectively.

name: 1,2-di-[(9Z)-octadecenoyl]-sn-glycero-3-phosphoethanolamine
definition: A 1,2-diacyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphoethanolamine in which the acyl substituent both at positions 1 and 2 is specified as (9Z)-octadecenoyl respectively.

name: (R)-acetoacetylcarnitine
definition: An O-acyl-L-carnitine in which the acyl group is specified as acetoacetyl.

name: (R)-3-hydroxybutyrylcarnitine
definition: An O-hydroxybutyryl-L-carnitine in which the acyl group is specified as 3-hydroxybutyryl.

name: (R)-2,6-dimethylheptanoylcarnitine
definition: An optically active form of 2,6-dimethylheptanoylcarnitine having (R)-configuration.

name: 1,2-di-[(9E)-octadecenoyl]-sn-glycero-3-phosphoethanolamine
definition: A 1,2-diacyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphoethanolamine in which both acyl substituents are specified as (9E)-octadecenoyl.

name: 1,2-di-[(6Z)-octadecenoyl]-sn-glycero-3-phosphoethanolamine
definition: A 1,2-diacyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphoethanolamine in which the acyl substituent both at positions 1 and 2 is specified as (6Z)-octadecenoyl respectively.

name: 1,2-di-(9Z,12Z-octadecadienoyl)-sn-glycero-3-phosphoethanolamine
definition: A 1,2-diacyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphoethanolamine in which the acyl substituent both at positions 1 and 2 is specified as (9Z,12Z)-octadecadienoyl respectively.

name: 2,6-dimethylheptanoyl-CoA(4-)
definition: A multi-methyl-branched fatty acyl-CoA(4-) obtained by deprotonation of the phosphate and diphosphate OH groups of 2,6-dimethylheptanoyl-CoA; major species at pH 7.3.

name: 1,2-di-(6Z,9Z-octadecadienoyl)-sn-glycero-3-phosphoethanolamine
definition: A 1,2-diacyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphoethanolamine in which the acyl substituent both at positions 1 and 2 is specified as (6Z,9Z)-octadecadienoyl respectively.

name: ethyl myristate
definition: A long-chain fatty acid ethyl ester resulting from the formal condensation of the carboxy group of myristic acid with the hydroxy group of ethanol.

name: L-selenohomocysteine zwitterion
definition: An L-alpha-amino acid zwitterion obtained from L-selenohomocysteine by transfer of a proton from the carboxy group to the amino group. It is the major species at pH 7.3.

name: ethyl linolenate
definition: A long-chain fatty acid ethyl ester resulting from the formal condensation of the carboxy group of linolenic acid with the hydroxy group of ethanol.

name: 2-hydroxytridecanoic acid
definition: A 2-hydroxy fatty acid that is tridecanoic acid substituted by  a hydroxy group at position 2.

name: 2-hydroxypentadecanoic acid
definition: A 2-hydroxy fatty acid that is pentadecanoic acid substituted by a hydroxy group at position 2.

name: 2-hydroxyheptadecanoic acid
definition: A 2-hydroxy fatty acid that is heptadecanoic acid (margaric acid) substituted by a hydroxy group at position 2.

name: 2-hydroxynonadecanoic acid
definition: A  2-hydroxy fatty acid that is nonadecanoic acid substituted by a hydroxy group at position 2.

name: ethyl stearidonate
definition: A long-chain fatty acid ethyl ester resulting from the formal condensation of the carboxy group of stearidonic acid with the hydroxy group of ethanol.

name: 2-hydroxyhenicosanoic acid
definition: A 2-hydroxy fatty acid that is henicosanoic acid substituted by a hydroxy group at position 2.

name: 2-hydroxytricosanoic acid
definition: A 2-hydroxy fatty acid that is tricosanoic acid substituted by a hydroxy group at position 2.

name: ethyl arachidate
definition: A long-chain fatty acid ethyl ester resulting from the formal condensation of the carboxy group of arachidic (icosanoic) acid with the hydroxy group of ethanol.

name: 2-hydroxypentacosanoic acid
definition: A 2-hydroxy fatty acid that is pentacosanoic acid substituted by a hydroxy group at position 2.

name: omega-hydroxyheptacosanoic acid
definition: A omega-hydroxy fatty acid that is  heptacosanoic acid substituted by a hydroxy group at position 27.

name: ethyl (11Z)-icosenoate
definition: A long-chain fatty acid ethyl ester resulting from the formal condensation of the carboxy group of (11Z)-icosenoic acid with the hydroxy group of ethanol.

name: omega-hydroxyoctacosanoic acid
definition: An omega-hydroxy fatty acid that is octacosanoic acid substituted by a hydroxy group at position 28.

name: omega-hydroxynonacosanoic acid
definition: A omega-hydroxy fatty acid that is nonacosanoic acid substituted by a hydroxy group at position 29.

name: (2S)-methylsuccinyl-CoA(5-)
definition: An acyl-CoA oxoanion arising from deprotonation of the phosphate, diphosphate and carboxy groups of (2S)-methylsuccinyl-CoA; major species at pH 7.3.

name: nonacosanoic acid
definition: A very long-chain fatty acid comprising of 29 carbon atoms.

name: omega-hydroxyhentriacontanoic acid
definition: An omega-hydroxy fatty acid that is hentriacontanoic acid (a C31 acid) substituted by a hydroxy group at position 31.

name: ethyl (13Z)-icosenoate
definition: A long-chain fatty acid ethyl ester resulting from the formal condensation of the carboxy group of (13Z)-icosenoic acid with the hydroxy group of ethanol.

name: omega-hydroxytritriacontanoic acid
definition: An omega-hydroxy fatty acid that is tritriacontanoic acid (C33) acid) substituted by a hydroxy group at position 33.

name: 10-methyldodecanoic acid
definition: A methyl-branched fatty acid that is dodecanoic acid (lauric acid) substituted by a methyl group at position 10.

name: ethyl arachidonate
definition: A long-chain fatty acid ethyl ester resulting from the formal condensation of the carboxy group of arachidonic acid with the hydroxy group of ethanol.

name: 14-methylhexadecanoic acid
definition: A methyl-branched fatty acid that is hexadecanoic acid (palmitic acid) substituted by a methyl group at position 14.

name: 16-methyloctadecanoic acid
definition: A methyl-branched fatty acid that is octadecanoic acid substituted by a methyl group at position 16.

name: ethyl (8Z,11Z,14Z,17Z)-icosatetraenoate

name: 18-methylicosanoic acid
definition: A methyl-branched fatty acid that is  arachidic acid substituted by a methyl group at position 18.

name: 20-methyldocosanoic acid
definition: A methyl-branched fatty acid that is docosanoic acid (behenic acid) substituted by a methyl group at position 20.

name: nitroxyl
definition: A nitrogen oxoacid consisting of an oxygen atom nouble-bonded to an NH group.

name: GDP-D-mannose

name: GDP-D-mannose(2-)
definition: A nucleotide-sugar oxoanion obtained by deprotonation of the diphosphate OH groups of GDP-D-mannose; major species at pH 7.3.

name: 22-methyltetracosanoic acid
definition: A methyl-branched fatty acid that is tetracosanoic acid (lignoceric acid) substituted by a methyl group at position 22.

name: 24-methylhexacosanoic acid
definition: A  methyl-branched fatty acid that is  cerotic acid substituted by a methyl group at position 24.

name: 26-methyloctacosanoic acid
definition: A methyl-branched fatty acid that is octacosanoic acid (montanic acid) substituted by a methyl group at position 26.

name: GDP-alpha-D-mannuronate
definition: A GDP-D-mannuronate in which the anomeric centre of the mannuronate fragment has alpha-configuration.

name: 28-methyltriacontanoic acid
definition: A methyl-branched fatty acid that is triacontanoic acid (melissic acid) substituted by a methyl group at position 28.

name: ethyl (11Z)-docosenoate
definition: A long-chain fatty acid ethyl ester resulting from the formal condensation of the carboxy group of (11Z)-docosenoic acid with the hydroxy group of ethanol.

name: 10-methylundecanoic acid
definition: A methyl-branched fatty acid that is  undecanoic acid substituted by a methyl group at position 10.

name: ethyl (13Z)-docosenoate

name: ethyl (4Z,7Z,10Z,13Z,16Z)-henicosapentaenoate

name: ethyl (4Z,7Z,10Z,13Z,16Z)-docosapentaenoate
definition: A long-chain fatty acid ethyl ester resulting from the formal condensation of the carboxy group of (4Z,7Z,10Z,13Z,16Z)-docosapentaenoic acid with the hydroxy group of ethanol.

name: hexane-2,5-diol
definition: A glycol that is hexane substituted by hydroxy groups at positions 2 and 5.

name: Jeffamine M-600
definition: A polyether that is a nine-membered polypropylene glycol terminated by an amino group at one end and a methoxyethyl termination at the other. A common crystallisation reagent.

name: 16-methylheptadecanoic acid
definition: A methyl-branched fatty acid that is heptadecanoic acid (margaric acid) substituted by a methyl group at position 16.

name: nogalonate(2-)
definition: An oxo monocarboxylic acid anion obtained by deprotonation of the carboxy as well as the 5-hydroxy group of nogalonic acid. It is the major microspecies at pH 7.3 (according to Marvin v 6.2.0.).

name: 18-methylnonadecanoic acid
definition: A methyl-branched fatty acid that is nonadecanoic acid substituted by a methyl group at position 18.

name: 12-deoxynogalonate(1-)
definition: An oxo monocarboxylic acid anion that is the conjugate base of 12-deoxynogalonic acid, obtained by deprotonation of the carboxy group. It is the major microspecies at pH 7.3 (according to Marvin v 6.2.0.).

name: 20-methylhenicosanoic acid
definition: A methyl-branched fatty acid that is  henicosanoic acid substituted by a methyl group at position 20.

name: (11Z)-18-hydroxyoctadecenoyl-CoA(4-)
definition: A monounsaturated fatty acyl-CoA(4-) obtained by deprotonation of the phosphate and diphosphate OH groups of (11Z)-18-hydroxyoctadecenoyl-CoA; major species at pH 7.3.

name: 22-methyltricosanoic acid

name: 24-methylpentacosanoic acid
definition: A methyl-branched fatty acid that is pentacosanoic acid substituted by a methyl group at position 24.

name: beta-D-Galp-(1->4)-beta-D-GlcpNAc-(1->3)-[beta-D-Galp-(1->4)-beta-D-GlcpNAc-(1->6)]-D-GalpNAc
definition: A branched amino pentasaccharide comprising two galactosyl-(1->4)-N-acetylglucosaminyl units linked beta(1->3) and beta(1->6) to a D-galactose residue.

name: 26-methylheptacosanoic acid
definition: A methyl-branched fatty acid that is heptacosanoic acid substituted by a methyl group at position 26.

name: 28-methylnonacosanoic acid
definition: A  methyl-branched fatty acid that is nonacosanoic acid substituted by a methyl group at position 28.

name: 12-methyltridecan-1-ol
definition: A long-chain primary fatty alcohol that is tridecan-1-ol substituted a methyl group at position 12.

name: 14-methylpentadecan-1-ol
definition: A long-chain primary fatty alcohol that is  pentadecan-1-ol substituted by a methyl group at position 14.

name: 16-methylheptadecan-1-ol
definition: A long-chain primary fatty alcohol that is heptadecan-1-ol substituted by a hydroxy group at position 1 and a methyl group at position 16.

name: dapdiamide E zwitterion
definition: A peptide zwitterion obtained by transfer of a proton from the carboxy to the amino terminus of dapdiamide C; major species at pH 7.3. NB Although the relative configuration of the epoxide moiety has been assigned as trans, it has not yet been established whether the absolute configuration is R,R (as drawn) or S,S.

name: 3-amino-N-(trans-3-carbamoyloxirane-2-carbonyl)-L-alanine zwitterion
definition: An amino acid zwitterion obtained by transfer of a proton from the carboxy to the amino group of 3-amino-N-(trans-3-carbamoyloxirane-2-carbonyl)-L-alanine; major species at pH 7.3. NB Although the relative configuration of the epoxide moiety has been assigned as trans, it has not yet been established whether the absolute configuration is R,R (as drawn) or S,S.

name: 18-methylnonadecan-1-ol
definition: A long-chain primary fatty alcohol that is  nonadecan-1-ol substituted by a methyl group at position 18.

name: 20-methylhenicosan-1-ol
definition: A long-chain primary fatty alcohol that is  henicosan-1-ol substituted by a methyl group at position 20.

name: 22-methyltricosan-1-ol
definition: A very long-chain primary fatty alcohol that is  tricosan-1-ol substituted by a methyl group at position 22.

name: 24-methylpentacosan-1-ol
definition: A very long-chain primary fatty alcohol that is  pentacosan-1-ol substituted by a methyl group at position 24.

name: 26-methylheptacosan-1-ol
definition: A very long-chain primary fatty alcohol that is  heptacosan-1-ol substituted by a methyl group at position 26.

name: 28-methylnonacosan-1-ol
definition: An ultra-long-chain primary fatty alcohol that is nonacosan-1-ol substituted by a methyl group at position 28.

name: 14-methylhexadecan-1-ol
definition: A long-chain primary fatty alcohol that is hexadecan-1-ol substituted by a methyl group at position 14.

name: 7-hydroxylaurate
definition: A hydroxy fatty acid anion that is the conjugate base of 7-hydroxylauric acid, obtained by deprotonation of the carboxy group; major species at pH 7.3.

name: 16-methyloctadecan-1-ol
definition: A long-chain primary fatty alcohol that is octadecan-1-ol (stearyl alcohol) substituted by a methyl group at position 16.

name: 18-methylicosan-1-ol
definition: A long-chain primary fatty alcohol that is icosan-1-ol substituted by a methyl group at position 18.

name: 20-methyldocosan-1-ol
definition: A long-chain primary fatty alcohol that is docosan-1-ol substituted by a methyl group at position 20.

name: omega-hydroxyphytanic acid
definition: A hydroxy fatty acid obtained by hydroxylation of one of the two terminal methyl groups of phytanic acid.

name: 22-methyltetracosan-1-ol
definition: A very long-chain primary fatty alcohol that is tetracosan-1-ol substituted by a methyl group at position 22.

name: 24-methylhexacosan-1-ol
definition: A very long-chain primary fatty alcohol that is  hexacosan-1-ol substituted by a methyl group at psotion 24.

name: 26-methyloctacosan-1-ol
definition: A very long-chain primary fatty alcohol that is octacosan-1-ol substituted by a methyl group at position 26.

name: 28-methyltriacontan-1-ol
definition: An ultra-long-chain primary fatty alcohol that is triacontan-1-ol substituted by a methyl group at position 28.

name: 30-methyldotriacontan-1-ol
definition: An ultra-long-chain primary fatty alcohol that is dotriacontan-1-ol substituted by a methyl group at position 30.

name: 32-methyltetratriacontan-1-ol
definition: An ultra-long-chain primary fatty alcohol that is tetratriacontan-1-ol substituted by a methyl group at position 32.

name: ethyl hexadecanoate

name: N-acetyl-D-muramoyl-L-alanine

name: ethyl palmitoleate
definition: A long-chain fatty acid ethyl ester resulting from the formal condensation of the carboxy group of  palmitoleic acid with the hydroxy group of ethanol.

name: ethyl (6Z,9Z,12Z)-hexadeca-6,9,12,15-tetraenoate
definition: A long-chain fatty acid ethyl ester resulting from the formal condensation of the carboxy group of (6Z,9Z,12Z,15Z)-hexadecatetraenoic acid with the hydroxy group of ethanol.

name: omega-hydroxy-15-methylpalmitic acid
definition: A hydroxy fatty acid obtained by hydroxylation of one of the two terminal methyl groups of isoheptadecanoic acid.

name: ethyl oleate
definition: A long-chain fatty acid ethyl ester resulting from the formal condensation of the carboxy group of  oleic acid  with the hydroxy group of ethanol.

name: N-acetyl-9-O-acetyl-alpha-neuraminic acid
definition: A member of the class of N-acetylneuraminic acids that is alpha-neuraminic acid which has acetylated on N-5 and O-9.

name: ethyl cis-vaccenate
definition: A long-chain fatty acid ethyl ester resulting from the formal condensation of the carboxy group of cis-vaccenic acid with the hydroxy group of ethanol.

name: alpha-Neup5,9Ac2-(2->6)-beta-D-Galp-(1->4)-beta-D-GlcpNAc
definition: A linear amino trisaccharide comprising an N,9-O-diacetyl-alpha-neuraminyl residue (2->6)-linked to a beta-D-galactosyl residue, which is in turn linked (1->4) to N-acetyl-beta-D-glucosamine.

name: triacontanal
definition: A long-chain fatty aldehyde resulting from the formal oxidation of the hydroxy group of triacontan-1-ol.

name: (11Z)-Delta(11)-fatty acyl-CoA(4-)
definition: Any Delta(11)-fatty acyl-CoA(4-)in which the Delta(11) double bond has Z configuration.

name: 11,12-saturated fatty acyl-CoA(4-)

name: (11E)-Delta(11)-fatty acyl-CoA(4-)
definition: Any Delta(11)-fatty acyl-CoA(4-) in which the double bond at the 11-12 position of the fatty acyl group has E configuration.

name: dotriacontanal
definition: A long-chain fatty aldehyde resulting from the formal oxidation of the hydroxy group of dotriacontan-1-ol.

name: 1,2-tetradecanediol
definition: A glycol that is tetradecane bearing two hydroxy substituents located at positions 1 and 2.

name: 7-demethylmitomycin B(2-)
definition: A phenolate anion obtained by removal of two protons from position C-8 and O-6 of 7-demethylmitomycin B. It is the major microspecies at pH 7.3 (according to Marvin v 6.2.0.).

name: 7-demethylmitomycin A(2-)
definition: A phenolate anion obtained by removal of two protons from position C-8 and O-6 of 7-demethylmitomycin A. It is the major microspecies at pH 7.3 (according to Marvin v 6.2.0.).

name: 1,2-octadecanediol
definition: A glycol that is octadecane bearing two hydroxy substituents located at positions 1 and 2.

name: 1,2-icosanediol
definition: A glycol that is icosane bearing two hydroxy substituents located at positions 1 and 2.

name: 1,2-hexacosanediol
definition: A glycol that is hexacosane bearing two hydroxy substituents located at positions 1 and 2.

name: 1,2-octacosanediol
definition: A glycol that is octacosane bearing two hydroxy substituents located at positions 1 and 2.

name: 13-hydroxy-alpha-tocopherol
definition: A member of the class of chromanols that is (+)-alpha-tocopherol bearing an additional hydroxy substituent at position 13'.

name: 13-hydroxy-gamma-tocopherol
definition: A member of the class of chromanols that is (+)-gamma-tocopherol bearing an additional hydroxy substituent at position 13'.

name: 1,2-triacontanediol
definition: A glycol that is triacontane bearing two hydroxy substituents located at positions 1 and 2.

name: cholesteryl nonadecenoate
definition: A cholesterol ester obtained by the formal condensation of  cholesterol with nonadecenoic acid (the position of double bond is unspecified).

name: cholesteryl henicosenoate
definition: A cholesterol ester obtained by the formal condensation of  cholesterol with henicosenoic acid (with the double bond at unspecified position).

name: 1,2-dipalmitoyl-sn-glycero-3-phospho-(1D-myo-inositol-5-phosphate)(3-)
definition: A 1-phosphatidyl-1D-myo-inositol 5-phosphate(3-) obtained by deprotonation of the phosphate OH groups of 1,2-dipalmitoyl-sn-glycero-3-phospho-(1D-myo-inositol-5-phosphate); major species at pH 7.3.

name: cholesteryl (5Z,8Z,11Z,14Z,17Z-eicosapentaenoate)
definition: A cholesterol ester obtained by the formal condensation of  cholesterol with all-cis-5,8,11,14,17-icosapentaenoic acid.

name: (4R)-ipsdienol
definition: A meroterpenoid that is (4R)-octa-2,7-dien-4-ol substituted at positions 2 and 6 by methyl and methylidene groups respectively.

name: (2E,6E,10E)-geranylgeranic acid
definition: A diterpenoid obtained by formal oxidation of the CH2OH group of (E,E,E)-geranylgeraniol to the corresponding carboxylic acid.

name: cholesteryl tetracosadienoate
definition: A  cholesterol ester obtained by the formal condensation of  cholesterol with tetracosadienoic acid (the position of the two double bonds is unspecified).

name: oleoyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphate(2-)
definition: A lysophosphatidate 18:1 in which the acyl group is specified as oleoyl (attached at either sn-1 or sn-2 position).

name: 1,2-dihexadecadienoyl-sn-glycerol
definition: A 1,2-diacyl-sn-glycerol in which both the acyl groups are specified as hexadecadienoyl (the position of the two double bonds is unspecified).

name: acarbose 7(IV)-phosphate(1-)
definition: An organophosphate oxoanion obtained by deprotonation of the phosphate OH groups as well as protonation of the amino group of acarbose 7(IV)-phosphate; major species at pH 7.3.

name: alpha-Neu5Ac-(2->3)-beta-D-Gal-(1->3)-beta-D-GalNAc-(1->4)-[alpha-Neu5Ac-(2->3)]-beta-D-Gal-(1->4)-beta-D-Glc-(1<->1')-Cer(d18:1/22:1)
definition: A sialopentaosylceramide consisting of a alpha-Neu5Ac-(2->3)-beta-D-Gal-(1->3)-beta-D-GalNAc-(1->4)-[alpha-Neu5Ac-(2->3)]-beta-D-Gal-(1->4)-beta-D-Glucosyl unit attached to a Cer(d18:1/22:1).

name: (2E,6E,10E,14E)-omega-hydroxygeranylgeranic acid
definition: A diterpenoid obtained by hydroxylation of one of the terminal methyl groups of (2E,6E,10E)-geranylgeranic acid.

name: 2-ethylacrylic acid
definition: An alpha,beta-unsaturated monocarboxylic acid that is acrylic acid in which the hydrogen at position 2 is substituted by an ethyl group.

name: 2-ethylacrylate
definition: A monocarboxylic acid anion that is the  conjugate base of 2-ethylacrylic acid.

name: 2-methylglutarate(2-)
definition: A dicarboxylic acid dianion obtained by deprotonation of the carboxy groups of 2-methylglutaric acid.

name: 2-aminoadipate(2-)
definition: A dicarboxylic acid dianion that is the conjugate base of 2-aminoadipic acid.

name: MS-566
definition: A member of the class of thienotriazolodiazepines that is the methyl ester of [(6R)-4-(4-chlorophenyl)-2,3,9-trimethyl-6H-thieno[3,2-f][1,2,4]triazolo[4,3-a][1,4]diazepin-6-yl]acetic acid.

name: alpha-Neu5Ac-(2->3)-beta-D-Gal-(1->3)-beta-D-GalNAc-(1->4)-[alpha-Neu5Ac-(2->3)]-beta-D-Gal-(1->4)-beta-D-Glc-(1<->1')-Cer(d18:1/23:0)
definition: A sialopentaosylceramide consisting of a alpha-Neu5Ac-(2->3)-beta-D-Gal-(1->3)-beta-D-GalNAc-(1->4)-[alpha-Neu5Ac-(2->3)]-beta-D-Gal-(1->4)-beta-D-Glucosyl unit attached to a Cer(d18:1/23:0).

name: alpha-Neu5Ac-(2->3)-beta-D-Gal-(1->3)-beta-D-GalNAc-(1->4)-[alpha-Neu5Ac-(2->3)]-beta-D-Gal-(1->4)-beta-D-Glc-(1<->1')-Cer(d18:1/24:2)
definition: A sialopentaosylceramide consisting of a alpha-Neu5Ac-(2->3)-beta-D-Gal-(1->3)-beta-D-GalNAc-(1->4)-[alpha-Neu5Ac-(2->3)]-beta-D-Gal-(1->4)-beta-D-Glucosyl unit attached to a Cer(d18:1/24:2), the position of the double bond in the tetracosadienoyl group being unspecified. .

name: (2E,6E,10E)-omega-hydroxyfarnesyl diphosphate
definition: A terpenyl phosphate obtained by hydroxylation of one of the terminal methyl groups of (2E,6E)-farnesyl diphosphate

name: alpha-Neu5Ac-(2->3)-beta-D-Gal-(1->4)-beta-D-Glc-(1<->1')-Cer(d18:1/22:1(13Z))
definition: A sialotriaosylceramide consisting of beta-D-GalNAc-(1->4)-[alpha-Neu5Ac-(2->3)]-beta-D-Gal-(1->4)-beta-D-Glc attached to the primary hydroxy function of ceramide(d18:1/22:1(13Z)).

name: alpha-Neu5Ac-(2->3)-beta-D-Gal-(1->4)-beta-D-Glc-(1<->1')-Cer(d18:1/23:0)
definition: A sialotriaosylceramide consisting of beta-D-GalNAc-(1->4)-[alpha-Neu5Ac-(2->3)]-beta-D-Gal-(1->4)-beta-D-Glc attached to the primary hydroxy function of ceramide(d18:1/23:0).

name: alpha-Neu5Ac-(2->3)-beta-D-Gal-(1->4)-beta-D-Glc-(1<->1')-Cer(d18:1/24:1(15Z))
definition: A sialotriaosylceramide consisting of beta-D-GalNAc-(1->4)-[alpha-Neu5Ac-(2->3)]-beta-D-Gal-(1->4)-beta-D-Glc attached to the primary hydroxy function of ceramide(d18:1/24:1(15Z)).

name: gamma-carboxy-L-glutamate(2-) residue
definition: An alpha-amino-acid residue anion obtained by deprotonation of the free carboxy groups of gamma-carboxy-L-glutamate residue; major species at pH 7.3.

name: alpha-Neu5Ac-(2->3)-beta-D-Gal-(1->4)-beta-D-Glc-(1<->1')-Cer(d18:1/24:2)
definition: A sialotriaosylceramide consisting of beta-D-GalNAc-(1->4)-[alpha-Neu5Ac-(2->3)]-beta-D-Gal-(1->4)-beta-D-Glc attached to the primary hydroxy function of ceramide(d18:1/24:2), the position of the double bond in the tetracosadienoyl group being unspecified.

name: 3-methylpalmitoyl-CoA
definition: A long-chain fatty acyl-CoA that results from the formal condensation of the thiol group of coenzyme A with the carboxy group of 3-methylpalmitic acid,

name: 1-octadecenoyl-2-octadecadienoyl-sn-glycero-3-phospho-(1'-sn-glycerol)
definition: A 1,2-diacyl-sn-glycero-3-phospho-(1'-sn-glycerol) in which the 1- and 2-acyl groups are specified as octadecenoyl and octadecadienoyl respectively.

name: 3-(methylthio)acryloyl-CoA(4-)
definition: An acyl-CoA(4-) oxoanion arising from deprotonation of the phosphate and diphosphate OH groups of 3-(methylthio)acryloyl-CoA; major species at pH 7.3.

name: 3-hydroxy-3-(methylthio)propanoyl-CoA(4-)
definition: An acyl-CoA(4-) oxoanion arising from deprotonation of the phosphate and diphosphate OH groups of 3-hydroxy-3-(methylthio)propanoyl; major species at pH 7.3.

name: 3-oxopropanoyl-CoA(4-)
definition: An acyl-CoA(4-) oxoanion arising from deprotonation of the phosphate and diphosphate OH groups of 3-oxopropanoyl-CoA; major species at pH 7.3.

name: sodium gluconate
definition: An organic sodium salt having D-gluconate as the counterion.

name: alpha-D-Gal-(1->4)-beta-D-Gal-(1->4)-beta-D-Glc-(1<->1')-Cer(d18:1/22:1)
definition: A glycotriaosylceramide having alpha-D-galactosyl-(1->4)-beta-D-galactosyl-(1->4)-beta-D-glucosyl as the glycotriaosyl component attached to the Cer(d18:1/22:1), the position of double bond in the docosenoyl group being unspecified.

name: alpha-D-Gal-(1->4)-beta-D-Gal-(1->4)-beta-D-Glc-(1<->1')-Cer(d18:1/23:0)
definition: A glycotriaosylceramide having alpha-D-galactosyl-(1->4)-beta-D-galactosyl-(1->4)-beta-D-glucosyl as the glycotriaosyl component attached to the Cer(d18:1/23:0).

name: 1-octadecenoyl-2-icosatetraenoyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphoethanolamine
definition: A 1,2-diacyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphoethanolamine in which the acyl groups specified at position 1 and 2 are octadecenoyl and icosatetraenoyl respectively.

name: 1,2-dioctadecadienoyl-sn-glycero-3-phospho-(1'-sn-glycerol)
definition: A 1,2-diacyl-sn-glycero-3-phospho-(1'-sn-glycerol) in which the acyl groups are specified as octadecadienoyl.

name: sphingadienine-1-phosphate
definition: A sphingoid 1-phosphate that is sphingadienine substituted by a phospho group at position 1.

name: anticapsin
definition: An alanine derivative that is L-alanine bearing a 5-oxo-7-oxabicyclo[4.1.0]hept-2-yl substituent at position 3.

name: N(1),N(8)-bis(sinapoyl)-spermidine(1+)
definition: An ammonium ion resulting from the protonation of the non-acylated nitrogen of N(1),N(8)-bis(sinapoyl)-spermidine. The major species at pH 7.3.
