name: N(1),N(8)-bis(coumaroyl)spermidine(1+)
definition: An ammonium ion resulting from the protonation of the non-acylated nitrogen of N(1),N(8)-bis(coumaroyl)-spermidine. The major species at pH 7.3.

name: trans-4-coumaroyl-CoA(4-)
definition: An acyl-CoA(4-) oxoanion arising from deprotonation of the phosphate and diphosphate OH groups of trans-4-coumaroyl-CoA; major species at pH 7.3.

name: N-hexacosadienoylsphingosine-1-phosphocholine
definition: A sphingomyelind18:1 in which   the total number of carbons in the fatty acyl group is 26 with 2 double bonds.

name: eltrombopag
definition: A hydrazine in which each nitrogen atom is substituted, one by a 3'-carboxy-2-hydroxy[1,1'-biphenyl]-3-yl group and the other by a 1-(3,4-dimethylphenyl)-3-methyl-5-oxo-1,5-dihydro-4H-pyrazol-4-ylidene group.  A small molecule agonist of the c-mpl (TpoR) receptor (the physiological target of the hormone thrombopoietin), it has been developed as a medication for conditions that lead to thrombocytopenia (abnormally low platelet counts).

name: EC 2.6.1.16 (glutamine--fructose-6-phosphate transaminase (isomerizing)) inhibitor
definition: An EC 2.6.1.* (transaminase) inhibitor that interferes with the action of glutamine--fructose-6-phosphate transaminase (isomerizing) (EC 2.6.1.19).

name: thrombopoietin receptor agonist
definition: An agonist that selectively binds to and activates the thrombopoietin receptor [myeloproliferative leukemia protein or CD110 (Cluster of Differentiation 110)].

name: 2,5-hexanedione
definition: A diketone that is hexane substituted by oxo groups at positions 2 and 5. It is a toxic metabolite of hexane and of 2-hexanone

name: N-tricosenoylsphing-4-enine-1-phosphocholine
definition: A  sphingomyelin in which the N-acyl group and sphingoid base are specified as tricosenoyl and sphingosine respectively.

name: N-henicosanoylsphinganine-1-phosphocholine
definition: A N-acylsphinganine-1-phosphocholine in which the acyl group specified is henicosanoyl.

name: 1-[(1Z,11Z)-octadecadienyl]-2-palmitoyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphoethanolamine
definition: A 1-(alk-1-enyl)-2-acyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphoethanolamine in which the alk-1-enyl and acyl groups are specified as (1Z,11Z)-octadecadienyl and palmitoyl respectively.

name: 1-[(1Z,11Z)-octadecadienyl]-2-oleoyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphoethanolamine
definition: A 1-(alk-1-enyl)-2-acyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphoethanolamine in which the alk-1-enyl and acyl groups are specified as (1Z,11Z)-octadecadienyl and oleoyl respectively.

name: 1-octadecadienyl-2-icosatetraenoyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphoethanolamine
definition: A 1-(alk-1-enyl)-2-acyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphoethanolamine in which the alk-1-enyl and acyl groups are specified as octadecadienyl and icosatetraenoyl respectively.

name: N-hexacosanoylsphinganine-1-phosphocholine
definition: A sphingomyelin 44:0  in which the N-acyl group and sphingoid base are specified as hexacosanoyl and sphinganine respectively.

name: N-tridecanoylsphingosine-1-phosphocholine
definition: A sphingomyelin d18:1 in which the acyl group specified is tridecanoyl.

name: N-tetradecenoylsphingosine-1-phosphocholine
definition: A sphingomyelin d18:1 in which the acyl group specified is tetradecenoyl.

name: 2'-phospho-nucleotide 5'-phosphate(3-) residue
definition: A organic anionic group obtained by deprotonation of the phosphate OH groups of 2'-phospho-nucleotide 5'-phosphate residue; major species at pH 7.3.

name: 6-[5]-ladderane-1-hexanol
definition: A fatty alcohol that is 1-hexanol substituted by a [5]-ladderane at position 6.

name: tridecanoyl-CoA
definition: A long-chain fatty acyl-CoA that results from the formal condensation of the thiol group of coenzyme A with the carboxy group of tridecanoic acid.

name: 2-carboxypalmitoyl-CoA
definition: A 2-carboxyacyl-CoA that results from the formal condensation of the thiol group of coenzyme A with the carboxy group of 2-carboxypalmitic acid.

name: 2-carboxymyristoyl-CoA
definition: A 2-carboxyacyl-CoA that results from the formal condensation of the thiol group of coenzyme A with the carboxy group of 2-carboxymyristic acid.

name: cobalt(1+)
definition: A monovalent inorganic cation obtained from cobalt.

name: ladderane
definition: Any carbopolycyclic compound comprising of two or more cyclobutane rings fuse together to form a series of varying lengths. These compounds have been found to occur naturally in certain anaerobic bacteria of the phylum Planctomycetes.

name: methyl-Co(2+)
definition: A cobalt coordination entity that is methane in which one of the hydrogens is replaced by cobalt(2+)

name: 2-carboxylauroyl-CoA
definition: A 2-carboxyacyl-CoA that results from the formal condensation of the thiol group of coenzyme A with one of the carboxy groups of 2-carboxylauric acid.

name: 1-palmitoyl-2-(11Z-octadecenoyl)-sn-glycero-3-phosphocholine
definition: A phosphatidylcholine 34:1 in which the 1- and 2-acyl groups are specified as hexadecanoyl (palmitoyl) and 11Z-octadecenoyl (cis-vaccenoyl) respectively.

name: alpha-Neup5Gc-(2->6)-beta-D-Galp-(1->4)-beta-D-Glcp
definition: An amino trisaccharide comprised of alpha-neuraminic acid, beta-D-galactopyranose and beta-D-glucopyranose residues linked sequentially (2->6) and (1->4).

name: (3R)-3,6-diaminohexanoic acid
definition: A diamino acid that is hexanoic acid substituted at positions 3 and 6 by amino groups.

name: alpha-Neup5Ac-(2->6)-beta-D-Galp-(1->4)-[alpha-L-Fucp-(1->3)]-beta-D-Glcp
definition: A branched amino tetrasaccharide comprising alpha-N-glycoloylneuraminyl, beta-D-galactosyl, beta-D-glucopyranosyl and alpha-L-fucosyl residue.

name: skin lightening agent
definition: Any cosmetic used to lighten the colour of skin by reducing the concentration of melanin.

name: alpha-Neup5Ac-(2->3)-beta-D-Galp-(1->4)-alpha-L-Fucp-(1->3)-D-Glcp
definition: An amino tetrasaccharide comprising alpha-N-acetylneuraminyl, beta-D-galactosyl, D-glucopyranosyl and alpha-L-fucosyl residue.

name: EC 1.10.3.* (oxidoreductase acting on diphenols and related substances as donors with oxygen as acceptor) inhibitor
definition: An EC 1.10.* (oxidoreductase acting on diphenols and related substances as donors) inhibitor that interferes with the action of any such enzyme using oxygen as acceptor (EC 1.10.3.*).

name: EC 1.10.3.1 (catechol oxidase) inhibitor
definition: Any EC 1.10.3.* (oxidoreductase acting on diphenols and related substances as donors with oxygen as acceptor) inhibitor that interferes with the action of catechol oxidase (EC 1.10.3.1).

name: EC 1.10.3.2 (laccase) inhibitor
definition: Any EC 1.10.3.* (oxidoreductase acting on diphenols and related substances as donors with oxygen as acceptor) inhibitor that interferes with the action of laccase (EC 1.10.3.2).

name: EC 1.13.11.24 (quercetin 2,3-dioxygenase) inhibitor
definition: Any EC 1.13.11.* (oxidoreductase acting on single donors and incorporating 2 O atoms) inhibitor that interferes with the action of quercetin 2,3-dioxygenase (EC 1.13.1.24).

name: EC 1.4.3.3 (D-amino-acid oxidase) inhibitor
definition: Any EC 1.4.3.* (oxidoreductase acting on donor CH-NH2 group, oxygen as acceptor) inhibitor that interferes with the action of D-amino-acid oxidase (EC 1.4.3.3).

name: EC 2.7.11.31 {[hydroxymethylglutaryl-CoA reductase (NADPH)] kinase} activator
definition: An effector that binds to and activates the enzyme [hydroxymethylglutaryl-CoA reductase (NADPH)] kinase (EC 2.7.11.31)

name: alpha-L-Fucp-(1->2)-beta-D-Galp-(1->4)-beta-D-GlcpNAc-(1->3)-beta-D-Galp-(1->4)-beta-D-GlcpNAc
definition: A branched amino pentasaccharide consisting of two repeating units of beta-D-Gal-(1->4)-beta-D-GlcNAc joined by a (1->3)-linkage with an alpha-L-fucosyl residue attached at the 2-position of the galactose residue at the non-reducing end.

name: beta-D-Galp3S-(1->4)-[alpha-L-Fucp-(1->3)]-beta-D-Glcp
definition: beta-D-Galp3S-(1->4)-[alpha-L-Fucp-(1->3)]-D-Glcp with beta configuration at the glucose anomeric centre.  A trisaccharide derivative that consists of beta-D-glucose having an alpha-L-fucosyl residue attached at position 3 and a 3-sulfated beta-D-galactosyl residue attached at position 4.

name: 2-methylhexadecanoic acid
definition: A methyl-branched fatty acid that is hexadecanoic (palmitic) acid bearing a methyl substituent at position 2.

name: 12-methyloctadecanoic acid
definition: A methyl-branched fatty acid that is octadecanoic (stearic) acid bearing a methyl substituent at position 12.

name: 3-methylundecanoic acid
definition: A methyl-branched fatty acid that is undecanoic acid bearing a methyl substituent at position 3.

name: N-(tert-butyldimethylsilyl)-N-methyltrifluoroacetamide
definition: An N-silyl compound that is N-methyltrifluoroacetamide in which the amide nitrogen is replaced by a tert-butyldimethylsilyl group.

name: N,N-dimethylformamide dimethyl acetal
definition: An acetal obtained by formal condensation of N,N-dimethylformamide with methanol. N,N-dimethylformamide dimethyl acetal is a derivatisation agent used in gas-chromatography applications

name: trimethylphenylammonium hydroxide
definition: A quaternary ammonium salt that is the hydroxide of trimethylphenylammonium. It is a derivatisation agent used in gas chromatography/mass spectrometry applications.

name: N-trimethylsilylimidazole
definition: A member of the class of imidazoles in which the hydrogen at position 1 is replaced by a trimethylsilyl group. N-trimethylsilylimidazole is a derivatisation agent used in gas chromatography/mass spectrometry applications.

name: N-methyl-N-(trimethylsilyl)trifluoroacetamide
definition: An N-silyl compound that is N-methyltrifluoroacetamide in which the amide nitrogen is replaced by a trimethylsilyl group. N-methyl-N-(trimethylsilyl)trifluoroacetamide is a derivatisation agent used in gas chromatography/mass spectrometry applications.

name: pentafluorobenzenes
definition: Any member of the class of fluorobenzenes carrying five fluorine substituents at unspecified positions.

name: tetrafluorobenzene
definition: Any member of the class of fluorobenzenes carrying four fluorine substituents at unspecified positions.

name: N,O-bis(trimethylsilyl)trifluoroacetamide
definition: A silyl ether that is the N,O-bis(trimethylsilyl) derivative of trifluoroacetamide. N,O-bis(trimethylsilyl)trifluoroacetamide is a derivatisation agent used in gas chromatography/mass spectrometry applications.

name: hexamethyldisilazane
definition: An N-silyl compound obtained from ammonia by replacement of two of the hydrogens with trimethylsilyl groups.  Hexamethyldisilazane is a derivatisation agent used in gas chromatography mass spectrometry applications.

name: chlorotrimethylsilane
definition: A silyl chloride consisting of a central silicon atom covalently bound to one chloro and three methyl groups. Chlorotrimethylsilane is a derivatisation agent used in gas chromatography/mass spectrometry applications.

name: N-(trimethylsilyl)diethylamine
definition: An N-silyl compound that is diethylamine in which the amino hydrogen is replaced by a trimethylsilyl group. N-(trimethylsilyl)diethylamine is a derivatisation agent used in gas chromatography/mass spectrometry applications.

name: tert-butyldimethylsilyl chloride
definition: A silyl chloride consisting of a central silicon atom covalently bound to one chloro, one tert-butyl and two methyl groups. tert-Butyldimethylsilyl chloride is a derivatisation agent used in gas chromatography/mass spectrometry applications.

name: 15-dehydroprostaglandin A1(1-)
definition: A prostaglandin carboxylic acid anion that is the conjugate base of 15-dehydro-prostaglandin A1, obtained by deprotonation of the carboxy group.; major species at pH 7.3.

name: 12-methyloctadecanoyl-CoA
definition: A long-chain fatty acyl-CoA that results from the formal condensation of the thiol group of coenzyme A with the carboxy group of 12-methyloctadecanoic acid.

name: 2-methylhexadecanoyl-CoA
definition: A long-chain fatty acyl-CoA that results from the formal condensation of the thiol group of coenzyme A with the carboxy group of 2-methylhexadecanoic acid.

name: 3-methylundecanoyl-CoA
definition: A long-chain fatty acyl-CoA that results from the formal condensation of the thiol group of coenzyme A with the carboxy group of 3-methylundecanoic acid.

name: 1-oleoyl-2-stearoyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphoethanolamine
definition: A 1,2-diacyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphoethanolamine in which the acyl substituents at positions 1 and 2 are specified as oleoyl and stearoyl respectively.

name: isomyristoyl-CoA
definition: A long-chain fatty acyl-CoA that results from the formal condensation of the thiol group of coenzyme A with the carboxy group of isomyristic acid.

name: dapagliflozin
definition: A C-glycosyl comprising beta-D-glucose in which the anomeric hydroxy group is replaced by a 4-chloro-3-(4-ethoxybenzyl)phenyl group. Used (in the formo f its propanediol monohydrate) to improve glycemic control, along with diet and exercise, in adults with type 2 diabetes.

name: dapagliflozin propanediol monohydrate
definition: A hydrate that consists of dapagliflozin compounded with (S)-propylene glycol and hydrate in a (1:1:1) ratio. Used to improve glycemic control, along with diet and exercise, in adults with type 2 diabetes.

name: ascorbyl dipalmitate
definition: A fatty acid ester obtained by the formal condensation of the hydroxy groups at positions 5 and 6 of L-ascorbic acid with two molecules of  palmitic acid.

name: cedr-8(15)-en-9-ol
definition: A sesquiterpenoid that is cedr-8(15)-ene substituted by a hydroxy group at position 9.

name: Harvoni
definition: A mixture composed of ledipasvir and sofosbuvir, which is used for the treatment of chronic hepatitis C genotype 1 infection.

name: sofosbuvir
definition: A nucleotide conjugate that is used in combination with ledipasvir (under the trade name Harvoni) for the treatment of chronic hepatitis C genotype 1 infection.

name: methylsqualene
definition: A squalene triterpenoid consisting of  squalene substituted by a methyl group at unspecified position.

name: KT 5720
definition: An organic heterooctacyclic compound that is 1H,1'H-2,2'-biindole in which the nitrogens have undergone formal oxidative coupling to positions 2 and 5 of hexyl (3S)-3-hydroxy-2-methyltetrahydrofuran-3-carboxylate (the 2R,3S,5S product), and in which the 3 and 3' positions of the biindole moiety have also undergone formal oxidative coupling to positions 3 and 4 of 1,5-dihydro-2H-pyrrol-2-one.

name: demethylsqualene
definition: A squalene triterpenoid obtained by the loss of a methyl group from squalene.

name: cis-sesquisabinene hydrate
definition: A sesquiterpenoid that is bicyclo[3.1.0]hexane substituted by a methyl and hydroxy group at position 3 and a 2-methylhept-2-en-6-yl group at position 4.

name: Lys-Thr-Trp-Gly-Lys-Asn-Leu-Val-Phe
definition: An oligopeptide composed of L-lysine, L-threonine, L-tryptophan, glycine, L-asparagine, L-leucine, L-valine and L-phenylalanine joined in sequence by peptide linkages; corresponds to the sequence in the yellow feverspecific peptide epitope K9F.

name: ledipasvir
definition: A benzimidazole derivative that is used in combination with sofosbuvir (under the trade name Harvoni) for the treatment of chronic hepatitis C genotype 1 infection.

name: O-fumaryl-L-carnitine
definition: An O-acyl-L-carnitine in which the acyl group is specified as fumaryl.

name: EC 2.7.11.11 (cAMP-dependent protein kinase) inhibitor
definition: An EC 2.7.11.* (protein-serine/threonine kinase) inhibitor that interferes with the action of cAMP-dependent protein kinase (EC 2.7.11.11).

name: O-valeroyl-L-carnitine
definition: An O-acyl-L-carnitine in which the acyl group specified is valeroyl.

name: Lys-Thr-Trp-Gly-Lys-Asn-Leu-Val-Val
definition: An oligopeptide composed of L-lysine, L-threonine, L-tryptophan, glycine, L-asparagine, L-leucine, L-valine and L-valine joined in sequence by peptide linkages; synthetic variant K9V of the yellow fever specific peptide epitope K9F.

name: 4-saturated trans-2-enoyl-CoA(4-)
definition: Any 2,3-trans-enoyl CoA(4-) that is also saturated at position 4.

name: ethyl isothiocyanate
definition: An isothiocyanate having an ethyl group attached to the nitrogen.

name: (2E,4Z)-dienoyl-CoA(4-)
definition: A 2,3-trans-enoyl CoA(4-) obtained by deprotonation of the phosphate and diphosphate functions of any (2E,4Z)-dienoyl-CoA; major species at pH 7.3.

name: 4,5-saturated-trans-2-enoyl-CoA(4-)
definition: A 2,3-trans-enoyl CoA(4-) obtained by deprotonation of the phosphate and diphosphate functions of any 4,5-saturated-trans-2-cis-4-dienoyl-CoA; major species at pH 7.3.

name: KT 5823
definition: An organic heterooctacyclic compound that is 1H,1'H-2,2'-biindole in which the nitrogens have undergone formal oxidative coupling to positions 2 and 5 of methyl (3R)-3-methoxy-2-methyltetrahydrofuran-3-carboxylate (the 2S,3R,5R product), and in which the 3 and 3' positions of the biindole moiety have also undergone formal oxidative coupling to positions 3 and 4 of 1-methyl-1,5-dihydro-2H-pyrrol-2-one.

name: phenyl isothiocyanate
definition: An isothiocyanate having a phenyl group attached to the nitrogen; used for amino acid sequencing in the Edman degradation.

name: 2-hydroxypentanoyl-L-carnitine
definition: An O-acyl-L-carnitine in which the acyl group specified is 2-hydroxypentanoyl.

name: 3-hydroxy-(9Z)-hexadecenoyl-L-carnitine
definition: A O-hydroxyhexadecenoyl-L-carnitine in which the acyl group specified is 3-hydroxy-(9Z)-hexadecenoyl.

name: N-acetyl-alpha-L-talosaminuronic acid
definition: A carbohydrate acid derivative that is alpha-L-talosaminuronic acid in which the hydroxy group at position 2 is substituted by an acetamido group.

name: ethyl isocyanate
definition: An isocyanate having an ethyl group attached to the nitrogen.

name: trans-3-cis-5-octadienoyl-CoA(4-)
definition: A trans-3,cis-5-dienoyl-CoA(4-) obtained by deprotonation of the phosphate and diphosphate functions of trans-3-cis-5-octadienoyl-CoA; major species at pH 7.3.

name: glyinflanin H
definition: A chromenol that is 2,2-dimethyl-2H-chromen-5-ol substituted by a 6-hydroxy-1-benzofuran-2-yl group at position 6.

name: (3E,5Z)-dienoyl-CoA(4-)
definition: A trans-3-enoyl CoA(4-) obtained by deprotonation of the phosphate and diphosphate functions of any (3E,5Z)-dienoyl-CoA; major species at pH 7.3.

name: 6-saturated-trans,trans-2,4-dienoyl-CoA(4-)
definition: Any trans,trans-2,4-dienoyl-CoA(4-) that is also saturated at position 6.

name: EC 2.7.11.12 (cGMP-dependent protein kinase) inhibitor
definition: An EC 2.7.11.* (protein-serine/threonine kinase) inhibitor that interferes with the action of cGMP-dependent protein kinase (EC 2.7.11.12).

name: KT 5926
definition: An organic heterooctacyclic compound that is 5-propoxy-1H,1'H-2,2'-biindole in which the nitrogens have undergone formal oxidative coupling to positions 2 and 5 of methyl (3R)-3-hydroxy-2-methyltetrahydrofuran-3-carboxylate (the 2S,3R,5R product), and in which the 3 and 3' positions of the biindole moiety have also undergone formal oxidative coupling to positions 3 and 4 of 1,5-dihydro-2H-pyrrol-2-one.

name: anthraquinone-2,6-disulfonic acid
definition: A member of the class of anthraquinones that is 9,10-anthraquinone substituted at positions 2 and 6 by sulfo groups.

name: sodium polyanethol sulfonate macromolecule
definition: An organic sodium salt that is a macromolecule composed of repeating sodium polyanethol sulfonate units. For the sake of clarity, a representative structure is shown; there may also be some of the 3-sulfonated analogue present.

name: 2'-O-methylphaseollinisoflavan
definition: A methoxyisoflavan that is the 2'-O-methyl derivative of (-)-phaseollinisoflavan.

name: sodium polyanethol sulfonate polymer
definition: A vinyl polymer, composed of sodium polyanethol sulfonate macromolecules.

name: polyanethol sulfonate macromolecule
definition: A polyanionic polymer obtained by global deprotonation of the sulfo groups of polyanethol sulfonic acid. For the sake of clarity, a representative structure is shown; there may also be some of the 3-sulfonated analogue present.

name: polyanethol sulfonic acid macromolecule
definition: A vinyl polymer macromolecule composed of repeating polyanethol sulfonic acid units. For the sake of clarity, a representative structure is shown; there may also be some of the 3-sulfonated analogue present.

name: polyanethol sulfonic acid polymer
definition: A vinyl polymer, composed of polyanethol sulfonic acid macromolecules.

name: paraben
definition: A 4-hydroxybenzoate ester in which the esterifying alcohol is an alkanol (in diagram, R = alkyl). Commonly used as preservatives in cosmetic and pharmaceutical products.

name: 4'-O-methylbavachalcone
definition: A member if the class of  chalcones that is trans-chalcone substituted by a prenyl group at position 5', a hydroxy group at position 2' and methoxy groups at positions 4' and 4 respectively.

name: quercetin 5,7,3',4'-tetramethyl ether
definition: A tetramethoxyflavone that is  the 5,7,3',4'-tetramethy-derivative of quercetin.

name: kinocoumarin
definition: A member of the class of  coumarins that is 2H,8H-pyrano[3,2-g]chromen-2-one substituted by geminal methyl groups at position 8, a hydroxy group at position 5, and a 2-methylbut-3-en-2-yl group at positions 7 and 10.

name: 5,6,7,8-tetramethoxy-3',4'-methylenedioxyisoflavone
definition: A methoxyisoflavone that is isoflavone substituted by methoxy groups at positions 5, 6, 7 and 8 and methylenedioxy group across positions 3' and 4'.

name: (2S)-7,4'-dihydroxy-8-geranylflavanone
definition: A dihydroxyflavanone  that is (2S)-flavanone substituted by hydroxy groups at position 7 and 4' and a geranyl group at position 8.

name: aminocoumarin
definition: Any coumarin carrying at least one amino substituent.

name: ristocetin
definition: A heterodetic cyclic peptide  that is produced by species of Amycolatopsis and Nocardia.

name: 7,8-dihydroxanthopterin
definition: A dihydropterin that is the 7,8-dihydro derivative of xanthopterin.

name: 3-(1-cyanoethyl)benzoic acid
definition: Benzoic acid meta-substituted with a 1-cyanoethyl group.

name: glycitein 7-O-beta-D-(2'',4'',6''-O-triacetyl)glucopyranoside
definition: A glycosyloxyisoflavone that is the 2'',4'',6''-O-triacetyl- derivative of glycitin.

name: 12-(phosphonooxy)octadecanoic acid
definition: A carboxyalkyl phosphate that is octadecanoic acid carrying a phosphonooxy substituent at position 12.

name: 12-(phosphonooxy)octadecanoate(3-)
definition: An organophosphate oxoanion obtained by deprotonation of the carboxy and phosphate OH groups of 12-(phosphonooxy)octadecanoic acid; major species at pH 7.3.

name: formononetin 7-O-rutinoside
definition: A 4'-methoxyisoflavone that is the 7-O-rutinosyl derivative of formononetin.

name: (9E)-12-(phosphonooxy)octadecenoate(3-)
definition: An organophosphate oxoanion obtained by deprotonation of the carboxy and phosphate OH groups of 12-phosphonooxy-(9E)-octadecenoic acid; major species at pH 7.3.

name: cobalt(II) acetate
definition: A cobalt salt in which the cobalt metal is in the +2 oxidation state and the counter-anion is acetate.

name: beta-amino acid ester
definition: An amino acid ester resulting from the formal condensation of the carboxy group of a beta-amino acid with the hydroxy group of an alcohol or phenol.

name: (9Z)-12-(phosphonooxy)octadecenoic acid
definition: A carboxyalkyl phosphate that is (9Z)-octadecenoic (oleic) acid carrying a phosphonooxy substituent at position 12.

name: (9Z)-12-(phosphonooxy)octadecenoate(3-)
definition: An organophosphate oxoanion obtained by deprotonation of the carboxy and phosphate OH groups of (9Z)-12-(phosphonooxy)octadecenoic acid; major species at pH 7.3.

name: cyanidin 3-O-(2''-O-galloyl-beta-D-galactopyranoside)
definition: An anthocyanin cation that is cyanidin attached to a 2''-O-galloyl-beta-D-galactopyranosyl residue at position 3 via a glycosidic linkage.

name: (9S,10R)-10-hydroxy-9-(phosphonatooxy)octadecanoate
definition: An organophosphate oxoanion obtained by deprotonation of the carboxy and phosphate OH groups of (9S,10R)-10-hydroxy-9-(phosphonatooxy)octadecanoic acid; major species at pH 7.3.

name: (2S)-eriodictyol 7-O-(6''-O-galloyl)-beta-D-glucopyranoside
definition: A monosaccharide derivative that is  eriodictyol attached to a (6''-O-galloyl)-beta-D-glucopyranosyl residue at position 7 via a glycosidic linkage.

name: carboxymethylcellulose
definition: A polysaccharide derivative that is cellulose in which carboxymethyl groups are bound to some of the hydroxyl groups of the glucopyranose monomers.

name: (9S,10R)-dihydroxyoctadecanoate
definition: A hydroxy fatty acid anion that is the conjugate base of (9S,10R)-dihydroxyoctadecanoic acid, obtained by deprotonation of the carboxy group; major species at pH 7.3.

name: 3-hydroxytetradecanoic acid
definition: A 3-hydroxy fatty acid that is tetradecanoic (myristic) acid substituted at position 3 by a hydroxy group

name: luteolin 7-O-beta-D-glucoside-4'-(Z-2-methyl-2-butenoate)
definition: An enoate ester obtained by the formal condensation of the 4'-hydroxy group of luteolin 7-O-beta-D-glucoside with the carboxy group of angelic acid.

name: (9Z)-12-hydroxyoctadec-9-enoate
definition: A hydroxy fatty acid anion that is the conjugate base of (9Z)-12-hydroxyoctadec-9-enoic acid, obtained by deprotonation of the carboxy group; major species at pH 7.3.

name: quercetin 3-(6''-p-hydroxybenzoylgalactoside)
definition: A benzoate ester obtained by the formal condensation of 6''-hydroxy group of quercetin 3-O-beta-D-galactopyranoside with the carboxy group of 4-hydroxybenzoic acid.

name: (9E)-12-hydroxyoctadec-9-enoate
definition: A hydroxy fatty acid anion that is the conjugate base of (9E)-12-hydroxyoctadec-9-enoic acid, obtained by deprotonation of the carboxy group; major species at pH 7.3.

name: methyl 3,4-dicaffeoylquinate
definition: An  alkyl caffeate ester obtained by the formal condensation of hydroxy groups at positions 3 and 4 of methylquinate with  two molecules of trans-caffeic acid respectively.

name: Akynzeo
definition: A mixture composed of netupitant and palonosetron hydrochloride, which is used to treat nausea and vomiting in patients undergoing cancer chemotherapy.

name: netupitant
definition: A monocarboxylic acid amide obtained by formal condensation of the carboxy group of 2-[3,5-bis(trifluoromethyl)phenyl]-2-methylpropanoic acid with the secondary amino group of N-methyl-4-(2-methylphenyl)-6-(4-methylpiperazin-1-yl)pyridin-3-amine; an antiemetic used in combination with palonosetron hydrochloride (under the trade name Akynzeo) to treat nausea and vomiting in patients undergoing cancer chemotherapy.

name: dihydroconiferyl alcohol glucoside
definition: A primary alcohol that is dihydroconiferyl alcohol attached to a beta-D-glucopyranosyl residue at position 1 via a glycosidic linkage.

name: palonosetron hydrochloride
definition: A hydrochloride obtained by combining palonosetron with one molar equivalent of hydrogen chloride; an antiemetic used in combination with netupitant (under the trade name Akynzeo) to treat nausea and vomiting in patients undergoing cancer chemotherapy.

name: 15-hydroxysolavetivone
definition: A sesquiterpenoid that is solavetivone substituted by a hydroxy group at position 15.

name: 3-hydroxylubimin
definition: A vetispirane sesquiterpenoid that is  lubimin substituted by a hydroxy group at position 3.

name: palonosetron
definition: An organic heterotricyclic compound that is an antiemetic used (as its hydrochloride salt) in combination with netupitant (under the trade name Akynzeo) to treat nausea and vomiting in patients undergoing cancer chemotherapy.

name: 9'-hydroxyabscisic acid
definition: An  oxo monocarboxylic acid that is (+)-abscisic acid substituted by a hydroxy group at position 9'.

name: palonosetron(1+)
definition: An organic cation obtained by protonation of the endocyclic tertiary amino group of palonosetron.

name: prostaglandin G2 2-glyceryl ester
definition: A 2-monoglyceride obtained by formal condensation of the carboxy group of prostaglandin G2 with the 2-hydroxy group of glycerol.

name: prostaglandin H2 2-glyceryl ester
definition: A 2-monoglyceride obtained by formal condensation of the carboxy group of prostaglandin H2 with the 2-hydroxy group of glycerol.

name: gamma-aminooctyl-GTP
definition: A nucleoside triphosphate analogue that is GTP in which one of the OH groups at the gamma-position of the triphosphate is replaced by an 8-aminooctylamino group.

name: mirificin
definition: A flavone C-glycoside that is 7,4'-dihydroxyflavone substituted by a 6-O-[(2R,3R,4R)-3,4-dihydroxy-4-(hydroxymethyl)oxolan-2-yl]-beta-D-glucopyranosyl residue at position 8 via a C-glycosidic linkage.

name: euchrenone-a7
definition: A trihydroxyflavanone that is flavanone substituted by hydroxy groups at positions 7, 2' and 4' and a prenyl group at position 8.

name: nintedanib esylate
definition: An organosulfonate salt obtained by combining nintedanib with one molar equivalent of ethanesulfonic acid. A kinase inhibitor used for the treatment of idiopathic pulmonary fibrosis and cancer.

name: sphingoid-1-phosphocholine(1+)
definition: A quaternary ammonium ion that is a deacylated sphingomyelin with undefined sphingoid base.

name: nintedanib(1+)
definition: An organic cation obtained by protonation of nintedanib.

name: 11-epi-prostaglandin F2alpha(1-)
definition: A prostaglandin carboxylic acid anion that is the conjugate base of 11-epi-prostaglandin F2alpha, obtained by deprotonation of the carboxy group;  major species at pH 7.3.

name: prostaglandin D2 ethanolamide
definition: An N-acylethanolamine resulting from the formal condensation of the carboxy group of prostaglandin D2 with the amino group of ethanolamine.

name: 11beta-prostaglandin F2alpha ethanolamide
definition: An N-acylethanolamine resulting from the formal condensation of the carboxy group 11-epi-prostaglandin F2alpha with the amino group of ethanolamine.

name: finafloxacin
definition: A quinolone that is 4-oxo-1,4-dihydroquinoline-3-carboxylic acid which is substituted at positions 1, 6, 7 and 8 by cyclopropyl, fluoro, hexahydropyrrolo[3,4-b][1,4]oxazin-6-yl and cyano groups respectively; an antibiotic used for treatment of acute otitis externa (swimmer's ear) caused by the bacteria Pseudomonas aeruginosa and Staphylococcus aureus.

name: Viekira Pak
definition: A mixture composed of dasabuvir sodium hydrate, ombitasvir, paritaprevir and ritonavir which is used for treatment of chronic hepatitis C virus (HCV) genotype 1 infection as well as cirrhosis of the liver.

name: dasabuvir sodium hydrate
definition: A hydrate that is the monohydrate form of dasabuvir sodium; used in combination with ombitasvir, paritaprevir and ritonavir (under the trade name Viekira Pak) for treatment of chronic hepatitis C virus genotype 1 infection as well as cirrhosis of the liver.

name: dasabuvir sodium
definition: An organic sodium salt having dasabuvir(1-) as the counterion; used (in the form of the hydrate) in combination with ombitasvir, paritaprevir and ritonavir (under the trade name Viekira Pak) for treatment of chronic hepatitis C virus genotype 1 infection as well as cirrhosis of the liver.

name: dasabuvir(1-)
definition: An organic nitrogen anion obtained by deprotonation of the sulfonamide nitrogen of dasabuvir.

name: dasabuvir
definition: A member of the class of pyrimidone, which is (as the monohydrate of its sodium salt) in combination with ombitasvir, paritaprevir and ritonavir (under the trade name Viekira Pak) for treatment of chronic hepatitis C virus genotype 1 infection as well as cirrhosis of the liver.

name: ombitasvir
definition: A dipeptide derivative which is used which is in combination with dasabuvir sodium hydrate, paritaprevir and ritonavir (under the trade name Viekira Pak) for treatment of chronic hepatitis C virus genotype 1 infection as well as cirrhosis of the liver.

name: dihydroxycholanic acid
definition: Any member of the class of cholanic acids carrying two hydroxy substituents at unspecified positions.

name: hepatitis C virus nonstructural protein 5A inhibitor
definition: Any inhibitor of hepatitis C virus nonstructural protein 5A.

name: 1-palmitoleoyl-2-stearoyl-sn-glycero-3-phospho-(1'-sn-glycerol)
definition: A 1,2-diacyl-sn-glycero-3-phospho-(1'-sn-glycerol) in which the 1- and 2-acyl groups are specified as (9Z)-hexadec-9-enoyl (pamitoleoyl) and octadecanoyl (stearoyl) respectively.

name: L-iduronic acid
definition: Any iduronic acid having L-configuration.

name: paritaprevir
definition: An azamacrocycle which is used which is in combination with dasabuvir sodium hydrate, ombitasvir and ritonavir (under the trade name Viekira Pak) for treatment of chronic hepatitis C virus genotype 1 infection as well as cirrhosis of the liver.

name: O-[(9Z)-hexadecenoyl]-L-serine residue
definition: An alpha-amino-acid residue that is an L-serine residue in which the alcoholic hydroxy group has been acylated with a (9Z)-hexadec-9-enoyl group.

name: 1-(5Z,8Z,11Z,14Z,17Z)-docosapent-5,8,11,14,17-enoyl-2-stearoyl-sn-glycero-3-phospho-1D-myo-inositol
definition: 1-phosphatidyl-1D-myo-inositol in which the 1- and 2-acyl groups are specified as (5Z,8Z,11Z,14Z,17Z)-docosapent-5,8,11,14,17-enoyl and octadecanoyl (stearoyl) respectively.

name: Zerbaxa
definition: A mixture composed of tazobactam sodium and ceftolozane sulfate which is used for treatment of complicated intra-abdominal infections and complicated urinary tract infections.

name: tazobactam sodium
definition: An organic sodium salt having tazobactam(1-) as the counterion; used in combination with ceftolozane sulfate for treatment of complicated intra-abdominal infections and complicated urinary tract infections.

name: tazobactam(1-)
definition: A penicillinate anion that is the conjugate base of tazobactam, obtained by deprotonation of the carboxy group.

name: 9,10-epoxyoctadecanoate
definition: An epoxystearate resulting from the deprotonation of the carboxy group of 9,10-epoxyoctadecanoic acid (i.e. conjugate base of 9,10-epoxyoctadecanoic acid); the major species at pH 7.3.

name: peramivir hydrate
definition: A hydrate that is the trihydrate form of peramivir. Used for the treatment of acute uncomplicated influenza in patients 18 years and older who have been symptomatic for no more than two days.

name: N-arachidonoylsphingosine
definition: A N-acylsphingosine in which the ceramide N-acyl group is specified as arachidonoyl.

name: N-icosenoylsphingosine
definition: An N-acylsphingosine in which the acyl group contains 20 carbons and 1 double bond of unknown position.

name: N-icosenoylsphinganine
definition: A dihydroceramide in which the acyl group contains 20 carbons and 1 double bond of unknown position.

name: N-icosenoylphytosphingosine
definition: A phytoceramide in which the acyl group contains  20 carbons and 1 double bond of unknown position. Formula:C38H74NO4

name: alpha-hydroxyglycino group
definition: A C-terminal alpha-amino-acid residue that is a glycino group in which one of the alpha-hydrogens is replaced by a hydroxy group.

name: N-oleoylphytosphingosine
definition: A phytoceramide in which the N-acyl group is specified as oleoyl (9Z-octadecenoyl).

name: 3-hydroxytetradecanoyl-CoA
definition: A 3-hydroxy fatty acyl-CoA that results from the formal condensation of the thiol group of coenzyme A with the carboxy group of 3-hydroxytetradecanoic acid.

name: N-arachidonoylsphinganine
definition: A dihydroceramide in which the N-acyl group is specified as arachidonoyl.

name: N-arachidonoylphytosphingosine
definition: A phytoceramide in which the N-acyl group is specified as arachidonoyl.

name: 12-hydroxyoctadecanoic acid
definition: A hydroxy fatty acid that is stearic acid bearing a hydroxy substituent at position 12.

name: 12-hydroxyoctadecanoyl-CoA
definition: A hydroxy fatty acyl-CoA that results from the formal condensation of the thiol group of coenzyme A with the carboxy group of 12-hydroxyoctadecanoic acid.

name: N-acetyl-D-methionine
definition: An N-acetyl-D-amino acid in which the amino acid is D-methionine.

name: 15-hydroxypentadecanoyl-CoA
definition: A hydroxy fatty acyl-CoA that results from the formal condensation of the thiol group of coenzyme A with the carboxy group of 15-hydroxypentadecanoic acid.

name: omega-hydroxy fatty acyl-CoA
definition: A hydroxy fatty acyl-CoA that results from the formal condensation of the thiol group of coenzyme A with the carboxy group of any omega-hydroxy fatty acid.

name: 16-hydroxyhexadecanoyl-CoA
definition: An omega-hydroxy fatty acyl-CoA that results from the formal condensation of the thiol group of coenzyme A with the carboxy group of 16-hydroxyhexadecanoic acid.

name: 9-decenoyl-CoA
definition: A monounsaturated fatty acyl-CoA that results from the formal condensation of the thiol group of coenzyme A with the carboxy group of 9-decenoic acid.

name: N-acyllysophosphatidylethanolamine(1-)
definition: An anionic phospholipid obtained by deprotonation of the phosphate group of any N-acyllysophosphatidylethanolamine; major species at pH 7.3.

name: N-palmitoyl-1-oleoyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphoethanolamine(1-)
definition: An N-acyllysophosphatidylethanolamine(1-) in which the N-acyl group is specified as palmitoyl (hexadecanoyl) while the phosphatidyl acyl group is specified as oleoyl (9Z-octadecenoyl); major species at pH 7.3.

name: (2S)-2-methylheptadecanoic acid
definition: A methyl-branched fatty acid that is heptadecanoic (margaric) acid bearing a methyl substituent at position 2 (the S-enantiomer).

name: N-stearoyl-1-oleoyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphoethanolamine(1-)
definition: An N-acyllysophosphatidylethanolamine(1-) in which the N-acyl group is specified as stearoyl (octadecanoyl) while the phosphatidyl acyl group is specified as oleoyl (9Z-octadecenoyl); major species at pH 7.3.

name: N-acetyl-D-methionine(1-)
definition: A D-alpha-amino acid anion resulting from the removal of the proton from the carboxy group of N-acetyl-D-methionine.

name: N-icosanoyl-1-oleoyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphoethanolamine(1-)
definition: An N-acyllysophosphatidylethanolamine(1-) in which the N-acyl group is specified as icosanoyl while the phosphatidyl acyl group is specified as oleoyl; major species at pH 7.3.

name: N-arachidonoyl-1-oleoyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphoethanolamine(1-)
definition: An N-acyllysophosphatidylethanolamine(1-) in which the N-acyl group is specified as arachidonoyl while the phosphatidyl acyl group is specified as oleoyl; major species at pH 7.3.

name: alpha-hydroxyglycino(1-) group
definition: An alpha-amino-acid residue anion obtained by deprotonation of the carboxy group of alpha-hydroxyglycino group; major species at pH 7.3.

name: N-acyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphoethanolamine(1-)
definition: An anionic phospholipid obtained by deprotonation of the phosphate group of any N-acyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphoethanolamine; major species at pH 7.3.

name: N-hexadecanoyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphoethanolamine(1-)
definition: An N-acyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphoethanolamine(1-) in which the N-acyl group is specified as hexadecanoyl; major species at pH 7.3.

name: N-octadecanoyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphoethanolamine(1-)
definition: An N-acyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphoethanolamine(1-) in which the N-acyl group is specified as octadecanoyl (stearoyl); major species at pH 7.3.

name: N-icosanoyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphoethanolamine(1-)
definition: An N-acyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphoethanolamine(1-) in which the N-acyl group is specified as icosanoyl; major species at pH 7.3.

name: N-oleoyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphoethanolamine(1-)
definition: An N-acyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphoethanolamine(1-) in which the N-acyl group is specified as oleoyl (9Z-octadecenoyl); major species at pH 7.3.

name: prostaglandin D2 1-glyceryl ester
definition: A 1-monoglyceride resulting from the condensation of the carboxy group of prostaglandin D2 with the 1-hydroxy group of glycerol.

name: human blood serum metabolite
definition: Any metabolite (endogenous or exogenous) found in human blood serum samples.

name: gamma-caprolactone
definition: A gamma-lactone that is oxolan-2-one substituted by an ethyl group at position 5.

name: 15-deoxy-Delta(12,14)-prostaglandin J2(1-)
definition: A prostaglandin carboxylic acid anion that is the conjugate base of 15-deoxy-Delta(12,14)-prostaglandin J2. obtained by deprotonation of the carboxy group; major species at pH 7.3.

name: 1-myristoyl-2-oleoyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphoethanolamine
definition: A 1,2-diacyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphoethanolamine in which the 1- and 2-acyl groups are specified as myristoyl and oleoyl respectively.

name: 4-hydroxy-3-methylbenzoic acid
definition: A monohydroxybenzoic acid that is 4-hydroxybenzoic acid substituted by a methyl group at position 3.

name: (13Z,16Z,19Z,22Z)-2-hydroxyoctacosatetraenoic acid
definition: An ultra-long-chain fatty acid that is (13Z,16Z,19Z,22Z)-octacosatetraenoic acid substituted at position 2 by a hydroxy group.

name: 1-monooctanoylglycerol
definition: A 1-monoglyceride that has octanoyl as the acyl group.

name: 1-octanoyl-sn-glycerol
definition: A 1-acyl-sn-glycerol that has octanoyl as the 1-acyl group.

name: 3-octanoyl-sn-glycerol
definition: A 3-acyl-sn-glycerol that has octanoyl as the 3-acyl group.

name: (12Z,15Z,18Z,21Z,24Z)-2-hydroxytriacontapentaenoic acid
definition: An ultra-long-chain fatty acid that is (12Z,15Z,18Z,21Z,24Z)-triacontapentaenoic acid substituted at position 2 by a hydroxy group.

name: (14Z,17Z,20Z,23Z,26Z)-2-hydroxydotriacontapentaenoic acid
definition: An ultra-long-chain fatty acid that is (14Z,17Z,20Z,23Z,26Z)-dotriacontapentaenoic acid substituted at position 2 by a hydroxy group.

name: lathyrane diterpenoid
definition: Any tricyclic diterpenoid with a 11-membered macrocycle fused to a cyclopropane ring. They are commonly isolated from the plant species of the family Euphorbiaceae and have been found to exhibit cytotoxic and anti-inflammatory activities.

name: gellan gum
definition: A polysaccharide acid oxoanion produced by bacteria, which is used as a substitute for agar as gelling agent in various clinical bacteriological media.

name: hydroxyethylcellulose
definition: A polysaccharide derivative that is cellulose in which hydroxyethyl groups are bound to some of the hydroxyl groups of the glucopyranose monomers.

name: N-(4Z,7Z,10Z,13Z,16Z,19Z)-docosahexaenoyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphoethanolamine(1-)
definition: An N-acyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphoethanolamine(1-) in which the N-acyl group is specified as (4Z,7Z,10Z,13Z,16Z,19Z)-docosahexaenoyl; major species at pH 7.3.

name: teicoplanin A2-2
definition: A teicoplanin A2 that has 8-methylnonanoyl as the variable N-acyl group.

name: N-(4Z,7Z,10Z,13Z,16Z,19Z)-docosahexaenoylethanolamine
definition: An N-acylethanolamine 22:6 that is the ethanolamide of (4Z,7Z,10Z,13Z,16Z,19Z)-docosahexaenoic acid.

name: N-(icosanoyl)ethanolamine
definition: An N-(long-chain-acyl)ethanolamine that is the ethanolamide of eicosanoic acid.

name: succinoglucan
definition: A polysaccharide derivative composed mainly of a glucan in which succinoyl groups are bound to some of the hydroxyl groups of the glucopyranose monomers. The polysaccharide fragment consists of beta-(1->3)-, beta-(1->4)- and beta-(1->6)-linked glucose residues together with a small proportion of beta-(1->3)-linked galactose residues.

name: geranyl acetoacetate
definition: A monoterpenoid that is the carboxylic ester obtained by the formal condensation of  geraniol with acetoacetic acid.

name: 3-dehydro-D-gluconate
definition: A keto-D-gluconate that is the conjugate base of 3-dehydro-D-gluconic acid, obtained by deprotonation of the carboxy group.

name: 3-dehydro-D-gluconic acid
definition: A ketoaldonic acid that is D-gluconic acid in which the hydroxy group at position 3 has been oxidised to the corresponding ketone.

name: diethylamine
definition: A secondary aliphatic amine where both N-substituents are ethyl.

name: N-dodecanoylsphinganine
definition: A dihydroceramide in which the ceramide N-acyl group is specified as dodecanoyl (lauroyl).

name: N-(tetradecanoyl)ethanolamine
definition: An N-(long-chain-acyl)ethanolamine resulting from the formal condensation of the carboxy group of tetradecanoic acid (myristic acid) with the amino group of ethanolamine.

name: N-(dodecanoyl)ethanolamine
definition: An N-(long-chain-acyl)ethanolamine resulting from the formal condensation of the carboxy group of dodecanoic acid (myristic acid) with the amino group of ethanolamine.

name: potassium clavulanate
definition: A potassium salt having clavulanate as the counterion. It acts as a suicide inhibitor of bacterial beta-lactamase enzymes and has only weak anitbiotic activity when administered alone. However it can be used in combination with amoxicillin trihydrate (under the trade name Augmentin) for treatment of a variety of bacterial infections, where it prevents antibiotic inactivation by microbial lactamases.

name: amprolium
definition: An organic chloride salt having 1-[(4-amino-2-propylpyrimidin-5-yl)methyl]-2-methylpyridin-1-ium as the counterion. Used for prevention of coccidiosis in poultry and cattle.

name: amprolium(1+)
definition: A pyridinium ion that is the cationic portion of amprolium, a veterinary drug which is used for prevention of coccidiosis in poultry and cattle.

name: flumequine
definition: A racemate comprising equimolar amounts of R- and S-flumequine. A broad-spectrum antibiotic, formerly used in veterinary medicine for stock breeding and treatment of aquacultures.

name: (5Z)-icosenoyl-CoA(4-)
definition: A monounsaturated fatty acyl-CoA(4-) arising from deprotonation of the phosphate and diphosphate functions of (5Z)-icosenoyl-CoA; major species at pH 7.3.

name: 1,2-dihexadecanoyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphoglycerol(1-)
definition: A phosphatidylglycerol(1-) that is the conjugate base of 1,2-dihexadecanoyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphoglycerol obtained by deprotonation of the phosphate hydroxy group; major species at pH 7.3.

name: (Kdo)2-lipid A 1-diphosphate(7-) (E. coli)
definition: A carbohydrate acid derivative anion obtained by deprotonation of the carboxy, phosphate and diphosphate functions of (Kdo)2-lipid A 1-diphosphate; major species at pH 7.3.

name: (S)-flumequine
definition: A 9-fluoro-5-methyl-1-oxo-6,7-dihydro-1H,5H-pyrido[3,2,1-ij]quinoline-2-carboxylic acid that is the (S)-enantiomer of flumequine.

name: (R)-flumequine
definition: A 9-fluoro-5-methyl-1-oxo-6,7-dihydro-1H,5H-pyrido[3,2,1-ij]quinoline-2-carboxylic acid that is the (R)-enantiomer of flumequine.

name: pristinamycin
definition: A mixture of two chemically unrelated compounds produced by Streptomyces pristinaespiralis, comprising pristinamycin IA (a cyclic depsipeptide) and pristinamycin IIA (a macrolide) in a ratio of 30:70. An oral streptogramin antibiotic with bactericidal activity against Gram positive organisms including methicillin-resistant Staphylococcus aureus.

name: (3E)-phycocyanobilin(2-)
definition: A dicarboxylic acid dianion obtained by deprotonation of the carboxy groups of (3E)-phycocyanobilin; major species at pH 7.3.

name: (3E)-phycoerythrobilin(2-)
definition: A dicarboxylic acid dianion obtained by deprotonation of the carboxy groups of (3E)-phycoerythrobilin; major species at pH 7.3.

name: N-arachidonoyl-1,2-dioleoyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphoethanolamine(1-)
definition: An N-acylphosphatidylethanolamine(1-) in which the N-acyl group is specified as arachidonoyl while the phosphatidyl acyl groups are both specified as oleoyl; major species at pH 7.3.

name: 17beta-hydroxyandrostan-3-one
definition: A 17beta-hydroxy steroid that is testosterone in which the 4-5 double bond has been reduced to a single bond with unspecified configuration at position 5.

name: S-3-[(2R)-phycoerythrobilin]-L-cysteine(2-) residue
definition: An organic anionic group obtained by deprotonation of the carboxy groups of S-3-[(2R)-phycoerythrobilin]-L-cysteine residue; major species at pH 7.3.

name: S-3-[(2R)-phycocyanobilin]-L-cysteine(2-) residue
definition: An organic anionic group obtained by deprotonation of the carboxy groups of S-3-[(2R)-phycocyanobilin]-L-cysteine residue; major species at pH 7.3.

name: N-(polyunsaturated fatty acyl)ethanolamine
definition: An N-acylethanolamine resulting from the formal condensation of the carboxy group of any polyunsaturated fatty acid with the amino group of ethanolamine.

name: N-(monounsaturated fatty acyl)ethanolamine
definition: An N-acylethanolamine resulting from the formal condensation of the carboxy group of any monounsaturated fatty acid with the amino group of ethanolamine.

name: N-(saturated fatty acyl)ethanolamine
definition: Any N-acylethanolamine in which the acyl group is derived from a saturated fatty acid.

name: N-(11Z)-icosenoylsphingosine
definition: An N-icosenoylsphingosine in which the double bond is located at position 11 (the Z-geoisomer).

name: N-(11Z)-icosenoylsphinganine
definition: An N-icosenoylsphinganine in which the double bond is located at position 11 (the Z-geoisomer).

name: N-(11Z)-icosenoylphytosphingosine
definition: An N-icosenoylphytosphingosine in which the double bond is located at position 11 (the Z-geoisomer).

name: nucleoside 3',5'-cyclic phosphorothioate
definition: Any nucleoside monophosphate analogue that consists of a nucleoside 3',5'-cyclic phosphate in which the phosphate OH group is replaced by SH.

name: S-3-[(2R)-phycoviolobilin]-L-cysteine(2-) residue
definition: An organic anionic group obtained by deprotonation of the carboxy groups of S-3-[(2R)-phycoviolobilin]-L-cysteine residue; major species at pH 7.3.

name: phenyl sulfate
definition: A phenyl sulfate oxoanion resulting from the removal of a proton from the hydrogen sulfate group of phenyl hydrogen sulfate. Major structure at pH 7.3

name: biocytinamide
definition: An  amino acid amide formed by amidation of the carboxy function of biocytin: a fluorogenic reagent for specific C-terminal labelling of peptides and proteins by carboxypeptidase Y catalyzed transpeptidation reactions.

name: N,1,2-trioleoyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphoethanolamine(1-)
definition: An N-acylphosphatidylethanolamine(1-) in which the N-acyl group and the phosphatidyl acyl groups are specified as oleoyl (9Z-octadecenoyl); major species at pH 7.3.

name: N-stearoyl-1,2-dioleoyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphoethanolamine(1-)
definition: An N-acylphosphatidylethanolamine(1-) in which the N-acyl group is specified as stearoyl (octadecanoyl) while the phosphatidyl acyl groups are both specified as oleoyl (9Z-octadecenoyl); major species at pH 7.3.

name: N-lauroyl-1,2-dioleoyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphoethanolamine(1-)
definition: An N-acylphosphatidylethanolamine(1-) in which the N-acyl group is specified as lauroyl (dodecanoyl) while the phosphatidyl acyl groups are both specified as oleoyl (9Z-octadecenoyl); major species at pH 7.3.

name: N-capryl-1-palmitoyl-2-linoleoyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphoethanolamine(1-)
definition: An N-acylphosphatidylethanolamine(1-) in which the N-acyl group is specified as capryl (decanoyl) while the phosphatidyl acyl groups at position 1 and 2 are specified as palmitoyl (hexadecanoyl) and linoleoyl (9Z,12Z-octadecadienoyl) respectively; major species at pH 7.3.

name: N-capryloyl-1-palmitoyl-2-linoleoyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphoethanolamine(1-)
definition: An N-acylphosphatidylethanolamine(1-) in which the N-acyl group is specified as capryloyl (octanoyl) while the phosphatidyl acyl groups at position 1 and 2 are specified as palmitoyl (hexadecanoyl) and linoleoyl (9Z,12Z-octadecadienoyl) respectively; major species at pH 7.3.

name: N-caproyl-1-palmitoyl-2-linoleoyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphoethanolamine(1-)
definition: An N-acylphosphatidylethanolamine(1-) in which the N-acyl group is specified as caproyl (hexanoyl) while the phosphatidyl acyl groups at position 1 and 2 are specified as palmitoyl (hexadecanoyl) and linoleoyl (9Z,12Z-octadecadienoyl) respectively; major species at pH 7.3.

name: N-butyryl-1-palmitoyl-2-linoleoyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphoethanolamine(1-)
definition: An N-acylphosphatidylethanolamine(1-) in which the N-acyl group is specified as butyryl while the phosphatidyl acyl groups at position 1 and 2 are specified as palmitoyl (hexadecanoyl) and linoleoyl (9Z,12Z-octadecadienoyl) respectively; major species at pH 7.3.

name: N(1),N(8)-bis(sinapoyl)-spermidine
definition: A secondary amino compound that is spermidine in which each of the primary amino groups has been mono-acylated by formal condensation with trans-sinapic acid.

name: N-(decanoyl)ethanolamine
definition: An N-(saturated fatty acyl)ethanolamine that is the ethanolamide of decanoic acid.

name: N-(octanoyl)ethanolamine
definition: An N-(saturated fatty acyl)ethanolamine that is the ethanolamide of octanoic acid.

name: N-(hexanoyl)ethanolamine
definition: An N-saturated fatty acyl-ethanolamine that is the ethanolamide of hexanoic acid.

name: N-(butanoyl)ethanolamine
definition: An N-(saturated fatty acyl)ethanolamine that is the ethanolamide of butanoic acid.

name: S-3-[(2R)-phycourobilin]-L-cysteine(2-) residue
definition: An organic anionic group obtained by deprotonation of the carboxy groups of S-3-[(2R)-phycourobilin]-L-cysteine residue; major species at pH 7.3.

name: D-alloisoleucine zwitterion
definition: A D-alpha-amino acid zwitterion resulting from a transfer of a proton from the carboxy group to the amino group of D-alloisoleucine; major species at pH 7.3.

name: heparosan L-iduronic acid zwitterion
definition: A zwitterion derived from heparosan L-iduronic acid. It is the major microspecies at pH 7.3 (according to Marvin v 6.2.0.).

name: poly[(1->4)-beta-D-mannuronate]
definition: A polyanionic polymer obtained by global deprotonation of all the carboxy groups of (1->4)-beta-D-mannuronic acid; major species at pH 7.3.

name: beta-D-galacturonate
definition: A D-galactopyranuronate that has beta configuration at the anomeric centre.

name: beta-D-glucuronate
definition: A D-glucopyranuronate that has beta configuration at the anomeric centre.

name: silyl chloride
definition: Any organosilicon compound containing at least one silicon-chlorine bond.

name: N-silyl compound
definition: Any organosilicon compound that contains at least one silicon-nitrogen bond.

name: (R)-ethylmalonyl-CoA(5-)
definition: An acyl-CoA oxoanion arising from deprotonation of the phosphate, diphosphate and carboxy groups of (2R)-ethylmalonyl-CoA; major species at pH 7.3.

name: D-galactaro-1,4-lactone(1-)
definition: A carbohydrate acid anion resulting from the removal of a proton from the carboxylic acid group of D-galactaro-1,4-lactone.

name: trimethylphenylammonium
definition: A quaternary ammonium ion obtained by methylation of N,N-dimethylaniline.

name: N-(2-carbamoylphenyl)-2-(2,5-dimethoxyphenyl)quinoline-4-carboxamide
definition: A member of the class of quinolines that is the amide obtained from formal condensation of the carboxy group of 2-(2,5-dimethoxyphenyl)quinoline-4-carboxylic acid with the amino group of 2-aminobenzamide.

name: 3-[(dimethylamino)methyl]-5-[(4-methoxyphenyl)methylidene]-1,3-thiazolidine-2,4-dione
definition: A member of the class of thiazolidinones that is 3-[(dimethylamino)methyl]-1,3-thiazolidine-2,4-dione bearing an additional (4-methoxyphenyl)methylidene substituent at position 5.

name: (5E)-5-[(4-methoxyphenyl)methylidene]-1,1-dioxo-2,3-diphenyl-1,3-thiazolidin-4-one
definition: A member of the class of thiazolidinones that is 1,1-dioxo-2,3-diphenyl-1,3-thiazolidin-4-one bearing an additional (4-methoxyphenyl)methylidene substituent at position 5.

name: [5-hydroxy-3-methyl-5-(trifluoromethyl)-4,5-dihydropyrazol-1-yl]-[5-phenyl-7-(trifluoromethyl)pyrazolo[1,5-a]pyrimidin-2-yl]methanone
definition: A member of the class of pyrazolopyrimidines that is the amide obtained from formal condensation of the carboxy group of 5-phenyl-7-(trifluoromethyl)pyrazolo[1,5-a]pyrimidine-2-carboxylic acid with the endocyclic amino group of 3-methyl-5-(trifluoromethyl)-4,5-dihydropyrazol-5-ol.

name: 4-hydroxy-1-isobutyl-N-(5-methyl-1,3-thiazol-2-yl)-2-oxoquinoline-3-carboxamide
definition: A member of the class of quinolones that is the amide obtained from formal condensation of the carboxy group of 4-hydroxy-1-(2-methylpropyl)-2-oxo-1,2-dihydroquinoline-3-carboxylic acid with the amino group of 5-methyl-1,3-thiazol-2-amine.

name: 7-{2-hydroxy-3-[(naphthalen-1-yl)oxy]propyl}-3-methyl-8-(morpholin-4-yl)-3,7-dihydropurine-2,6-dione
definition: A member of the class of oxopurines that is 3-methyl-8-(morpholin-4-yl)-3,7-dihydropurine-2,6-dione bearing an additional 2-hydroxy-3-[(naphthalen-1-yl)oxy]propyl substituent at position 7.

name: 1-allyl-4-hydroxy-2-oxo-N-(1,3-thiazol-2-yl)-1,2-dihydroquinoline-3-carboxamide
definition: A member of the class of quinolones that is the amide obtained from formal condensation of the carboxy group of 1-allyl-4-hydroxy-2-oxo-1,2-dihydroquinoline-3-carboxylic acid with the amino group of 2-amino-1,3-thiazole.

name: 4,5-dihydroindolo[3,2-c]pyrrolo[3,2,1-ij]quinolin-7-one
definition: An organic heteropentacyclic compound that is 4,5-dihydroindolo[3,2-c]pyrrolo[3,2,1-ij]quinoline substituted at position 7 by an oxo group.

name: 1-(4-chlorophenyl)-3-[3-(3-chlorophenyl)-1,5,5-trimethyl-2-oxoimidazolidin-4-yl]urea
definition: A member of the class of imidazolidinones that is 1,5,5-trimethyl-2-oxoimidazolidine bearing additional m-chlorophenyl and N'-p-chlorophenylureido substituents at positions 3 and 4 respectively.

name: 2-(3-isopropyloxyphenyl)-N-(pyridin-4-yl)quinoline-4-carboxamide
definition: A member of the class of quinolines that is the amide obtained from formal condensation of the carboxy group of 2-(2-isopropyloxyphenyl)quinoline-4-carboxylic acid with the amino group of 4-aminopyridine.

name: UDP-4-dehydro-6-deoxy-alpha-D-glucose(2-)
definition: A UDP-4-dehydro-6-deoxy-D-glucose obtained by deprotonation of the phosphate OH groups of UDP-4-dehydro-6-deoxy-alpha-D-glucose; major species at pH 7.3.

name: dapdiamide A
definition: A member of the family of dapdiamides consisting of alanylvaline in which one of the methyl hydrogens of alanine is replaced by a fumaramoyl group.

name: dapdiamide B
definition: A member of the family of dapdiamides consisting of alanylisoleucine, in which one of the methyl hydrogens of alanine is replaced by a fumaramoyl group.

name: dapdiamide C
definition: A member of the family of dapdiamides consisting of alanylleucine, in which one of the methyl hydrogens of alanine is replaced by a fumaramoyl group.

name: N,1-dipalmitoyl-2-linoleoyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphoethanolamine(1-)
definition: An N-acylphosphatidylethanolamine(1-) in which the N-acyl group is specified as hexadecanoyl while the phosphatidyl acyl groups at position 1 and 2 are specified as hexadecanoyl and (9Z,12Z-octadecadienoyl) respectively; major species at pH 7.3.

name: N,1-dipalmitoyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphoethanolamine(1-)
definition: An N-acyllysophosphatidylethanolamine(1-) in which both the N-acyl and phosphatidyl acyl groups are specified as palmitoyl (hexadecanoyl); major species at pH 7.3.

name: D-glucaro-1,4-lactone(1-)
definition: A carbohydrate acid anion resulting from the removal of a proton from the carboxylic acid group of D-glucaro-1,4-lactone; major species at pH 7.3.

name: dapdiamide E
definition: A member of the family of dapdiamides consisting of 3-aminoalanylvaline, in which the N-terminus is acylated by a 3-carbamoyloxirane-2-carbonyl group. NB Although the relative configuration of the epoxide moiety has been assigned as trans, it has not yet been established whether the absolute configuration is R,R (as drawn) or S,S.

name: L-alloisoleucine zwitterion
definition: An amino acid zwitterion resulting from a transfer of a proton from the carboxy group to the amino group of L-alloisoleucine; major species at pH 7.3.

name: O-[S-(L-alloisoleucyl)pantetheine-4'-phosphoryl]serine zwitterionic residue
definition: A zwitterionic group derived from O-[S-(L-alloisoleucyl)pantetheine-4'-phosphoryl]serine residue; major species at pH 7.3.

name: 2-hydroxyoctacosanoic acid
definition: A 2-hydroxy fatty acid that is the 2-hydroxy derivative of octacosanoic acid.

name: 2-hydroxynervonic acid
definition: A 2-hydroxy fatty acid that is the 2-hydroxy derivative of nervonic acid.

name: 1,2-dioctanoyl-sn-glycero-3-phospho-(1D-myo-inositol-3,5-bisphosphate)(5-)
definition: A 1-phosphatidyl-1D-myo-inositol 3,5-bisphosphate(5-) arising from deprotonation of all five free phosphate OH groups of 1,2-dioctanoyl-sn-glycero-3-phospho-(1D-myo-inositol-3,5-bisphosphate); major species at pH 7.3.

name: 2-palmitoyl-3,6,6'-tristearoyl-2'-sulfo-alpha,alpha-trehalose
definition: A polyacyl alpha,alpha-trehalose derivative that is 2'-sulfo-alpha,alpha-trehalose carrying a palmitoyl group at position 2 and three stearoyl groups at positions 3, 6 and 6'

name: (4R)-3,4-dihydro-4-hydroxyphenylpyruvic acid
definition: A 3,4-dihydro-4-hydroxyphenylpyruvic acid having R-configuration.

name: 2-palmitoyl-3-stearoyl-2'-sulfo-alpha,alpha-trehalose
definition: A polyacyl alpha,alpha-trehalose derivative that is 2'-sulfo-alpha,alpha-trehalose carrying palmitoyl and stearoyl groups at positions 2 and 3 respectively.

name: N(3)-fumaroyl-(S)-2,3-diaminopropanoic acid
definition: An L-alanine derivative obtained by formal condensation of one of the carboxy groups of fumaric acid with the side-chain amino group of 3-amino-L-alanine.

name: N(3)-fumaramoyl-(S)-2,3-diaminopropanoic acid
definition: An L-alanine derivative obtained by formal condensation of the carboxy group of fumaric acid monoamide with the side-chain amino group of 3-amino-L-alanine.

name: 11,12-saturated fatty acyl-CoA
definition: Any fatty acyl-CoA in which the 11-12 bond of the fatty acyl group is saturated.

name: CDP-1-stearoyl-2-arachidonoyl-sn-glycerol(2-)
definition: A CDP-diacylglycerol(2-) obtained by deprotonation of the diphosphate OH groups of CDP-1-stearoyl-2-arachidonoyl-sn-glycerol; major species at pH 7.3.

name: CDP-1-palmitoyl-2-arachidonoyl-sn-glycerol(2-)
definition: A CDP-diacylglycerol(2-) obtained by deprotonation of the diphosphate OH groups of CDP-1-palmitoyl-2-arachidonoyl-sn-glycerol; major species at pH 7.3.

name: CDP-1,2-diarachidonoyl-sn-glycerol(2-)
definition: A CDP-diacylglycerol(2-) obtained by deprotonation of the diphosphate OH groups of CDP-1,2-diarachidonoyl-sn-glycerol; major species at pH 7.3.

name: CDP-1-stearoyl-2-linoleoyl-sn-glycerol(2-)
definition: A CDP-diacylglycerol(2-) obtained by deprotonation of the diphosphate OH groups of CDP-1-stearoyl-2-linoleoyl-sn-glycerol; major species at pH 7.3.

name: CDP-1-stearoyl-2-oleoyl-sn-glycerol(2-)
definition: A CDP-diacylglycerol(2-) obtained by deprotonation of the diphosphate OH groups of CDP-1-stearoyl-2-oleoyl-sn-glycerol; major species at pH 7.3.

name: CDP-1-stearoyl-2-(4Z,7Z,10Z,13Z,16Z,19Z)-docosahexaenoyl-sn-glycerol(2-)
definition: A CDP-diacylglycerol(2-) obtained by deprotonation of the diphosphate OH groups of CDP-1-stearoyl-2-docosahexaenoyl-sn-glycerol; major species at pH 7.3.

name: CDP-1,2-dilinoleoyl-sn-glycerol(2-)
definition: A CDP-diacylglycerol(2-) obtained by deprotonation of the diphosphate OH groups of CDP-1,2-dilinoleoyl-sn-glycerol; major species at pH 7.3.

name: CDP-1,2-dioleoyl-sn-glycerol(2-)
definition: A CDP-diacylglycerol(2-) obtained by deprotonation of the diphosphate OH groups of CDP-1,2-dioleoyl-sn-glycerol; major species at pH 7.3.

name: 3-[(1E,4R)-4-hydroxycyclohex-2-en-1-ylidene]pyruvic acid
definition: A 3-(4-hydroxycyclohex-2-en-1-ylidene)pyruvic acid having 1E,4R stereochemistry.

name: (3E)-3-[(1R,5R,6S)-5-hydroxy-7-oxabicyclo[4.1.0]heptan-2-ylidene]pyruvic acid
definition: A 2-oxo monocarboxylic acid that is pyruvic acid in which two of the methyl hydrogens are replaced by a 5-hydroxy-7-oxabicyclo[4.1.0]heptan-2-ylidene group (the 1R,5R,6S stereoisomer).

name: 3-[(1R,2S,5R,6S)-5-hydroxy-7-oxabicyclo[4.1.0]heptan-2-yl]pyruvic acid
definition: A 2-oxo monocarboxylic acid that is pyruvic acid in which one of the methyl hydrogens is replaced by a 5-hydroxy-7-oxabicyclo[4.1.0]heptan-2-yl group (the 1R,2S,5R,6S stereoisomer).

name: L-dihydroanticapsin
definition: An L-alanine derivative in which one of the methyl hydrogens of L-alanine is replaced by a 5-hydroxy-7-oxabicyclo[4.1.0]heptan-2-yl group.

name: tetramethylsilane
definition: An organosilicon compound that is silane in which the hydrogens have been replaced by methyl groups.

name: 3-(trimethylsilyl)propane-1-sulfonic acid
definition: An alkanesulfonic acid that is propanesulfonic acid substituted at position 3 by a trimethylsilyl group.

name: sodium 3-(trimethylsilyl)propionate
definition: An organic sodium salt composed of sodium and 3-(trimethylsilyl)propionate ions in a 1:1 ratio. It is used as internal reference in the NMR spectrum nuclear magnetic resonance for aqueous solvents (e.g. D2O).

name: ammonium bromide
definition: An ammonium salt composed of ammonium and bromide ions in a 1:1 ratio.

name: deuterated chloroform
definition: A deuterated compound that is an isotopologue of chloroform in which the hydrogen atom is replaced with deuterium. Commonly used as a solvent in proton NMR spectroscopy.

name: 3-hydroxy-2,4-dioxopentyl phosphate
definition: A phosphate monoester that is 1,3-dihydroxypentane-2,4-dione carrying a phospho at position 1.

name: 2-epi-5-epi-valiolone 7-phosphate
definition: A member of the class of cyclitols that is 2-epi-5-epi-valiolone carrying a phospho substituent at position 7.

name: dTDP-4-dehydro-2,6-dideoxy-alpha-D-glucose
definition: A dTDP-sugar having 4-dehydro-2,6-dideoxy-alpha-D-glucose as the sugar component.

name: dTDP-3,4-didehydro-2,6-dideoxy-alpha-D-glucose
definition: A dTDP-sugar having 3,4-didehydro-2,6-dideoxy-alpha-D-glucose as the sugar component.

name: 4-hydroxy-1-methyl-N-(5-methyl-1,3-thiazol-2-yl)-2-oxo-1,2-dihydro-3-quinolinecarboxamide
definition: A member of the class of quinolones that is the amide obtained from formal condensation of the carboxy group of 4-hydroxy-1-methyl-2-oxo-1,2-dihydroquinoline-3-carboxylic acid with the amino group of 2-amino-3-methyl-1,3-thiazole.

name: 4-hydroxy-1-isopentyl-N-(5-methyl-1,3-thiazol-2-yl)-2-oxoquinoline-3-carboxamide
definition: A member of the class of quinolones that is the amide obtained from formal condensation of the carboxy group of 4-hydroxy-1-isopentyl-2-oxo-1,2-dihydroquinoline-3-carboxylic acid with the amino group of 2-amino-3-methyl-1,3-thiazole.

name: 4-hydroxy-1-isobutyl-N-(4-methyl-1,3-thiazol-2-yl)-2-oxoquinoline-3-carboxamide
definition: A member of the class of quinolones that is the amide obtained from formal condensation of the carboxy group of 4-hydroxy-1-isobutyl-2-oxo-1,2-dihydroquinoline-3-carboxylic acid with the amino group of 2-amino-4-methyl-1,3-thiazole.

name: 1-butyl-N-(5-ethyl-1,3,4-thiadiazol-2-yl)-4-hydroxy-2-oxoquinoline-3-carboxamide
definition: A member of the class of quinolones that is the amide obtained from formal condensation of the carboxy group of 1-allyl-4-hydroxy-2-oxo-1,2-dihydroquinoline-3-carboxylic acid with the amino group of 2-amino-3-ethyl-1,3,4-thiadizole.

name: N-acetylsphingosine 1-phosphate(2-)
definition: A N-acylsphingosine 1-phosphate(2-) in which the N-acyl group is specified as acetyl; major species at pH 7.3.

name: N-octanoylsphingosine 1-phosphate(2-)
definition: An N-acylsphingosine 1-phosphate(2-) in which the N-acyl group is specified as octanoyl; major species at pH 7.3.

name: 8-methoxypyrene-1,3,6-trisulfonic acid
definition: An arenesulfonic acid consisting of pyrene methoxy-substituted at C-8 and substituted at C-1, -3 and 6 by sulfonic acid groups.

name: N-oleoylsphingosine 1-phosphate(2-)
definition: An N-acylsphingosine 1-phosphate(2-) in which the N-acyl group is specified as oleoyl; major species at pH 7.3.

name: 1,2-dilauroyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphate(2-)
definition: A 1-acyl-2-dodecanoyl-sn-glycerol-3-phosphate(2-) obtained by deprotonation of the phosphate OH groups of 1,2-dilauroyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphate; major species at pH 7.3.

name: 8-methoxypyrene-1,3,6-trisulfonate
definition: The arenesulfonate oxoanion that is 8-methoxypyrene-1,3,6-trisulfonic acid deprotonated at each of the three sulfonic acid substituents.

name: sodium 8-methoxypyrene-1,3,6-trisulfonate
definition: An organic sodium salt that is the trisodium salt of 8-methoxypyrene-1,3,6-trisulfonic acid. A highly water-soluble superpolar fluorescent probe for assaying cationic surfactants.

name: 1-heptadecanoyl-2-lauroyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphate
definition: A 1,2-diacyl-sn-glycerol 3-phosphate in which the phosphatidyl acyl groups at postions 1 and 2 are specified as heptadecanoyl and lauroyl respectively.

name: 1-heptadecanoyl-2-myristoyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphate
definition: A 1,2-diacyl-sn-glycerol 3-phosphate in which the phosphatidyl acyl groups at postions 1 and 2 are specified as heptadecanoyl and myristoyl respectively.

name: GABA reuptake inhibitor
definition: A compound that inhibits the re-uptake of the neurotransmitter GABA from the synapse into the pre-synaptic neuron, so increasing the extracellular concentrations of the neurotransmitter and hence increasing neurotransmission.

name: 1-heptadecanoyl-2-stearoyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphate
definition: A 1,2-diacyl-sn-glycerol 3-phosphate in which the phosphatidyl acyl groups at postions 1 and 2 are specified as heptadecanoyl and stearoyl respectively.

name: 1-heptadecanoyl-2-palmitoyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphate
definition: A 1,2-diacyl-sn-glycerol 3-phosphate in which the phosphatidyl acyl groups at postions 1 and 2 are specified as heptadecanoyl and palmitoyl respectively.

name: tiagabine(1+)
definition: An ammonium ion resulting from the protonation of the tertiary amino group of tiagabine.

name: tiagabine hydrochloride
definition: A hydrochloride resulting from the reaction of equimolar amounts of tiagabine and hydrogen chloride. A GABA reuptake inhibitor, it is used for the treatment of epilepsy.

name: 5'-AAGUCUCCACUCGAGUGUCCGAGCG-3' RNA fragment
definition: A synthetic RNA fragment comprised of five adenosine, seven guanosine, five uridine and eight cytidine residues connected by 3'->5' phosphodiester linkages in the sequence A-A-G-U-C-U-C-C-A-C-U-C-G-A-G-U-G-U-C-C-G-A-G-C-G.

name: 5'-AAGUGCAGAAGCGGUCAACCCAGUC-3'
definition: A synthetic RNA fragment comprised of eight adenosine, seven guanosine, three uridine and seven cytidine residues connected by 3'->5' phosphodiester linkages in the sequence A-A-G-U-C-U-C-C-A-C-U-C-G-A-G-U-G-U-C-C-G-A-G-C-G.

name: 5'-UGGGAAGACA-3'
definition: A synthetic RNA fragment comprised of one uridine, one cytidine, four adenosine and four guanosine residues connected by 3'->5' phosphodiester linkages in the sequence U-G-G-G-A-A-G-A-C-A.

name: 5'-AUGUAGAUUA-3'
definition: A synthetic RNA fragment comprised of four uridine, four adenosine and two guanosine residues connected by 3'->5' phosphodiester linkages in the sequence A-U-G-U-A-G-A-U-U-A.

name: 5'-UAUGUACACUACA-3'
definition: A synthetic RNA fragment comprised of five adenosine, one guanosine, four uridine and three cytidine residues connected by 3'->5' phosphodiester linkages in the sequence U-G-G-G-A-A-G-A-C-A.

name: alpha-D-Rhap4NFo-(1->2)-alpha-D-Rhap4NFo-(1->3)-alpha-D-Rhap4NFo
definition: An amino trisaccharide consisting of three N-formyl-alpha-D-perosamine residues linked sequentially (1->2) and (1->3).

name: alpha-D-Rhap4NFo-(1->3)-alpha-D-Rhap4NFo-(1->2)-alpha-D-Rhap4NFo
definition: An amino trisaccharide consisting of three N-formyl-alpha-D-perosamine residues linked sequentially (1->3) and (1->2).

name: alpha-D-Rhap4NFo-(1->2)-alpha-D-Rhap4NFo-(1->3)-alpha-D-Rhap4NFo-(1->2)-alpha-D-Rhap4NFo
definition: An amino tetrasaccharide consisting of four N-formyl-alpha-D-perosamine residues linked sequentially (1->2), (1->3) and (1->2).

name: alpha-D-Rhap4NFo-(1->2)-alpha-D-Rhap4NFo-(1->3)-alpha-D-Rhap4NFo-(1->2)-alpha-D-Rhap4NFo-(1->2)-alpha-D-Rhap4NFo
definition: An amino pentasaccharide consisting of five N-formyl-alpha-D-perosamine residues linked sequentially (1->2), (1->3), (1->2) and (1->2).

name: alpha-D-Rhap4NFo-(1->2)-alpha-D-Rhap4NFo-(1->2)-alpha-D-Rhap4NFo-(1->2)-alpha-D-Rhap4NFo-(1->3)-alpha-D-Rhap4NFo-(1->2)-alpha-D-Rhap4NFo-(1->2)-alpha-D-Rhap4NFo-(1->2)-alpha-D-Rhap4NFo-(1->2)-alpha-D-Rhap4NFo
definition: An amino nonasaccharide consisting of nine N-formyl-alpha-D-perosamine residues linked sequentially (1->2), (1->2), (1->2), (1->3), (1->2), (1->2), (1->2) and (1->2).

name: 1-heptadecanoyl-2-arachidonoyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphoserine
definition: A 3-sn-phosphatidyl-L-serine in which the acyl substituents at positions 1 and 2 are specified as heptadecanoyl and arachidonoyl respectively.

name: 1-heptadecanoyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphoserine
definition: A 1-acyl-sn-glycerophosphoserine in which the acyl group is specified as heptadecanoyl.

name: beta-D-Galp-(1->3)-beta-D-GlcpNAc-(1->3)-beta-D-Galp-(1->4)-[alpha-L-Fucp-(1->3)]-beta-D-GlcpNAc
definition: A branched amino pentasaccharide comprising a linear chain of beta-D-galactose, N-acetyl-beta-D-glucosamine, beta-D-galactose and N-acetyl-beta-D-glucosamine, linked (1->3), (1->3) and (1->4) respectively, with an alpha-L-fucose residue linked to the reducing-end N-acetyl-beta-D-glucosamine residue.

name: 1-stearoyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphoserine
definition: A 1-acyl-sn-glycerophosphoserine in which the acyl group is specified as stearoyl (octadecanoyl).

name: 3-dehydrocarnityl CoA(3-)
definition: A triply charged acyl-CoA oxoanion arising from deprotonation of the phosphate and diphosphate OH groups of 3-dehydrocarnityl CoA; major species at pH 7.3.

name: N,N,N-trimethylglycyl-CoA(3-)
definition: A triply charged acyl-CoA oxoanion arising from deprotonation of the phosphate and diphosphate OH groups of N,N,N-trimethylglycyl-CoA; major species at pH 7.3.

name: beta-D-Galp-(1->4)-beta-D-GlcpNAc-(1->6)-D-GalpNAc
definition: An amino trisaccharide comprised of a linear sequence of beta-D-galactose, N-acetyl-beta-D-glucosamine and N-acetyl-D-galactosamine linked (1->4) and (1->6).

name: 1-palmitoyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphoglycerol
definition: A 1-acyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphoglycerol in which the acyl group is specified as palmitoyl (hexadecanoyl).

name: 1-heptadecanoyl-2-arachidonoyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphoethanolamine
definition: A 1,2-diacyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphoethanolamine in which the acyl groups at positions 1 and 2 are specified as heptadecanoyl and arachidonoyl respectively.

name: 1-heptadecanoyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphoethanolamine
definition: A 1-acyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphoethanolamine in which the acyl group is specified as heptadecanoyl.

name: 1-oleoyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphoglycerol
definition: A 1-acyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphoglycerol in which the acyl group is specified as oleoyl.

name: sn-glycero-3-phosphoglycerol
definition: A glycerophosphoglycerol where both glycerol moieties are attached at primary positions and one stereocentre has R-configuration.

name: mitomycin A
definition: A member of the family of mitomycins that exhibits antibiotic and antitumour properties as well as a high level of toxicity.

name: 5-hydroxyectoine zwitterion
definition: An iminium betaine resulting from a transfer of a proton from the carboxy group to the imino group of 5-hydroxyectoine.  It is the major microspecies at pH 7.3 (according to Marvin v 6.2.0.).

name: (6S)-5,6,7,8-tetrahydropteroate
definition: A pteroate that is the conjugate base of (6S)-5,6,7,8-tetrahydropteroic acid, obtained by deprotonation of the carboxy group; major species at pH 7.3.

name: (Z)-hex-3-enoyl-CoA(4-)
definition: A monounsaturated fatty acyl-CoA(4-) obtained by deprotonation of the phosphate and diphosphate OH groups of (Z)-hex-3-enoyl-CoA; major species at pH 7.3.

name: mitomycin B
definition: A member of the family of mitomycins that exhibits antibiotic and antitumour properties.

name: dTDP-beta-L-daunosamine(1-)
definition: A nucleotide-sugar oxoanion that is the conjugate base of dTDP-beta-L-daunosamine, arising from deprotonation of the diphosphate group and protonation of the amino group. It is the major microspecies at pH 7.3 (according to Marvin v 6.2.0.).

name: 7-demethylmitomycin B
definition: A member of the family of mitomycins that is mitomycin B in which the methoxy group  on the quinone ring is replaced by a hydroxy group.

name: 7-demethylmitomycin A
definition: A member of the family of mitomycins that is mitomycin A in which the methoxy group on the quinone ring is replaced by a hydroxy group.

name: N-isopropyl-L-glutamine zwitterion
definition: An amino acid zwitterion obtained by transfer of a proton from the carboxy to the amino group of N-isopropyl-L-glutamine; major species at pH 7.3.

name: N-(gamma-L-glutamyl)-L-alaninol zwitterion
definition: An amino acid zwitterion obtained by transfer of a proton from the carboxy to the amino group of N-(gamma-L-glutamyl)-L-alaninol; major species at pH 7.3.

name: (S)-2-aminopropan-1-ol(1+)
definition: An ammonium ion resulting from the protonation of the amino group of (S)-2-aminopropan-1-ol. The major species at pH 7.3 according to Marvin ver. 6.2.0.

name: glycine transporter 2 inhibitor
definition: Any glycine transporter inhibitor that interferes with the action of glycine 2 transporters.

name: glycine transporter inhibitor
definition: Any substance that inhibits the action of glycine transporters.

name: 3-phenylpropionitrile
definition: A nitrile that is propionitrile in which one of the methyl hydrogens has been replaced by a phenyl group.

name: 1,2-dipalmitoyl-3-palmitoleoyl-sn-glycerol
definition: A triglyceride in which the acyl groups at positions 1 and 2 are specified as palmitoyl while that at position 3 is specified as palmitoleoyl.

name: trans-3-hydroxy-L-proline residue
definition: An alpha-amino-acid residue derived from trans-3-hydroxy-L-proline.

name: phosphatidylethanol
definition: A glycerophospholipid that is the monoethyl ester of any phosphatidic acid.

name: 11-deoxy-beta-rhodomycin zwitterion
definition: A zwitterion obtained by transfer of a proton from the 5-hydroxy to the tertiary amino group of 11-deoxy-beta-rhodomycin; major species at pH 7.3.

name: 1,2-dipalmitoyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphoethanol
definition: A phosphatidylethanol in which both phosphatidyl acyl groups are specified as palmitoyl (hexadecanoyl).

name: 2'-MANT-GDP
definition: A purine ribonucleoside 5'-diphosphate that is GDP substituted at position 2' by an N-methylanthraniloyl group.

name: glutamine hydroxamate zwitterion
definition: An amino acid zwitterion obtained by transfer of a proton from the carboxy to the amino group of glutamine hydroxamate; major species at pH 7.3.

name: 1-arachidonoyl-sn-glycero-3-phospho-L-serine
definition: An 1-acyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphoserine in which the 1-acyl group is specified as arachidonoyl.

name: alpha-D-Glcp-(1->6)-alpha-D-Glcp-(1->4)-alpha-D-Glcp-(1->4)-alpha-D-Glcp
definition: A glucotetrose consisting of alpha-maltotriose with a further alpha-D-glucose unit linked to O-6 of the glucose residue at the non-reducing end.

name: alpha-D-Glcp-(1->6)-alpha-D-Glcp-(1->4)-alpha-D-Glcp-(1->4)-alpha-D-Glcp-(1->6)-alpha-D-Glcp-(1->4)-alpha-D-Glcp-(1->4)-alpha-D-Glcp
definition: A heptasaccharide consisting of two alpha-maltotriose units linked (1->6), with a further alpha-D-glucose unit linked to O-6 of the glucose residue at the non-reducing end.

name: O-decenoyl-L-carnitine
