definition: An O-acyl-L-carnitine that is L-carnitine having decenoyl group as the acyl substituent in which the position of the double bond is unspecified.

name: trans,trans-2,4-hexadienoyl-CoA
definition: A trans,trans-2,3,4,5-tetradehydroacyl-CoA that results from the formal condensation of the thiol group of coenzyme A with the carboxy group of trans,trans-2,4-hexadienoic acid.

name: very long-chain (R)-3-hydroxyacyl-CoA(4-)
definition: An (R)-3-hydroxyacyl-CoA(4-) arising from deprotonation of the phosphate and diphosphate OH groups of any very long-chain (R)-3-hydroxyacyl-CoA; major species at pH 7.3.

name: O-decadienoyl-L-carnitine
definition: An O-acyl-L-carnitine that is L-carnitine having decadienoyl group as the acyl substituent in which the positions of the two double bonds are unspecified.

name: trans-3-hexenoyl-CoA
definition: A trans-3-enoyl-CoA that results from the formal condensation of the thiol group of coenzyme A with the carboxy group of trans-3-hexenoic acid.

name: (3E,7Z,10Z,13Z,16Z,19Z)-docosahexaenoyl-CoA
definition: A trans-3-enoyl-CoA that results from the formal condensation of the thiol group of coenzyme A with the carboxy group of (3E,7Z,10Z,13Z,16Z,19Z)-docosahexaenoic acid.

name: 2'-deoxyguanosine 5'-monophosphate(1-) residue
definition: An organic anionic group obtained by deprotonation of the phosphate OH group of dGMP residue; major species at pH 7.3.

name: O-dodecenoyl-L-carnitine
definition: An O-acyl-L-carnitine that is L-carnitine having dodecenoyl group as the acyl substituent in which the position of the double bond is unspecified.

name: O-dodecadienoyl-L-carnitine
definition: An O-acyl-L-carnitine that is L-carnitine having a dodecadienoyl group as the acyl substituent in which the positions of the two double bonds are unspecified.

name: 6-O-methyl dGMP(1-) residue
definition: An organic anionic group obtained by deprotonation of the phosphate OH group of 6-O-methyl dGMP residue; major species at pH 7.3.

name: O-tetradecenoyl-L-carnitine
definition: An O-acyl-L-carnitine that is L-carnitine having tetradecenoyl group as the acyl substituent in which the position of the double bond is unspecified.

name: O-hydroxytetradecenoyl-L-carnitine
definition: An O-acyl-L-carnitine that is L-carnitine having a hydroxytetradecenoyl group as the acyl substituent in which the positions of the hydroxy group and the double bond are unspecified.

name: O-tetradecadienoyl-L-carnitine
definition: An O-acyl-L-carnitine that is L-carnitine having a tetradecadienoyl group as the acyl substituent in which the positions of the two double bonds are unspecified.

name: 2'-deoxycytidine 5'-monophosphate(1-) residue
definition: An organic anionic group obtained by deprotonation of the phosphate OH group of deoxycytidine 5'-monophosphate residue; major species at pH 7.3.

name: O-(hydroxytetradecadienoyl)-L-carnitine
definition: An O-acyl-L-carnitine that is L-carnitine having a hydroxytetradecadienoyl group as the acyl substituent in which the positions of the two double bonds and the hydroxy group are unspecified.

name: O-hexadecenoyl-L-carnitine
definition: An O-acyl-L-carnitine that is L-carnitine having a hexadecenoyl group as the acyl substituent in which the position of the double bond is unspecified.

name: O-hydroxyhexadecenoyl-L-carnitine
definition: An O-acyl-L-carnitine that is L-carnitine having a hydroxyhexadecenoyl group as the acyl substituent in which the position of the hydroxy group and the double bond is unspecified.

name: O-hexadecadienoyl-L-carnitine
definition: An O-acyl-L-carnitine that is L-carnitine having a hexadecadienoyl group as the acyl substituent in which the positions of the two double bonds are unspecified.

name: O-hydroxyhexadecadienoyl-L-carnitine
definition: An O-acyl-L-carnitine that is L-carnitine having a hydroxyhexadecadienoyl group as the acyl substituent in which the positions of the two double bonds and the hydroxy group are unspecified.

name: O-(hydroxyhexadecanoyl)-L-carnitine
definition: An O-acyl-L-carnitine that is L-carnitine having a hydroxyhexadecanoyl group as the acyl substituent in which the position of the hydroxy group  is unspecified.

name: O-octadecenoyl-L-carnitine
definition: An O-acyl-L-carnitine that is L-carnitine having a octadecenoyl group as the acyl substituent in which the position of the double bond is unspecified.

name: O-hydroxyoctadecenoyl-L-carnitine
definition: An O-acyl-L-carnitine that is L-carnitine having a hydroxyoctadecenoyl group as the acyl substituent in which the position of the double bond and the hydroxy group is unspecified.

name: trisaccharide residue
definition: A divalent organic group that is three contiguous constituent monosaccharide units of an oligo- or poly-saccharide, formed formally by loss of the anomeric hydroxy group from the monosaccharide residue at its reducing end and of H from one of the hydroxy groups of the residue at its non-reducing end.

name: O-octadecadienoyl-L-carnitine
definition: An O-acyl-L-carnitine that is L-carnitine having a octadecadienoyl group as the acyl substituent in which the positions of the two double bonds are unspecified.

name: O-acryloyl-L-carnitine
definition: An O-acyl-L-carnitine having acryloyl as the acyl group.

name: [4)-alpha-D-Glcp-(1->4)-alpha-D-Glcp-(1->4)-alpha-D-Glcp-(1->] residue
definition: A trisaccharide residue obtained from alpha-maltotriose by removal of the anomeric hydroxy group from the residue at the reducing end and the hydrogen attached to the 4-hydroxy group of the residue at the non-reducing end. Corresponds to the minimal monoclonal antibody (Mab) binding epitope for the binding of Mabs to mycobacterial capsular alpha-glucans of Mycobacterium smegmatis.

name: 1,2-dioctanoyl-sn-glycero-3-phospho-(1D-myo-inositol-4-phosphate)(3-)
definition: A 1-phosphatidyl-1D-myo-inositol 4-phosphate(3-) arising from deprotonation of all three free phosphate OH groups of 1,2-dioctanoyl-sn-glycero-3-phospho-(1D-myo-inositol-4-phosphate); major species at pH 7.3.

name: O-malonyl-L-carnitine
definition: An O-acyl-L-carnitine in which the acyl group is specified as malonyl.

name: cobalt(II)-factor IV(6-)
definition: A precorrin carboxylic acid anion obtained by global deprotonation of the carboxy groups of cobalt(II)-factor IV. It is the major microspecies at pH 7.3 (according to Marvin v 6.2.0.).

name: O-hydroxybutyryl-L-carnitine
definition: An O-acyl-L-carnitine that is L-carnitine having a hydroxybutyryl group as the acyl substituent in which the positions of  the hydroxy group is unspecified.

name: O-methylmalonyl-L-carnitine
definition: An O-acyl-L-carnitine in which the acyl group specified is methylmalonyl.

name: 4-hydroxy-6-(2-hydroxytridecyl)-pyran-2-one
definition: A 6-alkyl-4-hydroxy-2H-pyran-2-one that is 4-hydroxy-2H-pyran-2-one in which the hydrogen at position 6 is replaced by a 2-hydroxytridecyl group.

name: 4-hydroxy-6-(11-hydroxyheptadecyl)-pyran-2-one
definition: A 6-alkyl-4-hydroxy-2H-pyran-2-one that is 4-hydroxy-2H-pyran-2-one in which the hydrogen at position 6 is replaced by an 11-hydroxyheptadecyl group.

name: O-hydroxyvaleroyl-L-carnitine
definition: An O-acyl-L-carnitine in which the acyl group specified is hydroxyvaleroyl in which the position of the hydroxy group is unspecified.

name: 4-hydroxy-6-(15-hydroxypentadecyl)-pyran-2-one
definition: A 6-alkyl-4-hydroxy-2H-pyran-2-one that is 4-hydroxy-2H-pyran-2-one in which the hydrogen at position 6 is replaced by a 15-hydroxypentadecyl group.

name: O-hydroxypropionyl-L-carnitine
definition: An O-acyl-L-carnitine in which the acyl group specified is hydroxypropionyl in which the position of the hydroxy group is unspecified..

name: 4-hydroxy-6-(non-8-en-1-yl)-pyran-2-one
definition: A 6-alkyl-4-hydroxy-2H-pyran-2-one that is 4-hydroxy-2H-pyran-2-one in which the hydrogen at position 6 is replaced by a non-8-en-1-yl group.

name: O-butenoyl-L-carnitine
definition: An O-acyl-L-carnitine in which the acyl group specified is butenoyl in which the position of the double bond is unspecified.

name: 4-hydroxy-6-(14-hydroxytetradecyl)-pyran-2-one
definition: A 6-alkyl-4-hydroxy-2H-pyran-2-one that is 4-hydroxy-2H-pyran-2-one in which the hydrogen at position 6 is replaced by a 14-hydroxytetradecyl group.

name: 6-(hexadecan-2-yl)-4-hydroxy-pyran-2-one
definition: A 6-alkyl-4-hydroxy-2H-pyran-2-one that is 4-hydroxy-2H-pyran-2-one in which the hydrogen at position 6 is replaced by a hexadecan-2-yl group.

name: 4-hydroxy-6-(2-methyldecyl)-pyran-2-one
definition: A 6-alkyl-4-hydroxy-2H-pyran-2-one that is 4-hydroxy-2H-pyran-2-one in which the hydrogen at position 6 is replaced by a 2-methyldecyl group.

name: 4-hydroxy-6-(11-methylheptadecyl)-pyran-2-one
definition: A 6-alkyl-4-hydroxy-2H-pyran-2-one that is 4-hydroxy-2H-pyran-2-one in which the hydrogen at position 6 is replaced by an 11-methylheptadecyl group.

name: 4-hydroxy-6-(11-methyldodecyl)-pyran-2-one
definition: A 6-alkyl-4-hydroxy-2H-pyran-2-one that is 4-hydroxy-2H-pyran-2-one in which the hydrogen at position 6 is replaced by an 11-methyldodecyl group.

name: 3-(trimethylsilyl)propionate
definition: A monocarboxylic acid anion that is the conjugate base of 3-(trimethylsilyl)propionic acid, obtained by deprotonation of the carboxy group.

name: 3-(trimethylsilyl)propionic acid
definition: An organosilicon compound that is propionic acid substituted at position 3 by a trimethylsilyl group. It is used as internal reference in the NMR spectrum nuclear magnetic resonance for aqueous solvents (e.g. D2O).

name: chloroeremomycin(2+)
definition: An organic cation obtained by deprotonation of the carboxy group and protonation of the three amino functions of chloroeremomycin; major species at pH 7.3.

name: cis-3-enoyl-CoA(4-)
definition: An acyl-CoA (4-) arising from deprotonation of the phosphate and diphosphate OH groups of any cis-3-enoyl-CoA; major species at pH 7.3.

name: 4-hydroxy-6-(13-hydroxy-2-oxononadecyl)pyran-2-one
definition: An acyl tetraketide pyran-2-one that is 4-hydroxy-2H-pyran-2-one in which the hydrogen at position 6 is replaced by a 13-hydroxy-2-oxononadecyl group.

name: epivancomycin(1+)
definition: An organic cation obtained by deprotonation of the carboxy group and protonation of the two amino functions of epivancomycin; major species at pH 7.3.

name: 4-hydroxy-6-(17-hydroxy-2-oxoheptadecyl)pyran-2-one
definition: An acyl tetraketide pyran-2-one that is 4-hydroxy-2H-pyran-2-one in which the hydrogen at position 6 is replaced by a 17-hydroxy-2-oxoheptadecyl group.

name: 4-saturated-trans-3-enoyl-CoA(4-)
definition: Any trans-3-enoyl-CoA(4-) that is also saturated at position 4.

name: 4-hydroxy-6-(2-oxoundec-10-en-1-yl)pyran-2-one
definition: An acyl tetraketide pyran-2-one that is 4-hydroxy-2H-pyran-2-one in which the hydrogen at position 6 is replaced by a 2-oxoundec-10-en-1-yl group.

name: 4-hydroxy-6-(16-hydroxy-2-oxohexadecyl)pyran-2-one
definition: An acyl tetraketide pyran-2-one that is 4-hydroxy-2H-pyran-2-one in which the hydrogen at position 6 is replaced by a 16-hydroxy-2-oxohexadecyl group.

name: 4-hydroxy-6-(3-methyl-2-oxoheptadecyl)pyran-2-one
definition: An acyl tetraketide pyran-2-one that is 4-hydroxy-2H-pyran-2-one in which the hydrogen at position 6 is replaced by a 3-methyl-2-oxoheptadecyl group.

name: 4-hydroxy-6-(4-methyl-2-oxododecyl)pyran-2-one

name: (11Z)-18-hydroxyoctadecenoyl-CoA

name: (9Z,12Z)-18-hydroxyoctadecadienoyl-CoA

definition: A dicarboxylic acid diamide consisting of 3-aminoalanine in which the alpha-amino fuunction is acylated by a 3-carbamoyloxirane-2-carbonyl group. NB Although the relative configuration of the epoxide moiety has been assigned as trans, it has not yet been established whether the absolute configuration is R,R (as drawn) or S,S.

name: 7-hydroxylauric acid

name: 6-(acylmethyl)-4-hydroxy-2H-pyran-2-one

It is a mimic of HuR mRNA nucleotides 671-692 and acts as an antagonist that deregulates human antigen R (HuR) expression and inhibits AKT(SER473) phosphorylation in prostate and other cancers.

name: O-glutaconyl-L-carnitine

name: 1,2,3,4-tetrahydroquinoline-2,4-dione
definition: A member of the class of quinolones that is 1,2,3,4-tetrahydroquinoline in which the hydrogens at positions 2 and 4 have been replaced by oxo groups.

name: (3E)-nonenoyl-CoA(4-)
definition: A trans-3-enoyl-CoA(4-) arising from deprotonation of the phosphate and diphosphate OH groups of (3E)-nonenoyl-CoA major species at pH 7.3.

name: N-acyllysophosphatidylethanolamine
definition: Any glycerophospholipid consisting of a lysophosphatidylethanolamine in which one of the amino hydrogens is replaced by an acyl group.

name: N-acyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphoethanolamine
definition: Any glycerophospholipid consisting of sn-glycero-3-phosphoethanolamine in which one of the amino hydrogens is replaced by an acyl group.

name: (3E)-phycoerythrobilin
definition: The (3E)-isomer of phycoerythrobilin.

name: N-stearoyl-1-oleoyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphoethanolamine
definition: An N-acyllysophosphatidylethanolamine in which the N-acyl group is specified as stearoyl (octadecanoyl) while the phosphatidyl acyl group is specified as oleoyl (9Z-octadecenoyl)

name: 9,10-epoxyoctadecanoic acid
definition: An epoxy fatty acid consisting of octadecanoic (stearic) acid with a single epoxide located between positions 9 and 10.

name: lixisenatide
definition: A forty-four membered polypeptide consisting of L-His, Gly, L-Glu, Gly, L-Thr, L-Phe, L-Thr, L-Ser, L-Asp, L-Leu, L-Ser, L-Lys, L-Gln, L-Met, L-Glu, L-Glu, L-Glu, L-Ala, L-Val, L-Arg, L-Leu, L-Phe, L-Ile, L-Glu, L-Trp, L-Leu, L-Lys, L-Asn, Gly, Gly, LPro, L-Ser, L-Ser, Gly, L-Ala, L-Pro, L-Pro, L-Ser, L-Lys, L-Lys, L-Lys, L-Lys, L-Lys, and L-Lys-NH2 residues joined in sequence. Used as an adjunct to diet and exercise for the treatment of adults with type II diabetes.

name: alpha-Neup5Ac-(2->6)-beta-D-Galp-(1->4)-beta-D-GlcpNAc-(1->3)-D-GalpNAc

name: oleocanthal
definition: A carboxylic ester that is the 2-(p-hydroxyphenyl)ethyl ester of (3S)-4-formyl-3-(2-oxoethyl)hex-4-enoic acid. Oleocanthal is found in olive oil but it is not clear whether the natural product is a mixture of E/Z isomers or a single isomer as the two isomers readily interconvert in solution; most pharmacological studies will have been performed using a mixture.

name: 3-phenylpropanoyl-CoA

name: 3-phenylpropanoyl-CoA(4-)

name: 4beta-hydroxycholesterol

name: 4beta,7alpha-dihydroxycholesterol
definition: An oxysterol that is cholesterol carrying two additional hydroxy groups at the 4beta and 7alpha positions.

name: N-(4Z,7Z,10Z,13Z,16Z,19Z)-docosahexaenoyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphoethanolamine

name: N-(2-hydroxyacyl)sphingoid

name: 1,2-dihexadecanoyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphoglycerol

name: monodechloroaminopyrrolnitrin

name: aminopyrrolnitrin

name: 1-decanoyl-2-oleoylglycerol

name: 1-[(9Z)-octadecenoyl]-2-[(9Z)-hexadecenoyl]-sn-glycero-3-phosphocholine
definition: A phosphatidylcholine 34:2 in which the acyl groups specified at positions 1 and 2 are (9Z)-octadecenoyl and (9Z)-hexadecenoyl respectively.

name: 1-tetradecanoyl-2-[(5Z,8Z,11Z,14Z)-eicosatetraenoyl]-sn-glycero-3-phosphocholine
definition: A phosphatidylcholine 34:4 in which teh acyl groups specified at positions 1 and 2 are tetradecanoyl and (5Z,8Z,11Z,14Z)-eicosatetraenoyl respectively.

name: 1-docosanoyl-2-tetradecanoyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphocholine
definition: A phosphatidylcholine 36:0 in which the acyl groups specified at positions 1 and 2 are docosanoyl and tetradecanoyl respectively.

name: (7Z,10Z)-hexadecadienoyl group
definition: A fatty-acyl group derived from (7Z,10Z)-hexadecadienoic acid.

name: O-[S-(6Z)-hexadecenoylpantetheine-4'-phosphoryl]serine(1-) residue
definition: An O-(S-acylpantetheine-4'-phosphoryl)serine(1-) residue in which the S-acyl group is specified as (6Z)-hexadecenoyl.

name: 1-[(11Z)-octadecenoyl]-2-octadecanoyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphocholine
definition: A 1-octadecanoyl-2-octadecenoyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphocholine in which the acyl groups specified at positions 1 and 2 are (11Z)-octadecenoyl and octadecanoyl respectively.

name: 1-[(9Z,12Z)-octadecadienoyl]-2-octadecanoyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphocholine
definition: A phosphatidylcholine 36:2 in which the acyl groups specified at positions 1 and 2 are (9Z,12Z)-octadecadienoyl and octadecanoyl respectively.

name: (25R)-3beta,4beta-dihydroxycholest-5-en-26-al
definition: A 26-oxo steroid resulting from the oxidation of the terminal methyl group of 4beta,26-dihydroxycholesterol to the corresponding aldehyde.

name: (25R)-3beta,4beta-dihydroxycholest-5-en-26-oate(1-)
definition: A steroid acid anion that is the conjugate base of (25R)-3beta,4beta-dihydroxycholest-5-en-26-oic acid, obtained by deprotonation of the carboxy group; major species at pH 7.3.

name: (8E,10E,12Z)-octadecatrienoyl group
definition: A fatty-acyl group derived from (8E,10E,12Z)-octadecatrienoic acid

name: 1-hexadecanoyl-2-[(5Z,8Z,11Z)-icosatrienoyl]-sn-glycero-3-phosphocholine
definition: A phosphatidylcholine 36:3 in which the acyl groups at positions 1 and 2 are specified as hexadecanoyl and (5Z,8Z,11Z)-icosatrienoyl respectively.

name: 1-[(9Z)-octadecenoyl]-2-[(6Z,9Z,12Z)-octadecatrienoyl]-sn-glycero-3-phosphocholine
definition: A phosphatidylcholine 36:4 in which the acyl groups specified at positions 1 and 2 are (9Z)-octadecenoyl and (6Z,9Z,12Z)-octadecatrienoyl respectively.

name: (5Z,9Z,12Z,15Z)-octadecatetraenoic acid
definition: An octadecatetraenoic acid having four double bonds located at positions 5, 9, 12 and 15 (the all-cis-isomer).

name: N-methyl-L-alpha-amino acid zwitterion
definition: An amino acid zwitterion obtained by transfer of a proton from the amino to the carboxy group of any N-methyl-L-alpha-amino acid; major species at pH 7.3.

name: (9Z,12E)-octadecadienoic acid
definition: An octadecadienoic acid having two double bonds located at positions 9 and 12 (the 9Z,12E-geoisomer).

name: (8E,10E,12Z)-octadecatrienoic acid
definition: A conjugated linolenic acid having three double bonds located at positions 8, 10 and 12 (the 8E,10E,12Z-geoisomer)

name: bromocresol purple
definition: A member of the class of 2,1-benzoxathioles that is 2,1-benzoxathiole 1,1-dioxide in which both of the hydrogens at position 3 have been substituted by 3-bromo-4-hydroxy-5-methylphenyl groups. A hydrophilic dye that is used as a pH indicator and to measure serum albumin concentrations.

name: cadmium nitrate tetrahydrate
definition: A hydrate that is the tetrahydrate form of cadmium nitrate.

name: cadmium sulfate hydrate
definition: A hydrate composed of cadmium sulfate and water in a 3:8 ratio.

name: calcium chloride dihydrate
definition: A hydrate that is the dihydrate form of calcium chloride.

name: calcium nitrate tetrahydrate
definition: A hydrate that is the tetrahydrate form of calcium nitrate.

name: 1-tetradecanoyl-2-tetracosanoyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphocholine
definition: A phosphatidylcholine 38:0 in which the acyl groups specified at positions 1 and 2 are tetradecanoyl and tetracosanoyl respectively.

name: 1-eicosanoyl-2-[(11Z)-octadecenoyl]-sn-glycero-3-phosphocholine
definition: A  phosphatidylcholine 38:1 in which the acyl groups specified at positions 1 and 2 are eicosanoyl and (11Z)-octadecenoyl respectively.

name: 1-[(5Z,8Z,11Z,14Z,17Z)-eicosapentaenoyl]-2-[(9Z)-octadecenoyl]-sn-glycero-3-phosphocholine
definition: A phosphatidylcholine 38:6 in which the acyl groups specified at positions 1 and 2 are (5Z,8Z,11Z,14Z,17Z)-eicosapentaenoyl and (9Z)-octadecenoyl respectively.

name: 1-tetracosanoyl-2-octadecanoyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphocholine
definition: A phosphatidylcholine 42:0 in which the acyl groups specified at positions 1 and 2 are tetracosanoyl and octadecanoyl respectively.

name: cobalt dinitrate
definition: A cobalt salt in which the cobalt metal is in the +2 oxidation state and the counter-anion is nitrate.

name: 1-docosanoyl-2-eicosanoyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphocholine
definition: A phosphatidylcholine 42:0 in which the acyl groups specified at positions 1 and 2 are docosanoyl and eicosanoyl respectively.

name: 1-eicosanoyl-2-docosanoyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphocholine
definition: A phosphatidylcholine 42:0 in which the acyl groups specified at positions 1 and 2 are eicosanoyl and docosanoyl respectively.

name: 1-tetracosanoyl-2-[(9Z)-octadecenoyl]-sn-glycero-3-phosphocholine
definition: A phosphatidylcholine 42:1 in which the acyl groups specified at positions 1 and 2 are tetracosanoyl and (9Z)-octadecenoyl respectively.

name: alpha-Kdo-(2->8)-alpha-Kdo-(2->4)-alpha-Kdo-(2->6)-lipid IVA(7-)
definition: A lipid IVA oxoanion obtained by deprotonation of the phospho and carboxy groups of alpha-Kdo-(2->8)-alpha-Kdo-(2->4)-alpha-Kdo-(2->6)-lipid IVA; major species at pH 7.3.

name: greigite
definition: An iron sulfide mineral with formula Fe3S4.

name: 1-octadecyl-2-octadecanoyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphocholine
definition: A phosphatidylcholine O-36:0 in which the alkyl and acyl groups specified at positions 1 and 2 are octadecyl and octadecanoyl respectively.

name: 1-hexadecyl-2-eicosanoyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphocholine
definition: A phosphatidylcholine O-36:0 in which the alkyl and acyl groups specified at positions 1 and 2 are hexadecyl and eicosanoyl respectively.

name: 1-[(1Z)-octadecenyl]-2-[(9Z)-octadecenoyl]-sn-glycero-3-phosphocholine
definition: A 1-(Z)-alk-1-enyl-2-acyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphocholine in which the alkeny and acyl group specified at positions 1 and 2 are (1Z)-octadecenyl and (9Z)-octadecenoyl respectively.

name: 1-hexadecyl-2-docosanoyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphocholine
definition: A phosphatidylcholine O-38:0 in which the alkyl and acyl groups specified at positions 1 and 2 are hexadecyl and docosanoyl respectively.

name: hexaammonium heptamolybdate tetrahydrate
definition: A hydrate that is the heptahydrate form of hexaammonium heptamolybdate.

name: 1-[(8Z,11Z,14Z,17Z)-icosatetraenoyl]-sn-glycero-3-phosphocholine
definition: A lysophosphatidylcholine 20:4 in which the the acyl group at position 1 is specified  as (8Z,11Z,14Z,17Z)-icosatetraenoyl.

name: 1-tetracosanoyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphocholine
definition: A lysophosphatidylcholine 24:0 in which the acyl group is specified as tetracosanoyl and is located at position 1.

name: 1-tetradecanoyl-2-decanoyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphocholine
definition: A phosphatidylcholine 24:0 in which the acyl groups specified at positions 1 and 2 are tetradecanoyl and decanoyl respectively.

name: 2',4',5',7'-tetrabromofluorescein
definition: A xanthene dye that is fluorescein bearing bromine substituents at positions 2', 4', 5' and 7'.

name: D-arabinofuranose 5-phosphate
definition: The furanose form of D-arabinose 5-phosphate.

name: 1-nonanoyl-2-pentadecanoyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphocholine
definition: A phosphatidylcholine 24:0 in which the acyl groups specified at positions 1 and 2 are nonanoyl and pentadecanoyl respectively.

name: O-[S-5-hexenoylpantetheine-4'-phosphoryl]serine(1-) residue
definition: An O-(S-acylpantetheine-4'-phosphoryl)serine(1-) residue in which the S-acyl group is specified as 5-hexenoyl.

name: O-[S-5-hexynoylpantetheine-4'-phosphoryl]serine(1-) residue
definition: An O-(S-acylpantetheine-4'-phosphoryl)serine(1-) residue in which the S-acyl group is specified as 5-hexynoyl.

name: butamben picrate
definition: An organoammonium salt resulting from the formal reaction of butamben with 0.5 mol eq. of picric acid.

name: 3beta-hydroxychola-5,22-dien-24-oyl-CoA
definition: A steroidal acyl-CoA that results from the formal condensation of the thiol group of coenzyme A with the carboxy group of 3beta-hydroxychola-5,22-dien-24-oic acid.

name: antifungal drug
definition: Any antifungal agent used to prevent or treat fungal infections in humans or animals.

name: antifungal agrochemical
definition: Any substance used in acriculture, horticulture, forestry, etc. for its fungicidal properties.

name: N-acetyl-beta-D-galactosaminyl-(1->4)-N-acetyl-beta-D-glucosaminyl-(1->2)-alpha-D-mannosyl group
definition: A mannosyl group derived from N-acetyl-beta-D-galactosaminyl-(1->4)-N-acetyl-beta-D-glucosaminyl-(1->2)-alpha-D-mannose.

name: 1,3-dicaffeoylquinate
definition: A quinate that is the conjugate base of 1,3-dicaffeoylquinic acid.

name: 1-propanoylproline
definition: A N-acylpyrrolidine that is proline substituted by a propanoyl group at the nitrogen atom.

name: magnesium dichloride hexahydrate
definition: A hydrate that is the hexahydrate form of magnesium dichloride.

name: 1-[(11Z)-octadecenoyl]-2-hexadecanoyl-sn-glycerol
definition: A diacylglycerol 34:1 in which the acyl groups specified at positions 1 and 2 are (11Z)-octadecenoyl and hexadecanoyl respectively.

name: N-acetyl-beta-D-glucosaminyl-(1->4)-N-acetyl-beta-D-glucosaminyl-(1->4)-N-acetyl-beta-D-glucosaminyl group
definition: An N-acetyl-D-glucosaminyl group derived from N-acetyl-beta-D-glucosaminyl-(1->4)-N-acetyl-beta-D-glucosaminyl-(1->4)-N-acetyl-beta-D-glucosamine. A trisaccharide group formed from the hydrolysis of chitin (a linear polymer of repeated GlcNAc units).

name: 2-dehydro-L-gluconic acid
definition: A  ketogluconic acid that is L-gluconic acid in which the hydroxy group at position 2 has been oxidized to a keto group.

name: 3-O-feruloyl-D-quinic acid
definition: A quinic acid that is the 3-O-feruloyl derivative of D-quinic acid.

name: 4-deoxythreonic acid
definition: The (2S,3R)-stereoisomer of 2,3-dihydroxybutanoic acid.

name: monoacylglycerol 20:5
definition: A monoglyceride in which the acyl group contains a total of 20 carbon atoms and 5 double bonds at unspecified positions.

name: imidazole antifungal agent
definition: A compound that has significant antifungal properties whose structure contains an imidazole moiety.

name: 2-nitrophenols
definition: A mononitrophenol that is 2-nitrophenol and its derivatives resulting from substitution of one or more of the hydrogens attached to the benzene ring by a non-nitro group.

name: (R)-uniconazole
definition: A (1E)-1-(4-chlorophenyl)-4,4-dimethyl-2-(1H-1,2,4-triazol-1-yl)pent-1-en-3-ol that has R configuration at the chiral centre. It is the enantiomer of the fungicide and plant growth retardant uniconazole-P; the fungicide and plant growth retardant uniconazole is the racemic mixture comprising equimolar amounts of (R)-uniconazole and uniconazole-P.

name: EC 1.14.13.78 (ent-kaurene oxidase) inhibitor
definition: An EC 1.14.13.* (oxidoreductase acting on paired donors, incorporating 1 atom of oxygen, with NADH or NADPH as one donor) inhibitor that interferes with the action of ent-kaurene oxidase (E.C. 1.14.13.78).

name: sodium fluorophosphate
definition: Sodium fluorophosphate, commonly abbreviated MFP, is an inorganic compound with the chemical formula Na2PO3F. Typical for a salt, MFP is odourless, colourless, and water-soluble. This salt is an ingredient in toothpastes.

name: 1-hexadecyl-2-[(5Z,8Z,11Z,14Z,17Z)-eicosapentaenoyl]-sn-glycero-3-phosphocholine
definition: A phosphatidylcholine O-36:5 in which the alkyl and acyl groups specified at positions 1 and 2 are hexadecyl and (5Z,8Z,11Z,14Z,17Z)-eicosapentaenoyl respectively.

name: phosphatidylcholine 33:1
definition: A 1,2-diacyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphocholine in which the acyl groups specified at C-1 and C-2 contain 33 carbons in total with 1 double bond.

name: RO4929097
definition: A member of the class of dibenzoazepines that is the amide formed from formal condensation of the carboxy group of 2,2-dimethyl-3-oxo-3-[(2,2,3,3,3-pentafluoropropyl)amino]propanoic acid with the amino group of (7S)-7-amino-5,7-dihydrodibenzo[b,d]azepin-6-one.

name: O-methylglutarylcarnitine
definition: An O-acylcarnitine in which the acyl group specified is methylglutaryl.

name: spirit blue base
definition: An aromatic amime that is the base component of spirit blue dye (the hydrochloride salt).

name: C5-acylcarnitine
definition: Any O-acylcarnitine in which the acyl group contains a total of 5 carbon atoms.

name: N-myristoylglycinate
definition: An N-acylglycinate that is the conjugate base of N-myristoylglycine, obtained by deprotonation of the carboxy group; major species at pH 7.3.

name: EC 1.14.13.97 (taurochenodeoxycholate 6alpha-hydroxylase) inhibitor
definition: An EC 1.14.13.* (oxidoreductase acting on paired donors, incorporating 1 atom of oxygen, with NADH or NADPH as one donor) inhibitor that interferes with the action of EC 1.14.13.97 (taurochenodeoxycholate 6alpha-hydroxylase).

name: N-[(2S,3S,4R)-1-(alpha-D-galactosyloxy)-3,4-dihydroxyoctadecan-2-yl]hexacosanethioamide
definition: A glycosphingolipid identical with alpha-galactosylceramide (alpha-GalCer) with the exception of the replacement of the C-2 carbonyl oxygen on the acyl chain with a sulfur atom.

name: 6H-dibenzo[b,d]pyran-6-one
definition: A benzochromenone that is 6H-dibenzo[b,d]pyran substituted by an oxo group at position 6.

name: 1-(3,4-dimethoxyphenyl)ethanol
definition: A member of the class of  benzyl alcohols that is 1-phenylethan-1-ol substituted by methoxy groups at positions 3 and 4 respectively.

name: 2-hydroxyhexanoic acid
definition: A hydroxy fatty acid that is caproic (hexanoic) acid substituted by a hydroxy group at position 2.

name: 3-hydroxymandelic acid
definition: A 2-hydroxy monocarboxylic acid that is mandelic acid substituted by a hydroxy group at position 3'.

name: 3-morpholinopropylamine
definition: A member of the class of  morpholines that is  morpholine substituted by a 3-aminopropyl group a the N atom.

name: 4-acetoxy acetophenone
definition: A methyl ketone that is acetophenone substituted by an acetoxy group at position 4.

name: 4-acetoxy benzaldehyde
definition: An acetate ester that is phenyl acetate substituted by a formyl group at position 4.

name: trans-coniferyl alcohol diacetate
definition: A phenyl acetate that is the diacetate derivative of coniferol.

name: methyl p-coumarate acetate
definition: A phenyl acetate obtained by the formal condensation of the hydroxy group of trans-4-coumaric acid with acetic acid.

name: methyl 4-acetoxy-3-methoxycinnamate
definition: A phenyl acetate obtained by the formal condensation of the carboxy group of acetic acid with the hydroxy group of methyl ferulate.

name: 3,4-dimethoxybenzyl acetate
definition: An acetate ester obtained by the formal condensation of  (3,4-dimethoxyphenyl)methanol (veratryl alcohol) with acetic acid.

name: cis-5-dodecenoic acid
definition: The cis-stereoisomer of 5-dodecenoic acid.

name: methyl-3,4-dimethoxycinnamate
definition: An alkyl cinnamate obtained by the formal condensation of carboxy group of 3,4-dimethoxycinnamic acid with methanol.

name: 4-coumaric acid methyl ester
definition: A cinnamate ester that is the methyl ester of 4-coumaric acid.

name: N-acetylhistidine
definition: A histidine derivative that is histidine in which one of the hydrogens of the alpha-amino group is substituted by an acetyl group.

name: syringylresinol diacetate
definition: A lignin that is the diacetate ester of syringylresinol.

name: trans-3-hexenedioic acid
definition: The trans-stereoisomer of 3-hexenedioic acid.

name: vanillyl beta-D-glucopyranoside
definition: A monosaccharide derivative that is vanillyl alcohol attached to a beta-D-glucopyranosyl residue at position 1.

name: veratrone
definition: An aromatic ketone that is propanone substituted by a 3,4-dimethoxyphenyl group at position 1, a hydroxy group at position 3 and a 2-methoxyphenoxy group at position 2 respectively.

name: loperamide(1+)
definition: An organic cation obtained by protonation of the tertiary amino function of loperamide.

name: 4-[2-(2-methyl-1,3-thiazol-4-yl)ethyl]-3-(non-8-en-1-yl)oxetan-2-one
definition: A beta-lactone carrying non-8-en-1-yl and 2-(2-methyl-1,3-thiazol-4-yl)ethyl substituents at positions 3 and 4 respectively.

name: propyl decanoate
definition: A decanoate ester obtained by the formal condensation of carboxy group of decanoic acid with propanol.

name: 1-hexadecanoyl-2-octadecanoyl-sn-glycerol
definition: A diacylglycerol 34:0 in which the acyl groups specified at positions 1 and 2 are hexadecanoyl and octadecanoyl respectively.

name: 2-oxohexadecanoic acid
definition: An oxo fatty acid that is the 2-oxo derivative of hexadecanoic (palmitic) acid.

name: stattic
definition: A member of the class of 1-benzothiophenes that is 1-benzothiophene-1,1-dioxide substituted at position 6 by a nitro group. Used as a radiosensitising agent for esophageal squamous cell carcinoma.

name: (R)-fluoxetine hydrochloride
definition: A hydrochloride obtained by reaction of (R)-fluoxetine with one equivalent of hydrochloric acid.

name: (S)-fluoxetine hydrochloride
definition: A hydrochloride obtained by reaction of (S)-fluoxetine with one equivalent of hydrochloric acid.

name: 1-acyl-2-palmitoylglycerolipid
definition: Any glycerolipid in which the acyl group at position 2 of the glycerol moiety is specified as palmitoyl.

name: flexirubin
definition: The parent member of the class of flexirubins obtained by formal condensation of the carboxy group of 17-(4-hydroxy-3-methylphenyl)heptadeca-2,4,6,8,10,12,14,16-octaenoic acid with one of the phenolic hydroxy groups of 2-dodecyl-5-methyl resorcinol.

name: 4alpha-hydroxymethyl-4beta-methyl-5alpha-8-cholesten-3beta-ol
definition: A 3beta-sterol that is 5alpha-cholest-8-en-3beta-ol carrying hydroxymethyl and methyl substituents at position 4.

name: lipid IVB(4-)
definition: An lipid IVA oxoanion arising from deprotonation of the phosphate OH groups of lipid IVB; major species at pH 7.3.

name: 4alpha-methyl-5alpha-cholest-8-en-3-one
definition: A 3-oxo steroid that is 5alpha-cholest-8-en-3-one carrying an additional methyl substituent at position 4alpha.

name: 4alpha-methyl-5alpha-cholest-8-en-3beta-ol
definition: A 3beta-sterol that is 5alpha-cholest-8-en-3beta-ol carrying an additional methyl substituent at position 4alpha.

name: acid fuchsin (free acid form)
definition: An arenesulfonic acid that is 3-[(4-amino-3-methylphenyl)(4-aminophenyl)methylidene]-6-iminocyclohexa-1,4-diene-1-sulfonic acid in which the hydrogens ortho to the amino functions are replaced by phenyl groups. The disodium salt is the biological stain 'acid fuchsin'.

name: 3beta-hydroxylanost-8-en-32-al
definition: A tetracyclic triterpenoid that is lanost-8-ene carrying hydroxy and oxo substituents at positions 3beta and 30 respectively.

name: benzimidazolylcarbamate fungicide
definition: Any carbamate fungicide that contains a benzimidazolyl group attached to the nitrogen of the carbamate moiety.

name: acid green 5(1+)
definition: The iminium ion derived from acid green 5 (the disodium salt).

name: 35-amino-3-methylbacteriohopane-30,31,32,33,34-pentol
definition: A member of the class of hopanoids that is bacteriohopane-30,31,32,33,34-pentol carrying additional methyl and amino substituents at positions 3 and 35 respectively. Isolated from Methylococcus capsulatus.

name: 35-aminobacteriohopane-31,32,33,34-tetrol
definition: A member of the class of hopanoids that is bacteriohopane-31,32,33,34-tetrol carrying an additional amino substituent at position 35. Isolated from Methylococcus capsulatus.

name: (7R)-6-deoxy-D-manno-oct-7-ulosuronate
definition: A carbohydrate acid anion obtained by deprotonation of the carboxy group of (7R)-6-deoxy-D-manno-oct-7-ulosuronic acid; major species at pH 7.3.

name: 8-amino-3,8-dideoxy-alpha-D-manno-oct-2-ulosonic acid zwitterion
definition: An amino acid zwitterion obtained by transfer of a proton from the carboxy to the amino group of 8-amino-3,8-dideoxy-alpha-D-manno-octulosonic acid; major species at pH 7.3.

name: 7-hydroxy-8-[(E)-phenyldiazenyl]naphthalene-1,3-disulfonic acid
definition: A naphthalenesulfonic acid that is naphthalene-1,3-disulfonic acid carrying additional hydroxy and phenyldiazenyl substituents at positions 7 and 8 respectively. The disodium salt is the biological stain 'orange G'.

name: 2-tert-butyl-9-fluoro-1,6-dihydrobenzo[h]imidazo[4,5-f]isoquinolin-7-one
definition: An organic heterotetracyclic compound that is 1,6-dihydrobenzo[h]imidazo[4,5-f]isoquinolin-7-one bearing additional tert-butyl and fluoro substituents at positions 2 and 9 respectively.

name: 4-[(2,4-dimethylphenyl)diazenyl]-3-hydroxynaphthalene-2,7-disulfonic acid
definition: A naphthalenesulfonic acid that is naphthalene-2,7-disulfonic acid carrying additional hydroxy and (2,4-dimethylphenyl)diazenyl substituents at positions 3 and 4 respectively. The disodium salt is the biological stain 'acid red 26'.

name: 7-hydroxy-8-[(naphthalen-1-yl)diazenyl]naphthalene-1,3-disulfonic acid
definition: A naphthalenesulfonic acid that is naphthalene-1,3-disulfonic acid carrying additional hydroxy and (naphthalen-1-yl)diazenylsubstituents at positions 7 and 8 respectively. The disodium salt is the biological stain 'acid red 44'.

name: tulipalin B
definition: A member of the class of butan-4-olides that is 3-methylidenebutan-4-olide carrying an additional hydroxy substituent at position 4 (the 4R-enantiomer)

name: 6-tuliposide B
definition: A 6-O-acyl-D-glucose in which the 6-acyl group is specified as (3S)-3,4-dihydroxy-2-methylidenebutanoyl. A secondary metabolite with potent antibacterial activity, occurring specifically in tulip anthers.

name: morpholine antifungal drug
definition: Any morpholine antifungal agent used to treat fungal infections in humans or animals.

name: trans-caffeoyl-CoA(4-)
definition: An acyl-CoA(4-) obtained by deprotonation of the phosphate and diphosphate OH groups of 3-trans-caffeoyl-CoA; major species at pH 7.3.

name: 3-oxocholesta-4,24-dien-26-oyl-CoA
definition: A steroidal acyl-CoA that results from the formal condensation of the thiol group of coenzyme A with the carboxy group of 3-oxocholesta-4,24-dien-26-oic acid.

name: N-[(Z)-dodec-2-enoyl]pyrrolidine
definition: A fatty amide resulting from the formal condensation of the carboxy group of (Z)-dodec-2-enoic acid with the amino group of pyrrolidine.

name: 6-hydroxy-N-methylmyosmine(1+)
definition: An organic cation obtained by protonation of the tertiary amino function of 6-hydroxy-N-methylmyosmine; major species at pH 7.3.

name: (2R)-2-methyltetradecanoyl-CoA
definition: A (2R)-2-methylacyl-CoA that results from the formal condensation of the thiol group of coenzyme A with the carboxy group of (2R)-2-methyltetradecanoic acid.

name: hexamidine
definition: A polyether that is the bis(4-guanidinophenyl) ether of hexane-1,6-diol.

name: florfenicol
definition: A carboxamide that is the N-dichloroacetyl derivative of (1R,2S)-2-amino-3-fluoro-1-[4-(methanesulfonyl)phenyl]propan-1-ol. A synthetic veterinary antibiotic that is used for treatment of bovine respiratory disease and foot rot; also used in aquaculture.

name: Biebrich scarlet (acid form)
definition: An arenesulfonic acid that is m-[(4-sulfophenyl)diazenyl]benzene-1-sulfonic acid carrying a (2-hydroxynaphthalen-1-yl)diazenyl substituent at position 2. The disodium salt is the biological stain 'Biebrich scarlet'.

name: Biebrich scarlet(2-)
definition: An organosulfonate oxoanion obtained by deprotonation of the sulfo groups of Biebrich scarlet.

name: 7-hydroxy-8-{[4-(phenyldiazenyl)phenyl]diazenyl}naphthalene-1,3-disulfonic acid
definition: A naphthalenesulfonic acid that is 7-hydroxynaphthalene-1,3-disulfonic acid substituted at position 8 by a [4-(phenyldiazenyl)phenyl]diazenyl group. The disodium salt is the biological stain 'woodstain scarlet'.

name: semicarbazone
definition: A hydrazone resulting from the formal condensation of an aldehyde or ketone with the non-acylated nitrogen of semicarbazide or its substituted derivatives.

name: 3-[(4-anilinophenyl)diazenyl]benzene-1-sulfonate
definition: An organosulfonate oxoanion obtained by deprotonation of the sulfo group of 3-[(4-anilinophenyl)diazenyl]benzene-1-sulfonic acid.

name: diacylglycerol 40:0
definition: A diglyceride in which the acyl groups  contain a total of 40 carbons and 0 double bonds.

name: lipid IIB
definition: A member of the class of lipid As that is lipid IIA in which one of the free OH groups on the two N-hydroxytetradecanoyl groups is carrying a palimitoyl group.

name: estra-1,5(10)-diene-3,4,17-trione
definition: An o-quinone resulting from the formal oxidation of the dihydroxyphenyl moiety of 4-hydroxyestrone.

name: 3-ethoxypropyl acetate
definition: An acetate ester that is propyl acetate substituted by an ethoxy group at position 3.

name: diethyl 2-hydroxypentanedioate
definition: A diester obtained by the formal condensation of both the carboxy groups of 2-hydroxyglutaric acid with two molecules of ethanol respectively.

name: 3-decanone
definition: A ketone that is decane in which the methylene hydrogens at position 3 are replaced by an oxo group.

name: 4-chlorobutanol
definition: A primary alcohol that is butan-1-ol substituted by a chloro group at position 4.

name: 7-tridecanol
definition: A secondary alcohol that s tridecane substituted by a hydroxy group at position 7.

name: ethyl 3-nonenoate
definition: A fatty acid ethyl ester obtained by the formal condensation of 3-nonenoic acid with ethanol.

name: 8-amino-3,8-dideoxy-alpha-D-manno-oct-2-ulosonic acid
definition: An amino monosaccharide obtained by replacement of the 8-hydroxy group of 3-deoxy-alpha-D-manno-oct-2-ulopyranosonic acid by an amino group.

name: 4-hydroxy-2-methylacetophenone
definition: A member of the class of acetophenones that is acetophenone substituted by a hydroxy group at position 4 and a methyl group at position 2 respectively.

name: benzocyclobutene
definition: A carbobicyclic compound that is benzene fused to a cyclobutane ring.

name: dodec-10-yn-1-ol
definition: An acetylenic compound that is dodecane carrying a triple bond at position 10 and a hydroxy group at position 1 respectively.

name: alizarin blue
definition: An organic heterotetracyclic compound that is naphtho[2,3-f]quinoline-7,12-dione carrying two additional hydroxy groups at positions 5 and 6. Used as an acid-base indicator. Between pH 0.0 and pH 1.6 it changes from pink to yellow, and between pH 6.0 and pH 7.6 it changes from yellow to green.

name: 3-pyridinol
definition: A monohydroxypyridine that is pyridine in which the hydrogen at position 3 has been replaced by a hydroxy group. It has been detected as a thermal degradation product from the smoke of the burning leaves of Salvia divinorum, a Mexican psychoactive plant.

name: beta-D-Galp-(1->4)-beta-D-GlcpNAc-(1->6)-[beta-D-Galp-(1->4)-beta-D-GlcpNAc-(1->2)]-alpha-D-Manp-(1->6)-{beta-D-Galp-(1->4)-beta-D-GlcpNAc-(1->4)-[beta-D-Galp-(1->4)-beta-D-GlcpNAc-(1->2)]-alpha-D-Manp-(1->3)}-beta-D-Manp-(1->4)-beta-D-GlcpNAc-(1->4)-beta-D-GlcpNAc
definition: An amino oligosaccharide that is a branched tridecasaccharide derivative in which beta-D-galactosyl-(1->4)-N-acetyl-beta-D-glucosaminyl-(1->2)-[beta-D-galactosyl-(1->4)-N-acetyl-beta-D-glucosaminyl-(1->6)]-alpha-D-mannosyl and beta-D-galactosyl-(1->4)-N-acetyl-beta-D-glucosaminyl-(1->2)-[beta-D-galactosyl-(1->4)-N-acetyl-beta-D-glucosaminyl-(1->4)]-alpha-D-mannosyl branched pentasaccharide units are linked (1->6) and (1->3) respectively to the mannose residue of a beta-D-mannosyl-(1->4)-N-acetyl-beta-D-glucosaminyl-(1->4)-N-acetyl-D-glucosamine trisaccharide.

name: alpha-D-Galp-(1->3)-beta-D-Galp-(1->3)-[alpha-L-Fucp-(1->4)]-beta-D-GlcpNAc-(1->2)-alpha-D-Manp-(1->3)-{alpha-D-Galp-(1->3)-beta-D-Galp-(1->3)-[alpha-L-Fucp-(1->4)]-beta-D-GlcpNAc-(1->2)-alpha-D-Manp-(1->6)}-beta-D-Manp-(1->4)-beta-D-GlcpNAc-(1->4)-D-GlcpNAc
definition: An amino oligosaccharide that is a tridecasaccharide derivative in which two alpha-D-galactosyl-(1->3)-beta-D-galactosyl-(1->3)-[alpha-L-fucosyl-(1->4)]-N-acetyl-beta-D-glucosaminyl-(1->2)-alpha-D-mannosyl branched pentasaccharide chains are linked (1->3) and (1->6) to the mannose residue of a beta-D-mannosyl-(1->4)-N-acetyl-beta-D-glucosaminyl-(1->4)-N-acetyl-D-glucosamine trisaccharide.

name: 5-epi-valiolone 7-phosphate
definition: A member of the class of cyclitols that is 5-epi-valiolone carrying a phospho substituent at position 7.

name: beta-D-GlcpNAc-(1->2)-alpha-D-Manp-(1->6)-[beta-D-Galp-(1->4)-beta-D-GlcpNAc-(1->2)-alpha-D-Manp-(1->3)]-beta-D-Manp-(1->4)-beta-D-GlcpNAc-(1->4)-D-GlcpNAc
definition: An amino octasaccharide in which an N-acetyl-beta-D-glucosaminyl-(1->2)-alpha-D-mannosyl disaccharide chain and a beta-D-galactosyl-(1->3)-N-acetyl-beta-D-glucosaminyl-(1->2)-alpha-D-mannosyl chain are linked (1->6) and (1->3) respectively to the mannose residue of a beta-D-mannosyl-(1->4)-N-acetyl-beta-D-glucosaminyl-(1->4)-N-acetyl-D-glucosamine trisaccharide.

name: methyl undecenate
definition: A fatty acid methyl ester of 10-undecenoic acid.

name: octyl formate
definition: A formate ester of  octan-1-ol.

name: isobutyl benzoate
definition: A benzoate ester obtained by the formal condensation of benzoic acid with isobutanol.

name: hexyl acetate
definition: The acetate ester of  hexan-1-ol.

name: isoxazoline
definition: An organic heteromonocyclic compound that is a dihydro derivative of any isoxazole.

name: (S)-fluxametamide
definition: A 4-[5-(3,5-dichlorophenyl)-5-(trifluoromethyl)-4,5-dihydro-1,2-oxazol-3-yl]-N-[(methoxyamino)methylidene]-2-methylbenzamide that is the (S)-enantiomer of fluxametamide.

name: (R)-fluxametamide
definition: A 4-[5-(3,5-dichlorophenyl)-5-(trifluoromethyl)-4,5-dihydro-1,2-oxazol-3-yl]-N-[(methoxyamino)methylidene]-2-methylbenzamide that is the (R)-enantiomer of fluxametamide.

name: epsilon-metofluthrin
definition: A carboxylic ester obtained by formal condensation between the carboxy group of (1R,3R)-2,2-dimethyl-3-[(1Z)-prop-1-en-1-yl]cyclopropane-1-carboxylic acid with the benzylic hydroxy group of [2,3,5,6-tetrafluoro-4-(methoxymethyl)phenyl]methanol.

name: ethyl 3-hexenoate
definition: A fatty acid ethyl ester of 3-hexenoic acid.

name: pydiflumetofen
definition: A racemate comprising equimolar amounts of (R)- and (S)-pydiflumetofen.

name: ethyl 4-octenoate
definition: A fatty acid ethyl ester of 4-octenoic acid.

name: N(2)-acyl-L-glutaminate
definition: An N-acyl-L-alpha-amino acid anion that is the conjugate base of N(2)-acyl-L-glutamine, obtained by deprotonation of the carboxy group; major structure at pH 7.3.

name: (4-hexyl-2,5-dioxo-2,5-dihydro-3-furanyl)acetic acid
definition: A cyclic dicarboxylic anhydride that is furan-2,5-dione substituted by at position 3 by a  carboxymethyl group and a hexyl group at position 4.

name: 7-octen-2-ol
definition: An olefinic compound that octan-2-ol carrying a double bond at position 7.

name: 3-methylsuccinic anhydride
definition: A tetrahydrofurandione that is succinic anhydride substituted by  a methyl group at position 3.

name: 1,3-dioxolane
definition: A cyclic acetal that is pentane in which the carbon atoms at positions 1 and 3 are replaced by oxygen atoms respectively.

name: 3-cyano-2-butanone
definition: A methyl ketone that is butan-2-one substituted by a cyano group at position 3.

name: 2,6-dimethyl-1,3,5,7-octatetraene
definition: An alkatetraene that is 1,3,5,7-octatetraene substituted by methyl groups at positions 2 and 6 respectively.

name: 4-hydroxyestrone
definition: A 4-hydroxy steroid that is estrone substituted by a hydroxy group at position 4.

name: 6alpha-hydroxyestrone
definition: A 6alpha-hydroxy steroid that is estrone substituted by an alpha-hydroxy group at position 6.

name: N-icosanoylglycine
definition: A N-acylglycine in which the acyl group is specified as icosanoyl.

name: 3-furaldehyde
definition: An aldehyde that is furan substituted by a formyl group at position 3.

name: alpha-L-Fucp-(1->2)-[alpha-D-Galp-(1->3)]-beta-D-Galp-(1->4)-beta-D-GlcpNAc-(1->3)-{alpha-L-Fucp-(1->2)-[alpha-D-Galp-(1->3)]-beta-D-Galp-(1->4)-beta-D-GlcpNAc-(1->6)}-D-GalpNAc
definition: An amino nonasaccharide in which two alpha-L-fucosyl-(1->2)-[beta-D-galactosyl-(1->3)]-beta-D-galactosyl-(1->4)-N-acetyl-beta-D-glucosaminyl chains are linked (1->3) and (1->6) to D-galactose.

name: alpha-L-Fucp-(1->2)-[alpha-D-GalpNAc-(1->3)]-beta-D-Galp-(1->4)-beta-D-GlcpNAc-(1->3)-{alpha-L-Fucp-(1->2)-[alpha-D-GalpNAc-(1->3)]-beta-D-Galp-(1->4)-beta-D-GlcpNAc-(1->6)}-D-GalpNAc
definition: An amino oligosaccharide that is an undecaasaccharide derivative in which two alpha-L-fucosyl-(1->2)-[N-acetyl-beta-D-galactosaminyl-(1->3)]-beta-D-galactosyl-(1->4)-N-acetyl-beta-D-glucosaminyl chains are linked (1->3) and (1->6) to D-galactose.

name: 4-hydroxypyridine
definition: A monohydroxypyridine that is pyridine in which the hydrogen at position 4 has been replaced by a hydroxy group.

name: alpha-D-GalpNAc-(1->3)-[alpha-L-Fucp-(1->2)]-beta-D-Galp-(1->4)-beta-D-GlcpNAc-(1->2)-alpha-D-Manp-(1->3)-{alpha-D-GalpNAc-(1->3)-[alpha-L-Fucp-(1->2)]-beta-D-Galp-(1->4)-beta-D-GlcpNAc-(1->2)-alpha-D-Manp-(1->6)}-beta-D-Manp-(1->4)-beta-D-GlcpNAc-(1->4)-[alpha-L-Fucp-(1->6)]-beta-D-GlcpNAc
definition: An amino oligosaccharide that is a tetradecasaccharide derivative in which two N-acetyl-alpha-D-galactosaminyl-(1->3)-[alpha-L-fucosyl-(1->2)]-beta-D-galactosyl-(1->4)-N-acetyl-beta-D-glucosaminyl-(1->2)-alpha-D-mannosyl branched pentasaccharide units are linked (1->3) and (1->6) to the mannose residue of a beta-D-mannosyl-(1->4)-N-acetyl-beta-D-glucosaminyl-(1->4)-[alpha-L-fucosyl-(1->6)]-N-acetyl-D-glucosamine branched tetrasaccharide.

name: 16beta-hydroxyestradiol
definition: A 3-hydroxy steroid that is 17beta-estradiol substituted by a beta-hydroxy group at position 16.

name: beta-D-GlcpNAc-(1->4)-[alpha-Neup5Ac-(2->3)-beta-D-Galp-(1->4)-beta-D-GlcpNAc-(1->2)-alpha-D-Manp-(1->3)]-[alpha-Neup5Ac-(2->3)-beta-DGalp-(1->4)-beta-D-GlcpNAc-(1->2)-alpha-D-Manp-(1->6)]-beta-D-Manp-(1->4)-beta-D-GlcpNAc-(1->4)-beta-D-GlcpNAc
definition: A branched amino oligosaccharide comprising a linear trisaccharide of beta-D-mannose and two N-acetyl-beta-D-glucosamine residues all linked in sequence (1->4), to the mannosyl residue of which is (1->4)-linked an Nacetyl-beta-D-glucosaminyl residue, together with two N-acetyl-alpha-neuraminyl-(2->3)-beta-D-galactosyl-(1->4)-N-acetyl-beta-D-glucosaminyl-(1->2)-alpha-D-mannosyl tetrasaccharide units linked (1->3) and (1->6).

name: methanediimine
definition: A carbodiimide in which both nitrogens are unsubstituted.

A branched amino oligosaccharide that is a pentasaccharide comprising a linear trisaccharide of beta-D-mannose and two N-acetyl-beta-D-glucosamine residues all linked in sequence (1->4), to the mannosyl residue of which are linked an N-acetyl-beta-D-glucosaminyl residue [via a (1->4) linkage], an N-acetyl-alpha-neuraminyl-(2->3)-beta-D-galactosyl-(1->4)-N-acetyl-beta-D-glucosaminyl-(1->4)-alpha-D-mannosyl(1->6) linear  tetrasaccharide chain [linked (1->6)], and an N-acetyl-alpha-neuraminyl-(2->3)-beta-D-galactosyl-(1->4)-N-acetyl-beta-D-glucosaminyl-(1->4)-[N-acetyl-alpha-neuraminyl-(2->3)-beta-D-galactosyl-(1->4)-N-acetyl-beta-D-glucosaminyl-(1->2)]-alpha-D-mannosyl branched heptasaccharide unit [linked (1->3)].

name: fast blue salt B
definition: An organic chloride salt composed of 3,3'-dimethoxy[1,1'-biphenyl]-4,4'-bis(diazonium), zinc and chloride ions in a ratio of 1:1:4. Used for detection of marijuana metabolites in urine.

name: 16beta-hydroxyestrone
definition: A 3-hydroxy steroid that is estrone substituted by a beta-hydroxy group at position 16.

name: azure C
definition: An organic chloride salt having 3-amino-7-(methylamino)phenothiazin-5-ium as the counterion.

name: victoria blue 4R
definition: An iminium salt composed of 4-([4-(dimethylamino)phenyl]{4-[methyl(phenyl)amino]naphthalen-1-yl}methylidene)-N,N-dimethylcyclohexa-2,5-dien-1-iminium and chloride ions in a 1:1 ratio. It binds to nucleic acids and can be used in standardised staining techniques suitable for automated cell-pattern recognition.

name: victoria blue B(1+)
definition: An iminium ion that forms the cationic portion of the histological dye 'victoria blue B'.

name: (25R)-3beta,26-dihydroxycholest-5-en-7-one
definition: An oxysterol that is 7-ketocholesterol which is substituted by a hydroxy group at position 26 and has R-configuration at position 25.

name: basic brown 1
definition: A bis(azo) compound that is 1,1'-(1,3-phenylene)bis(diazene) in which both azene hydrogens are replaced by 2,4-diaminophenyl groups. A metachromatic dye which stains acid mucins yellow. It is also a constituent of Papanicolaou's EA solutions, used for cervical, and other smears. Its dihydrochloride salt is also a biological dye known as Bismark brown Y.

name: pararosaniline
definition: A hydrochloride that is the monohydrochloride of 4,4'-[(4-iminocyclohexa-2,5-dien-1-ylidene)methanediyl]dianiline. One of the major constituents of Basic fuchsin, together with rosanilin, magenta II and new fuchsin.

name: magenta II
definition: A hydrochloride that is the monohydrochloride of 4-[(4-aminophenyl)(4-iminocyclohexa-2,5-dien-1-ylidene)methyl]-2-methylaniline. One of the minor constituents of Basic fuchsin, together with pararosanilin, rosanilin and new fuchsin.

name: magenta II free base
definition: An imine that is 4-methylidenecyclohexa-2,5-dien-1-imine in which both the hydrogens of the methylidene group are replaced by 4-amino-3-methylphenyl groups. The hydrochloride salt is the histological dye 'magenta II'.

name: (2E)-hex-2-en-1-yl propanoate
definition: The propanoate ester of (2E)-hex-2-en-1-ol.

name: isobutyl butyrate
definition: A butyrate ester resulting from the formal condensation of butanoic acid with isobutanol. It is used as a food flavour ingredient for apple, banana, peach and pinapple flavours in ice cream and confectionery.

name: pentyl butyrate
definition: The butyrate ester of pentan-1-ol.

name: ethyl 3-hydroxybutyrate
definition: The fatty acid ethyl ester of  3-hydroxybutyric acid.

name: (3S)-3-hydroxyoleoyl-CoA(4-)
definition: An (S)-3-hydroxyacyl-CoA(4-) obtained by deprotonation of the phosphate and diphosphate OH groups of (3S)-3-hydroxyoleoyl-CoA; major species at pH 7.3.

name: (24R,25R)-3alpha,7alpha,24-trihydroxy-5beta-cholestan-26-oyl-CoA(4-)
definition: An acyl-CoA(4-) arising from deprotonation of phosphate and diphosphate OH groups of (24R,25R)-3alpha,7alpha,24-trihydroxy-5beta-cholestan-26-oyl-CoA; major species at pH 7.3.

name: dihydroxy mycolic acid
definition: A 3-hydroxy fatty acid produced by Mycobacterium tuberculosis.

name: (-)-dihydroedulan II
definition: An organic heterobicyclic compound that is 3,4,4a,5,6,8a-hexahydro-2H-1-benzopyran substituted by methyl groups at positions  2, 5, 5 and 8a respectively.

name: (7Z)-3-oxohexadecenoyl-CoA(4-)
definition: A 3-oxo-fatty acyl CoA(4-) obtained by deprotonation of phosphate and diphosphate OH groups of (7Z)-3-oxohexadecenoyl-CoA; major species at pH 7.3.

name: (S)-prasugrel
definition: An 5-[2-cyclopropyl-1-(2-fluorophenyl)-2-oxoethyl]-4,5,6,7-tetrahydrothieno[3,2-c]pyridin-2-yl acetate that is the (S)-enantiomer of prasugrel (the racemate is a cardiovascular drug).

name: (S)-prasugrel(1+)
definition: An organic cation resulting from the protonation of the amino group of (S)-prasugrel.

name: 12alpha-hydroxy-3-oxo-5beta-cholan-24-oate
definition: A bile acid anion that is the conjugate base of 12alpha-hydroxy-3-oxo-5beta-cholan-24-oic acid, obtained by deprotonation of the carboxy group; major species at pH 7.3.

name: 7alpha,12alpha-dihydroxy-3-oxo-5beta-cholan-24-oate
definition: A bile acid anion that is the conjugate base of 7alpha,12alpha-dihydroxy-3-oxo-5beta-cholan-24-oic acid, obtained by deprotonation of the carboxy group; major species at pH 7.3.

name: (R)-warfarin sodium
definition: An organic sodium salt having 2-oxo-3-[(1R)-3-oxo-1-phenylbutyl]-2H-1-benzopyran-4-olate as the counterion (the racemate is warfarin sodium, an anticoagulant drug and rodenticide).

name: (S)-warfarin sodium
definition: An organic sodium salt having 2-oxo-3-[(1S)-3-oxo-1-phenylbutyl]-2H-1-benzopyran-4-olate as the counterion (the racemate is warfarin sodium, an anticoagulant drug and rodenticide).

name: prenyl-FMN
definition: A flavin mononucleotide resulting from the formal dehydrogenation of prenyl-FMNH2. It is an essential cofactor for the decarboxylase enzymes UbiD (Fdc1).

name: alpha-L-Fucp-(1->2)-beta-D-Galp-(1->4)-[alpha-L-Fucp-(1->3)]-beta-D-GlcpNAc-(1->2)-alpha-D-Manp-(1->6)-{alpha-L-Fucp-(1->2)-beta-D-Galp-(1->4)-[alpha-L-Fucp-(1->3)]-beta-D-GlcpNAc-(1->2)-alpha-D-Manp-(1->3)}-beta-D-Manp-(1->4)-beta-D-GlcpNAc-(1->4)-[alpha-L-Fucp-(1->6)]-beta-D-GlcpNAc
definition: A branched amino oligosaccharide that is a tetradecasaccharide derivative comprising a linear trisaccharide of beta-D-mannose and two N-acetyl-beta-D-glucosamine residues all linked in sequence (1->4), to the N-acetyl-beta-D-glucosamine residue at the reduciong end is linked (1->6) an L-fucosyl residue, and to the beta-D-mannose residue of which are linked N-acetyl-beta-D-glucosaminyl-(1->2)-[alpha-L-fucosyl-(1->3)]-[alpha-L-fucosyl-(1->2)-beta-D-galactosyl-(1->4)]-alpha-D-mannosyl and alpha-L-fucosyl-(1->3)-[alpha-L-fucosyl-(1->2)-beta-D-galactosyl-(1->4)]-N-acetyl-beta-D-glucosaminyl-(1->2)-alpha-D-mannosyl branched pentasaccharide units via (1->6) and (1->3) linkages respectively.

name: D-threonolactone
definition: A butan-4-olide that is dihydrofuran-2-one substituted at C-3 and C-4 by hydroxy groups (the 3S,4R-diastereomer).

name: 16alpha-hydroxydehydroepiandrosterone 3-sulfate
definition: An androstanoid that is dehydroepiandrosterone 3-sulfate substituted by a hydroxy group at the 16alpha-position.

name: (3S)-3-hydroxyicosanoyl-CoA
definition: A 3-hydroxyicosanoyl-CoA that results from the formal condensation of the thiol group of coenzyme A with the carboxy group of (3S)-hydroxyicosanoic acid.

name: alpha-L-Fucp-(1->2)-[alpha-D-Galp-(1->3)]-beta-D-Galp-(1->4)-beta-D-GlcpNAc-(1->6)-alpha-D-GalpNAc
definition: A branched amino pentasaccharide comprising a linear tetrasaccharide chain of alpha-D-galactose, beta-D-galactose, N-acetyl-beta-D-glucosamine and N-acetyl-alpha-D-galactosamine residues linked sequentially (1->3), (1->4) and (1->6), to the beta-D-galactose residue of which is also linked (1->2) an alpha-L-fucose residue.

name: alpha-L-Fucp-(1->2)-beta-D-Galp-(1->3)-beta-D-GlcpNAc-(1->3)-[alpha-L-Fucp-(1->2)-beta-D-Galp-(1->3)-beta-D-GlcpNAc-(1->6)]-alpha-D-GalpNAc
definition: An amino heptasaccharide in which two alpha-L-fucosyl-(1->2)-beta-D-galactosyl-(1->3)-N-acetyl-beta-D-glucosaminyl chains are linked (1->3) and (1->6) to alpha-D-galactose.

name: beta-D-GlcpNAc-(1->6)-[beta-D-GlcpNAc-(1->2)]-alpha-D-Manp-(1->6)-[beta-D-GlcpNAc-(1->4)]-{beta-D-GlcNAc-(1->4)-[beta-D-GlcpNAc-(1->2)]alpha-D-Manp-(1->3)}-beta-D-Manp-(1->4)-beta-D-GlcpNAc-(1->4)-[alpha-L-Fucp-(1->6)]-D-GlcpNAc
definition: A branched amino oligosaccharide that is an undecasaccharide derivative consisting of a linear trisaccharide of beta-D-mannose, N-acetyl-beta-D-glucosamine and N-acetyl-D-glucosamine residues all linked in sequence (1->4), to the mannosyl residue of which are linked an N-acetyl-beta-D-glucosaminyl residue [via a (1->4) linkage], an N-acetyl-beta-D-glucosaminyl-(1->2)-[N-acetyl-beta-D-glucosaminyl-(1->4)]-alpha-D-mannosyl branched trisaccharide unit [linked (1->3)], and an N-acetyl-beta-D-glucosaminyl-(1->2)-[N-acetyl-beta-D-glucosaminyl-(1->6)]-alpha-D-mannosyl branched trisaccharide unit [linked (1->6)], while to the N-acetyl-D-glucosamine residue at the reducing end is linked (1->6) an alpha-L-fucose residue.

name: 17-phenyl-18,19,20-trinor-prostaglandin E2
definition: A prostanoid that is 18,19,20-trinor-prostaglandin E2 in which one of the terminal methyl hydrogens has been replaced by a phenyl group.

name: 17-phenyl-18,19,20-trinor-prostaglandin D2
definition: A prostanoid that is 18,19,20-trinor-prostaglandin D2 in which one of the terminal methyl hydrogens has been replaced by a phenyl group.

name: 1-methyl-N,N-bis(trimethylsilyl)-5-[(trimethylsilyl)oxy]imidazol-2-amine
definition: A member of the class of imidazoles that is 1-methylimidazole substituted by bis(trimethylsilyl)amino and trimethylsilyl groups at positions 2 and 5 respectively.

name: O-[S-(2E,7Z-hexacosadienoylpantetheine)-4'-phosphoryl]-L-serine(1-) residue
definition: An O-[S-(2E)-2-enoylpantetheine-4'-phosphoryl]-L-serine(1-) residue in which the S-acyl group is specified as (2E,5Z)-hexacosadienoyl.

name: O-{S-[(3R,11Z)-3-hydroxytriacontenoylpantetheine]-4'-phosphoryl}-L-serine(1-) residue
definition: An O-[S-(3R)-3-hydroxyacylpantetheine-4'-phosphoryl]serine(1-) residue in which the S-acyl group is specified as (3R,11Z)-3-hydroxytriacontenoyl.

name: O-[S-(2E,11Z-triacontadienoylpantetheine)-4'-phosphoryl]-L-serine(1-) residue
definition: An O-[S-(2E)-2-enoylpantetheine-4'-phosphoryl]-L-serine(1-) residue in which the S-acyl group is specified as (2E,11Z)-triacontadienoyl.

name: O-[S-(3Z,15Z-tetratriacontadienoylpantetheine)-4'-phosphoryl]-L-serine(1-) residue
definition: An O-(S-acylpantetheine-4'-phosphoryl)serine(1-) residue in which the S-acyl group is specified as (3Z,15Z)-tetratriacontadienoyl.

name: O-[S-(15Z-tetratriacontenoylpantetheine)-4'-phosphoryl]-L-serine(1-) residue
definition: An O-(S-acylpantetheine-4'-phosphoryl)serine(1-) residue in which the S-acyl group is specified as (15Z)-tetratriacontenoyl.

name: O-[S-(2E,5Z,17Z-hexatriacontatrienoylpantetheine)-4'-phosphoryl]-L-serine(1-) residue
definition: An O-[S-(2E)-2-enoylpantetheine-4'-phosphoryl]-L-serine(1-) residue in which the S-acyl group is specified as (2E,5Z,17Z)-hexatriacontatrienoyl.

name: O-[S-(5Z,17Z-hexatriacontadienoylpantetheine)-4'-phosphoryl]-L-serine(1-) residue
definition: An O-(S-acylpantetheine-4'-phosphoryl)serine(1-) residue in which the S-acyl group is specified as (5Z,17Z)-hexatriacontadienoyl.

name: O-{S-[(7Z,19Z)-3-oxooctatriacontadienoylpantetheine]-4'-phosphoryl}-L-serine(1-) residue
definition: An O-(S-3-oxoacylpantetheine-4'-phosphoryl)-L-serine(1-) residue in which the S-acyl group is specified as (7Z,19Z)-3-oxooctatriacontadienoyl.

name: O-{S-[(3R,19Z,31Z)-3-hydroxypentacontadienoylpantetheine]-4'-phosphoryl}-L-serine(1-) residue
definition: An O-[S-(3R)-3-hydroxyacylpantetheine-4'-phosphoryl]serine(1-) residue in which the S-acyl group is specified as (3R,19Z,31Z)-3-hydroxypentacontadienoyl.

name: O-{S-[(3R,17Z)-3-hydroxyhexatriacontenoylpantetheine]-4'-phosphoryl}-L-serine(1-) residue
definition: An O-[S-(3R)-3-hydroxyacylpantetheine-4'-phosphoryl]serine(1-) residue in which the S-acyl group is specified as (3R,17Z)-3-hydroxyhexatriacontenoyl.

name: O-[S-(2E,17Z-hexatriacontadienoylpantetheine)-4'-phosphoryl]-L-serine(1-) residue
definition: An O-[S-(2E)-2-enoylpantetheine-4'-phosphoryl]-L-serine(1-) residue in which the S-acyl group is specified as (2E,17Z)-hexatriacontadienoyl.

name: O-{S-[(3R,5Z,21Z)-3-hydroxytetracontadienoylpantetheine]-4'-phosphoryl}-L-serine(1-) residue
definition: An O-[S-(3R)-3-hydroxyacylpantetheine-4'-phosphoryl]serine(1-) residue in which the S-acyl group is specified as (3R,5Z,21Z)-3-hydroxytetracontadienoyl.

name: O-[S-(2E,5Z,21Z-tetracontatrienoylpantetheine)-4'-phosphoryl]-L-serine(1-) residue
definition: An O-[S-(2E)-2-enoylpantetheine-4'-phosphoryl]-L-serine(1-) residue in which the S-acyl group is specified as (2E,5Z,21Z)-tetracontatrienoyl.

name: O-{S-[(3R,7Z,23Z)-3-hydroxydotetracontadienoylpantetheine]-4'-phosphoryl}-L-serine(1-) residue
definition: An O-[S-(3R)-3-hydroxyacylpantetheine-4'-phosphoryl]serine(1-) residue in which the S-acyl group is specified as (3R,7Z,23Z)-3-hydroxydotetracontadienoyl.

name: O-[S-(7Z,23Z-dotetracontadienoylpantetheine)-4'-phosphoryl]-L-serine(1-) residue
definition: An O-(S-acylpantetheine-4'-phosphoryl)serine(1-) residue in which the S-acyl group is specified as (7Z,23Z)-dotetracontadienoyl.

name: O-{S-[(9Z,25Z)-3-oxotetratetracontadienoylpantetheine]-4'-phosphoryl}-L-serine(1-) residue
definition: An O-(S-3-oxoacylpantetheine-4'-phosphoryl)-L-serine(1-) residue in which the S-acyl group is specified as (9Z,25Z)-3-oxotetratetracontadienoyl.

name: p-tolyl beta-D-glucuronide
definition: A glucosiduronic acid that is beta-D-glucuronic acid in which the anomeric hydroxyl hydrogen is replaced by a p-tolyl group.

name: (2R)-2-[(1R)-1-hydroxy-12-{2-[14-(2-icosylcyclopropyl)tetradecyl]cyclopropyl}dodecyl]hexacosanoate
definition: A C78 alpha-mycolate having a C52 meromycolic chain with two cis cyclopropyl functions and a saturated C26 alpha-branch. It is produced by Mycobacterium tuberculosis H37Ra.

name: tetradecamethylcycloheptasiloxane
definition: A macrocyclic organosiloxane composed from seven units of dimethylsiloxane.

name: (2R)-2-[(1R)-1-hydroxy-14-{2-[14-(2-icosylcyclopropyl)tetradecyl]cyclopropyl}tetradecyl]hexacosanoate
definition: A C80 alpha-mycolate having a C54 meromycolic chain with two cis cyclopropyl functions and a saturated C26 alpha-branch. It is produced by Mycobacterium tuberculosis H37Ra.

name: alpha-Neu5Ac-(2->8)-alpha-Neu5Ac-(2->3)-beta-Gal-(1->3)-beta-GalNAc-(1->4)-beta-Gal-(1->4)-beta-Glc-(1<->1')-Cer
definition: A sialotetraosylceramide consisting of a linear hexasaccharide made up from two sialyl residues, two galactose residues, one N-acetylgalactosamine residue and a glucose residue at the reducing end attached to the ceramide portion via a beta-linkage.

name: (2R)-2-[(1R)-14-{2-[(15Z)-hexatriacont-15-en-1-yl]cyclopropyl}-1-hydroxytetradecyl]hexacosanoate
definition: A C79 alpha-mycolate  having a saturated C26 alpha-branch and a C53 meromycolic chain with a distal cis-double bond and a proximal cis-cyclopropyl function. It is produced by Mycobacterium tuberculosis H37Ra.

name: beta-Gal-(1->3)-beta-GalNAc-(1->4)-[alpha-Neu5Ac-(2->8)-alpha-Neu5Ac-(2->8)-alpha-Neu5Ac-(2->3)]-beta-Gal-(1->4)-beta-Glc-(1<->1')-Cer
definition: A sialotetraosylceramide consisting of a branched heptasaccharide made up from three sialyl residues, two galactose residues, one N-acetylglucosamine residue and a glucose residue at the reducing end attached to the ceramide portion via a beta-linkage.

name: alpha-L-Fucp-(1->4)-[beta-D-Galp-(1->3)]-beta-D-GlcpNAc-(1->2)-alpha-D-Manp
definition: A branched amino tetrasaccharide consisting of a linear trisaccharide derivative of alpha-L-fucose, N-acetyl-beta-D-glucosamine and (at the reducing end) alpha-D-mannose residues linked sequentially (1->4) and (1->2), to the N-acetyl-beta-D-glucosamine residue of which is also linked (1->3) a beta-D-galactose residue.

name: 3-(m-hydroxyphenyl)propanoyl-CoA
definition: An acyl-CoA that results from the formal condensation of the thiol group of coenzyme A with the carboxy group of 3-(3-hydroxyphenyl)propanoic acid.

name: 3-phosphoglycerate(2-)
definition: A phosphoglycerate obtained by deprotonation of the carboxy group and one of the phosphate OH groups of 3-phosphoglyceric acid.

name: (7Z)-hexadecenoyl-CoA
definition: A hexadecenoyl-CoA that results from the formal condensation of the thiol group of coenzyme A with the carboxy group of (7Z)-hexadecenoic acid.

name: 3,7-diamino-5-phenylphenazin-5-ium
definition: An organic cation that is 5-phenylphenothiazin-5-ium substituted by amino groups at positions 3 and 7 as well as a nitro group at position 4. The chloride salt is the histological dye 'safranin O'.

name: beta-D-Galp-(1->4)-beta-D-GlcpNAc-(1->3)-beta-D-Galp-(1->4)-beta-D-GlcpNAc-(1->2)-alpha-D-Manp-(1->3)-[beta-D-Galp-(1->4)-beta-D-GlcpNAc-(1->3)-beta-D-Galp-(1->4)-beta-D-GlcpNAc-(1->2)-alpha-D-Manp-(1->6)]-beta-D-Manp-(1->4)-beta-D-GlcpNAc-(1->4)-beta-D-GlcpNAc
definition: A branched amino oligosaccharide that is a tridecasaccharide derivative consisting of a linear trisaccharide of beta-D-mannose and two N-acetyl-beta-D-glucosamine residues (one of which is at the reducing end) all linked in sequence (1->4), to the mannosyl residue of which are linked (1->3) and (1->6) two beta-D-galactosyl-(1->4)-N-acetyl-beta-D-glucosaminyl-(1->3)-beta-D-galactosyl-(1->4)-N-acetyl-beta-D-glucosaminyl-(1->2)-alpha-D-mannosyl linear pentasaccharide units.

name: cylindrospermopsin zwitterion
definition: A zwitterion resulting from the transfer of a proton from the sulfooxy group to one of the nitrogens of the guanidine group of cylindrospermopsin.

name: cylindrospermopsins
definition: A class of organic heterotricyclic compounds that consists of cylindrospermopsin and its structural analogues.

name: cylindrospermopsin
definition: A triazaacenaphthylene that is 2,2a,3,4,5,5a,6,7-octahydro-1H-1,8,8b-triazaacenaphthylene which is substituted at positions 3, 4, and 7 by methyl, sulfooxy, and (2,6-dioxo-1,2,3,6-tetrahydropyrimidin-4-yl)(hydroxy)methyl groups, respectively (the 2aS,3R,4S,5aS,7R stereoisomer in which the carbon bearing the hydroxy group has R configuration). It is a cyanotoxin produced by several species of freshwater cyanobacteria, such as Aphanizomenon ovalisporum.

name: prenyl phosphate(2-)
definition: An organophosphate oxoanion obtained by deprotonation of the phosphate OH groups of prenyl phosphate; major species at pH 7.3.

name: (3E)-tetradecenoyl-CoA
definition: An unsaturated fatty acyl-CoA that results from the formal condensation of the thiol group of coenzyme A with the carboxy group of (3E)-tetradecenoic acid.

name: alpha-Neu5Ac-(2->3)-beta-D-Gal-(1->3)-[alpha-L-Fuc-(1->4)]-beta-D-GlcNAc-(1->3)-beta-D-Gal-(1->4)-beta-D-Glc-(1<->1')-Cer(1-)
definition: An anionic ganglioside obtained by deprotonation of the neuraminosyl carboxy group of alpha-Neu5Ac-(2->3)-beta-D-Gal-(1->3)-[alpha-L-Fuc-(1->4)]-beta-D-GlcNAc-(1->3)-beta-D-Gal-(1->4)-beta-D-Glc-(1<->1')-Cer; major species at pH 7.3.

name: (2R)-2-[(1R)-1-hydroxy-18-{2-[10-(2-octadecylcyclopropyl)decyl]cyclopropyl}octadecyl]hexacosanoic acid
definition: A C78 mycolic acid having a C52 meromycolic chain with two cis cyclopropyl functions and a saturated C26 alpha-branch. It is produced by Mycobacterium tuberculosis H37Ra.

name: (2R)-2-[(1R)-1-hydroxy-16-{2-[10-(2-octadecylcyclopropyl)decyl]cyclopropyl}hexadecyl]hexacosanoic acid
definition: A C76 mycolic acid having a C50 meromycolic chain and a saturated C26 alpha-branch. It is produced by Mycobacterium tuberculosis H37Ra.

name: (2R)-2-[(1R)-1-hydroxy-20-{2-[10-(2-octadecylcyclopropyl)decyl]cyclopropyl}icosyl]tetracosanoic acid
definition: A C78 mycolic acid having a C54 meromycolic chain with two cis cyclopropyl functions and a saturated C24 alpha-branch. It is produced by Mycobacterium tuberculosis H37Ra.

name: (2R)-2-[(1R)-1-hydroxy-20-{2-[10-(2-octadecylcyclopropyl)decyl]cyclopropyl}icosyl]hexacosanoic acid
definition: A C80 mycolic acid having a C54 meromycolic chain with two cis cyclopropyl functions and a saturated C26 alpha-branch. It is produced by Mycobacterium tuberculosis H37Ra.

name: (2R)-2-[(1R)-1-hydroxy-18-{2-[10-(2-icosylcyclopropyl)decyl]cyclopropyl}octadecyl]hexacosanoic acid
definition: A C80 mycolic acid having a C54 meromycolic chain with two cis cyclopropyl functions and a saturated C26 alpha-branch. It is produced by Mycobacterium tuberculosis H37Ra.

name: alpha-L-Fucp-(1->2)-[alpha-D-Galp-(1->3)]-beta-D-Galp-(1->3)-alpha-D-GalpNAc-yl group
definition: A branched tetrasaccharide glucosaminyl group consisting of alpha-L-fucosyl, beta-D-galactosyl and N-acetyl-alpha-D-D-galactosaminyl residues linked sequentially (1->2) and (1->3), to the beta-D-galactosyl residue of which is also linked (1->3) an alpha-D-galactosyl residue. Blood group type-III B determinant.

name: D-ribitol 1-phosphate
definition: A ribitol phosphate that is D-ribitol carrying a single monophosphate substituent at position 1.

name: (3,4-dimethoxyphenyl)methyloxidanyl
definition: An organic radical obtained by abstraction of the hydroxy proton from (3,4-dimethoxyphenyl)methanol.

name: 2''-O-succinyl-ADP-D-ribose
definition: A nucleotide-sugar having ADP as the nucleotide fragment and 2-O-succinyl-D-ribofuranos-5-yl as the sugar component.

name: 2''-O-malonyl-ADP-D-ribose
definition: A nucleotide-sugar having ADP as the nucleotide fragment and 2-O-malonyl-D-ribofuranos-5-yl as the sugar component.

name: 2,3-saturated fatty acyl-CoA(4-)
definition: A fatty acyl-CoA(4-) obtained by deprotonation of the phosphate and diphosphate OH groups of any 2,3-saturated fatty acyl-CoA; major species at pH 7.3.

name: (S)-4-hydroxy-1-pyrroline-2-carboxylic acid
definition: A 4-hydroxy-1-pyrroline-2-carboxylic acid in which the 4-hydroxy group has S-configuration.

name: tripropionin
definition: A triglyceride obtained by formal acylation of the three hydroxy groups of glycerol by propionic acid.

name: alpha-D-galactosyl-(1->4)-beta-D-galactosyl-(1->4)-beta-D-glucosyl-(1<->1)-ceramide
definition: A glycotriaosylceramide having alpha-D-galactosyl-(1->4)-beta-D-galactosyl-(1->4)-beta-D-glucosyl component attached to the primary hydroxy function of a ceramide with undefined sphingoid base.

name: diacetin
definition: A diglyceride resulting from the formal condensation of any two of the hydroxy groups of glycerol with the carboxy groups of two molecules of acetic acid (either R1 = H and R2 = Ac, or R1 = Ac and R2 = H).

name: 1,4-naphthoquinone-2-carboxylic acid
definition: A dioxo monocarboxylic acid that is 1,4-naphthoquinone substituted at position 2 by a carboxy group.

name: brilliant green cation
definition: An iminium ion that is the cationic component of the histological dye 'brilliant green'.

name: 2-oxido-5-methylquinone
definition: An organic anion obtained by deprotonation of the hydroxy group of 2-hydroxy-5-methylquinone. It is the major microspecies at pH 7.3 (according to Marvin v 6.2.0.).

name: Sirius red 4B
definition: An organic sodium salt resulting from the formal condensation of Sirius red 4B (acid form) with two equivalents of sodium hydroxide. Used as the plasma stain in some trichrome staining methods.

name: Sirius red 4B (acid form)
definition: A naphthalenesulfonic acid that is 7-amino-4-hydroxy-3-({4-[(4-sulfophenyl)diazenyl]phenyl}diazenyl)naphthalene-2-sulfonic acid in which one of the amino hydrogens is replaced by a benzoyl group. The disodium salt is the histological dye 'Sirius red 4B'.

name: Pontamine sky blue 5B(4-)
definition: An organosulfonate oxoanion obtained by deprotonation of the sulfonic acid groups of Pontamine sky blue 5B (acid form).

name: Chrome fast yellow 8GL
definition: An organic sodium salt resulting from the formal condensation of Chrome fast yellow 8GL (acid form) with two equivalents of sodium hydroxide.

name: Congo corinth
definition: An organic sodium salt resulting from the formal condensation of Congo corinth (acid form) with two equivalents of sodium hydroxide. A histological dye used to stain frozen sections for rapid diagnosis and to demonstrate amuloid.

name: Congo corinth (acid form)
definition: An aminonaphthalenesulfonic acid that is 3,3'-[[1,1'-biphenyl]-4,4'-diylbis(diazene-2,1-diyl)]di(naphthalene-1-sulfonic acid) in which the two hydrogens at the 4-positions on the naphthalene rings are placed by amino and hydroxy groups. The disodium salt is the histological dye 'Congo corinth'.

name: Sirius scarlet GG
definition: An organic sodium salt that is the monosodium salt of 5-[(4-amino-5-methoxy-2-methylphenyl)diazenyl]-2-methoxybenzene-1-sulfonic acid. Occasionally used for the selective staining of amyloid.

name: Sudan black B
definition: A member of the class of perimidines that is 2,2-dimethyl-2,3-dihydro-1H-perimidine carrying a [4-(phenyldiazenyl)naphthalen-1-yl]diazenyl substituent at position 6. A fat-soluble dye predominantly used for demonstrating triglycerides in frozen sections and for staining of protein bound lipids in paraffin sections.

name: TTT-3002
definition: An organic heterooctacyclic compound that is 1H,1'H-2,2'-biindole in which the nitrogens have undergone formal oxidative coupling to positions 2 and 5 of 3-amino-N,2-dimethyloxolane-3-carboxamide (the 2R,3R,5S product), and in which the 3 and 3' positions of the biindole moiety have also undergone formal oxidative coupling to positions 3 and 4 of 1,5-dihydro-2H-pyrrol-2-one.

name: N(5)-methyl-argininium(1+) residue
definition: An alpha-amino-acid residue cation obtained by protonation of the guanidino group of N(5)-methyl-argininium residue.

name: penicilloyl group
definition: Any penicillinyl group formed from a penicillin by  nucleophilic cleavage of the beta-lactam ring.

name: beta-lactam antibiotic allergen
definition: Any beta-lactam antibiotic which causes the onset of an allergic reaction.

name: (2E,6E)-farnesyl monophosphate(2-)
definition: An organophosphate oxoanion that is the dianion obtained by removal of the two protons from the monophosphate group of (2E,6E)-farnesyl monophosphate. Major species at pH 7.3.

name: alpha-Neu5Ac-(2->8)-alpha-Neu5Ac-(2->3)-beta-Gal-(1->3)-beta-GalNAc-(1->4)-[alpha-Neu5Ac-(2->8)-alpha-Neu5Ac-(2->3)]-beta-Gal-(1->4)-beta-Glc-(1<->1')-Cer(d18:1/18:0)(4-)
definition: An anionic ganglioside obtained by deprotonation of the neuraminosyl carboxy groups of ganglioside GQ1b (d18:1/C18:0); major species at pH 7.3.

name: (9Z,12Z,15Z)-octadeca-9,12,15-trien-6-ynoyl-containing glycerolipid
definition: A glycerolipid where one of the acyl groups is specified as (9Z,12Z,15Z)-octadeca-9,12,15-trien-6-ynoyl

name: 6-deoxy-6-sulfo-D-gluconic acid
definition: A carbohydrate sulfonate that is D-gluconic acid in which the hydroxy group at position 6 is replaced by a sulfo group.

name: Sirius red F3B
definition: An organic sodium salt resulting from the formal condensation of Sirius red F3B (acid form) with six equivalents of sodium hydroxide. A polyazo dye used principally in staining methods for collagen and amyloid.

name: ethyl green
definition: An iminium salt composed of [4-([4-(dimethylamino)phenyl]{4-[ethyl(dimethyl)azaniumyl]phenyl}methylidene)cyclohexa-2,5-dien-1-ylidene](dimethyl)ammonium, bromide and chloride ions in a 1:1:1 ratio. A histological dye used to demonstrate nucleic acids by the Unna-Pappenheim stain, in conjunction with Pyronin Y.

name: ethyl green(1+)
definition: An iminium ion that forms the cationic portion of the histological dye 'ethyl green'.

name: 5-hydroxyimidazole-4-carboxamide
definition: A hydroxyimidazole that is 5-hydroxyimidazole in which the hydrogen at position 4 is replaced by an aminocarbonyl group.

name: hydroxyimidazole
definition: Any member of the class of imidazoles in which the imidazole ring is substituted by one or more hydroxy groups.

name: Fast green FCF(2-)
definition: An organosulfonate oxoanion obtained by the removal of three protons from Fast green FCF(1+).

name: Fast green FCF(1+)
definition: An iminium ion that is the free acid form of Fast green FCF.

name: gallein
definition: A xanthene dye that is fluoran carrying four hydroxy substituents at positions 3', 4', 5' and 6'.

name: Gallamin blue
definition: An organic chloride salt composed of 1-carbamoyl-7-(dimethylamino)-3,4-dihydroxyphenoxazin-5-ium and chloride ions in a 1:1 ratio. A histological dye used in solution with an iron alum mordant as a hematoxylin substitute in the H&E stain.

name: lorglumide sodium
definition: A racemate comprising equal amounts of (R)- and (S)-lorglumide sodium.

name: (S)-lorglumide sodium
definition: An organic sodium salt obtained by formal condensation of N(2)-(3,4-dichlorobenzoyl)-N,N-dipentyl-L-alpha-glutamine with one equivalent of sodium hydroxide. The racemate is lorglumide sodium, a CCK antagonist.

name: (R)-lorglumide sodium
definition: An organic sodium salt obtained by formal condensation of N(2)-(3,4-dichlorobenzoyl)-N,N-dipentyl-D-alpha-glutamine with one equivalent of sodium hydroxide. The racemate is lorglumide sodium, a CCK antagonist.

name: lorglumide
definition: A racemate comprising equal amounts of (R)- and (S)-lorglumide.

name: 4-nitrophenols
