definition: An anionic ganglioside that is the conjugate base of alpha-Neu5Ac-(2->3)-[beta-D-Gal-(1->3)-beta-D-GalNAc-(1->4)]-beta-D-Gal-(1->4)-beta-D-Glc-(1<->1')-Cer(d20:1) arising from deprotonation of the neuraminosyl carboxy group; major species at pH 7.3.

name: alpha-Neu5Ac-(2->3)-beta-D-Gal-(1->3)-beta-D-GalNAc-(1->4)-[alpha-Neu5Ac-(2->3)]-beta-D-Gal-(1->4)-beta-D-Glc-(1<->1')-Cer(d20:1)(2-)
definition: An anionic ganglioside that is the conjugate base of alpha-Neu5Ac-(2->3)-beta-D-Gal-(1->3)-beta-D-GalNAc-(1->4)-[alpha-Neu5Ac-(2->3)]-beta-D-Gal-(1->4)-beta-D-Glc-(1<->1')-Cer(d20:1) arising from deprotonation of the neuraminosyl carboxy groups; major species at pH 7.3.

name: lysophosphatidylethanolamine 16:0
definition: A lysophosphatidylethanolamine in which the acyl group has a fully saturated C16 chain and is attached to the glycero moiety at either position 1 or 2.

name: 1,2-dioctanoyl-3-beta-D-galactosyl-sn-glycerol
definition: A 1,2-diacyl-3-beta-D-galactosyl-sn-glycerol in which the acyl groups at positions 1 and 2 are specified as octanoyl.

name: lysophosphatidylglycerol
definition: A glycerophosphoglycerol resulting from partial hydrolysis of a phosphatidylglycerol, which removes one of the fatty acid groups. The structure is depicted in the image where R1 = acyl, R2 = H or where R1 = H, R2 = acyl.

name: lysophosphatidylglycerol 14:0
definition: A lysophosphatidylglycerol in which the acyl group has a fully saturated C14 chain and is attached to the glycero moiety at either position 1 or 2.

name: lysophosphatidylinositol 18:1
definition: A lysophosphatidyl-1D-myo-inositol in which the remaining acyl group (position not specified) contains 18 carbons and 1 double bond.

name: 3-[alpha-D-galactosyl-(1->6)-beta-D-galactosyl]-1,2-dioctoanoyl-sn-glycerol
definition: A glycolipid that consists of 1,2-dioctanoyl-sn-glycerol having an alpha-D-galactosyl-(1->6)-beta-D-galactosyl residue attached at position 3.

name: PA(18:0/22:4)
definition: A phosphatidic acid in which one acyl group has 18 carbons and is fully saturated while the other has 22 carbons and 4 double bonds.

name: 1-hexadecanoyl-2-heptadecanoyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphocholine
definition: A 1,2-diacyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphocholine where the acyl groups at positions 1 and 2 are hexadecanoyl and heptadecanoyl respectively.

name: phosphatidylcholine (18:0/20:2)
definition: A 1,2-diacyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphocholine in which one acyl group has 18 carbons and is fully saturated while the other has 20 carbons and 2 double bonds.

name: alpha-Neu5Ac-(2->3)-beta-D-Gal-(1->4)-beta-D-Glc-(1<->1')-Cer(d20:1)(1-)
definition: An anionic ganglioside that is the conjugate base of alpha-Neu5Ac-(2->3)-beta-D-Gal-(1->4)-beta-D-Glc-(1<->1')-Cer(d20:1) arising from deprotonation of the neuraminosyl carboxy group; major species at pH 7.3.

name: phosphatidylcholine (18:0/22:5)
definition: A 1,2-diacyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphocholine in which one acyl group has 18 carbons and is fully saturated while the other has 22 carbons and 5 double bonds.

name: 3-[alpha-D-galactosyl-(1->6)-beta-D-galactosyl]-1,2-bis(long-chain acyl)-sn-glycerol
definition: A glycolipid that consists of an alpha-D-galactosyl-(1->6)-beta-D-galactosyl residue attached at position 3 of a 1,2-diacyl-sn-glycerol moiety in which both acyl groups have a chain length of C12 or greater.

name: phosphatidylethanolamine (16:1/18:1)
definition: A phosphatidylethanolamine in which one acyl group has 16 carbons and 1 double bond while the other has 18 carbons and 1 double bond.

name: alpha-Neu5Ac-(2->3)-beta-D-Gal-(1->4)-beta-D-Glc-(1<->1')-Cer(d16:1)(1-)
definition: An anionic ganglioside that is the conjugate base of alpha-Neu5Ac-(2->3)-beta-D-Gal-(1->4)-beta-D-Glc-(1<->1')-Cer(d16:1) arising from deprotonation of the neuraminosyl carboxy group; major species at pH 7.3.

name: phosphatidylethanolamine (16:1/20:4)
definition: A phosphatidylethanolamine in which one acyl group has 16 carbons and 1 double bond while the other has 20 carbons and 4 double bonds.

name: phosphatidylethanolamine (18:0/20:2)
definition: A phosphatidylethanolamine in which one acyl group has 18 carbons and is fully saturated while the other has 20 carbons and 2 double bonds.

name: phosphatidylethanolamine (18:0/22:5)
definition: A phosphatidylethanolamine in which one acyl group has 18 carbons and is fully saturated while the other has 22 carbons and 5 double bonds.

name: 3-[alpha-D-galactosyl-(1->6)-beta-D-galactosyl]-2-mono(long-chain acyl)-sn-glycerol
definition: A glycolipid that consists of an alpha-D-galactosyl-(1->6)-beta-D-galactosyl residue attached at position 3 of a 2-monoacyl-sn-glycerol moiety in which the acyl group has a chain length of C12 or greater.

name: phosphatidylethanolamine (18:0/22:6)
definition: A phosphatidylethanolamine in which one acyl group has 18 carbons and is fully saturated while the other has 22 carbons and 6 double bonds.

name: beta-D-GalNAc-(1->4)-[alpha-Neu5Ac-(2->3)]-beta-D-Gal-(1->4)-beta-D-Glc-(1<->1)-Cer(d20:1)(1-)
definition: An anionic ganglioside that is the conjugate base of beta-D-GalNAc-(1->4)-[alpha-Neu5Ac-(2->3)]-beta-D-Gal-(1->4)-beta-D-Glc-(1<->1)-Cer(d20:1) arising from deprotonation of the neuraminosyl carboxy group; major species at pH 7.3.

name: phosphatidylethanolamine (18:1/22:4)
definition: A phosphatidylethanolamine in which one acyl group has 18 carbons and 1 double bond while the other has 22 carbons and 4 double bonds.

name: L-isoleucine 2-naphthylamide
definition: An L-isoleucine derivative that is the amide obtained by formal condensation of the carboxy group of L-isoleucine with the amino group of 2-naphthylamine.

name: 1-(1Z-hexadecenyl)-2-(8Z,11Z,14Z-icosatrienoyl)-sn-glycero-3-phosphoethanolamine
definition: A 1-(alk-1-enyl)-2-acyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphoethanolamine in which the alkyl and the acyl groups at positions 1 and 2 are specified as (1Z)-hexadecenyl and (8Z,11Z,14Z)-icosatrienoyl respectively.

name: 3-(beta-D-galactosyl)-2-mono(long-chain acyl)-sn-glycerol
definition: A galactoglycerolipid that consists of a beta-D-galactosyl residue attached at position 3 of a 2-monoacyl-sn-glycerol moiety in which the acyl group has a chain length of C12 or greater.

name: L-leucine 2-naphthylamide
definition: An L-leucine derivative that is the amide obtained by formal condensation of the carboxy group of L-leucine with the amino group of 2-naphthylamine.

name: 3-(beta-D-galactosyl)-1,2-bis(long-chain acyl)-sn-glycerol
definition: A beta-D-galactopyranosyl diglyceride in which both acyl groups have a chain length of C12 or greater.

name: L-lysine 2-naphthylamide
definition: An L-lysine derivative that is the amide obtained by formal condensation of the carboxy group of L-lysine with the amino group of 2-naphthylamine.

name: 1-(1Z-hexadecenyl)-2-(4Z,7Z,10Z,13Z,16Z,19Z-docosahexaenoyl)-sn-glycero-3-phosphoethanolamine
definition: A 1-(alk-1-enyl)-2-acyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphoethanolamine in which the alkyl and the acyl groups at positions 1 and 2 are specified as (1Z)-hexadecenyl and (4Z,7Z,10Z,13Z,16Z,19Z)-docosahexaenoyl respectively.

name: alpha-Neup5Ac-(2->6)-beta-D-Galp-(1->4)-beta-D-GlcpNAc-(1->3)-beta-D-Galp-(1->4)-beta-D-GlcpNAc-(1->6)-[alpha-Neup5Ac-(2->6)-beta-D-Galp-(1->4)-beta-D-GlcpNAc-(1->3)-beta-D-Galp-(1->4)-beta-D-GlcpNAc-(1->3)]-alpha-D-GalpNAc
definition: A branched amino oligosaccharide that is an undecasaccharide derivative in which two N-acetyl-alpha-neuraminyl-(2->6)-beta-D-galactosyl-(1->4)-N-acetyl-beta-D-glucosaminyl-(1->3)-beta-D-galactosyl-(1->4)-N-acetyl-beta-D-glucosaminyl pentasaccharide chains are linked (1->3) and (1->6) to an N-acetyl-alpha-D-galactosamine residue at the reducing end.

name: 2-octanoyl-3-(beta-D-galactosyl)-sn-glycerol
definition: A 3-(beta-D-galactosyl)monooctanoyl-sn-glycerol in which the octanoyl group is located at position 2.

name: 1-(1Z-octadecenyl)-2-hexadecanoyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphoethanolamine
definition: A 1-(alk-1-enyl)-2-acyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphoethanolamine in which the alkyl and the acyl groups at positions 1 and 2 are specified as (1Z)-octadecenyl and hexadecanoyl respectively.

name: 1-(1Z-octadecenyl)-2-linoleoyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphoethanolamine
definition: A 1-(alk-1-enyl)-2-acyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphoethanolamine in which the alkenyl and acyl groups are specified asas (1Z)-octadecenyl and linoleoyl respectively.

name: 1-(1Z-octadecenyl)-2-(8Z,11Z,14Z-icosatrienoyl)-sn-glycero-3-phosphoethanolamine
definition: A 1-(alk-1-enyl)-2-acyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphoethanolamine in which the alkyl and the acyl groups at positions 1 and 2 are specified as (1Z)-octadecenyl and (8Z,11Z,14Z)-icosatrienoyl respectively.

name: 1-(1Z-octadecenyl)-2-(4Z,7Z,10Z,13Z,16Z-docosapentaenoyl)-sn-glycero-3-phosphoethanolamine
definition: A 1-(alk-1-enyl)-2-acyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphoethanolamine in which the alkyl and the acyl groups at positions 1 and 2 are specified as (1Z)-octadecenyl and (4Z,7Z,10Z,13Z,16Z)-docosapentaenoyl respectively.

name: 1-(1Z,11Z-octadecadienyl)-2-linoleoyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphoethanolamine
definition: A 1-(alk-1-enyl)-2-acyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphoethanolamine in which the alkyl and the acyl groups at positions 1 and 2 are specified as (1Z,11Z)-octadecadienyl and linoleoyl respectively.

name: 1-(1Z,9Z-octadecadienyl)-2-(4Z,7Z,10Z,13Z,16Z,19Z-docosahexaenoyl)-sn-glycero-3-phosphoethanolamine
definition: A 1-(alk-1-enyl)-2-acyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphoethanolamine in which the alkyl and the acyl groups at positions 1 and 2 are specified as (1Z,9Z)-octadecadienyl and (4Z,7Z,10Z,13Z,16Z,19Z)-docosahexaenoyl respectively.

name: phosphatidylinositol (18:1/20:4)
definition: A 1-phosphatidyl-1D-myo-inositol in which one acyl group has 18 carbons and 1 double bond while the other has 20 carbons and 4 double bonds.

name: phosphatidylserine (16:1/18:0)
definition: A phosphatidyl-L-serine in which one acyl group has 16 carbons and 1 double bond while the other has 18 carbons and is fully saturated.

name: phosphatidylserine (18:0/20:4)
definition: A phosphatidyl-L-serine in which one acyl group has 18 carbons and is fully saturated while the other has 20 carbons and 4 double bonds.

name: phosphatidylserine (20:4/20:4)
definition: A phosphatidyl-L-serine in which both acyl groups have 20 carbons and 4 double bonds.

name: N-nonadecanoylsphinganine-1-phosphocholine
definition: An N-acylsphinganine-1-phosphocholine in which the ceramide N-acyl group is specified as nonadecanoyl.

name: 3-[alpha-D-galactosyl-(1->6)-beta-D-galactosyl]-2-octoanoyl-sn-glycerol
definition: A glycoglycerolipid that consists of 3-[alpha-D-galactosyl-(1->6)-beta-D-galactosyl]-sn-glycerol in which the glycerol portion is acylated at position 2 by an octanoyl group.

name: N-(11Z-icosenoyl)-sphingosine-1-phosphocholine
definition: A sphingomyelin d18:1 in which the ceramide N-acyl group is specified as (11Z)-icosenoyl.

name: alpha-Neu5Ac-(2->3)-beta-D-Gal-(1->3)-beta-D-GalNAc-(1->4)-[alpha-Neu5Ac-(2->3)]-beta-D-Gal-(1->4)-beta-D-Glc-(1<->1')-Cer(d18:1/21:0)
definition: An alpha-NeuNAc-(2->3)-beta-D-Gal-(1->3)-beta-D-GalNAc-(1->4)-[alpha-NeuNAc-(2->3)]-beta-D-Gal-(1->4)-beta-D-Glc-(1<->1')-Cer in which the ceramide N-acyl group is specified as henicosanoyl.

name: alpha-Neu5Ac-(2->3)-beta-D-Gal-(1->3)-beta-D-GalNAc-(1->4)-[alpha-Neu5Ac-(2->8)-alpha-Neu5Ac-(2->8)-alpha-Neu5Ac-(2->3)]-beta-D-Gal-(1->4)-beta-D-Glc-(1<->1')-Cer(d18:1/24:0)
definition: An alpha-Neu5Ac-(2->3)-beta-Gal-(1->3)-beta-GalNAc-(1->4)-[alpha-Neu5Ac-(2->8)-alpha-Neu5Ac-(2->8)-alpha-Neu5Ac-(2->3)]-beta-Gal-(1->4)-beta-Glc-(1<->1')-Cer in which the ceramide N-acyl group is specified as tetracosanoyl.

name: beta-D-galactosyl-(1<->1')-N-octadecanoylsphinganine
definition: A beta-D-galactosyl-(1<->1')-N-acylsphinganine in which the acyl group is specified as octadecanoyl.

name: (7Z,10Z,13Z)-hexadecatrienoate
definition: A hexadecatrienoate that is the conjugate base of (7Z,10Z,13Z)-hexadecatrienoic acid, obtained by deprotonation of the carboxy group; major species at pH 7.3.

name: beta-D-galactosyl-(1<->1')-N-[(15Z)-tetracosenoyl]sphinganine
definition: A beta-D-galactosyl-(1<->1')-N-acylsphinganine in which the acyl group is specified as (15Z)-tetracosenoyl.

name: alpha-Neu5Ac-(2->8)-alpha-Neu5Ac-(2->3)-beta-D-Gal-(1->3)-beta-D-GalNAc-(1->4)-[alpha-Neu5Ac-(2->3)]-beta-D-Gal-(1->4)-beta-D-Glc-(1<->1')-Cer(3-)
definition: An anionic ganglioside arising from deprotonation of the neuraminosyl carboxy groups of alpha-Neu5Ac-(2->8)-alpha-Neu5Ac-(2->3)-beta-D-Gal-(1->3)-beta-D-GalNAc-(1->4)-[alpha-Neu5Ac-(2->3)]-beta-D-Gal-(1->4)-beta-D-Glc-(1<->1')-Cer; major species at pH 7.3.

A branched amino oligosaccharide that is a nonadecasaccharide derivative consisting of a linear trisaccharide of beta-D-mannose and two N-acetyl-beta-D-glucosamine residues all linked in sequence (1->4), to the mannosyl residue of which are linked linked (1->3) and (1->6) two N-acetyl-alpha-neuraminyl-(2->6)-beta-D-galactosyl-(1->4)-N-acetyl-beta-D-glucosaminyl-(1->3)-beta-D-galactosyl-(1->4)-N-acetyl-beta-D-glucosaminyl-(1->3)-beta-D-galactosyl-(1->4)-N-acetyl-beta-D-glucosaminyl-(1->2)-alpha-D-mannosyl linear octasaccharide units.

A branched amino oligosaccharide that is an nonadecasaccharide derivative consisting of a linear trisaccharide of beta-D-mannose and two N-acetyl-beta-D-glucosamine residues all linked in sequence (1->4), to the mannosyl residue of which are linked linked (1->3) and (1->6) two N-acetyl-alpha-neuraminyl-(2->3)-beta-D-galactosyl-(1->4)-N-acetyl-beta-D-glucosaminyl-(1->3)-beta-D-galactosyl-(1->4)-N-acetyl-beta-D-glucosaminyl-(1->3)-beta-D-galactosyl-(1->4)-N-acetyl-beta-D-glucosaminyl-(1->2)-alpha-D-mannosyl linear octasaccharide units.

A branched amino oligosaccharide that is a pentadecasaccharide derivative consisting of a linear trisaccharide of beta-D-mannose and two N-acetyl-beta-D-glucosamine residues all linked in sequence (1->4), to the mannosyl residue of which are linked linked (1->3) and (1->6) two N-acetyl-alpha-neuraminyl-(2->6)-beta-D-galactosyl-(1->4)-N-acetyl-beta-D-glucosaminyl-(1->3)-beta-D-galactosyl-(1->4)-N-acetyl-beta-D-glucosaminyl-(1->2)-alpha-D-mannosyl linear hexasaccharide units.

name: 1,2-di-(9Z,12Z-octadecadienoyl)-3-(beta-D-galactosyl)-sn-glycerol
definition: A 1,2-diacyl-3-beta-D-galactosyl-sn-glycerol in which the groups at the 1- and 2-positions are both linoleoyl (9Z,12Z-octadecadienoyl).

name: 1-(9Z-octadecenoyl)-2-hexadecanoyl-3-beta-D-galactosyl-sn-glycerol
definition: A 1,2-diacyl-3-beta-D-galactosyl-sn-glycerol in which the 1- and 2-acyl groups are specified as oleoyl and palmitoyl respectively.

name: beta-D-GlcpNAc-(1->3)-alpha-L-Fucp
definition: An amino disaccharide in which D-GlcNAc is linked beta(1->3) to L-fucose which has alpha-configuration at its anomeric centre.

name: beta-D-Galp-(1->3)-beta-D-GalpNAc-(1->4)-[alpha-Neup5Ac-(2->8)-alpha-Neup5Ac-(2->8)-alpha-Neup5Ac-(2->3)]-beta-D-Galp-(1->4)-beta-D-Glcp
definition: A branched amino heptasaccharide consisting of a linear tetrasaccharide of beta-D-galactose, N-acetyl-beta-D-galactosamine, beta-D-galactose and beta-D-glucose residues linked sequentially (1->3), (1->4) and (1->4), to the galactose residue proximal to the reducing end is also linked (2->3) an N-acetyl-alpha-neuraminyl-(2->8)-N-acetyl-alpha-neuraminyl-(2->8)-N-acetyl-alpha-neuraminyl trisaccharide side-chain.  The carbohydrate moiety of ganglioside GT1c.

name: S-[(2E,6E)-farnesyl]-L-cysteinate residue
definition: An alpha-amino-acid residue anion derived from S-[(2E,6E)-farnesyl]-L-cysteine zwitterion; major species at pH 7.3.

name: S-[(2E,6E)-farnesyl]-L-cysteine methyl ester residue
definition: An alkylamino group derived from S-[(2E,6E)-farnesyl]-L-cysteine methyl ester.

name: alpha-Neu5Ac-(2->8)-alpha-Neu5Ac-(2->3)-beta-Gal-(1->3)-beta-GalNAc-(1->4)-[alpha-Neu5Ac-(2->8)-alpha-Neu5Ac-(2->8)-alpha-Neu5Ac-(2->3)]-beta-Gal-(1->4)-beta-Glc-Cer(5-)
definition: An anionic ganglioside arising from deprotonation of the neuraminosyl carboxy groups of a ganglioside GP1c with undefined sphingoid base and fatty acyl chain; major species at pH 7.3.

name: 3-(beta-D-galactosyl)-monododecanoyl-sn-glycerol
definition: A galactoglycerolipid consisting of 3-(beta-D-galactosyl)-sn-glycerol in which the glyceryl moiety is acylated at either position O1 or O2 by a dodecanoyl group.

name: L-leucinate residue
definition: An alpha-amino-acid residue anion derived from L-leucinate. Major structure at pH 7.3.

name: methyl L-leucinato group
definition: An alkylamino group derived from methyl L-leucinate.

name: victoria blue R
definition: An iminium salt composed of 4-{[4-(dimethylamino)phenyl][4-(ethylamino)naphthalen-1-yl]methylidene}-N,N-dimethylcyclohexa-2,5-dien-1-iminium and chloride ions in a 1:1 ratio.

name: victoria blue R(1+)
definition: An iminium ion that forms the cationic portion of the histological dye 'victoria blue R'.

name: alkali blue 4B
definition: An organic sodium salt having 2-(4-{(4-amino-3-methylphenyl)[4-(phenylimino)cyclohexa-2,5-dien-1-ylidene]methyl}anilino)benzene-1-sulfonate as the counterion. It is used for staining elastic fibres.

name: PI-103
definition: An organic heterotricyclic compound that is pyrido[3',2':4,5]furo[3,2-d]pyrimidine substituted at positions 2 and 4 by 3-hydroxyphenyl and morpholin-4-yl groups respectively. A dual-kinase inhibitor with anti-cancer properties.

name: 4-O-(2-acetamido-2-deoxy-beta-D-glucopyranosyl)-5-O-phosphono-D-ribitol
definition: A disaccharide phosphate consisting of 2-O-(N-acetyl-beta-D-glucosaminyl)ribitol phosphorylated at O-1 of the ribitol residue; a ligand epitope of Staphylococcus aureus.

name: N-cyclopropyl-3-{4-[(cyclopropylmethyl)carbamoyl]phenyl}-4-methylbenzamide
definition: A dicarboxylic acid diamide obtained by condensation of the 3- and 4'-carboxy groups of 6-methyl[1,1'-biphenyl]-3,4'-dicarboxylic acid with cyclpropylamine and cyclpropylmethylamine respectively.

name: VX-745
definition: A member of the class of pyrimidopyridazines that is 6H-pyrimido[1,6-b]pyridazin-6-one substituted at positions 2 and 5 by (2,4-difluorophenyl)sulfanyl and 2,6-dichlorophenyl groups respectively

name: 4-chloro-6-{5-[(2-morpholin-4-ylethyl)amino]-1,2-benzisoxazol-3-yl}benzene-1,3-diol
definition: A member of the class of 1,2-benzoxazoles carrying 2,4-dihydroxy-4-chlorophenyl and (2-morpholin-4-ylethyl)amino substituents at positions 3 and 5 respectively.

name: 9-cyclopentyl-N(8)-(2-fluorophenyl)-N(2)-(4-methoxyphenyl)-9H-purine-2,8-diamine
definition: A member of the class of purines that is carrying 9-cyclopentyl-9H-purine-2,8-diamine in which the amino groups at positions 2 and 8 are carrying 4-methoxyphenyl and 2-fluorophenyl substituents respectively.

name: sotrastaurin
definition: A member of the class of maleimides that is maleimide which is substituted at position 3 by an indol-3-yl group and at position 4 by a quinazolin-4-yl group, which in turn is substituted at position 2 by a 4-methylpiperazin-1-yl group. It is a potent and selective inhibitor of protein kinase C and has been investigated as an immunosuppresant in renal transplant patients.

name: alkali Blue G
definition: An aminobenzenesulfonic acid that is 2-aminobenzenesulfonic acid in which one of the amino hydrogens is replaced by a 4-{(4-amino-3-methylphenyl)[4-(phenylimino)cyclohexa-2,5-dien-1-ylidene]methyl} group.

name: PQIP
definition: A member of the class of imidazopyrazines that is imidazo[1,5-a]pyrazin-8-amine carrying additional 2-phenylquinolin-7-yl and 3-(4-methylpiperazin-1-yl)cyclobutyl groups at positions 1 and 3 respectively. It is an inhibitor of insulin growth factor 1 receptor (IGF-1 receptor, IGFR1R) tyrosine kinase.

name: ICPD-26
definition: A member of the class of thiadiazoles that is 1,2,3-thiadiazole substituted at positions 4 and 5 by 2,4-dihydroxy-4-chlorophenyl and 4-methoxyphenyl groups respectively.

name: ICPD-47
definition: A member of the class of thiadiazoles that is 1,2,3-thiadiazole substituted at positions 4 and 5 by 2,4-dihydroxy-4-chlorophenyl and 4-methoxyphenyl groups respectively.

name: 1-[5-t-butyl-2-(4-methylphenyl)pyrazol-3-yl]-3-[4-(2-phenylmethoxyethyl)-1,3-thiazol-2-yl]urea
definition: A member of the class of ureas obtained by formal condensation of the carboxy group of [3-tert-butyl-1-(4-methylphenyl)pyrazol-5-yl]carbamic acid with the amino group of 4-[2-(benzyloxy)ethyl]-1,3-thiazol-2-amine.

name: N(2)-[3-methoxy-4-(morpholin-4-yl)phenyl]-N(4)-(quinolin-3-yl)pyrimidine-2,4-diamine
definition: A member of the class of aminopyrimidines that is pyrimidine-2,4-diamine substituted at positions N-2 and N-4 by 3-methoxy-4-(morpholin-4-yl)phenyl and quinolin-3-yl groups respectively.

name: 1-(3-{5-[4-(aminomethyl)phenyl]-1H-pyrrolo[2,3-b]pyridin-3-yl}phenyl)-3-(2-phenoxyphenyl)urea
definition: A member of the class of phenylureas obtained by formal condensation of the carboxy group of (3-{5-[4-(aminomethyl)phenyl]pyrrolo[2,3-b]pyridin-3-yl}phenyl)carbamic acid with the amino group of 2-phenoxyaniline. An inhibitor of tyrosine kinase.

name: 4-methyl-N-[3-(morpholin-4-yl)phenyl]-3-[3-(piperidin-4-yl)-1,2-benzoxazol-6-yl]benzamide
definition: A biaryl resulting from the formal oxidative coupling of the 6 position of 3-(piperidin-4-yl)-1,2-benzoxazole with the 3 position of p-toluic acid and subsequent condensation of the carboxy group with the primary amino group of 3-(morpholin-4-yl)aniline to give the corresponding carboxamide. An inhibitor of p38-alpha MAP kinase.

name: methyl 3-[2-(2-thienyl)acetamido]thiophene-2-carboxylate
definition: A carboxamide resulting from the formal condensation of the carboxy group of 2-thienylacetic acid with the amino group of methyl 3-aminothiophene-2-carboxylate. It is a selective inhibitor of c-Jun N-terminal kinases (JNKs).

name: N-cyclopropyl-2',6-dimethyl-4'-(5-methyl-1,3,4-oxadiazol-2-yl)biphenyl-3-carboxamide
definition: A member of the class of biphenyls that is biphenyl in which one of the phenyl groups is substituted at positions 2and 4 by a methyl and a 5-methyl-1,3,4-oxadiazol-2-yl groups, respectively, while the other phenyl group is substituted at positions 2 and 5 by a methyl and an N-(cyclopropyl)aminocarbohyl group, respectively. An inhibitor of p38-alpha MAP kinase.

name: ZSTK-474
definition: A triamino-1,3,5-triazine that is 1,3,5-triazine in which two of the hydrogens have been replaced by morpholin-4-yl groups while the third hydrogen has been replaced by a 2-(difluoromethyl)benzimidazol-1-yl group. It is an inhibitor of phosphatidylinositol 3-kinase.

name: medium-chain fatty acyl-CoA(4-)
definition: An acyl-CoA oxoanion that results from deprotonation of the phosphate and diphosphate groups of any medium-chain fatty acyl-CoA; major species at pH 7.3.

name: mepiquat
definition: A quaternary ammonium ion has that has two methyl groups and a pentamethylene-1,5-diyl group attached to the nitrogen. Its salts are used as plant growth inhibitors.

name: 1-(9Z,12Z,15Z)-octadecatrienoyl-2-(7Z,10Z,13Z)-hexadecatrienoyl-3-(beta-D-galactosyl)-sn-glycerol
definition: A 1,2-diacyl-3-(beta-D-galactosyl)-sn-glycerol in which the 1- and 2- acyl groups are specified as (9Z,12Z,15Z)-octadecatrienoyl and (7Z,10Z,13Z)-hexadecatrienoyl respectively.

name: 1-(9S,13S,12-oxophytodienoyl)-2-(7Z,10Z,13Z)-hexadecatrienoyl-3-(beta-D-galactosyl)-sn-glycerol
definition: A 1,2-diacyl-3-(beta-D-galactosyl)-sn-glycerol in which the 1- and 2- acyl groups are specified as (9S,13S-12-oxophytodienoyl) and (7Z,10Z,13Z)-hexadecatrienoyl respectively.

name: 2-(7Z,10Z,13Z)-hexadecatrienoyl-3-(beta-D-galactosyl)-sn-glycerol
definition: A 2-acyl-3-(beta-D-galactosyl)-sn-glycerol in which the acyl group at the 2 position is specified as (7Z,10Z,13Z)-hexadecatrienoyl.

name: 2-[(5Z,8Z,11Z)-icosatrienoyl]-sn-glycero-3-phosphoethanolamine
definition: A lysophosphatidylethanolamine 20:3 in which the acyl group is specified as (5Z,8Z,11Z)-icosatrienoyl and is located at position 2.

name: phosphatidic acid 38:7
definition: A 1,2-diacyl-sn-glycerol 3-phosphate in which the acyl groups at C-1 and C-2 contain 38 carbons in total with 5 double bonds.

name: hexadecatrienoate
definition: A polyunsaturated fatty acid anion obtained by deprotonation of the carboxy group of any hexadecatrienoic acid; major species at pH 7.3.

name: 4-O-(2-acetamido-2-deoxy-beta-D-glucopyranosyl)-D-ribitol
definition: An amino disaccharide consisting of N-acetyl-D-glucosamine attached to D-ribitol via a beta-(1->4)-linkage; epitope of Staphylococcus aureus.

name: alpha-Neu5Ac-(2->3)-[beta-D-Gal-(1->3)-beta-D-GalNAc-(1->4)]-beta-D-Gal-(1->4)-beta-D-Glc-(1<->1')-Cer(d20:1)
definition: A sialotetraosylceramide consisting of a alpha-Neu5Ac-(2->3)-[beta-D-Gal-(1->3)-beta-D-GalNAc-(1->4)]-beta-D-Gal-(1->4)-beta-D-Glc moiety attached via a glycosidic bond at position 1 of N-acylicosasphingosine.

name: alpha-Neu5Ac-(2->3)-beta-D-Gal-(1->4)-beta-D-Glc-(1<->1')-Cer(d20:1)
definition: A sialodiosylceramide that consists of an alpha-Neu5Ac-(2->3)-beta-D-Gal-(1->4)-beta-D-Glc moiety attached via a glycosidic bond at position 1 of N-acylicosasphingosine.

name: alpha-Neu5Ac-(2->3)-beta-D-Gal-(1->3)-beta-D-GalNAc-(1->4)-[alpha-Neu5Ac-(2->3)]-beta-D-Gal-(1->4)-beta-D-Glc-(1<->1')-Cer(d20:1)
definition: A sialodiosylceramide that consists of an alpha-Neu5Ac-(2->3)-beta-D-Gal-(1->3)-beta-D-GalNAc-(1->4)-[alpha-Neu5Ac-(2->3)]-beta-D-Gal-(1->4)-beta-D-Glc moiety attached via a glycosidic bond at position 1 of N-acylicosasphingosine.

name: N-(2,6-dichlorobenzoyl)-4-[1,6-dimethyl-2-oxo-4-(trifluoromethyl)-1,2-dihydropyridin-3-yl]-L-phenylalanine
definition: An L-phenylalanine derivative that is N-(2,6-dichlorobenzoyl)-L-phenylalanine carrying an additional 1,6-dimethyl-2-oxo-4-(trifluoromethyl)-1,2-dihydropyridin-3-yl substituent at position 4 on the phenyl ring.

name: alpha-Neu5Ac-(2->3)-beta-D-Gal-(1->4)-beta-D-Glc-(1<->1')-Cer(d16:1)
definition: A sialodiosylceramide that consists of an alpha-Neu5Ac-(2->3)-beta-D-Gal-(1->4)-beta-D-Glc moiety attached via a glycosidic bond at position 1 of N-acylhexadecasphingosine.

name: beta-D-GalNAc-(1->4)-[alpha-Neu5Ac-(2->3)]-beta-D-Gal-(1->4)-beta-D-Glc-(1<->1)-Cer(d20:1)
definition: A sialotriosylceramide that consists of a beta-D-GalNAc-(1->4)-[alpha-Neu5Ac-(2->3)]-beta-D-Gal-(1->4)-beta-D-Glc moiety attached via a glycosidic bond at position 1 of N-acylicosasphingosine.

name: S-[(2E,6E)-farnesyl]-L-cysteino group
definition: An L-alpha-amino acid residue derived from S-[(2E,6E)-farnesyl]-L-cysteine

name: L-beta-isoaspartate residue
definition: An anionic amino-acid residue formed following deamidation of L-asparagine or dehydration of L-aspartate residue.

name: L-ornithine 2-naphthylamide
definition: An L-ornithine derivative that is the amide obtained by formal condensation of the carboxy group of L-ornithine with the amino group of 2-naphthylamine.

name: L-isoaspartate alpha-methyl ester residue
definition: An amino acid residue derived from L-isoaspartic acid alpha-methyl ester.

name: L-phenylalanine 2-naphthylamide
definition: An L-phenylalanine derivative that is the amide obtained by formal condensation of the carboxy group of L-phenylalanine with the amino group of 2-naphthylamine.

name: L-proline 2-naphthylamide
definition: An L-proline derivative that is the amide obtained by formal condensation of the carboxy group of L-proline with the amino group of 2-naphthylamine.

name: 5-oxo-L-proline 2-naphthylamide
definition: An L-proline derivative that is the amide obtained by formal condensation of the carboxy group of 5-oxo-L-proline with the amino group of 2-naphthylamine.

name: uridylyl-L-tyrosine(1-) residue
definition: An alpha-amino-acid residue anion obtained by deprotonation of the phosphate OH group of uridylyl-L-tyrosine residue; major species at pH 7.3.

name: L-serine 2-naphthylamide
definition: An L-serine derivative that is the amide obtained by formal condensation of the carboxy group of L-serine with the amino group of 2-naphthylamine.

name: L-threonine 2-naphthylamide
definition: An L-threonine derivative that is the amide obtained by formal condensation of the carboxy group of L-threonine with the amino group of 2-naphthylamine.

name: monodecanoylglycerol
definition: A monoglyceride in which the acyl group is decanoyl (capryl) with the position of acylation unspecified.

name: L-tryptophan 2-naphthylamide
definition: An L-tryptophan derivative that is the amide obtained by formal condensation of the carboxy group of L-tryptophan with the amino group of 2-naphthylamine.

name: L-tyrosine 2-naphthylamide
definition: An L-tyrosine derivative that is the amide obtained by formal condensation of the carboxy group of L-tyrosine with the amino group of 2-naphthylamine.

name: L-valine 2-naphthylamide
definition: An L-valine derivative that is the amide obtained by formal condensation of the carboxy group of L-valine with the amino group of 2-naphthylamine.

name: L-leucine 4-methoxy-2-naphthylamide
definition: An L-leucine derivative that is the amide obtained by formal condensation of the carboxy group of L-leucine with the amino group of 4-methoxy-2-naphthylamine.

name: O-[S-2,3-dihydroxybenzoylpantetheine-4'-phosphoryl]-L-serine(1-) residue
definition: An O-(S-acylpantetheine-4'-phosphoryl)-L-serine(1-) residue in which the S-acyl group is specified as S-2,3-dihydroxybenzoyl.

name: L-alanyl-L-alanine 2-naphthylamide
definition: An N-(2-naphthyl)carboxamide obtained by formal condensation of the carboxy group of L-alanyl-L-alanine with the amino group of 2-naphthylamine.

name: L-alanyl-L-phenylalanyl-L-proline 2-naphthylamide
definition: An N-(2-naphthyl)carboxamide obtained by formal condensation of the carboxy group of L-alanyl-L-phenylalanyl-L-proline with the amino group of 2-naphthylamine.

name: beta-alanine 2-naphthylamide
definition: A beta-alanine derivative that is the amide obtained by formal condensation of the carboxy group of beta-alanine with the amino group of 2-naphthylamine.

name: pyrimidopyridazine
definition: Any organic heterobicyclic compound containing ortho-fused pyrimidine and pyridazine rings.

name: 2'-deoxyadenosine 5'-monophosphate(1-) residue
definition: An organic anionic group obtained by deprotonation of the phosphate OH group of 2'-deoxyadenosine 5'-monophosphate (dAMP) residue; major species at pH 7.3.

name: C-terminal Gly-Gly-AMP(1-) group
definition: An organic anionic group obtained by deprotonation of deprotonation of the phosphate OH group of C-terminal Gly-Gly-AMP residue

name: C-terminal N-glycylaminoethanethioic S-acid residue
definition: An alkylamino group derived from N-glycylaminoethanethioic S-acid.

name: vatalanib
definition: A member of the class of phthalazines that is phthalazine in which the hydrogens at positions 1 and 4have been replaced by a p-chlorophenylamino group and a pyridin-4-ylmethyl group, respectively. It is a multi-targeted tyrosine kinase inhibitor for all isoforms of VEGFR, PDGFR and c-Kit.

name: 4-(5-methyl-3-phenylisoxazol-4-yl)pyrimidin-2-amine
definition: A member of the class of isoxazoles carrying phenyl, 2-aminopyrimidin-4-yl and methyl substituents at positions 3, 4 and 5 respectively.

name: 4-phenylpyrimidine
definition: A biaryl that is pyrimidine substituted at position 4 by a phenyl group.

name: vatalanib succinate
definition: A succinate salt obtained by combining vatalanib with one molar equivalent of succinic acid. It is a multi-targeted tyrosine kinase inhibitor for all isoforms of VEGFR, PDGFR and c-Kit.

name: SGX-523
definition: A member of the class of triazolopyridazines that is 6-(1-methylpyrazol-4-yl)[1,2,4]triazolo[4,3-b]pyridazine-3-thiol in which the thiol hydrogen is replaced by a quinolin-6-yl group.

name: 5-(5-chloro-1H-pyrrolo[2,3-d]pyrimidin-4-yl)-4,5,6,7-tetrahydro-1H-imidazo[4,5-c]pyridine
definition: An imidazopyridine that is 4,5,6,7-tetrahydro-1H-imidazo[4,5-c]pyridine in which the amino hydrogen is replaced by a 5-chloro-1H-pyrrolo[2,3-d]pyrimidin-4-yl group. A potent inhibitor of AKT1 kinase.

name: AMG-208
definition: A member of the class of quinolines that is 7-methoxyquinoline substituted at position 4 by a (6-phenyl[1,2,4]triazolo[4,3-b]pyridazin-3-yl)methoxy group. AMG exhibits antitumour activity, particularly in prostate cancer.

name: 2-(6-methoxy-1-oxo-1,3-dihydro-2H-isoindol-2-yl)-N-[4-(piperazin-1-yl)pyridin-3-yl]-1,3-thiazole-4-carboxamide
definition: An aromatic amide obtained by formal condensation of the amino group of 2-(6-methoxy-1-oxo-1,3-dihydro-2H-isoindol-2-yl)-1,3-thiazole-4-carboxylic acid with the primary amino group of 4-(piperazin-1-yl)pyridin-3-amine.

name: leupeptin hemisulfate
definition: A peptide sulfate salt obtained by combining leupeptin with 0.5 molar equivalents of sulfuric acid.

name: omega-conotoxin GVIA
definition: A heterodetic cyclic polypeptide consisting of the linear sequence Cys-Lys-Ser-Hyp-Gly-Ser-Ser-Cys-Ser-Hyp-Thr-Ser-Tyr-Asn-Cys-Cys-Arg-Ser-Cys-Asn-Hyp-Tyr-Thr-Lys-Arg-Cys-Tyr-NH2 with three disulfide bridges between cysteine residues 1-16, 8-19 and 15-26. Isolated from the venom of the fish-hunting snail Conus geographus.

name: 5-hydroperoxy-15-HETE(1-)
definition: An icosanoid anion that is the conjugate base of 5-hydroperoxy-15-HETE, obtained by deprotonation of the carboxy group; major species at pH 7.3.

name: 5(S)-HETE(1-)
definition: An icosanoid anion that is the conjugate base of 5(S)-HETE, obtained by deprotonation of the hydroxy group; major species at pH 7.3.

name: perfluorododecanoic acid
definition: A fluoroalkanoic acid that is dodecanoic acid in which all of the hydrogens attached to carbon atoms are replaced by fluorines. It is a highly persistent, bioaccumulative breakdown product of stain- and grease-proof coatings on food packaging, soft furnishings and carpets.

name: ribonucleotide residue(1-)
definition: An organic anionic group obtained by deprotonation of the phosphate OH group of any ribonucleotide residue; major species at pH 7.3.

name: 2'-O-methylribonucleotide(1-) residue
definition: An organic anionic group obtained by deprotonation of the phosphate OH group of any 2'-O-methylribonucleotide residue; major species at pH 7.3.

name: GSK690693
definition: A member of the class of imidazopyridines that is 4-(1-ethylimidazo[4,5-c]pyridin-4-yl)-2-methylbut-3-yn-2-ol carrying additional 2-(4-amino-1,2,5-oxadiazol-3-yl and [(3S)-piperidin-3-yl]methoxy substituents at positions 4 and 7 respectively.

name: 4-{2-[4-(3,10-dibromo-8-chloro-6,11-dihydro-5H-benzo[5,6]cyclohepta[1,2-b]pyridin-11-yl)piperidin-1-yl]-2-oxoethyl}piperidine-1-carboxamide
definition: A benzocycloheptapyridine that is benzo[5,6]cyclohepta[1,2-b]pyridine which is substituted at positions 3 and 10 by bromines, at position 8 by chlorine, and at position 11 by an N-acetylpiperidin-4-yl group in which one of the hydrogens of the acetyl moiety has been replaced by a 1-carbamoylpiperidin-4-yl group.

name: torkinib
definition: A member of the class of pyrazolopyrimidines that is 1H-pyrazolo[3,4-d]pyrimidine substituted by isopropyl, 5-hydroxyindol-2-yl and amino groups at positions 1, 3 and 4 respectively. It is a potent inhibitor of mTOR and exhibits anti-cancer properties.

name: 12(S)-HETE(1-)
definition: An icosanoid anion that is the conjugate base of 12(S)-HETE, obtained by deprotonation of the carboxy group; major species at pH 7.3.

name: SB-239063
definition: A member of the class of imidazoles carrying 4-hydroxycyclohexyl, 4-fluorophenyl and 2-methoxypyrimidin-4-yl substituents at positions 1, 4 and 5 respectively.

name: torin 2
definition: A member of the class of pyridoquinolines that is benzo[h][1,6]naphthyridin-2-one carrying additional 3-(trifluoromethyl)phenyl and 6-aminopyridin-3-yl substituents at positions 1 and 9 respectively. It is a potent inhibitor of mTOR and exhibits anti-cancer properties.

name: talmapimod
definition: An indolecarboxamide obtained by formal condensation of the carboxy group of 6-chloro-3-[(dimethylamino)(oxo)acetyl]-1-methylindole-5-carboxylic acid with the secondary amino group  of (2S,5R)-1-[(4-fluorophenyl)methyl]-2,5-dimethylpiperazine. It is a potent inhibitor of MAPK and exhibits anti-cancer properties.

name: pamapimod
definition: A member of the class of pyridopyrimidines that is 8-methylpyrido[2,3-d]pyrimidin-7(8H)-one carrying additional (1,5-dihydroxypentan-3-yl)amino and 2,4-difluorophenoxy substituents at positions 2 and 6 respectively. It is a potent inhibitor of MAPK and is used for treatment of rheumatoid arthritis.

name: IC-87114
definition: A member of the class of quinazolines that is quinazolin-4(3H)-one carrying (6-amino-9H-purin-9-yl)methyl, 2-methylphenyl and methyl substituents at positions 2, 3 and 5 respectively.

name: BIIB021
definition: A member of the class of 2-aminopurines that is 2-aminopurine which is substituted by a chlorine at position 6 and by a (4-methoxy-3,5-dimethylpyridin-2-yl)methyl group at position 9.

name: metformin(1+)
definition: A guanidinium ion obtained by monoprotonation of metformin.

name: U-73122
definition: An aza-steroid that is 3-O-methyl-17beta-estradiol in which the 17beta-hydroxy group is replaced by a 6-(maleimid-1-yl)hexylamino group. An inibitor of phospholipase C.

name: EC 5.3.1.1 (triose-phosphate isomerase) inhibitor
definition: Any EC 5.3.1.* (intramolecular oxidoreductase interconverting aldoses and ketoses) inhibitor that interferes with the action of a triose-phosphate isomerase (EC 5.3.1.1).

name: U0126.EtOH
definition: An addition compound obtained by combining equimolar amounts of (2Z,3Z)-bis{amino[(2-aminophenyl)sulfanyl]methylidene}butanedinitrile (U0126) and ethanol. An inhibitor of mitogen-activated protein kinase that also exhibits anti-cancer properties.

name: 12(S)-HHTrE(1-)
definition: A polyunsaturated fatty acid anion that is the conjugate base of 12(S)-HHTrE, obtained by deprotonation of the carboxy group; major species at pH 7.3.

name: anthra[1,9-cd]pyrazol-6(2H)-one
definition: A member of the class of anthrapyrazoles that is anthra[1,9-cd]pyrazole substituted at position 6 by an oxo group. An inhibitor of c-Jun N-terminal kinase.

name: thromboxane B2(1-)
definition: A thromboxane anion that is the conjugate base of thromboxane B2, obtained by deprotonation of the carboxy group; major species at pH 7.3.

name: 11-oxo-ETE(1-)
definition: A polyunsaturated oxo fatty acid anion that is the conjugate base of 11-oxo-ETE, obtained by deprotonation of the carboxy group; major species at pH 7.3.

name: anthrapyrazole
definition: Any organic heterotetracyclic compound consisting of a pyrazole ring ortho-fused to an anthracene.

name: strychnine hydrochloride
definition: A hydrochloride obtained by combining strychnine with one molar equivalent of hydrogen chloride.

name: strychnine(1+)
definition: An indole alkaloid cation obtained by protonation of the tertiary amino group of strychnine.

name: potassium 2-(4-carboxylatophenyl)-4,4,5,5-tetramethylimidazoline-1-oxyl-3-oxide
definition: A potassium salt having 2-(4-carboxylatophenyl)-4,4,5,5-tetramethylimidazoline-1-oxyl-3-oxide as the counterion.

name: carboxy-PTIO
definition: A mmeber of the class of imidazolines and organic radical that is 4,4,5,5-tetramethyl-3-oxo-4,5-dihydro-1H-3lambda(5)-imidazol-1-yl]oxidanyl substituted at position 2 by a 4-carboxyphenyl group.

name: gamendazole
definition: A member of the class of indazoles that is 3-(indazol-3-yl}prop-2-enoic acid carrying additional 2,4-dichlorobenzyl and trifluoromethyl substituents at positions 1 and 6 respectively. An orally active antispermatogenic compound with antifertility effects that is a potential male contraceptive drug.

name: carboxylato-PTIO
definition: A benzoate that is the conjugate base of carboxy-PTIO, obtained by deprotonation of the carboxy group.

name: SB 203580
definition: A member of the class of imidazoles carrying 4-methylsulfinylphenyl, 4-pyridyl and 4-fluorophenyl substituents at positions 2, 4 and 5 respectively. An inhibitor of mitogen-activated protein kinase.

name: Ro 41-5253
definition: A thiochromane that is 3,4-dihydro-2H-1-benzothiopyran S,S-dioxide in which the hydrogens at position 4 are both replaced by methyl groups, the hydrogens at position 7 is replaced by a heptyloxy group, while the hydrogen at position 6 is replaced by a 1-phenylprop-1-en-2-yl group, the phenyl group of which is substituted at the para position by a carboxy group. It is a selective antagonist for retinoic acid receptor alpha.

name: 20-hydroxylipoxin A4(1-)
definition: A lipoxin anion that is the conjugate base of 20-hydroxylipoxin A4 arising from deprotonation of the carboxylic acid function; major species at pH 7.3.

name: retinoic acid receptor modulator
definition: A nuclear receptor modulator that affects the retinoic acid receptor

name: nuclear receptor modulator
definition: Any receptor modulator acting on nuclear receptors

name: receptor modulator
definition: A drug that acts as an antagonist, agonist, reverse agonist, or in some other fashion when interacting with cellular receptors.

name: 20-hydroxylipoxin B4(1-)
definition: A lipoxin anion that is the conjugate base of 20-hydroxy-lipoxin B4 arising from deprotonation of the carboxylic acid function; major species at pH 7.3.

name: S-methyl-L-thiocitrulline
definition: An L-arginine derivative in which the guanidino NH2 group of L-arginine is replaced by a methylsufanyl group.

name: retinoic acid receptor alpha antagonist
definition: A retinoic acid receptor antagonist that antagonises retinoic acid receptor alpha.

name: 5,20-DiHETE(1-)
definition: An icosanoid anion that is the conjugate base of 5,20-DiHETE, arising from deprotonation of the carboxylic acid function; major species at pH 7.3.

name: 8-HETE(1-)
definition: An icosanoid anion that is the conjugate base of 8-HETE arising from deprotonation of the carboxylic acid function; major species at pH 7.3.

name: 8,20-DiHETE(1-)
definition: An icosanoid anion that is the conjugate base of 8,20-DiHETE arising from deprotonation of the carboxylic acid function; major species at pH 7.3.

name: 12-HETE(1-)
definition: An icosanoid anion that is the conjugate base of 12-HETE arising from deprotonation of the carboxylic acid function; major species at pH 7.3.

name: 12,20-DiHETE(1-)
definition: An icosanoid anion that is the conjugate base of 12,20-DiHETE arising from deprotonation of the carboxylic acid function; major species at pH 7.3.

name: 20-oxoleukotriene B4(1-)
definition: A leukotriene anion that is the conjugate base of 20-oxoleukotriene B4 arising from deprotonation of the carboxylic acid function; major species at pH 7.3.

name: N-[3-(aminomethyl)benzyl]acetamidine
definition: An aralkylamine that is Nbenzylacetamidine substituted at position 3 on the benzene ring by an aminomethyl group. An inhibitor of nitric oxide synthase.

name: 20-hydroxy-20-oxoleukotriene B4(2-)
definition: A leukotriene anion that is the conjugate base of 20-hydroxy-20-oxoleukotriene B4 arising from deprotonation of the carboxylic acid functions; major species at pH 7.3.

name: 6-trans-leukotriene B4(1-)
definition: A leukotriene anion that is the conjugate base of 6-trans-leukotriene B4 arising from deprotonation of the carboxylic acid function; major species at pH 7.3.

name: AM-251
definition: A carbohydrazide obtained by formal condensation of the carboxy group of 1-(2,4-dichlorophenyl)-5-(4-iodophenyl)-4-methyl-1H-pyrazole-3-carboxylic acid with the amino group of 1-aminopiperidine. An antagonist at the CB1 cannabinoid receptor.

name: very long-chain 3-oxoacyl-CoA(4-)
definition: A 3-oxoacyl-CoA(4-) arising from deprotonation of the phosphate and diphosphate OH groups of any very long-chain 3-oxoacyl-CoA (very long-chain = chain length greater than C22); major species at pH 7.3.

name: 3-oxoacyl-CoA(4-)
definition: An acyl-CoA(4-) arising from deprotonation of the phosphate and diphosphate OH groups of any 3-oxoacyl-CoA; major species at pH 7.3.

name: L-glutamyl-L-glutamic acid 2-naphthylamide
definition: An N-(2-naphthyl)carboxamide obtained by formal condensation of the C-terminal carboxy group of L-glutamyl-L-glutamic acid with the amino group of 2-naphthylamine.

name: L-glutamylglycine 2-naphthylamide
definition: An N-(2-naphthyl)carboxamide obtained by formal condensation of the C-terminal carboxy group of L-glutamylglycine with the amino group of 2-naphthylamine.

name: L-glutamylglycyl-L-arginine 2-naphthylamide
definition: An N-(2-naphthyl)carboxamide obtained by formal condensation of the C-terminal carboxy group of L-glutamylglycyl-L-arginine with the amino group of 2-naphthylamine.

name: N-glutaryl-L-phenylalanine 2-naphthylamide
definition: An N-(2-naphthyl)carboxamide obtained by formal condensation of the C-terminal carboxy group of N-glutaryl-L-phenylalanine with the amino group of 2-naphthylamine.

name: very long-chain 2,3,4-saturated fatty acyl CoA(4-)
definition: A very long-chain acyl CoA(4-) obtained by deprotonation of the phosphate and diphosphate OH groups of any very-long-chain 2,3,4-saturated fatty acyl CoA; major species at pH 7.3.

name: 20-hydroxy-6-trans-leukotriene B4(1-)
definition: A leukotriene anion that is the conjugate base of 20-hydroxy-6-trans-leukotriene B4 arising from deprotonation of the carboxylic acid function; major species at pH 7.3.

name: glycylglycine 2-naphthylamide
definition: An N-(2-naphthyl)carboxamide obtained by formal condensation of the carboxy group of glycylglycine with the amino group of 2-naphthylamine.

name: glycyl-L-phenylalanine 2-naphthylamide
definition: An N-(2-naphthyl)carboxamide obtained by formal condensation of the carboxy group of glycyl-L-phenylalanine with the amino group of 2-naphthylamine.

name: glycyl-L-proline 2-naphthylamide
definition: An N-(2-naphthyl)carboxamide obtained by formal condensation of the carboxy group of glycyl-L-proline with the amino group of 2-naphthylamine.

name: very long-chain acyl-CoA(4-)
definition: An acyl-CoA(4-) obtained by deprotonation of the phosphate and diphosphate OH groups of a very-long-chain acyl-CoA; major species at pH 7.3.

name: 5-HEPE(1-)
definition: An icosanoid anion that is the conjugate base of 5-HEPE arising from deprotonation of the carboxylic acid function; major species at pH 7.3.

name: glycyl-L-tryptophan 2-naphthylamide
definition: An N-(2-naphthyl)carboxamide obtained by formal condensation of the carboxy group of glycyl-L-tryptophan with the amino group of 2-naphthylamine.

name: BMS-453
definition: A member of the class of dihydronaphthalenes that is 1,2-dihydronaphthalene which is substituted at positions 1, 1, 4, and 6 by methyl, methyl, phenyl, and 2-(p-carboxyphenyl)vinyl groups, respectively (the E isomer). It is a potent retinoic acid receptor gamma (RARbeta) agonist that acts as an antagonist against RARalpha and RARgamma.

name: dihydronaphthalenes
definition: Any carbobycyclic compound that is a dihydronaphthalene or a compound obtained from a dihydronaphthalene by formal substitution of one or more hydrogens.

name: L-leucylglycine 2-naphthylamide
definition: An N-(2-naphthyl)carboxamide obtained by formal condensation of the carboxy group of L-leucylglycine with the amino group of 2-naphthylamine.

name: retinoic acid receptor beta agonist
definition: Any retinoic acid receptor (RAR) agonist with specificity for RARbeta.

name: N-benzoyl-L-leucine 2-naphthylamide
definition: An N-(2-naphthyl)carboxamide obtained by formal condensation of the carboxy group of N-benzoyl-L-leucine with the amino group of 2-naphthylamine.

name: retinoic acid receptor gamma antagonist
definition: A retinoic acid receptor antagonist that antagonises retinoic acid receptor gamma.

name: N-benzoyl-L-valylglycine 4-methoxy-2-naphthylamide
definition: A dipeptide amide obtained by formal condensation of the carboxy group of N-benzoyl-L-valylglycine with the amino group of 4-methoxy-2-naphthylamine.

name: N-benzoyl-L-arginine 2-naphthylamide
definition: An N-{1-[(naphthalen-2-yl)amino]-1-oxo-3-phenylpropan-2-yl}benzamide that is the amide obtained by formal condensation of the carboxy group of N-benzoyl-L-arginine with the amino group of 2-naphthylamine.

name: N-carbobenzyloxy-glycylglycyl-L-arginine 2-naphthylamide
definition: An N-(2-naphthyl)carboxamide obtained by formal condensation of the carboxy group of N-carbobenzyloxy-glycylglycyl-L-arginine with the amino group of 2-naphthylamine.

name: antidote to cyanide poisoning
definition: A role borne by a molecule that acts to counteract or neutralize the deleterious effects of cyanide.

name: L-seryl-L-tyrosine 2-naphthylamide
definition: An N-(2-naphthyl)carboxamide obtained by formal condensation of the carboxy group of L-seryl-L-tyrosine with the amino group of 2-naphthylamine.

name: antidote to opioid poisoning
definition: A role borne by a molecule that acts to counteract or neutralise the deleterious effects of opioids.

name: naloxone(1+)
definition: An ammonium ion resulting from the protonation of the nitrogen of naloxone.

name: 2-deoxy-D-galactopyranose
definition: A deoxygalactose that is D-galactopyranose in which the hydroxy group at position 2 has been replaced by a hydrogen.

name: 2-deoxy-D-ribofuranose
definition: A deoxypentose that is D-ribofuranose in which the hydroxy group at position C-2 is replaced by hydrogen.

name: N-acetyl-D-glucosaminyl-N-acetylmuramoyl-L-alanyl-D-glutamyl-6-carboxy-L-lysyl-D-alanine(2-)
definition: A peptide anion obtained from N-acetyl-D-glucosaminyl-N-acetylmuramoyl-L-alanyl-D-glutamyl-6-carboxy-L-lysyl-D-alanine; major structure at pH 7.3.

name: N-acetyl-D-glucosaminyl-(1->4)-N-acetylmuramoyl-L-alanyl-D-glutamyl-6-carboxy-L-lysine(2-)
definition: A peptide anion obtained from N-acetyl-D-glucosaminyl-(1->4)-N-acetylmuramoyl-L-alanyl-D-glutamyl-6-carboxy-L-lysine. Major structure at pH 7.3

name: alpha-mannofuranuronic acid gamma-lactone
definition: A carbohydrate lactone obtained by intramolecular condensation of the 6-carboxy group with the 3-hydroxy group of alpha-mannofuranuronic acid.

name: D-glycero-D-gulo-heptopyranose
definition: An aldoheptose that is the D-glycero-diastereomer of D-gulo-heptopyranose

name: alpha-D-Manp6P-(1->3)-alpha-D-Manp-(1->3)-alpha-D-Manp-(1->3)-alpha-D-Manp-(1->2)-D-Manp
definition: An oligosaccharide phosphate consisting of four alpha(1->3)-linked D-mannose residues, with the residue at the non-reducing end carrying a phosphate group at position 6, and with that at the reducing end being alpha(1->2)-linked to a further D-mannose residue; prepared from the phosphomannan fraction of Hansenula holstii.

name: eukaryotic translation elongation factor 1alpha 1 inhibitor
definition: Any compound that inihibits the human protein, eukaryotic translation elongation factor 1alpha 1.

name: 3-[alpha-D-galactosyl-(1->6)-beta-D-galactosyl]-monooctanoyl-sn-glycerol
definition: A glycoglycerolipid that consists of 3-[alpha-D-galactosyl-(1->6)-beta-D-galactosyl]-sn-glycerol in which the glycerol portion is acylated at either position 1 or position 2 by an octanoyl group.

name: 3-(beta-D-galactosyl)monooctanoyl-sn-glycerol
definition: A galactoglycerolipid that consists of 3-(beta-D-galactosyl)-sn-glycerol in which the glycerol portion is acylated at either position 2 or position 1 by an octanoyl group.

name: 3-(beta-D-galactosyl)mono(long-chain acyl)-sn-glycerol
definition: A galactoglycerolipid that consists of a beta-D-galactosyl residue attached at position 3 of a monoacyl-sn-glycerol moiety in which the acyl group has a chain length of C12 or greater, attached either at position 1 or at position 2.

name: 12(S)-HETrE(1-)
definition: An icosanoid anion anion that is the conjugate base of 12(S)-HETrE arising from deprotonation of the carboxylic acid function; major species at pH 7.3.

name: 12(S)-HpEPE(1-)
definition: A 12-HPEPE anion that is the conjugate base of 12(S)-HpEPE arising from deprotonation of the carboxylic acid function; major species at pH 7.3.

name: 13(S)-HOTrE(1-)
definition: A polyunsaturated fatty acid anion that is the conjugate base of 13S-HOTrE arising from deprotonation of the carboxylic acid function; major species at pH 7.3.

name: 3-[alpha-D-galactosyl-(1->6)-beta-D-galactosyl]-mono(long-chain acyl)-sn-glycerol
definition: A glycoglycerolipid that consists of 3-[alpha-D-galactosyl-(1->6)-beta-D-galactosyl]-sn-glycerol in which the glycerol portion is acylated at either position 1 or position 2 by any long-chain acyl group.

name: alpha-D-Manp-(1->3)-[alpha-D-Manp-(1->6)]-alpha-D-Manp-(1->6)-[alpha-D-Manp6P-(1->2)-alpha-D-Manp-(1->3)]-beta-D-Manp-(1->4)-beta-D-GlcpNAc-(1->4)-D-GlcpNAc
definition: An oligosaccharide phosphate consisting of a linear chain of beta-D-mannose, N-acetyl-beta-D-glucosamine and N-acetyl-D-glucosamine residues all linked (1->4), to the mannose residue of which are also linked (1->3) and (1->6) respectively a 6-O-phosphono-alpha-D-mannosyl-(1->2)-alpha-D-mannosyl disaccharide unit and an alpha-D-mannosyl-(1->3)-[alpha-D-mannosyl-(1->6)]-alpha-D-mannosyl branched trisaccharide unit.

name: 11-oxo-ETE
definition: An oxoicosatetraenoic acid that is (5Z,8Z,12E,14Z)-icosatetraenoic acid bearing a single oxo substituent located at position 12.

name: C-terminal Gly-Gly(1-) residue
definition: An organic anionic group obtained by deprotonation of deprotonation of the phosphate OH group of C-terminal Gly-Gly residue

name: S-substituted glutathione(1-)
definition: A peptide anion obtained by deprotonation of the carboxy groups and concomitant protonation of the amino group of any S-substituted glutathione. Major structure at pH 7.3

name: AKT1 kinase inhibitor
definition: A serine/threonine kinase inhibitor that specifically inhibits RAC-alpha serine/threonine-protein kinase (ATK1).

name: 13-oxo-9Z,11E-ODE(1-)
definition: A polyunsaturated fatty acid anion that is the conjugate base of 13-oxo-9Z,11E-ODE, arising from deprotonation of the carboxylic acid function; major species at pH 7.3.

name: C-terminal proteinogenic amino-acid residue(1-)
definition: An alpha-amino-acid residue anion obtained by deprotonation of the carboxy group of any C-terminal proteinogenic amino acid.

name: C-terminal S-(Gly-Gly)-L-Cys zwitterion residue
definition: A zwitterionic group obtained by transfer of a proton from the carboxy to the amino group of C-terminal S-(Gly-Gly)-L-Cys residue; major species at pH 7.3.

name: aurachin B(1-)
definition: An organic cation that is the conjugate base of aurachin B, obtained by deprotonation of the 3-hydroxy group. It is the major microspecies at pH 7.3 (according to Marvin v 6.2.0.).

name: lasalocid sodium
definition: The sodium salt of lasalocid. It is a veterinary ionophore antibiotic used for prevention and treatment of coccidiosis in poultry.

name: rhaponticin
definition: A stilbenoid that is rhapontigenin substituted at position 3 by a beta-D-glucosyl group.

name: lasalocid
definition: A polyether antibiotic used for prevention and treatment of coccidiosis in poultry.

name: SL-327
definition: A nitrile that is acrylonitrile in which the hydrogen attached to the same carbon as the cyano group has been replaced by an o-(trifluoromethyl)phenyl group, while the remaining hydrogens of the ethenyl group have been replaced by amino and (4-aminophenyl)sulfanyl groups. The configuration of the double bond is not specified. It is an inhibitor of MEK1 and MEK2.

name: LY-165163
definition: A N-arylpiperazine that is piperazine susbtituted by 2-(4-aminophenyl)ethyl and 3-(trifluoromethyl)phenyl groups at positions 1 and 4, respectively. It is a selective 5-HT1A serotonin receptor agonist and 5-HT1D serotonin receptor antagonist.

name: SU4312
definition: A member of the class of oxindoles that is 3-methyleneoxindole in which one of the hydrogens of the methylene group has been replaced by a p-(dimethylamino)phenyl group.  SU 4312 is a vascular endothelial growth factor (VEGF) receptor protein tyrosine kinase 1/2 and platelet derived growth factor (PDGF) receptor inhibitor. It also inhibits the neuronal nitric oxide synthase (NOS) and exhibits neuroprotection against NO-mediated neurotoxicity.

name: xylazine
definition: A methyl benzene that is 1,3-dimethylbenzene which is substituted by a 5,6-dihydro-4H-1,3-thiazin-2-ylnitrilo group at position 2. It is an alpha2 adrenergic receptor agonist and frequently used in veterinary medicine as an emetic and sedative with analgesic and muscle relaxant properties.

name: N,N'-bis(diphenylmethyl)ethane-1,2-diamine
definition: A diamine that is ethane-1,2-diamine in which both amino groups are substituted by diphenylmethyl groups. It is an allosteric agonist of the metabotropic glutamate receptor 7 (mGluR7).

name: ketotifen
definition: An organic heterotricyclic compound that is 4,9-dihydro-10H-benzo[4,5]cyclohepta[1,2-b]thiophen-10-one which is substituted at position 4 by a 1-methylpiperidin-4-ylidene group. A blocker of histamine H1 receptors with a stabilising action on mast cells, it is used (usually as its hydrogen fumarate salt) for the treatment of asthma, where it may take several weeks to exert its full effect.

name: kenpaullone
definition: An indolobenzazepine that is paullone in which the hydrogen at position 9 is replaced by a bromo substituent. It is an ATP-competitive inhibitor of cyclin-dependent kinases (CDKs) and glycogen synthase kinase 3beta (GSK3beta).

name: etamivan
definition: Phenol substituted at C-2 and C-4 by a methoxy group and an N,N-diethylaminocarbonyl group respectively. A respiratory stimulant drug related to nikethamide, it has now fallen largely into disuse.

name: N-benzylquinazolin-4-amine
definition: A member of the class of quinazolines that is quinazoline which is substituted by a benzylnitrilo group at position 4.

name: ML228
definition: A member of the class of 1,2,4-triazines in which the triazine ring is substituted at positions 3, 5, and 6 by pyridin-2-yl, ([biphenyl]-4-ylmethyl)amin, and methyl groups, respectively. It is an activator of the hypoxia inducible factor (HIF) pathway.

name: 1,2,3,4,5,6-hexabromocyclohexane
definition: A bromohydrocarbon that is cyclohexane in which the hydrogen at positions 1,2,3,4,5 and 6 have been replaced by bromo groups. It is a potent inhibitor of JAK2 tyrosine kinase autophosphorylation.

name: sulfaguanidine
definition: A sulfonamide incorporating a guanidine moiety used to block the synthesis of folic acid; mostly used in veterinary medicine

name: LY404039
definition: An organic heterobicyclic compound that is (1S,5R)-2-thiabicyclo[3.1.0]hexane carrying oxo, oxo, amino, carboxy, and carboxy groups at positions 2, 2, 4S, 4S, and 6S, respectively. It is a potent agonist of group II metabotropic glutamate receptors mGluR2 mGluR3 (Ki = 149 nM and 92 nM, respectively) and exhibits antipsychotic and anxiolytic efficacy in animal models.

name: orlistat
definition: A carboxylic ester resulting from the formal condensation of the carboxy group of N-formyl-L-leucine with the hydroxy group of (3S,4S)-3-hexyl-4-[(2S)-2-hydroxytridecyl]oxetan-2-one. A pancreatic lipase inhibitor, it is used as an anti-obesity drug.

name: doxofylline
definition: An oxopurine that is a derivative of xanthine, methylated at N-1 and N-3 and carrying a 1,3-dioxolan-2-ylmethyl group at N-7, used in the treatment of asthma.

name: 1,1,1-propanetricarboxylic acid
definition: A acid that is propane in which three carboxy groups are attached at the C-1 position.

name: N-succinimidyl 5-(3-azidopropylamino)-5-oxopentanoate
definition: An N-hydroxysuccinimide ester derived from  5-(3-azidopropylamino)-5-oxopentanoic acid.

name: 5-(3-azidopropylamino)-5-oxopentanoic acid
definition: An oxo monocarboxylic acid in which pentanoic acid is substituted at C-5 with an oxo group and a 3-azidopropylamino group.

name: 5-chlorospiro[indole-3,2'-[1,3]oxathiolan]-2(1H)-one
definition: A monothioketal formed from 5-chloro-1H-indole-2,3-dione. It has been studied for its anticonvulsant properties.

name: (S)-1,2-di-O-dodecanylglycero-3-glutaric acid 6'-methylresorufin ester
definition: A diester obtained by formal condensation of the carboxy groups of glutaric acid with the hydroxy groups of (S)-1,2-di-O-dodecanylglycerol and 7-hydroxy-6-methylphenoxazin-3-one.

name: viteagnusin I
definition: A labdane diterpenoid that is isolated from the fruits of Vitex agnus-castus.

name: 15-HPETE
definition: A HPETE that consists of (5Z,8Z,11Z,13E)-icosatetraenoic acid in which the hydroperoxy group is located at position 15.

name: 13-HPODE
definition: An HPODE (hydroperoxyoctadecadienoic acid) in which the double bonds are at positions 9 and 11 (E and Z  geometry, respectively) and the hydroperoxy group is at position 13.

name: pyrrolysine
definition: An N-acyl-amino acid that is lysine in which one of the amino nitrogens at position N6 is replaced by a 3-methyl-3,4-dihydro-2H-pyrrole-2-carbonyl group.

name: (7Z,10Z,13R,14E,16Z,19Z)-13-hydroxydocosapentaenoic acid
definition: A polyunsaturated hydroxy fatty acid that consists of (7Z,10Z,14E,16Z,19Z)-docosapentaenoic acid bearing a single hydroxy substituent at the 13R-position.

name: N-butyl-N-(4-hydroxybutyl)nitrosamine
definition: A nitrosamine that has butyl and 4-hydroxybutyl substituents. In mice, it causes high-grade, invasive cancers in the urinary bladder, but not in any other tissues.

name: saintopin
definition: A member of the class of tetracenequinones that is tetracene-5,12-dione in which the hydrogens at positions 1, 3, 8, 10, and 11 have been replaced by hydroxy groups. Isolated from Paecilomyces.

name: alpha-D-Man-(1->3)-beta-D-Man-(1->4)-beta-D-GlcNAc
definition: An amino trisaccharide consisting of two D-mannose residues, linked alpha(1->3), and an N-acetyl-D-glucosamine residue, linked alpha(1->4), at the reducing end. An intermediate glycan structure of glycosylated proteins

name: alpha-D-Man-(1->3)-[alpha-D-Man-(1->6)]-beta-D-Man-(1->4)-beta-D-GlcNAc
definition: A branched amino tetrasaccharide comprised of an alpha-D-mannosyl residue linked (1->6) to the middle mannose of alpha-D-Man-(1->3)-beta-D-Man-(1->4)-beta-D-GlcNAc. An intermediate glycan structure of glycosylated proteins.

name: alpha-D-Man-(1->3)-[alpha-D-Man-(1->3)-[alpha-D-Man-(1->6)]-alpha-D-Man-(1->6)]-beta-D-Man-(1->4)-beta-D-GlcNAc
definition: A six-membered branched glucosamine oligosaccharide consisting of five D-mannosyl residues and one N-acetylglucosamine residue (the latter being located at the reducing end). An intermediate glycan structure of glycosylated proteins.

name: alpha-D-Man-(1->2)-alpha-D-Man-(1->3)-[alpha-D-Man-(1->2)-alpha-D-Man-(1->3)-[alpha-D-Man-(1->2)-alpha-D-Man-(1->6)]-alpha-D-Man-(1->6)]-beta-D-Man-(1->4)-beta-D-GlcNAc
definition: A nine-membered branched glucosamine oligosaccharide consisting of eight D-mannosyl residues and one N-acetylglucosamine residue (the latter being located at the reducing end). An intermediate glycan structure of glycosylated proteins.

name: alpha-D-Man-(1->2)-alpha-D-Man-(1->2)-alpha-D-Man-(1->3)-[alpha-D-Man-(1->3)-[alpha-D-Man-(1->2)-alpha-D-Man-(1->6)]-alpha-D-Man-(1->6)]-beta-D-Man-(1->4)-beta-D-GlcNAc
definition: A nine-membered branched glucosamine oligosaccharide consisting of eight D-mannosyl residues and one N-acetylglucosamine residue (the latter being located at the reducing end). An intermediate glycan structure of glycosylated proteins.

name: alpha-D-Man-(1->2)-alpha-D-Man-(1->2)-alpha-D-Man-(1->3)-[alpha-D-Man-(1->6)-[alpha-D-Man-(1->2)-alpha-D-Man-(1->3)]-alpha-D-Man-(1->6)]-beta-D-Man-(1->4)-beta-D-GlcNAc
definition: A nine-membered branched glucosamine oligosaccharide consisting of eight D-mannosyl residues and one N-acetylglucosamine residue (the latter being located at the reducing end). An intermediate glycan structure of glycosylated proteins.

name: alpha-D-Man-(1->2)-alpha-D-Man-(1->2)-alpha-D-Man-(1->3)-[alpha-D-Man-(1->2)-alpha-D-Man-(1->3)-[alpha-D-Man-(1->2)-alpha-D-Man-(1->6)]-alpha-D-Man-(1->6)]-beta-D-Man-(1->4)-beta-D-GlcNAc
definition: A ten-membered branched glucosamine oligosaccharide consisting of nine D-mannosyl residues and one N-acetylglucosamine residue (the latter being located at the reducing end). An intermediate glycan structure of glycosylated proteins

name: 5(S),15(S)-DiHETE
definition: A DiHETE that is (6E,8Z,11Z,13E)-icosatetraenoic acid in which the two hydroxy substituents are placed at the 5S- and 15S-positions.

name: (5S)-hydroperoxy-18-hydroxy-EPE
definition: An icosanoid that is (6E,8Z,11Z,14Z,16E)-icosa-6,8,11,14,16-pentaenoic acid substituted at positions 5S and 18 by hydroperoxy and hydroxy groups respectively.

name: O-octenedioylcarnitine
definition: An O-acylcarnitine obtained by formal condensation of one of the carboxy groups of any octenedioic acid with the hydroxy group of carnitine.

name: O-octadecadiendioylcarnitine
definition: An O-acylcarnitine obtained by formal condensation of one of the carboxy groups of any  octadecadiendioic acid with the hydroxy group of carnitine.

name: O-[(3R,11Z,14Z)-3-hydroxyicosadienoyl]carnitine
definition: An O-acylcarnitine in which the O-acyl group is specified as (3R,11Z,14Z)-3-hydroxyicosadienoyl.

name: bacteriochlorophyllide g
definition: A chlorophyllide obtained by hydrolysis of the terpenoid ester moiety of bacteriochlorophyll g.

name: alpha-Neu5Ac-(2->8)-alpha-Neu5Ac-(2->3)-beta-D-Gal-(1<->1')-N-acylsphingosine
definition: A sialomonoglycosylceramide that consists of an alpha-Neu5Ac-(2->8)-alpha-Neu5Ac-(2->3)-beta-D-Gal moiety attached via a glycosidic bond at position 1 of N-acylsphingosine.

name: 14-oxo-DoHE
definition: An oxo fatty acid that consists of (4Z,7Z,10Z,12E,16Z,19Z)-docosahexaenoic acid carrying a single oxo substituent at position 14.

name: 12,18-dihydroxyoctadecanoate
definition: A hydroxy fatty acid anion that is the conjugate base of 12,18-dihydroxyoctadecanoic acid, obtained by deprotonation of the carboxy group; major species at pH 7.3.

name: ricinoleate
definition: A hydroxy fatty acid anion that is the conjugate base of ricinoleic acid, obtained by deprotonation of the carboxy group; major species at pH 7.3.

name: lysophosphatidylethanolamine 18:2
definition: A lysophosphatidylethanolamine in which the acyl group (position not specified) contains 18 carbons and 2 double bonds.

name: lysophosphatidylcholine(0:0/16:0)
definition: A 2-acyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphocholine in which the 2-acyl group contains 16 carbons and is fully saturated.

name: lysophosphatidylcholine(0:0/16:1)
definition: A 2-acyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphocholine in which the 2-acyl group contains 16 carbons and 1 double bond.

name: lysophosphatidylcholine(0:0/18:0)
definition: A 2-acyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphocholine in which the 2-acyl group contains 18 carbons and is fully saturated.

name: (9Z,12R)-12,18-dihydroxyoctadecenoate
definition: A hydroxy fatty acid anion that is the conjugate base of (9Z,12R)-12,18-dihydroxyoctadecenoic acid, obtained by deprotonation of the carboxy group; major species at pH 7.3.

name: 5,20-diHEPE(1-)
definition: An icosanoid anion that is the conjugate base of 5,20-di-HEPE arising from deprotonation of the carboxylic acid group; major species at pH 7.3.

name: lysophosphatidylcholine(0:0/18:2)
definition: A 2-acyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphocholine in which the 2-acyl group contains 18 carbons and 2 double bonds.

name: lysophosphatidylcholine(0:0/20:4)
definition: A 2-acyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphocholine in which the 2-acyl group contains 20 carbons and 4 double bonds.

name: lysophosphatidylcholine(0:0/20:5)
definition: A 2-acyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphocholine in which the 2-acyl group contains 20 carbons and 5 double bonds.

name: lysophosphatidylcholine(16:1/0:0)
definition: A 1-acyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphocholine in which the 1-acyl group contains 16 carbons and 1 double bond.

name: (20S,23)-dihydroxyvitamin D3
definition: A hydroxycalciol that consists of vitamin D3 (calciol) carrying additional hydroxy groups  at positions 20 (with S-configuration) and 23.

name: (20S,23,24)-trihydroxyvitamin D3
definition: A hydroxycalciol that consists of vitamin D3 (calciol) carrying additional hydroxy groups  at positions 20 (with S-configuration), 23 and 24.

name: (20S,23,25)-trihydroxyvitamin D3
definition: A hydroxycalciol that consists of vitamin D3 (calciol) carrying additional hydroxy groups at positions 20 (with S-configuration), 23 and 25.

name: lysophosphatidylcholine(18:2/0:0)
definition: A 1-acyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphocholine in which the 1-acyl group contains 18 carbons and 2 double bonds.

name: lysophosphatidylcholine(20:4/0:0)
definition: A 1-acyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphocholine in which the 1-acyl group contains 20 carbons and 4 double bonds.

name: 1-icosapentaenoyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphocholine
definition: A 1-acyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphocholine in which the 1-acyl group contains 20 carbons and 5 double bonds.

name: lysophosphatidylcholine 22:4
definition: A lysophosphatidylcholine in which the acyl group (position not specified) contains 22 carbons and 4 double bonds.

name: lysophosphatidylcholine(18:0/0:0)
definition: A 1-acyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphocholine in which the 1-acyl group contains 18 carbons and is fully saturated.

name: 2-methylbutanedioic acid
definition: A dicarboxylic acid that is butanedioic acid substituted at position 2 by a methyl group.

name: (S)-methylsuccinic acid
definition: A 2-methylbutanedioic acid in which the methyl group at position 2 has S-configuration.

name: (R)-methylsuccinic acid
definition: A 2-methylbutanedioic acid in which the methyl group at position 2 has R-configuration.

name: (R)-oleoylcarnitine hydrochloride
definition: A quaternary ammonium salt obtained by combining (R)-oleoylcarnitine with one molar equivalent of hydrogen chloride.

name: phosphatidylethanolamine O-39:5
definition: An alkyl,acyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphoethanolamine in which the alkyl or acyl groups at positions 1 and 2 contain a total of 39 carbons and 5 double bonds.

name: phosphatidylcholine O-33:2
definition: An alkyl,acyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphocholine in which the alkyl or acyl groups at positions 1 and 2 contain a total of 33 carbons and 2 double bonds.

name: phosphatidylcholine 35:4
definition: A 1,2-diacyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphocholine in which the acyl groups at C-1 and C-2 contain 35 carbons in total with 4 double bonds.

name: laureth-5
definition: A hydroxypolyether that is pentaethylene glycol in which one of the terminal hydrogens is replaced by a dodecyl group.

name: 4-(2,6-dichlorobenzamido)-N-(piperidin-4-yl)-pyrazole-3-carboxamide
definition: A member of the class of pryrazoles that is 4-amino-1H-pyrazole-3-carboxylic acid in which the primary amino group has been acylated by a 2,6-dichlorobenzoyl group and in which the carboxylic acid has been converted into a carboxamide by formal condensation with the primary amino group of 4-aminopiperidine.

name: 2-methoxy-N-[3-[4-[3-methyl-4-[(6-methyl-3-pyridinyl)oxy]anilino]-6-quinazolinyl]prop-2-enyl]acetamide
definition: A member of the class of quinazolines that is quinazoline substituted by {3-methyl-4-[(6-methylpyridin-3-yl)oxy]phenyl}amino and 3-(2-methoxyacetamido)prop-1-en-1-yl groups at positions 4 and 6, respectively.

name: AZD-1152
definition: A member of the of quinazolines that is 4-aminoquinazolin-7-ol in which the amino group at position 4 has been substituted by a 5-[2-(3-fluoroanilino)-2-oxoethyl]-1H-pyrazol-3-yl group, while the hydroxy group at position 7 has been converted into the corresponding 3-[ethyl(2-hydroxyethyl)aminopropyl ether.

name: ZM447439
definition: A member of the class of quinazolines that is quinazoline which is substituted at positions 4, 6 and 7 by a (4-benzamidophenyl)nitrilo group, methoxy group and a 3-(morpholin-4-yl)propoxy group, respectively. It is an ATP-competitive inhibitor of Aurora A and Aurora B kinases with IC50 of 110 nM and 130 nM, respectively.

name: PF-00477736
definition: A diazepinoindole that is 8-amino-4,5-dihydro-6H-[1,2]diazepino[4,5,6-cd]indol-6-one which is substituted at position 2 by a 1-methylpyrazol-4-yl group and in which the amino group at position 8 has undergone condensation with the carboxy group of (2R)-2-cyclohexylglycine to give the corresponding carboxamide. It is an inhibitor of checkpoint kinase 1 (Chk 1).

name: N-(5-{[(5-tert-butyl-1,3-oxazol-2-yl)methyl]sulfanyl}-1,3-thiazol-2-yl)piperidine-4-carboxamide
definition: A secondary carboxamide resulting from the formal condensation of the carboxy group of piperidine-4-carboxylic acid with the amino group of 5-{[(5-tert-butyl-1,3-oxazol-2-yl)methyl]sulfanyl}-1,3-thiazol-2-amine. It is an ATP-competitive inhibitor of CDK2, CDK7 and CDK9 kinases and exhibits anti-cancer properties.

name: momelotinib
definition: A benzamide obtained by formal condensation of the carboxy group of 4-{2-[4-(morpholin-4-yl)anilino]pyrimidin-4-yl}benzoic acid with the primary amino group of aminoacetonitrile. It is an ATP-competitive JAK1/JAK2 inhibitor with IC50 of 11 nM and 18 nM, respectively. Used for the treatment of patients with intermediate- or high-risk myelofibrosis.

name: linifanib
definition: A member of the class of phenylureas that is urea in which one of the nitrogens is substituted by a 2-fluoro-5-methylphenyl group, while the other is substituted by a p-(3-amino-1H-indazol-4-yl)phenyl group. It is a potent, selective inhibitor of vascular endothelial growth factor and platelet-derived growth factor receptor tyrosine kinases.

name: [2-methoxy-5-({[2-(2,4,6-trimethoxyphenyl)ethenyl]sulfonyl}methyl)anilino]acetate
definition: A monocarboxylic acid anion that is the conjugate base of N-[2-methoxy-5-({[2-(2,4,6-trimethoxyphenyl)ethenyl]sulfonyl}methyl)phenyl]glycine, obtained by the deprotonation of the carboxy group. The major species at pH 7.3.

name: KN-93
definition: A sulfonamide resulting from the formal condensation of p-methoxybenzenesulfonic acid with the anilino nitrogen of 2-(aminomethyl)-N-(2-hydroxyethyl)aniline in which the hydrogens of the primary amino group have been replaced by methyl and p-chlorocinnamyl groups. KN-93 is a selective inhibitor of  Ca(2+)/calmodulin-dependent protein kinase II.

name: 1-(6-chloro-5-fluoroindol-1-yl)-propan-2-amine
definition: A member of the class of indoles that is 6-chloro-5-fluoroindole in which the hydrogen attached to the nitrogen has been replaced by a 2-aminopropyl group.

name: 4-[2-[[1-hydroxy-1-(4-hydroxyphenyl)propan-2-yl]amino]ethyl]phenol
definition: A secondary amino compound that is 4-(2-amino-1-hydroxypropyl)phenol in which one of the hydrogens attached to the nitrogen is replaced by a 2-(4-hydroxyphenyl)ethyl group.

name: eliprodil
definition: A racemate comprising equimolar amounts of (R)- and (S)-eliprodil. It is a non-competitive N-methyl-D-aspartate (NMDA) receptor antagonist and an anti-ischaemic agent that exhibits neuroprotective properties.

name: 2-(4-hydroxy-3,5-dimethoxyphenyl)-3-(hydroxymethyl)-2,3-dihydro-7H-pyrano[2,3-g][1,4]benzodioxin-7-one
definition: A pyranobenzodioxin obtained by formal cyclocodensation between syringylglycerol and esculetin. It is found in Arabidopsis thaliana.

name: PD-153035(1+)

name: 5-aminofluorescein
definition: A primary amino compound that is fluorescein carrying an amino substituent at C-5. Building block/intermediate for the synthesis of the fluorescent dye flourescein; also used to produce N-(fluorescein-5-yl)maleamic acid.

name: purinergic receptor P2 antagonist
definition: An antagonist at purinergic P2 receptors

name: tetrasodium 5'-phosphonatopyridoxal-6-azobenzene-2,4-disulfonate
definition: An organic sodium salt that is the tetrasodium salt of 5'-phosphopyridoxal-6-azobenzene-2,4-disulfonic acid

name: purinergic receptor P2X antagonist
definition: An antagonist at purinergic P2X receptors

name: 5'-phosphonatopyridoxal-6-azobenzene-2,4-disulfonate
definition: An organophosphate oxoanion obtained by deprotonation of the phospho and sulfo groups of 5'-phosphopyridoxal-6-azobenzene-2,4-disulfonic acid.

name: semaxanib
definition: An oxindole that is 3-methyleneoxindole in which one of the hydrogens of the methylene group is replaced by a 3,5-dimethylpyrrol-2-yl group.

name: beta-aminopropionitrile hemifumarate
definition: A fumarate salt prepared from beta-aminopropionitrile by reaction of one molecule of fumaric acid for every two molecules of beta-aminopropionitrile.

name: collagen cross-linking inhibitor
definition: Any compound that inhibits collagen cross-linking.

name: beta-ammoniopropionitrile
definition: A primary ammonium ion obtained by protonation of the amino function of beta-aminopropionitrile.

name: Solvent yellow 56
definition: An azobenzene that is N,N-diethylaniline substituted at position 4 by a phenylazo group.

name: orantinib
definition: An oxindole that is 3-methyleneoxindole in which one of the hydrogens of the methylene group is substituted by a 2-(2-carboxyethyl)-3,5-dimethylpyrrol-3-yl group. It is an ATP-competitive inhibitor of the tyrosine kinase activity of fibroblast growth factor receptor 1.

name: CMP-8-amino-3,8-dideoxy-alpha-D-manno-oct-2-ulosonate(1-)
definition: A nucleotide-sugar oxoanion that is the conjugate base of CMP-8-amino-3,8-dideoxy-alpha-D-manno-oct-2-ulosonic acid; major species at pH 7.3.

name: charcoal
definition: A mixture that is the black porous residue, consisting of carbon and any remaining ash, obtained by pyrolysis of animal or vegetable matter in a limited supply of air.

name: CHIR 99021
definition: A member of the class of aminopyrimidines that is 2-aminopyrimidine substituted at positions N2, 5 and 6 by (5-cyanopyridin-2-yl)ethyl, 4-methylimidazol-2-yl and 2,4-dichlorophenyl groups respectively.

name: EC 2.7.11.26 (tau-protein kinase) inhibitor
definition: An EC 2.7.11.* (protein-serine/threonine kinase) inhibitor that interferes with the action of tau-protein kinase inhibitor (EC 2.7.11.26).

name: SB 415286
definition: A member of the class of maleimides carrying 3-chloro-4-hydroxyphenylamino and 2-nitrophenyl substituents at positions 3 and 4 respectively.

name: SB 431542
definition: A member of the class of benzamides that is 4-(imidazol-2-yl)benzamide carrying additional 1,3-benzodioxol-5-yl and pyridin-2-yl substituents at positions 4 and 5 respectively on the imidazole ring.

name: 3-methyl-4-oxo-1,2,3,4-tetrahydroquinoline-2-carbaldehyde
definition: An amino aldehyde that is 1,2,3,4-tetrahydroquinoline which is substituted at positions 2, 3, and 4 by formyl, methyl, and oxo groups, respectively.

name: o-aminoacetophenone
definition: An aromatic ketone that is acetophenone in which one of the ortho hydrogens of the phenyl group has been replaced by an amino group.

name: rac-1,2-di-O-dodecanylglycero-3-glutaric acid 6'-methylresorufin ester
definition: A racemate comprising equal amounts of (R)- and (S)-1,2-di-O-dodecanylglycero-3-glutaric acid 6'-methylresorufin ester. A fluorescent substrate used to study lipase activity in vitro.

name: N-butyl-N-(3-carboxypropyl)nitrosamine
definition: A nitrosamine that has butyl and 4-carboxybutyl substituents. It is the principal metabolite of the bladder carcinogen N-butyl-N-(4-hydroxybutyl)nitrosamine (BHBN-4).

name: 4-(dimethylamino)benzaldehyde
definition: A member of the class of benzaldehydes that is benzaldehyde carrying a dimethylamino substituent at position 4. Used as an indicator for detection of indoles and hydrazine.

name: 4-methylumbelliferyl alpha-D-galactoside
definition: An alpha-D-galactoside having a 4-methylumbelliferyl substituent at the anomeric position

name: 4-methylumbelliferyl beta-D-galactoside
definition: A beta-D-galactoside having a 4-methylumbelliferyl substituent at the anomeric position.

name: 4-methylumbelliferyl beta-D-glucoside
