name: 3,3',5,5'-tetrabromobisphenol A
definition: A bromobisphenol that is 4,4'-methanediyldiphenol in which the methylene hydrogens are replaced by two methyl groups and the phenyl rings are substituted by bromo groups at positions 2, 2', 6 and 6'. It is a brominated flame retardant.

name: 3-monobromobisphenol A
definition: a

name: atom
definition: A chemical entity constituting the smallest component of an element having the chemical properties of the element.

name: gamma-tocotrienol
definition: A tocotrienol that is chroman-6-ol substituted by methyl groups at positions 2, 7 and 8 and a farnesyl chain at position 2. A vitamin E family member that has potent anti-cancer properties against a wide-range of cancers.

name: antimicrobial agent
definition: A substance that kills or slows the growth of microorganisms, including bacteria, viruses, fungi and protozoans.

name: carboxylic ester
definition: An ester of a carboxylic acid, R(1)C(=O)OR(2), where R(1) = H or organyl and R(2) = organyl.

name: arabinonic acid
definition: a

name: idonate
definition: a

name: catecholamine
definition: 4-(2-Aminoethyl)pyrocatechol [4-(2-aminoethyl)benzene-1,2-diol] and derivatives formed by substitution.

name: 4-methylthio-2-oxobutanoic acid
definition: A 2-oxo monocarboxylic acid derived from L-methionine via the action of methionine transaminase.

name: carboxylic acid
definition: A carbon oxoacid acid carrying at least one -C(=O)OH group and having the structure RC(=O)OH, where R is any any monovalent functional group. Carboxylic acids are the most common type of organic acid.

name: cytosin1-yl group
definition: An organic group obtained by removal of the hydrogen attached to the nitrogen at position 1 from cytosine.

name: gedunin
definition: A pentacyclic triterpenoid natural product found  particularly in Azadirachta indica and Cedrela odorata.

name: (2S)-poncirin
definition: A  flavanone glycoside that is  4'-methoxy-5,7-dihydroxyflavanone attached to a neohesperidose (alpha-L-rhamnopyranosyl-(1->2)-beta-D-glucopyranose) residue via a glycosidic linkage. It has been isolated from the fruits of Poncirus trifoliata and exhibits inhibitory activity against liopolysaccharide (LPS)-induced prostaglandin E2 and interleukin-6 (IL-6) production.

name: alpha-D-Gal-(1->3)-beta-D-Gal-(1->4)-beta-D-GlcNAc-(1->2)-alpha-D-Man-(1->3)-[alpha-D-Gal-(1->3)-beta-D-Gal-(1->4)-beta-D-GlcNAc-(1->2)-alpha-D-Man-(1->6)]-beta-D-Man-(1->4)-beta-D-GlcNAc-(1->4)-beta-D-GlcNAc
definition: An amino oligosaccharide that is a undecasaccharide derivative in which two tetrasaccharide branches, each formed from alpha-D-galactosyl-(1->3)-beta-D-galactosyl-(1->4)-N-acetyl-beta-D-glucosaminyl-(1->2)-alpha-D-mannose, are linked (1->3) and (1->6) to the mannose residue of a trisaccharide chain consisting of mannose and two N-acetylglucosamine residues all linked beta(1->4) with a beta-configuration of the anomeric carbon of the N-acetylglucosamine residue at the reducing end.

name: (E)-2-epi-beta-caryophyllene
definition: A sesquiterpene with a [7.2.0]-bicyclic structure comprising fused 9- and 4-membered rings, with a cis-ring junction, a methylidene group at position 9, and methyl groups at positions 3, 11, and 11.

name: 13-oxo-9Z,11E-ODE
definition: An oxooctadecadienoic acid that consists of 9Z,11E-octadecadienoic acid bearing an additional 13-keto substituent. In addtion it has been found as a natural product found in Carthamus oxyacantha.

name: longirostrerone A
definition: An  azaphilone that is 9,9a-dihydro-6H-furo[2,3-h]isochromene-6,8(6aH)-dione substituted by a 4-hydroxy-2-methyl-6-oxocyclohexyl group at position 3, a methyl group at position 6a and a 4,6,8-trimethyldeca-2,4-dienoyl group at position 9. Isolated from Chaetomium longirostre, it exhibits cytotoxic and antimalarial activities.

name: longirostrerone C
definition: An azaphilone that is 9,9a-dihydro-6H-furo[2,3-h]isochromene-6,8(6aH)-dione substituted by a 6-methyl-2-oxocyclohex-3-en-1-yl group at position 3, a methyl group at position 6a and a 4,6,8-trimethyldeca-2,4-dienoyl group at position 9. Isolated from Chaetomium longirostre, it exhibits cytotoxic and antimalarial activities.

name: cannabidiol
definition: An cannabinoid that is cyclohexene which is substituted by a methyl group at position 1, a 2,6-dihydroxy-4-pentylphenyl group at position 3, and a prop-1-en-2-yl group at position 4.

name: isovitexin 8-C-beta-glucoside
definition: A C-glycosyl compound that is isovitexin in which the hydrogen at position 8 is replaced by a beta-D-glucosyl residue.

name: akuammicine
definition: A monoterpenoid indole alkaloid with formula C20H22N2O2, isolated from several plant species including Alstonia spatulata, Catharanthus roseus and Vinca major.

name: phenazopyridine
definition: A diaminopyridine that is 2,6-diaminopyridine substituted at position 3 by a phenylazo group. A local anesthetic that has topical analgesic effect on mucosa lining of the urinary tract. Its use is limited by problems with toxicity (primarily blood disorders) and potential carcinogenicity.

name: 1-hexadecanoyl-2-(9Z,12Z-octadecadienoyl)-sn-glycero-3-phosphocholine
definition: A phosphatidylcholine 34:2 in which the 1- and 2-acyl groups are specified as hexadecanoyl (palmitoyl) and 9Z,12Z-octadecadienoyl (linoleoyl) respectively.

name: gamma-Glu-Gln
definition: A dipeptide obtained by formal condensation of the gamma-carboxy group of glutamic acid with the amino group of glutamine

name: PPARbeta/delta agonist
definition: A PPAR modulator which activates the peroxisome proliferator-activated receptor-beta/delta.

name: 1-tetradecanoyl-2-(11Z-octadecenoyl)-sn-glycero-3-phosphocholine
definition: A phosphatidylcholine 32:1 in which the acyl groups at C-1 and C-2 are tetradecanoyl and (11Z)-octadec-11-enoyl respectively.

name: 16-carboxy-17,18,19,20-tetranor-leukotriene E3
definition: An icosanoid that is leukotriene E4 in which the non-conjugated double bond has been reduced to a single bond and four methylene groups have been lost from the resulting carboxyalkyl chain.

name: 5,6-dihydrouridine 5'-monophosphate
definition: A uridine 5'-phosphate that is the 5,6-dihydro derivative of uridine 5'-monophosphate.

name: Pro-Hyp
definition: A dipeptide composed of L-proline and L-hydroxyproline residues. It is a biomarker for bone collagen degradation.

name: peonidin 3-O-beta-D-glucoside
definition: An anthocyanin cation that is the 3-O-beta-D-glucoside of peonidin (methylcyanidin).

name: rhamnetin
definition: A monomethoxyflavone that is quercetin methylated at position 7.

name: 1-myristoyl-2-oleoyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphatidylglycerol(1-)
definition: A 1,2-diacyl-sn-glycero-3-phospho-(1'-sn-glycerol)(1-) in which the 1- and 2-acyl groups are specified as myristoyl and oleoyl respectively; major species at pH 7.3.

name: beta-D-galactosyl-(1->4)-beta-D-glucosyl-N-(hexacosanoyl)sphingosine
definition: A beta-D-galactosyl-(1->4)-beta-D-glucosylceramide where the ceramide N-acyl group is specified as hexacosanoyl.

name: 2-tetradecanoylglycerol
definition: A 2-monoglyceride where the acyl group is tetradecanoyl (myristoyl).

name: 4-O-sinapoylquinic acid
definition: A cinnamate ester obtained by formal condensation of the carboxy group of sinapic acid with the 4-hydroxy group of (-)-quinic acid.

name: mammalian metabolite
definition: Any animal metabolite produced during a metabolic reaction in mammals.

name: 2'-3'-cGAMP
definition: A cyclic purine dinucleotide that consists of AMP and GMP units cyclised via 3',5'- and 2',5'-linkages respectively.

name: 1-(beta-D-galactosyl)-N-behenoylsphingosine
definition: A D-galactosyl-N-acylsphingosine where the ceramide N-acyl group is docosananoyl and the D-galactosyl component has beta anomeric configuration.

name: thioflavine T
definition: An organic chloride salt having 2-[4-(dimethylamino)phenyl]-3,6-dimethyl-1,3-benzothiazol-3-ium as the counterion. It is widely used to visualise and quantify the presence of amyloids, both in vitro and in vivo.

name: 1-alkyl-3-acylglycerol
definition: A monoglyceride in which the acyl group is located at position 3 with an additional alkyl substituent at position 1.

name: notoginsenoside R1
definition: A ginsenoside found in Panax notoginseng that is dammarane which is substituted by hydroxy groups at the 3beta, 6alpha, 12beta and 20 pro-S positions, in which the hydroxy groups at positions 6 and 20 have been converted to the corresponding beta-D-xylopyranosyl-(1->2)-beta-D-glucopyranoside and beta-D-glucopyranoside respectively, and in which a double bond has been introduced at the 24-25 position.

name: carminic acid
definition: A tetrahydroxyanthraquinone that is that is 1,3,4,6-tetrahydroxy-9,10-anthraquinone substituted by a methyl group at position 8, a carboxy group at position 7 and a 1,5-anhydro-D-glucitol moiety at position 2 via a C-glycosidic linkage. It is a natural dye isolated from several insects such as Dactylopius coccus.

name: fluorometholone acetate
definition: A steroid ester resulting from the formal condensation of the 17-hydroxy function of fluorometholone with acetic acid. Used in the treatment of steroid responsive inflammatory conditions of the palpebral and bulbar conjunctiva, cornea, and anterior segment of the eye.

name: guanosine 5'-[beta,gamma-imido]triphosphate
definition: A nucleoside triphosphate analogue that is GTP in which the oxygen atom bridging the beta- to the gamma- phosphate is replaced by a nitrogen atom A non-hydrolyzable analog of GTP, it binds tightly to G-protein in the presence of Mg(2+).

name: alpha-amino acid zwitterion
definition: An amino acid zwitterion obtained by transfer of a proton from the carboxy to the amino group of any alpha-amino acid; major species at pH 7.3.

name: beta-D-galactosyl-(1->4)-beta-D-glucosyl-(1<->1)-ceramide
definition: Any glycodiaosylceramide having beta-D-galactosyl-(1->4)-beta-D-glucose as the disaccharide component and undefined sphingoid base.

name: thyroid stimulating hormone
definition: a

name: tebuconazole
definition: A racemate composed of equimolar amounts of (R)- and (S)-tebuconazole. A fungicide effective against various smut and bunt diseases in cereals and other field crops.

name: Evans blue
definition: An organic sodium salt that is the tetrasodium salt of 6,6'-{(3,3'-dimethyl[1,1'-biphenyl]-4,4'-diyl)bis[diazene-2,1-diyl]}bis(4-amino-5-hydroxynaphthalene-1,3-disulfonate). It is sometimes used as a counterstain, especially in fluorescent methods to suppress background autofluorescence.

name: alpha-N-acetylneuraminosyl-(2->3)-[beta-D-galactosyl-(1->3)-N-acetyl-beta-D-galactosaminyl-(1->4)]-beta-D-galactosyl-(1->4)-beta-D-glucosyl-(1<->1')-ceramide(1-)
definition: An anionic ganglioside that is the conjugate base alpha-N-acetylneuraminosyl-(2->3)-[beta-D-galactosyl-(1->3)-N-acetyl-beta-D-galactosaminyl-(1->4)]-beta-D-galactosyl-(1->4)-beta-D-glucosyl-(1<->1')-ceramide arising from deprotonation of the neuraminosyl carboxy group; major species at pH 7.3.

name: oritavancin
definition: A semisynthetic glycopeptide used (as its bisphosphate salt) for the treatment of acute bacterial skin and skin structure infections caused or suspected to be caused by susceptible isolates of designated Gram-positive microorganisms including MRSA.

name: N-acylhexadecasphingosine
definition: A ceramide consisting of an hexadecasphing-4-enine base having an unspecified fatty acyl group attached to the nitrogen.

name: N-acetyl-beta-D-galactosaminyl-(1->4)-[alpha-N-acetylneuraminosyl-(2->3)]-beta-D-galactosyl-(1->3)-N-acetyl-beta-D-galactosaminyl-(1->4)-[alpha-N-acetylneuraminosyl-(2->3)]-beta-D-galactosyl-(1->4)-beta-D-glucosyl-(1<->1')-ceramide(2-)
definition: An anionic ganglioside arising from deprotonation of the neuraminosyl carboxy groups of N-acetyl-beta-D-galactosaminyl-(1->4)-[alpha-N-acetylneuraminosyl-(2->3)]-beta-D-galactosyl-(1->3)-N-acetyl-beta-D-galactosaminyl-(1->4)-[alpha-N-acetylneuraminosyl-(2->3)]-beta-D-galactosyl-(1->4)-beta-D-glucosyl-(1<->1')-ceramide; major species at pH 7.3.

name: 7alpha-hydroxy-3-oxo-4-cholestenoic acid
definition: A cholestanoid that is cholest-4-en-26-oic acid substituted by an alpha-hydroxy group at position 7 and an oxo group at position 3. It is an intermediate metabolite in the bile acid synthesis.

name: 4,4'-diaponeurosporenoic acid
definition: An apo carotenoid triterpenoid that is 4,4'-diapolycopene in which one of the terminal methyl groups has been oxidised to the corresponding carboxylic acid.

name: 1-linoleoyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphoethanolamine
definition: A 1-acyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphoethanolamine in which the acyl group is specified as linoleoyl.

name: N-(hexadecanoyl)-beta-D-galactosylsphingosine
definition: A D-galactosyl-N-acylsphingosine in which the ceramide N-acyl group is specified as hexadecanoyl.

name: 4-dodecyl-2,6-dimethylmorpholine
definition: A member of the class of morpholines that is 2,6-dimethylmorpholine in which the hydrogen attached to the nitrogen is replaced by a dodecyl group. The configuration at positions 2 and 6 is unknown or unspecified.

name: orciprenaline sulfate
definition: A racemate composed of equimolar amounts of (R)- and (S)-orciprenaline sulfate. Used to relax the airway muscles and improve breathing for patients suffering from asthma or bronchitis.

name: N-lignoceroylsphingosine-1-phosphocholine
definition: A sphingomyelin d18:1 in which the ceramide N-acyl group is specified as lignoceroyl (tetracosanoyl).

name: N-hexacosanoylsphingosine-1-phosphocholine
definition: A sphingomyelin d18:1 in which the ceramide N-acyl group is specified as hexacosanoyl.

name: O-(S-3-oxoicosanoylpantetheine-4'-phosphoryl)-L-serine(1-) residue
definition: An O-(S-3-oxoacylpantetheine-4'-phosphoryl)-L-serine(1-) residue in which the S-acyl group is specified as 3-oxoicosanoyl.

name: O-[S-(3R)-hydroxyicosanoylpantetheine-4-phosphoryl]serine(1-) residue
definition: An O-(S-acylpantetheine-4-phosphoryl)serine(1-) residue in which the S-acyl group is specified as (3R)-hydroxyicosanoyl.

name: thifensulfuron-methyl
definition: A methyl ester resulting from the formal condensation of the carboxy group of thifensulfuron with methanol. It is used  as a post-emergence herbicide for the control of grass and broad-leaved weeds.

name: pendimethalin
definition: A member of the class of substituted anilines that is N-(pentan-3-yl)aniline bearing two additional nitro substituents at positions 2 and 6 as well as two methyl substituents at positions 3 and 4. A herbicide used to control most annual grasses and many annual broad-leaved weeds.

name: tribenuron
definition: An N-sulfonylurea that is N-(2-carboxybenzenesulfonyl)urea bearing additional methyl and 4-methoxy-6-methyl-1,3,5-triazin-2-yl substituents at position N3. A foliar acting, post-emergence herbicide used to control broad-leaved weeds in cereals, normally used as the methyl variant.

name: juvenile hormone I
definition: A member of the juvenile hormone family of compounds that is the methyl ester of methyl (2E,6E,10R,11S)-10,11-epoxy-7-ethyl-3,11-dimethyl-2,6-tridecanoic acid.

name: 3-oxo-23,24-bisnorchol-4-en-22-oyl-CoA(4-)
definition: An acyl-CoA oxoanion resulting from the removal of all four protons from the phosphate and diphosphate groups of 3-oxo-23,24-bisnor-chol-4-en-22-oyl-CoA; major species at pH 7.3.

name: amino acid derivative
definition: Any derivative of an amino acid resulting from reaction at an amino group, carboxy group, side-chain functional group, or from the replacement of any hydrogen by a heteroatom. The definition normally excludes peptides containing amino acid residues.

name: 1-O-(1,2-saturated-alkyl)-sn-glycerol
definition: A 1-O-alkyl-sn-glycerol in which the alkyl group has a saturated bond between carbons 1 and 2.

name: 4-fluorophenylalanine
definition: A phenylalanine derivative in which the hydrogen at position 4 on the benzene ring is replaced by a fluoro group.

name: pentanal
definition: A saturated fatty aldehyde composed from five carbons in a straight chain.

name: 2,6-dimethylheptanoyl carnitine
definition: A C9-acylcarnitine in which the acyl group specified is 2,6-dimethylheptanoyl.

name: quinmerac
definition: A quinolinemonocarboxylic acid that is quinoline-8-carboxylic acid carrying additional methyl and chloro substituents at positions 3 and 7 respectively. A residual herbicide used to control broad-leaved weeds on a range of crops including cereals, rape and beet.

name: 12-hydroxyoctadecanoate
definition: A hydroxy saturated fatty acid anion that is the conjugate base of 12-hydroxyoctadecanoic acid, obtained by deprotonation of the carboxy group; major species at pH 7.3.

name: 13(S)-HOTrE
definition: The (13S)-stereoisomer of HOTrE.

name: 1-stearoyl-2-(7Z,10Z,13Z,16Z-docosatetraenoyl)-sn-glycero-3-phosphoserine
definition: A 3-sn-phosphatidyl L-serine in which the phosphatidyl acyl groups at positions 1 and 2 are stearoyl and 7Z,10Z,13Z,16Z-docosatetraenoyl respectively.

name: 1-[(9Z,12Z)-octadecadienoyl]-2-[(5Z,8Z,11Z,14Z)-icosatetraenoyl]-sn-glycero-3-phosphocholine
definition: A phosphatidylcholine 38:6 in which the acyl groups specified at positions 1 and 2 are (9Z,12Z)-octadecadienoyl and (5Z,8Z,11Z,14Z)-icosatetraenoyl respectively.

name: 1-hexadecanoyl-2-[(7Z,10Z,13Z,16Z)-docosatetraenoyl]-sn-glycero-3-phosphocholine
definition: A  phosphatidylcholine 38:4  in which the acyl groups at positions 1 and 2 are hexadecanoyl and (7Z,10Z,13Z,16Z)-docosatetraenoyl respectively.

name: 2-(6-aminohexylamino)-cAMP
definition: A 3',5'-cyclic purine nucleotide that is 3',5'-cyclic AMP in which the hydrogen at position 2 on the purine fragment is replaced by a 6-aminohexylamino group

name: 8-(6-aminohexylamino)-cAMP
definition: A 3',5'-cyclic purine nucleotide that is 3',5'-cyclic AMP in which the hydrogen at position 2 on the purine fragment is replaced by a 6-aminohexylamino group.

name: alpha-Neu5Ac-(2->3)-beta-D-Gal(1->3)beta-GalNAc-(1->4)-[alpha-Neu5Ac-(2->3)]-beta-Gal-(1->4)-beta-Glc-(1->1')-Cer(d18:1/18:0)
definition: A alpha-N-acetylneuraminosyl-(2->3)-beta-D-galactosyl-(1->3)-N-acetyl-beta-D-galactosaminyl-(1->4)-[alpha-N-acetylneuraminosyl-(2->3)]-beta-D-galactosyl-(1->4)-beta-D-glucosylceramide in which the ceramide N-acyl group is specified as octadecanoyl (stearoyl).

name: beta-D-galactosyl-N-[(15Z)-tetracosenoyl]sphingosine
definition: A N-acyl-beta-D-galactosylsphingosine in which the acyl group is (15Z)-tetracosenoyl.

name: 2-deoxy-D-glucopyranose
definition: A 2-deoxy-D-glucose that is D-glucopyranose in which the hydroxy group at position 2 has been replaced by a hydrogen.

name: 1-octadecanoyl-2-[(9Z,12Z)-octadecadienoyl]-sn-glycero-3-phosphocholine
definition: A phosphatidylcholine 36:2 in which the acyl groups positions 1 and 2 are specified as octadecanoyl and (9Z,12Z)-octadecadienoyl respectively.

name: 1-octadecanoyl-2-(4Z,7Z,10Z,13Z,16Z,19Z-docosahexaenoyl)-sn-glycero-3-phosphocholine
definition: A phosphatidylcholine 40:6 in which the acyl groups at positions  1 and 2 are octadecanoyl and (4Z,7Z,10Z,13Z,16Z,19Z)-docosahexaenoyl respectively.

name: ethyl (5Z,8Z,11Z,14Z,17Z)-icosapentaenoate
definition: A long-chain fatty acid ethyl ester resulting from the formal condensation of the carboxy group of (5Z,8Z,11Z,14Z,17Z)-icosapentaenoic acid with the hydroxy group of ethanol.

name: (R)-crotonylcarnitine
definition: A O-butenoyl-L-carnitine  in which the acyl group is specified as crotonyl.

name: ethyl (4Z,7Z,10Z,13Z,16Z,19Z)-docosahexaenoate
definition: A long-chain fatty acid ethyl ester resulting from the formal condensation of the carboxy group of (4Z,7Z,10Z,13Z,16Z,19Z)-docosahexaenoic acid with the hydroxy group of ethanol.

name: trans,trans-2,4-dienoyl-CoA(4-)
definition: A 2,3-trans-enoyl CoA(4-) obtained by deprotonation of the phosphate and diphosphate functions of any trans,trans-2,4-dienoyl-CoA; major species at pH 7.3.

name: (9E)-12-(phosphonooxy)octadecenoic acid
definition: A carboxyalkyl phosphate that is (9E)-octadecenoic acid carrying a phosphonooxy substituent at position 12.

name: methyl nogalonate
definition: The methyl ester of nogalonic acid.

name: 9,10-dihydroxystearate
definition: A long-chain fatty acid anion that is the conjugate base of 9,10-dihydroxystearic acid, obtained by deprotonation of the carboxy group; major species at pH 7.3.

name: peramivir
definition: A member of the class of guanidines that is used (as its trihydrate) for the treatment of acute uncomplicated influenza in patients 18 years and older who have been symptomatic for no more than two days.

name: 15-deoxy-Delta(12,14)-prostaglandin J2-2-glyceryl ester
definition: A 2-monoglyceride resulting from the condensation of the carboxy group of 15-deoxy-Delta(12,14)-prostaglandin J2 with the  hydroxy group at position 2 of glycerol.

name: spiramycin I
definition: A macrolide antibiotic produced by various Streptomyces species that is used to treat toxoplasmosis and various other infections of soft tissues.

name: 5-methyl dCMP(1-) residue
definition: An organic anionic group obtained by deprotonation of the phosphate OH group of 5-methyl dCMP residue; major species at pH 7.3.

name: trans-4-hydroxy-L-proline betaine
definition: An amino-acid betaine that is trans-4-hydroxy-L-proline zwitterion in which both of the hydrogens attached to the nitrogen have been replaced by methyl groups.

name: N-hexadecenoylsphingosine-1-phosphocholine
definition: A  sphingomyelin 34:2 in which the ceramide N-acyl group contains 16 carbons and 1 double bond.

name: sphingomyelin d18:1/18:1
definition: A sphingomyelin d18:1 in which the fatty acyl group contains 16 carbons and 1 double bond

name: sphingomyelin 39:1
definition: A sphingomyelin in which the total number of carbons in the sphingoid base and fatty acyl groups is 39 with 1 double bond.

name: 5-amino-5-(4-hydroxybenzyl)-6-(D-ribitylimino)-5,6-dihydrouracil
definition: A member of the class of pyrimidones that is 5,6-diamino-5-[(4-hydroxyphenyl)methyl]pyrimidine-2,4-dione in which the imino hydrogen at position 6 is replaced by a D-ribityl group.

name: (9Z,11E,13E,15Z)-octadecatetraenoyl group
definition: A parinaroyl group derived from (9Z,11E,13E,15Z)-octadecatetraenoic (alpha-parinaric) acid.

name: 5beta-dihydroaldosterone
definition: A 3-oxo-5beta-steroid formed from aldosterone by reduction across the C4-C5 double bond.

name: 2-hydroxyethyl salicylate
definition: A benzoate ester obtained by the formal condensation of carboxy group of  salicylic acid with one of the hydroxy groups of ethylene glycol

name: buddlenol C
definition: A guaiacyl lignin that is syringaresinol in which one of the phenolic hydrogens is replaced by a guaiacylglycerol group. It is found in Arabidopsis thaliana.

name: acid green 5
definition: An organic sodium salt having 3-[(ethyl{4-[(4-{ethyl[(3-sulfonatophenyl)methyl]amino}phenyl)(4-sulfonatophenyl)methylidene]cyclohexa-2,5-dien-1-ylidene}azaniumyl)methyl]benzene-1-sulfonate as the counterion. It is the standard dye in North American for staining collagen and is also used extensively in plant histology.

name: (R)-warfarin
definition: A 4-hydroxy-3-(3-oxo-1-phenylbutyl)-2H-1-benzopyran-2-one that has (R)-configuration (the racemate is warfarin, an anticoagulant drug and rodenticide).

name: aralkylammonium
definition: A primary ammonium ion obtained by protonation of the amino group of an aralkylamine; major species at pH 7.3.

name: coprostanol
definition: A member of the class of phytosterols that is 5beta-cholestane carrying a hydroxy substituent at the 3beta-position.

name: Leu-enkephalin
definition: A pentapeptide comprising L-tyrosine, glycine, glycine, L-phenylalanine and L-leucine residues joined in sequence by peptide linkages. It is an endogenous opioid peptide produced in vertebrate species, including rodents, primates and humans that results from decomposition of proenkephalin or dynorphin and exhibits antinociceptive properties.

name: isopropyl dodecanoate
definition: A fatty acid ester obtained by the formal condensation of carboxy group of dodecanoic acid with propan-2-ol. A metabolite found in human saliva.

name: cyclo(L-His-L-Pro)
definition: A homodetic cyclic peptide resulting from the formal condensation of both the amino and acid groups of L-histidine with the acid and amino groups of L-proline. It is a metabolite of thyrotropin-releasing hormone (TRH).

name: dTDP-2,3-dehydro-2,6-dideoxy-4-keto-alpha-D-glucose
definition: A dTDP-sugar having 2,3-dehydro-2,6-dideoxy-4-keto-alpha-D-glucose as the sugar component.

name: (S)-2-methylbutanoyl-CoA
definition: A (2S)-2-methylacyl-CoA that results from the formal condensation of the thiol group of coenzyme A with the carboxy group of (2S)-2-methylbutanoic acid.

name: 11beta,13-dihydrolactucin
definition: A sesquiterpene lactone obtained by formal hydrogenation across the 11,13-double bond of lactucin. Found in chicory

name: N-(indol-3-ylacetyl)glycine
definition: An N-acylglycine in which the N-acyl group is specified as indol-3-ylacetyl.

name: dibenzothiophene sulfone
definition: A sulfone resulting from the oxidation of the sulfur atom of dibenzothiophene.

name: S-(5-deoxy-beta-D-ribos-5-yl)-L-homocysteine
definition: An S-(5-deoxy-D-ribos-5-yl)-L-homocysteine in which the anomeric centre has beta-configuration.

name: succinic acid-d4
definition: A deuterated compound that is succinic acid in which the four methylene hydrogens are replaced by deuterium.

name: alpha-D-Gal-(1->3)-beta-D-Gal-(1->4)-[alpha-L-Fuc-(1->3)]-beta-D-GlcNAc-(1->3)-beta-D-Gal-(1->4)-beta-D-Glc-(1<->1')-Cer
definition: A glycohexaosylceramide having an alpha-D-Gal-(1->3)-beta-D-Gal-(1->4)-[alpha-L-Fuc-(1->3)]-beta-D-GlcNAc-(1->3)-beta-D-Gal-(1->4)-beta-D-Glc component attached to the primary hydroxy function of a ceramide with undefined sphingoid base and fatty acyl chain.

name: phosphatidylserine(18:1/22:1)
definition: A 3-sn-phosphatidyl-L-serine in which the 1- and 2-acyl groups are octadecenoyl and docosenoyl respectively.

name: N(6)-methyl-2'-deoxyadenosine 5'-monophosphate(1-) residue
definition: An organic anionic group obtained by deprotonation of the phosphate OH group of N(6)-methyl-dAMP residue; major species at pH 7.3.

name: U0126
definition: An aryl sulfide that is (2Z,3Z)-bis[amino(sulfanyl)methylidene]butanedinitrile in which the sulfanyl hydrogens are replaced by 2-aminophenyl groups. An inhibitor of mitogen-activated protein kinase that also exhibits anti-cancer properties.

name: O-(chloroacetylcarbamoyl)fumagillol
definition: A carbamate ester that is fumagillol in which the hydroxy group has been converted to the corresponding N-(chloroacetyl)carbamate derivative.

name: antidote to organophosphate poisoning
definition: A role borne by a molecule that acts to counteract or neutralise the deleterious effects of organophosphates or acetylcholinesterase inhibitors (nerve agents).

name: 2-hydroxy-6-oxo-2,4-heptadienoic acid
definition: An alpha,beta-unsaturated monocarboxylic acid that is 2,4-heptadienoic acid substituted by hydroxy and oxo groups at positions 2 and 6 respectively.

name: 5-[(E)-caffeoyl]shikimate
definition: A hydroxy monocarboxylic acid anion that is the conjugate base of 5-[(E)-caffeoyl]shikimic acid. Major structure at pH 7.3

name: 3-cis-hydroxy-beta,epsilon-caroten-3'-one
definition: a

name: epithienamycin E
definition: A member of the class of carbapenems that is (5R,6R)-3-{[(E)-2-aminoethenyl]sulfanyl}-6-[(1S)-1-hydroxyethyl]-7-oxo-1-azabicyclo[3.2.0]hept-2-ene-2-carboxylic acid in which the free hydroxy and amino groups are carrying sulfo and acetyl substituents respectively.

name: N-acetyl-alpha-D-galactosaminyl-(1->3)-[alpha-L-fucosyl-(1->2)]-beta-D-galactosyl-(1->4)-N-acetyl-beta-D-glucosaminyl-(1->3)-beta-D-galactosyl-(1->4)-beta-D-glucosyl-(1<->1')-N-acylsphinganine
definition: A glycohexaosylceramide having N-acetyl-alpha-D-galactosaminyl-(1->3)-[alpha-L-fucosyl-(1->2)]-beta-D-galactosyl-(1->4)-N-acetyl-beta-D-glucosaminyl-(1->3)-beta-D-galactosyl-(1->4)-beta-D-glucosyl component attached to the primary hydroxy function of a ceramide with d18:0 sphingoid base and undefined fatty acyl chain.

name: 4-methoxy-3-indolylmethylamine
definition: An aminoalkylindole that is 3-(aminomethyl)indole in which the hydrogen at position 4 has been replaced by a methoxy group.

name: guaiacylglycerol beta-coniferyl ether
definition: A guaiacyl lignin that is guaiacylglycerol in which the hydrogen on the 2-hydroxy function has been replaced by a beta-coniferyl group.

name: dehydrodiconiferyl alcohol
definition: A guaiacyl lignin obtained by cyclodimerisation of coniferol.

name: AZD-8055
definition: A pyridopyrimidine that is pyrido[2,3-d]pyrimidine which is substituted at positions 2 and 4 by (3S)-3-methylmorpholin-4-yl groups and at position 5 by a 3-(hydroxymethyl)-4-methoxyphenyl group. It is an mTOR complex 1/2 (mTORC1/2) dual inhibitor [mTOR = mammalian target of rapamycin].

name: SU6656
definition: A member of the class of oxindoles that is 3-methyleneoxindole in which the hydrogeh at position 5 has been replaced by a dimethylaminosulfonyl group and in which one of the hydrogens of the methylene group has been replaced by a 4,5,6,7-tetrahydro-indol-2-yl group. It is a specific inhibitor of Src family kinase.

name: sepantronium
definition: An organic cation that is 1-(2-methoxyethyl)-2-methyl-1H-naphtho[2,3-d]imidazole-4,9-dione in which the nitrogen at position 3 of the napthoimidazole moiety has been alkylated by a pyrazin-2-ylmethyl group.

name: nalidixic acid
definition: A monocarboxylic acid comprising 1,8-naphthyridin-4-one substituted by carboxylic acid, ethyl and methyl groups at positions 3, 1, and 7, respectively. An orally administered antibacterial, it is used in the treatment of lower urinary-tract infections due to Gram-negative bacteria, including the majority of E. coli, Enterobacter, Klebsiella, and Proteus species.

name: ciprofloxacin
definition: A  quinolone that is quinolin-4(1H)-one bearing cyclopropyl, carboxylic acid, fluoro and piperazin-1-yl substituents at positions 1, 3, 6 and 7, respectively.

name: norfloxacin
definition: A quinolinemonocarboxylic acid with broad-spectrum antibacterial activity against most gram-negative and gram-positive bacteria. Norfloxacin is bactericidal and its mode of action depends on blocking of bacterial DNA replication by binding itself to an enzyme called DNA gyrase.

name: diclofenamide
definition: A sulfonamide that is benzene-1,3-disulfonamide in which the hydrogens at positions 4 and 5 are substituted by chlorine. An oral carbonic anhydrase inhibitor, it partially suppresses the secretion (inflow) of aqueous humor in the eye and so reduces intraocular pressure. It is used for the treatment of glaucoma.

name: diltiazem
definition: A 5-[2-(dimethylamino)ethyl]-2-(4-methoxyphenyl)-4-oxo-2,3,4,5-tetrahydro-1,5-benzothiazepin-3-yl acetate in which both stereocentres have S configuration. A calcium-channel blocker and vasodilator, it is used as the hydrochloride in the management of angina pectoris and hypertension.

name: IPA-3
definition: An organic disulfide obtained by oxidative dimerisation of 1-sulfanylnaphthalen-2-ol.

name: compound E
definition: An L-alanine derivative that is the amide obtained by formal condensation of the carboxy group of N-[(3,5-difluorophenyl)acetyl]-L-alanine with the amino group of (3S)-3-amino-1-methyl-5-phenyl-1,3-dihydro-2H-1,4-benzodiazepin-2-one. An inhibitor of memapsin 2 (gamma-secretase).

name: sorbinil
definition: An azaspiro compound having a monofluoro-substituted chromane skeleton spiro-linked to an imidazolidinedione ring.

name: thiopental
definition: A barbiturate, the structure of which is that of 2-thiobarbituric acid substituted at C-5 by ethyl and sec-pentyl groups.

name: methohexital
definition: A barbiturate, the structure of which is that of barbituric acid substituted at N-1 by a methyl group and at C-5 by allyl and 1-methylpent-2-ynyl groups.

name: sulfisoxazole
definition: A sulfonamide antibacterial with an oxazole substituent. It has antibiotic activity against a wide range of gram-negative and gram-positive organisms.

name: p-aminohippuric acid
definition: An N-acylglycine that is the 4-amino derivative of hippuric acid; used as a diagnostic agent in the measurement of renal plasma flow.

name: nordazepam
definition: A 1,4-benzodiazepinone having phenyl and chloro substituents at positions 5 and 7 respectively; it has anticonvulsant, anxiolytic, muscle relaxant and sedative properties but is used primarily in the treatment of anxiety.

name: lomefloxacin
definition: A fluoroquinolone antibiotic, used (generally as the hydrochloride salt) to treat bacterial infections including bronchitis and urinary tract infections. It is also used to prevent urinary tract infections prior to surgery.

name: oleamide
definition: A fatty amide derived from oleic acid.

name: benzocaine
definition: A benzoate ester having 4-aminobenzoic acid as the acid component and ethanol as the alcohol component. A surface anaesthetic, it is used to suppress the gag reflex, and as a lubricant and topical anaesthetic on the larynx, mouth, nasal cavity, respiratory tract, oesophagus, rectum, urinary tract, and vagina.

name: 4-chloroacetanilide
definition: Acetamide substituted on nitrogen by a para-chlorophenyl group.

name: delavirdine
definition: The amide resulting from the formal condensation of 5-[(methylsulfonyl)amino]-1H-indole-2-carboxylic acid and 4-amino group of 1-[3-(isopropylamino)pyridin-2-yl]piperazine, delavirdine is a non-nucleoside reverse transcriptase inhibitor with activity specific for HIV-1. Viral resistance emerges rapidly when delavirdine is used alone, so it is therefore used (as the methanesulfonic acid salt) with other antiretrovirals for combination therapy of HIV infection.

name: fentanyl
definition: A monocarboxylic acid amide resulting from the formal condensation of the aryl amino group of N-phenyl-1-(2-phenylethyl)piperidin-4-amine with propanoic acid.

name: N-tetracosanoyl-15-methylhexadecasphingosine-1-phosphocholine
definition: A sphingomyelin 41:1 obtained by formal condensation of the carboxy group of tetracosanoic acid with the amino group of 15-methylhexadecasphingosine-1-phosphocholine. It is a metabolite of the nematode Caenorhabditis elegans.

name: 1-octadecanoyl-2-arachidonoyl-sn-glycero-3-phospho-D-myo-inositol(1-)
definition: A 1-octadecanoyl-2-acyl-sn-glycero-3-phospho-1D-myo-inositol(1-) in which the 2-acyl group is specified as (5Z,8Z,11Z,14Z)-icosa-5,8,11,14-tetraenoyl (arachidonoyl).

name: N-glycolylneuraminyllactosylceramide
definition: A sialotriaosylceramide in which the triaosyl group is 3,5-dideoxy-5-(2-hydroxyacetamido)-D-glycero-alpha-D-galacto-non-2-ulopyranonosyl-(2->3)-beta-D-galactopyranosyl-(1->4)-beta-D-glucopyranosyl attached to the primary hydroxy function of ceramide. A tumour antigen found in solid tumors such as breast carcinoma, nonsmall cell lung cancer, and melanoma, but not usually detected in normal human cells.

name: (S)-2-hydroxy-3-methylbutyrate
definition: The S-enantiomer of 2-hydroxy-3-methylbutyrate. The conjugate base of (S)-2-hydroxy-3-methylbutyric acid, formed by loss of a proton from the carboxy group, it is the major species present at physiological pH.
